WEBVTT

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:17.339
Scholastic Audio presents Wings of Fire

00:00:17.339 --> 00:00:19.260
Book 6.

00:00:19.320 --> 00:00:20.579
Moon rising.

00:00:20.640 --> 00:00:24.780
By 2ET Sutherland, read by Shannon

00:00:24.780 --> 00:00:25.620
McManus.

00:00:43.679 --> 00:00:51.060
The Jade Mountain Prophecy.

00:00:51.119 --> 00:00:55.200
Beware the darkness of dragons.

00:00:55.259 --> 00:00:58.320
Beware the stalker of dreams.

00:00:58.380 --> 00:01:01.979
Beware the talons of power and fire.

00:01:02.039 --> 00:01:05.519
Beware one who is not what she seems.

00:01:05.579 --> 00:01:09.299
Something is coming to shake the earth.

00:01:09.359 --> 00:01:12.000
Something is coming to scorch the

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:12.420
ground.

00:01:12.480 --> 00:01:15.780
Jade Mountain will fall beneath thunder

00:01:15.780 --> 00:01:16.560
and ice.

00:01:16.680 --> 00:01:19.439
Unless the lost city of night can be

00:01:19.439 --> 00:01:19.739
found.

00:01:31.799 --> 00:01:34.920
Prologue.

00:01:35.040 --> 00:01:36.480
Four years ago.

00:01:36.599 --> 00:01:40.500
The volcano was restless, and so were the

00:01:40.500 --> 00:01:42.000
dragons in the night wing fortress.

00:01:42.120 --> 00:01:45.239
Secret keeper felt the mountain rumble

00:01:45.239 --> 00:01:47.219
under her talons as she hurried through

00:01:47.219 --> 00:01:48.000
the stone halls.

00:01:48.060 --> 00:01:50.159
There were too many dragons awake.

00:01:50.219 --> 00:01:52.859
Too many witnesses who might wonder where

00:01:52.859 --> 00:01:54.299
she was going in the middle of the night

00:01:54.299 --> 00:01:57.540
she kept her head down, but she felt the

00:01:57.540 --> 00:01:59.819
curious looks, sliding under her scales

00:01:59.819 --> 00:02:01.260
with each dragon she passed.

00:02:01.319 --> 00:02:04.200
How many of them knew what tonight should

00:02:04.200 --> 00:02:04.620
have been?

00:02:04.680 --> 00:02:06.239
Did anyone remember?

00:02:06.299 --> 00:02:09.180
She didn't need to count days to know.

00:02:09.300 --> 00:02:11.460
Her bones ached with knowing.

00:02:11.520 --> 00:02:14.520
It was like a voice in her head screaming

00:02:14.520 --> 00:02:15.900
tonight, it's hatching.

00:02:15.960 --> 00:02:17.520
Hurry, don't get caught.

00:02:17.580 --> 00:02:18.060
Hurry.

00:02:18.120 --> 00:02:20.759
Because if it happened, and she wasn't

00:02:20.759 --> 00:02:20.939
there.

00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:24.840
She imagined hungry panthers prowling the

00:02:24.840 --> 00:02:27.840
undergrowth, dangerous crocodiles, with

00:02:27.840 --> 00:02:30.479
gleaming teeth, or unpredictable curious

00:02:30.479 --> 00:02:32.819
idiot dragons, who might do anything with

00:02:32.819 --> 00:02:34.319
a mysterious abandoned egg.

00:02:34.379 --> 00:02:37.199
But she couldn't run, not with other

00:02:37.199 --> 00:02:38.759
night wings still awake and watching

00:02:38.759 --> 00:02:39.060
her.

00:02:39.120 --> 00:02:41.699
Why tonight of all nights?

00:02:41.759 --> 00:02:45.180
Usually everyone in the tribe slept like

00:02:45.180 --> 00:02:46.919
sloths from dusk to dawn.

00:02:46.979 --> 00:02:50.039
Just before she reached the ledge, she

00:02:50.039 --> 00:02:51.900
passed mastermind and Farsight.

00:02:51.960 --> 00:02:54.360
Mastermind gave her a hard stare.

00:02:54.419 --> 00:02:57.719
He knows, she thought with a stab of

00:02:57.719 --> 00:02:58.080
panic.

00:02:58.139 --> 00:03:00.780
But it was Farsight, who stopped and

00:03:00.780 --> 00:03:01.259
spoke to her.

00:03:01.319 --> 00:03:06.000
Oh, secret keeper, poor dear, she said

00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:07.020
folding her wings.

00:03:07.080 --> 00:03:09.419
Secret keeper winced.

00:03:09.539 --> 00:03:11.340
Her name had never sounded more

00:03:11.340 --> 00:03:12.060
appropriate.

00:03:12.120 --> 00:03:15.180
Sometimes she wondered if her name had

00:03:15.180 --> 00:03:16.080
made her this way.

00:03:16.139 --> 00:03:18.659
If she was unconsciously trying to live

00:03:18.659 --> 00:03:20.819
up to it, with the biggest, most

00:03:20.819 --> 00:03:23.520
unforgivable secret a nightwing could

00:03:23.520 --> 00:03:23.699
have.

00:03:23.759 --> 00:03:27.539
The egg you lost was due to hatch tonight

00:03:27.539 --> 00:03:27.960
wasn't it?

00:03:28.020 --> 00:03:29.280
Are you all right?

00:03:29.400 --> 00:03:30.840
Farside went on.

00:03:30.900 --> 00:03:32.699
Do you want someone to sit with you?

00:03:32.759 --> 00:03:34.379
No.

00:03:34.500 --> 00:03:37.020
Secret keeper curled her claws in and

00:03:37.020 --> 00:03:37.560
shook her head.

00:03:37.620 --> 00:03:39.719
I'm fine, she said.

00:03:39.780 --> 00:03:41.699
Just going to get some air.

00:03:41.759 --> 00:03:44.159
Do you want company?

00:03:44.219 --> 00:03:45.539
Farside asked.

00:03:45.599 --> 00:03:47.699
Behind her, mastermind frowned

00:03:47.699 --> 00:03:48.300
irritably.

00:03:48.360 --> 00:03:51.419
I know it's not the same, but when Morrow

00:03:51.419 --> 00:03:52.379
Seaer took my egg.

00:03:52.439 --> 00:03:55.080
Secret keeper could only think of one way

00:03:55.080 --> 00:03:57.599
to stop her, and it was harsh, but she

00:03:57.599 --> 00:04:00.539
had to because she had to go right now.

00:04:00.599 --> 00:04:04.319
It's not the same at all, she snapped

00:04:04.319 --> 00:04:06.479
shooting a burst of flame out her nose.

00:04:06.539 --> 00:04:09.719
You have 2 surviving dragonettes, and one

00:04:09.719 --> 00:04:10.979
of them is off on the continent being

00:04:10.979 --> 00:04:13.319
pampered and overfed, and worshiped by

00:04:13.319 --> 00:04:14.219
the talons of peace.

00:04:14.280 --> 00:04:15.900
So don't try to act like you understand

00:04:15.900 --> 00:04:16.259
me.

00:04:16.319 --> 00:04:19.980
Farsight recoiled as if Secret Keeper had

00:04:19.980 --> 00:04:20.399
bitten her.

00:04:20.459 --> 00:04:24.059
Mastermind looked startled, perhaps a bit

00:04:24.059 --> 00:04:26.639
impressed, maybe a little suspicious.

00:04:26.759 --> 00:04:30.120
Secret keeper whirled and fled up the

00:04:30.120 --> 00:04:31.680
corridor before either of them could say

00:04:31.680 --> 00:04:32.699
anything else.

00:04:32.759 --> 00:04:34.500
I'll apologize tomorrow.

00:04:34.560 --> 00:04:35.579
She'll forgive me.

00:04:35.639 --> 00:04:37.319
Farsight dislike that.

00:04:37.379 --> 00:04:40.379
She took a running leap off the ledge, and

00:04:40.379 --> 00:04:42.180
soared down toward the black sand beach

00:04:42.180 --> 00:04:45.120
behind her, the volcano rumbled again.

00:04:45.240 --> 00:04:48.540
The dark clouds overhead glowed with an

00:04:48.540 --> 00:04:49.439
ominous red light.

00:04:49.500 --> 00:04:52.620
The air was heavy and suffocating

00:04:52.620 --> 00:04:55.740
smelling of death and rotten eggs and

00:04:55.740 --> 00:04:56.339
burning rocks.

00:04:56.399 --> 00:04:59.639
Secret keeper swooped low over the red

00:04:59.639 --> 00:05:02.399
gold lava river, the brightest spot on

00:05:02.399 --> 00:05:04.319
the island, and then veered toward the

00:05:04.319 --> 00:05:04.680
cave.

00:05:04.740 --> 00:05:06.600
Only one guard tonight.

00:05:06.660 --> 00:05:09.300
Nobody really believed any of the

00:05:09.300 --> 00:05:11.100
rainforest dragons would find their

00:05:11.100 --> 00:05:11.639
secret tunnel.

00:05:11.699 --> 00:05:13.800
The guards were often asleep when she

00:05:13.800 --> 00:05:16.139
came, and secret keeper had frequently

00:05:16.139 --> 00:05:17.879
been able to sneak past without waking

00:05:17.879 --> 00:05:18.120
them.

00:05:18.180 --> 00:05:19.920
But not tonight.

00:05:19.980 --> 00:05:22.560
Prey Hunter was sitting out on the ledge

00:05:22.560 --> 00:05:24.540
overlooking the beach, watching the

00:05:24.540 --> 00:05:26.639
volcano and fidgeting nervously.

00:05:26.699 --> 00:05:28.680
Do you think it'll be tonight?

00:05:28.740 --> 00:05:31.259
He asked her as she landed beside him.

00:05:31.319 --> 00:05:33.720
It took her a frightening, disoriented

00:05:33.720 --> 00:05:35.879
moment to realize he hadn't guessed her

00:05:35.879 --> 00:05:36.180
secret.

00:05:36.240 --> 00:05:38.459
He probably didn't even remember that

00:05:38.459 --> 00:05:39.360
she'd lost her egg.

00:05:39.420 --> 00:05:42.180
She was only one of many dragons who had

00:05:42.180 --> 00:05:43.500
in the last few years after all.

00:05:43.620 --> 00:05:45.899
He was talking about the volcano.

00:05:45.959 --> 00:05:48.899
No, secret keeper said.

00:05:48.959 --> 00:05:51.180
Looking back at the hulking shape that

00:05:51.180 --> 00:05:53.339
loomed over all their lives.

00:05:53.399 --> 00:05:54.240
It can't be.

00:05:54.300 --> 00:05:56.579
Mastermind said we have more time before

00:05:56.579 --> 00:05:57.360
it erupts.

00:05:57.420 --> 00:05:59.040
Pray hunter snorted.

00:05:59.160 --> 00:06:00.120
Right.

00:06:00.240 --> 00:06:02.459
And I'll remember why we trust him any

00:06:02.459 --> 00:06:03.000
minute now.

00:06:03.060 --> 00:06:05.100
She knew what he meant.

00:06:05.160 --> 00:06:06.779
If mastermind was wrong.

00:06:06.839 --> 00:06:10.319
Well, that was why she'd made her choice

00:06:10.319 --> 00:06:10.800
wasn't it?

00:06:10.860 --> 00:06:12.720
That was the whole reason for her

00:06:12.720 --> 00:06:13.500
dangerous secret.

00:06:13.560 --> 00:06:16.560
Where are you going at this hour?

00:06:16.620 --> 00:06:19.079
Pray Hunter asked, eyeing her up and

00:06:19.079 --> 00:06:19.259
down?

00:06:19.379 --> 00:06:21.300
Shouldn't you have backup for night

00:06:21.300 --> 00:06:21.779
hunting?

00:06:21.839 --> 00:06:23.519
I'll be all right.

00:06:23.579 --> 00:06:24.899
Secret Keeper said.

00:06:24.959 --> 00:06:28.560
I just can't sleep, and I thought, maybe

00:06:28.560 --> 00:06:30.240
I'd bring back a salt or bear for

00:06:30.240 --> 00:06:31.139
greatness to give the queen.

00:06:31.199 --> 00:06:35.759
Ah, Pray Hunter nodded slyly, keeping the

00:06:35.759 --> 00:06:36.240
queen happy.

00:06:36.300 --> 00:06:37.920
Always a good idea.

00:06:37.980 --> 00:06:38.939
Right.

00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:40.259
See you soon then.

00:06:40.319 --> 00:06:43.680
Secret keeper edged past him, her heart

00:06:43.680 --> 00:06:44.160
pounding.

00:06:44.220 --> 00:06:46.740
She bolted through the cave and into the

00:06:46.740 --> 00:06:48.120
tunnel that led to the rainforest.

00:06:48.180 --> 00:06:50.279
Hurry, hurry.

00:06:50.339 --> 00:06:51.300
It's happening now.

00:06:51.360 --> 00:06:52.439
You have to be there.

00:06:52.500 --> 00:06:54.420
She fell through.

00:06:54.480 --> 00:06:56.519
Into the clearest, most brightly lit

00:06:56.519 --> 00:06:58.680
night she'd ever seen in the rainforest.

00:06:58.740 --> 00:07:00.240
The worst luck.

00:07:00.300 --> 00:07:02.879
She'd have to hope that no rain wings

00:07:02.879 --> 00:07:04.560
were out for a moonlit stroll tonight.

00:07:04.620 --> 00:07:06.899
Even through the thick canopy of the

00:07:06.899 --> 00:07:09.240
treetops overhead, she could see that 2

00:07:09.240 --> 00:07:10.620
of the 3 moons were full.

00:07:10.740 --> 00:07:13.560
Just like they were the night I left her

00:07:13.560 --> 00:07:13.980
here.

00:07:14.040 --> 00:07:15.779
Secret keeper stopped.

00:07:15.899 --> 00:07:18.000
Her heart seemed to be doing some kind of

00:07:18.000 --> 00:07:19.740
painful aerial loops in her chest.

00:07:19.800 --> 00:07:21.839
Her.

00:07:21.839 --> 00:07:23.819
Suddenly she just knew.

00:07:23.819 --> 00:07:25.259
She was certain.

00:07:25.379 --> 00:07:26.399
It would be female.

00:07:26.459 --> 00:07:29.939
She flew through the trees. following the

00:07:29.939 --> 00:07:31.680
small signs she'd left for herself.

00:07:31.800 --> 00:07:34.560
There wasn't time to travel quietly and

00:07:34.560 --> 00:07:35.220
cautiously.

00:07:35.279 --> 00:07:37.560
If a rain wing heard and followed her.

00:07:37.620 --> 00:07:40.439
Well, it wouldn't be a good night for

00:07:40.439 --> 00:07:41.220
that rain wing.

00:07:41.279 --> 00:07:44.399
Plunging down, down toward the fallen

00:07:44.399 --> 00:07:47.100
tree, the artful pile of leaves, the

00:07:47.100 --> 00:07:48.180
curving ferns.

00:07:48.600 --> 00:07:49.620
Finally she was here.

00:07:49.680 --> 00:07:52.560
Finally, Her egg was gone.

00:07:52.620 --> 00:07:55.860
Secret keeper scrabbled frantically in

00:07:55.860 --> 00:07:56.639
the dark hollow.

00:07:56.699 --> 00:07:57.480
It couldn't be.

00:07:57.540 --> 00:07:58.620
It couldn't be gone.

00:07:58.680 --> 00:08:01.500
One black egg in the darkest hiding place

00:08:01.500 --> 00:08:03.899
in this gigantic rainforest?

00:08:03.959 --> 00:08:04.560
Who could have found it?

00:08:04.620 --> 00:08:05.759
Where did they take it?

00:08:05.819 --> 00:08:08.100
I should have kept it with me.

00:08:08.160 --> 00:08:10.019
I shouldn't have lied to my tribe.

00:08:10.079 --> 00:08:12.060
I only wanted to protect her from that

00:08:12.060 --> 00:08:14.939
island, from the smoke and the smell and

00:08:14.939 --> 00:08:17.459
the rules and the misery, and from the

00:08:17.459 --> 00:08:19.560
constant fear that the earth will swallow

00:08:19.560 --> 00:08:20.639
us in fire at any moment.

00:08:20.759 --> 00:08:22.319
And now she's gone.

00:08:22.379 --> 00:08:25.800
This is my punishment for deceiving

00:08:25.800 --> 00:08:26.160
everyone.

00:08:26.220 --> 00:08:30.000
She whirled around, hissing, and her eye

00:08:30.000 --> 00:08:30.839
caught on something.

00:08:30.899 --> 00:08:34.139
Not far away, there was a clearing, a

00:08:34.139 --> 00:08:35.580
clearing where the moons broke through

00:08:35.580 --> 00:08:37.679
the trees, and illuminated the forest

00:08:37.679 --> 00:08:38.279
floor.

00:08:38.519 --> 00:08:41.399
In the center of the moonbeams, was her

00:08:41.399 --> 00:08:41.700
egg.

00:08:41.820 --> 00:08:44.820
At least, it had to be her egg.

00:08:44.879 --> 00:08:46.740
But it wasn't black anymore.

00:08:46.799 --> 00:08:49.320
The last time she'd been able to sneak

00:08:49.320 --> 00:08:51.240
out and check on it 3 days ago.

00:08:51.299 --> 00:08:54.299
It had been ebony black, like every night

00:08:54.299 --> 00:08:54.899
wing egg.

00:08:54.960 --> 00:08:58.740
Now it was an eerie silver color, as

00:08:58.740 --> 00:09:01.019
polished and glimmering, as if a piece of

00:09:01.019 --> 00:09:02.639
full moon had fallen from the sky.

00:09:02.700 --> 00:09:06.000
Secret keeper approached it warily.

00:09:06.059 --> 00:09:07.559
Was this a trick?

00:09:07.620 --> 00:09:10.080
Was someone watching, waiting to catch

00:09:10.080 --> 00:09:10.320
her?

00:09:10.379 --> 00:09:12.120
Mastermind?

00:09:12.179 --> 00:09:13.259
Greatness?

00:09:13.379 --> 00:09:15.779
Or was there something wrong with her

00:09:15.779 --> 00:09:16.139
egg?

00:09:16.200 --> 00:09:19.860
Five starburst shaped cracks already

00:09:19.860 --> 00:09:21.899
marked the smooth curve of the silver

00:09:21.899 --> 00:09:22.320
shell.

00:09:22.379 --> 00:09:25.740
Secret keeper circled it, inhaling the

00:09:25.740 --> 00:09:26.340
scents around it.

00:09:26.399 --> 00:09:28.740
How did it roll over here?

00:09:28.799 --> 00:09:30.539
Why did it change color?

00:09:30.600 --> 00:09:33.539
There were no clues in the mossy hollow

00:09:33.539 --> 00:09:35.759
where the egg now lay, bathed in

00:09:35.759 --> 00:09:36.299
moonlight.

00:09:36.360 --> 00:09:39.539
The egg rocked suddenly, and a long crack

00:09:39.539 --> 00:09:41.039
splintered across the top of it.

00:09:41.100 --> 00:09:43.740
Secret keeper felt a burst of panic.

00:09:43.799 --> 00:09:45.899
Was she supposed to help somehow?

00:09:45.960 --> 00:09:48.720
Should she crack the shell herself, or

00:09:48.720 --> 00:09:49.799
try to keep the egg warm?

00:09:49.860 --> 00:09:52.200
She'd never seen a hatching before.

00:09:52.320 --> 00:09:54.600
There were so few hatchings on the

00:09:54.600 --> 00:09:56.940
Nightwing Island, and hardly anyone was

00:09:56.940 --> 00:09:58.919
allowed to attend them, for fear of

00:09:58.919 --> 00:10:00.360
contaminating the precious new

00:10:00.360 --> 00:10:01.200
dragonettes.

00:10:01.259 --> 00:10:04.440
If she hadn't lied to everyone, about

00:10:04.440 --> 00:10:06.480
having stomach crams during a hunt in the

00:10:06.480 --> 00:10:08.700
rainforest, about the egg coming out

00:10:08.700 --> 00:10:11.279
cracked, about burying the pieces alone

00:10:11.279 --> 00:10:14.639
if she'd had her egg on the island, then

00:10:14.639 --> 00:10:16.080
she would probably have gotten to see a

00:10:16.080 --> 00:10:18.659
hatching in the last year, there had only

00:10:18.659 --> 00:10:21.120
been one, a dragonette called Mighty

00:10:21.120 --> 00:10:23.700
Claus, and expecting dragon would have

00:10:23.700 --> 00:10:25.679
been welcome to see how a hatching worked

00:10:25.679 --> 00:10:27.779
but not a dragon who'd lost an egg.

00:10:27.840 --> 00:10:30.480
There were several dragons on the island

00:10:30.480 --> 00:10:32.220
whose eggs had cracked before they

00:10:32.220 --> 00:10:34.740
hatched, and it was considered a kindness

00:10:34.740 --> 00:10:36.419
to keep them apart from the healthy eggs

00:10:36.419 --> 00:10:37.620
and dragonettes.

00:10:37.679 --> 00:10:40.559
So Secret Keeper had no idea what to do.

00:10:40.620 --> 00:10:42.779
She'd never heard of an egg turning

00:10:42.779 --> 00:10:43.139
silver.

00:10:43.200 --> 00:10:45.419
Had she done something wrong when she

00:10:45.419 --> 00:10:46.559
laid the egg all alone?

00:10:46.620 --> 00:10:49.320
Had she hidden it in a place that was bad

00:10:49.320 --> 00:10:49.620
for it?

00:10:49.679 --> 00:10:52.200
Maybe she was supposed to be turning it

00:10:52.200 --> 00:10:53.399
every night or something like that?

00:10:53.460 --> 00:10:55.799
Maybe she'd already ruined the

00:10:55.799 --> 00:10:57.240
dragonette's life before it even

00:10:57.240 --> 00:10:57.720
hatched.

00:10:57.779 --> 00:10:59.340
And what would happen now?

00:10:59.399 --> 00:11:02.159
What if her dragonette was broken?

00:11:02.220 --> 00:11:05.399
After all the lying and worrying, she

00:11:05.399 --> 00:11:06.960
wasn't sure she could survive if there

00:11:06.960 --> 00:11:07.559
was something wrong.

00:11:07.620 --> 00:11:10.860
I will love her anyway, she thought

00:11:10.860 --> 00:11:11.460
fiercely.

00:11:11.519 --> 00:11:13.019
Hoping that was true.

00:11:13.080 --> 00:11:16.500
Secret keeper brushed away tears, trying

00:11:16.500 --> 00:11:18.419
to focus, no matter what.

00:11:18.480 --> 00:11:20.759
There was a living dragonette in that egg

00:11:20.759 --> 00:11:21.720
trying to get out.

00:11:21.779 --> 00:11:24.720
She crouched, and gently wrapped her

00:11:24.720 --> 00:11:26.039
talons around the eggshell.

00:11:26.100 --> 00:11:28.620
The shell instantly splintered into a

00:11:28.620 --> 00:11:31.320
1000 pieces, showering the ground with

00:11:31.320 --> 00:11:33.840
glittering shards, sitting in between

00:11:33.840 --> 00:11:37.440
secret keeper's claws, blinking, was a

00:11:37.440 --> 00:11:38.879
tiny black dragonette.

00:11:39.000 --> 00:11:41.759
Oh, Secret Keeper gasped.

00:11:41.820 --> 00:11:45.120
The dragonette looked up, up, up at her

00:11:45.120 --> 00:11:47.519
mother's head and wings towering over

00:11:47.519 --> 00:11:47.700
her.

00:11:47.759 --> 00:11:51.419
She squeaked once, softly, and then stood

00:11:51.419 --> 00:11:54.419
up and shook herself, unfurling her own

00:11:54.419 --> 00:11:55.080
small wings.

00:11:55.139 --> 00:11:58.500
Secret keeper stared at her in awe.

00:11:58.559 --> 00:12:01.980
She was perfect, perfect in every way.

00:12:02.039 --> 00:12:04.919
Her scales gleamed as though they'd been

00:12:04.919 --> 00:12:05.639
polished.

00:12:05.820 --> 00:12:07.740
Her claws were miniature curved

00:12:07.740 --> 00:12:08.460
crescents.

00:12:08.519 --> 00:12:11.279
Her tail was the most perfect tail secret

00:12:11.279 --> 00:12:12.299
keeper had ever seen.

00:12:12.360 --> 00:12:14.759
She already looked healthier than every

00:12:14.759 --> 00:12:17.220
night wing secret keeper knew, and that

00:12:17.220 --> 00:12:17.580
was enough.

00:12:17.639 --> 00:12:20.879
That was exactly why secret keeper had

00:12:20.879 --> 00:12:21.659
risked so much.

00:12:21.720 --> 00:12:24.480
She wished she could share this moment

00:12:24.480 --> 00:12:25.860
with the dragonette's father.

00:12:25.919 --> 00:12:27.840
But he couldn't be trusted.

00:12:27.899 --> 00:12:30.779
He would almost certainly tell the tribe

00:12:30.779 --> 00:12:33.000
and insist she be raised on the island.

00:12:33.059 --> 00:12:35.519
If that meant he would never learn he had

00:12:35.519 --> 00:12:35.879
a daughter.

00:12:35.940 --> 00:12:37.080
Then too bad.

00:12:37.139 --> 00:12:39.899
The dragonette tilted her head back to

00:12:39.899 --> 00:12:41.399
stare up at the 2 full moons.

00:12:41.460 --> 00:12:43.860
Their silvery light reflected in her

00:12:43.860 --> 00:12:44.279
eyes.

00:12:44.340 --> 00:12:46.440
And secret keeper realized.

00:12:46.500 --> 00:12:48.360
There was one odd thing about her.

00:12:48.419 --> 00:12:50.940
A silver scale shown on the outside

00:12:50.940 --> 00:12:53.879
corner of each eye, like a teardrop about

00:12:53.879 --> 00:12:54.179
to fall.

00:12:54.240 --> 00:12:57.000
Odd, but beautiful.

00:12:57.059 --> 00:13:00.360
Her small talons reached toward the moons

00:13:00.360 --> 00:13:02.399
as if she wanted to pull them out of the

00:13:02.399 --> 00:13:03.659
sky and roll them around.

00:13:03.720 --> 00:13:06.659
Secret keeper picked her up, feeling

00:13:06.659 --> 00:13:09.299
large and unwieldy, with something so

00:13:09.299 --> 00:13:10.320
small and delicate.

00:13:10.440 --> 00:13:12.960
She lifted the dragonette up to see the

00:13:12.960 --> 00:13:15.179
moons, and then brought her in close

00:13:15.179 --> 00:13:16.559
cuddling her to her chest.

00:13:16.620 --> 00:13:19.740
I'm your mother, little one, she

00:13:19.740 --> 00:13:20.220
whispered.

00:13:20.279 --> 00:13:21.840
I'm going to call you.

00:13:21.899 --> 00:13:23.279
Moon Watcher.

00:13:23.399 --> 00:13:25.500
You're going to have the happiest life

00:13:25.500 --> 00:13:28.019
any dragon has ever had, and you're going

00:13:28.019 --> 00:13:29.100
to live forever and ever.

00:13:29.220 --> 00:13:31.740
And the volcano will never have you.

00:13:31.799 --> 00:13:35.340
Moon Watcher squeaked again and leaned

00:13:35.340 --> 00:13:36.360
into her mother's warmth.

00:13:36.480 --> 00:13:39.419
Secret keeper let go of the worrying and

00:13:39.419 --> 00:13:39.899
the guilt.

00:13:39.960 --> 00:13:42.000
She stopped thinking about what had

00:13:42.000 --> 00:13:43.620
happened or what was going to happen.

00:13:43.679 --> 00:13:46.080
She was right where she needed to be.

00:13:46.139 --> 00:13:49.740
A long, quiet time passed.

00:13:49.799 --> 00:13:52.500
And then, Secret keeper.

00:13:53.340 --> 00:13:54.600
A voice bellowed from the treetops.

00:13:54.659 --> 00:13:56.879
Secret keeper jolted awake.

00:13:56.940 --> 00:13:59.100
Her dragonette was curled in the curve of

00:13:59.100 --> 00:14:01.080
her wing, sleeping soundly.

00:14:01.139 --> 00:14:03.419
They were both brightly lit by the full

00:14:03.419 --> 00:14:05.700
moons of her head, and someone was

00:14:05.700 --> 00:14:06.899
shouting her name through the

00:14:06.899 --> 00:14:07.500
rainforest.

00:14:07.559 --> 00:14:10.860
Pray, hunter, she thought, idiot.

00:14:10.919 --> 00:14:12.659
What do the rain wings hurt him?

00:14:12.720 --> 00:14:15.059
Then she came fully awake and realized

00:14:15.059 --> 00:14:16.620
what would happen if he found her like

00:14:16.620 --> 00:14:19.080
this with a secret night wing

00:14:19.080 --> 00:14:19.679
dragonette?

00:14:19.740 --> 00:14:22.080
Moon Watcher would be taken straight back

00:14:22.080 --> 00:14:24.659
to the island, and Secret Keeper would be

00:14:24.659 --> 00:14:25.799
punished for lying about her.

00:14:25.860 --> 00:14:28.620
She wasn't sure how, but she knew

00:14:28.620 --> 00:14:30.179
anything that involved being separated

00:14:30.179 --> 00:14:32.100
from Moon Watcher would be unbearable.

00:14:32.159 --> 00:14:35.519
Moon Watcher, she whispered urgently.

00:14:35.580 --> 00:14:37.860
The dragonette opened sleepy eyes.

00:14:37.919 --> 00:14:39.600
We have to hide you.

00:14:39.720 --> 00:14:41.159
Ark?

00:14:41.279 --> 00:14:42.299
Her daughter answered.

00:14:42.360 --> 00:14:43.620
Come here.

00:14:43.679 --> 00:14:46.559
Secret keeper scooped her up and hurried

00:14:46.559 --> 00:14:48.059
back into the darker shadows of the

00:14:48.059 --> 00:14:48.360
forest.

00:14:48.419 --> 00:14:51.720
Moon Watcher squeaked sadly and reached

00:14:51.720 --> 00:14:52.559
for the moonlight again.

00:14:52.620 --> 00:14:55.139
No, you can't go out there.

00:14:55.200 --> 00:14:56.879
You have to stay hidden, do you

00:14:56.879 --> 00:14:57.179
understand?

00:14:57.240 --> 00:14:59.279
You must not let any dragon find you

00:14:59.279 --> 00:15:00.000
except mommy.

00:15:00.059 --> 00:15:03.240
Secret keeper crouch beside her hollow

00:15:03.240 --> 00:15:05.820
where the fallen log and thick ferns

00:15:05.820 --> 00:15:06.960
created a hidden space.

00:15:07.019 --> 00:15:09.419
She tucked Moon Watcher into the shadows

00:15:09.419 --> 00:15:11.580
and started pulling foliage over her to

00:15:11.580 --> 00:15:12.059
conceal her.

00:15:12.179 --> 00:15:15.059
Moon Watcher asked.

00:15:15.179 --> 00:15:17.100
She reached out and caught one of her

00:15:17.100 --> 00:15:18.480
mother's claws and her small front

00:15:18.480 --> 00:15:19.139
talons.

00:15:19.259 --> 00:15:20.759
Argh.

00:15:20.820 --> 00:15:24.840
No, I can't stay, Secret Keeper said.

00:15:24.899 --> 00:15:25.679
I'm sorry.

00:15:25.740 --> 00:15:27.120
You'll be safer if I go.

00:15:27.179 --> 00:15:29.759
Terrifying images flashed through her

00:15:29.759 --> 00:15:30.000
head.

00:15:30.059 --> 00:15:32.879
Nightwing hunters finding Moon Watcher by

00:15:32.879 --> 00:15:35.519
accident, or rain wings stumbling on her

00:15:35.519 --> 00:15:36.600
and taking her back to their own

00:15:36.600 --> 00:15:37.139
village.

00:15:37.200 --> 00:15:40.500
She couldn't, she mustn't, be seen by any

00:15:40.500 --> 00:15:41.460
other dragons.

00:15:41.519 --> 00:15:43.860
What had secret keeper been thinking?

00:15:43.919 --> 00:15:47.039
Hiding an egg was one thing, hiding a

00:15:47.039 --> 00:15:49.019
dragonette who could move and squeak and

00:15:49.019 --> 00:15:50.399
call for help was quite another.

00:15:50.460 --> 00:15:52.679
How could Moon Watcher possibly

00:15:52.679 --> 00:15:53.820
understand something like this?

00:15:53.879 --> 00:15:57.600
I'll be back as soon as I can, Secret

00:15:57.600 --> 00:15:58.320
Keeper promised.

00:15:58.379 --> 00:16:00.480
Please, please don't leave this spot

00:16:00.480 --> 00:16:01.200
until I come.

00:16:01.259 --> 00:16:01.980
All right.

00:16:02.039 --> 00:16:04.620
She realized that Moon Watcher was

00:16:04.620 --> 00:16:07.379
staring intently into her eyes, almost as

00:16:07.379 --> 00:16:09.120
if she was reading the images flashing

00:16:09.120 --> 00:16:09.899
through her mother's mind.

00:16:09.960 --> 00:16:12.000
Is it possible?

00:16:12.059 --> 00:16:14.879
The scrolls say Nightwings once had mind

00:16:14.879 --> 00:16:17.220
reading powers, but I thought that was

00:16:17.220 --> 00:16:18.840
just the lie we tell the rest of the

00:16:18.840 --> 00:16:20.039
tribe so they'll fear us.

00:16:20.100 --> 00:16:21.840
If it was ever true.

00:16:21.899 --> 00:16:23.759
It certainly hasn't been for the last

00:16:23.759 --> 00:16:24.659
several generations.

00:16:24.720 --> 00:16:27.779
Still, there was something about the way

00:16:27.779 --> 00:16:29.100
Moon Watcher was looking at her.

00:16:29.159 --> 00:16:31.860
Not quite knowing what she was doing

00:16:31.860 --> 00:16:34.799
Secret Keeper put her front talent gently

00:16:34.799 --> 00:16:36.539
on either side of Moon Watcher's head and

00:16:36.539 --> 00:16:38.639
whispered, Stay secret.

00:16:38.700 --> 00:16:39.720
Stay hidden.

00:16:39.779 --> 00:16:41.039
Stay safe.

00:16:41.159 --> 00:16:43.799
She thought as hard as she could about

00:16:43.799 --> 00:16:45.840
the dangers of the rainforest, and

00:16:45.840 --> 00:16:47.820
especially the dangers of other dragons.

00:16:47.879 --> 00:16:50.399
She pictured Moon Watcher curling into

00:16:50.399 --> 00:16:52.679
the ferns and not moving until her mother

00:16:52.679 --> 00:16:53.820
returned.

00:16:53.879 --> 00:16:56.220
Moon Watcher blinked, and then nodded

00:16:56.220 --> 00:16:56.580
slowly.

00:16:56.639 --> 00:16:59.340
She backed into the hollow and scratched

00:16:59.340 --> 00:17:00.419
leaves around herself.

00:17:00.480 --> 00:17:02.700
Secret keeper.

00:17:02.759 --> 00:17:04.319
Pray hunter shouted again.

00:17:04.380 --> 00:17:06.420
He sounded chillingly close.

00:17:06.480 --> 00:17:08.819
See you soon, little one.

00:17:08.940 --> 00:17:10.559
Secret keeper whispered.

00:17:10.680 --> 00:17:13.500
Her claws wanted to clutch the earth, to

00:17:13.500 --> 00:17:15.240
stay right here with her dragonette and

00:17:15.240 --> 00:17:16.079
never, ever leave.

00:17:16.200 --> 00:17:18.599
It was harder than anything she'd ever

00:17:18.599 --> 00:17:21.119
had to do before, but she made herself

00:17:21.119 --> 00:17:23.099
turn and fly off into the trees.

00:17:23.160 --> 00:17:26.099
The tears came, and she let them.

00:17:26.160 --> 00:17:29.279
Perhaps if he saw her crying, Prey Hunter

00:17:29.279 --> 00:17:30.720
would be too embarrassed to grill her

00:17:30.720 --> 00:17:32.819
about where she'd been for so long, and

00:17:32.819 --> 00:17:34.440
why she was coming back with no prey.

00:17:34.500 --> 00:17:37.440
Her wing beats faded into the darkness

00:17:37.440 --> 00:17:40.259
replaced by the chirping of crickets, the

00:17:40.259 --> 00:17:42.720
scurrying of lizards, and the stranger

00:17:42.720 --> 00:17:44.640
more unidentifiable noises of the

00:17:44.640 --> 00:17:45.660
rainforest at night.

00:17:45.720 --> 00:17:49.799
Somewhere, not too far away, a jaguar

00:17:49.799 --> 00:17:50.339
roared.

00:17:50.400 --> 00:17:52.319
Several moments passed.

00:17:52.380 --> 00:17:57.059
Said a small voice from the fern hollow.

00:17:57.119 --> 00:17:58.980
Nobody answered her.

00:17:59.099 --> 00:18:02.160
Oh, she said again softly.

00:18:02.220 --> 00:18:05.940
She was alone, with his shadows firmly

00:18:05.940 --> 00:18:08.279
wrapped around her, and no company except

00:18:08.279 --> 00:18:10.079
the frightening pictures her mother had

00:18:10.079 --> 00:18:11.700
left, trailing through her mind.

00:18:11.759 --> 00:18:13.619
Two hours old.

00:18:13.680 --> 00:18:16.859
And all she knew so far was that the

00:18:16.859 --> 00:18:19.200
world was a dangerous, terrifying place

00:18:19.200 --> 00:18:19.859
without her mother.

00:18:19.920 --> 00:18:23.460
Oh, Moon Watcher tried again.

00:18:23.519 --> 00:18:27.960
Rainforest noises, the small drip drop of

00:18:27.960 --> 00:18:29.039
rain starting to fall.

00:18:29.099 --> 00:18:33.059
A long pause, and then barely a whisper

00:18:33.059 --> 00:18:34.440
Mommy?

00:18:34.559 --> 00:18:38.519
Part one.

00:18:38.579 --> 00:18:41.339
Welcome to Jade Mountain.

00:18:41.400 --> 00:18:43.019
Chapter one.

00:18:43.079 --> 00:18:46.920
I don't want you to leave me here, Moon

00:18:46.920 --> 00:18:47.339
said.

00:18:47.400 --> 00:18:49.980
She fit perfectly under her mother's wing

00:18:49.980 --> 00:18:51.960
as if that spot had been shaped by the

00:18:51.960 --> 00:18:54.420
universe just for her, like a sign.

00:18:54.480 --> 00:18:55.980
This is where you should be.

00:18:56.039 --> 00:18:57.779
Stay here for always.

00:18:57.839 --> 00:19:00.660
Certainly do not let your mother abandon

00:19:00.660 --> 00:19:03.180
you on a windy mountaintop, positively

00:19:03.180 --> 00:19:04.980
swarming with strange dragons.

00:19:05.039 --> 00:19:07.920
They found a spot under a tree where they

00:19:07.920 --> 00:19:09.660
could watch the main arrival area for the

00:19:09.660 --> 00:19:11.759
school, which perhaps hadn't been the

00:19:11.759 --> 00:19:14.099
best idea, as now Moon was fairly sure

00:19:14.099 --> 00:19:16.079
she'd seen about a 1000 different kinds

00:19:16.079 --> 00:19:18.420
of dragon, all of them entirely too

00:19:18.420 --> 00:19:18.900
loud.

00:19:18.960 --> 00:19:22.140
She shied away as 2 mud wings galloped

00:19:22.140 --> 00:19:23.940
past her, shouting and laughing.

00:19:24.000 --> 00:19:27.299
He looked so big and rowdy.

00:19:27.299 --> 00:19:29.039
How is she supposed to learn anything

00:19:29.039 --> 00:19:30.779
when she might get trampled at any moment

00:19:30.779 --> 00:19:31.920
by her fellow students?

00:19:31.980 --> 00:19:34.140
And what if they hated her?

00:19:34.259 --> 00:19:36.359
She wouldn't even have to do anything

00:19:36.359 --> 00:19:38.819
wrong, although that seemed awfully

00:19:38.819 --> 00:19:39.900
likely to happen anyway.

00:19:39.960 --> 00:19:42.779
They'd hate her just for being a night

00:19:42.779 --> 00:19:43.140
wing.

00:19:43.200 --> 00:19:46.740
Everybody did, except the night wings, who

00:19:46.740 --> 00:19:48.240
hated her for not being enough of a night

00:19:48.240 --> 00:19:48.599
wing.

00:19:48.660 --> 00:19:51.900
I really, really don't want to stay here

00:19:51.900 --> 00:19:53.339
Moon said again.

00:19:53.460 --> 00:19:57.240
I know, her mother said kindly, but you

00:19:57.240 --> 00:19:57.599
have to.

00:19:57.660 --> 00:19:58.920
And it'll be good for you.

00:19:58.980 --> 00:20:00.720
I think you'll like it better than the

00:20:00.720 --> 00:20:01.500
Nightwing Village.

00:20:01.559 --> 00:20:01.980
Youll see.

00:20:02.099 --> 00:20:05.099
At least Jade Mountain won't be full of

00:20:05.099 --> 00:20:05.640
night wings.

00:20:05.700 --> 00:20:06.900
Her mind went on.

00:20:06.960 --> 00:20:09.119
I like being wherever you are.

00:20:09.180 --> 00:20:10.259
Moon said.

00:20:10.319 --> 00:20:12.299
And I don't mind the other night wings

00:20:12.299 --> 00:20:13.500
that much.

00:20:13.559 --> 00:20:15.839
Most of them are awful, and you know it.

00:20:15.900 --> 00:20:17.759
Secret keeper pointed out.

00:20:17.819 --> 00:20:20.819
They were both thinking of the stairs, the

00:20:20.819 --> 00:20:23.279
whispers, the open jealousy and hostility

00:20:23.279 --> 00:20:25.259
when secret keeper brought her healthy

00:20:25.259 --> 00:20:27.119
well fed dragonette back into the tribe.

00:20:27.180 --> 00:20:28.980
That was 6 months ago.

00:20:29.039 --> 00:20:31.559
After the volcano destroyed their island

00:20:31.559 --> 00:20:33.299
and all the night wings had moved into

00:20:33.299 --> 00:20:33.960
the rainforest.

00:20:34.019 --> 00:20:36.720
Queen Glory had officially forgiven her

00:20:36.720 --> 00:20:39.240
for breaking tribe rules, but that didn't

00:20:39.240 --> 00:20:40.380
mean anyone else had.

00:20:40.440 --> 00:20:42.779
Here you'll be with much nicer dragons

00:20:42.779 --> 00:20:44.640
like Sonny and Starflight.

00:20:44.700 --> 00:20:46.200
Remember you met them and you liked

00:20:46.200 --> 00:20:46.500
them?

00:20:46.559 --> 00:20:48.660
I want to be with you.

00:20:48.779 --> 00:20:50.759
Moon replied simply.

00:20:50.819 --> 00:20:53.819
It wasn't fair, to finally be given all

00:20:53.819 --> 00:20:55.920
the time she wanted with her mother, to

00:20:55.920 --> 00:20:57.299
be with her every moment of the day

00:20:57.299 --> 00:20:59.940
instead of stolen hours a few times a

00:20:59.940 --> 00:21:01.920
week, and then have to have it all taken

00:21:01.920 --> 00:21:02.460
away again.

00:21:02.519 --> 00:21:05.519
I'll visit, her mother promised.

00:21:05.579 --> 00:21:07.859
You'll see me all the time, and you'll

00:21:07.859 --> 00:21:08.400
make friends here.

00:21:08.460 --> 00:21:09.420
I'm sure you will.

00:21:09.480 --> 00:21:13.079
Well, I hope you will, my weird little

00:21:13.079 --> 00:21:13.619
diamond.

00:21:13.680 --> 00:21:16.740
I'm not a weird little diamond, Moon

00:21:16.740 --> 00:21:17.339
protested.

00:21:17.400 --> 00:21:20.279
Secret keeper crouched and put her face

00:21:20.279 --> 00:21:21.480
right in front of moons.

00:21:21.539 --> 00:21:24.420
You need to stop doing that, remember, she

00:21:24.420 --> 00:21:24.900
whispered.

00:21:24.960 --> 00:21:27.059
If you only hear it in your head, don't

00:21:27.059 --> 00:21:27.359
respond.

00:21:27.420 --> 00:21:29.519
No one can know about your curse.

00:21:29.519 --> 00:21:31.859
Everybody thinks Night Wings don't have

00:21:31.859 --> 00:21:32.400
powers anymore.

00:21:32.460 --> 00:21:34.559
They won't know what to do with you if

00:21:34.559 --> 00:21:35.039
they find out.

00:21:35.099 --> 00:21:37.500
And how will you make friends that way?

00:21:37.559 --> 00:21:39.180
Her mind worried.

00:21:39.240 --> 00:21:41.339
If you keep guessing their thoughts and

00:21:41.339 --> 00:21:42.299
making them uncomfortable.

00:21:42.359 --> 00:21:45.180
Or they might not believe you, and then

00:21:45.180 --> 00:21:46.079
they'll hate you for lying.

00:21:46.140 --> 00:21:47.940
So don't let them find out all right.

00:21:48.000 --> 00:21:51.059
I know, Moon answered.

00:21:51.119 --> 00:21:52.619
Stay secret.

00:21:52.680 --> 00:21:53.759
Stay hidden.

00:21:53.819 --> 00:21:54.599
Stay safe.

00:21:54.660 --> 00:21:57.299
All the years of pretending to have mind

00:21:57.299 --> 00:21:59.579
reading powers, had made the night wings

00:21:59.579 --> 00:22:01.859
truly fear the idea of any dragon reading

00:22:01.859 --> 00:22:02.640
their minds.

00:22:02.759 --> 00:22:04.019
She paused.

00:22:04.079 --> 00:22:06.900
So, isn't this really dangerous?

00:22:06.960 --> 00:22:09.059
What if I make a mistake here?

00:22:09.119 --> 00:22:11.220
With all these different kinds of dragons

00:22:11.220 --> 00:22:11.519
around?

00:22:11.579 --> 00:22:13.380
You won't.

00:22:13.500 --> 00:22:14.759
You'll be careful.

00:22:14.819 --> 00:22:16.980
Secret keeper said firmly.

00:22:17.039 --> 00:22:19.319
I know it's terrible to be the way you

00:22:19.319 --> 00:22:22.019
are, but if you keep it a secret, you can

00:22:22.019 --> 00:22:22.740
have a normal life.

00:22:22.799 --> 00:22:25.019
Know one needs to know that you're not a

00:22:25.019 --> 00:22:25.799
normal dragon.

00:22:25.859 --> 00:22:26.819
Understand?

00:22:26.880 --> 00:22:28.920
Are you ready to go inside?

00:22:28.980 --> 00:22:30.900
Not yet.

00:22:30.960 --> 00:22:32.039
Moon said.

00:22:32.099 --> 00:22:34.140
Can we watch for a little longer?

00:22:34.200 --> 00:22:36.599
Secret keeper sighed.

00:22:36.660 --> 00:22:37.799
Sure.

00:22:37.920 --> 00:22:40.200
She's so nervous all the time.

00:22:40.259 --> 00:22:42.660
I'm sure I was never that nervous when I

00:22:42.660 --> 00:22:43.440
was a dragonette.

00:22:43.500 --> 00:22:45.599
Moon frowned up at her mother.

00:22:45.720 --> 00:22:48.480
She was glad the mind listening only went

00:22:48.480 --> 00:22:51.779
one way, but sometimes, like now, she

00:22:51.779 --> 00:22:53.579
wished her own mind could shout back

00:22:53.579 --> 00:22:55.559
don't you think maybe there's a reason

00:22:55.559 --> 00:22:56.339
I'm like this?

00:22:56.460 --> 00:22:58.920
Oh, look!

00:22:58.980 --> 00:23:01.799
Secret Keeper said obliviously, her eyes

00:23:01.799 --> 00:23:02.700
lighting up.

00:23:02.759 --> 00:23:05.279
She pointed to the sky, where blue and

00:23:05.279 --> 00:23:06.960
green wings were sailing down toward

00:23:06.960 --> 00:23:07.140
them.

00:23:07.200 --> 00:23:08.880
Sea wings.

00:23:08.940 --> 00:23:10.559
Do you see the one with the ropes of

00:23:10.559 --> 00:23:10.980
pearls?

00:23:11.039 --> 00:23:12.240
I think that's their queen.

00:23:12.299 --> 00:23:15.660
Queen Coral, Moon recited.

00:23:15.720 --> 00:23:18.299
One thing she could do that didn't

00:23:18.299 --> 00:23:20.279
involve being stared at by other dragons

00:23:20.279 --> 00:23:22.079
or accidentally saying the wrong thing

00:23:22.079 --> 00:23:23.160
was study.

00:23:23.220 --> 00:23:25.740
And so she done a lot of that to prepare

00:23:25.740 --> 00:23:26.880
for Jade Mountain Academy.

00:23:26.940 --> 00:23:30.299
Those 2 must be her daughters, since she

00:23:30.299 --> 00:23:31.440
never lets them out of her sight.

00:23:31.500 --> 00:23:33.359
I don't know who the other one is.

00:23:33.420 --> 00:23:36.480
Remember not to show off, her mother

00:23:36.480 --> 00:23:37.019
said.

00:23:37.079 --> 00:23:40.140
I mean, thank you for telling me, but the

00:23:40.140 --> 00:23:41.759
other dragons might not like you if you

00:23:41.759 --> 00:23:42.960
always know all the answers.

00:23:43.019 --> 00:23:46.079
Moon stared down at her claws.

00:23:46.140 --> 00:23:48.660
It was pretty clear from secret keeper's

00:23:48.660 --> 00:23:50.279
thoughts that her mother was a lot more

00:23:50.279 --> 00:23:52.140
worried about whether other dragons would

00:23:52.140 --> 00:23:54.420
like Moon than she was about whether Moon

00:23:54.420 --> 00:23:55.079
would like them.

00:23:55.140 --> 00:23:57.960
That, in fact, didn't seem to be among

00:23:57.960 --> 00:23:58.980
her concerns at all.

00:23:59.039 --> 00:24:02.640
A deep blue sea wing came barreling out

00:24:02.640 --> 00:24:04.559
of the entrance cave as the other sea

00:24:04.559 --> 00:24:05.279
wings landed.

00:24:05.339 --> 00:24:08.160
You came, she called happily.

00:24:08.220 --> 00:24:10.619
Her wings flared out, and wrapped around

00:24:10.619 --> 00:24:12.779
the older daughter, who was a pale white

00:24:12.779 --> 00:24:15.839
pink, like the inside of seashells, the

00:24:15.839 --> 00:24:17.640
smaller daughter, who had to be less than

00:24:17.640 --> 00:24:20.039
a year old, bounced around their hug

00:24:20.039 --> 00:24:21.359
yelping and trying to get in.

00:24:21.420 --> 00:24:24.059
She was attached to the queen by a long

00:24:24.059 --> 00:24:26.519
harness, which kept getting tangled under

00:24:26.519 --> 00:24:27.779
her talons and tripping her.

00:24:27.839 --> 00:24:31.740
I'm really not sure about this, Queen

00:24:31.740 --> 00:24:33.180
Carl said in a rumbly voice.

00:24:33.240 --> 00:24:35.819
She was the same shade of blue as the sea

00:24:35.819 --> 00:24:37.380
wing who was now being tackled by the

00:24:37.380 --> 00:24:38.460
little dragonette.

00:24:38.519 --> 00:24:40.799
In fact, Moon guessed they might be

00:24:40.799 --> 00:24:41.400
mother and daughter.

00:24:41.460 --> 00:24:46.680
Oh, I'm a snail brain, she realized, that

00:24:46.680 --> 00:24:47.759
must be tsunami.

00:24:47.819 --> 00:24:50.819
The famous sea wing princess from the

00:24:50.819 --> 00:24:53.099
prophecy had been in the rainforest for a

00:24:53.099 --> 00:24:55.079
while, but moon hadn't met her before

00:24:55.079 --> 00:24:57.059
tsunami left to work on getting the Jade

00:24:57.059 --> 00:24:58.079
Mountain Academy ready.

00:24:58.140 --> 00:24:59.579
It'll be great.

00:24:59.700 --> 00:25:02.579
Tsunami promised the queen, I'll take

00:25:02.579 --> 00:25:03.359
care of anemone.

00:25:03.420 --> 00:25:04.079
I promise.

00:25:04.140 --> 00:25:05.940
She grinned at her sister.

00:25:06.000 --> 00:25:09.240
Me too, me too, yelled the small

00:25:09.240 --> 00:25:09.900
dragonette.

00:25:09.960 --> 00:25:11.460
I want to go to school too.

00:25:11.519 --> 00:25:14.339
She pounced on her harness and wrestled

00:25:14.339 --> 00:25:15.839
it to the ground, growling at it.

00:25:15.900 --> 00:25:19.859
You are much too young, Carl said

00:25:19.859 --> 00:25:20.400
sternly.

00:25:20.460 --> 00:25:22.619
She tugged the little princess upright.

00:25:22.680 --> 00:25:24.960
I can't risk anything happening to you

00:25:24.960 --> 00:25:26.940
especially while anemone is this far

00:25:26.940 --> 00:25:27.240
away.

00:25:27.299 --> 00:25:31.200
Maybe next year, Aucklet, Tsunami said.

00:25:31.259 --> 00:25:33.180
The little dragon beamed hopefully.

00:25:33.240 --> 00:25:35.339
The queen frowned at tsunami.

00:25:35.460 --> 00:25:38.039
And I'm only letting this happen because

00:25:38.039 --> 00:25:39.900
Anemone has been badgering me about it

00:25:39.900 --> 00:25:41.640
every day since she got your message

00:25:41.640 --> 00:25:43.799
about the school, but you can come home

00:25:43.799 --> 00:25:44.819
anytime.

00:25:44.940 --> 00:25:45.779
You understand?

00:25:45.839 --> 00:25:48.119
If you feel threatened or lonely or

00:25:48.119 --> 00:25:49.319
overworked or tired.

00:25:49.380 --> 00:25:53.220
I'll be fine, Anemone said, wriggling

00:25:53.220 --> 00:25:54.240
away from her mother's hug.

00:25:54.299 --> 00:25:57.240
Moon felt her own wings drooping.

00:25:57.299 --> 00:25:59.759
Why didn't secret keeper want to keep her

00:25:59.759 --> 00:26:00.420
clothes like that?

00:26:00.480 --> 00:26:03.180
Why wasn't she getting a speech about

00:26:03.180 --> 00:26:04.859
coming home the moment she got lonely?

00:26:04.920 --> 00:26:07.259
Was it because her mother thought she was

00:26:07.259 --> 00:26:07.680
cursed?

00:26:07.740 --> 00:26:10.680
Maybe secret keeper really wanted to keep

00:26:10.680 --> 00:26:12.180
moon as far away from her as possible?

00:26:12.240 --> 00:26:15.539
Her thoughts never quite said that, but

00:26:15.539 --> 00:26:17.099
she'd learned to block some of them over

00:26:17.099 --> 00:26:19.859
the last 4 years, and she did worry all

00:26:19.859 --> 00:26:21.539
the time about Moon's mind reading.

00:26:21.599 --> 00:26:24.480
Moon wasn't sure she wanted to be normal

00:26:24.480 --> 00:26:27.000
if it meant grumping around, thinking

00:26:27.000 --> 00:26:29.039
only her own thoughts, and mostly all

00:26:29.039 --> 00:26:31.380
about herself, the way most night wings

00:26:31.380 --> 00:26:31.559
did.

00:26:31.680 --> 00:26:33.839
But her mother seemed very sure that

00:26:33.839 --> 00:26:34.859
she'd be happier that way.

00:26:34.920 --> 00:26:37.680
Maybe acting normal was something she

00:26:37.680 --> 00:26:38.160
could learn here.

00:26:38.220 --> 00:26:40.019
Who's this?

00:26:40.079 --> 00:26:41.220
Tsunami asked.

00:26:41.279 --> 00:26:43.740
Turning to the last Sea Wing Dragonette

00:26:43.740 --> 00:26:46.019
who sat behind Queen Coral with a patient

00:26:46.019 --> 00:26:46.799
expression on his face.

00:26:46.920 --> 00:26:50.099
He looked about Moon's age, and he was

00:26:50.099 --> 00:26:52.680
dark green, like an emerald hidden in a

00:26:52.680 --> 00:26:54.839
cave, with flashes of brighter green

00:26:54.839 --> 00:26:56.940
underscales, and hints of gold in his

00:26:56.940 --> 00:26:57.119
eyes.

00:26:57.180 --> 00:27:00.299
He was a little plump, with a sweet extra

00:27:00.299 --> 00:27:02.759
curve to his snout and upper arms, and

00:27:02.759 --> 00:27:05.039
his webbed talons were splayed out, like

00:27:05.039 --> 00:27:06.599
he was worried the wind would shove him

00:27:06.599 --> 00:27:07.079
off the mountain.

00:27:07.140 --> 00:27:10.500
Unlike anemone and aucklet, he was not

00:27:10.500 --> 00:27:12.240
adorned with pearls and jewels.

00:27:12.299 --> 00:27:14.519
His only accessory was a kind of gold

00:27:14.519 --> 00:27:16.920
armband studded with glittering black

00:27:16.920 --> 00:27:17.220
rocks.

00:27:17.279 --> 00:27:20.940
This is one of your brothers, Queen Carl

00:27:20.940 --> 00:27:21.359
said.

00:27:21.420 --> 00:27:23.519
He heard about this and really wanted to

00:27:23.519 --> 00:27:23.880
come too.

00:27:23.940 --> 00:27:25.200
Which one are you again?

00:27:25.259 --> 00:27:29.460
Turtle. he said, shooting tsunami a

00:27:29.460 --> 00:27:30.000
friendly smile.

00:27:30.059 --> 00:27:32.039
One of my brothers?

00:27:32.099 --> 00:27:33.359
Tsunami echoed.

00:27:33.420 --> 00:27:36.660
I didn't realize, I mean, I guess I knew

00:27:36.660 --> 00:27:38.700
the male eggs were surviving every time

00:27:38.700 --> 00:27:40.440
your female eggs were destroyed by the

00:27:40.440 --> 00:27:42.779
orcas statue, but I didn't even think

00:27:42.779 --> 00:27:43.500
about having brothers.

00:27:43.619 --> 00:27:45.900
There are about 30 of us.

00:27:45.960 --> 00:27:47.700
Turtles said with a shrug.

00:27:47.759 --> 00:27:48.960
30?

00:27:49.019 --> 00:27:51.720
Tsunami shouted, I have 30 brothers.

00:27:51.839 --> 00:27:55.559
Well, 32, he said.

00:27:55.619 --> 00:27:58.380
His gays caught moon watching, and he

00:27:58.380 --> 00:28:00.059
wrinkled his snout in an amused way.

00:28:00.119 --> 00:28:02.400
Why didn't you mention this before?

00:28:02.460 --> 00:28:05.039
Tsunami demanded, whipping toward her

00:28:05.039 --> 00:28:05.579
mother?

00:28:05.640 --> 00:28:06.960
Who cares about them?

00:28:07.019 --> 00:28:08.279
Coral asked.

00:28:08.339 --> 00:28:10.019
They can't inherit the throne.

00:28:10.079 --> 00:28:13.559
Moon tilted her head at turtle, expecting

00:28:13.559 --> 00:28:16.319
reaction, and realized she wasn't hearing

00:28:16.319 --> 00:28:17.460
any thoughts from him.

00:28:17.519 --> 00:28:18.720
Nothing at all.

00:28:18.779 --> 00:28:20.759
Just a quiet hum.

00:28:20.819 --> 00:28:23.099
Almost a soothing blankness.

00:28:23.160 --> 00:28:25.079
That was strange.

00:28:25.140 --> 00:28:27.660
Moon had only met a few dragons who could

00:28:27.660 --> 00:28:29.700
block her reading at all, and then only

00:28:29.700 --> 00:28:31.740
sometimes, and they didn't even seem to

00:28:31.740 --> 00:28:32.700
know they could do it.

00:28:32.759 --> 00:28:35.099
A couple of night wings had prickly

00:28:35.099 --> 00:28:36.900
mental shields around some of their

00:28:36.900 --> 00:28:39.900
secrets, but Queen Glory was the best at

00:28:39.900 --> 00:28:40.380
it.

00:28:40.440 --> 00:28:42.900
The rain wing queen clearly wasn't

00:28:42.900 --> 00:28:44.579
intentionally shielding her thoughts from

00:28:44.579 --> 00:28:46.619
mind readers, but whenever she got

00:28:46.619 --> 00:28:48.059
uncomfortable.

00:28:48.119 --> 00:28:49.619
Some kind of instinctive wall went up

00:28:49.619 --> 00:28:50.160
around her mind.

00:28:50.220 --> 00:28:52.740
She did the same thing with her scales

00:28:52.740 --> 00:28:54.599
keeping them from showing her emotions.

00:28:54.660 --> 00:28:57.779
It was unsettling, but in a way that

00:28:57.779 --> 00:28:59.579
always made Moon really curious.

00:28:59.640 --> 00:29:00.839
What were they hiding?

00:29:00.900 --> 00:29:03.119
Was there shielding ability something

00:29:03.119 --> 00:29:04.980
they inherited, or something they

00:29:04.980 --> 00:29:05.940
instinctively developed?

00:29:06.000 --> 00:29:09.119
Turtle wasn't like glory or those night

00:29:09.119 --> 00:29:09.779
wings, though.

00:29:09.839 --> 00:29:12.359
His mind didn't feel like a thorny wall

00:29:12.359 --> 00:29:15.240
radiating, I've got secrets keep out.

00:29:15.299 --> 00:29:16.680
It was just...

00:29:16.680 --> 00:29:18.839
Serenely still.

00:29:18.960 --> 00:29:21.240
How is he hiding his thoughts so

00:29:21.240 --> 00:29:21.839
absolutely.

00:29:21.960 --> 00:29:24.720
He looked so placid and ordinary.

00:29:24.779 --> 00:29:27.839
On the other talent, one thing Moon had

00:29:27.839 --> 00:29:30.000
been able to figure out so far was that

00:29:30.000 --> 00:29:31.740
nobody was ordinary on the inside.

00:29:31.799 --> 00:29:34.259
Tsunami rolled her eyes.

00:29:34.319 --> 00:29:37.380
Well, I'm happy to meet you, turtle, she

00:29:37.380 --> 00:29:37.799
said.

00:29:37.859 --> 00:29:39.720
And I'm glad you're joining our school so

00:29:39.720 --> 00:29:40.559
I can get to know you better.

00:29:40.619 --> 00:29:43.799
I want to see everything before I leave

00:29:43.799 --> 00:29:45.480
said Queen Coral.

00:29:45.539 --> 00:29:47.759
Moon caught twin threads of annoyance

00:29:47.759 --> 00:29:50.160
from tsunami and anemone, but tsunami

00:29:50.160 --> 00:29:50.759
just nodded.

00:29:50.819 --> 00:29:52.680
Of course, come inside.

00:29:52.740 --> 00:29:55.319
As the sea wings disappeared into the

00:29:55.319 --> 00:29:57.660
cave, Turtle looked back at Moon one more

00:29:57.660 --> 00:30:00.420
time, and Moon suddenly had a dizzy

00:30:00.420 --> 00:30:02.519
tilting feeling that the mountain was

00:30:02.519 --> 00:30:03.599
sliding down toward her.

00:30:03.660 --> 00:30:06.900
Darkness flashed before her eyes, and

00:30:06.900 --> 00:30:09.599
then a strange image, in bits and pieces

00:30:09.599 --> 00:30:12.599
like a puzzle whirling together, a beach

00:30:12.599 --> 00:30:16.920
sunlight, and turtle, pinning anemone to

00:30:16.920 --> 00:30:19.740
the sand as the white pink dragon writhed

00:30:19.740 --> 00:30:20.339
in pain.

00:30:20.400 --> 00:30:21.779
Then it was gone.

00:30:21.839 --> 00:30:23.579
And when she blinked.

00:30:23.640 --> 00:30:25.619
So was the Sea Wing family.

00:30:25.680 --> 00:30:29.700
Chapter 2.

00:30:29.940 --> 00:30:32.400
Moon shivered.

00:30:32.460 --> 00:30:34.259
What was that?

00:30:34.380 --> 00:30:36.059
But she knew.

00:30:36.180 --> 00:30:38.700
She'd known since she read the scrolls

00:30:38.700 --> 00:30:41.279
that said, Nightwing powers include mind

00:30:41.279 --> 00:30:43.259
reading and visions of the future.

00:30:43.319 --> 00:30:45.720
That was where her nightmares came from

00:30:45.720 --> 00:30:47.099
the future.

00:30:47.160 --> 00:30:49.500
What she didn't know was whether the

00:30:49.500 --> 00:30:51.480
visions were inevitable. or how to

00:30:51.480 --> 00:30:54.059
interpret them, or what in Pyria to do

00:30:54.059 --> 00:30:55.859
about them since, as far as she could

00:30:55.859 --> 00:30:58.380
tell, she was the 1st nightwing and 100s

00:30:58.380 --> 00:31:00.359
of years to have the legendary powers of

00:31:00.359 --> 00:31:00.839
the tribe.

00:31:00.900 --> 00:31:03.000
Lucky me.

00:31:03.059 --> 00:31:05.400
And to the other night wings wouldn't be

00:31:05.400 --> 00:31:06.660
able to handle mind reading.

00:31:06.720 --> 00:31:09.000
She was pretty sure visions from the

00:31:09.000 --> 00:31:10.559
future weren't going to go over well

00:31:10.559 --> 00:31:10.859
either.

00:31:10.920 --> 00:31:13.200
She hadn't even told her mother about

00:31:13.200 --> 00:31:13.980
those.

00:31:14.039 --> 00:31:15.599
One curse was bad enough.

00:31:15.660 --> 00:31:18.839
Turtle hadn't looked sinister at all

00:31:18.839 --> 00:31:21.779
despite the weird blankness of his mind

00:31:21.779 --> 00:31:23.759
and she knew quite a lot about sinister

00:31:23.759 --> 00:31:26.039
vibes after living with the night wings

00:31:26.039 --> 00:31:28.440
for the last few months, but perhaps any

00:31:28.440 --> 00:31:30.240
dragon could become dangerous as they got

00:31:30.240 --> 00:31:33.359
older, although he hadn't looked much

00:31:33.359 --> 00:31:34.920
older or bigger in the vision.

00:31:34.980 --> 00:31:37.619
Or perhaps he was simply much better at

00:31:37.619 --> 00:31:39.660
hiding his true nature than any other

00:31:39.660 --> 00:31:40.920
dragon she'd met before.

00:31:40.980 --> 00:31:42.539
Wow.

00:31:42.599 --> 00:31:46.140
A real queen, Secret Keeper said.

00:31:46.259 --> 00:31:47.819
I've never seen one before.

00:31:47.880 --> 00:31:51.420
You see Queen Glory all the time, Moon

00:31:51.420 --> 00:31:53.160
pointed out, only half listening.

00:31:53.220 --> 00:31:56.400
Queen Glory is barely older than you are

00:31:56.400 --> 00:31:57.900
secret keeper answered.

00:31:57.960 --> 00:32:01.140
I mean, a real queen, someone who's ruled

00:32:01.140 --> 00:32:02.339
her tribe for years and years.

00:32:02.400 --> 00:32:05.579
Moon studied her mother sideways.

00:32:05.640 --> 00:32:08.279
Many of the night wings harbored bitter

00:32:08.279 --> 00:32:10.079
thoughts about having a rain wing for

00:32:10.079 --> 00:32:12.240
their queen now, but she didn't think her

00:32:12.240 --> 00:32:13.440
mother was one of the grumblers.

00:32:13.500 --> 00:32:17.099
All right, her mother said, suddenly and

00:32:17.099 --> 00:32:17.640
briskly.

00:32:17.700 --> 00:32:20.039
That's enough hiding in the shadows and

00:32:20.039 --> 00:32:20.519
observing.

00:32:20.579 --> 00:32:22.680
Time for you to go find your cave.

00:32:22.740 --> 00:32:24.059
Already?

00:32:24.119 --> 00:32:26.819
Moon was seized with a horribly familiar

00:32:26.819 --> 00:32:28.859
feeling of terror alone.

00:32:28.920 --> 00:32:30.779
Aren't you coming inside?

00:32:30.839 --> 00:32:33.119
This will be good for you.

00:32:33.180 --> 00:32:34.680
Her mother said.

00:32:34.740 --> 00:32:36.000
I hope.

00:32:36.059 --> 00:32:37.859
Remember Secret Keeper.

00:32:37.920 --> 00:32:38.880
Be strong.

00:32:38.940 --> 00:32:40.500
Just turn and fly away.

00:32:40.559 --> 00:32:43.319
I love you, and I will see you soon.

00:32:43.440 --> 00:32:47.039
Secret Keeper took a step back, averting

00:32:47.039 --> 00:32:49.200
her face, and Moon glimpsed a thought

00:32:49.200 --> 00:32:50.579
track her mother had been carefully

00:32:50.579 --> 00:32:51.119
burying.

00:32:51.180 --> 00:32:54.180
Oh, I hope this is the right thing.

00:32:54.240 --> 00:32:55.680
What am I doing?

00:32:55.740 --> 00:32:57.779
How do I know if this will be good for

00:32:57.779 --> 00:32:57.960
her?

00:32:58.019 --> 00:33:00.240
Moon's heart leaped.

00:33:00.359 --> 00:33:02.400
She doesn't want to leave me.

00:33:02.460 --> 00:33:05.039
She realized with a surge of hope.

00:33:05.099 --> 00:33:06.900
But her mother was already hugging her

00:33:06.900 --> 00:33:09.240
and whispering hurried goodbyes in her

00:33:09.240 --> 00:33:09.420
ear.

00:33:09.480 --> 00:33:12.000
Wait, Moon said desperately.

00:33:12.059 --> 00:33:14.220
What if I came next year instead?

00:33:14.279 --> 00:33:15.119
What if?

00:33:15.119 --> 00:33:18.299
Trust me, Moonbud, her mother said

00:33:18.299 --> 00:33:20.700
cupping moon's snout in her front

00:33:20.700 --> 00:33:21.119
talons.

00:33:21.180 --> 00:33:22.680
You will love it here.

00:33:22.740 --> 00:33:25.500
Just keep your curse hidden, and you'll

00:33:25.500 --> 00:33:25.799
be fine.

00:33:25.859 --> 00:33:29.400
Act normal, no matter what happens, and

00:33:29.400 --> 00:33:30.000
write to me soon.

00:33:30.059 --> 00:33:31.319
Goodbye.

00:33:31.380 --> 00:33:35.039
A moment later, Secret Keeper was just a

00:33:35.039 --> 00:33:37.200
dark shape, winging away through the

00:33:37.200 --> 00:33:39.900
threadbare clouds, taking Moon's heart

00:33:39.900 --> 00:33:40.440
away with her.

00:33:40.500 --> 00:33:43.740
Moon stayed under the tree for a while

00:33:43.740 --> 00:33:47.579
decidedly not crying, and watched more

00:33:47.579 --> 00:33:48.059
students arrive.

00:33:48.119 --> 00:33:51.420
There weren't actually a 1000, she knew.

00:33:51.480 --> 00:33:54.599
There were only 35 students, and it was a

00:33:54.599 --> 00:33:56.220
privilege to be one of the 1st few

00:33:56.220 --> 00:34:00.059
invited to attend, which made, why me?

00:34:00.059 --> 00:34:02.940
an even more mysterious question.

00:34:03.000 --> 00:34:05.759
Well then, she thought, when she couldn't

00:34:05.759 --> 00:34:06.420
put it off anymore.

00:34:06.480 --> 00:34:09.719
Imagine this is the rainforest, and

00:34:09.719 --> 00:34:11.639
you're hungry. and your mother's been

00:34:11.639 --> 00:34:14.099
gone for 3 days, and you can smell a

00:34:14.099 --> 00:34:15.659
bunch of bananas inside the cave.

00:34:15.719 --> 00:34:18.479
If I could be brave enough to feed myself

00:34:18.479 --> 00:34:21.119
when I had to, I can be brave enough to

00:34:21.119 --> 00:34:23.519
walk into a school and find the place I'm

00:34:23.519 --> 00:34:23.939
supposed to be.

00:34:24.000 --> 00:34:27.599
She shook back her wings, waited for a

00:34:27.599 --> 00:34:29.400
moment when all was quiet on the landing

00:34:29.400 --> 00:34:31.679
ledge, and darted forward into the

00:34:31.679 --> 00:34:33.659
yawning mouth of the entrance cave.

00:34:33.719 --> 00:34:38.219
Hello, a voice accosted her loudly, while

00:34:38.219 --> 00:34:40.079
Moon's eyes were still adjusting to the

00:34:40.079 --> 00:34:41.339
dimmer light inside.

00:34:41.400 --> 00:34:43.440
Welcome to the Great Hall of Jade

00:34:43.440 --> 00:34:44.039
Mountain.

00:34:44.099 --> 00:34:46.800
Let me guess, you're moon watcher, aren't

00:34:46.800 --> 00:34:46.980
you?

00:34:47.039 --> 00:34:49.320
I'm tremendously good at guessing.

00:34:49.380 --> 00:34:52.559
In fact, one might even say, I'm

00:34:52.559 --> 00:34:54.719
mysteriously good at it.

00:34:54.840 --> 00:34:58.559
The welcoming dragon, whose scales were

00:34:58.559 --> 00:35:01.500
midnight black, lowered her voice, almost

00:35:01.500 --> 00:35:04.980
as though I'm reading your mind, eh?

00:35:05.039 --> 00:35:07.440
Moon stared at the night wing and

00:35:07.440 --> 00:35:08.219
fright.

00:35:08.280 --> 00:35:10.139
Had she been discovered already before

00:35:10.139 --> 00:35:11.099
even saying a word?

00:35:11.159 --> 00:35:13.139
What will mother say?

00:35:13.199 --> 00:35:16.199
Just kidding, said the older knight

00:35:16.199 --> 00:35:16.619
wing.

00:35:16.679 --> 00:35:18.599
Maybe.

00:35:18.659 --> 00:35:20.400
I'm fate speaker.

00:35:20.460 --> 00:35:22.079
I'm not a teacher like the others.

00:35:22.139 --> 00:35:23.699
I'm just helping wherever I can.

00:35:23.760 --> 00:35:25.619
Here's your welcome scroll and your map.

00:35:25.739 --> 00:35:29.099
She throws 2 scrolls into Moon's talons.

00:35:29.159 --> 00:35:31.920
Hey, look, you have silver scales next to

00:35:31.920 --> 00:35:32.940
your eyes just like I do.

00:35:33.000 --> 00:35:35.340
Yours are bigger and sparklier though.

00:35:35.400 --> 00:35:36.719
It is Moon Watcher, right?

00:35:36.840 --> 00:35:39.659
Yes, um, Moon.

00:35:39.719 --> 00:35:43.079
Now she recognized this night wing, which

00:35:43.079 --> 00:35:44.460
she should have been able to do from her

00:35:44.460 --> 00:35:44.940
1st thought.

00:35:45.059 --> 00:35:47.579
She only knew 2 night wings apart from

00:35:47.579 --> 00:35:49.980
her mother, who didn't radiate gloom and

00:35:49.980 --> 00:35:50.579
anxiety.

00:35:50.639 --> 00:35:53.219
Starflight had a more thoughtful energy

00:35:53.219 --> 00:35:56.159
while fate speaker's hopefulness poured

00:35:56.159 --> 00:35:57.659
out of her like overenthusiastic

00:35:57.659 --> 00:35:58.380
sunlight.

00:35:58.440 --> 00:36:00.900
Moon had seen the 2 of them from afar in

00:36:00.900 --> 00:36:02.400
the Nightwing village several times

00:36:02.400 --> 00:36:04.559
although they had both chosen to live

00:36:04.559 --> 00:36:05.880
with the rain wings instead.

00:36:05.940 --> 00:36:08.760
She glanced around, wondering hopefully

00:36:08.760 --> 00:36:10.079
if Starflight was nearby.

00:36:10.139 --> 00:36:12.360
He was the night wing from the false

00:36:12.360 --> 00:36:14.639
prophecy, and he'd been blinded when the

00:36:14.639 --> 00:36:15.659
volcano exploded.

00:36:15.719 --> 00:36:18.659
Usually fate speaker was with him, guiding

00:36:18.659 --> 00:36:20.159
him, but not today.

00:36:20.280 --> 00:36:23.039
The enormous entrance cave looked as

00:36:23.039 --> 00:36:25.139
though it could fit 400 dragons

00:36:25.139 --> 00:36:27.480
comfortably, with room for more to soar

00:36:27.480 --> 00:36:30.780
overhead, sunlight poured in, illuminating

00:36:30.780 --> 00:36:33.000
the craggy walls and rippled ceiling

00:36:33.000 --> 00:36:35.159
where cascades of golden browned

00:36:35.159 --> 00:36:37.559
stalactites hung down, some of them

00:36:37.559 --> 00:36:39.420
reaching all the way to the floor to form

00:36:39.420 --> 00:36:40.619
twisted columns.

00:36:40.679 --> 00:36:43.559
Hanging against the back wall was a huge

00:36:43.559 --> 00:36:46.440
bronze gong with 3 flying dragons carved

00:36:46.440 --> 00:36:46.800
into it.

00:36:46.860 --> 00:36:49.980
A banner woven of green vines had been

00:36:49.980 --> 00:36:52.079
strung from one massive stalactite to

00:36:52.079 --> 00:36:54.000
another in the center of the cave, with

00:36:54.000 --> 00:36:56.039
letters spelled out in giant purple and

00:36:56.039 --> 00:36:56.760
white flowers.

00:36:56.820 --> 00:36:58.320
Welcome students.

00:36:58.440 --> 00:37:01.980
Two tunnel openings yawned along the left

00:37:01.980 --> 00:37:04.139
wall of the cave, two more on the right.

00:37:04.199 --> 00:37:06.840
Next to each one, a map was posted

00:37:06.840 --> 00:37:08.099
showing where the tunnels went.

00:37:08.159 --> 00:37:10.679
The whole cave was busy with bustling

00:37:10.679 --> 00:37:13.559
dragons, families saying goodbye, friends

00:37:13.559 --> 00:37:16.019
saying hello, a few dragons carrying

00:37:16.019 --> 00:37:17.340
around prey or scrolls.

00:37:17.400 --> 00:37:20.039
But Moon didn't see Sonny or Starfight

00:37:20.039 --> 00:37:21.599
anywhere, to her disappointment.

00:37:21.659 --> 00:37:22.980
Her mother was right.

00:37:23.039 --> 00:37:25.619
They had been kind to her, and Moon liked

00:37:25.619 --> 00:37:25.920
them.

00:37:25.980 --> 00:37:28.679
She particularly liked that, for the most

00:37:28.679 --> 00:37:30.599
part, their thoughts matched what they

00:37:30.599 --> 00:37:31.019
said and did.

00:37:31.079 --> 00:37:34.260
Moon, moon, moon.

00:37:34.320 --> 00:37:36.840
Fate speaker muttered, rolling a scroll

00:37:36.840 --> 00:37:38.340
between her claws on the floor and

00:37:38.340 --> 00:37:39.179
scanning it closely.

00:37:39.239 --> 00:37:42.360
Ah, here you are. 2nd tunnel on the left

00:37:42.360 --> 00:37:43.380
5th cave on the right.

00:37:43.440 --> 00:37:45.719
She flicked her tail and grinned at

00:37:45.719 --> 00:37:46.019
moon.

00:37:46.079 --> 00:37:47.940
You're going to love your clawmates.

00:37:48.000 --> 00:37:51.420
Apparently, I'm going to love all sorts

00:37:51.420 --> 00:37:53.880
of things, Moon thought, and then she

00:37:53.880 --> 00:37:55.380
noticed what fate speaker had said.

00:37:55.440 --> 00:37:57.179
Clawmates?

00:37:57.239 --> 00:37:57.840
she echoed.

00:37:57.900 --> 00:37:58.980
What are those?

00:37:59.039 --> 00:38:01.380
The dragons you're sharing a cave with.

00:38:01.500 --> 00:38:03.059
Fate speaker said brightly.

00:38:03.119 --> 00:38:06.659
Moon's wings shivered involuntarily, all

00:38:06.659 --> 00:38:09.420
the way out to her wingtips, sharing a

00:38:09.420 --> 00:38:11.400
cave, all the time.

00:38:11.460 --> 00:38:14.699
Ooh, here come some ice wings.

00:38:14.760 --> 00:38:16.380
Fate speaker cried.

00:38:16.440 --> 00:38:17.519
Want to stick around and meet them?

00:38:17.579 --> 00:38:19.380
No, thanks.

00:38:19.440 --> 00:38:20.760
Moon stammered.

00:38:20.820 --> 00:38:23.400
She hurried to the 2nd tunnel on the left

00:38:23.400 --> 00:38:25.619
and as she turned into it, she heard a

00:38:25.619 --> 00:38:28.199
whoosh of wings, and felt a cold chill

00:38:28.199 --> 00:38:29.280
sweep through the cave.

00:38:29.340 --> 00:38:32.460
She peeked back around the corner and saw

00:38:32.460 --> 00:38:35.579
2 haughty looking ice dragons pace inside

00:38:35.579 --> 00:38:36.179
frowning.

00:38:36.239 --> 00:38:38.880
No, she definitely did not want to meet

00:38:38.880 --> 00:38:41.340
them now or, in fact, ever.

00:38:41.400 --> 00:38:46.019
Fifth cave on the right, Moon murmured to

00:38:46.019 --> 00:38:47.280
herself, moving on.

00:38:47.340 --> 00:38:50.280
The tunnel wound in a curving shape, like

00:38:50.280 --> 00:38:52.619
a slithering tail, down into the mountain

00:38:52.619 --> 00:38:56.579
overhead, grass green and butterfly blue

00:38:56.579 --> 00:38:59.460
and hibiscus yellow glass globes, hung

00:38:59.460 --> 00:39:01.980
from a wire strung along the ceiling, each

00:39:01.980 --> 00:39:03.900
of them glowing with fire so the walls

00:39:03.900 --> 00:39:04.679
were lit with color.

00:39:04.800 --> 00:39:06.599
It didn't feel like she was going

00:39:06.599 --> 00:39:07.260
underground.

00:39:07.320 --> 00:39:09.780
It felt more like the sunlit canopy of

00:39:09.780 --> 00:39:10.440
the rainforest.

00:39:10.559 --> 00:39:13.860
Moon had been picturing dark gray tunnels

00:39:13.860 --> 00:39:16.920
and cramped stone caves, but now that she

00:39:16.920 --> 00:39:19.139
thought about it, she realized Sonny

00:39:19.139 --> 00:39:20.460
wouldn't have wanted her school to be

00:39:20.460 --> 00:39:22.679
anything like the gloomy caves under the

00:39:22.679 --> 00:39:24.420
mountain where the prophecy dragonettes

00:39:24.420 --> 00:39:24.719
grew up.

00:39:24.780 --> 00:39:27.780
Soon the tunnel straightened out, and

00:39:27.780 --> 00:39:29.760
Moon could see small cave openings all

00:39:29.760 --> 00:39:30.539
along either side.

00:39:30.599 --> 00:39:33.179
This must be the corridor of sleeping

00:39:33.179 --> 00:39:33.719
caves.

00:39:33.780 --> 00:39:36.059
She could sense that some of them had 2

00:39:36.059 --> 00:39:37.679
or 3 dragonettes inside already.

00:39:37.739 --> 00:39:40.860
Each cave she passed, seemed to be

00:39:40.860 --> 00:39:43.260
bristling with chatter and wings, and

00:39:43.260 --> 00:39:45.480
claws and spiky thoughts that clamored

00:39:45.480 --> 00:39:46.320
for space in her head.

00:39:46.380 --> 00:39:48.900
Father said they have a library.

00:39:48.960 --> 00:39:50.039
I'm going to learn to read.

00:39:50.099 --> 00:39:52.199
Oh, I hope I'm not the only one who can't

00:39:52.199 --> 00:39:52.619
read yet.

00:39:52.679 --> 00:39:54.119
That would be so embarrassing.

00:39:54.179 --> 00:39:56.760
What do they eat up in the mountains?

00:39:56.820 --> 00:39:59.579
We'd better get seagulls sometimes, and

00:39:59.579 --> 00:40:00.179
soon.

00:40:00.239 --> 00:40:01.440
Gosh, I'm hungry.

00:40:01.500 --> 00:40:03.360
Would anyone be mad at me if I went

00:40:03.360 --> 00:40:04.320
looking for seagulls?

00:40:04.380 --> 00:40:07.019
I wonder where the prophecy dragonets

00:40:07.019 --> 00:40:07.320
are.

00:40:07.440 --> 00:40:08.519
I wonder if they'll notice me.

00:40:08.579 --> 00:40:10.440
So cold here.

00:40:10.500 --> 00:40:11.760
I miss the desert.

00:40:11.820 --> 00:40:14.460
They really expect me to share a cave

00:40:14.460 --> 00:40:15.659
with a rain wing.

00:40:15.719 --> 00:40:19.260
Moon scrunched her eyes shut, trying to

00:40:19.260 --> 00:40:20.159
hold back the headache.

00:40:20.219 --> 00:40:22.500
This was what it had been like when she

00:40:22.500 --> 00:40:24.239
1st joined the Nightwing village.

00:40:24.300 --> 00:40:27.059
After the peace and quiet of solitary

00:40:27.059 --> 00:40:28.139
life in the rainforest.

00:40:28.199 --> 00:40:30.780
All those voices in her head had been a

00:40:30.780 --> 00:40:33.179
horrible shock, especially when they were

00:40:33.179 --> 00:40:34.920
all so resentful and hostile.

00:40:34.980 --> 00:40:38.159
They still echoed in there, even though

00:40:38.159 --> 00:40:40.079
the night wings were too far away now for

00:40:40.079 --> 00:40:41.099
her to actually hear them.

00:40:41.159 --> 00:40:43.019
It's not fair.

00:40:43.079 --> 00:40:45.119
Secret keeper should be punished.

00:40:45.179 --> 00:40:47.099
I bet she thinks she's better than us.

00:40:47.159 --> 00:40:49.860
Imagine getting to eat every day.

00:40:49.920 --> 00:40:51.780
That dragonette doesn't know anything

00:40:51.780 --> 00:40:54.000
about our tribe, or what we went through

00:40:54.000 --> 00:40:55.079
living on the volcano.

00:40:55.139 --> 00:40:56.579
How can she ever be one of us?

00:40:56.639 --> 00:41:00.119
She had a feeling, perhaps more of a

00:41:00.119 --> 00:41:02.099
wishful hope, that there should be a way

00:41:02.099 --> 00:41:03.420
to block out all the voices.

00:41:03.480 --> 00:41:05.760
But of course, there was no one who could

00:41:05.760 --> 00:41:06.539
teach her how to do that.

00:41:06.599 --> 00:41:09.539
Mostly she dealt with a night wing noise

00:41:09.539 --> 00:41:12.179
by escaping to the tallest tree or

00:41:12.179 --> 00:41:14.579
farthest waterfall, but where could she

00:41:14.579 --> 00:41:14.940
go here?

00:41:15.000 --> 00:41:18.360
She'd be stuck in classes or trapped in a

00:41:18.360 --> 00:41:20.699
cave with her claw mates.

00:41:20.760 --> 00:41:22.920
Her brain would always be full of the din

00:41:22.920 --> 00:41:24.360
of other dragons.

00:41:24.420 --> 00:41:27.900
I'll figure it out I'll make this work.

00:41:27.960 --> 00:41:31.320
Or I'll run back to the rainforest and

00:41:31.320 --> 00:41:32.699
deal with mother's disappointment.

00:41:32.760 --> 00:41:36.300
Moon opened her eyes again, and fixed her

00:41:36.300 --> 00:41:37.320
gaze on the 5th cave.

00:41:37.380 --> 00:41:40.320
She squeezed past a pair of chatting sand

00:41:40.320 --> 00:41:42.119
wings, who were taking up most of the

00:41:42.119 --> 00:41:44.219
tunnel, and one of them stared at her

00:41:44.219 --> 00:41:45.960
intently with his obsidian black eyes.

00:41:46.019 --> 00:41:49.380
Nightwing flashed through his head.

00:41:49.440 --> 00:41:51.300
Thorn doesn't like them.

00:41:51.420 --> 00:41:53.639
We just send a couple back to gloria as

00:41:53.639 --> 00:41:54.179
her prisoners.

00:41:54.239 --> 00:41:55.920
We have no idea what they can do in

00:41:55.920 --> 00:41:58.199
battle yet, especially if it's true they

00:41:58.199 --> 00:42:00.059
really have no powers at all, needs

00:42:00.059 --> 00:42:00.659
further study.

00:42:00.719 --> 00:42:02.400
She's kind of cool looking.

00:42:02.519 --> 00:42:04.559
With those silver scales by her eyes

00:42:04.559 --> 00:42:07.380
seems nervous, twitching our wings back

00:42:07.380 --> 00:42:08.519
to look smaller than she is.

00:42:08.579 --> 00:42:10.920
Up to something or shy.

00:42:10.980 --> 00:42:13.920
Moon tried not to look back at him as she

00:42:13.920 --> 00:42:14.460
went by.

00:42:14.519 --> 00:42:16.800
She tried to seem unobtrusive and

00:42:16.800 --> 00:42:18.539
harmless and part of the shadows.

00:42:18.659 --> 00:42:21.539
Her sleeping cave had a few stalactites

00:42:21.539 --> 00:42:23.460
hanging over the doorway, like jagged

00:42:23.460 --> 00:42:23.760
teeth.

00:42:23.820 --> 00:42:27.239
She decked inside and found more firelit

00:42:27.239 --> 00:42:29.820
glass globes strung across the ceiling in

00:42:29.820 --> 00:42:33.659
here, one green, one a fiery red gold, and

00:42:33.659 --> 00:42:33.960
one yellow.

00:42:34.019 --> 00:42:37.800
Two more globes, unlit, rested on ledges

00:42:37.800 --> 00:42:40.079
on either side of the door, and there was

00:42:40.079 --> 00:42:41.820
another at her level on the far side of

00:42:41.820 --> 00:42:42.179
the cave.

00:42:42.239 --> 00:42:45.480
She picked each one up, and breathed a

00:42:45.480 --> 00:42:47.460
small flame onto the candles inside to

00:42:47.460 --> 00:42:48.179
set them alight.

00:42:48.239 --> 00:42:50.400
Then surveyed the space nervously.

00:42:50.460 --> 00:42:52.920
It was nicer than she had expected.

00:42:52.980 --> 00:42:55.860
The doorway made up one wall, and a

00:42:55.860 --> 00:42:57.360
sleeping spot had been arranged along

00:42:57.360 --> 00:42:58.679
each of the other 3 walls.

00:42:58.739 --> 00:43:01.260
One of these was a bare rock ledge.

00:43:01.320 --> 00:43:03.659
Another was a pile of rainforest leaves

00:43:03.659 --> 00:43:06.480
and mosses, and the 3rd was a woven green

00:43:06.480 --> 00:43:08.760
hammock, ingeniously suspended from the

00:43:08.760 --> 00:43:09.000
roof.

00:43:09.059 --> 00:43:10.800
Moon hesitated.

00:43:10.860 --> 00:43:13.079
It seemed as if the beds had been

00:43:13.079 --> 00:43:14.820
deliberately designed with different

00:43:14.820 --> 00:43:17.099
dragons in mind, but she wasn't sure

00:43:17.099 --> 00:43:18.300
which one was meant for her.

00:43:18.360 --> 00:43:21.659
She knew which one she wanted, but how

00:43:21.659 --> 00:43:22.800
would someone else have guessed what

00:43:22.800 --> 00:43:23.579
she'd like?

00:43:23.639 --> 00:43:26.579
Maybe she should wait for her claw mates

00:43:26.579 --> 00:43:27.840
and see what they wanted.

00:43:27.900 --> 00:43:31.019
I wish I could have a private cave.

00:43:31.019 --> 00:43:33.480
Maybe if I asked Starflight really

00:43:33.480 --> 00:43:33.960
nicely.

00:43:34.019 --> 00:43:37.199
She noticed that there were also 5

00:43:37.199 --> 00:43:39.599
mahogany scroll racks arranged around the

00:43:39.599 --> 00:43:41.820
cave, about the height of her foreleg

00:43:41.820 --> 00:43:44.280
each polished until they were smooth as

00:43:44.280 --> 00:43:44.880
her scales.

00:43:44.940 --> 00:43:47.579
There was an empty one next to each bed

00:43:47.579 --> 00:43:49.199
and one on either side of the door.

00:43:49.320 --> 00:43:52.619
She took a closer look, and realized, with

00:43:52.619 --> 00:43:54.900
a jump of happiness, that the ones by the

00:43:54.900 --> 00:43:57.599
door were filled with scrolls, a little

00:43:57.599 --> 00:44:00.480
sign above these 2 said, free reading.

00:44:00.539 --> 00:44:01.980
Hope you like them.

00:44:02.039 --> 00:44:04.500
Moon slid her welcome scroll and her map

00:44:04.500 --> 00:44:06.960
scroll into one of the empty racks, then

00:44:06.960 --> 00:44:08.940
wrapped her tail around her back talons

00:44:08.940 --> 00:44:10.800
and started going through the scrolls by

00:44:10.800 --> 00:44:11.039
the door.

00:44:11.099 --> 00:44:13.739
It was a mix of all the kinds of things

00:44:13.739 --> 00:44:16.320
that interested her, history, adventure

00:44:16.320 --> 00:44:19.800
stories, ancient legends, encyclopedias

00:44:19.800 --> 00:44:21.960
of all the plants and animals in each

00:44:21.960 --> 00:44:23.099
tribe's territory.

00:44:23.159 --> 00:44:25.679
Suddenly she remembered Starflight

00:44:25.679 --> 00:44:27.239
finding her with a scroll one day.

00:44:27.300 --> 00:44:29.519
He had quizzed her on what she liked to

00:44:29.519 --> 00:44:29.760
read.

00:44:29.820 --> 00:44:33.719
If he chose these for me, he must have

00:44:33.719 --> 00:44:34.440
really been listening.

00:44:34.500 --> 00:44:37.440
She noticed that there weren't any other

00:44:37.440 --> 00:44:39.420
recent scrolls about the dragonettes of

00:44:39.420 --> 00:44:42.780
the prophecy, and their epic quest to end

00:44:42.780 --> 00:44:44.760
the war of Sandwing Succession.

00:44:44.820 --> 00:44:47.820
She guessed with a smile that whoever had

00:44:47.820 --> 00:44:51.900
selected these, Starflight, Sunny, Glory

00:44:51.900 --> 00:44:54.300
found those particular scrolls rather

00:44:54.300 --> 00:44:54.960
embarrassing.

00:44:55.019 --> 00:44:58.380
She also found one early reader scroll

00:44:58.380 --> 00:45:00.059
that must have been written for tiny

00:45:00.059 --> 00:45:02.579
dragonettes with giant letters and a

00:45:02.579 --> 00:45:03.599
guide to the alphabet.

00:45:03.659 --> 00:45:06.780
This seemed so out of place that she sat

00:45:06.780 --> 00:45:08.039
and puzzled over it for a minute.

00:45:08.099 --> 00:45:10.860
Is this for one of my clawmates?

00:45:10.980 --> 00:45:13.320
Am I going to be living with a one year

00:45:13.320 --> 00:45:13.619
old?

00:45:13.679 --> 00:45:16.380
Her mother had mentioned that the academy

00:45:16.380 --> 00:45:19.139
would take dragonettes of various ages, so

00:45:19.139 --> 00:45:21.119
maybe it was possible, although it seemed

00:45:21.119 --> 00:45:21.480
weird.

00:45:21.539 --> 00:45:24.960
Out of nowhere, Moon felt a sudden burst

00:45:24.960 --> 00:45:27.000
of angry energy like a spear driving

00:45:27.000 --> 00:45:27.840
through her skull.

00:45:27.900 --> 00:45:30.539
She crumbled forward, clutching her head

00:45:30.539 --> 00:45:33.000
as shouts and roars echoed in the hall.

00:45:33.059 --> 00:45:36.059
Get your fish smelling tail away from

00:45:36.059 --> 00:45:36.239
me.

00:45:36.300 --> 00:45:39.059
I faced bigger sea wings than him in

00:45:39.059 --> 00:45:40.079
battle if he's trying to start

00:45:40.079 --> 00:45:40.380
something.

00:45:40.440 --> 00:45:43.380
Don't you dare blow smoke in my face.

00:45:43.440 --> 00:45:46.199
She could be one of the sky wings, who

00:45:46.199 --> 00:45:47.760
destroyed our summer palace.

00:45:47.820 --> 00:45:50.400
Ow, Moon whispered.

00:45:50.460 --> 00:45:52.260
Ow, ow, ow.

00:45:52.320 --> 00:45:54.539
The headache was so blistering.

00:45:54.599 --> 00:45:56.579
She considered running into the rock wall

00:45:56.579 --> 00:45:59.699
to knock herself out, and then, very

00:45:59.699 --> 00:46:02.340
softly, under all the yelling she heard.

00:46:02.519 --> 00:46:03.960
Aha.

00:46:04.019 --> 00:46:05.639
There you are.

00:46:05.699 --> 00:46:09.900
Moon's head snapped up, and she winced as

00:46:09.900 --> 00:46:11.760
another bolt of pain crackled through

00:46:11.760 --> 00:46:12.179
it.

00:46:12.179 --> 00:46:15.539
This voice, it was unlike anything she'd

00:46:15.539 --> 00:46:16.380
ever heard before.

00:46:16.440 --> 00:46:19.320
It sounded crisp and clear and right in

00:46:19.320 --> 00:46:21.599
her ear. as if it was talking to her.

00:46:21.659 --> 00:46:24.719
I am talking to you.

00:46:24.780 --> 00:46:28.139
Instinctive fear whipped through moon's

00:46:28.139 --> 00:46:29.639
veins, paralyzing her.

00:46:29.699 --> 00:46:32.400
All of her mother's nightmare scenarios

00:46:32.400 --> 00:46:33.840
started playing again in her head.

00:46:33.900 --> 00:46:35.699
Don't trust anyone new.

00:46:35.760 --> 00:46:37.679
Don't trust anything unusual.

00:46:37.739 --> 00:46:39.780
Don't let anyone know what you can do.

00:46:39.840 --> 00:46:41.159
Stay secret.

00:46:41.219 --> 00:46:42.179
Stay hidden.

00:46:42.239 --> 00:46:43.260
Stay safe.

00:46:43.320 --> 00:46:46.139
Three moons, said the voice.

00:46:46.199 --> 00:46:47.760
Aren't you a jumpy one?

00:46:47.880 --> 00:46:49.440
Who are you?

00:46:49.500 --> 00:46:50.880
Moon whispered.

00:46:50.940 --> 00:46:52.019
Who are you?

00:46:52.139 --> 00:46:53.760
It answered back.

00:46:53.820 --> 00:46:56.579
And then, as if the speaker had plucked

00:46:56.579 --> 00:46:59.760
the answer from her thoughts, Hello, Moon

00:46:59.760 --> 00:47:00.300
Watcher.

00:47:00.360 --> 00:47:02.460
Another telepath?

00:47:02.519 --> 00:47:03.360
How is that possible?

00:47:03.420 --> 00:47:05.460
Moon tried to push back.

00:47:05.519 --> 00:47:08.159
She imagined reaching out with her talons

00:47:08.159 --> 00:47:10.500
trying to grab onto the voice and open up

00:47:10.500 --> 00:47:11.760
what was happening in the mind behind

00:47:11.760 --> 00:47:12.059
it.

00:47:12.119 --> 00:47:15.420
It's as if you've had no training at

00:47:15.420 --> 00:47:15.599
all.

00:47:15.719 --> 00:47:17.219
The voice chuckled.

00:47:17.280 --> 00:47:19.019
How old are you?

00:47:19.139 --> 00:47:23.699
Again, the pause, and this time, Moon

00:47:23.699 --> 00:47:25.500
thought furiously of as many different

00:47:25.500 --> 00:47:26.400
numbers as she could.

00:47:26.460 --> 00:47:31.139
9576, 12. 4 already.

00:47:31.199 --> 00:47:32.579
And that's all you can do.

00:47:32.639 --> 00:47:34.559
Who are you?

00:47:34.679 --> 00:47:35.820
Moon demanded.

00:47:35.940 --> 00:47:37.079
How are you doing that?

00:47:37.139 --> 00:47:39.719
You really have no idea.

00:47:39.780 --> 00:47:42.539
The voice mused, with a hint of

00:47:42.539 --> 00:47:43.019
puzzlement.

00:47:43.139 --> 00:47:44.280
Hmm.

00:47:44.340 --> 00:47:45.719
Fascinating.

00:47:45.780 --> 00:47:47.519
Let me think about that.

00:47:47.579 --> 00:47:51.059
She listened, pressing her temples to

00:47:51.059 --> 00:47:53.039
hold the headache at bay, but the voice

00:47:53.039 --> 00:47:53.760
didn't come back.

00:47:53.820 --> 00:47:55.679
Are you still there?

00:47:55.739 --> 00:47:56.940
She whispered.

00:47:57.000 --> 00:47:58.320
No response.

00:47:58.380 --> 00:48:00.480
Did I imagine it?

00:48:00.599 --> 00:48:02.340
Maybe I imagined it.

00:48:02.400 --> 00:48:04.980
Maybe the headache and all the noise out

00:48:04.980 --> 00:48:06.179
there just confused me.

00:48:06.239 --> 00:48:09.179
Or maybe migrating is finally driving me

00:48:09.179 --> 00:48:09.599
crazy.

00:48:09.659 --> 00:48:12.119
She shook her head and blinked.

00:48:12.179 --> 00:48:15.539
But if it was a real mind reader, maybe

00:48:15.539 --> 00:48:17.400
they could teach me how to use my powers

00:48:17.400 --> 00:48:20.940
or expose me to everyone, now that they

00:48:20.940 --> 00:48:23.519
know who I am, while I have no idea who

00:48:23.519 --> 00:48:23.880
they are.

00:48:23.940 --> 00:48:27.239
Moon drew her wings around her with an

00:48:27.239 --> 00:48:27.960
anxious shiver.

00:48:28.019 --> 00:48:30.179
Hey, now.

00:48:30.239 --> 00:48:32.940
Hey there, stop, stop, stop.

00:48:33.059 --> 00:48:35.519
A real voice called in the hallway

00:48:35.519 --> 00:48:36.960
interrupting the squabble.

00:48:37.019 --> 00:48:40.860
Clay clamored several voices at once in

00:48:40.860 --> 00:48:41.639
Moon's head.

00:48:41.699 --> 00:48:42.900
It's him.

00:48:42.960 --> 00:48:43.739
It's really him.

00:48:43.800 --> 00:48:46.139
Ooh, he's even cuter in real life.

00:48:46.199 --> 00:48:48.000
Ooh, look at his heroic limp.

00:48:48.059 --> 00:48:49.980
Ooh, I think he looked at me.

00:48:50.039 --> 00:48:53.099
Moon poked her head out of her cave and

00:48:53.099 --> 00:48:55.019
saw the large sloping back of the

00:48:55.019 --> 00:48:56.099
prophecy mud wing.

00:48:56.159 --> 00:48:59.099
Clay was gently holding apart a writhing

00:48:59.099 --> 00:49:01.500
sea wing and a hissing sky wing.

00:49:01.559 --> 00:49:04.380
It's only the 1st day, folks, he said

00:49:04.380 --> 00:49:05.159
genially.

00:49:05.219 --> 00:49:07.380
Nothing to be so grumpy about already.

00:49:07.440 --> 00:49:09.599
You're probably both just hungry.

00:49:09.659 --> 00:49:13.079
Cornelian, take a deep breath and see me

00:49:13.079 --> 00:49:13.260
later.

00:49:13.320 --> 00:49:15.539
Pike, walk with me.

00:49:15.599 --> 00:49:18.539
He spread his wing over the sea wing's

00:49:18.539 --> 00:49:20.760
shoulder and firmly guided him away down

00:49:20.760 --> 00:49:21.179
the tunnel.

00:49:21.239 --> 00:49:23.940
The sky wing watched them go with narrow

00:49:23.940 --> 00:49:25.739
eyes, growling to herself.

00:49:25.800 --> 00:49:29.579
Then, to Moon's alarm, she swung around

00:49:29.579 --> 00:49:31.559
and marched right into Moon's cave.

00:49:31.619 --> 00:49:34.320
Without saying a word, she threw herself

00:49:34.320 --> 00:49:37.079
onto the rock ledge bed, folded her large

00:49:37.079 --> 00:49:40.019
scarlet wings forward over her eyes, and

00:49:40.019 --> 00:49:42.059
proceeded to stew in sullen silence.

00:49:42.119 --> 00:49:45.960
One of my claw mates, moon realized.

00:49:46.019 --> 00:49:47.460
Yay.

00:49:47.519 --> 00:49:49.980
She blinked at the sky wing for a moment

00:49:49.980 --> 00:49:52.619
wondering if she should say something, her

00:49:52.619 --> 00:49:54.659
heart was beating fast, and the headache

00:49:54.659 --> 00:49:57.119
was still there, receding slowly toward

00:49:57.119 --> 00:49:57.900
the back of her skull.

00:49:57.960 --> 00:50:01.500
She cleared her throat, swallowed, opened

00:50:01.500 --> 00:50:04.019
her mouth, and then gave up and turned

00:50:04.019 --> 00:50:04.920
back to the scrolls.

00:50:04.980 --> 00:50:08.639
Several minutes later, a whirlwind burst

00:50:08.639 --> 00:50:11.099
into the cave, nearly trampling moon with

00:50:11.099 --> 00:50:12.300
bright yellow talons.

00:50:12.360 --> 00:50:14.159
Oh my gosh, sorry.

00:50:14.219 --> 00:50:15.059
It yelled.

00:50:15.119 --> 00:50:16.559
I didn't even see you there.

00:50:16.619 --> 00:50:18.900
I guess that's a nightwing skill, hiding

00:50:18.900 --> 00:50:19.980
in the shadows, right?

00:50:20.039 --> 00:50:20.699
Aha.

00:50:20.760 --> 00:50:23.039
They put me in with a night wing?

00:50:23.099 --> 00:50:24.360
hollered her brain.

00:50:24.480 --> 00:50:25.320
Hello?

00:50:25.380 --> 00:50:27.179
Isn't anyone worried about my potential

00:50:27.179 --> 00:50:28.440
post-traumatic stress?

00:50:28.559 --> 00:50:31.500
But the little rain wing didn't drop her

00:50:31.500 --> 00:50:33.179
enormous smile for a moment.

00:50:33.239 --> 00:50:35.340
Her scales too didn't shift.

00:50:35.400 --> 00:50:38.159
They stayed a blindingly bright banana

00:50:38.159 --> 00:50:40.980
yellow, dotted with splotches of alarming

00:50:40.980 --> 00:50:41.880
raspberry pink.

00:50:41.940 --> 00:50:45.300
She seized Moon's front talons and pumped

00:50:45.300 --> 00:50:46.199
them cheerfully up and down.

00:50:46.260 --> 00:50:47.880
Isn't this exciting?

00:50:47.940 --> 00:50:50.460
I'm so excited, I can hardly stand it.

00:50:50.519 --> 00:50:52.860
That's why I am this color, by the way.

00:50:52.920 --> 00:50:55.139
I have been trying all morning to turn

00:50:55.139 --> 00:50:57.179
myself something more dignified, and I

00:50:57.179 --> 00:50:57.840
can't do it.

00:50:57.900 --> 00:51:00.780
My scales are all like, yay, we're really

00:51:00.780 --> 00:51:02.460
here and will not listen to me.

00:51:02.519 --> 00:51:06.119
Moon noticed that there was one spot on

00:51:06.119 --> 00:51:08.519
the rain wing that wasn't eye meltingly

00:51:08.519 --> 00:51:11.280
colorful, a triangle of 3 small black

00:51:11.280 --> 00:51:13.920
smudges on her wing that looked like tiny

00:51:13.920 --> 00:51:14.820
splashes of ink.

00:51:14.880 --> 00:51:18.360
I'm Kikachu, the rain wing added

00:51:18.360 --> 00:51:18.840
beaming.

00:51:18.960 --> 00:51:20.760
You're noisy.

00:51:20.820 --> 00:51:23.639
The Skywing observed from under her

00:51:23.639 --> 00:51:23.880
wings.

00:51:24.000 --> 00:51:27.360
I love this place, Kinkachu said.

00:51:27.420 --> 00:51:29.639
She let go of Moon and bounced over to

00:51:29.639 --> 00:51:31.500
the hammock, while her thoughts went

00:51:31.500 --> 00:51:34.500
essentially, library, art, friends.

00:51:34.559 --> 00:51:36.539
Have you explored at all yet?

00:51:36.599 --> 00:51:38.940
There's the most amazing library.

00:51:39.000 --> 00:51:40.980
Not that I can read yet, but 0 my gosh

00:51:40.980 --> 00:51:43.860
I'm working on it really hard and an art

00:51:43.860 --> 00:51:44.340
cave.

00:51:44.460 --> 00:51:46.860
It's full of all these colors of paint

00:51:46.860 --> 00:51:49.500
like, like, like a couple of rain wings

00:51:49.500 --> 00:51:51.360
just emoded all over it.

00:51:51.420 --> 00:51:52.380
You guys.

00:51:52.440 --> 00:51:54.900
We should make amazing paintings and then

00:51:54.900 --> 00:51:56.099
decorate our cave with them.

00:51:56.159 --> 00:51:58.260
Wouldn't that be amazing?

00:51:58.320 --> 00:52:03.480
I might literally die of joy, said the

00:52:03.480 --> 00:52:04.380
sky wing flatly.

00:52:04.440 --> 00:52:07.199
You look way healthier than most of the

00:52:07.199 --> 00:52:08.039
other night wings.

00:52:08.159 --> 00:52:11.159
Kinkachu said to Moon, evidently deciding

00:52:11.159 --> 00:52:13.500
to ignore the Sky Wing for the moment.

00:52:13.559 --> 00:52:15.179
Your scales are so shiny.

00:52:15.239 --> 00:52:18.780
I'd almost guess you were a rain wing in

00:52:18.780 --> 00:52:19.920
disguise, but you're not.

00:52:19.980 --> 00:52:20.579
Are you?

00:52:20.639 --> 00:52:23.519
I didn't grow up on the volcano.

00:52:23.579 --> 00:52:25.199
Moon said softly.

00:52:25.260 --> 00:52:27.780
My mother hid my egg in the rainforest.

00:52:27.900 --> 00:52:32.099
Oh, Kinkachu said, and her brain went

00:52:32.099 --> 00:52:33.059
aha.

00:52:33.119 --> 00:52:34.380
I've heard of you.

00:52:34.440 --> 00:52:36.300
Wow, that's a relief.

00:52:36.300 --> 00:52:38.280
That means you weren't anywhere near the

00:52:38.280 --> 00:52:39.480
night wings who locked me up.

00:52:39.539 --> 00:52:42.239
I mean, I'm all for amnesty and making

00:52:42.239 --> 00:52:44.579
friends across tribes and forgiving each

00:52:44.579 --> 00:52:47.579
other and everything, but seriously, it

00:52:47.579 --> 00:52:49.139
was scary there.

00:52:49.199 --> 00:52:51.900
Like, I thought I might actually die.

00:52:51.960 --> 00:52:54.659
And so I figured maybe I'd start by

00:52:54.659 --> 00:52:57.059
making friends with some other tribes 1st

00:52:57.059 --> 00:53:00.360
and gradually work my way back around the

00:53:00.360 --> 00:53:01.019
night wings.

00:53:01.079 --> 00:53:03.239
But you're hardly a night wing at all.

00:53:03.300 --> 00:53:04.199
So that's okay then.

00:53:04.260 --> 00:53:06.179
Moon winced.

00:53:06.239 --> 00:53:09.119
Hardly a night wing at all was

00:53:09.119 --> 00:53:10.559
essentially what she'd been hearing in

00:53:10.559 --> 00:53:11.820
the night wings thoughts about her for

00:53:11.820 --> 00:53:12.119
months.

00:53:12.179 --> 00:53:14.940
It was a little brutal to hear someone

00:53:14.940 --> 00:53:16.019
just say it out loud.

00:53:16.079 --> 00:53:18.000
So what's your name?

00:53:18.059 --> 00:53:19.500
Kinkachu asked.

00:53:19.559 --> 00:53:21.000
Moon.

00:53:21.059 --> 00:53:25.199
I mean, Moon Watcher, but just Moon

00:53:25.199 --> 00:53:25.440
really.

00:53:25.500 --> 00:53:27.599
Sure, moon.

00:53:27.659 --> 00:53:28.980
And who are you?

00:53:29.099 --> 00:53:31.079
Kinkachu asked the Sky Wing.

00:53:31.139 --> 00:53:33.059
I'm a warrior.

00:53:33.119 --> 00:53:35.639
The Scarlet Dragon thought bitterly

00:53:35.639 --> 00:53:37.079
keeping her face hidden.

00:53:37.139 --> 00:53:40.380
A loyal soldier in Ruby's army, who never

00:53:40.380 --> 00:53:41.880
did anything to deserve this.

00:53:41.940 --> 00:53:44.579
This punishment of schooling, and being

00:53:44.579 --> 00:53:46.559
forced to live with ditzy and mumbles

00:53:46.559 --> 00:53:46.800
over there.

00:53:46.860 --> 00:53:50.099
Moon hunched her shoulders and looked

00:53:50.099 --> 00:53:51.059
down at her claws.

00:53:51.119 --> 00:53:52.320
That wasn't fair.

00:53:52.380 --> 00:53:54.119
She did not mumble.

00:53:54.179 --> 00:53:56.639
Kinkachu turned back to Moon.

00:53:56.699 --> 00:53:57.840
Her eyes sparkling.

00:53:57.900 --> 00:54:01.019
Ooh, it's a mystery, she said.

00:54:01.079 --> 00:54:03.900
We have to guess our 3rd claw mate's

00:54:03.900 --> 00:54:04.139
name.

00:54:04.199 --> 00:54:05.039
I'll go first.

00:54:05.099 --> 00:54:06.300
I bet it's...

00:54:06.300 --> 00:54:07.619
Squelch.

00:54:07.679 --> 00:54:08.400
What do you think?

00:54:08.460 --> 00:54:10.079
Squelch is a cute name, right?

00:54:10.139 --> 00:54:12.960
Moon didn't think she ought to smile

00:54:12.960 --> 00:54:15.780
given the wave of outrage coming off the

00:54:15.780 --> 00:54:16.500
sky wing.

00:54:16.559 --> 00:54:19.679
Squelch is a mud wing name, isn't it?

00:54:19.739 --> 00:54:20.760
She pointed out.

00:54:20.820 --> 00:54:23.280
True, said Kinkachu.

00:54:23.340 --> 00:54:24.719
Maybe her name is friendly.

00:54:24.780 --> 00:54:26.099
That would suit her so well.

00:54:26.159 --> 00:54:30.300
That's not a Skywing name either, Moon

00:54:30.300 --> 00:54:30.840
said.

00:54:30.900 --> 00:54:33.179
The red dragon's tail was twitching

00:54:33.179 --> 00:54:33.719
dangerously.

00:54:33.780 --> 00:54:36.239
Think outside the box, moon.

00:54:36.300 --> 00:54:37.139
Look at her.

00:54:37.199 --> 00:54:39.420
I'm sure she'd love to be called

00:54:39.420 --> 00:54:39.900
friendly.

00:54:39.960 --> 00:54:42.059
Let's do that until we find out her real

00:54:42.059 --> 00:54:42.420
name.

00:54:42.480 --> 00:54:45.480
Kinkachu said, and then broke down in

00:54:45.480 --> 00:54:46.500
helpless giggles.

00:54:46.559 --> 00:54:48.719
The Sky Wing unfolded herself

00:54:48.719 --> 00:54:51.300
majestically and glared at Kinkachu with

00:54:51.300 --> 00:54:52.260
her wings spread wide.

00:54:52.320 --> 00:54:55.380
I have fought in 14 battles.

00:54:55.440 --> 00:54:57.059
The Sky Wing thundered.

00:54:57.119 --> 00:55:00.420
No one giggles at me, least of all, a

00:55:00.420 --> 00:55:02.159
rain wing who can't even read and knows

00:55:02.159 --> 00:55:02.940
nothing about war.

00:55:03.000 --> 00:55:06.059
She jumped off her ledge, and swept

00:55:06.059 --> 00:55:07.079
furiously out the door.

00:55:07.139 --> 00:55:10.440
There was a pause, while Kinkachu got her

00:55:10.440 --> 00:55:11.280
giggles under control.

00:55:11.340 --> 00:55:15.300
Ouch, she said, but mostly fair.

00:55:15.420 --> 00:55:17.880
Although I think being imprisoned and

00:55:17.880 --> 00:55:20.159
experimented on by Nightwings, and then

00:55:20.159 --> 00:55:22.440
injured during a royal challenge should

00:55:22.440 --> 00:55:24.659
give me some battle credit, don't you?

00:55:24.719 --> 00:55:28.139
I, I think Clay said her name is

00:55:28.139 --> 00:55:29.639
Cornelian, maybe?

00:55:29.760 --> 00:55:30.960
Moon offered.

00:55:31.019 --> 00:55:33.840
Oh, that's pretty, Kinkaju said.

00:55:33.900 --> 00:55:35.880
Do you mind if I take the hammock, by the

00:55:35.880 --> 00:55:36.059
way?

00:55:36.119 --> 00:55:37.679
Moon shook her head.

00:55:37.739 --> 00:55:39.780
The moss bed is all right with me.

00:55:39.840 --> 00:55:42.300
That's what you slept on while you were

00:55:42.300 --> 00:55:43.920
growing up on the rainforest floor

00:55:43.920 --> 00:55:44.159
right?

00:55:44.219 --> 00:55:46.380
Kinkachu asked, nodding.

00:55:46.440 --> 00:55:48.539
This will be so great.

00:55:48.599 --> 00:55:50.940
We can bond over how much we miss papayas

00:55:50.940 --> 00:55:53.519
and adorable sloths, but I don't miss

00:55:53.519 --> 00:55:54.000
anything yet.

00:55:54.059 --> 00:55:55.380
It's too fabulous here.

00:55:55.440 --> 00:55:56.880
Come see the library.

00:55:56.940 --> 00:56:00.119
Oh, Moon said nervously.

00:56:00.179 --> 00:56:02.760
I think I'll stay here for a bit longer.

00:56:02.820 --> 00:56:06.780
I need to just, um, um, nonsense.

00:56:06.840 --> 00:56:08.099
Kinkaju said.

00:56:08.159 --> 00:56:10.260
She poked one of Moon's wings with her

00:56:10.260 --> 00:56:10.440
own.

00:56:10.500 --> 00:56:12.179
We are in a new place.

00:56:12.239 --> 00:56:13.980
This is really exciting.

00:56:14.099 --> 00:56:15.539
I want to show you everything.

00:56:15.599 --> 00:56:18.420
Oh, I hope she's not boring.

00:56:18.480 --> 00:56:20.519
Kinkachu's mind whispered.

00:56:20.579 --> 00:56:22.320
I don't mind shy.

00:56:22.380 --> 00:56:24.659
I can handle shy, but please don't be

00:56:24.659 --> 00:56:24.960
boring.

00:56:25.019 --> 00:56:27.960
Moon straightened her shoulders and

00:56:27.960 --> 00:56:29.099
folded her wings back.

00:56:29.159 --> 00:56:32.219
It meant trampling down her terror, but

00:56:32.219 --> 00:56:33.960
she absolutely did not want to seem

00:56:33.960 --> 00:56:36.119
boring to her 1st possible chance at a

00:56:36.119 --> 00:56:36.539
friend here.

00:56:36.599 --> 00:56:41.400
All right, let's go, she said, taking a

00:56:41.400 --> 00:56:41.940
deep breath.

00:56:42.000 --> 00:56:43.199
Yay!

00:56:43.260 --> 00:56:44.639
Kinkichu cried.

00:56:44.699 --> 00:56:46.500
She bounded out the door and moon

00:56:46.500 --> 00:56:46.980
followed.

00:56:47.039 --> 00:56:49.739
As she stepped into the hallway, she

00:56:49.739 --> 00:56:52.199
heard it again, that bell of a voice in

00:56:52.199 --> 00:56:52.559
her mind.

00:56:52.619 --> 00:56:55.920
Oh, moon watcher, my new favorite

00:56:55.920 --> 00:56:56.460
dragon.

00:56:56.519 --> 00:56:59.039
This dragonette with a brain full of

00:56:59.039 --> 00:57:00.960
bubbles is not your only possibility.

00:57:01.019 --> 00:57:03.719
I believe you and I are destined for

00:57:03.719 --> 00:57:04.380
great friendship.

00:57:04.440 --> 00:57:06.420
Moon shivered.

00:57:06.480 --> 00:57:07.619
Was it real?

00:57:07.679 --> 00:57:10.679
Was there a dragon somewhere reaching out

00:57:10.679 --> 00:57:11.039
to her?

00:57:11.099 --> 00:57:13.019
If so, how?

00:57:13.079 --> 00:57:13.739
And who was it?

00:57:13.800 --> 00:57:15.000
Another student?

00:57:15.059 --> 00:57:18.360
Was it a fellow nightwing, mysteriously

00:57:18.360 --> 00:57:21.000
hatched with the tribe's long lost powers

00:57:21.000 --> 00:57:21.960
just like her?

00:57:22.019 --> 00:57:24.659
How could she hide from someone who knew

00:57:24.659 --> 00:57:25.559
exactly what she was?

00:57:25.619 --> 00:57:28.079
I can help you.

00:57:28.139 --> 00:57:29.820
The voice whispered.

00:57:29.880 --> 00:57:31.440
And better yet.

00:57:31.500 --> 00:57:33.059
You can help me.

00:57:33.119 --> 00:57:37.380
Chapter 3.

00:57:37.679 --> 00:57:41.579
Moon couldn't handle a mystery mind voice

00:57:41.579 --> 00:57:44.159
and a new school full of noisy dragons

00:57:44.159 --> 00:57:45.000
all at the same time.

00:57:45.059 --> 00:57:47.699
She shoved her worries about the voice to

00:57:47.699 --> 00:57:49.739
the back of her head, and tried instead

00:57:49.739 --> 00:57:51.420
to wrestle with the exhausting energy

00:57:51.420 --> 00:57:52.920
radiating off Kinkachu.

00:57:52.980 --> 00:57:54.360
Where are we going?

00:57:54.420 --> 00:57:57.360
Moon asked the rain wing, as they headed

00:57:57.360 --> 00:57:59.159
along the tunnel, past all the sleeping

00:57:59.159 --> 00:58:00.780
caves, away from the great hall.

00:58:00.840 --> 00:58:02.940
She wondered if she should have brought

00:58:02.940 --> 00:58:03.539
her school map.

00:58:03.599 --> 00:58:06.300
Today is an exploring day.

00:58:06.360 --> 00:58:08.219
Kinkachu said with authority.

00:58:08.280 --> 00:58:10.380
They want every day to be kind of an

00:58:10.380 --> 00:58:11.039
exploring day.

00:58:11.099 --> 00:58:12.539
That's the idea of the school.

00:58:12.599 --> 00:58:14.699
Find out what you're interested in and

00:58:14.699 --> 00:58:15.119
explore it.

00:58:15.179 --> 00:58:18.480
I'm interested in going back to my mother

00:58:18.480 --> 00:58:19.380
Moon Thought.

00:58:19.440 --> 00:58:20.699
Can I explore that?

00:58:20.820 --> 00:58:22.619
They?

00:58:22.679 --> 00:58:23.820
She echoed instead.

00:58:23.880 --> 00:58:27.420
The dragonettes of destiny, Kinkaju said

00:58:27.420 --> 00:58:29.400
although they don't want anyone to call

00:58:29.400 --> 00:58:31.139
them that anymore, but what are we

00:58:31.139 --> 00:58:31.800
supposed to call them?

00:58:31.860 --> 00:58:34.860
The founders of the school makes sense

00:58:34.860 --> 00:58:36.900
too, I guess, but that makes them sound

00:58:36.900 --> 00:58:39.239
like they're perfectly ancient, like old

00:58:39.239 --> 00:58:41.579
slabs of rock way under the mountain.

00:58:41.639 --> 00:58:43.619
I'm really good friends with them.

00:58:43.739 --> 00:58:44.880
She confided.

00:58:44.940 --> 00:58:47.159
As streaks of dark purple shot through

00:58:47.159 --> 00:58:49.619
her scales, especially Queen Glory.

00:58:49.679 --> 00:58:51.000
We're practically best friends.

00:58:51.059 --> 00:58:53.039
They knew I wouldn't be able to read the

00:58:53.039 --> 00:58:54.000
announcements everywhere.

00:58:54.059 --> 00:58:57.119
I mean, not yet, so Sonny and Clay

00:58:57.119 --> 00:58:58.679
explain their whole plan to me ahead of

00:58:58.679 --> 00:58:58.860
time.

00:58:58.920 --> 00:59:00.960
Announcements?

00:59:01.019 --> 00:59:03.840
Moon paused to look around and saw a

00:59:03.840 --> 00:59:05.760
small rectangular board made of dark rock

00:59:05.760 --> 00:59:08.219
hanging under one of the torches.

00:59:08.280 --> 00:59:09.900
A note was written on it in chalk.

00:59:09.960 --> 00:59:12.840
Welcome to the Jade Mountain Academy.

00:59:12.900 --> 00:59:14.880
Feel free to explore the whole school

00:59:14.880 --> 00:59:16.440
today, and every day.

00:59:16.500 --> 00:59:17.820
Everything is for you.

00:59:17.880 --> 00:59:20.400
Food is available in the prey center.

00:59:20.460 --> 00:59:22.679
Talk to Clay if you'd like to sign up for

00:59:22.679 --> 00:59:23.519
a hunting party.

00:59:23.579 --> 00:59:26.460
Please come see any of us anytime with

00:59:26.460 --> 00:59:28.860
questions or requests or worries or

00:59:28.860 --> 00:59:29.219
anything.

00:59:29.280 --> 00:59:31.800
More information about tomorrow will be

00:59:31.800 --> 00:59:32.400
posted tonight.

00:59:32.460 --> 00:59:35.159
Small group discussion classes will begin

00:59:35.159 --> 00:59:35.639
in the morning.

00:59:35.699 --> 00:59:36.960
Have a wonderful day.

00:59:37.019 --> 00:59:40.800
What's a small group discussion class?

00:59:40.860 --> 00:59:42.000
Moon wondered?

00:59:42.119 --> 00:59:43.920
It's exactly what it sounds like

00:59:43.920 --> 00:59:45.360
Kinkachoo said.

00:59:45.420 --> 00:59:46.619
Come on, come on.

00:59:46.679 --> 00:59:49.079
She tugs on Moon's wing impatiently.

00:59:49.139 --> 00:59:51.360
And the physical contact flooded Moon

00:59:51.360 --> 00:59:53.039
with Kingaju's radiant excitement.

00:59:53.099 --> 00:59:57.000
Kinkatoo bounded up a side corridor, lined

00:59:57.000 --> 00:59:58.139
with hanging scrolls.

00:59:58.199 --> 01:00:00.599
As she followed, Moon saw that each

01:00:00.599 --> 01:00:02.099
scroll had a quote on it.

01:00:02.159 --> 01:00:04.980
She didn't have time to read them all, but

01:00:04.980 --> 01:00:07.260
she saw, knowledge is a flame in the

01:00:07.260 --> 01:00:10.800
darkness, and the claws of war are no

01:00:10.800 --> 01:00:12.179
match for the wings of wisdom.

01:00:12.239 --> 01:00:15.059
At the end, they turned into a space full

01:00:15.059 --> 01:00:17.039
of iridescent green sunlight.

01:00:17.099 --> 01:00:19.139
It was like stepping into a dream.

01:00:19.199 --> 01:00:22.260
Scrolls were everywhere, simply

01:00:22.260 --> 01:00:24.420
everywhere, in cubby holes along the

01:00:24.420 --> 01:00:26.699
walls, and more racks and cylinders

01:00:26.699 --> 01:00:27.420
around the cave.

01:00:27.480 --> 01:00:30.119
Every corner had a spot to curl up and

01:00:30.119 --> 01:00:33.300
read in, sometimes a rock ledge, sometimes

01:00:33.300 --> 01:00:35.519
a pile of moss, or an arrangement of

01:00:35.519 --> 01:00:36.539
carpets.

01:00:36.599 --> 01:00:39.119
Only one reader was in there, a quiet

01:00:39.119 --> 01:00:41.340
looking mud wing with a scroll curled on

01:00:41.340 --> 01:00:41.820
some reeds.

01:00:41.880 --> 01:00:44.039
She didn't look up as they came in.

01:00:44.219 --> 01:00:46.619
The only image moon got from her mind was

01:00:46.619 --> 01:00:48.599
something like ripples on a mud puddle.

01:00:48.659 --> 01:00:51.719
Sunbeams filtered down through skylights

01:00:51.719 --> 01:00:53.940
in the roof, and windows along one wall.

01:00:54.000 --> 01:00:56.159
Each of the holes was covered with

01:00:56.159 --> 01:00:57.420
something thin enough to let the light

01:00:57.420 --> 01:00:59.460
through, but strong enough to keep the

01:00:59.460 --> 01:01:00.480
wind and weather out.

01:01:00.539 --> 01:01:03.179
Moon tilted her head back and study the

01:01:03.179 --> 01:01:03.780
closest one.

01:01:03.840 --> 01:01:07.079
Emerald green, with traces of veins

01:01:07.079 --> 01:01:07.920
branching through it.

01:01:07.980 --> 01:01:10.679
Leaves, she whispered.

01:01:10.739 --> 01:01:12.900
Sonny and Glory got them in the

01:01:12.900 --> 01:01:13.440
rainforest.

01:01:13.500 --> 01:01:15.179
Kinkachu said proudly.

01:01:15.239 --> 01:01:17.579
We use them sometimes as roofs for our

01:01:17.579 --> 01:01:18.780
rain wing houses.

01:01:18.840 --> 01:01:20.760
Aren't they perfect for library windows?

01:01:20.820 --> 01:01:22.980
Hi, Starflight.

01:01:23.039 --> 01:01:25.500
She bounded over to a circular wooden

01:01:25.500 --> 01:01:27.119
desk in the center that was labeled

01:01:27.119 --> 01:01:28.139
librarian.

01:01:28.199 --> 01:01:30.420
A dark head popped up from behind the

01:01:30.420 --> 01:01:30.659
desk.

01:01:30.719 --> 01:01:32.760
Hey, Kinkaju.

01:01:32.880 --> 01:01:35.280
The blind nightwing leaned forward with a

01:01:35.280 --> 01:01:37.679
smile as Kinkachu brushed his claws with

01:01:37.679 --> 01:01:38.159
hers.

01:01:38.219 --> 01:01:39.960
Is that moon with you?

01:01:40.019 --> 01:01:43.139
Hi, Moon said shyly.

01:01:43.260 --> 01:01:45.420
There was nothing ever hurtful in

01:01:45.420 --> 01:01:46.440
Starflight's thoughts.

01:01:46.500 --> 01:01:48.840
His brain was always busy, busy, busy.

01:01:48.900 --> 01:01:51.539
But he never thought of her as not a real

01:01:51.539 --> 01:01:54.059
night wing, or dangerous and

01:01:54.059 --> 01:01:54.900
untrustworthy.

01:01:54.960 --> 01:01:58.139
He was like her, an outsider in his own

01:01:58.139 --> 01:02:00.539
tribe, and he liked scrolls too.

01:02:00.599 --> 01:02:02.460
She could hear the back of his mind

01:02:02.460 --> 01:02:04.320
ticking through all the things he still

01:02:04.320 --> 01:02:05.579
needed to do to get the library

01:02:05.579 --> 01:02:08.400
completely ready, that he smiled in the

01:02:08.400 --> 01:02:09.119
direction of her voice.

01:02:09.179 --> 01:02:11.519
Here's your library stamp.

01:02:11.579 --> 01:02:14.099
He said, sliding something out from under

01:02:14.099 --> 01:02:14.579
the desk.

01:02:14.639 --> 01:02:16.559
I thought you might come by today.

01:02:16.619 --> 01:02:18.719
Library stamp?

01:02:18.840 --> 01:02:21.480
Moon echoed curiously, taking it from

01:02:21.480 --> 01:02:21.659
him.

01:02:21.719 --> 01:02:24.960
It was a small rectangle of wood as long

01:02:24.960 --> 01:02:27.960
as 2 claws, with her name carved backward

01:02:27.960 --> 01:02:29.400
in raised letters on one side.

01:02:29.460 --> 01:02:33.179
We are testing out a system, he said.

01:02:33.239 --> 01:02:34.139
I'll show you.

01:02:34.199 --> 01:02:36.840
He brushed his talons over a row of

01:02:36.840 --> 01:02:39.420
scrolls lined up under the desk.

01:02:39.480 --> 01:02:41.400
Moon spotted a name carved at the wooden

01:02:41.400 --> 01:02:43.199
end of each one, arranged

01:02:43.199 --> 01:02:43.800
alphabetically.

01:02:43.860 --> 01:02:46.380
Starflight touched them lightly until he

01:02:46.380 --> 01:02:48.420
felt hers, which he pulled out and

01:02:48.420 --> 01:02:49.320
partially unrolled.

01:02:49.380 --> 01:02:51.360
The scroll was completely blank.

01:02:51.420 --> 01:02:54.780
When you want to borrow a scroll, he said

01:02:54.780 --> 01:02:56.099
you bring it up to me here.

01:02:56.159 --> 01:02:59.280
Each one has a unique carved stamp on the

01:02:59.280 --> 01:03:00.420
end, like these do.

01:03:00.480 --> 01:03:03.059
I'll stamp your name scroll with that end

01:03:03.059 --> 01:03:04.440
to show that you checked it out.

01:03:04.500 --> 01:03:07.079
And then when you bring it back, we stamp

01:03:07.079 --> 01:03:09.599
your card over the 1st image to show that

01:03:09.599 --> 01:03:10.440
it's been returned.

01:03:10.500 --> 01:03:11.579
Does that make sense?

01:03:11.699 --> 01:03:14.699
I think so, Moon said.

01:03:14.760 --> 01:03:17.039
She turned the stamp over in her claws.

01:03:17.820 --> 01:03:19.440
She'd never had anything that was really

01:03:19.440 --> 01:03:20.219
her own before.

01:03:20.280 --> 01:03:23.039
Can she have a pouch to keep it in?

01:03:23.099 --> 01:03:24.300
Kinkaju asked.

01:03:24.360 --> 01:03:25.619
Of course.

01:03:25.679 --> 01:03:28.199
Starflight fumbled under the desk again

01:03:28.199 --> 01:03:29.099
for a few minutes.

01:03:29.159 --> 01:03:31.320
Then pulled out a soft black leather

01:03:31.320 --> 01:03:33.179
pouch on a silver chain.

01:03:33.239 --> 01:03:35.460
Moon slipped the stamp inside the pouch

01:03:35.460 --> 01:03:37.139
and put the chain over her neck.

01:03:37.199 --> 01:03:39.480
It felt like her very 1st treasure.

01:03:39.599 --> 01:03:42.179
Thank you, she said.

01:03:42.239 --> 01:03:44.519
Let me know if I can help you find

01:03:44.519 --> 01:03:45.719
anything, he said.

01:03:45.780 --> 01:03:49.079
She heard a flurry of worried what ifs

01:03:49.079 --> 01:03:51.659
start up in his mind, circling a well

01:03:51.659 --> 01:03:53.880
worn track of anxiety about how to be a

01:03:53.880 --> 01:03:54.960
blind librarian.

01:03:55.019 --> 01:03:57.420
She also heard him firmly beat those

01:03:57.420 --> 01:03:58.019
worries back.

01:03:58.079 --> 01:04:00.179
He smiled in her direction again.

01:04:00.239 --> 01:04:02.639
I've been practicing to get the whole

01:04:02.639 --> 01:04:03.780
space memorized.

01:04:03.840 --> 01:04:06.480
Moon wondered how she could ask for what

01:04:06.480 --> 01:04:09.000
she really needed, Do you have any

01:04:09.000 --> 01:04:10.980
scrolls about ominous voices in your

01:04:10.980 --> 01:04:11.159
head?

01:04:11.219 --> 01:04:14.219
Sora, are you still here?

01:04:14.280 --> 01:04:16.739
Starflight asked, raising his voice a

01:04:16.739 --> 01:04:16.920
little.

01:04:16.980 --> 01:04:19.440
The mudwing by the windows lifted her

01:04:19.440 --> 01:04:19.980
head and nodded.

01:04:20.099 --> 01:04:22.320
He can't see you.

01:04:22.380 --> 01:04:24.960
Kinkaju reminded her in a loud whisper.

01:04:25.019 --> 01:04:26.639
Yes, she's still here.

01:04:26.699 --> 01:04:30.420
Sorry, the brown dragon said softly.

01:04:30.480 --> 01:04:33.179
It's all right, Starflight said.

01:04:33.239 --> 01:04:35.460
The twinge of sadness in his thoughts

01:04:35.460 --> 01:04:36.780
didn't spill into his voice.

01:04:36.840 --> 01:04:39.840
Sora, this is Kinkaju and Moon.

01:04:39.900 --> 01:04:42.119
Sora is one of Clay's sisters.

01:04:42.300 --> 01:04:45.119
Ooh, Kinkachu said.

01:04:45.179 --> 01:04:47.280
How does it feel to be related to someone

01:04:47.280 --> 01:04:47.820
famous?

01:04:47.880 --> 01:04:50.340
Probably a bit like being best friends

01:04:50.340 --> 01:04:51.119
with a queen?

01:04:51.179 --> 01:04:53.639
she answered herself, grinning

01:04:53.639 --> 01:04:55.920
ridiculously, which I am just

01:04:55.920 --> 01:04:58.619
incidentally, so, I mean, I totally get

01:04:58.619 --> 01:04:58.800
it.

01:04:58.920 --> 01:05:01.619
Soris smile was shy.

01:05:01.679 --> 01:05:03.900
And now Moon could sense tremors of

01:05:03.900 --> 01:05:06.239
anxiety in her that felt an awful lot

01:05:06.239 --> 01:05:07.500
like Moon's own fears.

01:05:07.559 --> 01:05:10.260
Clay's sister was as nervous about being

01:05:10.260 --> 01:05:11.400
here as Moon was.

01:05:11.460 --> 01:05:14.159
It was sort of reassuring actually, to

01:05:14.159 --> 01:05:15.659
find someone as scared as she was.

01:05:15.719 --> 01:05:18.780
Nice to meet you, Moon said.

01:05:18.840 --> 01:05:21.179
Maybe she could be my friend too.

01:05:21.239 --> 01:05:23.219
Maybe mother was right.

01:05:23.280 --> 01:05:25.980
Maybe I will meet dragons I like here.

01:05:26.039 --> 01:05:30.840
You too, Sora nearly whispered, rolling

01:05:30.840 --> 01:05:32.340
her scroll between her talons.

01:05:32.400 --> 01:05:35.340
Let's go to the music wing next, Kinkachu

01:05:35.340 --> 01:05:35.639
said.

01:05:35.639 --> 01:05:38.760
Or, ooh, I heard there's an old ghost

01:05:38.760 --> 01:05:40.980
living somewhere in Jade Mountain.

01:05:41.039 --> 01:05:42.059
Maybe we can find him.

01:05:42.179 --> 01:05:45.300
Moon's ears twitched. ghost.

01:05:45.360 --> 01:05:47.699
Was she hearing the voice of a ghost?

01:05:47.760 --> 01:05:50.099
That would be unsettling.

01:05:50.159 --> 01:05:53.340
You're talking about Stone Mover

01:05:53.340 --> 01:05:55.920
Starflight said, and he's not a ghost.

01:05:55.980 --> 01:05:58.739
He's Sonny's father, and he's a perfectly

01:05:58.739 --> 01:06:00.360
nice old nightwing who's lived here for

01:06:00.360 --> 01:06:00.719
ages.

01:06:00.840 --> 01:06:03.539
He sleeps a lot, and doesn't need little

01:06:03.539 --> 01:06:05.460
dragonettes sneaking up on him or

01:06:05.460 --> 01:06:07.320
pouncing on his tail to find out if he's

01:06:07.320 --> 01:06:07.559
real.

01:06:07.619 --> 01:06:09.179
He does like company though.

01:06:09.239 --> 01:06:11.219
So if you're interested in a polite

01:06:11.219 --> 01:06:13.139
conversation with him, I can tell you how

01:06:13.139 --> 01:06:13.619
to find him.

01:06:13.739 --> 01:06:19.199
Polite conversation, yawn, Kinkaju said

01:06:19.199 --> 01:06:21.059
with a shrug of her wings, you should

01:06:21.059 --> 01:06:22.260
tell everyone he's a ghost.

01:06:22.320 --> 01:06:23.639
That would be much more exciting.

01:06:23.699 --> 01:06:28.380
Not a ghost, but a real night wing, moon

01:06:28.380 --> 01:06:28.860
thought.

01:06:28.920 --> 01:06:31.199
Maybe he's the one who can talk in my

01:06:31.199 --> 01:06:31.380
head.

01:06:31.440 --> 01:06:34.440
She'd have to ask Starflight for

01:06:34.440 --> 01:06:36.539
directions later if she could work up the

01:06:36.539 --> 01:06:37.500
courage.

01:06:37.559 --> 01:06:38.820
Are you hungry, Moon?

01:06:38.940 --> 01:06:40.559
Kinkachu barreled on.

01:06:40.619 --> 01:06:41.699
I might be hungry.

01:06:41.760 --> 01:06:43.260
We could find the praise center.

01:06:43.320 --> 01:06:44.340
I haven't done that yet.

01:06:44.400 --> 01:06:46.079
Which way do the Praise Center

01:06:46.079 --> 01:06:46.559
Starflight?

01:06:46.619 --> 01:06:49.380
He touched his desk lightly, as if

01:06:49.380 --> 01:06:51.599
orienting himself, and then pointed at

01:06:51.599 --> 01:06:53.400
one of the 3 corridors that led away from

01:06:53.400 --> 01:06:53.880
the library.

01:06:53.940 --> 01:06:56.699
Sora, you want to come?

01:06:56.760 --> 01:06:58.679
Kinkachu asked, before Moon could think

01:06:58.679 --> 01:07:00.239
to invite the dragonette herself.

01:07:00.300 --> 01:07:02.760
The mud wing shook her head quickly and

01:07:02.760 --> 01:07:04.380
buried her nose in her scroll again.

01:07:04.440 --> 01:07:06.239
All right, see you soon.

01:07:06.300 --> 01:07:08.639
Kinkaju called over her shoulder as they

01:07:08.639 --> 01:07:08.880
left.

01:07:09.000 --> 01:07:12.119
This passageway slanted back down, and

01:07:12.119 --> 01:07:14.460
Moon thought, out toward the open air.

01:07:14.519 --> 01:07:17.219
They passed a couple of branches, but

01:07:17.219 --> 01:07:19.139
Kingachu barely glanced down them before

01:07:19.139 --> 01:07:19.920
continuing straight.

01:07:19.980 --> 01:07:23.039
After a few minutes, Moon caught the

01:07:23.039 --> 01:07:25.380
scent of living prey up ahead, and the

01:07:25.380 --> 01:07:27.840
jumble of several voices, both real world

01:07:27.840 --> 01:07:29.219
and inside her head.

01:07:29.280 --> 01:07:30.599
Uh-oh.

01:07:30.659 --> 01:07:32.940
It was even worse than it sounded.

01:07:33.000 --> 01:07:35.519
The prey center was total chaos.

01:07:35.579 --> 01:07:38.159
The opposite of the serene, well ordered

01:07:38.159 --> 01:07:38.940
library.

01:07:39.000 --> 01:07:41.340
It was a mammoth cave open to the air on

01:07:41.340 --> 01:07:43.739
one side, looking out over a mossy

01:07:43.739 --> 01:07:46.800
boulder strewn slope, towering cliffs and

01:07:46.800 --> 01:07:47.699
faraway peaks.

01:07:47.760 --> 01:07:50.039
There was a low wall of rocks built

01:07:50.039 --> 01:07:52.559
across the bottom of the opening, useless

01:07:52.559 --> 01:07:54.840
against dragons, of course, but perfect

01:07:54.840 --> 01:07:56.519
for keeping prey trapped inside.

01:07:56.639 --> 01:07:59.400
A fast flowing river swept along the wall

01:07:59.400 --> 01:08:01.679
opposite the opening, disappearing

01:08:01.679 --> 01:08:03.420
through an archway into the next cave.

01:08:03.480 --> 01:08:07.440
And there was prey all over the place.

01:08:07.500 --> 01:08:10.320
Shaggy, bleeding sheep blundered

01:08:10.320 --> 01:08:12.480
helplessly under the dragon's talons

01:08:12.480 --> 01:08:13.800
yelling in panic.

01:08:13.860 --> 01:08:16.800
Several speckled brown chickens, quail

01:08:16.800 --> 01:08:18.659
and pheasants, were racing around the

01:08:18.659 --> 01:08:21.479
floor, periodically bursting skyward in

01:08:21.479 --> 01:08:23.640
an explosion of feathers and squawks.

01:08:23.699 --> 01:08:26.699
In one corner, a fat black bear was

01:08:26.699 --> 01:08:29.279
squaring off a dragonette twice its size

01:08:29.279 --> 01:08:30.060
growling.

01:08:30.119 --> 01:08:33.000
Worse still, the cave was filled with

01:08:33.000 --> 01:08:34.079
shouting dragons.

01:08:34.140 --> 01:08:36.960
Most of them were mudwing, sandwing, and

01:08:36.960 --> 01:08:39.300
skywing dragonettes, who were gleefully

01:08:39.300 --> 01:08:40.920
trying to corner their rampaging

01:08:40.920 --> 01:08:41.340
chickens.

01:08:41.399 --> 01:08:44.219
They bellowed instructions at one another

01:08:44.219 --> 01:08:46.919
yowled when the pheasant dodged them, and

01:08:46.919 --> 01:08:48.779
shrieked hilariously whenever birds

01:08:48.779 --> 01:08:50.099
nearly flew up their snouts.

01:08:50.220 --> 01:08:52.739
At the same time, their minds were all

01:08:52.739 --> 01:08:55.739
shouting, worrying, planning, reacting.

01:08:55.800 --> 01:08:58.800
And it fell to moon, like 100 dragons

01:08:58.800 --> 01:08:59.699
talking at once.

01:08:59.760 --> 01:09:02.819
Clay, meanwhile, was standing on a tall

01:09:02.819 --> 01:09:04.920
boulder in the middle of the cave, trying

01:09:04.920 --> 01:09:06.239
to shout over all the noise.

01:09:06.300 --> 01:09:10.140
Everyone stop moving, he bellowed

01:09:10.140 --> 01:09:12.060
especially you chickens.

01:09:12.119 --> 01:09:13.619
Chickens, give up.

01:09:13.680 --> 01:09:15.060
We're going to eat you.

01:09:15.119 --> 01:09:16.439
There's nothing you can do about it.

01:09:16.500 --> 01:09:18.840
Stop running away right now.

01:09:18.899 --> 01:09:21.239
Squawk!

01:09:21.359 --> 01:09:23.219
The chicken shrilled back.

01:09:23.279 --> 01:09:25.739
Kinkachoo spotted a small mountain of

01:09:25.739 --> 01:09:27.599
fruit piled near the river and darted

01:09:27.599 --> 01:09:27.959
over to it.

01:09:28.020 --> 01:09:30.659
Another rain wing dragonette was there

01:09:30.659 --> 01:09:33.119
picking through the options, and Kinkatu

01:09:33.119 --> 01:09:34.560
shouted something cheerful at him.

01:09:34.619 --> 01:09:37.500
Moon hesitated, wishing she could sink

01:09:37.500 --> 01:09:38.939
right into the mountain and disappear.

01:09:39.000 --> 01:09:42.720
She was hungry, but it was so loud and

01:09:42.720 --> 01:09:44.399
horribly overwhelming in here.

01:09:44.460 --> 01:09:46.920
Maybe she could sneak back to her cave

01:09:46.920 --> 01:09:48.600
and wait to eat until the middle of the

01:09:48.600 --> 01:09:49.500
night.

01:09:49.560 --> 01:09:50.939
Surely it would be quieter then.

01:09:51.000 --> 01:09:53.939
But Kinkachu spotted her as she tried to

01:09:53.939 --> 01:09:54.539
sidle away.

01:09:54.600 --> 01:09:57.300
The rain wing flapped her wings wildly

01:09:57.300 --> 01:09:59.760
beckoning, and finally Moon had to duck

01:09:59.760 --> 01:10:02.039
her head and sprint over, hoping not to

01:10:02.039 --> 01:10:03.779
get hit by any chicken parts on her way.

01:10:03.899 --> 01:10:08.100
Moon, this is my friend, Coconut, Kinkachu

01:10:08.100 --> 01:10:08.399
said.

01:10:08.460 --> 01:10:11.579
Thought he was my friend, shimmered

01:10:11.579 --> 01:10:13.619
through her mind, and Moon had a moment

01:10:13.619 --> 01:10:15.960
to wonder if Kinkachu did have a dark

01:10:15.960 --> 01:10:18.600
bitter side after all, before Kinkachu

01:10:18.600 --> 01:10:21.359
added blithely, at least, I thought he

01:10:21.359 --> 01:10:23.460
was my friend, until I got abducted by

01:10:23.460 --> 01:10:26.159
bad guys for 3 weeks, and he didn't even

01:10:26.159 --> 01:10:27.899
notice, I was gone.

01:10:27.960 --> 01:10:29.939
She poked him pointedly with her tail.

01:10:30.060 --> 01:10:31.319
Hmm?

01:10:31.380 --> 01:10:34.079
Didn't I say I was sorry about that?

01:10:34.140 --> 01:10:37.199
Coconut mumbled, around a mouthful of

01:10:37.199 --> 01:10:37.859
papaya.

01:10:37.920 --> 01:10:40.619
His scales were a kind of quiet lavender

01:10:40.619 --> 01:10:42.840
blue, and his eyes were sleepy.

01:10:42.840 --> 01:10:44.699
Or did I?

01:10:44.819 --> 01:10:46.380
Something like that.

01:10:46.439 --> 01:10:48.960
Mostly you say, hmm?

01:10:49.020 --> 01:10:49.439
What?

01:10:49.560 --> 01:10:52.260
Every time I bring it up, Kinkachu said.

01:10:52.319 --> 01:10:53.579
She turned to Moon.

01:10:53.640 --> 01:10:56.520
I'm going to learn to read eons before he

01:10:56.520 --> 01:10:56.760
does.

01:10:56.819 --> 01:10:59.100
Why is that?

01:10:59.159 --> 01:11:01.199
Coconut asked mildly.

01:11:01.260 --> 01:11:04.439
Because I'm smart and you're not, Kinkaju

01:11:04.439 --> 01:11:04.920
pointed out.

01:11:04.979 --> 01:11:07.319
That was implied, coconut.

01:11:07.380 --> 01:11:08.340
It was subtext.

01:11:08.399 --> 01:11:12.539
Right, he said, not in the least

01:11:12.539 --> 01:11:13.079
offended.

01:11:13.140 --> 01:11:15.239
Perhaps because he only seemed to be

01:11:15.239 --> 01:11:16.920
partially following the conversation.

01:11:16.979 --> 01:11:21.180
The mangoes are pretty good, he said to

01:11:21.180 --> 01:11:21.600
Moon.

01:11:21.659 --> 01:11:24.840
I was told to eat them 1st because

01:11:24.840 --> 01:11:25.800
they're all ripe.

01:11:25.859 --> 01:11:29.340
I like bananas better, but mangoes are

01:11:29.340 --> 01:11:29.579
fine.

01:11:29.640 --> 01:11:32.279
I don't particularly like coconut

01:11:32.279 --> 01:11:32.399
though.

01:11:32.460 --> 01:11:35.579
Ironically, Kinkachoo said.

01:11:35.640 --> 01:11:36.779
What?

01:11:36.899 --> 01:11:37.680
He said.

01:11:37.739 --> 01:11:41.100
See, she said to Moon, grinning.

01:11:41.159 --> 01:11:44.340
Moon nodded, unable to speak through the

01:11:44.340 --> 01:11:47.699
cacophony inside and outsider ears, at

01:11:47.699 --> 01:11:49.439
least coconut's thoughts were slow and

01:11:49.439 --> 01:11:51.479
meaningless, although she thought she

01:11:51.479 --> 01:11:53.159
might go mad if she had to listen to them

01:11:53.159 --> 01:11:53.699
all day long.

01:11:53.760 --> 01:11:56.880
He passed her 3 mangoes, and she sliced

01:11:56.880 --> 01:11:57.840
them open with her claws.

01:11:57.960 --> 01:11:59.819
The way she'd taught herself to do when

01:11:59.819 --> 01:12:01.979
she was alone in the rainforest during

01:12:01.979 --> 01:12:04.020
one of her mother's longer absences.

01:12:04.079 --> 01:12:06.840
Woof, said a voice behind her.

01:12:06.899 --> 01:12:09.239
Moon jumped and nearly dropped her

01:12:09.239 --> 01:12:10.079
mangoes in the river.

01:12:10.140 --> 01:12:13.680
It's just me, Clay said to her kindly.

01:12:13.739 --> 01:12:15.960
I'm glad you found Kinkachu.

01:12:16.079 --> 01:12:18.000
I thought you 2 would be a good match.

01:12:18.060 --> 01:12:19.800
You did?

01:12:19.859 --> 01:12:21.720
Moon thought with bewilderment.

01:12:21.779 --> 01:12:23.819
She couldn't see anything in common

01:12:23.819 --> 01:12:25.560
between herself and the bubbly rain

01:12:25.560 --> 01:12:25.979
wing.

01:12:26.039 --> 01:12:28.199
Clay shoot a chicken away from the fruit

01:12:28.199 --> 01:12:30.899
and glanced around the tumultuous cave.

01:12:30.960 --> 01:12:35.579
So, he said, my plan hasn't gone exactly

01:12:35.579 --> 01:12:37.439
as planned.

01:12:37.500 --> 01:12:41.039
Clay, this place is madness.

01:12:41.100 --> 01:12:42.840
Kinkajoo said with a laugh.

01:12:42.899 --> 01:12:46.079
I know, he said ruefully.

01:12:46.140 --> 01:12:47.460
We'll try something different tomorrow.

01:12:47.520 --> 01:12:49.979
I thought it would be fun to bring in

01:12:49.979 --> 01:12:52.020
live prey and let everyone chase it

01:12:52.020 --> 01:12:52.260
around.

01:12:52.319 --> 01:12:54.539
That's what we did in our cave

01:12:54.539 --> 01:12:55.079
sometimes.

01:12:55.140 --> 01:12:58.079
Growing up, when the guardians wanted us

01:12:58.079 --> 01:13:00.000
to practice hunting, but wouldn't let us

01:13:00.000 --> 01:13:00.539
go outside.

01:13:00.600 --> 01:13:02.819
But I guess it was a little more

01:13:02.819 --> 01:13:06.239
manageable with 5 dragonette, then 35.

01:13:06.420 --> 01:13:09.000
He wrinkled a snout at the nearest

01:13:09.000 --> 01:13:10.079
panicking sheep.

01:13:10.079 --> 01:13:11.640
Kinkachu shook her head.

01:13:11.699 --> 01:13:14.460
I see anyone who is gross enough to eat

01:13:14.460 --> 01:13:16.319
something that's alive and wriggling

01:13:16.319 --> 01:13:17.640
deserves to get pecked.

01:13:17.699 --> 01:13:20.039
You should take those dragons out hunting

01:13:20.039 --> 01:13:21.840
with you, and leave the rest of us here

01:13:21.840 --> 01:13:24.119
to enjoy our quiet, sensible fruit in

01:13:24.119 --> 01:13:24.600
peace.

01:13:24.659 --> 01:13:27.539
That's a good idea.

01:13:27.600 --> 01:13:28.920
Clay said.

01:13:28.979 --> 01:13:31.800
In the meanwhile, maybe I'll get tsunami

01:13:31.800 --> 01:13:33.659
and see if she can help me calm things

01:13:33.659 --> 01:13:33.899
down.

01:13:33.960 --> 01:13:37.560
He gave Moon another reassuring smile, and

01:13:37.560 --> 01:13:38.939
hurried out at the pray center.

01:13:39.000 --> 01:13:43.859
Moon heard the words quiet, and peace, and

01:13:43.859 --> 01:13:46.439
calm, as if from a long way away.

01:13:46.500 --> 01:13:49.020
Through the raucous noise of the dragon

01:13:49.020 --> 01:13:50.880
minds around her, she could sense

01:13:50.880 --> 01:13:52.439
something running toward the cave.

01:13:52.500 --> 01:13:55.619
Something like a small thread of pure

01:13:55.619 --> 01:13:57.840
terror, so tiny.

01:13:57.899 --> 01:14:00.239
It could be blown away in a breeze, but

01:14:00.239 --> 01:14:00.960
so intense.

01:14:01.020 --> 01:14:01.920
She couldn't miss it.

01:14:01.979 --> 01:14:04.859
Even in a howling gale of emotions in the

01:14:04.859 --> 01:14:05.520
prey center.

01:14:05.579 --> 01:14:07.199
Who is that?

01:14:07.260 --> 01:14:09.899
And why is their mind so strange?

01:14:09.960 --> 01:14:12.779
There were no words to go along with the

01:14:12.779 --> 01:14:13.260
emotions.

01:14:13.319 --> 01:14:15.119
And there was something fuzzy about it.

01:14:15.180 --> 01:14:17.819
Could it be a really young dragonette?

01:14:17.880 --> 01:14:19.920
She lifted her head and turned to watch

01:14:19.920 --> 01:14:23.640
for it, but as she did, a vast icicle of

01:14:23.640 --> 01:14:26.520
cold fury, stabbed through her brain and

01:14:26.520 --> 01:14:28.920
she staggered back, crushing the mangoes

01:14:28.920 --> 01:14:30.479
in her talons with an involuntary

01:14:30.479 --> 01:14:33.300
convulsion, bright yellow orange pulp

01:14:33.300 --> 01:14:35.640
splattered all over kinkachu and coconut

01:14:35.640 --> 01:14:36.840
and the rocks around them.

01:14:36.840 --> 01:14:39.779
Kinkachu let out a startled yelp.

01:14:39.840 --> 01:14:42.479
But before Moon could apologize, or even

01:14:42.479 --> 01:14:45.180
get speech back under her control, a

01:14:45.180 --> 01:14:46.619
louder commotion erupted near one of the

01:14:46.619 --> 01:14:47.039
tunnels.

01:14:47.100 --> 01:14:49.020
Catch it.

01:14:49.079 --> 01:14:49.739
Mine.

01:14:49.800 --> 01:14:50.699
I claim it mine.

01:14:50.760 --> 01:14:51.779
It went that way.

01:14:51.840 --> 01:14:55.140
All the mud wings and sky wings abandoned

01:14:55.140 --> 01:14:57.420
the chickens at once and bolted over to

01:14:57.420 --> 01:14:58.260
that side of the cave.

01:14:58.319 --> 01:15:00.779
Moon felt that the right of fear twist

01:15:00.779 --> 01:15:02.699
higher and brighter, as if it had been

01:15:02.699 --> 01:15:03.239
set on fire.

01:15:03.359 --> 01:15:06.060
And then a small shape shot between the

01:15:06.060 --> 01:15:08.640
dragons and came pelting across the cave

01:15:08.640 --> 01:15:11.399
dodging sheep and chickens, and Moon saw

01:15:11.399 --> 01:15:12.420
what everyone was chasing.

01:15:12.479 --> 01:15:14.220
A scavenger.

01:15:14.279 --> 01:15:17.520
She'd read about them and seen drawings

01:15:17.520 --> 01:15:19.560
but she'd never encountered a real

01:15:19.560 --> 01:15:20.399
scavenger before.

01:15:20.460 --> 01:15:22.380
She'd never given them much thought.

01:15:22.439 --> 01:15:25.079
Apart from stealing the sandwing treasure

01:15:25.079 --> 01:15:27.479
and killing Queen Oasis 20 years ago

01:15:27.479 --> 01:15:29.100
there were just creatures who happened to

01:15:29.100 --> 01:15:30.960
live on the same planet as the dragons

01:15:30.960 --> 01:15:34.439
but suddenly, this one was right here, and

01:15:34.439 --> 01:15:36.239
blazing in her mind as brightly as any

01:15:36.239 --> 01:15:36.720
dragon.

01:15:36.840 --> 01:15:39.600
She saw it spot the sheep and chickens

01:15:39.600 --> 01:15:41.340
including the ones that had been caught

01:15:41.340 --> 01:15:43.619
and half eaten already, and she saw it

01:15:43.619 --> 01:15:45.659
stumble as a bolt of despair went through

01:15:45.659 --> 01:15:45.899
it.

01:15:45.960 --> 01:15:49.920
Why can I feel the scavenger's fear, but

01:15:49.920 --> 01:15:51.659
nothing from the sheep or the chickens

01:15:51.659 --> 01:15:52.500
she wondered.

01:15:52.619 --> 01:15:53.880
Aren't they the same?

01:15:53.939 --> 01:15:57.720
The icy anger she'd felt before, swept

01:15:57.720 --> 01:15:59.819
into the cave like an avenging blizzard

01:15:59.819 --> 01:16:03.720
an ice wing, pale blue as a frozen ocean

01:16:03.720 --> 01:16:06.000
with glittering scales like overlapping

01:16:06.000 --> 01:16:06.659
chips of ice.

01:16:06.720 --> 01:16:09.060
He stormed through the yelling crowd of

01:16:09.060 --> 01:16:10.680
dragonettes who were still trying to find

01:16:10.680 --> 01:16:12.840
the scavenger underfoot, and Moon

01:16:12.840 --> 01:16:15.060
realized he was chasing the little animal

01:16:15.060 --> 01:16:15.479
as well.

01:16:15.600 --> 01:16:18.239
The scavenger didn't stand a chance.

01:16:18.300 --> 01:16:21.239
He'd fled into the worst possible place.

01:16:21.300 --> 01:16:23.340
Someone in the pray center was definitely

01:16:23.340 --> 01:16:25.979
going to catch him and eat him, and Moon

01:16:25.979 --> 01:16:28.859
would have to feel his awful terror as it

01:16:28.859 --> 01:16:29.159
happened.

01:16:29.220 --> 01:16:30.899
She couldn't watch it die.

01:16:30.960 --> 01:16:33.000
She couldn't let that happen to something

01:16:33.000 --> 01:16:36.659
so scared, so helpless and alive, and

01:16:36.659 --> 01:16:39.180
alone, and clearly aware what was about

01:16:39.180 --> 01:16:40.140
to happen to it.

01:16:40.380 --> 01:16:42.600
Moon bolted over to the scavenger.

01:16:42.659 --> 01:16:44.640
Cut it off as it tried to dodge around

01:16:44.640 --> 01:16:48.119
her, darted left to block its retreat, and

01:16:48.119 --> 01:16:49.619
deftly snatched it up in her claws.

01:16:49.680 --> 01:16:51.239
It's all right.

01:16:51.300 --> 01:16:52.619
She whispered to it.

01:16:52.680 --> 01:16:54.060
I'm not going to hurt you.

01:16:54.119 --> 01:16:55.920
It did no good.

01:16:55.979 --> 01:16:58.859
The scavenger's heartbreaking fear buzzed

01:16:58.859 --> 01:17:01.020
even more clearly in her mind now that

01:17:01.020 --> 01:17:01.619
she was holding it.

01:17:01.680 --> 01:17:04.739
It put its little paws over its head and

01:17:04.739 --> 01:17:07.260
curled into a ball between her talons.

01:17:07.319 --> 01:17:09.960
Silence slowly spread across the cave.

01:17:10.079 --> 01:17:13.319
Moon looked up and found the ice wing

01:17:13.319 --> 01:17:14.340
only inches away.

01:17:14.399 --> 01:17:16.920
Glaring at her with dark blue eyes.

01:17:17.039 --> 01:17:21.600
Nightwing, he thought, with a flash of

01:17:21.600 --> 01:17:23.640
vicious hatred that made her wince.

01:17:23.699 --> 01:17:27.420
He hissed slowly, exhaling a hint of

01:17:27.420 --> 01:17:29.100
deadly frost breath into the air between

01:17:29.100 --> 01:17:29.399
them.

01:17:29.460 --> 01:17:33.659
You have 10 seconds to give me back my

01:17:33.659 --> 01:17:34.500
scavenger.

01:17:34.560 --> 01:17:37.979
He snarled, before I slice your face

01:17:37.979 --> 01:17:38.220
off.

01:17:38.340 --> 01:17:42.600
Chapter 4.

01:17:42.899 --> 01:17:46.260
So much for keeping my head down and

01:17:46.260 --> 01:17:48.779
staying inconspicuous, moon thought

01:17:48.779 --> 01:17:50.880
feeling the eyes and thoughts of every

01:17:50.880 --> 01:17:52.439
dragon in the cave on her.

01:17:52.500 --> 01:17:55.680
The ice wing was frighteningly beautiful

01:17:55.680 --> 01:17:58.859
with horns like deadly icicles and sharp

01:17:58.859 --> 01:18:01.140
spikes at the end of his whip thin tail

01:18:01.140 --> 01:18:03.359
his gaze pinned her down like a spear.

01:18:03.420 --> 01:18:06.720
Never seen one look like that before.

01:18:06.779 --> 01:18:08.220
She heard him think.

01:18:08.279 --> 01:18:10.800
Didn't know they had silver scales

01:18:10.800 --> 01:18:12.539
anywhere except under their wings.

01:18:12.600 --> 01:18:14.880
Those ones by her eyes are remarkable.

01:18:14.939 --> 01:18:18.600
And she looks like she's listening to

01:18:18.600 --> 01:18:18.779
something.

01:18:18.840 --> 01:18:22.199
A brief wave of curiosity shivered

01:18:22.199 --> 01:18:24.060
through his thoughts, and then was

01:18:24.060 --> 01:18:26.159
abruptly buried in a landslide of anger

01:18:26.159 --> 01:18:27.899
and self loathing.

01:18:27.960 --> 01:18:28.560
What am I thinking?

01:18:28.619 --> 01:18:31.319
Nightwings killed him, and I hate them

01:18:31.319 --> 01:18:31.739
all.

01:18:31.800 --> 01:18:32.880
All of them.

01:18:32.939 --> 01:18:36.420
Moon tore her eyes away from his, wishing

01:18:36.420 --> 01:18:37.619
she could shut her powers off.

01:18:37.680 --> 01:18:40.020
She could have known from his expression

01:18:40.020 --> 01:18:40.800
that he hated her.

01:18:40.859 --> 01:18:43.079
She didn't need to see the layers of how

01:18:43.079 --> 01:18:44.460
complicated his feelings were.

01:18:44.520 --> 01:18:46.140
Who did we kill?

01:18:46.260 --> 01:18:48.300
Someone he loved obviously.

01:18:48.359 --> 01:18:51.180
She found it easy to believe the night

01:18:51.180 --> 01:18:53.039
wings she knew deserved his hatred.

01:18:53.100 --> 01:18:56.340
I wish I could be someone else, someone

01:18:56.340 --> 01:18:57.479
he would give half a chance.

01:18:57.539 --> 01:19:01.619
Five seconds, he snarled.

01:19:01.739 --> 01:19:06.300
No, Moon said, forcing the word out past

01:19:06.300 --> 01:19:08.579
the scavenger's terror and the sharp

01:19:08.579 --> 01:19:10.319
edges of the ice wing's anger.

01:19:10.380 --> 01:19:14.699
That is my scavenger. he hissed.

01:19:14.819 --> 01:19:17.880
My idiot clawmate let it out, but it is

01:19:17.880 --> 01:19:20.279
mine, and I did not bring it all the way

01:19:20.279 --> 01:19:22.560
here to see it eaten by a lying, smoke

01:19:22.560 --> 01:19:23.880
breathing night wing.

01:19:23.939 --> 01:19:27.479
He took a step closer, and Moon felt the

01:19:27.479 --> 01:19:29.159
cold coming off his scales.

01:19:29.220 --> 01:19:31.920
I could freeze you one part at a time.

01:19:32.039 --> 01:19:35.279
First your horns, then snap them off.

01:19:35.340 --> 01:19:39.180
Then your tail, freeze it, and snap it

01:19:39.180 --> 01:19:42.180
off, then your claws, and your wings.

01:19:42.239 --> 01:19:43.800
Should I go on?

01:19:43.859 --> 01:19:46.739
Moon closed her talons around the

01:19:46.739 --> 01:19:48.779
scavenger, Anne brought her wings forward

01:19:48.779 --> 01:19:49.680
to wrap around it too.

01:19:49.739 --> 01:19:52.439
It was impossible to focus her thoughts.

01:19:52.500 --> 01:19:55.439
The ice wing's mind was so bright, like

01:19:55.439 --> 01:19:57.300
the sun dazzling off a glacier.

01:19:57.359 --> 01:20:00.119
In between his threats, were images of

01:20:00.119 --> 01:20:02.460
another ice wing, laughing and shouting

01:20:02.460 --> 01:20:03.000
in the snow.

01:20:03.060 --> 01:20:06.000
Then the same dragon, surrounded by sky

01:20:06.000 --> 01:20:07.739
wings in a mountain forest.

01:20:07.800 --> 01:20:09.840
She couldn't follow the threads.

01:20:09.899 --> 01:20:12.960
If that was the dragon he mourned, how

01:20:12.960 --> 01:20:14.760
did he get killed by Nightwings, if he

01:20:14.760 --> 01:20:16.140
was captured by Skywings.

01:20:16.199 --> 01:20:18.420
If the ice wing wanted to eat this

01:20:18.420 --> 01:20:20.819
scavenger, why had he brought it all the

01:20:20.819 --> 01:20:21.239
way here?

01:20:21.300 --> 01:20:24.720
If he hated Moon so much, how could he

01:20:24.720 --> 01:20:26.939
also be noticing how gently she held the

01:20:26.939 --> 01:20:27.359
scavenger?

01:20:27.420 --> 01:20:31.560
Say something, she yelled at herself, but

01:20:31.560 --> 01:20:33.119
already she couldn't remember what he'd

01:20:33.119 --> 01:20:35.340
said, and what she'd only seen inside his

01:20:35.340 --> 01:20:35.579
mind.

01:20:35.640 --> 01:20:38.579
Hey, calm down, all right.

01:20:38.640 --> 01:20:40.979
A sand wing shoved his way through the

01:20:40.979 --> 01:20:43.079
watching crowd and stepped between moon

01:20:43.079 --> 01:20:43.920
and the ice wing.

01:20:43.979 --> 01:20:46.920
Moon recognized him as the dragon she'd

01:20:46.920 --> 01:20:49.619
made eye contact with outsider cave, the

01:20:49.619 --> 01:20:51.180
one who had noticed how nervous she was.

01:20:51.239 --> 01:20:54.420
No one is getting sliced up or frozen and

01:20:54.420 --> 01:20:55.020
snapped apart.

01:20:55.079 --> 01:20:56.640
He said to the ice wing.

01:20:56.699 --> 01:20:57.899
What is wrong with you?

01:20:57.960 --> 01:21:00.239
Did you even try just asking nicely?

01:21:00.359 --> 01:21:02.100
He turned to Moon.

01:21:02.159 --> 01:21:05.880
Hey, I'm the idiot claw mate, although

01:21:05.880 --> 01:21:07.319
most dragons call me Kibli.

01:21:07.380 --> 01:21:09.420
My intimidating acquaintance here is

01:21:09.420 --> 01:21:09.779
winter.

01:21:09.840 --> 01:21:10.979
What's your name?

01:21:11.039 --> 01:21:14.460
He had a gold earring in one ear, with a

01:21:14.460 --> 01:21:16.680
warm, orange, amber teardrop hanging from

01:21:16.680 --> 01:21:16.920
it.

01:21:16.979 --> 01:21:19.260
A few dark brown freckles stood out on

01:21:19.260 --> 01:21:21.359
his nose, which also bore a small

01:21:21.359 --> 01:21:22.619
zigzagging scar.

01:21:22.680 --> 01:21:25.020
The rest of him was a light sandy color.

01:21:25.079 --> 01:21:27.840
His poisonous barbed tail was tucked

01:21:27.840 --> 01:21:30.239
neatly into a safe spiral, although it

01:21:30.239 --> 01:21:32.039
kept twitching in winter's direction.

01:21:32.039 --> 01:21:35.100
He looked like a normal sand wing, but he

01:21:35.100 --> 01:21:37.079
didn't think like one, or like any

01:21:37.079 --> 01:21:38.220
dragons she'd met before.

01:21:38.279 --> 01:21:41.640
Brushing against Kibley's mind was like

01:21:41.640 --> 01:21:43.020
stepping into a speeding river.

01:21:43.079 --> 01:21:45.840
He was almost unconsciously scanning the

01:21:45.840 --> 01:21:48.060
cave as he spoke to her, assessing

01:21:48.060 --> 01:21:50.100
threats, and deciding which dragons were

01:21:50.100 --> 01:21:51.420
the most dangerous.

01:21:51.479 --> 01:21:52.619
She was not on the list.

01:21:52.680 --> 01:21:55.079
While he was focusing on diffusing

01:21:55.079 --> 01:21:57.119
Winter's tension and negotiating with

01:21:57.119 --> 01:21:59.579
Moon, he was also checking escape routes

01:21:59.579 --> 01:22:01.680
and noting who wore the most jewelry.

01:22:01.739 --> 01:22:04.140
A small part of his brain was even

01:22:04.140 --> 01:22:06.060
clocking a chicken in his peripheral

01:22:06.060 --> 01:22:08.039
vision that he thought might scurry close

01:22:08.039 --> 01:22:08.760
enough for him to catch.

01:22:08.819 --> 01:22:11.819
This did not help clear her mind at all.

01:22:11.880 --> 01:22:13.800
They were waiting for an answer from

01:22:13.800 --> 01:22:14.460
her.

01:22:14.520 --> 01:22:15.359
To what question?

01:22:15.420 --> 01:22:16.260
Her name?

01:22:16.319 --> 01:22:17.579
Moon.

01:22:17.640 --> 01:22:19.380
She managed to whisper.

01:22:19.439 --> 01:22:21.420
Moon what?

01:22:21.479 --> 01:22:22.979
The ice wing snapped.

01:22:23.039 --> 01:22:24.420
Moon what?

01:22:24.479 --> 01:22:26.279
She didn't understand the question.

01:22:26.340 --> 01:22:28.500
The scavenger was moving between her

01:22:28.500 --> 01:22:31.199
claws, and his fear now had streaks of

01:22:31.199 --> 01:22:33.359
confusion in it, which was muddling up

01:22:33.359 --> 01:22:35.819
Moon's head as well, not to mention the

01:22:35.819 --> 01:22:37.619
crowd of watching dragons in their

01:22:37.619 --> 01:22:38.939
excited mind clamor.

01:22:39.000 --> 01:22:40.140
Maybe they'll fight.

01:22:40.199 --> 01:22:42.479
I wonder what scavengers taste like.

01:22:42.539 --> 01:22:44.340
Why isn't she saying anything?

01:22:44.399 --> 01:22:46.920
I can't believe she took a scavenger.

01:22:46.979 --> 01:22:49.439
I bet if he slices her face off, he'll

01:22:49.439 --> 01:22:50.460
totally get expelled.

01:22:50.520 --> 01:22:52.319
Moon what?

01:22:52.439 --> 01:22:54.119
Winter nearly shouted.

01:22:54.180 --> 01:22:55.800
Come on, Nightwing.

01:22:55.859 --> 01:22:57.659
We know your names are all lies.

01:22:57.720 --> 01:22:58.920
So what's yours?

01:22:58.979 --> 01:23:02.279
Moon Destroyer, Moon Eater, Moon Crusher

01:23:02.279 --> 01:23:03.779
Winter.

01:23:03.840 --> 01:23:06.899
You need to seriously cool down, Kibley

01:23:06.899 --> 01:23:07.319
yelled.

01:23:07.380 --> 01:23:08.880
He shot a granite moon.

01:23:08.939 --> 01:23:09.720
Get it?

01:23:09.779 --> 01:23:10.859
Because he's an ice wing?

01:23:10.920 --> 01:23:11.520
I know.

01:23:11.579 --> 01:23:12.300
I'm hilarious.

01:23:12.359 --> 01:23:16.619
It's Moon Watcher, said Kingachu, coming

01:23:16.619 --> 01:23:17.520
up behind Moon.

01:23:17.579 --> 01:23:19.920
She twined her tail around Moon.

01:23:19.979 --> 01:23:22.500
Moon knew that the rain wing was trying

01:23:22.500 --> 01:23:24.960
to be reassuring and supportive, but the

01:23:24.960 --> 01:23:26.819
effect was that Kinkaju's thoughts were

01:23:26.819 --> 01:23:29.640
suddenly as loud as thunder, clashing up

01:23:29.640 --> 01:23:32.039
against the scavengers' small, hot spark

01:23:32.039 --> 01:23:32.579
of terror.

01:23:32.640 --> 01:23:34.560
An ice wing.

01:23:34.619 --> 01:23:37.380
He's so glittery and fierce and dangerous

01:23:37.380 --> 01:23:39.779
plus a heroic sand wing.

01:23:39.840 --> 01:23:41.520
So much drama already.

01:23:41.579 --> 01:23:42.420
I love school.

01:23:42.479 --> 01:23:43.020
I love it.

01:23:43.079 --> 01:23:43.500
I love it.

01:23:43.560 --> 01:23:45.479
Moon Watcher.

01:23:45.600 --> 01:23:48.600
Winter muttered, deflating a little.

01:23:48.659 --> 01:23:51.359
There was something shivery about hearing

01:23:51.359 --> 01:23:53.939
him say her name, but Moon couldn't tell

01:23:53.939 --> 01:23:55.920
if that was just because Kinkaju was

01:23:55.920 --> 01:23:57.960
having starry eyed sparkle thoughts about

01:23:57.960 --> 01:23:58.979
him all over her brain.

01:23:59.100 --> 01:24:02.039
Listen, Kibley said.

01:24:02.100 --> 01:24:03.180
This is my fault.

01:24:03.239 --> 01:24:06.000
I wanted a closer look, so I opened the

01:24:06.000 --> 01:24:07.920
cage, and that thing was halfway down the

01:24:07.920 --> 01:24:09.659
tunnel before we could even sneeze.

01:24:09.720 --> 01:24:11.880
But I promise you, this scavenger does

01:24:11.880 --> 01:24:12.659
belong to winter.

01:24:12.720 --> 01:24:14.760
So we're asking you nicely.

01:24:14.819 --> 01:24:16.979
Please, don't eat it.

01:24:17.039 --> 01:24:20.880
Get your teeth anywhere near Bandit, and

01:24:20.880 --> 01:24:21.720
you will lose them.

01:24:21.779 --> 01:24:23.579
Winter snarled.

01:24:23.640 --> 01:24:26.640
You are not at all clear on the concept

01:24:26.640 --> 01:24:28.920
of asking nicely, are you?

01:24:28.979 --> 01:24:30.119
Kibley said to him.

01:24:30.180 --> 01:24:32.699
Bandit?

01:24:32.760 --> 01:24:33.420
Moon echoed.

01:24:33.479 --> 01:24:36.960
Who names their dinner, or keeps it in a

01:24:36.960 --> 01:24:37.319
cage?

01:24:37.380 --> 01:24:39.899
She had a sinking feeling that she had

01:24:39.899 --> 01:24:41.520
terribly misread this situation.

01:24:41.640 --> 01:24:42.779
Why?

01:24:42.840 --> 01:24:45.600
Why, in all the furious, jumbled thoughts

01:24:45.600 --> 01:24:47.760
inside Winter's head, hadn't she seen

01:24:47.760 --> 01:24:50.279
anything about him not wanting to eat the

01:24:50.279 --> 01:24:50.760
scavenger?

01:24:50.819 --> 01:24:53.819
Indeed, Kibley said.

01:24:53.880 --> 01:24:55.920
The scavenger with a silly name is

01:24:55.920 --> 01:24:56.640
Winter's pet.

01:24:56.760 --> 01:24:59.579
Nobody told me we could bring pets here.

01:24:59.640 --> 01:25:01.800
But I guess the nephew of the ice wing

01:25:01.800 --> 01:25:04.260
queen, get some special privileges.

01:25:04.319 --> 01:25:06.420
And if you didn't know, he was Queen

01:25:06.420 --> 01:25:07.680
Glacier's nephew.

01:25:07.739 --> 01:25:09.840
Don't worry, he'd have told you sometime

01:25:09.840 --> 01:25:10.739
in the next 5 minutes.

01:25:10.800 --> 01:25:12.960
I only mentioned it.

01:25:13.079 --> 01:25:16.020
Winter said irately, because it seems

01:25:16.020 --> 01:25:18.779
entirely obvious to me that the niece and

01:25:18.779 --> 01:25:21.000
nephew of the ice wing queen should each

01:25:21.000 --> 01:25:22.619
be given a private cave.

01:25:22.680 --> 01:25:24.779
So I wanted you to know we wouldn't have

01:25:24.779 --> 01:25:27.060
to be claw mates for very long, as there

01:25:27.060 --> 01:25:28.920
has clearly been some kind of mistake.

01:25:28.979 --> 01:25:32.880
Here's hoping, Kibley said.

01:25:32.939 --> 01:25:37.020
So, Moon, can we catch you a sheep or

01:25:37.020 --> 01:25:37.920
something instead?

01:25:37.979 --> 01:25:40.800
Another 1000000 thoughts flashed through

01:25:40.800 --> 01:25:42.659
his head in the space of 2 heartbeats.

01:25:42.720 --> 01:25:44.640
What do night wings like?

01:25:44.699 --> 01:25:46.619
Never trained for bargaining with a night

01:25:46.619 --> 01:25:46.979
wing.

01:25:47.039 --> 01:25:49.020
Can't be too different from other dragons

01:25:49.020 --> 01:25:49.260
right?

01:25:49.319 --> 01:25:50.640
Start with food.

01:25:50.699 --> 01:25:52.920
But she doesn't look like a dragon who

01:25:52.920 --> 01:25:53.880
thinks about prey a lot.

01:25:53.939 --> 01:25:55.500
Not treasure either.

01:25:55.560 --> 01:25:56.340
Scrolls?

01:25:56.399 --> 01:25:58.739
She has a cool scrollish look about her.

01:25:58.800 --> 01:25:59.640
What can we offer?

01:25:59.699 --> 01:26:02.100
If she eats him, winter will be furious.

01:26:02.159 --> 01:26:04.199
Maybe I can get him a new scavenger.

01:26:04.260 --> 01:26:07.380
I wasn't going to eat him, she blurted

01:26:07.380 --> 01:26:09.420
quickly. before she could get lost again

01:26:09.420 --> 01:26:10.739
in all the tracks of thoughts around

01:26:10.739 --> 01:26:11.039
her.

01:26:11.100 --> 01:26:13.140
I didn't want anyone to eat him.

01:26:13.199 --> 01:26:15.300
Nobody can eat him, not ever.

01:26:15.359 --> 01:26:18.479
Winter tilted his head curiously at her

01:26:18.479 --> 01:26:20.939
and she felt his fury thaw a little.

01:26:21.000 --> 01:26:24.300
That is exactly how I feel about it.

01:26:24.359 --> 01:26:27.659
Great, Kibley said.

01:26:27.720 --> 01:26:28.920
Weird but great.

01:26:28.979 --> 01:26:31.140
We're all on the same roll of the scroll

01:26:31.140 --> 01:26:31.500
then.

01:26:31.560 --> 01:26:33.600
He looked expectantly at Moon.

01:26:33.659 --> 01:26:35.819
She tried to block him out so she could

01:26:35.819 --> 01:26:37.079
listen to Winter's thoughts for a

01:26:37.079 --> 01:26:37.260
moment.

01:26:37.319 --> 01:26:39.420
It seemed to be true.

01:26:39.479 --> 01:26:42.479
He was keeping the scavenger as a pet, and

01:26:42.479 --> 01:26:44.220
would violently dismember anyone who

01:26:44.220 --> 01:26:44.819
tried to eat it.

01:26:44.880 --> 01:26:47.640
She didn't think the scavenger understood

01:26:47.640 --> 01:26:47.819
that.

01:26:47.880 --> 01:26:50.579
He seemed as terrified of winter as all

01:26:50.579 --> 01:26:52.859
the other dragons, but at least he'd be

01:26:52.859 --> 01:26:54.960
safer in winter's cage than anywhere else

01:26:54.960 --> 01:26:55.560
in the academy.

01:26:55.619 --> 01:26:58.619
She carefully unwound her tail from

01:26:58.619 --> 01:27:00.720
Kikachu's, and lifted the little creature

01:27:00.720 --> 01:27:02.159
into winter's talons.

01:27:02.399 --> 01:27:04.739
His claws brushed against hers as she did

01:27:04.739 --> 01:27:05.939
and she flinched.

01:27:06.060 --> 01:27:08.819
Both at the cold, and at the furious

01:27:08.819 --> 01:27:11.159
turmoil of guilt and self loathing inside

01:27:11.159 --> 01:27:11.460
him.

01:27:11.520 --> 01:27:13.380
Ew.

01:27:13.439 --> 01:27:15.420
Winter protested, peering at the

01:27:15.420 --> 01:27:15.960
scavenger.

01:27:16.020 --> 01:27:17.819
You got him all sticky.

01:27:17.939 --> 01:27:20.579
Moon realized that her claws were still

01:27:20.579 --> 01:27:22.739
covered in crushed mango, and she gotten

01:27:22.739 --> 01:27:24.300
bits of it all over Winter's pet.

01:27:24.359 --> 01:27:27.060
Sorry, she said softly.

01:27:27.119 --> 01:27:31.500
I just, she was just saving him, Kinkachu

01:27:31.500 --> 01:27:32.039
pointed out.

01:27:32.100 --> 01:27:33.899
You could actually say thank you.

01:27:34.020 --> 01:27:37.020
Hmm, Winter said.

01:27:37.079 --> 01:27:39.600
Moon sensed clay approaching along one of

01:27:39.600 --> 01:27:41.460
the tunnels, along with someone else

01:27:41.460 --> 01:27:43.619
whose mind was warm and nearly as excited

01:27:43.619 --> 01:27:44.880
as Gingaju's.

01:27:44.939 --> 01:27:47.579
Sonny, she gasped with relief.

01:27:47.640 --> 01:27:50.520
She really needed to not be the center of

01:27:50.520 --> 01:27:51.300
attention anymore.

01:27:51.359 --> 01:27:54.420
Winter took his pet over to the river and

01:27:54.420 --> 01:27:57.180
dunked him in, prompting several shocked

01:27:57.180 --> 01:27:58.500
squeaking noises from Bandit.

01:27:58.560 --> 01:28:01.140
What does she know about scavengers?

01:28:01.260 --> 01:28:02.819
Moon heard him think?

01:28:02.880 --> 01:28:05.039
I wonder if she can figure out what's

01:28:05.039 --> 01:28:05.939
wrong with Bandit.

01:28:06.000 --> 01:28:08.279
Not that I would ever ask a night wing

01:28:08.279 --> 01:28:08.579
for anything.

01:28:08.640 --> 01:28:10.739
He's hungry.

01:28:10.800 --> 01:28:13.739
Moon blurted, and immediately wanted to

01:28:13.739 --> 01:28:14.520
bite her tongue off.

01:28:14.579 --> 01:28:16.380
Winter gave her a cold look.

01:28:16.439 --> 01:28:18.239
No, he isn't.

01:28:18.300 --> 01:28:20.460
I offered him a piece of desert rat this

01:28:20.460 --> 01:28:22.500
morning on the way here, and a bit of

01:28:22.500 --> 01:28:24.840
walrus the day before that, but he didn't

01:28:24.840 --> 01:28:25.319
eat either of them.

01:28:25.380 --> 01:28:28.319
He lifted the dripping wet scavenger up

01:28:28.319 --> 01:28:29.640
and inspected him narrowly.

01:28:29.699 --> 01:28:31.859
The little creature had flopped over and

01:28:31.859 --> 01:28:33.899
curled into a ball again, shivering.

01:28:33.960 --> 01:28:36.779
In fact, he hasn't eaten since Queen

01:28:36.779 --> 01:28:38.760
Glacier called him and gave him to me 4

01:28:38.760 --> 01:28:39.119
days ago.

01:28:39.180 --> 01:28:41.640
I gather that scavengers eat fairly

01:28:41.640 --> 01:28:42.300
infrequently.

01:28:42.359 --> 01:28:45.420
Or maybe it hates you, and is trying to

01:28:45.420 --> 01:28:46.380
starve itself to death.

01:28:46.439 --> 01:28:48.239
Kibley offered helpfully.

01:28:48.300 --> 01:28:49.800
Winter frowned.

01:28:49.859 --> 01:28:51.659
Scavengers don't do that.

01:28:51.779 --> 01:28:53.100
Do they?

01:28:53.159 --> 01:28:55.439
He drinks water when I give it to him.

01:28:55.500 --> 01:29:00.000
Have you, um, Moon faltered as he turned

01:29:00.000 --> 01:29:01.319
his scowl on her?

01:29:01.560 --> 01:29:02.880
Have I what?

01:29:03.000 --> 01:29:04.020
He snapped.

01:29:04.079 --> 01:29:07.020
Sonny's warm scales brushed against moons

01:29:07.020 --> 01:29:09.180
as the sand wing came hurrying in.

01:29:09.239 --> 01:29:11.520
Hello, she said brightly.

01:29:11.579 --> 01:29:14.159
She was smaller than Winter and Kibley

01:29:14.159 --> 01:29:16.859
not much bigger than Moon and Kinkajoo.

01:29:16.920 --> 01:29:19.260
Moon liked the way her mind felt, all

01:29:19.260 --> 01:29:20.699
hopeful and determined.

01:29:20.760 --> 01:29:21.960
What's all the excitement?

01:29:22.020 --> 01:29:24.960
Behind them, Clay started shooing the

01:29:24.960 --> 01:29:25.800
watching crowd away.

01:29:25.859 --> 01:29:27.960
Moon could hear them grumbling about

01:29:27.960 --> 01:29:30.119
wanting to eat the scavenger, or wishing

01:29:30.119 --> 01:29:31.859
there had been a bigger fight, both

01:29:31.859 --> 01:29:33.119
allowed and in their heads.

01:29:33.180 --> 01:29:36.479
Fate speaker told me you brought a pet

01:29:36.479 --> 01:29:38.340
Sonny said, turning to Winter.

01:29:38.399 --> 01:29:39.479
Is that it?

01:29:39.539 --> 01:29:42.239
Aw, I met a couple just about that size

01:29:42.239 --> 01:29:42.659
once.

01:29:42.720 --> 01:29:45.779
Winter arched his long neck and looked

01:29:45.779 --> 01:29:46.920
down his nose at her.

01:29:46.979 --> 01:29:50.220
Queen Glacier said I could have him if I

01:29:50.220 --> 01:29:52.319
agreed to come here, he said

01:29:52.319 --> 01:29:53.039
challengingly.

01:29:53.100 --> 01:29:56.100
If you say I can't keep him, I'm going

01:29:56.100 --> 01:29:56.340
home.

01:29:56.399 --> 01:29:59.880
But you definitely can't have it there

01:29:59.880 --> 01:30:02.279
Sonny pointed out, in a reasonable

01:30:02.279 --> 01:30:02.939
voice.

01:30:03.000 --> 01:30:05.159
A scavenger couldn't possibly survive the

01:30:05.159 --> 01:30:06.600
cold in Glacier's palace.

01:30:06.659 --> 01:30:10.739
Well, Winter hesitated, clearly ruffled

01:30:10.739 --> 01:30:12.960
by the logic of this, I don't care.

01:30:13.020 --> 01:30:14.340
I'll figure out a way.

01:30:14.520 --> 01:30:15.720
I'm keeping him, that's my point.

01:30:15.779 --> 01:30:19.859
I don't mind if you do, but remember, pets

01:30:19.859 --> 01:30:22.140
can be a lot of work, Sonny said

01:30:22.140 --> 01:30:24.300
especially a new pet you're still getting

01:30:24.300 --> 01:30:24.659
used to.

01:30:24.720 --> 01:30:27.239
You should ask Starflight if he has any

01:30:27.239 --> 01:30:28.680
scrolls on the care and feeding of

01:30:28.680 --> 01:30:29.340
scavengers.

01:30:29.399 --> 01:30:32.460
I'm sure I can manage.

01:30:32.579 --> 01:30:33.960
Winter said.

01:30:34.020 --> 01:30:36.180
He started shaking Bandit to get the

01:30:36.180 --> 01:30:37.319
excess water off.

01:30:37.380 --> 01:30:39.659
The little scavenger yelped and tried to

01:30:39.659 --> 01:30:41.699
hang on to one of the dragon's claws

01:30:41.699 --> 01:30:43.680
Moon's talons twitched.

01:30:43.739 --> 01:30:46.079
She wished she were brave enough to grab

01:30:46.079 --> 01:30:47.880
Bandit back and hold him more carefully.

01:30:48.000 --> 01:30:51.119
There's an awful lot we don't know about

01:30:51.119 --> 01:30:53.159
scavengers, Sonny said.

01:30:53.220 --> 01:30:55.979
Maybe your winglet can study him, and

01:30:55.979 --> 01:30:57.720
we'll tell everyone there's a no eating

01:30:57.720 --> 01:31:00.359
scavenger's policy, but you still have to

01:31:00.359 --> 01:31:01.739
take care of him and keep him safe.

01:31:01.800 --> 01:31:05.340
Sunny shifted her wings, and Moon caught

01:31:05.340 --> 01:31:06.659
the worries going through her mind.

01:31:06.720 --> 01:31:09.539
Did that sound bossy enough or too

01:31:09.539 --> 01:31:10.079
bossy?

01:31:10.140 --> 01:31:12.539
Will anyone ever take me seriously as the

01:31:12.539 --> 01:31:13.079
boss of anything?

01:31:13.140 --> 01:31:18.359
No one would dare hurt my scavenger, said

01:31:18.359 --> 01:31:18.840
winter.

01:31:18.899 --> 01:31:20.819
Not if they know he belongs to me.

01:31:20.880 --> 01:31:23.760
Perhaps I should get him a collar, and a

01:31:23.760 --> 01:31:24.420
label of some sort.

01:31:24.539 --> 01:31:27.720
Belongs to the nephew of Queen Glacier.

01:31:27.779 --> 01:31:29.880
Kibley suggested with a straight face.

01:31:29.939 --> 01:31:32.760
Winter nodded thoughtfully, then shot him

01:31:32.760 --> 01:31:33.539
a suspicious look.

01:31:33.600 --> 01:31:37.800
But, Sonny went on, is it all right with

01:31:37.800 --> 01:31:38.699
you, Kibley?

01:31:38.760 --> 01:31:40.920
It'll be in the cave you're sharing, so

01:31:40.920 --> 01:31:42.779
you have to say yes too.

01:31:42.840 --> 01:31:44.760
Otherwise, perhaps we can switch you to a

01:31:44.760 --> 01:31:45.359
different cave.

01:31:45.359 --> 01:31:47.760
If we can find someone who won't mind the

01:31:47.760 --> 01:31:48.239
scavenger.

01:31:48.300 --> 01:31:50.939
Winter cleared his throat importantly.

01:31:51.000 --> 01:31:53.880
Perhaps you have forgotten that Queen

01:31:53.880 --> 01:31:57.239
Glacier is my aunt, he said, as though

01:31:57.239 --> 01:31:59.399
Sonny might be too dim to know such basic

01:31:59.399 --> 01:32:00.180
facts about the world.

01:32:00.239 --> 01:32:04.020
My sister is her niece, and therefore in

01:32:04.020 --> 01:32:04.739
line for the throne.

01:32:04.859 --> 01:32:07.800
Obviously, we should each have a private

01:32:07.800 --> 01:32:08.399
cave.

01:32:08.460 --> 01:32:12.539
That would defeat the purpose, Sonny said

01:32:12.539 --> 01:32:13.140
cheerfully.

01:32:13.199 --> 01:32:15.300
Living together is part of the school's

01:32:15.300 --> 01:32:17.340
mission of getting to know each other.

01:32:17.399 --> 01:32:19.380
Believe me, the sea wing queen's daughter

01:32:19.380 --> 01:32:21.899
is here, and she's sharing a cave too.

01:32:21.960 --> 01:32:25.140
With a lot less grumbling about it, I

01:32:25.140 --> 01:32:27.899
might add, her mind observed, but she

01:32:27.899 --> 01:32:28.979
kept that to herself.

01:32:29.039 --> 01:32:31.800
Besides, we haven't expanded far enough

01:32:31.800 --> 01:32:33.539
into the mountain for everyone to have

01:32:33.539 --> 01:32:34.140
their own cave.

01:32:34.260 --> 01:32:37.439
I don't mind, Kibley said.

01:32:37.500 --> 01:32:39.840
I mean, I don't mind a scavenger.

01:32:39.899 --> 01:32:41.819
His owner is the one I might be allergic

01:32:41.819 --> 01:32:42.060
to.

01:32:42.119 --> 01:32:44.880
Moon tilted her head at Kibley.

01:32:44.939 --> 01:32:47.460
Sonny had given him an easy way to get

01:32:47.460 --> 01:32:49.560
out of sharing Winter's cave, but he

01:32:49.560 --> 01:32:50.159
wasn't taking it.

01:32:50.220 --> 01:32:52.439
He actually wanted to be Winter's

01:32:52.439 --> 01:32:54.420
clawmate, although she couldn't see why.

01:32:54.479 --> 01:32:57.840
It wasn't quite that Kibley liked him, but

01:32:57.840 --> 01:32:59.399
it was a little bit that Kibley wanted

01:32:59.399 --> 01:33:01.859
Winter to like him, and he also kept

01:33:01.859 --> 01:33:04.199
thinking of a pair of big, bad tempered

01:33:04.199 --> 01:33:05.159
sand wings.

01:33:05.220 --> 01:33:08.520
His brother and sister, in comparison to

01:33:08.520 --> 01:33:08.819
winter.

01:33:08.939 --> 01:33:11.640
In addition, he seemed to be teasing

01:33:11.640 --> 01:33:14.340
Winter on purpose as a kind of maneuvered

01:33:14.340 --> 01:33:15.180
to make friends with him.

01:33:15.239 --> 01:33:17.939
All she could really figure out was that

01:33:17.939 --> 01:33:19.739
Kibley was more than a little complicated

01:33:19.739 --> 01:33:20.279
on the inside.

01:33:20.399 --> 01:33:24.659
Don't cause trouble, Sonny reprimanded

01:33:24.659 --> 01:33:24.899
him.

01:33:24.960 --> 01:33:26.880
Sweeping one of her wings up to stop

01:33:26.880 --> 01:33:28.800
winter from lunging at his claw mate.

01:33:28.859 --> 01:33:32.039
I'm not, Kibley protested innocently.

01:33:32.100 --> 01:33:34.979
Someone should probably mention that the

01:33:34.979 --> 01:33:36.720
scavenger's not going to last very long

01:33:36.720 --> 01:33:36.840
though.

01:33:36.960 --> 01:33:38.760
It looks like it's wilting.

01:33:38.880 --> 01:33:41.819
Hey, what if it has some kind of disease

01:33:41.819 --> 01:33:42.119
or something?

01:33:42.180 --> 01:33:44.279
It doesn't.

01:33:44.340 --> 01:33:45.960
Winter growled.

01:33:46.020 --> 01:33:48.300
He held banded up and poked him gently

01:33:48.300 --> 01:33:49.319
with one claw.

01:33:49.380 --> 01:33:51.659
Bandit whimpered, and flopped to the

01:33:51.659 --> 01:33:52.020
side.

01:33:52.079 --> 01:33:55.319
Don't die, Winter thought in a panic.

01:33:55.380 --> 01:33:57.840
He glanced around and caught Moon's eyes

01:33:57.840 --> 01:33:58.079
again.

01:33:58.140 --> 01:34:00.359
She tried to look away, but he was

01:34:00.359 --> 01:34:01.800
already leaning toward her urgently.

01:34:01.859 --> 01:34:03.899
What were you going to say before?

01:34:04.020 --> 01:34:06.899
He demanded about feeding Bandit.

01:34:06.960 --> 01:34:11.340
I, I just, I think I read somewhere that

01:34:11.340 --> 01:34:13.739
they prefer to cook their meat, is all

01:34:13.739 --> 01:34:14.880
she stammered.

01:34:15.000 --> 01:34:17.399
Have you given him anything besides raw

01:34:17.399 --> 01:34:17.699
meat?

01:34:17.760 --> 01:34:20.220
If he's hungry?

01:34:20.279 --> 01:34:22.020
He should eat anything, Winter said

01:34:22.020 --> 01:34:22.560
grumpily.

01:34:22.619 --> 01:34:25.619
I think she's right, Sonny said.

01:34:25.739 --> 01:34:26.760
I have a.

01:34:27.420 --> 01:34:30.420
She paused, and her mind went, friend

01:34:30.420 --> 01:34:33.000
former jailer, dragon who nearly got me

01:34:33.000 --> 01:34:33.239
killed.

01:34:33.359 --> 01:34:36.779
She settled for, I know someone who kept

01:34:36.779 --> 01:34:39.060
a scavenger for years, and I think he

01:34:39.060 --> 01:34:40.140
cooked all her meat for her.

01:34:40.199 --> 01:34:43.560
Well, how am I supposed to cook anything

01:34:43.560 --> 01:34:44.039
for him?

01:34:44.100 --> 01:34:46.020
Winter demanded angrily.

01:34:46.079 --> 01:34:48.779
Ice Wings had frost breath instead of

01:34:48.779 --> 01:34:49.140
fire.

01:34:49.199 --> 01:34:52.199
Moon knew all he could do was freeze the

01:34:52.199 --> 01:34:53.039
scavenger's food.

01:34:53.100 --> 01:34:56.039
Someone will help you, Sonny said.

01:34:56.100 --> 01:34:58.439
That's one of the many great things about

01:34:58.439 --> 01:34:59.939
making friends from other tribes.

01:35:00.000 --> 01:35:03.359
Ha, Winter thought bitterly.

01:35:03.420 --> 01:35:06.840
I would help you, Moon thought, if you'd

01:35:06.840 --> 01:35:07.140
let me.

01:35:07.199 --> 01:35:10.079
You could give him fruit instead.

01:35:10.140 --> 01:35:11.340
Kinkachu suggested.

01:35:11.399 --> 01:35:12.060
Here.

01:35:12.119 --> 01:35:14.880
She scampered over to the fruit pile and

01:35:14.880 --> 01:35:16.560
came back with a talon full of berries

01:35:16.560 --> 01:35:17.279
and a banana.

01:35:17.340 --> 01:35:19.260
Fruit?

01:35:19.319 --> 01:35:21.779
Winter said, wrinkling his snout.

01:35:21.840 --> 01:35:22.859
Disgusting.

01:35:22.979 --> 01:35:26.159
Kinkatoo took a blueberry, which was

01:35:26.159 --> 01:35:27.840
about the size of one of the scavengers

01:35:27.840 --> 01:35:30.000
paws, and poked Bandit's nose with it.

01:35:30.060 --> 01:35:32.399
Here you go, she said.

01:35:32.460 --> 01:35:34.979
Mmm, blueberry, eat that.

01:35:35.039 --> 01:35:38.039
Bandit blinked, and rubbed away the blue

01:35:38.039 --> 01:35:38.760
juice on his face.

01:35:38.819 --> 01:35:41.579
He glanced up at Winter, then over at

01:35:41.579 --> 01:35:43.619
Kingaju, then reached out and took the

01:35:43.619 --> 01:35:45.000
blueberry in both his paws.

01:35:45.060 --> 01:35:47.640
He stared at it for a moment, then bit

01:35:47.640 --> 01:35:48.060
into it.

01:35:48.119 --> 01:35:49.979
He's relieved.

01:35:50.039 --> 01:35:53.819
Moon realized, and wary, but too hungry

01:35:53.819 --> 01:35:54.300
to care.

01:35:54.359 --> 01:35:55.920
Ha!

01:35:55.979 --> 01:35:58.199
Kinkaju said, giving the scavenger

01:35:58.199 --> 01:35:59.159
another blueberry.

01:35:59.220 --> 01:36:00.779
See, Moon was right.

01:36:00.840 --> 01:36:01.500
He's hungry.

01:36:01.619 --> 01:36:05.220
Moon shivered as both Winter and Kibley

01:36:05.220 --> 01:36:06.180
turned to stare at her.

01:36:06.239 --> 01:36:08.399
Winter's eyes even more suspicious than

01:36:08.399 --> 01:36:08.699
before.

01:36:08.760 --> 01:36:10.920
How did you know that?

01:36:10.979 --> 01:36:12.119
he demanded.

01:36:12.180 --> 01:36:15.840
Oh, mother, Moon thought anxiously.

01:36:15.899 --> 01:36:18.600
It's only my 1st day, and I'm already

01:36:18.600 --> 01:36:20.100
making mistakes all over the place.

01:36:20.159 --> 01:36:23.100
How am I supposed to hide what I can do

01:36:23.100 --> 01:36:25.739
with this many dragons watching me, and

01:36:25.739 --> 01:36:27.180
so many ways to mess up.

01:36:27.239 --> 01:36:30.779
Just to guess, she said softly.

01:36:30.840 --> 01:36:34.020
Lucky guess, said Kibley.

01:36:34.079 --> 01:36:36.479
And although his tone was friendly, she

01:36:36.479 --> 01:36:38.460
could hear the chords of wariness echoing

01:36:38.460 --> 01:36:39.119
in his mind too.

01:36:39.180 --> 01:36:41.760
She's smarter than she wants us to know.

01:36:41.819 --> 01:36:43.800
Watch out for night wings.

01:36:43.859 --> 01:36:44.819
That's what Thorn said.

01:36:44.880 --> 01:36:46.319
Never trust them.

01:36:46.439 --> 01:36:48.420
She looks too pretty to be evil.

01:36:48.479 --> 01:36:50.279
But what is she hiding?

01:36:50.399 --> 01:36:54.840
Moon took a step back, and then another, I

01:36:54.840 --> 01:36:55.380
I have to go.

01:36:55.439 --> 01:36:58.260
She whirled and hurried out of the prey

01:36:58.260 --> 01:37:00.720
center cave, feeling everyone watching as

01:37:00.720 --> 01:37:02.279
though their eyes were crawling right

01:37:02.279 --> 01:37:05.220
inside her scales, unspoken whispers

01:37:05.220 --> 01:37:06.239
swirled through her head.

01:37:06.300 --> 01:37:07.680
What's wrong with her?

01:37:07.739 --> 01:37:09.659
Weird as dragon I've ever seen.

01:37:09.720 --> 01:37:11.880
Don't understand why she didn't just eat

01:37:11.880 --> 01:37:12.119
it.

01:37:12.180 --> 01:37:14.100
Hope she's not in my group.

01:37:14.220 --> 01:37:16.380
And threading through all of it.

01:37:16.439 --> 01:37:19.319
The pure icy chill of winter's last

01:37:19.319 --> 01:37:19.800
thought.

01:37:19.859 --> 01:37:22.439
I thought they said the Nightwings

01:37:22.439 --> 01:37:23.579
couldn't read minds after all.

01:37:23.699 --> 01:37:26.760
So why does it seem like she read mine?

01:37:26.819 --> 01:37:31.079
Chapter 5.

01:37:31.380 --> 01:37:34.739
Moon hid in her cave for the rest of the

01:37:34.739 --> 01:37:35.039
day.

01:37:35.100 --> 01:37:37.140
She pretended to be asleep when her

01:37:37.140 --> 01:37:39.720
clawmates came back, even though Kinkaju

01:37:39.720 --> 01:37:41.579
hopefully wrestled around, and dropped

01:37:41.579 --> 01:37:43.739
several scrolls in an effort to wake her

01:37:43.739 --> 01:37:43.859
up.

01:37:43.920 --> 01:37:46.500
The rain wings mind was buzzing with how

01:37:46.500 --> 01:37:48.479
much she wanted to talk about winter and

01:37:48.479 --> 01:37:50.939
Kibley and the scavenger, which was

01:37:50.939 --> 01:37:52.680
exactly what Moon wanted to avoid.

01:37:52.739 --> 01:37:55.739
Eventually, Kinkachu went off to find

01:37:55.739 --> 01:37:57.300
someone named Tamarin.

01:37:57.359 --> 01:38:00.180
Cornelian curled up on her ledge, and

01:38:00.180 --> 01:38:01.380
Moon fell asleep for real.

01:38:01.439 --> 01:38:04.020
The nightmare came immediately this

01:38:04.020 --> 01:38:04.319
time.

01:38:04.380 --> 01:38:07.920
Ever since the comet 6 months ago, she'd

01:38:07.920 --> 01:38:09.899
had the same awful recurring dream

01:38:09.899 --> 01:38:12.119
although the details sometimes changed.

01:38:12.180 --> 01:38:15.420
A roaring avalanche crushed dragonettes

01:38:15.420 --> 01:38:15.960
in its path.

01:38:16.020 --> 01:38:19.199
Lightning split the sky as thunder rolled

01:38:19.199 --> 01:38:20.520
through the jagged peaks.

01:38:20.579 --> 01:38:23.880
Dragons screamed in terror and died all

01:38:23.880 --> 01:38:26.819
around her, their death spasms shuddering

01:38:26.819 --> 01:38:27.300
through her mind.

01:38:27.359 --> 01:38:30.000
That's Jade Mountain.

01:38:30.060 --> 01:38:32.939
She realized for the 1st time, watching

01:38:32.939 --> 01:38:34.859
the earth shake and crack open.

01:38:34.920 --> 01:38:37.800
The fang shaped peaks crumbling into a

01:38:37.800 --> 01:38:39.000
slide of deadly boulders.

01:38:39.119 --> 01:38:41.579
Jade Mountain is falling.

01:38:41.640 --> 01:38:43.020
She couldn't move.

01:38:43.079 --> 01:38:45.539
She couldn't speak, couldn't call for

01:38:45.539 --> 01:38:47.880
help, couldn't warn the dying dragons.

01:38:47.939 --> 01:38:51.359
She could only stand and watch as pain

01:38:51.359 --> 01:38:53.340
pounded through her head, and the world

01:38:53.340 --> 01:38:55.140
was destroyed right under her claws.

01:38:55.199 --> 01:38:57.060
This can't be real.

01:38:57.180 --> 01:38:58.680
It's just a nightmare.

01:38:58.739 --> 01:39:01.619
It's just everything I worry about, and

01:39:01.619 --> 01:39:02.819
everything mother worries about.

01:39:02.880 --> 01:39:05.220
And now probably everything all the

01:39:05.220 --> 01:39:08.340
dragons around me worry about, all rolled

01:39:08.340 --> 01:39:11.279
into my head and exploding, not a vision

01:39:11.279 --> 01:39:13.439
not a prophecy, not the future.

01:39:13.500 --> 01:39:16.619
Please, it can't be the future.

01:39:16.680 --> 01:39:21.060
A sandwing on fire, screaming, cracks

01:39:21.060 --> 01:39:23.579
appearing all along Jade Mountain, opening

01:39:23.579 --> 01:39:25.859
right under the talons of dragons, and

01:39:25.859 --> 01:39:27.420
swallowing them into the ground.

01:39:27.479 --> 01:39:30.300
A dragon who looked like kinkatoo, but

01:39:30.300 --> 01:39:32.699
white with fear, shrieking as falling

01:39:32.699 --> 01:39:33.899
rocks crushed her tail.

01:39:33.960 --> 01:39:35.760
Wake up.

01:39:35.819 --> 01:39:37.619
Moon screamed at herself.

01:39:37.680 --> 01:39:40.619
Talons and teeth, you poor little

01:39:40.619 --> 01:39:41.340
dragonette.

01:39:41.399 --> 01:39:44.819
A huge shape suddenly loomed beside her

01:39:44.819 --> 01:39:46.979
as if another mountain had materialized

01:39:46.979 --> 01:39:47.640
out of the ground.

01:39:47.699 --> 01:39:50.220
She had a lightning fast impression of

01:39:50.220 --> 01:39:53.039
silver and black, and then vast talons

01:39:53.039 --> 01:39:55.319
closed around her claws, and she was

01:39:55.319 --> 01:39:57.180
suddenly yanked out of the nightmare into

01:39:57.180 --> 01:40:01.800
darkness, cool, still, peaceful darkness

01:40:01.800 --> 01:40:04.439
darkness with no voices in her head

01:40:04.439 --> 01:40:07.560
nothing burning or collapsing, no noise

01:40:07.560 --> 01:40:10.079
or catastrophe, or panicking.

01:40:10.140 --> 01:40:14.460
It was, in fact, the 1st silence she'd

01:40:14.460 --> 01:40:16.500
found since arriving at Jade Mountain.

01:40:16.560 --> 01:40:18.720
She wanted to rest in it forever.

01:40:18.779 --> 01:40:22.439
Moon took a deep breath, and then another

01:40:22.439 --> 01:40:25.020
and gradually her heart slowed down.

01:40:25.079 --> 01:40:27.840
This was still a dream, she knew.

01:40:27.899 --> 01:40:31.979
Someone, the other telepath, had lifted

01:40:31.979 --> 01:40:33.960
her out of the nightmare, but she was

01:40:33.960 --> 01:40:34.439
still asleep.

01:40:34.500 --> 01:40:38.340
He'd brought her mind somewhere quiet, and

01:40:38.340 --> 01:40:41.279
she guessed he was waiting nearby, after

01:40:41.279 --> 01:40:42.779
a long, long while.

01:40:42.840 --> 01:40:47.100
There was a voice in the dark, softly, you

01:40:47.100 --> 01:40:48.659
are a mess.

01:40:48.720 --> 01:40:51.899
Moon hunched her wings forward and

01:40:51.899 --> 01:40:52.859
wrapped them around herself.

01:40:52.920 --> 01:40:57.659
She whispered, I know, someone should be

01:40:57.659 --> 01:41:00.779
punished for letting you get this way, the

01:41:00.779 --> 01:41:01.380
voice growled.

01:41:01.439 --> 01:41:05.220
No one knows I'm like this, she said

01:41:05.220 --> 01:41:06.420
shaking her head.

01:41:06.479 --> 01:41:07.859
She hesitated.

01:41:07.979 --> 01:41:10.439
Thank you, for...

01:41:10.439 --> 01:41:12.359
That what you...

01:41:12.359 --> 01:41:16.380
You should be able to do that yourself, he

01:41:16.380 --> 01:41:16.619
said.

01:41:16.680 --> 01:41:18.899
She thought it was a he.

01:41:19.020 --> 01:41:21.119
It was hard to tell sometimes from a

01:41:21.119 --> 01:41:22.619
dragon's internal voice.

01:41:22.680 --> 01:41:24.479
She could sense nothing else about the

01:41:24.479 --> 01:41:24.960
speaker.

01:41:25.020 --> 01:41:27.539
When he was silent, it was as though

01:41:27.539 --> 01:41:28.260
there was nothing there.

01:41:28.319 --> 01:41:31.739
It was sort of creepy, a voice with

01:41:31.739 --> 01:41:32.460
nothing behind it.

01:41:32.520 --> 01:41:35.399
She couldn't sense any emotions or

01:41:35.399 --> 01:41:35.880
thoughts.

01:41:35.939 --> 01:41:40.199
There was just emptiness, as blank as the

01:41:40.199 --> 01:41:41.159
dark walls around her.

01:41:41.159 --> 01:41:44.279
Was this how ordinary dragons felt every

01:41:44.279 --> 01:41:44.579
day?

01:41:44.640 --> 01:41:47.939
That everyone else was just a face, and

01:41:47.939 --> 01:41:50.520
noise on a completely opaque backdrop?

01:41:50.579 --> 01:41:52.739
And all you could know about someone was

01:41:52.739 --> 01:41:54.359
what they chose to show and tell you?

01:41:54.420 --> 01:41:56.399
Why can't you do anything?

01:41:56.460 --> 01:41:57.659
He asked.

01:41:57.720 --> 01:41:59.460
Shield your thoughts.

01:41:59.520 --> 01:42:01.199
Silence the voices.

01:42:01.260 --> 01:42:02.699
By all the moons.

01:42:02.760 --> 01:42:04.619
Why has nobody trained you to step

01:42:04.619 --> 01:42:05.460
outside your visions?

01:42:05.520 --> 01:42:07.979
That wasn't a vision.

01:42:08.039 --> 01:42:09.180
She said quickly.

01:42:09.239 --> 01:42:10.680
It was just a nightmare.

01:42:10.800 --> 01:42:12.779
Really?

01:42:12.840 --> 01:42:15.060
He said, sounding amused.

01:42:15.119 --> 01:42:16.800
That's your opinion.

01:42:16.859 --> 01:42:19.380
She didn't want to talk about the

01:42:19.380 --> 01:42:21.119
possible future destruction of Jade

01:42:21.119 --> 01:42:21.539
Mountain.

01:42:21.600 --> 01:42:24.060
Who trained you?

01:42:24.060 --> 01:42:24.420
she asked.

01:42:24.479 --> 01:42:26.640
My father, he said.

01:42:26.760 --> 01:42:29.399
Oh, said Moon.

01:42:29.460 --> 01:42:31.140
She'd never met her father.

01:42:31.199 --> 01:42:33.539
And secret keeper didn't want to talk

01:42:33.539 --> 01:42:33.960
about him.

01:42:34.020 --> 01:42:36.720
All she would ever say was that he'd died

01:42:36.720 --> 01:42:38.220
when the volcano erupted.

01:42:38.279 --> 01:42:40.500
Moon had only learned his name by reading

01:42:40.500 --> 01:42:41.819
it in her mother's mind.

01:42:41.880 --> 01:42:43.439
Marosir.

01:42:43.560 --> 01:42:45.300
That sounds nice.

01:42:45.359 --> 01:42:48.180
Now he was definitely amused.

01:42:48.239 --> 01:42:50.939
You wouldn't say so, if you'd ever know

01:42:50.939 --> 01:42:51.239
my father.

01:42:51.300 --> 01:42:52.979
What volcano?

01:42:53.039 --> 01:42:55.739
I, I didn't.

01:42:55.739 --> 01:42:57.659
Moon fumbled for an answer.

01:42:57.720 --> 01:43:00.359
He just plucked that information out of

01:43:00.359 --> 01:43:01.260
her passing thought.

01:43:01.319 --> 01:43:03.239
Please, don't do that.

01:43:03.300 --> 01:43:04.800
Do what?

01:43:04.859 --> 01:43:07.500
Ah, invade your privacy.

01:43:07.560 --> 01:43:10.140
Rummage through your memories.

01:43:10.199 --> 01:43:12.119
That would be intrusive of me, wouldn't

01:43:12.119 --> 01:43:12.300
it?

01:43:12.359 --> 01:43:15.300
But isn't it what you do to other dragons

01:43:15.300 --> 01:43:16.439
every moment of the day?

01:43:16.500 --> 01:43:19.020
Not on purpose.

01:43:19.079 --> 01:43:21.359
Moon cried, horrified.

01:43:21.420 --> 01:43:22.500
I don't want to.

01:43:22.560 --> 01:43:24.479
I wish I could stop myself.

01:43:24.539 --> 01:43:27.600
I know it's a curse, and it's terrible

01:43:27.600 --> 01:43:29.399
hearing what everyone is thinking all the

01:43:29.399 --> 01:43:31.439
time, and I don't want to know the future

01:43:31.439 --> 01:43:36.359
especially if, especially if it's, like

01:43:36.359 --> 01:43:37.020
that.

01:43:37.140 --> 01:43:40.319
She turned, spreading one wing into the

01:43:40.319 --> 01:43:42.239
darkness and hit solid rock.

01:43:42.300 --> 01:43:44.819
She spread her claws and reached out

01:43:44.819 --> 01:43:47.340
realizing she was surrounded by rock on

01:43:47.340 --> 01:43:48.060
all sides.

01:43:48.060 --> 01:43:51.479
Don't wish to be ordinary moon watcher.

01:43:51.539 --> 01:43:53.220
Said the voice in the dark.

01:43:53.279 --> 01:43:55.140
Why would you ever wish for that?

01:43:55.199 --> 01:43:57.479
Your powers are a gift.

01:43:57.539 --> 01:43:58.739
Don't you know that?

01:43:58.800 --> 01:44:01.680
She brushed her talons along the rough

01:44:01.680 --> 01:44:03.300
crevices of the wall beside her.

01:44:03.359 --> 01:44:04.439
A gift?

01:44:04.500 --> 01:44:06.600
Not according to my mother.

01:44:06.659 --> 01:44:10.260
How strange, he mused.

01:44:10.319 --> 01:44:13.260
I've never met anyone who would call our

01:44:13.260 --> 01:44:14.399
powers a curse.

01:44:14.460 --> 01:44:17.640
Other powers, yes, but not ours.

01:44:17.699 --> 01:44:22.439
She says, Everyone will hate me if they

01:44:22.439 --> 01:44:24.720
find out what I can do, Moon said.

01:44:24.779 --> 01:44:26.939
Not that they like me very much to start

01:44:26.939 --> 01:44:27.180
with.

01:44:27.300 --> 01:44:30.060
Why does it matter if they hate you?

01:44:30.119 --> 01:44:31.260
He asked.

01:44:31.319 --> 01:44:32.819
You're better than they are.

01:44:32.939 --> 01:44:34.739
You can do amazing things.

01:44:34.800 --> 01:44:37.859
Although, you could do more amazing

01:44:37.859 --> 01:44:39.899
things, if you'd had any training.

01:44:39.960 --> 01:44:42.420
Right now, you're a little pathetic.

01:44:42.479 --> 01:44:46.140
Thanks very much, Moon said, clicking her

01:44:46.140 --> 01:44:46.560
wings back.

01:44:46.619 --> 01:44:48.720
C, he said.

01:44:48.840 --> 01:44:51.060
Just then you felt angry at me.

01:44:51.119 --> 01:44:53.939
Perhaps you could even hate me a little

01:44:53.939 --> 01:44:54.119
bit.

01:44:54.180 --> 01:44:56.340
But you still want to talk to me.

01:44:56.399 --> 01:44:58.260
Because of my power.

01:44:58.319 --> 01:44:59.699
You're drawn to me.

01:44:59.760 --> 01:45:01.680
The same will be true for you.

01:45:01.739 --> 01:45:03.479
Once they know what you can do.

01:45:03.539 --> 01:45:05.460
Dragons will need you.

01:45:05.520 --> 01:45:07.199
You'll be able to do anything you want.

01:45:07.260 --> 01:45:10.199
What if I want to have friends?

01:45:10.260 --> 01:45:12.359
Dragons who aren't scared of me.

01:45:12.420 --> 01:45:15.840
I'll be your friend, he said.

01:45:15.899 --> 01:45:18.119
Entering her thought as if she'd spoken

01:45:18.119 --> 01:45:18.420
aloud.

01:45:18.539 --> 01:45:21.239
I'm not even remotely scared of you.

01:45:21.300 --> 01:45:24.359
She suspected he was joking, but it was

01:45:24.359 --> 01:45:24.779
hard to tell.

01:45:24.840 --> 01:45:28.560
Besides, dragons who are scared of you

01:45:28.560 --> 01:45:29.699
can be very useful.

01:45:29.760 --> 01:45:32.579
Tell me, would you really give up your

01:45:32.579 --> 01:45:33.359
powers if you could?

01:45:33.420 --> 01:45:36.239
Moon thought about everything her mother

01:45:36.239 --> 01:45:37.020
had always told her.

01:45:37.140 --> 01:45:39.359
And then she thought about being able to

01:45:39.359 --> 01:45:40.560
see inside everyone?

01:45:40.619 --> 01:45:42.720
And she thought about the time her

01:45:42.720 --> 01:45:44.460
visions had saved her from a falling

01:45:44.460 --> 01:45:44.819
tree.

01:45:44.880 --> 01:45:46.979
And she thought about what it would be

01:45:46.979 --> 01:45:49.680
like for her mind to really be empty and

01:45:49.680 --> 01:45:52.560
quiet all the time, the way it was now.

01:45:52.619 --> 01:45:54.539
No.

01:45:54.600 --> 01:45:57.720
She admitted finally, I don't want to be

01:45:57.720 --> 01:45:59.579
like other dragons.

01:45:59.640 --> 01:46:02.279
I just want them to not mind that I'm

01:46:02.279 --> 01:46:03.779
different, if that makes sense.

01:46:03.840 --> 01:46:07.319
I want to stop being scared. of being

01:46:07.319 --> 01:46:10.439
found out, of what my visions mean, of

01:46:10.439 --> 01:46:11.640
other dragons, of everything.

01:46:11.699 --> 01:46:16.439
I think, I can help you with that, he

01:46:16.439 --> 01:46:16.739
said.

01:46:16.800 --> 01:46:18.600
Who are you?

01:46:18.659 --> 01:46:20.100
She asked again.

01:46:20.159 --> 01:46:22.260
There was a long pause.

01:46:22.319 --> 01:46:26.880
You really don't know, he said, as if he

01:46:26.880 --> 01:46:27.779
finally believed it.

01:46:27.840 --> 01:46:29.760
How would I?

01:46:29.880 --> 01:46:32.279
She tried pushing back with her mind

01:46:32.279 --> 01:46:34.560
trying to get beyond the blank wall of

01:46:34.560 --> 01:46:36.960
nothing that went with a voice, but she

01:46:36.960 --> 01:46:38.939
didn't know how, and she couldn't find

01:46:38.939 --> 01:46:39.899
anything there at all.

01:46:39.960 --> 01:46:42.060
Are you another student?

01:46:42.060 --> 01:46:43.319
Or a teacher?

01:46:43.380 --> 01:46:45.420
Why haven't I heard you before?

01:46:45.479 --> 01:46:48.060
She touched the rock with one of her

01:46:48.060 --> 01:46:48.600
talons?

01:46:48.659 --> 01:46:50.579
Can we meet in real life?

01:46:50.640 --> 01:46:52.859
I have so many questions.

01:46:52.920 --> 01:46:54.539
How?

01:46:54.600 --> 01:46:56.939
Can you not know about me?

01:46:57.000 --> 01:46:58.199
He asked.

01:46:58.260 --> 01:47:01.020
I can't find any mention of me in your

01:47:01.020 --> 01:47:01.619
mind anywhere.

01:47:01.680 --> 01:47:04.859
There was a very long, thoughtful

01:47:04.859 --> 01:47:05.279
silence.

01:47:05.340 --> 01:47:08.340
You must be another night wing, right?

01:47:08.399 --> 01:47:09.600
Moon guest.

01:47:09.659 --> 01:47:11.760
But then why wouldn't you have spoken to

01:47:11.760 --> 01:47:13.739
me before when we were all back in the

01:47:13.739 --> 01:47:14.100
village?

01:47:14.159 --> 01:47:16.319
Or are you stone mover?

01:47:16.380 --> 01:47:18.479
The dragon Starflight told us about?

01:47:18.539 --> 01:47:21.659
There were only 5 Nightwing students at

01:47:21.659 --> 01:47:22.920
the school, including her.

01:47:22.979 --> 01:47:25.500
She tried to think about who else had

01:47:25.500 --> 01:47:26.220
been sent here.

01:47:26.279 --> 01:47:27.779
Mind reader?

01:47:27.840 --> 01:47:29.640
That would be funny, if her name were

01:47:29.640 --> 01:47:32.220
actually true, but Moon had seen into her

01:47:32.220 --> 01:47:35.220
mind and didn't think so, mighty Claus

01:47:35.220 --> 01:47:37.859
Fearless, or there was one other

01:47:37.859 --> 01:47:39.840
Nightwing Dragonette, a couple of years

01:47:39.840 --> 01:47:42.119
older, who she hadn't met before because

01:47:42.119 --> 01:47:44.100
his parents hated Secret Keeper and

01:47:44.100 --> 01:47:44.640
avoided her.

01:47:44.760 --> 01:47:45.899
It could be him.

01:47:45.960 --> 01:47:48.180
Or fate speaker.

01:47:48.239 --> 01:47:50.699
But fate speaker hadn't had anything like

01:47:50.699 --> 01:47:52.380
this in her wide open mind either.

01:47:52.500 --> 01:47:56.579
The night wings are in the rainforest

01:47:56.579 --> 01:47:56.939
now.

01:47:57.000 --> 01:48:00.119
The voice mused, instead of answering her

01:48:00.119 --> 01:48:00.479
question.

01:48:00.539 --> 01:48:02.399
Interesting.

01:48:02.460 --> 01:48:04.319
I can't reach that far.

01:48:04.380 --> 01:48:07.739
But I don't know any of those dragons, so

01:48:07.739 --> 01:48:09.960
more time is passed than I realized.

01:48:10.020 --> 01:48:12.899
Moon touched her head, puzzled.

01:48:13.439 --> 01:48:14.939
Was he not from the tribe?

01:48:15.000 --> 01:48:16.800
Was he not a night wing at all?

01:48:16.859 --> 01:48:19.619
More time has passed since what?

01:48:19.739 --> 01:48:20.699
she asked.

01:48:20.819 --> 01:48:23.520
What year is it?

01:48:23.579 --> 01:48:24.840
Moon Watcher.

01:48:24.899 --> 01:48:27.720
She breathed a plume of fire into the

01:48:27.720 --> 01:48:30.720
dark, nothing but rock around her, no

01:48:30.720 --> 01:48:33.899
other dragons in sight, How long?

01:48:34.020 --> 01:48:36.539
Since the scorching, he asked.

01:48:36.600 --> 01:48:39.119
Surely this is something you've learned

01:48:39.119 --> 01:48:40.680
from one of your beloved scrolls.

01:48:40.739 --> 01:48:44.100
Moon knew he'd just get the answer from

01:48:44.100 --> 01:48:46.979
her brain anyway. 5,012 years?

01:48:47.039 --> 01:48:48.359
She answered.

01:48:48.420 --> 01:48:49.680
A pause.

01:48:49.739 --> 01:48:51.119
What?

01:48:51.239 --> 01:48:52.500
He roared.

01:48:52.560 --> 01:48:55.319
And then suddenly, with a wrenching twist

01:48:55.319 --> 01:48:57.300
in her stomach, Moon Watcher woke up.

01:48:57.359 --> 01:49:00.180
She lay there on the moss for a moment

01:49:00.180 --> 01:49:02.460
feeling as if she'd been dropped from a

01:49:02.460 --> 01:49:05.220
great height, and plunged into a vat of

01:49:05.220 --> 01:49:07.619
noise, because even in the middle of the

01:49:07.619 --> 01:49:10.020
night, mines were buzzing all around her

01:49:10.020 --> 01:49:13.199
carnelian's dreams were belligerent and

01:49:13.199 --> 01:49:15.899
blood soaked, kinkachoos were sunny and

01:49:15.899 --> 01:49:18.060
colorful, but with a hint of anxiety

01:49:18.060 --> 01:49:20.279
around the edges, that her waking mind

01:49:20.279 --> 01:49:22.619
normally wouldn't allow in.

01:49:22.680 --> 01:49:23.939
What just happened?

01:49:24.000 --> 01:49:25.319
Are you still there?

01:49:25.380 --> 01:49:27.899
She tried reaching out to the mystery

01:49:27.899 --> 01:49:29.579
voice, but there was no answer.

01:49:29.640 --> 01:49:33.060
Along the passage, she could sense 4

01:49:33.060 --> 01:49:35.520
dragonets still awake, each in a

01:49:35.520 --> 01:49:37.920
different cave, their brains circling

01:49:37.920 --> 01:49:38.399
nervously.

01:49:38.460 --> 01:49:40.920
Was one of them the voice who'd been

01:49:40.920 --> 01:49:41.460
talking to her?

01:49:41.460 --> 01:49:43.079
It didn't seem like it.

01:49:43.140 --> 01:49:45.479
They were all preoccupied with their own

01:49:45.479 --> 01:49:47.399
troubles, and none of them were thinking

01:49:47.399 --> 01:49:48.119
about her at all.

01:49:48.180 --> 01:49:51.539
Moon recognized one of them as Sora.

01:49:51.600 --> 01:49:53.699
The Mudwing was doing some kind of

01:49:53.699 --> 01:49:56.340
breathing ritual, where she imagined mud

01:49:56.340 --> 01:49:59.579
pouring over all her fears, burying them

01:49:59.579 --> 01:50:01.739
so all moon could see was ripples.

01:50:01.800 --> 01:50:04.319
Another dragonette was reading, but

01:50:04.319 --> 01:50:05.640
couldn't concentrate on the words.

01:50:05.699 --> 01:50:08.760
He kept thinking, everyone will know, I

01:50:08.760 --> 01:50:09.300
don't belong here.

01:50:09.420 --> 01:50:11.460
Of the sleepers.

01:50:11.520 --> 01:50:13.680
Several of their dreams echoed with

01:50:13.680 --> 01:50:14.699
images from the war.

01:50:14.760 --> 01:50:17.399
A few of them nearly as bad as Moon's

01:50:17.399 --> 01:50:17.819
nightmare.

01:50:17.939 --> 01:50:20.760
She stretched her mind until she found

01:50:20.760 --> 01:50:23.159
Winter and Kibley's cave by the little

01:50:23.159 --> 01:50:25.739
spark the scavenger gave off, even in his

01:50:25.739 --> 01:50:25.920
sleep.

01:50:26.039 --> 01:50:28.619
The ice wing was deep in a sleep without

01:50:28.619 --> 01:50:31.439
dreams, but Kibli's dreams were worried

01:50:31.439 --> 01:50:33.899
in an odd way, and seemed to involve

01:50:33.899 --> 01:50:36.060
other sand wings throwing snakes at him.

01:50:36.119 --> 01:50:37.319
All right.

01:50:37.380 --> 01:50:39.420
So if it wasn't one of the students in

01:50:39.420 --> 01:50:41.340
the sleeping caves, it had to be one of

01:50:41.340 --> 01:50:42.180
the older dragons.

01:50:42.300 --> 01:50:45.060
Maybe it was time to try to find Stone

01:50:45.060 --> 01:50:45.659
Mover.

01:50:45.720 --> 01:50:47.880
If she could track down his cave on her

01:50:47.880 --> 01:50:50.159
own, she could ask if he was the voice in

01:50:50.159 --> 01:50:50.939
her head.

01:50:51.000 --> 01:50:53.460
She stepped over to the doorway as

01:50:53.460 --> 01:50:56.100
quietly as she could, but her tail bumped

01:50:56.100 --> 01:50:58.260
one of the scroll racks, and it rattled

01:50:58.260 --> 01:50:58.859
across the floor.

01:50:58.920 --> 01:51:01.500
Kinkachu made a sleeping noise of

01:51:01.500 --> 01:51:02.220
protest.

01:51:02.220 --> 01:51:05.520
In her dream, Cornelian growled and

01:51:05.520 --> 01:51:07.199
whirled around to face a new attacker.

01:51:07.260 --> 01:51:09.899
Moon held her breath until they were

01:51:09.899 --> 01:51:12.060
still, and then she picked up her map of

01:51:12.060 --> 01:51:15.000
the academy, whisked into the hallway, and

01:51:15.000 --> 01:51:16.619
turned to head deeper into the mountain.

01:51:16.739 --> 01:51:19.859
Her guess was that Stone Mover lived on

01:51:19.859 --> 01:51:22.319
the far side, probably as far from the

01:51:22.319 --> 01:51:23.939
school as he could get, so he wouldn't be

01:51:23.939 --> 01:51:24.359
disturbed.

01:51:24.420 --> 01:51:27.899
She chose the quietest, darkest paths

01:51:27.899 --> 01:51:30.239
breathing out small plumes of flame to

01:51:30.239 --> 01:51:31.260
study the map as she went.

01:51:31.380 --> 01:51:34.619
Stone Mover's K wasn't marked, but there

01:51:34.619 --> 01:51:36.119
were notes on the map about areas to

01:51:36.119 --> 01:51:39.180
avoid, passage too narrow for dragons

01:51:39.180 --> 01:51:42.300
down this way, or swarms of bats here.

01:51:42.359 --> 01:51:45.000
As the voices from the school grew

01:51:45.000 --> 01:51:47.220
quieter, she listened intently for

01:51:47.220 --> 01:51:50.220
anything else, a different mind, or the

01:51:50.220 --> 01:51:52.979
sound of dragon claws, she knew the other

01:51:52.979 --> 01:51:54.420
mind reader could shield his thoughts

01:51:54.420 --> 01:51:56.460
from her, but perhaps if he was

01:51:56.460 --> 01:51:58.859
distracted, or she caught him unguarded

01:51:58.859 --> 01:52:01.439
or if she managed to get closer to him

01:52:01.439 --> 01:52:04.079
well, maybe something would filter

01:52:04.079 --> 01:52:04.260
through.

01:52:04.319 --> 01:52:07.739
And then, in a dark tunnel with a low

01:52:07.739 --> 01:52:10.380
roof, to her surprise, she did hear

01:52:10.380 --> 01:52:10.800
someone.

01:52:10.859 --> 01:52:14.340
Lost another scale today, I think.

01:52:14.399 --> 01:52:16.680
And she didn't come.

01:52:16.800 --> 01:52:20.279
But then, why would she?

01:52:20.340 --> 01:52:24.600
That was followed by a long sound, like a

01:52:24.600 --> 01:52:27.239
mental sigh, and then she heard the echo

01:52:27.239 --> 01:52:29.699
of a real sigh reverberate off the walls

01:52:29.699 --> 01:52:30.119
around her.

01:52:30.119 --> 01:52:32.819
It came from a branch of the tunnel off

01:52:32.819 --> 01:52:33.300
to her right.

01:52:33.359 --> 01:52:35.579
She ducked her head and climbed up the

01:52:35.579 --> 01:52:36.060
passageway.

01:52:36.119 --> 01:52:40.560
This mind's thoughts were very, very slow

01:52:40.560 --> 01:52:43.439
as if they were boulders being pushed up

01:52:43.439 --> 01:52:43.859
a hill.

01:52:43.920 --> 01:52:46.199
Hungry again.

01:52:46.319 --> 01:52:49.079
Nothing I can do about that.

01:52:49.140 --> 01:52:51.359
Moon hesitated.

01:52:51.420 --> 01:52:53.880
He didn't sound like the dragon she'd

01:52:53.880 --> 01:52:55.680
been talking to, but she'd come this

01:52:55.680 --> 01:52:55.920
far.

01:52:55.979 --> 01:52:59.819
She heard scales scraping against stone

01:52:59.819 --> 01:53:02.340
cautiously, she crept around the next

01:53:02.340 --> 01:53:04.380
corner, and there he was.

01:53:04.439 --> 01:53:07.920
A huge dragon lay stretched out against

01:53:07.920 --> 01:53:09.960
the cave wall, with his eyes half

01:53:09.960 --> 01:53:10.439
closed.

01:53:10.500 --> 01:53:13.380
A torch flickered from a post near his

01:53:13.380 --> 01:53:13.619
head.

01:53:13.680 --> 01:53:16.859
His scales were shades of gray and black

01:53:16.859 --> 01:53:20.220
and he looked, weighted down, almost more

01:53:20.220 --> 01:53:21.960
like a statue than a real dragon.

01:53:22.020 --> 01:53:25.020
But real black eyes opened to stare at

01:53:25.020 --> 01:53:25.680
her as she came in.

01:53:25.739 --> 01:53:27.479
Hello?

01:53:27.539 --> 01:53:28.739
She whispered.

01:53:28.800 --> 01:53:31.560
Hmm, he said.

01:53:31.619 --> 01:53:34.199
There was no flash of recognition in his

01:53:34.199 --> 01:53:34.500
eyes.

01:53:34.560 --> 01:53:36.899
Surely if this were the dragon in her

01:53:36.899 --> 01:53:38.100
head, he'd know who she was.

01:53:38.159 --> 01:53:39.960
Are you?

01:53:40.199 --> 01:53:41.939
Are you stone mover?

01:53:42.000 --> 01:53:42.720
she asked.

01:53:42.779 --> 01:53:44.939
He exhaled slowly.

01:53:45.000 --> 01:53:47.579
Without lifting his head, he answered

01:53:47.579 --> 01:53:49.680
Unfortunately.

01:53:49.739 --> 01:53:51.539
Yes.

01:53:51.600 --> 01:53:54.539
I'm Moon Watcher, she said.

01:53:54.600 --> 01:54:00.899
My 1st visitor, from the academy, he

01:54:00.899 --> 01:54:01.500
rasped.

01:54:01.560 --> 01:54:05.100
Apart from Sonny, of course.

01:54:05.159 --> 01:54:10.800
She said I might have other dragons to

01:54:10.800 --> 01:54:13.079
talk to from time to time.

01:54:13.140 --> 01:54:16.800
But there has been no one so far.

01:54:16.859 --> 01:54:19.920
Not even sunny today.

01:54:19.979 --> 01:54:24.239
It's only the 1st day, Moon explained.

01:54:24.359 --> 01:54:26.399
I'm sure someone else will be along soon

01:54:26.399 --> 01:54:29.159
and it was probably a really busy day for

01:54:29.159 --> 01:54:29.819
Sonny.

01:54:29.880 --> 01:54:33.300
Hmm, he said again.

01:54:33.359 --> 01:54:37.020
There was a long pause, and Moon couldn't

01:54:37.020 --> 01:54:38.399
help thinking that for a dragon who

01:54:38.399 --> 01:54:40.560
supposedly longed for company, he

01:54:40.560 --> 01:54:41.819
certainly had very little to say.

01:54:41.880 --> 01:54:44.279
He didn't even have very much to think.

01:54:44.340 --> 01:54:47.340
His mind was slowly revolving back around

01:54:47.340 --> 01:54:48.720
to how hungry he was.

01:54:48.779 --> 01:54:51.359
She couldn't ask him if he'd been talking

01:54:51.359 --> 01:54:54.720
to her in her head, if it wasn't him, and

01:54:54.720 --> 01:54:56.460
she was fairly sure now that it wasn't

01:54:56.460 --> 01:54:58.319
then she'd be giving herself away.

01:54:58.380 --> 01:55:00.840
But maybe she could try a more roundabout

01:55:00.840 --> 01:55:01.199
approach.

01:55:01.260 --> 01:55:04.739
You must know a lot about Nightwings, she

01:55:04.739 --> 01:55:04.979
said.

01:55:05.100 --> 01:55:09.720
Because I'm so old, he creaked.

01:55:09.779 --> 01:55:11.939
I suppose.

01:55:12.060 --> 01:55:15.359
Compared to you, I certainly am.

01:55:15.420 --> 01:55:20.399
Oh, no, I just, I mean, I was wondering

01:55:20.399 --> 01:55:22.199
if there were any mind readers in your

01:55:22.199 --> 01:55:22.800
generation.

01:55:22.920 --> 01:55:24.000
Moon said.

01:55:24.119 --> 01:55:26.760
He let out a kind of grunt that might

01:55:26.760 --> 01:55:27.600
have been a chuckle.

01:55:27.659 --> 01:55:29.520
Ah, no.

01:55:29.579 --> 01:55:33.600
No, the mind readers are all gone.

01:55:33.720 --> 01:55:37.500
For many, many moons now.

01:55:37.560 --> 01:55:41.939
There are always young dragons who hope

01:55:41.939 --> 01:55:44.279
the legendary gifts will reappear.

01:55:44.340 --> 01:55:48.300
But we are far better off without them.

01:55:48.420 --> 01:55:51.479
That kind of power.

01:55:51.600 --> 01:55:54.659
Will ruin your life.

01:55:54.720 --> 01:55:56.939
Moon shivered.

01:55:57.060 --> 01:55:58.920
That was the same thing her mother had

01:55:58.920 --> 01:56:01.260
always said, but this dragon was

01:56:01.260 --> 01:56:01.800
different.

01:56:01.859 --> 01:56:04.500
He knew what he was talking about, because

01:56:04.500 --> 01:56:06.479
now she could see his own curse in his

01:56:06.479 --> 01:56:06.720
mind.

01:56:06.779 --> 01:56:09.600
He was an animus dragon.

01:56:09.659 --> 01:56:12.600
A miserable one who wished he had never

01:56:12.600 --> 01:56:15.060
been hatched, a dragon whose power had

01:56:15.060 --> 01:56:16.199
stolen his one love.

01:56:16.260 --> 01:56:20.640
His hope for a family, his home, and in

01:56:20.640 --> 01:56:23.399
the end, his very scales, which were

01:56:23.399 --> 01:56:25.020
turning to stone around him.

01:56:25.079 --> 01:56:27.420
What she couldn't see was how.

01:56:27.479 --> 01:56:29.760
She couldn't see all the steps and

01:56:29.760 --> 01:56:31.020
choices that had brought him here.

01:56:31.079 --> 01:56:33.479
What if she chose differently?

01:56:33.539 --> 01:56:36.060
Was it possible to have powers and not

01:56:36.060 --> 01:56:36.960
lose everything else?

01:56:37.020 --> 01:56:39.659
The mind reader who'd been speaking to

01:56:39.659 --> 01:56:40.739
her seemed to think so.

01:56:40.800 --> 01:56:42.479
If she could find him?

01:56:42.539 --> 01:56:45.420
If she could learn from him, maybe she

01:56:45.420 --> 01:56:47.039
could avoid stone mover's fate.

01:56:47.100 --> 01:56:49.500
He certainly seemed like a better role

01:56:49.500 --> 01:56:51.060
model than this poor dragon.

01:56:51.119 --> 01:56:53.399
I'm sorry, she said.

01:56:53.460 --> 01:56:54.779
I should get back.

01:56:54.840 --> 01:56:57.180
It was nice to meet you.

01:56:57.239 --> 01:57:00.300
You too.

01:57:00.479 --> 01:57:02.699
He said with another sigh.

01:57:02.760 --> 01:57:05.399
It took Moon a while to find her way

01:57:05.399 --> 01:57:05.579
back.

01:57:05.640 --> 01:57:08.220
She was relieved when she finally saw the

01:57:08.220 --> 01:57:10.680
light of the sleeping caves up ahead, and

01:57:10.680 --> 01:57:12.119
she hadn't been gone as long as she'd

01:57:12.119 --> 01:57:12.359
thought.

01:57:12.420 --> 01:57:15.779
The same 4 dragons were still awake, and

01:57:15.779 --> 01:57:18.479
Carnelian was deep in the same dream, now

01:57:18.479 --> 01:57:19.680
battling an ice wing.

01:57:19.739 --> 01:57:21.960
As she approached her sleeping cave

01:57:21.960 --> 01:57:24.000
something tugged insistently at her

01:57:24.000 --> 01:57:24.239
mind.

01:57:24.359 --> 01:57:26.460
Someone's dream, perhaps?

01:57:26.520 --> 01:57:29.340
But as she let herself follow it, suddenly

01:57:29.340 --> 01:57:30.779
she found she was listening to a

01:57:30.779 --> 01:57:33.359
conversation, as clear as parrot

01:57:33.359 --> 01:57:34.680
shrieking in the rainforest.

01:57:34.739 --> 01:57:38.100
I see how you benefit from this plan, but

01:57:38.100 --> 01:57:39.479
I'm not hearing any guarantees from me.

01:57:39.539 --> 01:57:41.939
Killing is easy enough, but if I kill

01:57:41.939 --> 01:57:43.500
them, how do I know you'll tell me the

01:57:43.500 --> 01:57:43.739
truth?

01:57:43.800 --> 01:57:45.720
And what happens to him if they catch

01:57:45.720 --> 01:57:45.899
me?

01:57:46.020 --> 01:57:48.060
They won't catch you.

01:57:48.180 --> 01:57:51.479
Said a deeper, more slithery voice, just

01:57:51.479 --> 01:57:51.899
do it.

01:57:51.960 --> 01:57:54.659
Do this for me, and I'll give you the one

01:57:54.659 --> 01:57:55.680
thing you want most.

01:57:55.739 --> 01:57:59.819
Moon froze, staring around the deserted

01:57:59.819 --> 01:58:01.020
hallway.

01:58:01.079 --> 01:58:01.680
What was that?

01:58:01.800 --> 01:58:05.100
It wasn't the mind reader's voice, not

01:58:05.100 --> 01:58:06.720
the one moon was starting to think of as

01:58:06.720 --> 01:58:07.199
her friend.

01:58:07.260 --> 01:58:10.380
These voices were close by, and the

01:58:10.380 --> 01:58:12.539
conversation was happening between minds

01:58:12.539 --> 01:58:13.319
not out loud.

01:58:13.380 --> 01:58:15.119
How could that be possible?

01:58:15.180 --> 01:58:17.640
Where there even more telepaths here?

01:58:17.699 --> 01:58:20.579
And why were they talking about killing?

01:58:20.640 --> 01:58:24.060
Moon closed her eyes and tried to listen

01:58:24.060 --> 01:58:24.899
as hard as she could.

01:58:24.960 --> 01:58:27.300
But now she couldn't separate out the

01:58:27.300 --> 01:58:28.619
conversation she was looking for.

01:58:28.680 --> 01:58:31.920
It had either ended, or faded back into

01:58:31.920 --> 01:58:33.840
the confusing, rolling sounds of the

01:58:33.840 --> 01:58:34.619
dreams around her?

01:58:34.680 --> 01:58:36.359
Her eyes popped open.

01:58:36.420 --> 01:58:38.159
That's the answer.

01:58:38.279 --> 01:58:40.199
A dream visitor.

01:58:40.260 --> 01:58:43.680
Someone had been using a dream visitor to

01:58:43.680 --> 01:58:45.180
talk to one of the dragonettes at the

01:58:45.180 --> 01:58:48.119
school, and whoever it was, was planning

01:58:48.119 --> 01:58:48.840
a murder.

01:58:48.899 --> 01:58:53.399
Chapter 6.

01:58:53.460 --> 01:58:58.439
It's morning, Kinkaju sang, pouncing on

01:58:58.439 --> 01:58:59.159
Moon's Tale.

01:58:59.220 --> 01:59:00.479
Isn't that wonderful?

01:59:00.539 --> 01:59:03.899
Moon blinked hazily at the rain wing, who

01:59:03.899 --> 01:59:05.520
was now more pink than yellow, but

01:59:05.520 --> 01:59:06.779
altogether still too bright.

01:59:06.840 --> 01:59:09.060
She felt as if she'd only just fallen

01:59:09.060 --> 01:59:09.899
back to sleep.

01:59:09.899 --> 01:59:12.840
It is the opposite of wonderful.

01:59:12.899 --> 01:59:15.239
Carnelian observed grouchily.

01:59:15.300 --> 01:59:17.340
She flung her wings over her head.

01:59:17.340 --> 01:59:19.260
We get to meet our winglet today.

01:59:19.319 --> 01:59:20.699
Kinkatu cried.

01:59:20.760 --> 01:59:21.840
Isn't that exciting?

01:59:21.899 --> 01:59:24.539
She nudged Moon's tail with her own, and

01:59:24.539 --> 01:59:25.920
then plunked herself down on the moss

01:59:25.920 --> 01:59:28.500
beside her, giving off so much delighted

01:59:28.500 --> 01:59:30.899
energy that Moon felt both contagiously

01:59:30.899 --> 01:59:33.420
uplifted by it, and exhausted at the same

01:59:33.420 --> 01:59:33.600
time.

01:59:33.659 --> 01:59:35.640
What does that mean?

01:59:35.699 --> 01:59:39.359
Our winglet, she asked, hoping perhaps

01:59:39.359 --> 01:59:40.680
you could fall back to sleep while

01:59:40.680 --> 01:59:41.640
Kinkaju explained.

01:59:41.699 --> 01:59:43.859
She missed the feeling of her mother's

01:59:43.859 --> 01:59:45.659
scales at her back while she slept.

01:59:45.720 --> 01:59:47.760
She wondered if her mother missed her

01:59:47.760 --> 01:59:48.180
too.

01:59:48.180 --> 01:59:51.899
Oh, it's the best idea, Kinkachu said.

01:59:51.960 --> 01:59:54.239
I mean, all right, I was a little worried

01:59:54.239 --> 01:59:57.119
about it at 1st because I was like, act

01:59:57.119 --> 01:59:58.500
that means I'll have to make friends with

01:59:58.500 --> 02:00:01.199
a night wing, but now that I know it's

02:00:01.199 --> 02:00:02.819
you, there's nothing more to worry about

02:00:02.819 --> 02:00:05.279
because you're just lovely and not in the

02:00:05.279 --> 02:00:07.319
business of kidnapping or experimenting

02:00:07.319 --> 02:00:08.279
on dragons after all.

02:00:08.399 --> 02:00:09.180
Right?

02:00:09.239 --> 02:00:11.159
She poked Moon's shoulder.

02:00:11.220 --> 02:00:13.319
Right, Moon agreed.

02:00:13.380 --> 02:00:13.920
What?

02:00:13.979 --> 02:00:17.220
We've been organized into 5 winglets.

02:00:17.279 --> 02:00:18.000
Get it?

02:00:18.060 --> 02:00:20.399
It's not a whole wing of dragons, just a

02:00:20.399 --> 02:00:23.100
smaller group, so a winglet.

02:00:23.159 --> 02:00:25.319
Five groups of 7 dragonettes with one

02:00:25.319 --> 02:00:26.340
dragon from each tribe.

02:00:26.399 --> 02:00:28.500
We're in the jade winglet.

02:00:28.560 --> 02:00:30.300
My friend Tamarind is in the gold

02:00:30.300 --> 02:00:30.960
winglet.

02:00:31.020 --> 02:00:33.000
The idea is that we'll work with the

02:00:33.000 --> 02:00:35.039
other 6 dragonettes and get to be friends

02:00:35.039 --> 02:00:36.600
with them, and then we'll totally

02:00:36.600 --> 02:00:39.239
understand all the tribes, and nobody

02:00:39.239 --> 02:00:42.300
will ever want to go to war ever again.

02:00:42.359 --> 02:00:43.020
It's brilliant.

02:00:43.079 --> 02:00:43.619
I love it.

02:00:43.680 --> 02:00:45.779
I can't wait to meet our SeaWing.

02:00:45.899 --> 02:00:46.920
They sound so weird.

02:00:46.979 --> 02:00:48.779
Let's go, let's go, let's go.

02:00:48.899 --> 02:00:52.140
Kinkachu seized Moon's tail and tried to

02:00:52.140 --> 02:00:52.920
drag her to the door.

02:00:52.979 --> 02:00:55.199
All right, I'm coming.

02:00:55.260 --> 02:00:57.659
Moon protested, wriggling free.

02:00:57.720 --> 02:00:59.939
She rubbed her eyes as Kinkachu bounced

02:00:59.939 --> 02:01:02.279
ahead to the door, and then, with a

02:01:02.279 --> 02:01:04.500
horrible jolt, she remembered what she'd

02:01:04.500 --> 02:01:05.340
heard the night before.

02:01:05.399 --> 02:01:09.239
If I kill them, Moon shivered from wings

02:01:09.239 --> 02:01:09.659
to tail.

02:01:09.720 --> 02:01:11.880
If someone at the school was planning a

02:01:11.880 --> 02:01:13.920
murder, she had to tell Sonny or

02:01:13.920 --> 02:01:16.500
Starfight, but she couldn't, not without

02:01:16.500 --> 02:01:17.640
revealing her own secret.

02:01:17.699 --> 02:01:20.039
But I have to warn them.

02:01:20.159 --> 02:01:21.119
Don't I?

02:01:21.180 --> 02:01:24.000
Her mother's favorite rule rang in her

02:01:24.000 --> 02:01:24.359
head.

02:01:24.420 --> 02:01:25.619
Stay secret.

02:01:25.680 --> 02:01:26.819
Stay hidden.

02:01:26.880 --> 02:01:27.779
Stay safe.

02:01:27.840 --> 02:01:29.760
And what if I'm wrong?

02:01:29.819 --> 02:01:32.100
Maybe it was just a dream.

02:01:32.220 --> 02:01:34.319
My dream or someone else's.

02:01:34.380 --> 02:01:37.619
But it had definitely felt like 2 voices

02:01:37.619 --> 02:01:38.399
talking to each other.

02:01:38.460 --> 02:01:42.119
What good is having this power if I can't

02:01:42.119 --> 02:01:43.260
do anything about what I hear?

02:01:43.319 --> 02:01:46.979
I have to go to the library, Moon said.

02:01:47.039 --> 02:01:48.779
She didn't know enough about dream

02:01:48.779 --> 02:01:49.500
visitors.

02:01:49.560 --> 02:01:51.659
All she knew was that there were 3 of

02:01:51.659 --> 02:01:54.300
them, created by an animus dragon 1000s

02:01:54.300 --> 02:01:55.079
of years ago.

02:01:55.260 --> 02:01:57.779
She knew there were sapphires, and she

02:01:57.779 --> 02:01:59.579
knew any dragon who held one could walk

02:01:59.579 --> 02:02:02.039
in another dragon's dreams, and sometimes

02:02:02.039 --> 02:02:03.539
communicate with a dreamer that way.

02:02:03.600 --> 02:02:05.760
But she didn't know who had them now.

02:02:05.819 --> 02:02:08.340
The scrolls she'd read said they were

02:02:08.340 --> 02:02:09.239
lost centuries ago.

02:02:09.300 --> 02:02:11.699
Maybe if she could figure out where they

02:02:11.699 --> 02:02:14.039
were, she could find a way to warn

02:02:14.039 --> 02:02:16.260
Starflight and the others without giving

02:02:16.260 --> 02:02:17.279
away her own power.

02:02:17.340 --> 02:02:21.359
You can't go to the library now, Kinkachu

02:02:21.359 --> 02:02:22.140
said.

02:02:22.199 --> 02:02:23.880
She held up one of the little boards with

02:02:23.880 --> 02:02:25.020
a message chalked on it.

02:02:25.079 --> 02:02:27.359
We have our 1st class with our winglet

02:02:27.359 --> 02:02:27.720
this morning.

02:02:27.779 --> 02:02:30.779
The sound of the bronze metal gong being

02:02:30.779 --> 02:02:33.659
struck reverberated through the halls.

02:02:33.720 --> 02:02:37.500
Bong, bong, bong, 3 times.

02:02:37.560 --> 02:02:39.300
That's the 1st warning.

02:02:39.359 --> 02:02:40.619
Kinkachu said.

02:02:40.680 --> 02:02:41.819
Come on, carnelian.

02:02:41.880 --> 02:02:43.859
She grabbed a scroll from one of the

02:02:43.859 --> 02:02:45.779
racks by the door and threw it at the

02:02:45.779 --> 02:02:46.439
Skywing's head.

02:02:46.560 --> 02:02:48.300
We have to figure out where our meeting

02:02:48.300 --> 02:02:49.079
cave is.

02:02:49.140 --> 02:02:51.659
Cornelian unfolded our wings with a

02:02:51.659 --> 02:02:54.420
majestic scowl. and flowed off the rock

02:02:54.420 --> 02:02:56.520
ledge like a wrathful waterfall.

02:02:56.699 --> 02:02:59.399
She stalked past Kinkaju and Moon without

02:02:59.399 --> 02:03:02.460
a word, and turned left, clearing a path

02:03:02.460 --> 02:03:04.020
through the milling dragonettes with a

02:03:04.020 --> 02:03:04.859
force of her glare.

02:03:04.920 --> 02:03:07.380
Does that mean she knows where we're

02:03:07.380 --> 02:03:07.680
going?

02:03:07.680 --> 02:03:09.119
Kinkatu asked Moon.

02:03:09.239 --> 02:03:11.340
Moon spread her wings with a confused

02:03:11.340 --> 02:03:12.119
shrug.

02:03:12.239 --> 02:03:13.859
Well, one way to find out.

02:03:13.979 --> 02:03:16.439
Kinkachu bounded after the sky wing.

02:03:16.560 --> 02:03:17.939
Moon hesitated.

02:03:18.000 --> 02:03:19.979
She didn't want to be late for her very

02:03:19.979 --> 02:03:22.380
1st class, although getting to the

02:03:22.380 --> 02:03:24.659
library to research dream visitors seemed

02:03:24.659 --> 02:03:27.060
more important, but her teacher and

02:03:27.060 --> 02:03:29.340
clawmates were waiting, and she could

02:03:29.340 --> 02:03:31.260
always go to the library after class.

02:03:31.319 --> 02:03:33.659
And maybe she'd find a way to ask about

02:03:33.659 --> 02:03:35.340
dream visitors during the discussion.

02:03:35.399 --> 02:03:39.000
Reluctantly, she followed Kinkaju, keeping

02:03:39.000 --> 02:03:40.680
her head down to avoid the looks from the

02:03:40.680 --> 02:03:41.460
dragons around her.

02:03:41.520 --> 02:03:43.739
That didn't help to block out their

02:03:43.739 --> 02:03:44.340
thoughts, though.

02:03:44.399 --> 02:03:46.680
The ones who noticed her definitely

02:03:46.680 --> 02:03:48.119
remembered the scene from the praise

02:03:48.119 --> 02:03:48.479
center.

02:03:48.539 --> 02:03:52.199
There were echoing murmurs of, oh, there's

02:03:52.199 --> 02:03:53.579
the weird night wing who doesn't talk.

02:03:53.640 --> 02:03:56.760
And she's the one who tried to steal that

02:03:56.760 --> 02:04:00.840
ice wing scavenger, and seems stuck up

02:04:00.840 --> 02:04:02.880
like all the other night wings. doesn't

02:04:02.880 --> 02:04:03.779
want to make friends with anyone.

02:04:03.840 --> 02:04:07.260
After a minute she realized, though, that

02:04:07.260 --> 02:04:09.000
most of the dragonettes were too busy

02:04:09.000 --> 02:04:10.920
worrying about their 1st class to pay

02:04:10.920 --> 02:04:11.760
much attention to her.

02:04:11.819 --> 02:04:14.039
What will they think of me?

02:04:14.100 --> 02:04:16.260
Was the prevailing whisper in all their

02:04:16.260 --> 02:04:17.340
minds?

02:04:17.399 --> 02:04:18.060
Will anyone like me?

02:04:18.119 --> 02:04:19.920
What if I say something stupid?

02:04:19.979 --> 02:04:22.560
She didn't catch any thoughts about

02:04:22.560 --> 02:04:25.859
strange dreams or murder plots, although

02:04:25.859 --> 02:04:27.060
it was hard to tell through all the

02:04:27.060 --> 02:04:27.359
noise.

02:04:27.420 --> 02:04:30.180
Carnelian went through the great hall

02:04:30.180 --> 02:04:32.279
where fate speaker was sitting proudly

02:04:32.279 --> 02:04:35.039
with a mallet next to the bronze gong, and

02:04:35.039 --> 02:04:36.779
chose a tunnel on the opposite side

02:04:36.779 --> 02:04:37.739
slanting up.

02:04:37.800 --> 02:04:39.720
To Moon Surprise.

02:04:39.779 --> 02:04:42.060
This passageway was lined with plants

02:04:42.060 --> 02:04:44.880
some with pale green heart shaped leaves

02:04:44.880 --> 02:04:46.380
growing out of the cracks in the rock

02:04:46.380 --> 02:04:48.899
others with vigorous bundles of dark

02:04:48.899 --> 02:04:51.600
purple leaves sprouting from small pots

02:04:51.600 --> 02:04:52.140
of dirt.

02:04:52.199 --> 02:04:55.500
Green vines cover the ceiling, winding

02:04:55.500 --> 02:04:57.539
around the green and yellow globe lights

02:04:57.539 --> 02:04:59.819
with long blue flowers hanging down like

02:04:59.819 --> 02:05:00.720
dragon tails.

02:05:00.779 --> 02:05:03.840
A rivulet of silvery water trickled down

02:05:03.840 --> 02:05:06.000
the center of the tunnel, carving a small

02:05:06.000 --> 02:05:07.319
groove in the stone.

02:05:07.380 --> 02:05:09.899
As they went higher, the air felt more

02:05:09.899 --> 02:05:12.539
damp. until finally they ended up in a

02:05:12.539 --> 02:05:15.000
cave, swarming with vines that was open

02:05:15.000 --> 02:05:16.079
to the sky on one side.

02:05:16.140 --> 02:05:19.260
Water cascaded down the back wall like a

02:05:19.260 --> 02:05:22.020
moving, bubbling tapestry, pouring into a

02:05:22.020 --> 02:05:23.760
small pool that fed into the stream in

02:05:23.760 --> 02:05:24.119
the tunnel.

02:05:24.180 --> 02:05:27.600
Tsunami sat on the ledge with the morning

02:05:27.600 --> 02:05:30.300
sun shining behind her, grinning at them

02:05:30.300 --> 02:05:30.779
as they came in.

02:05:30.840 --> 02:05:33.600
Her royal blue scales looked as if they

02:05:33.600 --> 02:05:34.739
were made of melted sky.

02:05:34.800 --> 02:05:39.000
About time, she thought, her tail shifted

02:05:39.000 --> 02:05:40.979
rustling the trails of leaves that

02:05:40.979 --> 02:05:43.020
spilled across the floor and out onto the

02:05:43.020 --> 02:05:43.500
mountainside.

02:05:43.619 --> 02:05:46.619
My own fault, forgetting up at the crack

02:05:46.619 --> 02:05:48.539
of dawn, but really, it's time to get

02:05:48.539 --> 02:05:48.899
started.

02:05:49.020 --> 02:05:49.800
Let's go.

02:05:49.920 --> 02:05:51.840
Moon ducked her head.

02:05:51.899 --> 02:05:53.819
There was something about the sea wing

02:05:53.819 --> 02:05:55.680
that made her nervous, and it was only

02:05:55.680 --> 02:05:57.479
partly the fact that her thoughts were so

02:05:57.479 --> 02:05:58.079
loud.

02:05:58.140 --> 02:06:03.119
Bong, bong, went the gong, only twice

02:06:03.119 --> 02:06:03.600
this time.

02:06:03.659 --> 02:06:06.119
Hello, tsunami said.

02:06:06.180 --> 02:06:07.619
Welcome to your 1st class.

02:06:07.680 --> 02:06:09.479
Nice work finding the right cave.

02:06:09.539 --> 02:06:12.539
Cornelian, Kinkachu, and Moon Watcher

02:06:12.539 --> 02:06:12.779
right?

02:06:12.840 --> 02:06:14.399
Oh, be impressed.

02:06:14.460 --> 02:06:16.739
I've been practicing so hard to memorize

02:06:16.739 --> 02:06:18.840
all of you. 35 new names.

02:06:18.899 --> 02:06:21.779
Easy as cows for Starflight, but a whole

02:06:21.779 --> 02:06:23.520
lot trickier for me and Clay, believe

02:06:23.520 --> 02:06:24.000
me.

02:06:24.060 --> 02:06:26.100
I mean, it helps that I knew some of you

02:06:26.100 --> 02:06:26.699
before, of course.

02:06:26.760 --> 02:06:29.699
Like me, Kinkachu trilled.

02:06:29.760 --> 02:06:31.380
Tail Kisser.

02:06:31.500 --> 02:06:33.060
Cornelian thought grumpily.

02:06:33.119 --> 02:06:35.760
Someone moved in the tunnel behind Moon

02:06:35.760 --> 02:06:38.279
and she turned to see a smallish mud wing

02:06:38.279 --> 02:06:40.380
coming into the cave with a sea wing

02:06:40.380 --> 02:06:40.920
close behind him.

02:06:40.979 --> 02:06:43.439
She didn't recognize the mud wing. but

02:06:43.439 --> 02:06:44.159
the sea wing.

02:06:44.220 --> 02:06:47.640
Turtle, tsunami said enthusiastically.

02:06:47.699 --> 02:06:48.899
Oh, good.

02:06:48.960 --> 02:06:51.000
I asked to be given your winglet first.

02:06:51.060 --> 02:06:53.399
Hey, everyone, this is my brother.

02:06:53.520 --> 02:06:55.140
Can you believe I have a brother?

02:06:55.199 --> 02:06:57.119
Or a 1000000 brothers, apparently?

02:06:57.180 --> 02:06:59.399
But I'm just assuming this one's the best

02:06:59.399 --> 02:07:00.359
since he's here right now.

02:07:00.420 --> 02:07:03.420
She slung one wing over his shoulders and

02:07:03.420 --> 02:07:04.680
gave him a toothy grin.

02:07:04.739 --> 02:07:06.479
Turtle smiled back at her.

02:07:06.539 --> 02:07:07.739
It's true.

02:07:07.800 --> 02:07:08.640
I am.

02:07:08.699 --> 02:07:11.699
Moon studied the green Sea Wing

02:07:11.699 --> 02:07:14.100
Dragonette, remembering the vision she'd

02:07:14.100 --> 02:07:16.319
had when she 1st saw him, the vision of

02:07:16.319 --> 02:07:18.899
him attacking anemone, could he be the

02:07:18.899 --> 02:07:20.039
one from the dream last night?

02:07:20.100 --> 02:07:22.319
Was someone trying to convince him to

02:07:22.319 --> 02:07:23.100
kill his sisters?

02:07:23.159 --> 02:07:26.279
She tried cautiously to reach into his

02:07:26.279 --> 02:07:28.439
mind, which she didn't exactly know how

02:07:28.439 --> 02:07:29.340
to do.

02:07:29.399 --> 02:07:31.319
It was like trying to listen harder in

02:07:31.319 --> 02:07:31.920
one direction.

02:07:31.979 --> 02:07:35.100
Most dragons were constantly broadcasting

02:07:35.100 --> 02:07:37.500
their thoughts and feelings, but turtles

02:07:37.500 --> 02:07:40.199
still had that odd quiet around him, as

02:07:40.199 --> 02:07:41.340
though his brain were wrapped in

02:07:41.340 --> 02:07:41.760
blankets.

02:07:41.819 --> 02:07:44.819
It was almost peaceful, leaning into his

02:07:44.819 --> 02:07:47.159
thoughts, but also a little terrifying

02:07:47.159 --> 02:07:49.800
because Moon had absolutely no idea what

02:07:49.800 --> 02:07:50.699
was going on in there.

02:07:50.760 --> 02:07:53.640
Is there any chance he's the voice in my

02:07:53.640 --> 02:07:53.880
head?

02:07:53.939 --> 02:07:56.640
Are there any sea wing telepaths?

02:07:56.760 --> 02:07:58.560
If he can shield his thoughts?

02:07:58.619 --> 02:08:00.359
Maybe he can send them too.

02:08:00.420 --> 02:08:01.979
Mystery voice?

02:08:02.039 --> 02:08:03.539
Are you, turtle?

02:08:03.600 --> 02:08:06.539
He called her staring at him and smiled

02:08:06.539 --> 02:08:08.399
but there was no clear answer in his

02:08:08.399 --> 02:08:08.819
expression.

02:08:08.880 --> 02:08:12.659
This is my call mate, Umber, Turtle said

02:08:12.659 --> 02:08:14.460
turning to the little brown mudwing.

02:08:14.520 --> 02:08:17.640
Oh, Kinkaju said, Clay's brother.

02:08:17.699 --> 02:08:21.239
Sora's brother, Moon thought, and

02:08:21.239 --> 02:08:23.460
realized she'd been hoping Sora would be

02:08:23.460 --> 02:08:24.119
in their winglet.

02:08:24.180 --> 02:08:27.359
That's right, Umber said.

02:08:27.420 --> 02:08:29.399
His mind rippled with warmth and

02:08:29.399 --> 02:08:31.079
anticipation in a way that matched

02:08:31.079 --> 02:08:31.979
kinkajoo's.

02:08:32.039 --> 02:08:35.220
Moon could also sense relief, almost an

02:08:35.220 --> 02:08:37.739
ongoing permanent state of relief, that

02:08:37.739 --> 02:08:39.119
seemed to have to do with not being at

02:08:39.119 --> 02:08:39.600
war anymore.

02:08:39.659 --> 02:08:43.140
Ooh, the Jade Winglet is so cool

02:08:43.140 --> 02:08:44.939
Kinkachoo said happily.

02:08:45.000 --> 02:08:47.100
I wonder who will get for our ice wing

02:08:47.100 --> 02:08:47.939
and sand wing.

02:08:48.000 --> 02:08:49.319
Does Sunny have any sisters?

02:08:49.380 --> 02:08:52.020
But Moon could now sense the last 2

02:08:52.020 --> 02:08:54.420
dragonettes coming up the tunnel, and her

02:08:54.420 --> 02:08:55.020
heart dropped.

02:08:55.079 --> 02:08:58.979
Actually, tsunami said, after yesterday

02:08:58.979 --> 02:09:00.960
we decided to switch a couple of dragons

02:09:00.960 --> 02:09:03.359
around since you guys seemed like a good

02:09:03.359 --> 02:09:03.720
match.

02:09:03.779 --> 02:09:06.720
She flicked her tail at Winter and Kibley

02:09:06.720 --> 02:09:07.800
as they stepped into the cave.

02:09:07.859 --> 02:09:10.439
You've already met, you're all interested

02:09:10.439 --> 02:09:11.399
in scavengers.

02:09:11.460 --> 02:09:13.140
We think you'll fit well together.

02:09:13.199 --> 02:09:17.640
Went the warning bell one final time.

02:09:17.699 --> 02:09:21.119
Moon stared into winter's cold blue eyes

02:09:21.119 --> 02:09:23.340
and felt as if ice was traveling across

02:09:23.340 --> 02:09:25.020
her scales to her wingtips.

02:09:25.079 --> 02:09:27.119
How could she hide from him if they were

02:09:27.119 --> 02:09:28.500
constantly in class together?

02:09:28.560 --> 02:09:31.500
It's her, he thought.

02:09:31.560 --> 02:09:34.079
And an echo came from Kibble's mind as

02:09:34.079 --> 02:09:34.260
well.

02:09:34.319 --> 02:09:35.819
It's her.

02:09:35.880 --> 02:09:39.720
Now I can keep an eye on her, thought

02:09:39.720 --> 02:09:40.079
one.

02:09:40.140 --> 02:09:43.079
Now I can figure her out, thought the

02:09:43.079 --> 02:09:43.319
other.

02:09:43.380 --> 02:09:45.779
Did she just get more tense as we came

02:09:45.779 --> 02:09:46.020
in?

02:09:46.079 --> 02:09:48.899
Is it winter she's worried about, or both

02:09:48.899 --> 02:09:49.199
of us?

02:09:49.260 --> 02:09:51.539
She looks a little scared of everyone.

02:09:51.600 --> 02:09:53.760
But also likes she can take care of

02:09:53.760 --> 02:09:54.060
herself.

02:09:54.180 --> 02:09:56.340
If everyone would just leave her alone.

02:09:56.399 --> 02:09:58.920
She likes that rain wing, though, her

02:09:58.920 --> 02:10:00.659
claw mate, the one who's all heart.

02:10:00.720 --> 02:10:02.699
I wonder if I can get her to like me.

02:10:02.760 --> 02:10:05.880
I'll find out why she knows so much about

02:10:05.880 --> 02:10:06.899
scavengers.

02:10:07.020 --> 02:10:07.979
Winter thought.

02:10:08.039 --> 02:10:12.000
I'll find out everything about her I

02:10:12.000 --> 02:10:12.600
could protect her.

02:10:12.659 --> 02:10:13.560
Would she want that?

02:10:13.619 --> 02:10:14.939
Kibley wondered.

02:10:15.060 --> 02:10:16.260
It's what I do best.

02:10:16.319 --> 02:10:18.359
It's what I've done for Thorn since I was

02:10:18.359 --> 02:10:18.600
three.

02:10:18.659 --> 02:10:21.239
She said I need to find something else to

02:10:21.239 --> 02:10:23.579
do with myself, that I'm wasting my

02:10:23.579 --> 02:10:25.800
potential, and she has enough dragons to

02:10:25.800 --> 02:10:27.960
protect her, as if I trust any of them.

02:10:28.020 --> 02:10:30.539
Wonder what Thorn would think of Moon?

02:10:30.600 --> 02:10:31.680
Is she a threat?

02:10:31.739 --> 02:10:34.500
Or the kind of dragonette the outlaws are

02:10:34.500 --> 02:10:35.159
sworn to protect?

02:10:35.220 --> 02:10:37.680
Why haven't I figured her out yet?

02:10:37.739 --> 02:10:41.520
And then, more softly, but chiming from

02:10:41.520 --> 02:10:42.779
somewhere inside both of them.

02:10:42.840 --> 02:10:45.300
I wonder what she thinks of me.

02:10:45.359 --> 02:10:47.100
She didn't know.

02:10:47.159 --> 02:10:49.800
She wasn't sure quite what she thought of

02:10:49.800 --> 02:10:50.399
either of them.

02:10:50.460 --> 02:10:52.979
She kind of wanted to hide from them, but

02:10:52.979 --> 02:10:53.939
she also wanted to keep listening.

02:10:54.000 --> 02:10:56.819
It was hard, actually, to have any

02:10:56.819 --> 02:10:58.380
thoughts of her own when so many others

02:10:58.380 --> 02:11:00.539
were crowding in all at once.

02:11:00.600 --> 02:11:02.579
From across the cave, Kinkaju was

02:11:02.579 --> 02:11:05.460
brimming with ee, the ominous, handsome

02:11:05.460 --> 02:11:07.140
glittery, brooding, ice wing.

02:11:07.199 --> 02:11:10.920
Umber thought quietly, wow, he's

02:11:10.920 --> 02:11:11.399
gorgeous.

02:11:11.520 --> 02:11:14.039
And Cornelian sat down with her wings

02:11:14.039 --> 02:11:15.960
folded and scowled at her talons.

02:11:16.020 --> 02:11:17.100
Bah.

02:11:17.159 --> 02:11:17.939
I hate everyone.

02:11:18.000 --> 02:11:20.159
All of these dragons would be useless in

02:11:20.159 --> 02:11:20.399
battle.

02:11:20.460 --> 02:11:23.699
Moon found herself edging a little closer

02:11:23.699 --> 02:11:26.100
to Turtle, who was like a small island of

02:11:26.100 --> 02:11:28.020
peace in the middle of the cross currents

02:11:28.079 --> 02:11:30.960
8 dragons in one small cave.

02:11:31.079 --> 02:11:32.520
All thinking at the same time.

02:11:32.579 --> 02:11:35.100
How is she going to get through this?

02:11:35.159 --> 02:11:37.800
Let's go around and introduce ourselves

02:11:37.800 --> 02:11:39.000
Tsunami said.

02:11:39.119 --> 02:11:41.100
I mean, maybe it's unnecessary, but

02:11:41.100 --> 02:11:42.779
that's what Sonny said to do.

02:11:42.840 --> 02:11:44.399
And then she said, I probably wouldn't

02:11:44.399 --> 02:11:46.979
listen to her anyway, so I am proving her

02:11:46.979 --> 02:11:47.399
wrong.

02:11:47.460 --> 02:11:48.180
So there.

02:11:48.239 --> 02:11:50.699
I'm tsunami if anyone didn't know.

02:11:50.760 --> 02:11:52.859
I was going to give myself a title like

02:11:52.859 --> 02:11:54.659
commander of recruitment.

02:11:54.720 --> 02:11:57.000
But then for some reason, everyone voted

02:11:57.000 --> 02:11:58.859
that I would be terrible at recruiting

02:11:58.859 --> 02:12:00.659
whatever that is all about.

02:12:00.720 --> 02:12:03.239
So they made me head of school instead.

02:12:03.300 --> 02:12:05.819
So, I'm pretty much the boss.

02:12:05.880 --> 02:12:07.739
And I'm running your 1st small group

02:12:07.739 --> 02:12:10.140
discussion class, which was Glory's big

02:12:10.140 --> 02:12:12.119
idea, so I figure we'll figure it out

02:12:12.119 --> 02:12:12.479
together.

02:12:12.539 --> 02:12:13.979
Any questions?

02:12:14.039 --> 02:12:16.979
Yeah, said Cornelian.

02:12:17.039 --> 02:12:18.600
Are we stuck with this group?

02:12:18.659 --> 02:12:21.960
That's not quite how I would put it, said

02:12:21.960 --> 02:12:23.220
tsunami, but yes.

02:12:23.340 --> 02:12:27.600
What if we would prefer to be in a group

02:12:27.600 --> 02:12:30.600
with other ice wings, Winter asked, such

02:12:30.600 --> 02:12:31.199
as my sister?

02:12:31.260 --> 02:12:34.319
That's not how the winglets are set up

02:12:34.319 --> 02:12:36.600
Tsunami said, but you'll be in some

02:12:36.600 --> 02:12:38.399
bigger group classes with her and have

02:12:38.399 --> 02:12:39.720
plenty of time to make other friends as

02:12:39.720 --> 02:12:40.380
well.

02:12:40.439 --> 02:12:42.420
I love our winglet.

02:12:42.479 --> 02:12:43.979
Kinkachu volunteered.

02:12:44.039 --> 02:12:45.899
When do we eat?

02:12:46.020 --> 02:12:47.159
Umber asked.

02:12:47.279 --> 02:12:49.739
Just kidding. pretending to be clay.

02:12:49.800 --> 02:12:52.739
He grinned, then shot a look at Kibley.

02:12:52.800 --> 02:12:54.119
Did he think that was funny?

02:12:54.180 --> 02:12:55.680
I hope that was funny.

02:12:55.739 --> 02:12:57.180
Did I sound like an idiot?

02:12:57.239 --> 02:13:00.720
Oh, it's Kibley, he noticed.

02:13:00.779 --> 02:13:02.039
Moon realized.

02:13:02.100 --> 02:13:03.539
Not winter.

02:13:03.600 --> 02:13:06.539
It was impossible to ignore how handsome

02:13:06.539 --> 02:13:08.880
Winter was, especially with Kinkachu

02:13:08.880 --> 02:13:11.279
thinking about it all the time, but it

02:13:11.279 --> 02:13:12.899
was true that Kibley was good looking too

02:13:12.899 --> 02:13:15.359
in a warmer way, now that she looked.

02:13:15.420 --> 02:13:17.579
His thoughts were so distractingly

02:13:17.579 --> 02:13:19.560
fascinating that she hadn't noticed it

02:13:19.560 --> 02:13:19.800
before.

02:13:19.859 --> 02:13:21.479
Ha!

02:13:21.539 --> 02:13:24.359
Actually, I brought food, tsunami said.

02:13:24.420 --> 02:13:26.819
She cleared aside a tangle of vines and

02:13:26.819 --> 02:13:29.279
revealed a carved stone bowl full of fish

02:13:29.279 --> 02:13:30.960
which she set in the middle of the

02:13:30.960 --> 02:13:31.140
floor.

02:13:31.260 --> 02:13:32.460
Help yourselves.

02:13:32.520 --> 02:13:36.060
Awesome, said Turtle.

02:13:36.119 --> 02:13:39.119
Yuck, said Kinkachoo.

02:13:39.180 --> 02:13:41.100
I'll wait and have a banana later

02:13:41.100 --> 02:13:41.340
thanks.

02:13:41.399 --> 02:13:44.460
Moon took a step toward the fish, but so

02:13:44.460 --> 02:13:46.500
did Winter, and she jumped back to stay

02:13:46.500 --> 02:13:47.039
out of his way.

02:13:47.100 --> 02:13:49.500
He gave her a curious look.

02:13:49.560 --> 02:13:51.300
She's frightened of me.

02:13:51.359 --> 02:13:53.579
Mother would be so proud.

02:13:53.640 --> 02:13:57.119
He turned away, skewing a fish on one of

02:13:57.119 --> 02:13:57.600
his claws.

02:13:57.659 --> 02:14:00.420
I guess I did threaten to slice off her

02:14:00.420 --> 02:14:01.020
face.

02:14:01.079 --> 02:14:04.979
Here, Kibley said, taking a fish and

02:14:04.979 --> 02:14:07.260
handing it to Moon, she could feel the

02:14:07.260 --> 02:14:09.359
heat rising from his sand yellow scales

02:14:09.359 --> 02:14:10.199
as she accepted it.

02:14:10.260 --> 02:14:11.819
Thanks.

02:14:11.880 --> 02:14:12.840
She said.

02:14:12.899 --> 02:14:15.300
He smiled crookedly at her, thinking

02:14:15.300 --> 02:14:17.399
rushing busy thoughts about what else he

02:14:17.399 --> 02:14:19.380
could do to get her to like him, and

02:14:19.380 --> 02:14:21.000
trying to fit her into a pattern of other

02:14:21.000 --> 02:14:22.319
dragons he'd known before.

02:14:22.380 --> 02:14:25.020
She had never met a dragon who had so

02:14:25.020 --> 02:14:25.920
many thoughts a minute.

02:14:26.039 --> 02:14:28.500
Consciously he was thinking about her.

02:14:28.560 --> 02:14:30.960
Unconsciously, he was observing that

02:14:30.960 --> 02:14:33.720
carnelian was the most battle scarred, and

02:14:33.720 --> 02:14:36.060
probably the most unpredictable dragon in

02:14:36.060 --> 02:14:38.399
a cave, so he was angling his tail toward

02:14:38.399 --> 02:14:41.220
her, just as a precaution, and part of

02:14:41.220 --> 02:14:42.600
him was also remembering what he knew

02:14:42.600 --> 02:14:44.939
about tsunami and the kinds of dragons

02:14:44.939 --> 02:14:47.220
she liked, while yet another part was

02:14:47.220 --> 02:14:48.479
planning to go out and survey the

02:14:48.479 --> 02:14:48.960
mountains later.

02:14:49.020 --> 02:14:52.140
It was almost like reading a scroll, or

02:14:52.140 --> 02:14:53.939
maybe like reading 5 scrolls at once.

02:14:54.000 --> 02:14:56.159
Moon wished she could escape his

02:14:56.159 --> 02:14:57.840
attention and just listen to him think

02:14:57.840 --> 02:14:58.319
for a while.

02:14:58.380 --> 02:15:02.399
Right, introductions, said tsunami.

02:15:02.460 --> 02:15:04.020
Cornelian, want to go first?

02:15:04.079 --> 02:15:07.560
No. muttered the Skywings brain.

02:15:07.619 --> 02:15:09.180
She heaved a deep sigh.

02:15:09.300 --> 02:15:11.279
I'm carnelian.

02:15:11.340 --> 02:15:12.779
There was a pause.

02:15:12.899 --> 02:15:14.819
Anything else?

02:15:14.880 --> 02:15:16.199
Tsunami prompted.

02:15:16.260 --> 02:15:17.819
What should we know about you?

02:15:17.880 --> 02:15:19.260
Family, favorite color?

02:15:19.380 --> 02:15:19.680
Anything?

02:15:19.739 --> 02:15:22.920
Carnelian growled, low in her throat.

02:15:23.039 --> 02:15:26.520
I'm a loyal subject of Queen Ruby, she

02:15:26.520 --> 02:15:27.000
said finally.

02:15:27.060 --> 02:15:29.520
I'm in the camp that believes Queen

02:15:29.520 --> 02:15:32.220
Scarlet is dead, and if she isn't, I'd be

02:15:32.220 --> 02:15:34.020
happy to kill her myself to protect my

02:15:34.020 --> 02:15:34.859
queen's throne.

02:15:34.920 --> 02:15:37.560
I'm here because my queen told me to be

02:15:37.560 --> 02:15:39.720
although I should be training with my

02:15:39.720 --> 02:15:42.359
battalion and guarding her palace, not

02:15:42.359 --> 02:15:44.279
eating slimy, wet fish with a bunch of

02:15:44.279 --> 02:15:45.600
spineless dragonettes.

02:15:45.659 --> 02:15:47.699
She founded them all for a moment.

02:15:47.819 --> 02:15:50.100
And my favorite color is red.

02:15:50.159 --> 02:15:54.600
Insecure, Kibley thought, studying

02:15:54.600 --> 02:15:55.260
carnelian.

02:15:55.319 --> 02:15:57.180
Only comfortable when she's fighting.

02:15:57.239 --> 02:16:00.239
Worried will think she's dumb, and that

02:16:00.239 --> 02:16:02.579
Queen Ruby will find out she's dumb, and

02:16:02.579 --> 02:16:04.319
all our chances of advancing to general

02:16:04.319 --> 02:16:05.399
one day will be ruined.

02:16:05.520 --> 02:16:08.039
Is she as stupid as she thinks she is?

02:16:08.100 --> 02:16:09.359
Have to wait and see.

02:16:09.420 --> 02:16:11.399
Moon blinked at him.

02:16:11.460 --> 02:16:14.100
None of that was obvious, but it was all

02:16:14.100 --> 02:16:15.840
there in the less conscious parts of

02:16:15.840 --> 02:16:16.739
Carnelian's mind.

02:16:16.800 --> 02:16:17.939
He was right.

02:16:18.000 --> 02:16:19.560
How could he know all that?

02:16:19.619 --> 02:16:22.500
He couldn't be a mind reader, surely, or

02:16:22.500 --> 02:16:23.399
she'd be able to tell.

02:16:23.460 --> 02:16:25.859
Had he figured all that out just?

02:16:25.859 --> 02:16:27.659
By noticing?

02:16:27.720 --> 02:16:30.539
All right, said tsunami.

02:16:30.600 --> 02:16:31.380
Good to know.

02:16:31.439 --> 02:16:32.579
Kinkaju?

02:16:32.639 --> 02:16:35.279
Bright flares of yellow and purple shot

02:16:35.279 --> 02:16:36.839
across the rain wings scales.

02:16:36.899 --> 02:16:38.159
Oh, sure.

02:16:38.520 --> 02:16:39.540
I'm Kinkachu.

02:16:39.600 --> 02:16:41.639
I'm a rain wing, and I've never met any

02:16:41.639 --> 02:16:44.159
sea wings or sand wings or ice wings

02:16:44.159 --> 02:16:44.399
before.

02:16:44.459 --> 02:16:47.099
I mean, apart from the dragonettes of

02:16:47.099 --> 02:16:48.719
destiny, of course, because I'm really

02:16:48.719 --> 02:16:49.979
good friends with them.

02:16:50.040 --> 02:16:52.620
I'm excited to learn how to read, and I

02:16:52.620 --> 02:16:54.120
want to know everything about all your

02:16:54.120 --> 02:16:54.719
tribes.

02:16:54.780 --> 02:16:57.299
And I think the school is the best idea

02:16:57.299 --> 02:16:58.139
in the world.

02:16:58.200 --> 02:17:00.840
And my favorite color is yellow.

02:17:00.899 --> 02:17:04.440
Of course it is, Carnelian said.

02:17:04.500 --> 02:17:07.020
Should I tell them about being a night

02:17:07.020 --> 02:17:07.860
wing prisoner?

02:17:07.920 --> 02:17:09.239
Kinkachu wondered.

02:17:09.360 --> 02:17:11.459
Now, that's a little grim for 1st

02:17:11.459 --> 02:17:11.940
impressions.

02:17:12.000 --> 02:17:16.260
Your turn, Kinkachu said, Bumping Moon's

02:17:16.260 --> 02:17:16.860
side.

02:17:16.920 --> 02:17:19.020
A flurry of happy thoughts leaped through

02:17:19.020 --> 02:17:21.299
her scales into moon, pushing her past

02:17:21.299 --> 02:17:22.020
her nervousness.

02:17:22.139 --> 02:17:25.379
I Moon Watcher, she said softly.

02:17:25.440 --> 02:17:27.239
But please call me Moon.

02:17:27.360 --> 02:17:28.739
Or nothing.

02:17:28.799 --> 02:17:30.179
That would be all right too.

02:17:30.239 --> 02:17:33.299
I guess I can't say, please don't talk to

02:17:33.299 --> 02:17:33.659
me at all.

02:17:33.719 --> 02:17:34.499
Can I?

02:17:34.559 --> 02:17:38.459
Um, I grew up in the rainforest.

02:17:38.520 --> 02:17:42.000
And I'm a mind reader, and I can see the

02:17:42.000 --> 02:17:42.299
future.

02:17:42.360 --> 02:17:44.399
And I'm afraid Turtle might kill his

02:17:44.399 --> 02:17:46.500
sister, and I'm pretty sure someone is

02:17:46.500 --> 02:17:48.479
spying on our dreams, and that the whole

02:17:48.479 --> 02:17:49.979
mountain might fall on us one day.

02:17:50.040 --> 02:17:52.139
Also, I miss my mother.

02:17:52.260 --> 02:17:56.879
I, like scrolls, she finished nervously.

02:17:56.940 --> 02:18:01.139
How did she grow up in the rainforest?

02:18:01.200 --> 02:18:02.459
Winter thought.

02:18:02.520 --> 02:18:05.100
Narrowing his eyes at her, but tsunami

02:18:05.100 --> 02:18:06.899
had already turned away, and Moon

02:18:06.899 --> 02:18:09.180
couldn't jump in to explain, in case he

02:18:09.180 --> 02:18:10.860
guessed that she'd read his mind again

02:18:10.860 --> 02:18:13.739
she focused on her talons, avoiding his

02:18:13.739 --> 02:18:14.219
gaze.

02:18:14.219 --> 02:18:16.979
Me too, said Turtle.

02:18:17.040 --> 02:18:19.500
At least, I like scrolls that weren't

02:18:19.500 --> 02:18:20.040
written by my mother.

02:18:20.100 --> 02:18:23.340
I've read way too many of those He rolled

02:18:23.340 --> 02:18:23.760
his eyes.

02:18:23.819 --> 02:18:25.440
I'm Turtle, by the way.

02:18:25.500 --> 02:18:29.159
Used to being invisible, Kibley thought

02:18:29.159 --> 02:18:31.379
tilting his head at turtle, almost

02:18:31.379 --> 02:18:32.639
prefers it, but not always.

02:18:32.700 --> 02:18:33.840
Easy going.

02:18:33.899 --> 02:18:35.760
Doesn't want to try hard enough to be

02:18:35.760 --> 02:18:36.120
noticed.

02:18:36.180 --> 02:18:38.399
I wonder how much that armband is worth.

02:18:38.459 --> 02:18:40.799
Don't recognize the kind of stones.

02:18:40.860 --> 02:18:42.659
He looks like he wants to go back to

02:18:42.659 --> 02:18:42.899
bed.

02:18:42.959 --> 02:18:45.479
Moonless and intently.

02:18:45.540 --> 02:18:47.159
She hadn't been able to figure out

02:18:47.159 --> 02:18:48.420
anything about turtle at all.

02:18:48.479 --> 02:18:51.120
Kimberly seemed to think the sea wing was

02:18:51.120 --> 02:18:51.540
harmless.

02:18:51.600 --> 02:18:53.819
She wondered what he'd think if she told

02:18:53.819 --> 02:18:54.659
him about her vision.

02:18:54.719 --> 02:18:57.119
Not that that conversation was ever going

02:18:57.119 --> 02:18:57.419
to happen.

02:18:57.479 --> 02:19:00.840
I'm Kibley, said the Sandwing.

02:19:00.899 --> 02:19:03.180
I was one of Thorn's outlaws before she

02:19:03.180 --> 02:19:03.780
became queen.

02:19:03.899 --> 02:19:07.020
My plan is to learn everything as fast as

02:19:07.020 --> 02:19:09.059
possible and then get back to help her

02:19:09.059 --> 02:19:10.079
run the kingdom of sand.

02:19:10.139 --> 02:19:14.099
I'm sure she's lost without you, Winters

02:19:14.099 --> 02:19:14.879
said scathingly.

02:19:14.940 --> 02:19:17.879
And I'm sure you're perfectly essential

02:19:17.879 --> 02:19:20.879
to the operation of your kingdom, Kibley

02:19:20.879 --> 02:19:21.299
shot back.

02:19:21.360 --> 02:19:24.899
Winter frowned, and Kibley thought, ah

02:19:24.899 --> 02:19:25.920
that hit home.

02:19:25.979 --> 02:19:26.879
I was right.

02:19:26.940 --> 02:19:28.979
He doesn't think he's worth much to his

02:19:28.979 --> 02:19:31.379
family, although he would like us all to

02:19:31.379 --> 02:19:31.860
think differently.

02:19:31.920 --> 02:19:35.159
And I'm umber, said Clay's brother.

02:19:35.219 --> 02:19:38.039
I think, I think we might have been in a

02:19:38.039 --> 02:19:39.839
battle together once, he said to

02:19:39.839 --> 02:19:40.439
Carnelian.

02:19:40.500 --> 02:19:42.479
I mean, you look familiar.

02:19:42.540 --> 02:19:46.739
Oh, she said, squinting at him.

02:19:46.799 --> 02:19:48.119
Her frown softened.

02:19:48.180 --> 02:19:50.459
I didn't realize you fought in the war

02:19:50.459 --> 02:19:50.700
too.

02:19:50.760 --> 02:19:54.299
Where sky wings and mud wings were on the

02:19:54.299 --> 02:19:56.219
same side, she thought quietly.

02:19:56.280 --> 02:19:58.559
Maybe I do have allies here.

02:19:58.680 --> 02:20:01.379
Yeah, with my brothers and sisters.

02:20:01.440 --> 02:20:04.139
My brother Reed is our leader, he said

02:20:04.139 --> 02:20:06.600
but he said Zora and Marsh and I could

02:20:06.600 --> 02:20:08.280
come to school now that the war is over

02:20:08.280 --> 02:20:10.020
since there's so much we wanted to

02:20:10.020 --> 02:20:10.260
learn.

02:20:10.319 --> 02:20:12.420
I miss him and pheasant though.

02:20:12.479 --> 02:20:15.659
Memories flashed through his head, of

02:20:15.659 --> 02:20:18.239
flying, surrounded by other brown dragons

02:20:18.239 --> 02:20:20.639
whisking through clouds and turning and

02:20:20.639 --> 02:20:23.760
diving all together, marshes, a muddy

02:20:23.760 --> 02:20:25.020
swamp camp.

02:20:25.079 --> 02:20:27.059
A large brown dragon cuffed his shoulder

02:20:27.059 --> 02:20:27.719
affectionately.

02:20:27.780 --> 02:20:30.180
Another one dropped a pig in front of him

02:20:30.180 --> 02:20:32.459
and waved for him and Zora to share it

02:20:32.459 --> 02:20:34.379
all of them laughing around a fire.

02:20:34.440 --> 02:20:37.860
They can visit any time, tsunami

02:20:37.860 --> 02:20:38.340
promised.

02:20:38.399 --> 02:20:40.500
They can even camp out and live here if

02:20:40.500 --> 02:20:41.940
they want, the more the merrier.

02:20:42.000 --> 02:20:45.120
They're working for Queen Mohen right now

02:20:45.120 --> 02:20:46.440
Umbre explained.

02:20:46.559 --> 02:20:48.239
But maybe one day.

02:20:48.299 --> 02:20:51.420
His wings drooped a fraction of an inch

02:20:51.420 --> 02:20:52.799
and then he pulled them back up.

02:20:52.860 --> 02:20:57.420
Well, I am Winter, said Winter.

02:20:57.479 --> 02:21:01.379
Queen Glacier's nephew, Kibley said at

02:21:01.379 --> 02:21:02.280
the same time as he did.

02:21:02.280 --> 02:21:04.739
Winter straightened up and glittered

02:21:04.739 --> 02:21:05.700
dangerously at him.

02:21:05.760 --> 02:21:09.000
Don't you mock me, he said.

02:21:09.059 --> 02:21:10.559
I wouldn't dream of it.

02:21:10.620 --> 02:21:12.120
Kibley said innocently.

02:21:12.180 --> 02:21:15.360
If you're the head of school, Winter said

02:21:15.360 --> 02:21:16.079
to tsunami.

02:21:16.139 --> 02:21:18.000
Does that mean you're the dragon to talk

02:21:18.000 --> 02:21:19.379
to about getting a private cave?

02:21:19.440 --> 02:21:23.340
Why, yes, I am, Tsunami said.

02:21:23.399 --> 02:21:24.420
The answer is no.

02:21:24.540 --> 02:21:26.040
See?

02:21:26.100 --> 02:21:29.520
I'm your destiny, Kibley said to Winter

02:21:29.520 --> 02:21:30.600
with a cheerful shrug.

02:21:30.719 --> 02:21:32.819
Wish he were my destiny.

02:21:32.879 --> 02:21:35.399
Umber and Kinkachu thought nearly

02:21:35.399 --> 02:21:38.040
simultaneously, Moon smothered a giggle

02:21:38.040 --> 02:21:39.780
and got a pleased look from Kibley.

02:21:39.840 --> 02:21:42.360
Can we get on with the discussion?

02:21:42.420 --> 02:21:43.500
Winter asked.

02:21:43.559 --> 02:21:45.719
What exactly is the point of this?

02:21:45.780 --> 02:21:48.600
The point is to talk about anything you

02:21:48.600 --> 02:21:49.260
want to talk about.

02:21:49.319 --> 02:21:50.459
Tsunami said.

02:21:50.520 --> 02:21:52.500
To find out what dragons from other

02:21:52.500 --> 02:21:54.780
tribes think, and see things from a new

02:21:54.780 --> 02:21:55.319
point of view?

02:21:55.379 --> 02:21:57.719
I'm sure it'll be different when you have

02:21:57.719 --> 02:21:59.819
this class with Starflight or clay or

02:21:59.819 --> 02:22:02.399
sunny, but I, for one, think you guys

02:22:02.399 --> 02:22:03.059
should pick the topic.

02:22:03.120 --> 02:22:05.940
All right, Winter said.

02:22:06.000 --> 02:22:08.940
I want to talk about Nightwing Powers.

02:22:09.000 --> 02:22:12.360
As far as Moon could hear, no one noticed

02:22:12.360 --> 02:22:13.920
her expression of terror before she

02:22:13.920 --> 02:22:16.739
managed to fix her face, except maybe

02:22:16.739 --> 02:22:18.840
Kibley, who thought, is she all right?

02:22:18.899 --> 02:22:21.479
Winter's such a moonlicking crocodile

02:22:21.479 --> 02:22:22.680
picking on her for no reason.

02:22:22.739 --> 02:22:26.040
Kinkajoo also glanced at Moon and thought

02:22:26.040 --> 02:22:27.239
poor thing.

02:22:27.299 --> 02:22:29.040
She's not going to enjoy that.

02:22:29.100 --> 02:22:32.100
Maybe we could talk about the war instead

02:22:32.100 --> 02:22:33.479
the rain wing suggested.

02:22:33.540 --> 02:22:35.760
I want to know what Queen Thorn is like.

02:22:35.819 --> 02:22:37.620
You've been inside the Sandwing

02:22:37.620 --> 02:22:38.520
stronghold, haven't you?

02:22:38.579 --> 02:22:39.959
She asked Kibley.

02:22:40.020 --> 02:22:43.620
Wait, I'm confused about the night wings

02:22:43.620 --> 02:22:46.079
too, Turtles said, before Kibley could

02:22:46.079 --> 02:22:46.319
answer.

02:22:46.379 --> 02:22:48.420
Is it true they don't have powers

02:22:48.420 --> 02:22:48.840
anymore?

02:22:48.899 --> 02:22:50.579
Just because they moved to the

02:22:50.579 --> 02:22:51.239
rainforest?

02:22:51.360 --> 02:22:54.299
I heard a rumor that they never had

02:22:54.299 --> 02:22:54.899
powers.

02:22:54.959 --> 02:22:57.959
Cornelian chimed in, suddenly animated.

02:22:58.020 --> 02:23:00.180
That they made all of that up, and

02:23:00.180 --> 02:23:01.920
they've been lying to us for 1000s of

02:23:01.920 --> 02:23:02.459
years.

02:23:02.520 --> 02:23:06.299
But what about the Dragonhead prophecy

02:23:06.299 --> 02:23:08.940
Umber challenged, flicking his tail, about

02:23:08.940 --> 02:23:10.799
my brother and his friends ending the

02:23:10.799 --> 02:23:11.040
war.

02:23:11.100 --> 02:23:14.040
That was clearly real because look, it

02:23:14.040 --> 02:23:14.399
came true.

02:23:14.459 --> 02:23:18.360
No, it wasn't, Moon thought.

02:23:18.420 --> 02:23:20.760
All the night wings know it was false

02:23:20.760 --> 02:23:22.500
because there haven't been any true

02:23:22.500 --> 02:23:24.180
prophets in the tribe in forever.

02:23:24.239 --> 02:23:26.760
But they won't admit that to anyone

02:23:26.760 --> 02:23:27.780
outside the tribe.

02:23:27.899 --> 02:23:29.520
Not even her.

02:23:29.579 --> 02:23:31.139
She'd figured it out by reading their

02:23:31.139 --> 02:23:31.500
minds.

02:23:31.559 --> 02:23:34.079
Most of them are furious that the world

02:23:34.079 --> 02:23:35.159
knows they have no powers.

02:23:35.219 --> 02:23:39.000
What if they're lying now, and they

02:23:39.000 --> 02:23:40.979
secretly do have powers, but don't want

02:23:40.979 --> 02:23:42.840
us to know, Turtle asked.

02:23:42.899 --> 02:23:45.479
Moon shivered and voluntarily, and

02:23:45.479 --> 02:23:47.040
focused on the fish in her claws.

02:23:47.100 --> 02:23:49.500
Oh, snail droppings.

02:23:49.559 --> 02:23:51.540
Tsunami cursed inside her head.

02:23:51.600 --> 02:23:53.700
I told Starflight we get asked about

02:23:53.700 --> 02:23:53.879
this.

02:23:53.940 --> 02:23:56.100
I never remember our story.

02:23:56.280 --> 02:23:57.420
And why should I have to lie?

02:23:57.420 --> 02:23:59.819
to protect the night wing's precious

02:23:59.819 --> 02:24:02.340
reputation, or the worthless talons of

02:24:02.340 --> 02:24:02.760
peace?

02:24:02.819 --> 02:24:04.979
Who cares that the prophecy wasn't real

02:24:04.979 --> 02:24:06.479
now that the war is over?

02:24:06.540 --> 02:24:09.059
It doesn't really matter, right?

02:24:09.120 --> 02:24:10.379
She hedged.

02:24:10.440 --> 02:24:11.579
The war is over.

02:24:11.639 --> 02:24:13.319
There are no more prophecies.

02:24:13.379 --> 02:24:15.719
We can do whatever we want, which

02:24:15.719 --> 02:24:17.579
includes ignoring the night wings if we

02:24:17.579 --> 02:24:17.940
want to.

02:24:18.000 --> 02:24:19.319
No offense, Moon.

02:24:19.379 --> 02:24:21.540
It matters.

02:24:21.600 --> 02:24:24.540
If they were manipulating us, Winter

02:24:24.540 --> 02:24:25.020
hissed.

02:24:25.139 --> 02:24:27.120
Do they have powers or not?

02:24:27.180 --> 02:24:29.040
Or did they when they lived in their

02:24:29.040 --> 02:24:30.000
secret location?

02:24:30.059 --> 02:24:33.239
If so, were all of them psychic or just a

02:24:33.239 --> 02:24:33.479
few?

02:24:33.540 --> 02:24:35.340
And how did they lose them?

02:24:35.399 --> 02:24:37.200
He shook his head.

02:24:37.260 --> 02:24:39.659
His icicle sharp spikes clattering

02:24:39.659 --> 02:24:40.079
faintly.

02:24:40.139 --> 02:24:42.840
There are 1000s of dragons who are still

02:24:42.840 --> 02:24:44.159
terrified of the night wings.

02:24:44.219 --> 02:24:46.200
They deserve to know the truth.

02:24:46.260 --> 02:24:49.680
Tsunami looked calm, but Moon could hear

02:24:49.680 --> 02:24:50.940
her squirming on the inside.

02:24:51.000 --> 02:24:54.959
I totally agree with you, the sea wing

02:24:54.959 --> 02:24:55.139
thought.

02:24:55.200 --> 02:24:59.459
Well, nobody's sure what the truth is, she

02:24:59.459 --> 02:25:00.000
said finally.

02:25:00.059 --> 02:25:02.100
Nobody's sure.

02:25:02.159 --> 02:25:05.340
Winter swept one glittering pale blue

02:25:05.340 --> 02:25:06.299
wing toward moon.

02:25:06.360 --> 02:25:07.860
We have one right here.

02:25:07.920 --> 02:25:10.440
This is all about understanding other

02:25:10.440 --> 02:25:11.520
tribes, isn't it?

02:25:11.579 --> 02:25:13.079
Can't we ask her?

02:25:13.139 --> 02:25:14.940
Three moons.

02:25:15.000 --> 02:25:17.520
The horrible force of 7 pairs of eyes

02:25:17.520 --> 02:25:21.899
staring at her, green, amber, black, blue

02:25:21.899 --> 02:25:24.959
orange, ranging from curious to hostile

02:25:24.959 --> 02:25:27.059
with matching tidal waves of emotion

02:25:27.059 --> 02:25:29.459
behind them, Moon wondered what anyone

02:25:29.459 --> 02:25:31.799
would do if she bolted from the cave, and

02:25:31.799 --> 02:25:33.239
maybe flew all the way back to the

02:25:33.239 --> 02:25:34.379
rainforest without stopping.

02:25:34.500 --> 02:25:36.899
Moon doesn't know anything.

02:25:37.020 --> 02:25:39.000
Kinkachu jumped in loyally.

02:25:39.059 --> 02:25:41.040
She wasn't raised with the other night

02:25:41.040 --> 02:25:41.579
wings.

02:25:41.639 --> 02:25:43.979
Her mother hid her in the rainforest.

02:25:44.040 --> 02:25:46.139
She's been told all the same lies as

02:25:46.139 --> 02:25:46.620
everyone else.

02:25:46.680 --> 02:25:50.340
Moon thought perhaps she loved Kinkaju at

02:25:50.340 --> 02:25:52.139
that moment, more than any other dragon

02:25:52.139 --> 02:25:52.979
she'd ever known.

02:25:53.040 --> 02:25:56.399
Please, please believe her, she prayed.

02:25:56.520 --> 02:25:58.500
Don't ask me any more questions.

02:25:58.559 --> 02:26:00.479
Oh.

02:26:00.540 --> 02:26:03.120
Winter gave Moon that look again.

02:26:03.180 --> 02:26:05.399
The one like she had shifted her scales

02:26:05.399 --> 02:26:07.079
and turned out to be a different dragon

02:26:07.079 --> 02:26:09.840
than he'd expected, or possibly a howler

02:26:09.840 --> 02:26:11.459
monkey, and not a dragon at all.

02:26:11.520 --> 02:26:14.639
Maybe I don't have to hate her after all

02:26:14.639 --> 02:26:15.600
he thought.

02:26:15.659 --> 02:26:19.620
But still, a night wing, a night wing, and

02:26:19.620 --> 02:26:20.639
none of them can be trusted.

02:26:20.760 --> 02:26:24.239
Aha, Kibley thought.

02:26:24.299 --> 02:26:25.979
That explains some things.

02:26:26.040 --> 02:26:28.260
She doesn't have the same beaten down yet

02:26:28.260 --> 02:26:30.600
insufferably smug aura of the other night

02:26:30.600 --> 02:26:31.079
wings.

02:26:31.139 --> 02:26:32.940
Does she miss the rainforest?

02:26:33.000 --> 02:26:35.219
Or is she happy to finally be with other

02:26:35.219 --> 02:26:35.760
dragons?

02:26:35.819 --> 02:26:37.680
Was she lonely?

02:26:37.739 --> 02:26:39.239
Must have been alone a lot.

02:26:39.360 --> 02:26:40.860
Maybe she prefers it.

02:26:40.920 --> 02:26:42.780
Or maybe she's not used to making

02:26:42.780 --> 02:26:43.139
friends.

02:26:43.200 --> 02:26:45.180
I could be her friend.

02:26:45.239 --> 02:26:46.440
Careful, Kibley.

02:26:46.500 --> 02:26:47.819
Figure her out first.

02:26:47.879 --> 02:26:51.420
Look, the important thing is that if the

02:26:51.420 --> 02:26:53.219
Nightwings ever did have powers, they

02:26:53.219 --> 02:26:56.159
don't anymore, Tsunami said, spreading

02:26:56.159 --> 02:26:58.079
her wings so the sun shone through her

02:26:58.079 --> 02:27:00.540
royal pattern of phosphorescent scales.

02:27:00.600 --> 02:27:03.059
As long as everyone knows that, the night

02:27:03.059 --> 02:27:04.799
wings can't manipulate the other tribes

02:27:04.799 --> 02:27:05.219
ever again.

02:27:05.280 --> 02:27:07.739
So just remember that there's no mind

02:27:07.739 --> 02:27:09.959
reading, and there's definitely no seeing

02:27:09.959 --> 02:27:10.500
the future.

02:27:10.559 --> 02:27:13.319
Nightwings are not these all powerful

02:27:13.319 --> 02:27:14.940
mystery dragons who know everything.

02:27:15.000 --> 02:27:17.520
And if someone ever tells you you're in a

02:27:17.520 --> 02:27:19.739
prophecy, tell them to eat their tails.

02:27:19.799 --> 02:27:21.959
I wish I could have done that to the

02:27:21.959 --> 02:27:23.819
talent of peace a lot sooner.

02:27:23.940 --> 02:27:26.159
She wouldn't believe me.

02:27:26.280 --> 02:27:27.780
Moon realized.

02:27:27.840 --> 02:27:30.420
If I went to tsunami about the voices I

02:27:30.420 --> 02:27:32.760
heard, or my vision of Jade Mountain

02:27:32.760 --> 02:27:33.360
collapsing.

02:27:33.420 --> 02:27:35.579
She'd think I was lying.

02:27:35.639 --> 02:27:39.120
She doesn't trust Nightwings, or anyone

02:27:39.120 --> 02:27:41.100
who tries to tell her what to do, or what

02:27:41.100 --> 02:27:41.940
her future will be.

02:27:42.000 --> 02:27:45.239
But winter started to protest.

02:27:45.299 --> 02:27:47.280
Who wants to go hunting?

02:27:47.340 --> 02:27:49.079
tsunami nearly shouted.

02:27:49.139 --> 02:27:50.459
I know I do.

02:27:50.520 --> 02:27:51.959
Great idea, tsunami.

02:27:52.020 --> 02:27:53.639
No arguing with the head of school.

02:27:53.700 --> 02:27:54.479
Off we go.

02:27:54.600 --> 02:27:57.360
She shot off the ledge and whooshed away

02:27:57.360 --> 02:27:58.200
into the clouds.

02:27:58.260 --> 02:27:59.700
Carnelian snorted.

02:27:59.760 --> 02:28:02.520
I guess that discussion is over, she

02:28:02.520 --> 02:28:02.760
said.

02:28:02.879 --> 02:28:05.520
Moon let herself smile at the fact that

02:28:05.520 --> 02:28:08.399
fearless, awe inspiring tsunami had been

02:28:08.399 --> 02:28:09.899
the one to bolt, not her.

02:28:10.020 --> 02:28:13.020
But her smile faded, as winter paced

02:28:13.020 --> 02:28:14.639
across the cave and stopped right in

02:28:14.639 --> 02:28:15.059
front of her.

02:28:15.180 --> 02:28:18.000
He studied her with his piercing gaze

02:28:18.000 --> 02:28:21.299
almost as if he could read her mind, if

02:28:21.299 --> 02:28:22.559
he just stared at her long enough.

02:28:22.680 --> 02:28:25.739
His scales were so bright. and so cold.

02:28:25.799 --> 02:28:29.639
His eyes so weirdly blue, and suspicious

02:28:29.639 --> 02:28:32.579
and angry, and sad, all at the same

02:28:32.579 --> 02:28:32.819
time.

02:28:32.879 --> 02:28:35.520
Hey, winter, leave her alone.

02:28:35.579 --> 02:28:38.399
Kibley said, sliding up next to Moon.

02:28:38.459 --> 02:28:39.959
She's not the enemy.

02:28:40.020 --> 02:28:43.200
Pyrrhea is at peace now.

02:28:43.260 --> 02:28:44.399
Turtle agreed.

02:28:44.459 --> 02:28:46.020
There are no more enemies.

02:28:46.079 --> 02:28:48.840
Because the queen signed a peace

02:28:48.840 --> 02:28:51.239
agreement, and accepted Thorn as the new

02:28:51.239 --> 02:28:53.340
sandwing queen, Winter thought.

02:28:53.399 --> 02:28:55.920
But there are some things that cannot be

02:28:55.920 --> 02:28:58.799
forgiven, that should not be forgiven.

02:28:58.860 --> 02:29:01.139
And we're supposed to just sit back and

02:29:01.139 --> 02:29:02.459
let the night wings get away with it.

02:29:02.520 --> 02:29:06.479
It wasn't her, though, whispered another

02:29:06.479 --> 02:29:09.299
part of his mind, but she's still one of

02:29:09.299 --> 02:29:09.479
them.

02:29:09.600 --> 02:29:13.739
You say you don't know anything, Winter

02:29:13.739 --> 02:29:16.379
said, settling his wings, but you know

02:29:16.379 --> 02:29:17.399
the other night wings.

02:29:17.459 --> 02:29:19.620
You can find out the truth and come back

02:29:19.620 --> 02:29:21.000
to tell us, right?

02:29:21.059 --> 02:29:23.219
Ha.

02:29:23.280 --> 02:29:25.500
They'd probably tell an ice swing all

02:29:25.500 --> 02:29:27.180
their secrets long before they ever trust

02:29:27.180 --> 02:29:28.799
me, Moon thought.

02:29:28.860 --> 02:29:32.159
Um, she said, maybe?

02:29:32.219 --> 02:29:34.500
I want to know everything about their

02:29:34.500 --> 02:29:36.120
powers, he said.

02:29:36.239 --> 02:29:37.979
Were they ever real?

02:29:38.040 --> 02:29:39.000
How do we know they're gone?

02:29:39.059 --> 02:29:41.940
What else are they lying to us about?

02:29:42.000 --> 02:29:43.500
He cleared his throat.

02:29:43.559 --> 02:29:46.680
If I'm scary enough, she'll do what I

02:29:46.680 --> 02:29:46.920
want.

02:29:47.040 --> 02:29:48.540
His mind whispered.

02:29:48.600 --> 02:29:50.760
That's what mother would say.

02:29:50.819 --> 02:29:54.659
I mean you, what else are you lying to us

02:29:54.659 --> 02:29:54.899
about?

02:29:54.959 --> 02:29:58.260
Hey, igloo face, that's not cool.

02:29:58.319 --> 02:29:59.639
Kibble barked.

02:29:59.700 --> 02:30:03.000
Yeah, Moon's in our Winglet, Kinkaju said

02:30:03.000 --> 02:30:03.540
bristling.

02:30:03.600 --> 02:30:05.100
We're supposed to support each other.

02:30:05.159 --> 02:30:08.100
I'm with igloo face.

02:30:08.159 --> 02:30:09.360
Cornelian said.

02:30:09.420 --> 02:30:12.059
She stood up and stretched her massive

02:30:12.059 --> 02:30:14.579
wings, making umber duck so he wouldn't

02:30:14.579 --> 02:30:15.420
get whacked in the head.

02:30:15.479 --> 02:30:17.879
If we were supposed to get all snugly

02:30:17.879 --> 02:30:19.680
with each other, there shouldn't be any

02:30:19.680 --> 02:30:20.459
more secrets.

02:30:20.520 --> 02:30:22.739
Let's make her tell us everything.

02:30:22.799 --> 02:30:26.940
Her orange eyes glared at moon, and an

02:30:26.940 --> 02:30:29.399
ominous image flashed through her head, of

02:30:29.399 --> 02:30:31.739
moon pinned under her talons.

02:30:31.799 --> 02:30:32.879
I wasn't joking.

02:30:32.940 --> 02:30:35.700
Tsunami yelled, swooping by outside.

02:30:35.760 --> 02:30:36.959
We're going hunting.

02:30:37.020 --> 02:30:37.379
Come on.

02:30:37.500 --> 02:30:40.799
Cornelian stalked to the ledge and leaped

02:30:40.799 --> 02:30:41.040
out.

02:30:41.100 --> 02:30:43.260
Umber glanced at the others.

02:30:43.319 --> 02:30:46.860
Poor moon, he thought, but I want to know

02:30:46.860 --> 02:30:47.520
the truth too.

02:30:47.639 --> 02:30:49.559
And then hurried after her.

02:30:49.620 --> 02:30:51.299
Turtle shrugged.

02:30:51.360 --> 02:30:53.399
Whatever you guys decide.

02:30:53.520 --> 02:30:56.280
And a moment later, he was gone as well

02:30:56.280 --> 02:30:58.979
leaving Moon, Kinkachu, Kibley, and

02:30:58.979 --> 02:30:59.760
Winter facing off.

02:30:59.819 --> 02:31:02.219
I'll fight him if I have to.

02:31:02.280 --> 02:31:04.319
Kibley was thinking fiercely.

02:31:04.379 --> 02:31:07.020
He curls his claws like he relies on his

02:31:07.020 --> 02:31:08.040
front talons in fighting.

02:31:08.100 --> 02:31:10.139
So I'll go for his shoulder 1st.

02:31:10.200 --> 02:31:11.940
Slow him down without doing too much

02:31:11.940 --> 02:31:12.360
damage.

02:31:12.420 --> 02:31:14.940
Have to disable his snout to stop his

02:31:14.940 --> 02:31:15.780
frost breath too.

02:31:15.840 --> 02:31:18.299
Well, moon like it if I fight for her.

02:31:18.360 --> 02:31:20.459
Or see the kind of dragon who would

02:31:20.459 --> 02:31:22.200
rather see me try a peaceful argument

02:31:22.200 --> 02:31:22.500
first.

02:31:22.559 --> 02:31:24.899
Kingaju would like me either way.

02:31:24.959 --> 02:31:26.219
I like that about her.

02:31:26.280 --> 02:31:28.319
But I can't even guess about Moon.

02:31:28.440 --> 02:31:31.440
Doesn't seem like a fighter, but she's

02:31:31.440 --> 02:31:32.579
not scared in a normal way.

02:31:32.639 --> 02:31:34.379
Hope she stands up to him.

02:31:34.440 --> 02:31:36.180
She can't let him get away with

02:31:36.180 --> 02:31:37.319
intimidating her like that.

02:31:37.379 --> 02:31:39.840
On Moon's other side.

02:31:39.899 --> 02:31:43.200
It is so weird that I can't tell what

02:31:43.200 --> 02:31:45.000
he's feeling by looking at a scales

02:31:45.000 --> 02:31:47.100
Kinkachu thought, watching winter.

02:31:47.159 --> 02:31:51.299
His shiny, shiny, gorgeous scales don't

02:31:51.299 --> 02:31:51.840
get distracted.

02:31:51.899 --> 02:31:54.659
No being mean to my new best friend, no

02:31:54.659 --> 02:31:56.040
matter how dazzling you are.

02:31:56.100 --> 02:31:59.100
Moon blinked at Kinkachu, her fear

02:31:59.100 --> 02:32:01.079
shrinking, new best friend?

02:32:01.139 --> 02:32:02.340
Did she mean that?

02:32:02.399 --> 02:32:04.920
Or was Kingachu the kind of dragon who

02:32:04.920 --> 02:32:06.600
had a new best friend every 2 minutes?

02:32:06.659 --> 02:32:10.260
Either way, for these 2 minutes, at least

02:32:10.260 --> 02:32:11.100
she had backup.

02:32:11.159 --> 02:32:13.139
Even if she hadn't done anything to earn

02:32:13.139 --> 02:32:13.319
it.

02:32:13.379 --> 02:32:16.200
She turned and met Winter's eyes, which

02:32:16.200 --> 02:32:17.520
felt a little like staring into a

02:32:17.520 --> 02:32:18.000
glacier.

02:32:18.059 --> 02:32:20.459
All right, she said.

02:32:20.579 --> 02:32:23.100
But please stop trying to scare me.

02:32:23.159 --> 02:32:26.399
She hesitated, and then, riding one of

02:32:26.399 --> 02:32:28.620
Kibley's sharp observations, she added

02:32:28.620 --> 02:32:31.200
You are not as terrifying as you think

02:32:31.200 --> 02:32:31.559
you are.

02:32:31.620 --> 02:32:35.159
He took a surprised step back, his mind

02:32:35.159 --> 02:32:35.760
whirling.

02:32:35.819 --> 02:32:38.819
Nice, Kinkachu thought, grinning.

02:32:38.879 --> 02:32:39.479
Take that.

02:32:39.600 --> 02:32:42.899
Knew she was cool. thought Kibley.

02:32:43.020 --> 02:32:45.299
Stop liking her.

02:32:45.360 --> 02:32:48.360
Winter ordered himself with an internal

02:32:48.360 --> 02:32:48.780
growl.

02:32:48.899 --> 02:32:50.760
Remember what father said.

02:32:50.819 --> 02:32:52.260
They're all liars.

02:32:52.319 --> 02:32:55.319
Be strong, be vigilant, strike first.

02:32:55.379 --> 02:32:56.579
Trust nobody.

02:32:56.639 --> 02:32:59.280
Not even interesting night wings, with

02:32:59.280 --> 02:33:00.780
silver teardrop scales.

02:33:00.840 --> 02:33:03.059
Fine, he said.

02:33:03.120 --> 02:33:05.340
You find out the truth about Nightwing

02:33:05.340 --> 02:33:05.700
powers.

02:33:05.760 --> 02:33:08.100
And you stopped threatening everybody

02:33:08.100 --> 02:33:09.540
Kinkachu said.

02:33:09.600 --> 02:33:12.299
He paused, and then an unexpected

02:33:12.299 --> 02:33:13.500
expression creased his face.

02:33:13.559 --> 02:33:16.440
Hey, I didn't promise anything about

02:33:16.440 --> 02:33:17.879
everybody, he said.

02:33:17.940 --> 02:33:18.840
Just her.

02:33:18.899 --> 02:33:21.360
I have an ice wing warrior mystique to

02:33:21.360 --> 02:33:21.959
maintain after all.

02:33:22.020 --> 02:33:23.280
Come on.

02:33:23.340 --> 02:33:26.040
He looked at Moon again, and then he

02:33:26.040 --> 02:33:28.559
turned and jumped out into the sky, flying

02:33:28.559 --> 02:33:29.760
after tsunami and the others.

02:33:29.819 --> 02:33:33.899
I'm probably wrong, Kibley said, but I

02:33:33.899 --> 02:33:36.180
think my clawmate just made a joke.

02:33:36.239 --> 02:33:37.260
Is that possible?

02:33:37.319 --> 02:33:41.639
Inside, he was thinking, yes, I knew that

02:33:41.639 --> 02:33:42.540
dragon was in there.

02:33:42.600 --> 02:33:44.459
If I can just drag him out.

02:33:44.579 --> 02:33:46.739
Moon returned his smile.

02:33:46.860 --> 02:33:49.139
You were totally hallucinating.

02:33:49.200 --> 02:33:50.459
Kinkachu agreed.

02:33:50.520 --> 02:33:51.959
Too many smoke berries.

02:33:52.020 --> 02:33:53.879
Are you all right?

02:33:53.940 --> 02:33:55.559
Kibley asked Moon.

02:33:55.620 --> 02:33:56.639
She nodded.

02:33:56.760 --> 02:33:58.860
She was more all right than she'd been in

02:33:58.860 --> 02:33:59.219
months.

02:33:59.340 --> 02:34:00.840
Mind reading was one thing.

02:34:00.959 --> 02:34:02.579
One awful thing.

02:34:02.639 --> 02:34:04.680
When you were surrounded by dragons who

02:34:04.680 --> 02:34:06.959
hated you, as she had been in the night

02:34:06.959 --> 02:34:07.559
wing village.

02:34:07.620 --> 02:34:09.360
But when you were with dragons who

02:34:09.360 --> 02:34:11.639
actually liked you, or wanted to like you

02:34:11.639 --> 02:34:13.200
for whatever mysterious reason.

02:34:13.260 --> 02:34:15.899
Well, she didn't expect it to last.

02:34:15.959 --> 02:34:18.420
What happens if they find out the truth

02:34:18.420 --> 02:34:18.840
about me?

02:34:18.899 --> 02:34:21.420
But for now, it was kind of great.

02:34:21.479 --> 02:34:24.059
What's a smoke berry?

02:34:24.120 --> 02:34:26.399
Kibli asked Kingaju as they started

02:34:26.399 --> 02:34:27.239
toward the ledge.

02:34:27.299 --> 02:34:30.659
Oh, they're crazy, Kinkachu said.

02:34:30.719 --> 02:34:33.000
I had some other rain wing healers were

02:34:33.000 --> 02:34:34.260
working on my wing injury.

02:34:34.319 --> 02:34:37.500
They gave me the wildest hallucinations

02:34:37.500 --> 02:34:39.899
flying pandhers, quetzals, the size of

02:34:39.899 --> 02:34:42.420
dragons, scavengers with superpowers.

02:34:42.479 --> 02:34:44.159
You name it, I saw everything.

02:34:44.219 --> 02:34:46.620
They soared into the sky.

02:34:46.680 --> 02:34:49.440
Moon started to follow them, but stopped

02:34:49.440 --> 02:34:51.780
on the ledge, feeling the wind whip

02:34:51.780 --> 02:34:54.299
around her, up in the clear, cloudless

02:34:54.299 --> 02:34:54.840
sky.

02:34:54.899 --> 02:34:57.239
Her new friends were diving and whirling

02:34:57.239 --> 02:35:00.540
like flower petals in a rainforest storm

02:35:00.540 --> 02:35:03.059
gold and scarlet and green and pale

02:35:03.059 --> 02:35:03.420
blue.

02:35:03.479 --> 02:35:06.180
Don't get too comfortable, little moon

02:35:06.180 --> 02:35:08.520
said the whispering voice softly.

02:35:08.579 --> 02:35:11.280
Even mind readers can be taken by

02:35:11.280 --> 02:35:13.500
surprise, when they think they know whom

02:35:13.500 --> 02:35:13.860
to trust.

02:35:13.920 --> 02:35:17.340
The dragons who like you now are the ones

02:35:17.340 --> 02:35:18.659
most likely to betray you.

02:35:18.719 --> 02:35:21.420
Believe me, I know.

02:35:21.479 --> 02:35:25.860
Chapter 7.

02:35:25.920 --> 02:35:30.000
Moon rose through the sky, feeling the

02:35:30.000 --> 02:35:32.280
paper soft brush of thin clouds parting

02:35:32.280 --> 02:35:33.239
around her dark wings.

02:35:33.299 --> 02:35:35.940
It was quieter up here, but not quiet

02:35:35.940 --> 02:35:36.180
enough.

02:35:36.239 --> 02:35:38.639
She wondered how high she'd have to get

02:35:38.639 --> 02:35:40.319
before she couldn't hear anyone anymore.

02:35:40.379 --> 02:35:42.959
She wondered if it was possible to get

02:35:42.959 --> 02:35:44.700
high enough that even her mystery friend

02:35:44.700 --> 02:35:45.659
couldn't reach her mind.

02:35:45.719 --> 02:35:49.440
A furry smell caught her attention, and

02:35:49.440 --> 02:35:50.760
she spun to study the ground.

02:35:50.819 --> 02:35:53.639
There, a mountain goat clambering between

02:35:53.639 --> 02:35:56.159
2 rocks behind a screen of straggly

02:35:56.159 --> 02:35:56.579
bushes.

02:35:56.639 --> 02:35:59.879
Moon glanced around, but tsunami and most

02:35:59.879 --> 02:36:01.739
of the others were circling over a glassy

02:36:01.739 --> 02:36:03.120
lake, looking for fish.

02:36:03.180 --> 02:36:06.600
The closest dragon to moon was Kibley, who

02:36:06.600 --> 02:36:08.399
was trying extremely hard to seem as if

02:36:08.399 --> 02:36:09.299
he wasn't watching her.

02:36:09.299 --> 02:36:11.940
Cornelian was within shouting distance

02:36:11.940 --> 02:36:14.819
drifting on her vast wings, but Moon

02:36:14.819 --> 02:36:16.860
wasn't about to do any shouting, and

02:36:16.860 --> 02:36:18.600
certainly not to get the grumpy Sky Wings

02:36:18.600 --> 02:36:19.020
attention.

02:36:19.079 --> 02:36:22.680
Guess that means this goat is mine, she

02:36:22.680 --> 02:36:25.020
thought, with a tiny bit of glee.

02:36:25.079 --> 02:36:28.860
Swooping suddenly into a dive, moon

02:36:28.860 --> 02:36:30.180
plummeted down toward the ground.

02:36:30.239 --> 02:36:33.059
Below her, the goat saw her shadow coming

02:36:33.059 --> 02:36:35.399
and let out a bleeding scream of fear.

02:36:35.459 --> 02:36:38.040
It scrambled quickly up the rocks, and

02:36:38.040 --> 02:36:40.200
tried to leap into a narrow ravine, where

02:36:40.200 --> 02:36:41.520
dragons would not be able to follow.

02:36:41.579 --> 02:36:44.219
But it wasn't fast enough.

02:36:44.280 --> 02:36:46.500
Moon twisted in a quick spiral and

02:36:46.500 --> 02:36:49.079
snatched the goat in midair, whisking it

02:36:49.079 --> 02:36:51.059
back up into the sky, and killing it in

02:36:51.059 --> 02:36:53.100
one motion, with a squeeze of her claws.

02:36:53.159 --> 02:36:54.600
Wow.

02:36:54.659 --> 02:36:56.700
Kibli shouted from above her.

02:36:56.760 --> 02:36:57.899
How did you do that?

02:36:57.959 --> 02:36:59.760
Cornelian, did you see that?

02:36:59.819 --> 02:37:02.940
The sky wing flew closer, eyeing the dead

02:37:02.940 --> 02:37:03.840
goat jealously.

02:37:03.899 --> 02:37:06.120
I thought Nightwings didn't know how to

02:37:06.120 --> 02:37:06.360
hunt.

02:37:06.479 --> 02:37:09.959
I thought so too, Kinkatoo chimed in.

02:37:10.020 --> 02:37:12.479
The rain wing sailed up from a bramble

02:37:12.479 --> 02:37:13.379
covered slope.

02:37:13.440 --> 02:37:15.479
Her snout was stained with dark purple

02:37:15.479 --> 02:37:16.440
blackberry juice.

02:37:16.500 --> 02:37:19.079
Starflight told me that they do this

02:37:19.079 --> 02:37:21.360
thing where they bite their prey, and

02:37:21.360 --> 02:37:23.700
then wait for it to die of infection, and

02:37:23.700 --> 02:37:25.739
then they sniff it out and eat the dead

02:37:25.739 --> 02:37:26.280
things.

02:37:26.399 --> 02:37:29.340
It sounds super horrible, like even worse

02:37:29.340 --> 02:37:30.479
than regular hunting.

02:37:30.540 --> 02:37:33.299
Gross, Kibli agreed.

02:37:33.360 --> 02:37:35.879
They're not supposed to do that anymore

02:37:35.879 --> 02:37:36.959
Moon said.

02:37:37.020 --> 02:37:39.239
Glory and Death Bringer are teaching them

02:37:39.239 --> 02:37:42.780
how to hunt properly, and I just, I, um

02:37:42.780 --> 02:37:45.540
taught myself to hunt in the rainforest.

02:37:45.600 --> 02:37:49.500
Mother was always leaving me alone, so I

02:37:49.500 --> 02:37:50.040
kind of had to.

02:37:50.100 --> 02:37:51.959
She held out the goat.

02:37:52.020 --> 02:37:54.719
Um, maybe we can share it?

02:37:54.780 --> 02:37:56.159
Really?

02:37:56.219 --> 02:37:57.420
Kibley said.

02:37:57.479 --> 02:37:58.379
That would be great.

02:37:58.440 --> 02:38:00.540
I'm going to need more practice to figure

02:38:00.540 --> 02:38:01.440
out how to hunt here.

02:38:01.500 --> 02:38:04.920
The land is all folded and squiggly.

02:38:04.979 --> 02:38:06.420
Too many hiding places.

02:38:06.479 --> 02:38:09.659
Give me a big flat desert and some half

02:38:09.659 --> 02:38:11.639
asleep sunbathing lizards any day.

02:38:11.700 --> 02:38:14.579
Moon Guest, it wouldn't take him long to

02:38:14.579 --> 02:38:16.379
master hunting in the mountains.

02:38:16.440 --> 02:38:17.940
His eyes were darting across the

02:38:17.940 --> 02:38:20.100
landscape below them, and he was storing

02:38:20.100 --> 02:38:22.139
away observations in neat stacks in his

02:38:22.139 --> 02:38:22.319
mind.

02:38:22.379 --> 02:38:24.780
He was also trying to gauge whether she

02:38:24.780 --> 02:38:26.760
meant it about sharing the goat, and

02:38:26.760 --> 02:38:28.440
whether she'd like him better if he was

02:38:28.440 --> 02:38:30.420
self-sufficient, or if he accepted her

02:38:30.420 --> 02:38:31.979
offer with appropriate gratitude.

02:38:32.040 --> 02:38:34.440
I can catch my own food.

02:38:34.500 --> 02:38:36.719
Carnelian said stiffly.

02:38:36.780 --> 02:38:39.659
She swung away, broadcasting offended

02:38:39.659 --> 02:38:41.280
thoughts, moon winced.

02:38:41.340 --> 02:38:44.459
Nice work, Moon, tsunami called.

02:38:44.520 --> 02:38:45.899
We've caught a few things too.

02:38:45.959 --> 02:38:47.579
Let's take all this back to the pray

02:38:47.579 --> 02:38:48.479
center and eat there.

02:38:48.540 --> 02:38:50.340
Another sea wing.

02:38:50.399 --> 02:38:52.680
This one, a blue green adult dragon with

02:38:52.680 --> 02:38:54.540
a scar on his side, had joined them with

02:38:54.540 --> 02:38:56.700
a net, which was now full of squirming

02:38:56.700 --> 02:38:57.000
fish.

02:38:57.059 --> 02:38:59.639
He hefted it in his talons and nodded to

02:38:59.639 --> 02:39:02.040
tsunami, who tilted her wings and soared

02:39:02.040 --> 02:39:03.239
back toward Jade Mountain.

02:39:03.299 --> 02:39:06.600
The others followed her, one by one, with

02:39:06.600 --> 02:39:08.100
moon flapping slowly at the back.

02:39:08.159 --> 02:39:09.959
The goat was heavy.

02:39:10.139 --> 02:39:12.299
It smelled of meat, and the blood that

02:39:12.299 --> 02:39:14.459
had left dark red streaks on her claws.

02:39:14.579 --> 02:39:16.379
But the thought of going back into the

02:39:16.379 --> 02:39:18.180
prey center was enough to make her lose

02:39:18.180 --> 02:39:18.840
her appetite.

02:39:18.899 --> 02:39:21.479
The noise, the memory of everyone's

02:39:21.479 --> 02:39:22.020
staring at her.

02:39:22.079 --> 02:39:24.899
She was tempted to get lost on the way.

02:39:24.959 --> 02:39:28.559
If you are always cowering in a cave

02:39:28.559 --> 02:39:28.920
alone.

02:39:28.979 --> 02:39:31.139
You'll be wasting your powers completely

02:39:31.139 --> 02:39:32.520
the voice muttered.

02:39:32.639 --> 02:39:34.260
Easy for you to say.

02:39:34.319 --> 02:39:35.639
Moon shot back.

02:39:35.700 --> 02:39:37.620
Clearly, you don't get splitting

02:39:37.620 --> 02:39:39.059
headaches every time you walk into a

02:39:39.059 --> 02:39:39.420
crowd.

02:39:39.479 --> 02:39:42.780
Why has no one taken care of you?

02:39:42.840 --> 02:39:44.040
The voice wondered.

02:39:44.159 --> 02:39:47.159
Even if the skills are lost, there must

02:39:47.159 --> 02:39:48.959
be scrolls about coping techniques.

02:39:49.020 --> 02:39:52.440
No one thinks I need scrolls like that

02:39:52.440 --> 02:39:55.620
even if they do still exist, Moon pointed

02:39:55.620 --> 02:39:55.979
out.

02:39:55.979 --> 02:39:59.159
If anyone found out what I can do, I'd

02:39:59.159 --> 02:40:00.659
probably be thrown out of the tribe.

02:40:00.719 --> 02:40:02.879
I'd definitely be thrown out of school.

02:40:02.940 --> 02:40:05.700
I'd probably be thrown off the peak of

02:40:05.700 --> 02:40:07.739
Jade Mountain, or into the ocean.

02:40:07.799 --> 02:40:10.200
This is not a popular power to have right

02:40:10.200 --> 02:40:11.639
now is what I'm trying to say.

02:40:11.700 --> 02:40:14.760
You don't need to be popular if you're

02:40:14.760 --> 02:40:15.120
powerful.

02:40:15.180 --> 02:40:18.180
The voice chuckled, then it stilled for a

02:40:18.180 --> 02:40:21.000
moment, and added musingly, although

02:40:21.000 --> 02:40:22.500
perhaps a little more popularity.

02:40:22.559 --> 02:40:24.479
Would have been helpful in my situation.

02:40:24.540 --> 02:40:27.120
Another thoughtful pause.

02:40:27.239 --> 02:40:30.959
In any case, listen, and perhaps I can

02:40:30.959 --> 02:40:31.139
help.

02:40:31.260 --> 02:40:32.879
I am listening.

02:40:32.940 --> 02:40:36.180
Imagine the sound of ocean waves.

02:40:36.239 --> 02:40:39.479
I've never heard ocean waves, Moon

02:40:39.479 --> 02:40:40.020
admitted.

02:40:40.079 --> 02:40:41.159
What?

02:40:41.219 --> 02:40:42.540
The voice demanded.

02:40:42.600 --> 02:40:44.340
Were you raised under a mountain?

02:40:44.399 --> 02:40:45.600
Fine.

02:40:45.659 --> 02:40:49.319
Then some other repetitive, soothing

02:40:49.319 --> 02:40:50.040
noise.

02:40:50.100 --> 02:40:53.040
Moon caught a wind current and tilted her

02:40:53.040 --> 02:40:55.020
wings, shifting the goat's weight between

02:40:55.020 --> 02:40:55.739
her talons.

02:40:55.799 --> 02:40:57.659
Would rain work?

02:40:57.719 --> 02:40:59.760
Yes, exactly.

02:40:59.819 --> 02:41:02.280
Fill your head with rain.

02:41:02.340 --> 02:41:06.059
Moon thought of all the long, lonely days

02:41:06.059 --> 02:41:08.639
and nights she'd spent hidden in her fern

02:41:08.639 --> 02:41:11.100
burrow, listening to the rain patter on

02:41:11.100 --> 02:41:13.379
the leaves all around her, watching the

02:41:13.379 --> 02:41:15.540
raindrops slowly drip from the ends of

02:41:15.540 --> 02:41:18.600
the curled fronds onto her tail, wishing

02:41:18.600 --> 02:41:20.280
she could hear the approaching whoosh of

02:41:20.280 --> 02:41:21.540
her mother's wings instead.

02:41:21.600 --> 02:41:24.659
You tragic little dragon.

02:41:24.719 --> 02:41:26.639
The voice said sympathetically.

02:41:26.700 --> 02:41:30.479
I'm not a tragic little dragon, Moon

02:41:30.479 --> 02:41:31.079
