02:41:31.139 --> 02:41:32.340
I'm lucky.

02:41:32.399 --> 02:41:34.440
I didn't have to grow up on the volcano.

02:41:34.500 --> 02:41:36.059
Mother saved me.

02:41:36.120 --> 02:41:37.620
Hmm.

02:41:37.739 --> 02:41:40.500
She seems to have a lot of opinions about

02:41:40.500 --> 02:41:42.479
what's best for you, none of which

02:41:42.479 --> 02:41:44.040
involve finding out your preferences

02:41:44.040 --> 02:41:44.159
first.

02:41:44.219 --> 02:41:47.159
Before Moon could defend her mother, he

02:41:47.159 --> 02:41:47.579
went on.

02:41:47.639 --> 02:41:51.479
Now, hold on to that falling rain sound.

02:41:51.540 --> 02:41:54.180
And then imagine that you're taking each

02:41:54.180 --> 02:41:56.399
voice you hear. and slipping it inside

02:41:56.399 --> 02:41:57.420
one of the raindrops.

02:41:57.479 --> 02:42:00.420
Do that, as you enter a cave full of

02:42:00.420 --> 02:42:03.239
dragons, and after a minute, all their

02:42:03.239 --> 02:42:05.700
insignificant mental howling will be

02:42:05.700 --> 02:42:07.079
drowned in the downpour.

02:42:07.139 --> 02:42:09.180
Moon concentrated for a minute.

02:42:09.239 --> 02:42:11.399
The voice chuckled in her mind again.

02:42:11.459 --> 02:42:14.459
Oh, it won't work with mine dragging it.

02:42:14.520 --> 02:42:16.379
I'm not so easily submerged.

02:42:16.440 --> 02:42:19.920
Go try it on that yammering rain wing, or

02:42:19.920 --> 02:42:21.899
the frenetically intelligent, strangely

02:42:21.899 --> 02:42:23.040
desperate sand wing.

02:42:23.100 --> 02:42:26.159
Moon wanted to ask when he meant by

02:42:26.159 --> 02:42:28.500
calling Kibley desperate, but she could

02:42:28.500 --> 02:42:30.180
see the opening to the pray center below

02:42:30.180 --> 02:42:30.299
her.

02:42:30.360 --> 02:42:32.940
Winter and Turtle were already gliding

02:42:32.940 --> 02:42:35.520
down to the entrance, and beyond them, she

02:42:35.520 --> 02:42:38.040
could see the flash of scales and milling

02:42:38.040 --> 02:42:38.459
tales.

02:42:38.520 --> 02:42:41.100
The pray center was as busy today as

02:42:41.100 --> 02:42:42.600
yesterday, if not more so.

02:42:42.600 --> 02:42:45.239
She needed to master this new trick right

02:42:45.239 --> 02:42:45.420
away.

02:42:45.479 --> 02:42:48.120
She beat her wings to soar closer to

02:42:48.120 --> 02:42:50.879
Kinkachu, whose mind was going, I wonder

02:42:50.879 --> 02:42:51.840
what we'll do after lunch.

02:42:51.899 --> 02:42:55.559
Ooh, maybe reading practice or history or

02:42:55.559 --> 02:42:55.979
music.

02:42:56.100 --> 02:42:58.440
Sunny says the sandwings are a

02:42:58.440 --> 02:42:59.760
surprisingly musical tribe.

02:42:59.819 --> 02:43:02.520
Kind of hard to imagine Kibli singing, I

02:43:02.520 --> 02:43:02.879
must say.

02:43:02.940 --> 02:43:04.379
Ha ha.

02:43:04.440 --> 02:43:05.760
Imagine winter singing.

02:43:05.819 --> 02:43:08.639
I wonder if he can scowl and sing and

02:43:08.639 --> 02:43:10.500
look darkly handsome and mortally

02:43:10.500 --> 02:43:12.239
offended all at the same time.

02:43:12.299 --> 02:43:13.620
Probably.

02:43:13.680 --> 02:43:16.319
Oh, I have to remember to take Tamarind

02:43:16.319 --> 02:43:17.579
to where the blackberry bushes are.

02:43:17.639 --> 02:43:19.860
I hope Glory visits us soon.

02:43:19.920 --> 02:43:23.280
Moon imagined collapsing Kinkachu's

02:43:23.280 --> 02:43:25.319
thoughts into a raindrop and whisking

02:43:25.319 --> 02:43:27.420
them into the quiet background storm.

02:43:27.479 --> 02:43:31.020
It almost seemed to work until Kinkaju

02:43:31.020 --> 02:43:33.120
spotted her, turned pink and grinned.

02:43:33.180 --> 02:43:36.780
Her mind went, moon, she's so funny, all

02:43:36.780 --> 02:43:39.000
quiet on the outside, but secretly a

02:43:39.000 --> 02:43:39.840
total fierce face.

02:43:39.899 --> 02:43:42.000
It is more difficult.

02:43:42.059 --> 02:43:43.860
When the thoughts were specifically about

02:43:43.860 --> 02:43:44.100
you.

02:43:44.159 --> 02:43:46.680
The voice in Moon's head pointed out.

02:43:46.739 --> 02:43:49.860
And easier when there are many voices at

02:43:49.860 --> 02:43:50.459
once.

02:43:50.520 --> 02:43:53.340
This works best in a crowded room, not so

02:43:53.340 --> 02:43:55.079
well in a 2 dragon conversation.

02:43:55.139 --> 02:43:57.180
Also, it takes practice.

02:43:57.239 --> 02:44:00.659
I'll practice, Moon vowed.

02:44:00.719 --> 02:44:03.000
She angled her wings and swooped down

02:44:03.000 --> 02:44:05.340
toward the prey center, side by side with

02:44:05.340 --> 02:44:06.120
Kinkachu.

02:44:06.180 --> 02:44:08.280
The hubbub of thoughts rose up to envelop

02:44:08.280 --> 02:44:08.579
her.

02:44:08.639 --> 02:44:10.319
Totally hungry.

02:44:10.379 --> 02:44:12.840
Why must I be in the same cave as her?

02:44:12.899 --> 02:44:14.819
What did I just eat?

02:44:14.879 --> 02:44:18.600
If that medwing makes one more grotesque

02:44:18.600 --> 02:44:19.379
slurping noise.

02:44:19.440 --> 02:44:21.719
The dragonettes weren't in the war.

02:44:21.780 --> 02:44:23.639
It's easy for them to talk about

02:44:23.639 --> 02:44:24.360
forgiveness.

02:44:24.420 --> 02:44:27.239
This papaya tastes boring.

02:44:27.299 --> 02:44:30.540
I guess I normally like papaya.

02:44:30.600 --> 02:44:33.360
But this one is sort of boring all the

02:44:33.360 --> 02:44:33.840
way through.

02:44:33.899 --> 02:44:35.819
Like eating water.

02:44:35.879 --> 02:44:37.920
Boring water.

02:44:37.979 --> 02:44:40.979
I wonder when it will be suntime.

02:44:41.040 --> 02:44:44.100
Maybe I should try a different papaya

02:44:44.100 --> 02:44:44.819
after this one.

02:44:44.879 --> 02:44:47.639
But what if the next papaya?

02:44:47.700 --> 02:44:48.840
Is boring too.

02:44:48.899 --> 02:44:51.540
The last train of thought was clearly

02:44:51.540 --> 02:44:52.559
coming from coconut.

02:44:52.620 --> 02:44:55.500
Moon seized his thoughts and slid them

02:44:55.500 --> 02:44:57.120
into the sound of rain in her mind.

02:44:57.180 --> 02:44:58.500
It worked.

02:44:58.620 --> 02:45:01.079
She waited a minute to be sure she

02:45:01.079 --> 02:45:03.420
couldn't hear him anymore, and then did a

02:45:03.420 --> 02:45:05.459
delighted flip in the sky before landing

02:45:05.459 --> 02:45:07.739
outside the cave, can get you laughed.

02:45:07.860 --> 02:45:09.780
You look happy all of a sudden.

02:45:09.840 --> 02:45:13.379
Just figuring something out, Moon said.

02:45:13.440 --> 02:45:15.719
Coconut and his meaningless thoughts were

02:45:15.719 --> 02:45:16.139
one thing.

02:45:16.200 --> 02:45:18.120
They were practically background noise

02:45:18.120 --> 02:45:18.780
already.

02:45:18.840 --> 02:45:20.879
She reached out to grab the nearest sea

02:45:20.879 --> 02:45:21.659
wings thoughts.

02:45:21.719 --> 02:45:23.639
Lebs brought us fish.

02:45:23.700 --> 02:45:24.959
I could eat his tail.

02:45:25.020 --> 02:45:27.360
I'm so hungry. and tried the same trick.

02:45:27.479 --> 02:45:30.299
Her mental voice melted into the noise

02:45:30.299 --> 02:45:31.799
like just another raindrop.

02:45:31.860 --> 02:45:35.340
This is amazing, Moon thought.

02:45:35.399 --> 02:45:36.180
Thank you.

02:45:36.239 --> 02:45:39.420
It is the 1st trick a mind reading

02:45:39.420 --> 02:45:41.819
Dragonette learns, the voice said.

02:45:41.879 --> 02:45:43.680
Otherwise, they could go mad.

02:45:43.799 --> 02:45:45.899
You should have had these lessons soon

02:45:45.899 --> 02:45:46.500
after hatching.

02:45:46.559 --> 02:45:49.440
It is rather a wonder you're as tenuously

02:45:49.440 --> 02:45:50.159
sane as you are.

02:45:50.219 --> 02:45:53.340
Very funny, Moon thought back.

02:45:53.399 --> 02:45:56.040
But seriously, I was alone most of the

02:45:56.040 --> 02:45:56.280
time.

02:45:56.340 --> 02:45:58.139
So it was never this bad before.

02:45:58.200 --> 02:46:00.600
Luckily, I didn't need to shut out the

02:46:00.600 --> 02:46:01.799
sloths and toucans.

02:46:01.860 --> 02:46:04.260
She noticed Kinkaju watching her

02:46:04.260 --> 02:46:04.860
curiously.

02:46:04.920 --> 02:46:06.360
Are you all right?

02:46:06.420 --> 02:46:07.799
The rain wing asked.

02:46:07.860 --> 02:46:09.959
You looked like your head was taking a

02:46:09.959 --> 02:46:11.399
walk on one of the moons for a minute.

02:46:11.459 --> 02:46:13.620
What does that look like?

02:46:13.680 --> 02:46:14.819
Moon asked.

02:46:14.940 --> 02:46:17.219
Kinkachoo's scales turned purplish

02:46:17.219 --> 02:46:17.520
black.

02:46:17.579 --> 02:46:20.280
She wrinkled her nose and gave the tip of

02:46:20.280 --> 02:46:23.520
the mountain a glassy eyed stare, talons

02:46:23.520 --> 02:46:24.299
and tails.

02:46:24.360 --> 02:46:25.739
Moon said giggling.

02:46:25.799 --> 02:46:27.479
Please tell me I don't really make that

02:46:27.479 --> 02:46:28.020
face.

02:46:28.079 --> 02:46:31.979
Fish, shouted several dragons inside the

02:46:31.979 --> 02:46:32.520
