Moon and Kinkaju edged past the flapping

02:46:44.639 --> 02:46:46.799
mass of wings, and found a spot near the

02:46:46.799 --> 02:46:48.780
river where Moon could slice up her goat

02:46:48.780 --> 02:46:50.940
while Kinkaju raided the fruit pile.

02:46:51.000 --> 02:46:54.360
Raindrops, Moon thought, battling the

02:46:54.360 --> 02:46:55.079
noise in her head.

02:46:55.139 --> 02:46:56.700
She took a deep breath.

02:46:56.760 --> 02:46:58.739
It's all raindrops.

02:46:58.799 --> 02:47:01.620
She was concentrating so hard that she

02:47:01.620 --> 02:47:03.659
jumped when Kibley swept up and sat down

02:47:03.659 --> 02:47:04.139
next to her.

02:47:04.260 --> 02:47:07.799
Sorry. he said, tilting his wings away

02:47:07.799 --> 02:47:08.159
from her.

02:47:08.219 --> 02:47:10.979
You said the goat, remember?

02:47:11.040 --> 02:47:13.020
But if you changed your mind, no

02:47:13.020 --> 02:47:13.440
worries.

02:47:13.500 --> 02:47:15.000
I can go wrestle for a fish instead.

02:47:15.059 --> 02:47:17.040
Another fish.

02:47:17.159 --> 02:47:18.600
How unappealing.

02:47:18.659 --> 02:47:21.420
Not sure I'll ever get used to slimy, wet

02:47:21.420 --> 02:47:23.159
sea creatures sliding down my throat.

02:47:23.219 --> 02:47:25.200
But I don't want her to think I can't

02:47:25.200 --> 02:47:25.739
feed myself.

02:47:25.799 --> 02:47:27.540
Maybe I'm not that hungry.

02:47:27.600 --> 02:47:29.760
No, of course.

02:47:29.819 --> 02:47:31.620
Here, Moon said.

02:47:31.680 --> 02:47:33.899
She used her claws to slice away half of

02:47:33.899 --> 02:47:35.100
the goat and pushed it toward him.

02:47:35.159 --> 02:47:37.979
I could totally get a fish away from all

02:47:37.979 --> 02:47:40.440
those dragons, Kibley informed her, in

02:47:40.440 --> 02:47:41.100
case you were wondering.

02:47:41.159 --> 02:47:43.260
If living in the rainforest on your own

02:47:43.260 --> 02:47:45.180
makes you good at hunting, then let me

02:47:45.180 --> 02:47:47.100
tell you, being a dragonette in the

02:47:47.100 --> 02:47:49.500
scorpion den, with a family who hates you

02:47:49.500 --> 02:47:51.180
makes you really good at stealing

02:47:51.180 --> 02:47:53.700
fighting, scrounging, and tricking

02:47:53.700 --> 02:47:55.379
dragons into looking the other way while

02:47:55.379 --> 02:47:56.760
you nab their roasted camels.

02:47:56.879 --> 02:47:59.399
Why did your family hate you?

02:47:59.459 --> 02:48:00.479
Moon asked.

02:48:00.600 --> 02:48:01.860
Oh.

02:48:01.920 --> 02:48:03.959
He looked awkward for a minute.

02:48:04.020 --> 02:48:05.579
They sort of hate everyone.

02:48:05.639 --> 02:48:06.420
It's no big deal.

02:48:06.479 --> 02:48:09.299
Moon could sense that it had certainly

02:48:09.299 --> 02:48:11.219
been a big deal for the 1st 3 years of

02:48:11.219 --> 02:48:12.059
his life, at least.

02:48:12.120 --> 02:48:14.700
The pace of his conscious thoughts slowed

02:48:14.700 --> 02:48:16.559
for a moment, and she caught a flash of

02:48:16.559 --> 02:48:19.379
his mother, a large sandwing with snake

02:48:19.379 --> 02:48:21.899
like patterns down her spine, hissing at

02:48:21.899 --> 02:48:23.760
tiny Kibley and 2 other bigger

02:48:23.760 --> 02:48:24.420
dragonettes.

02:48:24.479 --> 02:48:26.700
She saw his brother and sister beating

02:48:26.700 --> 02:48:28.319
him, and threatening him with their

02:48:28.319 --> 02:48:31.079
venomous tails, just to steal his talon

02:48:31.079 --> 02:48:32.159
full of date palms.

02:48:32.219 --> 02:48:35.399
She saw an old male sandwing radiating

02:48:35.399 --> 02:48:37.500
authority, stalking through to inspect

02:48:37.500 --> 02:48:38.940
them with beauty black eyes.

02:48:39.000 --> 02:48:42.059
She saw little Kibley, offering a stolen

02:48:42.059 --> 02:48:44.520
coconut to his mother, his face hopeful

02:48:44.520 --> 02:48:46.860
and she saw him thrown against a wall for

02:48:46.860 --> 02:48:47.579
weakness instead.

02:48:47.639 --> 02:48:50.399
None of that was going to fit in a

02:48:50.399 --> 02:48:50.940
raindrop.

02:48:51.000 --> 02:48:55.200
I'm sorry, she said to Kibley, and then

02:48:55.200 --> 02:48:56.760
gasped with sudden pain.

02:48:56.819 --> 02:48:58.920
She couldn't stop herself from doubling

02:48:58.920 --> 02:49:01.139
over as a new vision blistered through

02:49:01.139 --> 02:49:01.620
her mind.

02:49:01.680 --> 02:49:03.540
This wasn't a passing memory.

02:49:03.600 --> 02:49:06.000
Those were always a little blurred and

02:49:06.000 --> 02:49:07.739
jumbled together with a dragon's other

02:49:07.739 --> 02:49:10.620
thoughts, but visions like this, scenes

02:49:10.620 --> 02:49:13.440
of the future, came bright and clear, even

02:49:13.440 --> 02:49:15.959
if just for a moment, usually along with

02:49:15.959 --> 02:49:17.219
a lightning sharp headache.

02:49:17.280 --> 02:49:20.399
In this one, the same old sand wing

02:49:20.399 --> 02:49:22.739
loomed over Kibley, his snout twisted

02:49:22.739 --> 02:49:23.219
with hatred.

02:49:23.280 --> 02:49:26.159
Behind him hulked Kibley's brother and

02:49:26.159 --> 02:49:28.500
sister, now fully grown and even more

02:49:28.500 --> 02:49:31.079
menacing, wearing medallions etched with

02:49:31.079 --> 02:49:32.219
some kind of bird.

02:49:32.280 --> 02:49:34.559
Kibley curled his tail up dangerously and

02:49:34.559 --> 02:49:36.360
shouted, where is she?

02:49:36.420 --> 02:49:37.920
into their sneering faces.

02:49:37.979 --> 02:49:41.399
Hey, she heard his voice saying in the

02:49:41.399 --> 02:49:41.879
real world.

02:49:41.940 --> 02:49:43.860
Whoa, what happened?

02:49:43.920 --> 02:49:44.459
Moon?

02:49:44.579 --> 02:49:45.540
Everything all right?

02:49:45.600 --> 02:49:48.479
Moon blinked, shaking the vision away.

02:49:48.540 --> 02:49:51.059
The pale gray walls of the prey center

02:49:51.059 --> 02:49:52.440
came back into focus around her.

02:49:52.500 --> 02:49:55.020
Bright sunlight reached across the floor

02:49:55.020 --> 02:49:57.180
to glint off Kibley's amber earring.

02:49:57.299 --> 02:49:59.399
One of his talons was resting lightly on

02:49:59.399 --> 02:50:01.739
hers, and his mind was spiraling with

02:50:01.739 --> 02:50:03.120
curiosity and concern.

02:50:03.180 --> 02:50:06.000
Yes, sorry, it's nothing.

02:50:06.059 --> 02:50:07.020
She said.

02:50:07.079 --> 02:50:08.579
I get these headaches.

02:50:08.639 --> 02:50:09.840
It's gone now.

02:50:09.899 --> 02:50:10.979
Sorry.

02:50:11.040 --> 02:50:13.200
You were saying about your family?

02:50:13.260 --> 02:50:16.020
Does she really want to know?

02:50:16.079 --> 02:50:17.399
Kibley wondered.

02:50:17.459 --> 02:50:18.899
Or is she distracting me?

02:50:18.959 --> 02:50:20.159
Should I be worried?

02:50:20.280 --> 02:50:22.379
Headaches like that don't sound normal.

02:50:22.440 --> 02:50:25.200
Thorn took sword leaf root for her

02:50:25.200 --> 02:50:25.680
headaches.

02:50:25.739 --> 02:50:27.540
I wonder if I can find some of that for

02:50:27.540 --> 02:50:27.899
Moon.

02:50:28.020 --> 02:50:29.520
My family.

02:50:29.639 --> 02:50:31.799
She doesn't need to know all the horrible

02:50:31.799 --> 02:50:32.280
details.

02:50:32.340 --> 02:50:34.860
It's all sand in the wind now anyway.

02:50:34.979 --> 02:50:37.379
He shrugged casually.

02:50:37.440 --> 02:50:40.620
I joined the outlaws when I was 3, and

02:50:40.620 --> 02:50:41.940
mother was happy to shove me out the

02:50:41.940 --> 02:50:42.180
door.

02:50:42.239 --> 02:50:44.940
The best news of my life is that I'll

02:50:44.940 --> 02:50:46.379
never have to see any of my family ever

02:50:46.379 --> 02:50:46.739
again.

02:50:46.799 --> 02:50:51.600
But that's not true, Moon realized, not

02:50:51.600 --> 02:50:52.680
according to her vision.

02:50:52.739 --> 02:50:55.139
If that was really the future, then

02:50:55.139 --> 02:50:57.059
Kibley's awful family wasn't done with

02:50:57.059 --> 02:50:57.360
him yet.

02:50:57.420 --> 02:50:59.159
What do they want from him?

02:50:59.219 --> 02:51:01.920
Who was the old male sandwing?

02:51:01.920 --> 02:51:03.479
And who was the she?

02:51:03.600 --> 02:51:04.680
Kibli had been asking about?

02:51:04.739 --> 02:51:06.600
His mother, Thorn?

02:51:06.659 --> 02:51:08.700
I wish I could warn him.

02:51:08.760 --> 02:51:10.559
I wish I could save him.

02:51:10.620 --> 02:51:13.319
Moon turned back to her lunch with a

02:51:13.319 --> 02:51:13.739
sigh.

02:51:13.799 --> 02:51:15.899
If only she lived in a world where

02:51:15.899 --> 02:51:17.520
dragons weren't afraid of her powers

02:51:17.520 --> 02:51:19.440
where she could tell everyone about them

02:51:19.440 --> 02:51:22.020
without losing her new friends, a world

02:51:22.020 --> 02:51:24.000
where they'd believe her, and wouldn't

02:51:24.000 --> 02:51:24.959
hate her for what she could do.

02:51:25.020 --> 02:51:27.659
If only the night wings hadn't ruined

02:51:27.659 --> 02:51:29.219
everything with their centuries of lies.

02:51:29.280 --> 02:51:32.280
Then I could do some good with everything

02:51:32.280 --> 02:51:33.780
rattling around in my brain.

02:51:33.840 --> 02:51:36.180
I could use it to help dragons, couldn't

02:51:36.180 --> 02:51:36.299
I?

02:51:36.360 --> 02:51:39.120
Her mystery voice didn't respond.

02:51:39.180 --> 02:51:41.760
I have to go to the library.

02:51:41.819 --> 02:51:43.020
Moon remembered.

02:51:43.079 --> 02:51:45.899
Maybe I can't help Kibley, but if I can

02:51:45.899 --> 02:51:47.879
find out about the dream visitors and

02:51:47.879 --> 02:51:50.520
figure out whom I heard last night, maybe

02:51:50.520 --> 02:51:52.260
I can still save someone.

02:51:52.319 --> 02:51:56.819
Chapter 8.

02:51:56.879 --> 02:52:00.959
I should go, Moon said to Kingajoo.

02:52:01.020 --> 02:52:02.639
As soon as the rain wing came back from

02:52:02.639 --> 02:52:03.299
the fruit pile.

02:52:03.360 --> 02:52:06.479
No, Kinkitu cried, we're eating

02:52:06.479 --> 02:52:06.959
together.

02:52:07.020 --> 02:52:08.940
You haven't even finished your hairy

02:52:08.940 --> 02:52:10.680
smelly carcass thing, sit.

02:52:10.799 --> 02:52:12.840
She nudged Moon back to sitting.

02:52:12.899 --> 02:52:15.899
Just for 5 minutes, she wheedled.

02:52:15.959 --> 02:52:18.540
Moon wanted to argue, but there was a

02:52:18.540 --> 02:52:20.579
threat of anxiety in Kingachu's mind.

02:52:20.639 --> 02:52:21.840
Don't leave me alone.

02:52:21.899 --> 02:52:24.659
Please stay and be my best friend, that

02:52:24.659 --> 02:52:25.440
she couldn't resist.

02:52:25.500 --> 02:52:26.879
Sure.

02:52:26.940 --> 02:52:29.819
Okay, she said, and was rewarded with

02:52:29.819 --> 02:52:31.020
glowing pink scales.

02:52:31.079 --> 02:52:33.239
Can you tone that down?

02:52:33.299 --> 02:52:36.299
Umber asked Kingachu, as he and Turtle

02:52:36.299 --> 02:52:37.920
joined them, each carrying a fish.

02:52:37.979 --> 02:52:40.739
I mean, it's a very exciting color that I

02:52:40.739 --> 02:52:43.079
can say I've ever seen before, but it's a

02:52:43.079 --> 02:52:45.959
little bright, suggested turtle.

02:52:46.020 --> 02:52:48.059
Noticeable?

02:52:48.120 --> 02:52:48.780
Tried umber.

02:52:48.840 --> 02:52:52.200
Eyeball scorching, offered Kibley.

02:52:52.260 --> 02:52:54.959
This happens when I'm happy.

02:52:55.020 --> 02:52:57.000
Kinkachu said, unruffled.

02:52:57.059 --> 02:52:59.760
But if you prefer something more sedate

02:52:59.760 --> 02:53:02.940
she turned a vibrant shade of lime green

02:53:02.940 --> 02:53:05.700
splashed with violet spots, moon nearly

02:53:05.700 --> 02:53:07.260
choked on her goat.

02:53:07.319 --> 02:53:07.979
Ah!

02:53:08.040 --> 02:53:09.959
Kibli yelped, covering his eyes.

02:53:10.020 --> 02:53:13.139
I don't actually know you, Umber said to

02:53:13.139 --> 02:53:13.799
Kingaju.

02:53:13.860 --> 02:53:15.719
You might be totally serious right now.

02:53:15.780 --> 02:53:17.879
No, I'm just kidding.

02:53:17.940 --> 02:53:20.520
Kinkachu said with a giggle, bumping moon

02:53:20.520 --> 02:53:21.180
side again.

02:53:21.239 --> 02:53:23.819
I can be totally ordinary and boring.

02:53:23.879 --> 02:53:24.299
Don't worry.

02:53:24.360 --> 02:53:27.659
Her scales shifted again, rippling to the

02:53:27.659 --> 02:53:30.059
same quiet brown as umbers, and she gave

02:53:30.059 --> 02:53:31.920
him a wide eyed, see?

02:53:31.979 --> 02:53:33.479
Boring stare.

02:53:33.600 --> 02:53:36.719
Boring hasn't exactly made it onto my

02:53:36.719 --> 02:53:38.579
list of words to describe you, Moon

02:53:38.579 --> 02:53:39.000
said.

02:53:39.059 --> 02:53:41.639
Winter, Kinkachu shouted.

02:53:41.639 --> 02:53:43.799
The ice wing paused in the act of

02:53:43.799 --> 02:53:45.659
sweeping majestically past them.

02:53:45.719 --> 02:53:48.780
Yes, he said frostily to Kingachu.

02:53:48.840 --> 02:53:50.520
Don't you want to sit with us?

02:53:50.579 --> 02:53:51.959
Kinkachu asked.

02:53:52.020 --> 02:53:54.000
I mean, since we're your winglet now and

02:53:54.000 --> 02:53:54.299
everything?

02:53:54.420 --> 02:53:57.540
A wave of ice blue shimmered across her

02:53:57.540 --> 02:54:00.180
scales and then vanished again. moon

02:54:00.180 --> 02:54:02.819
tried and failed to stuff all the dreamy

02:54:02.819 --> 02:54:04.620
thoughts from Kinkachu's head into a

02:54:04.620 --> 02:54:05.219
raindrop.

02:54:05.280 --> 02:54:07.620
Winter looked down his nose at the rain

02:54:07.620 --> 02:54:07.979
wing.

02:54:08.040 --> 02:54:12.600
Absolutely not, he said, and stalked away

02:54:12.600 --> 02:54:14.639
toward another ice wing perched on a

02:54:14.639 --> 02:54:16.319
ledge slightly above the rest of the

02:54:16.319 --> 02:54:16.739
dragons.

02:54:16.799 --> 02:54:19.079
He's so tortured.

02:54:19.139 --> 02:54:21.180
Kingachu sighed happily.

02:54:21.239 --> 02:54:24.600
You're a little weird, Moon pointed out.

02:54:24.659 --> 02:54:27.479
Kinkachu was about to reply when a hush

02:54:27.479 --> 02:54:28.319
fell over the cave.

02:54:28.379 --> 02:54:31.500
They all twisted around and saw anemone

02:54:31.500 --> 02:54:33.120
pace slowly through the door with her

02:54:33.120 --> 02:54:35.879
head held high, followed by a thin, quiet

02:54:35.879 --> 02:54:36.959
looking sand wing.

02:54:37.020 --> 02:54:40.739
The sea wing princess, rippled through

02:54:40.739 --> 02:54:41.639
everyone's minds.

02:54:41.700 --> 02:54:46.319
Oh, thank the moons, anemone said

02:54:46.319 --> 02:54:48.780
spotting the net of fish, her voice clear

02:54:48.780 --> 02:54:49.260
and high.

02:54:49.319 --> 02:54:51.719
I haven't eaten since we left Queen

02:54:51.719 --> 02:54:52.979
Morehan's palace yesterday.

02:54:53.040 --> 02:54:56.280
She stepped delicately around a sand wing

02:54:56.280 --> 02:54:57.360
who was chewing something on the floor

02:54:57.360 --> 02:55:00.000
and surveyed the few small fish that

02:55:00.000 --> 02:55:01.020
hadn't been claimed yet.

02:55:01.079 --> 02:55:04.200
A number of mud wings, sea wings, and sky

02:55:04.200 --> 02:55:07.139
wings were clustered nearby, brown and

02:55:07.139 --> 02:55:09.840
green and red scales side by side as they

02:55:09.840 --> 02:55:10.260
ate.

02:55:10.319 --> 02:55:11.399
Hmm.

02:55:11.520 --> 02:55:15.780
I'd like that one, Anemone said sweetly.

02:55:15.840 --> 02:55:18.780
She pointed at a giant gray fish with a

02:55:18.780 --> 02:55:21.659
pale speckled pink belly, a night wing

02:55:21.659 --> 02:55:24.299
the one moon didn't know, already had his

02:55:24.299 --> 02:55:26.159
claws around it, and was lifting it to

02:55:26.159 --> 02:55:26.340
his mouth.

02:55:26.459 --> 02:55:28.920
He paused and stared at her.

02:55:28.920 --> 02:55:31.319
She gazed back innocently, her chin

02:55:31.319 --> 02:55:31.799
raised.

02:55:31.860 --> 02:55:34.979
Oh, said the night wing.

02:55:35.040 --> 02:55:36.000
This one?

02:55:36.059 --> 02:55:39.059
That one, said Anemone.

02:55:39.120 --> 02:55:40.860
It's my favorite kind.

02:55:40.920 --> 02:55:43.799
This one, the time eating, he said.

02:55:43.860 --> 02:55:47.159
You heard her, snapped one of the sea

02:55:47.159 --> 02:55:47.700
wings.

02:55:47.760 --> 02:55:49.979
A skinny grayish blue dragon whose

02:55:49.979 --> 02:55:51.360
hostile mental vibration seemed

02:55:51.360 --> 02:55:52.379
familiar.

02:55:52.440 --> 02:55:54.600
Moon thought for a minute, and then

02:55:54.600 --> 02:55:56.579
guessed that he was the same one Clay had

02:55:56.579 --> 02:55:58.079
separated from carnelian in the hallway

02:55:58.079 --> 02:55:58.620
yesterday.

02:55:58.680 --> 02:56:01.020
Pike, if she remembered right.

02:56:01.079 --> 02:56:06.299
But I'm eating this one, said the night

02:56:06.299 --> 02:56:08.280
wing, in a tone of deep confusion.

02:56:08.340 --> 02:56:12.059
Oh, but I would like it very match, said

02:56:12.059 --> 02:56:12.659
Anemone.

02:56:12.719 --> 02:56:14.399
Anemone.

02:56:14.459 --> 02:56:16.440
Tsunami tried to interrupt, stepping

02:56:16.440 --> 02:56:16.739
forward.

02:56:16.799 --> 02:56:19.620
Don't you know this is the sea wing

02:56:19.620 --> 02:56:20.100
princess?

02:56:20.159 --> 02:56:21.540
Pike snarled.

02:56:21.600 --> 02:56:23.760
He shoved himself in the night wing's

02:56:23.760 --> 02:56:25.500
face and flexed his webbed talons.

02:56:25.559 --> 02:56:27.299
The heir to the throne.

02:56:27.360 --> 02:56:29.040
Give her the fish, now.

02:56:29.100 --> 02:56:32.280
Ah, said the night wing.

02:56:32.340 --> 02:56:35.579
She's not my princess, though, his brain

02:56:35.579 --> 02:56:36.180
mumbled.

02:56:36.239 --> 02:56:38.459
Clay hurried over through the silence

02:56:38.459 --> 02:56:40.379
that had slowly fallen around Pike

02:56:40.379 --> 02:56:42.000
anemone and the night wing.

02:56:42.000 --> 02:56:43.920
Most of the other dragons were staring at

02:56:43.920 --> 02:56:46.620
them, except for Coconut, who was deeply

02:56:46.620 --> 02:56:47.760
focused on a bunch of grapes.

02:56:47.819 --> 02:56:51.299
Hey, this is an understandable mistake

02:56:51.299 --> 02:56:52.620
Clay said.

02:56:52.680 --> 02:56:54.659
Gently scooting the night wing back away

02:56:54.659 --> 02:56:55.260
from Pike.

02:56:55.319 --> 02:56:58.260
We haven't posted any prey center rules

02:56:58.260 --> 02:56:59.459
yet, but we will.

02:56:59.520 --> 02:57:02.700
Basically, whoever gets their claws on it

02:57:02.700 --> 02:57:04.440
first, they get to eat it.

02:57:04.559 --> 02:57:07.319
If we find that doesn't work, we'll

02:57:07.319 --> 02:57:09.180
revisit the rules in a couple of weeks

02:57:09.180 --> 02:57:10.620
but that's how it is right now.

02:57:10.680 --> 02:57:11.760
All right?

02:57:11.819 --> 02:57:13.680
Pike scowled.

02:57:13.739 --> 02:57:15.780
But the princess wants that fish.

02:57:15.840 --> 02:57:18.479
This one's going to be trouble.

02:57:18.540 --> 02:57:21.780
Moon heard from Clay's mind, clear as

02:57:21.780 --> 02:57:22.139
day.

02:57:22.200 --> 02:57:23.100
He sighed.

02:57:23.219 --> 02:57:25.799
I do, Anemone agreed.

02:57:25.860 --> 02:57:27.959
She looked up at clay with large blue

02:57:27.959 --> 02:57:28.500
eyes.

02:57:28.559 --> 02:57:30.479
Mother would want me to have it.

02:57:30.540 --> 02:57:35.219
There's lots of other fish, Clay said, and

02:57:35.219 --> 02:57:36.659
you're welcome to join us in the evening

02:57:36.659 --> 02:57:38.760
when we go out to catch more in one of

02:57:38.760 --> 02:57:39.780
the mountain lakes.

02:57:39.899 --> 02:57:43.559
That'll be fun, Tsunami said, elbowing

02:57:43.559 --> 02:57:44.520
her sister heartily.

02:57:44.579 --> 02:57:45.540
I'll come too.

02:57:45.600 --> 02:57:47.280
There are some awesome lakes I want to

02:57:47.280 --> 02:57:48.299
show you, not far from here.

02:57:48.420 --> 02:57:50.280
Anemone blinked.

02:57:50.340 --> 02:57:52.799
She looked from clay to tsunami, and then

02:57:52.799 --> 02:57:54.959
narrowed her eyes at the night wing, who

02:57:54.959 --> 02:57:56.700
was surreptitiously starting to chew on

02:57:56.700 --> 02:57:57.479
the fish's tail.

02:57:57.540 --> 02:58:00.000
So that's how it's going to be?

02:58:00.059 --> 02:58:03.840
I don't like this at all. said her mind

02:58:03.840 --> 02:58:07.500
but her mouth said, oh, very well.

02:58:07.620 --> 02:58:10.440
Moon wondered if she'd imagined the ghost

02:58:10.440 --> 02:58:12.420
of a smile that whisked across Turtle's

02:58:12.420 --> 02:58:12.659
face.

02:58:12.719 --> 02:58:16.799
You can have my fish princess, Pike said

02:58:16.799 --> 02:58:18.959
handing her a dripping salmon that he'd

02:58:18.959 --> 02:58:20.399
already sliced lengthwise with his

02:58:20.399 --> 02:58:20.819
claws.

02:58:20.819 --> 02:58:23.399
Anemone looked down her nose at it, then

02:58:23.399 --> 02:58:24.000
shook her head.

02:58:24.059 --> 02:58:26.459
I'm not actually that hungry after all.

02:58:26.520 --> 02:58:28.200
Come on, ostrich.

02:58:28.319 --> 02:58:31.200
She swept out of the cave, deliberately

02:58:31.200 --> 02:58:32.159
avoiding clay.

02:58:32.219 --> 02:58:34.559
The sand wing glanced around, thinking

02:58:34.559 --> 02:58:36.600
disappointed, hungry thoughts, but

02:58:36.600 --> 02:58:37.739
hurried after the princess.

02:58:37.799 --> 02:58:39.959
Pike hissed at the night wing.

02:58:40.020 --> 02:58:42.959
You'll pay for this big tail, he

02:58:42.959 --> 02:58:43.500
snarled.

02:58:43.559 --> 02:58:45.719
Nobody disrespects the sea wing

02:58:45.719 --> 02:58:46.139
princess.

02:58:46.200 --> 02:58:50.459
Time to cool down, Pike, Tsunami said

02:58:50.459 --> 02:58:51.000
sternly.

02:58:51.059 --> 02:58:53.760
Pike hissed again. but slunk off with his

02:58:53.760 --> 02:58:54.059
salmon.

02:58:54.180 --> 02:58:57.959
Oh, dear, thought Clay.

02:58:58.020 --> 02:59:00.420
Moon watched him smile at the night wing

02:59:00.420 --> 02:59:02.219
as if nothing was wrong, and then give

02:59:02.219 --> 02:59:04.379
tsunami a, we should talk about that.

02:59:04.440 --> 02:59:05.040
Look.

02:59:05.100 --> 02:59:07.260
She rolled her eyes and hurried after her

02:59:07.260 --> 02:59:07.620
sister.

02:59:07.680 --> 02:59:10.979
Umber's whole face lit up as Clay paced

02:59:10.979 --> 02:59:11.459
over to them.

02:59:11.520 --> 02:59:15.120
Hey, Clay said affectionately, nudging

02:59:15.120 --> 02:59:15.780
his little brother.

02:59:15.899 --> 02:59:17.639
We're a marsh and sora.

02:59:17.700 --> 02:59:19.319
Coming over now.

02:59:19.379 --> 02:59:21.299
Umber said, waving his wings.

02:59:21.420 --> 02:59:24.239
Moon sat up and saw Sora approaching with

02:59:24.239 --> 02:59:26.520
another dragon who looked like her, only

02:59:26.520 --> 02:59:27.719
more fidgety and nervous.

02:59:27.780 --> 02:59:30.479
Sora's expression was subdued, but

02:59:30.479 --> 02:59:33.420
painful anxiety clawed at her insides, all

02:59:33.420 --> 02:59:35.100
jumbled into scraps of thoughts.

02:59:35.159 --> 02:59:36.299
Are we safe?

02:59:36.360 --> 02:59:37.440
Miss Reed.

02:59:37.559 --> 02:59:38.940
I saw her.

02:59:39.000 --> 02:59:40.680
Can't sleep, not safe anywhere.

02:59:40.739 --> 02:59:42.120
Oh, crane.

02:59:42.239 --> 02:59:43.260
I wish you were here.

02:59:43.319 --> 02:59:46.200
The mud wing took a deep breath, and

02:59:46.200 --> 02:59:48.540
started the same internal ritual Moon had

02:59:48.540 --> 02:59:49.559
found her in the night before.

02:59:49.620 --> 02:59:53.760
Zora imagined mud, slowly poring over all

02:59:53.760 --> 02:59:56.159
her worries, leaving only a rippling

02:59:56.159 --> 02:59:57.059
peaceful swamp.

02:59:57.120 --> 03:00:00.479
She is like me, Moon thought.

03:00:00.540 --> 03:00:03.600
Everyone here was anxious in some way, but

03:00:03.600 --> 03:00:06.360
with Sora, it ran deeper, all the way to

03:00:06.360 --> 03:00:07.139
paralyzing fear.

03:00:07.260 --> 03:00:09.659
She wanted to escape as much as Moon

03:00:09.659 --> 03:00:09.899
did.

03:00:09.959 --> 03:00:13.020
Or at least the way I wanted to escape

03:00:13.020 --> 03:00:13.620
yesterday.

03:00:13.680 --> 03:00:15.299
Now.

03:00:15.479 --> 03:00:18.659
Well, she had to admit, now she was

03:00:18.659 --> 03:00:20.100
wondering if maybe her mother was right.

03:00:20.159 --> 03:00:22.500
Maybe school wasn't so terrible after

03:00:22.500 --> 03:00:22.739
all.

03:00:22.799 --> 03:00:24.719
Poor Zora.

03:00:24.780 --> 03:00:27.719
She needs a crazy enthusiastic clawmate

03:00:27.719 --> 03:00:29.100
like Kinkaju to take care of her.

03:00:29.159 --> 03:00:30.840
Or maybe I can help her.

03:00:30.899 --> 03:00:33.659
Maybe because I know how scared she is.

03:00:33.780 --> 03:00:35.520
Maybe I can make her feel better.

03:00:35.579 --> 03:00:38.219
Maybe that's one good thing I can do with

03:00:38.219 --> 03:00:38.700
my powers.

03:00:38.760 --> 03:00:42.899
This is my brother and sister, Umber

03:00:42.899 --> 03:00:43.200
said.

03:00:43.260 --> 03:00:44.940
Marsh is really fast.

03:00:45.000 --> 03:00:47.639
You should see him fly, and Sora knows

03:00:47.639 --> 03:00:48.239
everything.

03:00:48.299 --> 03:00:50.340
She's the only one who ever practiced her

03:00:50.340 --> 03:00:50.639
reading.

03:00:50.700 --> 03:00:53.340
He beamed at them both as if they were

03:00:53.340 --> 03:00:55.500
the most special, perfect dragons in the

03:00:55.500 --> 03:00:55.799
world.

03:00:55.860 --> 03:00:59.219
Hey, Kibley greeted them, his mouth half

03:00:59.219 --> 03:00:59.819
full of goat.

03:00:59.879 --> 03:01:01.559
He looked as though he wasn't

03:01:01.559 --> 03:01:03.780
particularly paying attention, but a part

03:01:03.780 --> 03:01:06.180
of him whispered, That's the mud wing

03:01:06.180 --> 03:01:06.899
sibling bond.

03:01:06.959 --> 03:01:10.200
Loyal like the outlaws are to Thorn

03:01:10.200 --> 03:01:11.280
probably more so.

03:01:11.340 --> 03:01:13.799
Wish I had a brother and sister I liked

03:01:13.799 --> 03:01:14.280
that much.

03:01:14.340 --> 03:01:17.280
Actually, a brother and sister who didn't

03:01:17.280 --> 03:01:18.899
actively try to kill me every time they

03:01:18.899 --> 03:01:21.000
see me would be a dramatic improvement.

03:01:21.059 --> 03:01:23.340
I'm moon, remember?

03:01:23.399 --> 03:01:25.680
Moon said to Sora, trying to look

03:01:25.680 --> 03:01:27.059
friendly and non-threatening.

03:01:27.180 --> 03:01:28.319
Would you like some?

03:01:28.440 --> 03:01:30.479
She held out a piece of her prey.

03:01:30.540 --> 03:01:32.340
So I gave her a shy smile.

03:01:32.399 --> 03:01:33.719
Thank you.

03:01:33.840 --> 03:01:36.840
She took the goat leg in her claws, tore

03:01:36.840 --> 03:01:38.399
it in half, and gave the other half to

03:01:38.399 --> 03:01:38.700
Marsh.

03:01:38.760 --> 03:01:41.040
Who's in your winglet?

03:01:41.040 --> 03:01:42.059
Umber asked.

03:01:42.120 --> 03:01:44.280
Marsh, you're in the copper winglet

03:01:44.280 --> 03:01:44.459
right?

03:01:44.520 --> 03:01:48.299
Yeah, that's my clawmate, Marsh said

03:01:48.299 --> 03:01:49.860
nodding over at coconut.

03:01:49.979 --> 03:01:52.200
Ha, Kibley thought.

03:01:52.260 --> 03:01:53.340
That's perfect.

03:01:53.399 --> 03:01:55.680
But the slowest, least threatening dragon

03:01:55.680 --> 03:01:57.600
in the world, with the most nervous.

03:01:57.659 --> 03:02:00.000
Not even this twitchy mudwing could be

03:02:00.000 --> 03:02:02.280
scared of that sloth, masquerading as a

03:02:02.280 --> 03:02:02.879
dragon over there.

03:02:02.940 --> 03:02:06.420
Marsh looked around, twisting his claws

03:02:06.420 --> 03:02:07.319
in nervous circles.

03:02:07.379 --> 03:02:09.840
I don't remember the other names yet.

03:02:09.959 --> 03:02:11.819
That's all right.

03:02:11.879 --> 03:02:13.319
You'll figure them out.

03:02:13.379 --> 03:02:14.520
Sora?

03:02:14.579 --> 03:02:16.139
Clay prompted his sister.

03:02:16.200 --> 03:02:17.639
Anyone really nice?

03:02:17.760 --> 03:02:20.879
She fiddled with a meat in her talons

03:02:20.879 --> 03:02:22.200
pulling out tufts of fur.

03:02:22.260 --> 03:02:24.959
There's a rain wing in my winglet who

03:02:24.959 --> 03:02:25.379
seems nice.

03:02:25.500 --> 03:02:26.819
She's blind.

03:02:26.879 --> 03:02:28.559
Tamarin!

03:02:28.620 --> 03:02:29.760
Kingachu cried.

03:02:29.819 --> 03:02:31.860
Oh, you must be in a gold winglet.

03:02:31.920 --> 03:02:32.700
She's my best friend.

03:02:32.760 --> 03:02:35.700
Moon decided not to be hurt by this.

03:02:35.760 --> 03:02:37.920
She knew Kinkaju would have other best

03:02:37.920 --> 03:02:40.500
friends, possibly 6 more by the end of

03:02:40.500 --> 03:02:40.979
lunchtime.

03:02:41.040 --> 03:02:45.239
A sandwing named Onyx, Sora said, counting

03:02:45.239 --> 03:02:45.959
on her claws.

03:02:46.020 --> 03:02:49.440
That same wing over there, Pike, his claw

03:02:49.440 --> 03:02:52.079
mates, a night wing called Big Tail, and

03:02:52.079 --> 03:02:54.659
a sky wing with a bad scar across a snout

03:02:54.659 --> 03:02:56.639
and my claw mate.

03:02:56.700 --> 03:02:59.219
She nodded at the far wall.

03:02:59.280 --> 03:03:01.739
At the ice wing seated on the ledge next

03:03:01.739 --> 03:03:02.520
to winter.

03:03:02.579 --> 03:03:04.799
They were both gazing disdainfully down

03:03:04.799 --> 03:03:06.120
at the eating dragons.

03:03:06.120 --> 03:03:09.420
Above them, sharp, twisting stalactites

03:03:09.420 --> 03:03:11.159
studded the roof of the alcove where they

03:03:11.159 --> 03:03:13.440
sat, almost as though they were glaring

03:03:13.440 --> 03:03:14.879
out of a mouth filled with enormous

03:03:14.879 --> 03:03:15.180
teeth.

03:03:15.239 --> 03:03:17.639
Winter sister.

03:03:17.760 --> 03:03:18.780
Kibley said.

03:03:18.840 --> 03:03:20.579
And you and I are in the same tent

03:03:20.579 --> 03:03:21.000
friend.

03:03:21.059 --> 03:03:22.620
She as stuck up as her brother?

03:03:22.680 --> 03:03:24.659
Has she mentioned being in line for the

03:03:24.659 --> 03:03:25.799
ice wing throne yet?

03:03:25.860 --> 03:03:28.260
Sora blinked at the ice wings.

03:03:28.319 --> 03:03:31.020
Ripples shuddered across the mud puddles

03:03:31.020 --> 03:03:33.180
in her mind, but she refused to let

03:03:33.180 --> 03:03:34.260
whatever was under their escape.

03:03:34.319 --> 03:03:37.139
Her name is icicle.

03:03:37.200 --> 03:03:40.319
To be honest, Clay admitted.

03:03:40.379 --> 03:03:43.200
From what we'd heard about Icicle, we

03:03:43.200 --> 03:03:44.819
figured we had to put her in the same

03:03:44.819 --> 03:03:46.979
cave as the nicest, least defensive

03:03:46.979 --> 03:03:48.059
dragon we could think of.

03:03:48.180 --> 03:03:50.459
So there wouldn't be any casualties the

03:03:50.459 --> 03:03:51.120
1st week of school.

03:03:51.180 --> 03:03:53.760
I hope it's going all right, Zora.

03:03:53.819 --> 03:03:56.399
His sister dropped her gaze to her

03:03:56.399 --> 03:03:56.819
clause.

03:03:56.879 --> 03:03:58.860
It's fine, she said.

03:03:58.979 --> 03:04:02.520
Let me know if not, Clay said gently.

03:04:02.639 --> 03:04:04.680
It's really important to me that you be

03:04:04.680 --> 03:04:05.100
happy here.

03:04:05.159 --> 03:04:07.139
So I nodded.

03:04:07.200 --> 03:04:09.299
Thinking of the same brothers and sisters

03:04:09.299 --> 03:04:10.979
Moon had seen in Umber's mind.

03:04:11.040 --> 03:04:13.799
Don't we have history together next?

03:04:13.860 --> 03:04:14.940
Turtle asked.

03:04:15.000 --> 03:04:17.399
Our winglet and your winglet together.

03:04:17.459 --> 03:04:19.379
Do we?

03:04:19.440 --> 03:04:20.700
Umber said delighted.

03:04:20.760 --> 03:04:23.159
I think so, Kibley said.

03:04:23.219 --> 03:04:24.899
Moon could see that he had the days

03:04:24.899 --> 03:04:26.280
schedule memorized.

03:04:26.340 --> 03:04:28.440
Plus a detailed layout of the school map

03:04:28.440 --> 03:04:30.479
in his head, but he was pretending to

03:04:30.479 --> 03:04:31.799
still be figuring things out with the

03:04:31.799 --> 03:04:32.219
rest of them.

03:04:32.280 --> 03:04:35.940
I have to go to the library first, Moon

03:04:35.940 --> 03:04:37.799
said to Kinkachu, but I'll catch up to

03:04:37.799 --> 03:04:38.040
you.

03:04:38.100 --> 03:04:41.159
She stood up and paused, listening to the

03:04:41.159 --> 03:04:43.500
uneasy rippling quiet in Sora's mind.

03:04:43.559 --> 03:04:46.260
Do you want to come with me?

03:04:46.319 --> 03:04:47.700
She asked Zora.

03:04:47.760 --> 03:04:50.040
The mud wing blinked at her in surprise.

03:04:50.100 --> 03:04:52.799
I do, she said, standing up.

03:04:52.799 --> 03:04:54.840
As they headed out of the pray center

03:04:54.840 --> 03:04:56.940
together, Moon could hear the reactions

03:04:56.940 --> 03:04:57.840
stirring behind them.

03:04:57.959 --> 03:05:00.479
That was nice of Moon.

03:05:00.479 --> 03:05:01.680
Umber thought.

03:05:01.739 --> 03:05:04.379
Ah, maybe they'll be friends.

03:05:04.440 --> 03:05:06.120
Went through Clay's mind.

03:05:06.180 --> 03:05:08.280
Does she like her better than me?

03:05:08.340 --> 03:05:10.440
Kinkachu thought forlornly.

03:05:10.500 --> 03:05:13.500
My boring little claw made with a night

03:05:13.500 --> 03:05:13.979
wing?

03:05:14.040 --> 03:05:16.079
Came a frigid thought from across the

03:05:16.079 --> 03:05:16.739
cave.

03:05:16.860 --> 03:05:18.959
What's that all about?

03:05:19.079 --> 03:05:23.280
Moon hurried into the stone tunnel, trying

03:05:23.280 --> 03:05:24.899
hard to think about raindrops.

03:05:24.959 --> 03:05:26.940
They were halfway to the library before

03:05:26.940 --> 03:05:29.459
she realized that neither she nor Sora

03:05:29.459 --> 03:05:30.540
had said a word the whole walk.

03:05:30.600 --> 03:05:35.100
Um, Moon said, the library's great, isn't

03:05:35.100 --> 03:05:35.280
it?

03:05:35.340 --> 03:05:36.780
Sora nodded.

03:05:36.840 --> 03:05:39.780
I like the leaf windows, Moon added.

03:05:39.840 --> 03:05:41.280
Sora nodded again.

03:05:41.340 --> 03:05:43.799
Me too, she whispered.

03:05:43.920 --> 03:05:46.500
Is this what I seem like to everyone

03:05:46.500 --> 03:05:46.860
else?

03:05:46.920 --> 03:05:48.180
Moon wondered.

03:05:48.299 --> 03:05:50.459
Shy and really hard to talk to.

03:05:50.520 --> 03:05:52.559
Maybe I should try a little harder.

03:05:52.620 --> 03:05:55.379
It's easy to talk to my mystery friend

03:05:55.379 --> 03:05:57.000
but I don't have to hide anything from

03:05:57.000 --> 03:05:57.239
him.

03:05:57.299 --> 03:06:00.360
I guess I couldn't, even if I wanted to.

03:06:00.420 --> 03:06:03.299
Starflight sat up as they came into the

03:06:03.299 --> 03:06:05.819
library, setting aside a stone tablet

03:06:05.819 --> 03:06:06.959
with letters carved into it.

03:06:07.079 --> 03:06:08.280
Hello?

03:06:08.280 --> 03:06:09.600
he said tentatively.

03:06:09.659 --> 03:06:12.719
It's Moon and Sora, Moon said.

03:06:12.780 --> 03:06:16.020
Oh, hi, he said relaxing.

03:06:16.079 --> 03:06:18.959
Sora, I found that scroll on ice wings

03:06:18.959 --> 03:06:19.200
for you.

03:06:19.319 --> 03:06:21.780
He set a scroll across the desk with his

03:06:21.780 --> 03:06:22.379
claws.

03:06:22.440 --> 03:06:25.440
Sora glanced at Moon, ducked her head, and

03:06:25.440 --> 03:06:27.719
mumbled something like, figuring out my

03:06:27.719 --> 03:06:28.260
clawmate.

03:06:28.379 --> 03:06:31.020
She took the scroll and scurried over to

03:06:31.020 --> 03:06:31.920
her spot by the windows.

03:06:31.979 --> 03:06:34.260
How are you, Moon?

03:06:34.319 --> 03:06:35.520
Starflight asked.

03:06:35.579 --> 03:06:37.200
How was class this morning?

03:06:37.260 --> 03:06:38.819
Terrifying.

03:06:38.940 --> 03:06:40.559
All right.

03:06:40.620 --> 03:06:42.659
Interesting she said.

03:06:42.719 --> 03:06:44.639
Do you have any scrolls about dream

03:06:44.639 --> 03:06:45.299
visitors?

03:06:45.360 --> 03:06:47.940
He tipped his head, frowning a little.

03:06:48.000 --> 03:06:49.799
I'm sure we do.

03:06:49.860 --> 03:06:50.399
Why?

03:06:50.459 --> 03:06:51.479
You didn't.

03:06:51.540 --> 03:06:53.520
I mean, you haven't been visited by

03:06:53.520 --> 03:06:54.239
someone, have you?

03:06:54.299 --> 03:06:57.540
I'm just curious, Moon said quickly.

03:06:57.600 --> 03:06:59.579
Someone mentioned them.

03:06:59.639 --> 03:07:02.340
Um, in class, and I don't know anything

03:07:02.340 --> 03:07:02.700
about them.

03:07:02.760 --> 03:07:05.579
Starflight slid out from behind the desk

03:07:05.579 --> 03:07:08.219
and started walking along the shelves

03:07:08.219 --> 03:07:09.659
touching the carvings here and there.

03:07:09.719 --> 03:07:13.079
If you ever do see a strange dragon in

03:07:13.079 --> 03:07:14.940
your dreams, let me know all right

03:07:14.940 --> 03:07:16.979
especially if she's a Sky Wing.

03:07:17.100 --> 03:07:20.579
A viciously scary orange dragon wreathed

03:07:20.579 --> 03:07:22.139
in smoke flashed through his mind.

03:07:22.139 --> 03:07:24.180
A sky wing?

03:07:24.239 --> 03:07:25.440
Moon said alertly.

03:07:25.500 --> 03:07:26.280
Why?

03:07:26.340 --> 03:07:28.139
Starflight side.

03:07:28.260 --> 03:07:32.760
Queen Scarlet, X Queen Scarlet, is out

03:07:32.760 --> 03:07:34.860
there with a dream visitor, and she hates

03:07:34.860 --> 03:07:35.159
us.

03:07:35.219 --> 03:07:37.379
I worry sometimes that she'll start

03:07:37.379 --> 03:07:39.059
scaring our students in their dreams.

03:07:39.120 --> 03:07:41.940
And that's far from the worst she could

03:07:41.940 --> 03:07:42.180
do.

03:07:42.239 --> 03:07:43.860
He thought anxiously.

03:07:43.920 --> 03:07:46.799
How did she get her dream visitor?

03:07:46.860 --> 03:07:47.579
Moon asked.

03:07:47.700 --> 03:07:49.739
We're not entirely sure.

03:07:49.799 --> 03:07:51.059
Starflight said.

03:07:51.120 --> 03:07:53.219
He tilted his wings back and scratched

03:07:53.219 --> 03:07:54.299
his head.

03:07:54.360 --> 03:07:56.280
She must have found it while she was

03:07:56.280 --> 03:07:58.979
imprisoned in Burns weirdling Tower, and

03:07:58.979 --> 03:08:00.420
Burne must not have known it was there.

03:08:00.479 --> 03:08:04.379
My theory is, the Scarlet founded in or

03:08:04.379 --> 03:08:06.659
on this Nightwing Dragon Corpse she

03:08:06.659 --> 03:08:08.280
disemboweled, somehow.

03:08:08.399 --> 03:08:12.780
Oh, Moon said, does anyone know where the

03:08:12.780 --> 03:08:14.100
other 2 dream visitors are?

03:08:14.159 --> 03:08:17.159
To her surprise, Starflight nodded.

03:08:17.399 --> 03:08:18.840
We know one for sure.

03:08:18.899 --> 03:08:20.159
It's right here in the school.

03:08:20.280 --> 03:08:22.079
I think Sonny has it this week.

03:08:22.139 --> 03:08:24.899
She got it from a scavenger, who stole it

03:08:24.899 --> 03:08:26.819
from the sand wings, and we're pretty

03:08:26.819 --> 03:08:28.860
sure the other dream visitor was lost in

03:08:28.860 --> 03:08:29.280
the volcano.

03:08:29.340 --> 03:08:32.100
I found it in the night wing treasury, but

03:08:32.100 --> 03:08:33.840
someone stole it from me shortly before

03:08:33.840 --> 03:08:34.979
the island exploded.

03:08:35.040 --> 03:08:37.200
You don't know who?

03:08:37.319 --> 03:08:38.819
He shook his head.

03:08:38.879 --> 03:08:41.159
Flickers of guilt ricocheting through his

03:08:41.159 --> 03:08:41.399
mind.

03:08:41.459 --> 03:08:42.659
Here.

03:08:42.719 --> 03:08:45.120
He brushed his talons across his section

03:08:45.120 --> 03:08:47.280
of the wall and then chose a scroll and

03:08:47.280 --> 03:08:48.059
held it out for her.

03:08:48.120 --> 03:08:51.180
This should be the animus histories.

03:08:51.239 --> 03:08:53.819
It's about several animus touched objects

03:08:53.819 --> 03:08:55.799
but the dream visitors definitely have a

03:08:55.799 --> 03:08:56.219
section in there.

03:08:56.280 --> 03:08:58.680
Thanks, Moon said.

03:08:58.739 --> 03:09:01.020
Could she have heard Queen Scarlet in

03:09:01.020 --> 03:09:02.040
someone's dream last night?

03:09:02.100 --> 03:09:04.860
Another awful thought followed that one.

03:09:04.920 --> 03:09:07.500
She hesitated, but she had to ask.

03:09:07.559 --> 03:09:10.920
Could a dragon ever use a dream visitor

03:09:10.920 --> 03:09:12.600
to talk to someone while they're awake?

03:09:12.659 --> 03:09:15.360
I mean, like in their heads.

03:09:15.420 --> 03:09:18.780
Now, Starflight looked really puzzled.

03:09:18.840 --> 03:09:21.840
No, that wouldn't make sense, he said.

03:09:21.899 --> 03:09:24.420
The way they're enchanted is to get into

03:09:24.420 --> 03:09:25.680
dreams, nothing else.

03:09:25.739 --> 03:09:27.059
Why do you ask?

03:09:27.120 --> 03:09:30.840
Just a story I heard once, Moon said.

03:09:30.899 --> 03:09:33.420
I promise you, little moon.

03:09:33.479 --> 03:09:35.579
I am no sky wing.

03:09:35.639 --> 03:09:38.100
Then who are you?

03:09:38.219 --> 03:09:39.899
Moon thought back fiercely.

03:09:40.020 --> 03:09:42.180
No answer. of course.

03:09:42.239 --> 03:09:44.879
She took the scroll over to a ledge by

03:09:44.879 --> 03:09:47.040
the biggest window, and curled up their

03:09:47.040 --> 03:09:48.719
back against a tapestry covered wall.

03:09:48.780 --> 03:09:51.360
There were more animus touched objects

03:09:51.360 --> 03:09:53.579
than she would have expected, considering

03:09:53.579 --> 03:09:54.899
there hadn't been that many animus

03:09:54.899 --> 03:09:56.459
dragons and Pyreus history.

03:09:56.520 --> 03:09:58.500
At least as far as anyone knew.

03:09:58.559 --> 03:10:01.079
She stopped on a spread with a beautiful

03:10:01.079 --> 03:10:03.959
drawing of a tall, sweeping pavilion, 12

03:10:03.959 --> 03:10:06.959
stories high, made of white stone, and

03:10:06.959 --> 03:10:08.700
looking as if it had grown straight out

03:10:08.700 --> 03:10:10.680
of the water into this perfect shape.

03:10:10.739 --> 03:10:14.459
The Sea Wing Summer Palace read the

03:10:14.459 --> 03:10:17.159
caption, made of stone enchanted by

03:10:17.159 --> 03:10:20.280
albatross, a sea wing prints, to grow

03:10:20.280 --> 03:10:21.479
into a tower he designed.

03:10:21.540 --> 03:10:25.200
That's really pretty, Moon thought

03:10:25.200 --> 03:10:27.479
brushing one claw lightly across the

03:10:27.479 --> 03:10:28.020
drawing.

03:10:28.079 --> 03:10:29.940
I wish I could create something like

03:10:29.940 --> 03:10:30.180
that.

03:10:30.239 --> 03:10:33.239
She rolled the scroll to read the longer

03:10:33.239 --> 03:10:34.200
paragraph on the side.

03:10:34.260 --> 03:10:38.340
Albatross was one of the 1st known animus

03:10:38.340 --> 03:10:41.040
dragons hatched over 2000 years ago

03:10:41.040 --> 03:10:43.799
before anyone truly understood the limits

03:10:43.799 --> 03:10:44.280
of this power.

03:10:44.340 --> 03:10:47.459
He used his animus magic to create many

03:10:47.459 --> 03:10:49.739
things, including the beautiful summer

03:10:49.739 --> 03:10:52.559
palace pavilion, whose location is known

03:10:52.559 --> 03:10:53.760
only to sea wings.

03:10:53.819 --> 03:10:57.180
But at the time, nobody realized the

03:10:57.180 --> 03:11:00.180
terrible price of using animus powers, and

03:11:00.180 --> 03:11:02.760
nobody saw that albatross was slowly

03:11:02.760 --> 03:11:03.360
going insane.

03:11:03.420 --> 03:11:06.899
Not until the Royal Sea Wing Massacre.

03:11:06.959 --> 03:11:10.139
It was a devastating shock to the entire

03:11:10.139 --> 03:11:13.139
kingdom of the sea, when Albatross, who

03:11:13.139 --> 03:11:14.520
had been hailed as one of the greatest

03:11:14.520 --> 03:11:17.819
sea wings of all time, suddenly snapped

03:11:17.819 --> 03:11:19.379
and tried to murder his entire family.

03:11:19.440 --> 03:11:23.399
He managed to kill 9 dragons, including

03:11:23.399 --> 03:11:25.799
his sister, the queen, his own daughter

03:11:25.799 --> 03:11:28.139
and her husband before someone was able

03:11:28.139 --> 03:11:29.940
to stop him with a spear to his chest.

03:11:30.000 --> 03:11:32.700
Among the few who survived where his

03:11:32.700 --> 03:11:35.520
young grandson, Fathom, and granddaughter

03:11:35.520 --> 03:11:36.000
Pearl.

03:11:36.120 --> 03:11:39.180
Pearl ascended the throne peacefully, and

03:11:39.180 --> 03:11:40.079
ruled for many years.

03:11:40.200 --> 03:11:43.559
One of her 1st edicts was to outlaw the

03:11:43.559 --> 03:11:45.299
use of animus magic anywhere in her

03:11:45.299 --> 03:11:45.719
kingdom.

03:11:45.780 --> 03:11:49.319
Her brother, Fathom, was an animus dragon

03:11:49.319 --> 03:11:51.540
himself, but after the massacre.

03:11:51.600 --> 03:11:54.780
He refused to ever use his power, except

03:11:54.780 --> 03:11:55.500
perhaps once.

03:11:55.559 --> 03:11:57.299
See, fathom.

03:11:57.360 --> 03:11:58.979
Moon shivered.

03:11:59.040 --> 03:12:00.540
What an awful story.

03:12:00.600 --> 03:12:03.420
I guess there are worse powers than mine

03:12:03.420 --> 03:12:04.020
in the world.

03:12:04.079 --> 03:12:06.780
At least mind reading only made her

03:12:06.780 --> 03:12:08.579
socially anxious and gave her headaches.

03:12:08.639 --> 03:12:10.620
She was pretty sure it wasn't turning her

03:12:10.620 --> 03:12:11.579
homicidal, though.

03:12:11.639 --> 03:12:14.100
She found the section on dream visitors

03:12:14.100 --> 03:12:16.200
and studied the drawing of the 3 star

03:12:16.200 --> 03:12:17.280
shaped sapphires.

03:12:17.340 --> 03:12:20.340
Dream visitors, read the caption

03:12:20.340 --> 03:12:22.920
enchanted by a night wing named Dark

03:12:22.920 --> 03:12:25.440
Stalker, to allow whichever dragon holds

03:12:25.440 --> 03:12:27.239
one to walk in any other dragon's

03:12:27.239 --> 03:12:27.540
dreams.

03:12:27.600 --> 03:12:30.780
Moon hadn't realized they were made by a

03:12:30.780 --> 03:12:31.139
Nightwing.

03:12:31.260 --> 03:12:32.879
She unrolled it to the longer

03:12:32.879 --> 03:12:33.420
description.

03:12:33.540 --> 03:12:36.600
The 1st known animus dragon in the

03:12:36.600 --> 03:12:39.540
Nightwing tribe, Dark Stalker, also had

03:12:39.540 --> 03:12:42.299
the powers of mind reading and prophecy

03:12:42.299 --> 03:12:44.040
making him a truly formidable dragon.

03:12:44.100 --> 03:12:47.399
He created 3 dream visitors, so there

03:12:47.399 --> 03:12:49.500
would be one for him, one for his best

03:12:49.500 --> 03:12:50.879
friend, C.

03:12:50.879 --> 03:12:54.180
Fathom, and one for his beloved, a dragon

03:12:54.180 --> 03:12:55.200
named Clearsight.

03:12:55.260 --> 03:12:57.840
They were intended to link the three, no

03:12:57.840 --> 03:12:58.979
matter how far apart they were.

03:12:59.040 --> 03:13:01.079
That's sweet.

03:13:01.139 --> 03:13:02.219
Moon thought.

03:13:02.280 --> 03:13:05.040
If it were her, who would she give dream

03:13:05.040 --> 03:13:05.700
visitors to?

03:13:05.819 --> 03:13:07.440
Mother, of course.

03:13:07.500 --> 03:13:10.620
She felt a twinge of sadness, and also

03:13:10.620 --> 03:13:13.500
guilt that she'd managed not to miss her

03:13:13.500 --> 03:13:15.239
mother every 2nd she'd been gone.

03:13:15.299 --> 03:13:16.920
Who else?

03:13:16.979 --> 03:13:18.180
Kinkachu?

03:13:18.239 --> 03:13:21.059
The idea of kinkaju flinging rainbows

03:13:21.059 --> 03:13:23.399
around in moon's dreams, as well as in

03:13:23.399 --> 03:13:24.719
her waking thoughts, was a little

03:13:24.719 --> 03:13:25.200
alarming.

03:13:25.260 --> 03:13:27.840
The answer is no one really.

03:13:27.899 --> 03:13:29.879
Moon admitted to herself.

03:13:29.940 --> 03:13:32.639
She didn't want anyone to see inside her

03:13:32.639 --> 03:13:33.360
subconscious.

03:13:33.420 --> 03:13:36.059
If they did, she was sure they'd never

03:13:36.059 --> 03:13:36.600
trust her again.

03:13:36.659 --> 03:13:39.959
Ultimately, Dark Stalker grew to be too

03:13:39.959 --> 03:13:42.540
powerful, and his ambitions began to

03:13:42.540 --> 03:13:43.979
terrify the dragons around him.

03:13:44.040 --> 03:13:46.319
He claimed he'd found a way to make

03:13:46.319 --> 03:13:47.579
himself immortal.

03:13:47.639 --> 03:13:49.079
Rumor had it.

03:13:49.139 --> 03:13:51.479
He planned to overthrow the night wing

03:13:51.479 --> 03:13:53.579
queen and seize the throne for himself.

03:13:53.639 --> 03:13:56.579
After he killed his own father with an

03:13:56.579 --> 03:13:59.159
aspect of animus power that no one had

03:13:59.159 --> 03:14:01.079
ever seen before, the tribe agreed.

03:14:01.139 --> 03:14:03.239
He was too dangerous to be free.

03:14:03.299 --> 03:14:06.299
The details of the trap set for dark

03:14:06.299 --> 03:14:09.059
stalker are lost to history, but it is

03:14:09.059 --> 03:14:10.500
certain that he and Clearsight

03:14:10.500 --> 03:14:12.540
disappeared one night, and were probably

03:14:12.540 --> 03:14:14.459
both killed at the same time.

03:14:14.520 --> 03:14:16.739
It is also believed that he was

03:14:16.739 --> 03:14:18.899
ultimately taken down with an animus

03:14:18.899 --> 03:14:21.899
touched object created by Fathom, the

03:14:21.899 --> 03:14:23.700
only time Fathom ever used his power.

03:14:23.760 --> 03:14:27.239
Fear of the dark stalker lingered in the

03:14:27.239 --> 03:14:29.520
night wing tribe, however, causing them

03:14:29.520 --> 03:14:31.680
to move to a new secret home in case he

03:14:31.680 --> 03:14:32.340
ever returned.

03:14:32.399 --> 03:14:35.340
Nightwing ghost stories still speak of

03:14:35.340 --> 03:14:37.500
him, and there are those who believe that

03:14:37.500 --> 03:14:40.260
one day, dark stalker may yet rise again

03:14:40.260 --> 03:14:42.180
and come seeking his revenge.

03:14:42.239 --> 03:14:44.760
Night wing ghosts.

03:14:44.819 --> 03:14:47.040
Moon thought, touching the scroll

03:14:47.040 --> 03:14:47.579
lightly.

03:14:47.639 --> 03:14:50.459
Mother never told me any traditional

03:14:50.459 --> 03:14:51.840
night wing ghost stories.

03:14:51.899 --> 03:14:54.000
She had much more effective ways of

03:14:54.000 --> 03:14:56.520
terrifying me, just by telling me about

03:14:56.520 --> 03:14:59.459
the volcano and the rain wings, and what

03:14:59.459 --> 03:15:01.139
would happen if another night wing ever

03:15:01.139 --> 03:15:02.340
found me in the rainforest.

03:15:02.399 --> 03:15:05.340
She rolled the scroll in either direction

03:15:05.340 --> 03:15:07.200
but there was no more information about

03:15:07.200 --> 03:15:08.219
the dream visitors.

03:15:08.280 --> 03:15:11.100
Read the section on Fathom.

03:15:11.159 --> 03:15:13.620
The mysterious voice suddenly commanded

03:15:13.620 --> 03:15:16.920
in her head, Unfathom, Moon Thought

03:15:16.920 --> 03:15:17.760
glancing up.

03:15:17.879 --> 03:15:20.819
Sora shifted slightly, but kept her eyes

03:15:20.819 --> 03:15:22.920
on the scroll in front of her, drowning

03:15:22.920 --> 03:15:25.020
her worries under a deluge of words about

03:15:25.020 --> 03:15:25.680
ice wings.

03:15:25.739 --> 03:15:27.000
Why?

03:15:27.059 --> 03:15:28.860
To find out what he did with his dream

03:15:28.860 --> 03:15:29.399
visitor?

03:15:29.459 --> 03:15:33.360
Just read it, the voice said.

03:15:33.420 --> 03:15:35.700
And there was an odd vibration to it that

03:15:35.700 --> 03:15:37.860
she hadn't heard before, like an egg

03:15:37.860 --> 03:15:39.299
shuddering before it cracked.

03:15:39.360 --> 03:15:42.360
What do you know about Fathom that I

03:15:42.360 --> 03:15:45.000
don't, Moon wondered, as she rolled

03:15:45.000 --> 03:15:45.719
through the scroll.

03:15:45.780 --> 03:15:48.120
She quickly found the section on Fathom

03:15:48.120 --> 03:15:50.520
alongside a giant illustrated question

03:15:50.520 --> 03:15:50.819
mark.

03:15:50.879 --> 03:15:54.780
Grandson of Albatross, the perpetrator of

03:15:54.780 --> 03:15:56.819
the Royal Sea Wing Massacre, see

03:15:56.819 --> 03:15:59.940
Albatross, Fathom was so traumatized by

03:15:59.940 --> 03:16:02.100
his family's murder, that he swore an

03:16:02.100 --> 03:16:04.079
oath to his sister Pearl, the new Sea

03:16:04.079 --> 03:16:06.059
Wing Queen, that he would never use his

03:16:06.059 --> 03:16:06.840
animus magic.

03:16:06.899 --> 03:16:09.959
Fathom was sent to the knight kingdom to

03:16:09.959 --> 03:16:12.420
befriend and guide a young animus dragon

03:16:12.420 --> 03:16:13.739
named Dark Stalker.

03:16:13.799 --> 03:16:17.639
The hope was that Fathom's sad story, his

03:16:17.639 --> 03:16:20.159
caution, and his understandable wariness

03:16:20.159 --> 03:16:22.319
about their powers, would have a positive

03:16:22.319 --> 03:16:24.479
effect on the ambitious, brilliant night

03:16:24.479 --> 03:16:25.020
wing.

03:16:25.079 --> 03:16:27.959
At 1st it seemed to work, and they became

03:16:27.959 --> 03:16:28.860
close friends.

03:16:28.979 --> 03:16:31.500
But Dark Stalker could not be convinced

03:16:31.500 --> 03:16:34.440
that his powers were dangerous, and as he

03:16:34.440 --> 03:16:36.959
used them more and more, Fathom and the

03:16:36.959 --> 03:16:38.399
other night wings became afraid of him.

03:16:38.459 --> 03:16:41.219
Fathom was among the 1st to sound a

03:16:41.219 --> 03:16:43.500
warning about his friend, and the stories

03:16:43.500 --> 03:16:45.299
say he was the one who convinced

03:16:45.299 --> 03:16:47.819
Clearsight that dark stalker could not be

03:16:47.819 --> 03:16:48.239
trusted.

03:16:48.299 --> 03:16:51.120
The legend says that Fathom finally

03:16:51.120 --> 03:16:54.479
agreed to use his power just once, to

03:16:54.479 --> 03:16:56.819
enchant an object that could stop dark

03:16:56.819 --> 03:16:59.579
stalker, since nothing and nobody else

03:16:59.579 --> 03:16:59.879
could.

03:16:59.940 --> 03:17:02.639
Whatever the object was, it must have

03:17:02.639 --> 03:17:02.940
worked.

03:17:03.000 --> 03:17:05.639
As dark stalker disappeared, and was

03:17:05.639 --> 03:17:06.239
never seen again.

03:17:06.299 --> 03:17:10.739
How sad, Moon thought, studying the

03:17:10.739 --> 03:17:12.600
picture of a worried looking sea wing.

03:17:12.659 --> 03:17:15.959
He must have felt awful, doing that to

03:17:15.959 --> 03:17:16.319
his friend.

03:17:16.379 --> 03:17:18.780
I wonder what he enchanted.

03:17:18.840 --> 03:17:22.260
There was a deep pause, and Moon could

03:17:22.260 --> 03:17:24.120
almost have sworn that she felt the

03:17:24.120 --> 03:17:25.680
mountain tremble slightly under her

03:17:25.680 --> 03:17:26.459
talons.

03:17:26.520 --> 03:17:29.159
It was a bracelet.

03:17:29.219 --> 03:17:32.100
The voice whispered, soft as leaves

03:17:32.100 --> 03:17:32.459
falling.

03:17:32.579 --> 03:17:34.739
Moon blinked at the scroll.

03:17:34.799 --> 03:17:35.819
What?

03:17:35.879 --> 03:17:37.739
A bracelet.

03:17:37.799 --> 03:17:39.180
A wrist cuff.

03:17:39.239 --> 03:17:41.940
Enchanted to put me to sleep forever.

03:17:42.000 --> 03:17:43.860
Since I couldn't die.

03:17:43.920 --> 03:17:46.680
That story about making myself immortal

03:17:46.680 --> 03:17:47.159
is true.

03:17:47.219 --> 03:17:49.500
They had to come up with something else.

03:17:49.559 --> 03:17:53.040
Her whole body felt numb, like ice was

03:17:53.040 --> 03:17:54.299
sweeping across her scales.

03:17:54.360 --> 03:17:56.040
I knew it.

03:17:56.100 --> 03:17:57.540
The voice went on.

03:17:57.600 --> 03:17:59.520
I knew when she pulled it out.

03:17:59.639 --> 03:18:02.639
Right before she put it on me, I thought

03:18:02.639 --> 03:18:04.860
Fathom must have touched that.

03:18:04.920 --> 03:18:07.799
He broke his sacred oath to his sister.

03:18:07.860 --> 03:18:09.600
Just to betray me.

03:18:09.719 --> 03:18:12.180
But I wasn't sure until now.

03:18:12.180 --> 03:18:14.700
What are you saying?

03:18:14.819 --> 03:18:18.000
Moon asked, pressing her claws into the

03:18:18.000 --> 03:18:18.659
stone below her.

03:18:18.719 --> 03:18:22.620
I'm saying, nice to meet you, Moon.

03:18:22.739 --> 03:18:25.860
My name is Dark Stalker.

03:18:25.920 --> 03:18:29.940
Part two.

03:18:30.000 --> 03:18:31.979
Stay hidden.

03:18:32.100 --> 03:18:34.020
Chapter 9.

03:18:34.079 --> 03:18:38.520
But you can't be, Moon whispered.

03:18:38.579 --> 03:18:41.219
Then realized she'd spoken aloud when

03:18:41.219 --> 03:18:43.260
Zora looked up and blinked at her.

03:18:43.319 --> 03:18:44.819
She turned toward the wall and thought

03:18:44.819 --> 03:18:47.879
Dark Stalker lived over 2000 years ago.

03:18:47.940 --> 03:18:49.739
I know.

03:18:49.799 --> 03:18:51.360
He sighed.

03:18:51.479 --> 03:18:54.420
I've been asleep a long time apparently.

03:18:54.479 --> 03:18:57.719
I suspect this bracelet was supposed to

03:18:57.719 --> 03:18:58.739
keep me that way forever.

03:18:58.799 --> 03:19:00.719
So what happened?

03:19:00.840 --> 03:19:01.920
Moon asked.

03:19:02.520 --> 03:19:03.299
Why are you awake now?

03:19:03.360 --> 03:19:05.520
It's broken.

03:19:05.579 --> 03:19:06.600
He said.

03:19:06.659 --> 03:19:10.620
After 2000 years, almost anything becomes

03:19:10.620 --> 03:19:10.979
weaker.

03:19:11.040 --> 03:19:13.979
Something must have jarred it, and

03:19:13.979 --> 03:19:14.399
snapped it off.

03:19:14.459 --> 03:19:16.440
The earthquakes?

03:19:16.500 --> 03:19:17.520
Moon wondered.

03:19:17.579 --> 03:19:19.739
There was a comet 6 months ago.

03:19:19.739 --> 03:19:22.559
As it passed by, there were a lot of

03:19:22.559 --> 03:19:24.059
earthquakes and strange weather.

03:19:24.120 --> 03:19:27.780
That's when I woke up, he said.

03:19:27.840 --> 03:19:29.520
So you're probably right.

03:19:29.579 --> 03:19:31.500
Moon hesitated.

03:19:31.559 --> 03:19:33.780
Six months ago was also when her

03:19:33.780 --> 03:19:36.000
nightmares had started, the ones about

03:19:36.000 --> 03:19:37.260
Jade Mountain falling.

03:19:37.319 --> 03:19:39.479
Was she seeing visions of something that

03:19:39.479 --> 03:19:41.340
would ultimately be caused by Dark

03:19:41.340 --> 03:19:42.299
Stalker's awakening?

03:19:42.360 --> 03:19:45.299
I'm not actually a monster.

03:19:45.360 --> 03:19:47.639
No matter what the scrolls and ghost

03:19:47.639 --> 03:19:49.319
stories say, he said.

03:19:49.379 --> 03:19:50.639
Can't you tell?

03:19:50.700 --> 03:19:52.680
Where are you?

03:19:52.739 --> 03:19:54.840
She asked, instead of answering.

03:19:54.899 --> 03:19:56.879
That I don't know.

03:19:56.940 --> 03:20:00.059
Somewhere dark, covered in stone.

03:20:00.120 --> 03:20:01.079
I can't move.

03:20:01.139 --> 03:20:03.899
I can only think.

03:20:03.959 --> 03:20:06.299
He let out an odd sort of chuckle.

03:20:06.420 --> 03:20:09.239
Perhaps you can see why I was so pleased

03:20:09.239 --> 03:20:09.659
to find you.

03:20:09.780 --> 03:20:12.420
I can hear others, but no one else can

03:20:12.420 --> 03:20:12.719
hear me.

03:20:12.780 --> 03:20:15.959
Makes for lots of very boring, one-sided

03:20:15.959 --> 03:20:16.559
conversations.

03:20:16.620 --> 03:20:18.840
She didn't know what else to say.

03:20:18.899 --> 03:20:20.459
She'd expected.

03:20:20.520 --> 03:20:23.579
Well, another dragon like her. someone

03:20:23.579 --> 03:20:24.959
she can meet and go flying with.

03:20:25.020 --> 03:20:27.540
She had not expected to be talking to the

03:20:27.540 --> 03:20:29.280
legendary monster of night wing

03:20:29.280 --> 03:20:29.879
nightmares.

03:20:29.940 --> 03:20:33.299
I'm not a monster.

03:20:33.360 --> 03:20:35.280
He said again quietly.

03:20:35.340 --> 03:20:37.799
It seems history has painted me that

03:20:37.799 --> 03:20:38.100
way.

03:20:38.340 --> 03:20:40.260
But perhaps that's what happens when you

03:20:40.260 --> 03:20:41.700
disappear before you can tell your own

03:20:41.700 --> 03:20:44.280
story, and only your enemies are left to

03:20:44.280 --> 03:20:44.760
finish it.

03:20:44.819 --> 03:20:47.940
Or your best friend turned enemies

03:20:47.940 --> 03:20:48.299
apparently.

03:20:48.360 --> 03:20:51.479
Moon rolled back to the dark stalker

03:20:51.479 --> 03:20:53.879
section of the scroll, a handsome dark

03:20:53.879 --> 03:20:55.620
face stared regally out at her.

03:20:55.680 --> 03:20:58.379
He had the same silver scales in the

03:20:58.379 --> 03:20:59.340
corners of his eyes too.

03:20:59.399 --> 03:21:04.079
Formidable dragon, Dark Stalker said, with

03:21:04.079 --> 03:21:06.780
mild amusement, I suppose that's true.

03:21:06.899 --> 03:21:09.180
But it is not my fault.

03:21:09.239 --> 03:21:10.500
I was born with these powers.

03:21:10.559 --> 03:21:12.719
I think you know something about that.

03:21:12.780 --> 03:21:16.440
I've never plotted to steal any thrones

03:21:16.440 --> 03:21:19.440
though, Moon pointed out, or killed my

03:21:19.440 --> 03:21:19.680
father.

03:21:19.799 --> 03:21:23.340
I think you would, if you'd had my

03:21:23.340 --> 03:21:23.639
father.

03:21:23.700 --> 03:21:26.459
I saved the tribe from him.

03:21:26.520 --> 03:21:28.559
Dark soccer argued.

03:21:28.620 --> 03:21:30.780
He was a lot worse than I am.

03:21:30.899 --> 03:21:33.719
This Scrolls version of the story is

03:21:33.719 --> 03:21:34.920
highly oversimplified.

03:21:34.979 --> 03:21:37.559
As for being king, why not?

03:21:37.620 --> 03:21:40.260
Just because we've only ever had queens

03:21:40.260 --> 03:21:42.000
does that mean a king is impossible?

03:21:42.059 --> 03:21:44.280
Why would I have all these gifts?

03:21:44.280 --> 03:21:46.680
If I wasn't supposed to use them to lead

03:21:46.680 --> 03:21:47.940
and protect the tribe?

03:21:48.000 --> 03:21:51.780
It felt as though he'd suddenly seized

03:21:51.780 --> 03:21:53.280
her mind in an iron grip.

03:21:53.340 --> 03:21:55.440
Moon winced touching her head.

03:21:55.500 --> 03:21:58.799
Listen, Dark Stalker said.

03:21:58.860 --> 03:22:01.739
I could see the future, but not just any

03:22:01.739 --> 03:22:02.040
future.

03:22:02.159 --> 03:22:04.379
All the possible futures.

03:22:04.440 --> 03:22:06.479
Do you understand what that means?

03:22:06.540 --> 03:22:08.760
I could have guided the tribe along the

03:22:08.760 --> 03:22:12.000
best path to safety. and glory and power

03:22:12.000 --> 03:22:13.200
and everything else.

03:22:13.260 --> 03:22:16.139
At each crossroad, I would have known the

03:22:16.139 --> 03:22:16.739
right thing to do.

03:22:16.799 --> 03:22:19.680
I loved my tribe, Moon Watcher.

03:22:19.739 --> 03:22:22.319
I would have been the best ruler they'd

03:22:22.319 --> 03:22:22.680
ever had.

03:22:22.739 --> 03:22:23.399
I know it.

03:22:23.459 --> 03:22:26.459
I saw the futures where I was king

03:22:26.459 --> 03:22:29.520
benevolent and beloved, married to

03:22:29.520 --> 03:22:31.680
Clearsight, with 6 little dragonettes of

03:22:31.680 --> 03:22:31.979
our own.

03:22:32.040 --> 03:22:33.840
Those were possible.

03:22:33.899 --> 03:22:35.159
It could have happened.

03:22:35.280 --> 03:22:37.979
If anyone had had faith in me.

03:22:38.100 --> 03:22:41.340
He paused, then went on.

03:22:41.399 --> 03:22:43.260
She saw them too.

03:22:43.379 --> 03:22:47.280
Clearsight had the gift of prophecy, as

03:22:47.280 --> 03:22:47.819
strong as mine.

03:22:47.879 --> 03:22:51.420
She knew those futures existed, but she

03:22:51.420 --> 03:22:53.280
also saw the ones where I turned toward

03:22:53.280 --> 03:22:55.680
evil, destroying instead of protecting.

03:22:55.799 --> 03:22:58.379
She didn't believe me that I could avoid

03:22:58.379 --> 03:22:58.920
those paths.

03:22:59.040 --> 03:23:02.879
In the end, I guess you didn't believe in

03:23:02.879 --> 03:23:03.239
me at all.

03:23:03.299 --> 03:23:05.760
I wonder what happened to her.

03:23:05.879 --> 03:23:08.940
There was another really long pause.

03:23:09.000 --> 03:23:11.579
This is going to sound weird.

03:23:11.639 --> 03:23:14.520
Moon offered, but I kind of want to give

03:23:14.520 --> 03:23:15.299
you a hug right now.

03:23:15.420 --> 03:23:17.879
Dark Stalker barked a laugh.

03:23:17.940 --> 03:23:20.340
How did she surprise you then?

03:23:20.399 --> 03:23:21.479
Moon asked.

03:23:21.540 --> 03:23:24.540
If you could see all these futures, How

03:23:24.540 --> 03:23:25.920
did she trick you with a bracelet?

03:23:25.979 --> 03:23:30.659
I had too much faith in her, he said.

03:23:30.719 --> 03:23:33.360
I saw the possibility that she would

03:23:33.360 --> 03:23:36.059
betray me in more than one future, but

03:23:36.059 --> 03:23:36.780
further down the line.

03:23:36.840 --> 03:23:39.840
I didn't want to believe it, so I never

03:23:39.840 --> 03:23:40.920
studied those paths.

03:23:40.979 --> 03:23:43.500
Just as she was supposed to stop looking

03:23:43.500 --> 03:23:45.360
down my darker paths as well.

03:23:45.420 --> 03:23:48.780
Up until the last moment, even with

03:23:48.780 --> 03:23:50.520
visions of blackness pressing against

03:23:50.520 --> 03:23:50.760
me.

03:23:50.819 --> 03:23:52.680
I still thought I could change your

03:23:52.680 --> 03:23:52.920
mind.

03:23:52.979 --> 03:23:56.520
That I could talk into trusting me, so we

03:23:56.520 --> 03:23:57.899
could fly into our bright, perfect

03:23:57.899 --> 03:23:58.319
future.

03:23:58.440 --> 03:24:01.799
He made a kind of growl, but Moon

03:24:01.799 --> 03:24:02.879
couldn't tell what was behind it.

03:24:02.940 --> 03:24:05.100
Bitterness, revenge.

03:24:05.159 --> 03:24:07.920
Despair, loneliness.

03:24:07.979 --> 03:24:11.159
I never saw any of this back then, though

03:24:11.159 --> 03:24:12.180
he said.

03:24:12.239 --> 03:24:15.420
I suppose prophecy doesn't extend 2000

03:24:15.420 --> 03:24:16.079
years forward.

03:24:16.200 --> 03:24:17.459
Not even for me.

03:24:17.520 --> 03:24:21.239
So you don't know what happens next, Moon

03:24:21.239 --> 03:24:21.540
said.

03:24:21.600 --> 03:24:26.399
All I can see is darkness, he said

03:24:26.399 --> 03:24:26.879
softly.

03:24:26.940 --> 03:24:30.120
All I can do is hope.

03:24:30.180 --> 03:24:32.040
Hope for what?

03:24:32.100 --> 03:24:35.459
Hope, for someone to set me free.

03:24:35.520 --> 03:24:38.280
You, specifically.

03:24:38.340 --> 03:24:41.940
Moon jumped up, dropping the Animus

03:24:41.940 --> 03:24:42.959
History's scroll.

03:24:43.020 --> 03:24:45.479
Starflight turned his head toward her, and

03:24:45.479 --> 03:24:47.100
Sora blinked up in surprise.

03:24:47.159 --> 03:24:49.799
Sorry, Moon said.

03:24:49.860 --> 03:24:51.899
Just had a thought.

03:24:51.959 --> 03:24:54.180
How can I set you free?

03:24:54.239 --> 03:24:55.260
She cried.

03:24:55.319 --> 03:24:56.340
I'm nobody.

03:24:56.399 --> 03:24:59.340
We have no idea where you are, and you're

03:24:59.340 --> 03:25:02.819
you're, The most dangerous dragon in

03:25:02.819 --> 03:25:03.840
pyrea history.

03:25:03.959 --> 03:25:05.879
Dark Stalker said dryly.

03:25:05.940 --> 03:25:08.340
You shouldn't believe everything you read

03:25:08.340 --> 03:25:08.700
Moon.

03:25:08.819 --> 03:25:11.940
Even if I did agree to do it, Moon

03:25:11.940 --> 03:25:15.360
thought, which I'm not saying I will, how

03:25:15.360 --> 03:25:15.780
could I?

03:25:15.840 --> 03:25:18.180
There's something I need.

03:25:18.239 --> 03:25:19.319
He said.

03:25:19.379 --> 03:25:23.100
Moon can get you called, sticking your

03:25:23.100 --> 03:25:23.879
head into the library.

03:25:23.940 --> 03:25:25.979
Didn't you hear the 3 gongs?

03:25:26.040 --> 03:25:27.540
We have to get to history class.

03:25:27.600 --> 03:25:28.860
Zora, you too.

03:25:28.920 --> 03:25:32.579
Sora scrambled to her feet, dropped her

03:25:32.579 --> 03:25:34.680
scroll with a clatter, and fumbled around

03:25:34.680 --> 03:25:35.639
trying to roll it back up.

03:25:35.700 --> 03:25:38.639
Moon picked up the animus histories

03:25:38.639 --> 03:25:40.319
wondering if she could skip class

03:25:40.319 --> 03:25:40.799
somehow.

03:25:40.860 --> 03:25:42.959
She kind of wanted to keep talking to

03:25:42.959 --> 03:25:45.180
Dark Stalker, which would be hard to do

03:25:45.180 --> 03:25:47.280
in a cave full of dragons all thinking at

03:25:47.280 --> 03:25:48.059
the top of their brains.

03:25:48.120 --> 03:25:50.159
Hi, Starflight.

03:25:50.219 --> 03:25:52.799
I am super excited, Kinkachu said.

03:25:52.860 --> 03:25:55.139
I don't know anything about history.

03:25:55.200 --> 03:25:58.739
I have a 1000000 questions for webs, like

03:25:58.739 --> 03:26:00.059
what's the scorching?

03:26:00.120 --> 03:26:01.799
And is it true there used to be

03:26:01.799 --> 03:26:03.059
scavengers everywhere?

03:26:03.120 --> 03:26:05.340
And who started the talents of peace?

03:26:05.399 --> 03:26:07.920
And what's the big ice wing tragedy from

03:26:07.920 --> 03:26:08.700
the past?

03:26:08.700 --> 03:26:11.760
and a scream of terror suddenly echoed

03:26:11.760 --> 03:26:12.540
through the tunnels?

03:26:12.600 --> 03:26:13.680
Help!

03:26:13.739 --> 03:26:14.879
Somebody shrieked.

03:26:14.940 --> 03:26:17.159
More screams, and the clamor of running

03:26:17.159 --> 03:26:18.840
dragons joined the tumult.

03:26:18.899 --> 03:26:21.540
The sky wing, she's here to kill us all.

03:26:21.600 --> 03:26:25.739
Chapter 10.

03:26:26.040 --> 03:26:30.479
Queen Scarlet, shot through Starflight's

03:26:30.479 --> 03:26:31.860
mind as they leaped over the desk.

03:26:31.920 --> 03:26:33.180
She's come for us.

03:26:33.299 --> 03:26:35.219
Find somewhere to hide.

03:26:35.280 --> 03:26:37.799
He cried to Moon, Kinkaju, and Zora.

03:26:37.860 --> 03:26:40.020
He stumbled forward, talons

03:26:40.020 --> 03:26:40.620
outstretched.

03:26:40.680 --> 03:26:42.180
Don't let her see you.

03:26:42.239 --> 03:26:45.000
Which way to the great hall, he thought

03:26:45.000 --> 03:26:45.659
frantically.

03:26:45.719 --> 03:26:47.100
I have to get there.

03:26:47.159 --> 03:26:47.879
I have to protect them.

03:26:47.940 --> 03:26:49.260
Who?

03:26:49.319 --> 03:26:50.459
Kikachu yelped.

03:26:50.520 --> 03:26:51.600
Who are we hiding from?

03:26:51.659 --> 03:26:54.840
Sora curled into a ball on the reeds

03:26:54.840 --> 03:26:55.260
trembling.

03:26:55.319 --> 03:26:57.780
Horrible images were lurching up from the

03:26:57.780 --> 03:27:00.180
mud puddle in her brain, dragons on

03:27:00.180 --> 03:27:00.540
fire.

03:27:00.600 --> 03:27:04.559
Dragons screaming, spears bristling, a

03:27:04.559 --> 03:27:06.299
little brown dragon bleeding from her

03:27:06.299 --> 03:27:07.739
neck as she plummeted to the ground.

03:27:07.799 --> 03:27:10.319
Moon clutched her head.

03:27:10.379 --> 03:27:12.959
The images weren't just coming from Sora

03:27:12.959 --> 03:27:14.399
all over the school.

03:27:14.459 --> 03:27:16.799
Dragonettes who'd been in the war were

03:27:16.799 --> 03:27:18.719
hearing the alarm and having awful

03:27:18.719 --> 03:27:19.379
flashbacks.

03:27:19.440 --> 03:27:21.479
She could hardly think straight through

03:27:21.479 --> 03:27:23.280
all the violence reeling around in her

03:27:23.280 --> 03:27:23.520
head.

03:27:23.579 --> 03:27:25.200
Raindrops.

03:27:25.260 --> 03:27:26.219
She tried to think.

03:27:26.280 --> 03:27:28.379
That won't work here.

03:27:28.440 --> 03:27:30.000
Dark Stalker said.

03:27:30.059 --> 03:27:31.680
Everyone is too panicked.

03:27:31.739 --> 03:27:34.139
Find the calmest voice and anger

03:27:34.139 --> 03:27:34.559
yourself.

03:27:34.620 --> 03:27:35.760
Focus on it.

03:27:35.819 --> 03:27:38.100
It'll help if it's someone who knows

03:27:38.100 --> 03:27:38.760
what's going on.

03:27:38.819 --> 03:27:42.479
Moon closed her eyes and searched rapidly

03:27:42.479 --> 03:27:43.620
through the tumult around her.

03:27:43.680 --> 03:27:46.799
Her mind landed, unexpectedly, in

03:27:46.799 --> 03:27:47.520
carnelians.

03:27:47.579 --> 03:27:50.940
She won't hurt me, Carnelian was thinking

03:27:50.940 --> 03:27:52.680
wary but unafraid.

03:27:52.739 --> 03:27:54.540
I wonder if she remembers me.

03:27:54.600 --> 03:27:58.920
So it's not Queen Scarlet, Moon realized

03:27:58.920 --> 03:28:01.079
or Cornelian would be angrier than that.

03:28:01.139 --> 03:28:03.899
Starflight was already hurrying away to

03:28:03.899 --> 03:28:06.000
the great hall, his wings brushing the

03:28:06.000 --> 03:28:08.459
rock walls on either side, his talons

03:28:08.459 --> 03:28:09.659
reaching forward anxiously.

03:28:09.719 --> 03:28:11.760
Moon started after him.

03:28:11.819 --> 03:28:13.260
Aren't we hiding?

03:28:13.319 --> 03:28:14.399
Kinkaju asked.

03:28:14.459 --> 03:28:16.079
Is that what you want to do?

03:28:16.139 --> 03:28:17.100
Moon asked.

03:28:17.159 --> 03:28:21.120
No, Kinkaju said, flaring green and

03:28:21.120 --> 03:28:23.459
purple and white and yellow in dizzying

03:28:23.459 --> 03:28:23.940
spirals.

03:28:24.000 --> 03:28:26.159
I thought that's what you would want to

03:28:26.159 --> 03:28:28.440
do, but chasing after him to see what's

03:28:28.440 --> 03:28:30.120
happening is much more exciting.

03:28:30.180 --> 03:28:31.979
I love my clawmate.

03:28:32.040 --> 03:28:33.719
She thought ecstatically.

03:28:33.780 --> 03:28:35.399
Bounding along beside Moon.

03:28:35.520 --> 03:28:37.979
They burst into the hall only a few

03:28:37.979 --> 03:28:39.420
moments behind Starflight.

03:28:39.479 --> 03:28:42.120
A sky wing stood in the center of the

03:28:42.120 --> 03:28:44.819
cave, staring wildly around her with

03:28:44.819 --> 03:28:46.200
eerie blue eyes.

03:28:46.260 --> 03:28:49.319
Smoke rose from her shimmering, metallic

03:28:49.319 --> 03:28:50.219
orange scales.

03:28:50.280 --> 03:28:54.000
Most students had fled, but winter and

03:28:54.000 --> 03:28:55.500
icicles stood in one of the tunnel

03:28:55.500 --> 03:28:57.840
entrances, glaring at the sky wing.

03:28:57.899 --> 03:29:00.000
Carnelian was there too, watching

03:29:00.000 --> 03:29:00.659
curiously.

03:29:00.719 --> 03:29:03.600
Two other dragons had apparently fainted

03:29:03.600 --> 03:29:06.059
before they could run away, a sea wing

03:29:06.059 --> 03:29:07.620
and a sand wing moon didn't know.

03:29:07.680 --> 03:29:09.719
Who's there?

03:29:09.780 --> 03:29:13.020
Starflight called, his voice shaking.

03:29:13.079 --> 03:29:15.600
Moon realized that he was trying to look

03:29:15.600 --> 03:29:18.180
brave, but that he was almost paralyzed

03:29:18.180 --> 03:29:18.659
with fear.

03:29:18.719 --> 03:29:21.780
His visions of the former Skywing queen

03:29:21.780 --> 03:29:24.540
were intensely replaying over and over

03:29:24.540 --> 03:29:26.520
most of them featuring Starflight

03:29:26.520 --> 03:29:28.559
bleeding in some kind of arena while she

03:29:28.559 --> 03:29:28.920
laughed.

03:29:28.979 --> 03:29:32.459
But the dragon he was afraid of, was not

03:29:32.459 --> 03:29:33.540
the dragon here in front of them.

03:29:33.600 --> 03:29:36.360
Moon didn't know who this was, or

03:29:36.360 --> 03:29:37.020
anything about her.

03:29:37.079 --> 03:29:39.719
Trying to look into the newcomer's mind

03:29:39.719 --> 03:29:41.399
was like touching an inferno.

03:29:41.459 --> 03:29:43.860
She couldn't read a single thought in the

03:29:43.860 --> 03:29:44.159
blaze.

03:29:44.219 --> 03:29:47.940
That's not Queen Scarlet, Moon said

03:29:47.940 --> 03:29:48.899
touching his shoulder.

03:29:48.959 --> 03:29:50.459
It's not?

03:29:50.459 --> 03:29:51.840
Starflight said.

03:29:51.899 --> 03:29:54.000
His wings collapsed with relief.

03:29:54.059 --> 03:29:58.500
Peril, Clay shouted, as he hurried into

03:29:58.500 --> 03:30:01.200
the cave, moving fast despite his limp.

03:30:01.260 --> 03:30:02.340
You came.

03:30:02.459 --> 03:30:06.420
Oh, great, tsunami thought, coming in

03:30:06.420 --> 03:30:07.020
right behind him.

03:30:07.139 --> 03:30:09.659
Peril instinctively shrank away from

03:30:09.659 --> 03:30:10.260
clay.

03:30:10.319 --> 03:30:12.840
But the wall of flames in her mind cooled

03:30:12.840 --> 03:30:14.579
for a brief moment as she looked at him.

03:30:14.700 --> 03:30:17.579
Moon caught a stab of fierce, desperate

03:30:17.579 --> 03:30:20.219
love and guilt, and then the fire

03:30:20.219 --> 03:30:22.139
swallowed everything coherent again.

03:30:22.200 --> 03:30:24.659
Clay didn't seem to notice her pulling

03:30:24.659 --> 03:30:24.899
away.

03:30:24.959 --> 03:30:27.540
He took one of Parel's talons and pressed

03:30:27.540 --> 03:30:30.299
it between his, a sizzling sound and

03:30:30.299 --> 03:30:32.459
burning smell rose from his scales where

03:30:32.459 --> 03:30:34.979
they touched, but when he let go, the

03:30:34.979 --> 03:30:36.780
burn healed over almost instantly.

03:30:36.840 --> 03:30:39.840
When we didn't hear from you, we assumed

03:30:39.840 --> 03:30:40.559
you weren't coming.

03:30:40.620 --> 03:30:41.819
Tsunami said.

03:30:41.879 --> 03:30:45.299
I thought I could find her, peril said

03:30:45.299 --> 03:30:47.159
tearing her gaze away from clay.

03:30:47.219 --> 03:30:48.600
But she's nowhere.

03:30:48.600 --> 03:30:50.280
I don't know where else to look.

03:30:50.340 --> 03:30:51.239
I'm sorry.

03:30:51.299 --> 03:30:55.139
Don't be, Clay said wholeheartedly.

03:30:55.260 --> 03:30:56.700
We're glad you're here.

03:30:56.760 --> 03:31:00.959
That's only true for him, Moon thought

03:31:00.959 --> 03:31:02.520
not remotely for anyone else.

03:31:02.639 --> 03:31:05.340
Peril's lucky she doesn't have mind

03:31:05.340 --> 03:31:05.760
reading.

03:31:05.819 --> 03:31:08.639
Almost every dragon who knew she was here

03:31:08.639 --> 03:31:12.659
was brimming with hostility, fear, fury

03:31:12.659 --> 03:31:14.639
or, in most cases, all three.

03:31:14.760 --> 03:31:18.059
We don't have a group for you, tsunami

03:31:18.059 --> 03:31:19.860
said, folding her wings back.

03:31:19.920 --> 03:31:21.840
We didn't know you were coming, so

03:31:21.840 --> 03:31:23.879
there's a sky wing in each winglet

03:31:23.879 --> 03:31:24.120
already.

03:31:24.180 --> 03:31:26.340
I don't have to stay.

03:31:26.399 --> 03:31:28.079
Pearl mumbled.

03:31:28.139 --> 03:31:30.120
She edged back a step toward the

03:31:30.120 --> 03:31:30.540
outside.

03:31:30.600 --> 03:31:33.479
But I want you to, Clay said.

03:31:33.600 --> 03:31:36.360
If Scarlet's looking for you too, we'll

03:31:36.360 --> 03:31:37.260
all be safer together.

03:31:37.319 --> 03:31:39.420
Don't worry about the winglets.

03:31:39.479 --> 03:31:40.260
We'll figure it out.

03:31:40.319 --> 03:31:43.020
He shot Tsunami a frown.

03:31:43.079 --> 03:31:44.459
Don't scare her away.

03:31:44.520 --> 03:31:46.620
She deserves a 2nd chance.

03:31:46.680 --> 03:31:50.100
Tsunami rolled her eyes, but a memory of

03:31:50.100 --> 03:31:52.200
peril saving Clay's life kept her from

03:31:52.200 --> 03:31:54.299
saying the rest of the snappish things in

03:31:54.299 --> 03:31:54.540
her head.

03:31:54.600 --> 03:31:57.059
I'll go ask Sonny where we should put

03:31:57.059 --> 03:31:57.239
you.

03:31:57.299 --> 03:31:59.760
She said instead, and swept away.

03:31:59.819 --> 03:32:02.100
She can't stay here.

03:32:02.219 --> 03:32:04.680
Winter suddenly barked, stepping

03:32:04.680 --> 03:32:04.979
forward.

03:32:05.040 --> 03:32:06.959
He jabbed a claw at peril.

03:32:07.020 --> 03:32:10.260
That dragon killed more than 20 ice wing

03:32:10.260 --> 03:32:10.620
prisoners.

03:32:10.680 --> 03:32:13.500
She was Queen Scarlet's favorite weapon.

03:32:13.559 --> 03:32:15.659
It's one thing to force us to work with

03:32:15.659 --> 03:32:18.479
deceitful night wings. and low born sand

03:32:18.479 --> 03:32:21.180
wings, but a straight up murderer.

03:32:21.239 --> 03:32:22.799
No one is going to stand for this.

03:32:22.860 --> 03:32:27.659
Besides, she's dangerous, his sister

03:32:27.659 --> 03:32:30.239
pointed out, in a smooth, high pitched

03:32:30.239 --> 03:32:32.700
voice, whether she is still working for

03:32:32.700 --> 03:32:35.879
Queen Scarlet, or not.

03:32:35.879 --> 03:32:38.639
The tone of her voice made it perfectly

03:32:38.639 --> 03:32:40.379
clear which of those she believed.

03:32:40.440 --> 03:32:43.139
A lot of dragons have done things they

03:32:43.139 --> 03:32:45.540
need to be forgiven for, Clay pointed

03:32:45.540 --> 03:32:45.780
out.

03:32:45.840 --> 03:32:48.719
Just around the corner, moon felt tsunami

03:32:48.719 --> 03:32:51.180
hear him, pause, and wince.

03:32:51.299 --> 03:32:53.040
Especially in the war.

03:32:53.100 --> 03:32:56.100
The agreement between the queens was

03:32:56.100 --> 03:32:57.180
amnesty for everyone.

03:32:57.239 --> 03:32:59.940
No grudges, no revenge.

03:33:00.000 --> 03:33:02.700
Easy for him to say.

03:33:02.760 --> 03:33:05.879
Winter thought bitterly, and the ice wing

03:33:05.879 --> 03:33:07.260
from the mountains shot through his head

03:33:07.260 --> 03:33:09.540
again, this time along with the word

03:33:09.540 --> 03:33:13.559
brother, fighting in battles, following

03:33:13.559 --> 03:33:15.120
orders from your general.

03:33:15.180 --> 03:33:17.639
That's normal warfare, he said.

03:33:17.700 --> 03:33:20.579
Killing prisoners while they're chained

03:33:20.579 --> 03:33:22.860
up or forcing them to fight a monster.

03:33:22.920 --> 03:33:24.659
How is that forgivable?

03:33:24.719 --> 03:33:28.559
Peril seemed to be shrinking and burning

03:33:28.559 --> 03:33:30.299
hotter at the same time.

03:33:30.360 --> 03:33:32.520
Her weird eyes glowered at winter through

03:33:32.520 --> 03:33:32.940
the smoke.

03:33:33.000 --> 03:33:37.379
Even Queen Ruby hasn't agreed to pardon

03:33:37.379 --> 03:33:39.780
that dragon, Icicle pointed out.

03:33:39.840 --> 03:33:42.299
She's been banned from the Sky Wing

03:33:42.299 --> 03:33:43.860
Palace, hasn't she?

03:33:43.920 --> 03:33:46.979
All the more reason to welcome her here

03:33:46.979 --> 03:33:48.360
Clay said.

03:33:48.420 --> 03:33:51.420
We're starting over, and 2nd chances are

03:33:51.420 --> 03:33:52.079
the whole point.

03:33:52.139 --> 03:33:54.479
He smiled at peril again.

03:33:54.540 --> 03:33:57.180
She lashed her tail and ducked her head.

03:33:57.239 --> 03:33:59.399
Come on, let's go see the others.

03:33:59.459 --> 03:34:02.579
Clay added diplomatically, waving peril

03:34:02.579 --> 03:34:04.139
toward the tunnel where tsunami had

03:34:04.139 --> 03:34:04.860
disappeared.

03:34:04.920 --> 03:34:07.440
Icicle turned to Winter as they left and

03:34:07.440 --> 03:34:07.979
hissed.

03:34:08.040 --> 03:34:10.920
I'll send a messenger to Queen Glacier

03:34:10.920 --> 03:34:11.280
tonight.

03:34:11.340 --> 03:34:15.000
The gong sounded twice, echoing through

03:34:15.000 --> 03:34:15.600
the tunnels.

03:34:15.659 --> 03:34:18.540
Time for history, Kinkaju said

03:34:18.540 --> 03:34:19.020
cheerfully.

03:34:19.079 --> 03:34:20.219
Come on, winter.

03:34:20.340 --> 03:34:23.459
Icicle gave him an amused arch look.

03:34:23.520 --> 03:34:25.020
How adorable.

03:34:25.079 --> 03:34:27.959
A rain wing with a crush on my brother.

03:34:28.079 --> 03:34:30.840
Winter shifted his wings uncomfortably

03:34:30.840 --> 03:34:32.639
and started after Kinkaju.

03:34:32.700 --> 03:34:34.559
She thinks it's funny.

03:34:34.680 --> 03:34:36.600
But if she knew what I've been feeling

03:34:36.600 --> 03:34:38.760
Who I've been thinking about?

03:34:38.819 --> 03:34:41.639
He slammed a wall of ice down over his

03:34:41.639 --> 03:34:44.459
thoughts, almost hard enough for Moon to

03:34:44.459 --> 03:34:46.379
fill the vibrations in her own skull.

03:34:46.379 --> 03:34:49.079
The history lesson cave was far down

03:34:49.079 --> 03:34:49.979
inside the mountain.

03:34:50.040 --> 03:34:52.559
At the intersection of 3 winding narrow

03:34:52.559 --> 03:34:52.979
tunnels.

03:34:53.040 --> 03:34:55.319
There were fewer of the fire globes along

03:34:55.319 --> 03:34:55.979
these tunnels.

03:34:56.040 --> 03:34:58.200
The ones here were shades of orange and

03:34:58.200 --> 03:35:00.479
blue, and they were interspersed with

03:35:00.479 --> 03:35:01.379
flickering torches.

03:35:01.440 --> 03:35:04.680
Moon noticed that Kinkachoo edged quickly

03:35:04.680 --> 03:35:06.299
past the open flames.

03:35:06.360 --> 03:35:08.459
The rain wing also didn't love the

03:35:08.459 --> 03:35:11.100
claustrophobic closeness of the walls, or

03:35:11.100 --> 03:35:12.780
how much darker it was this far down.

03:35:12.899 --> 03:35:16.979
Inside, the history cave's stone walls

03:35:16.979 --> 03:35:19.260
were covered in maps, the paper curling

03:35:19.260 --> 03:35:21.360
up at the edges, with different borders

03:35:21.360 --> 03:35:22.739
and years written on each one.

03:35:22.799 --> 03:35:25.799
Stacks of scrolls were piled untidily

03:35:25.799 --> 03:35:27.899
everywhere, overflowing the wooden racks

03:35:27.899 --> 03:35:28.559
provided for them.

03:35:28.620 --> 03:35:31.739
Webbs stood in the center of the cave

03:35:31.739 --> 03:35:33.540
waiting for everyone to gather in a

03:35:33.540 --> 03:35:34.139
circle around him.

03:35:34.200 --> 03:35:36.719
Moon sensed that he was the one who'd

03:35:36.719 --> 03:35:38.760
chosen the space, and that he preferred

03:35:38.760 --> 03:35:40.979
the dimmer, more underground feeling.

03:35:41.040 --> 03:35:43.139
He was the sea wing who'd brought the

03:35:43.139 --> 03:35:45.180
fish in the net, and he was a lot older

03:35:45.180 --> 03:35:46.739
than the prophecy dragonettes.

03:35:46.860 --> 03:35:49.440
Trails of regret ran underneath all his

03:35:49.440 --> 03:35:51.840
thoughts, even when he mostly focused on

03:35:51.840 --> 03:35:52.920
the lesson he was about to give.

03:35:52.979 --> 03:35:56.100
Moon wondered why he was here, and how

03:35:56.100 --> 03:35:57.360
he'd gotten the scar on his side.

03:35:57.420 --> 03:36:01.139
Moon's winglet filed in, and so did

03:36:01.139 --> 03:36:01.739
Sora's.

03:36:01.799 --> 03:36:04.440
As each dragon entered, Moon slipped

03:36:04.440 --> 03:36:06.299
their minds into the background rainstorm

03:36:06.299 --> 03:36:08.399
noise, and she felt her wings relax.

03:36:08.520 --> 03:36:12.299
Even in a cave filled with 15 dragons, she

03:36:12.299 --> 03:36:12.840
could be all right.

03:36:12.899 --> 03:36:15.959
Her head didn't hurt, and she didn't feel

03:36:15.959 --> 03:36:17.159
overwhelmed or confused.

03:36:17.219 --> 03:36:20.219
She could think her own thoughts, thanks

03:36:20.219 --> 03:36:21.299
to dark stalker.

03:36:21.360 --> 03:36:24.899
Moon noticed that Icicle and Saurus sat

03:36:24.899 --> 03:36:27.120
on opposite ends of a cave and didn't

03:36:27.120 --> 03:36:27.540
speak to each other.

03:36:27.600 --> 03:36:30.120
The other night wing was the male

03:36:30.120 --> 03:36:33.479
uninspiringly named Bigtail, the one Pike

03:36:33.479 --> 03:36:34.620
had growled at.

03:36:34.680 --> 03:36:36.659
Now she realized they were claw mates.

03:36:36.719 --> 03:36:38.819
She guessed that would be an

03:36:38.819 --> 03:36:40.620
uncomfortable cave to sleep in tonight.

03:36:40.680 --> 03:36:43.500
Big tail glanced at Moon and then quickly

03:36:43.500 --> 03:36:45.420
away, as if he didn't want to be

03:36:45.420 --> 03:36:46.319
associated with her.

03:36:46.379 --> 03:36:50.159
Pike slid past him, glowering, and nearly

03:36:50.159 --> 03:36:51.719
flicked Big Tail's nose with one of his

03:36:51.719 --> 03:36:52.020
wings.

03:36:52.079 --> 03:36:55.200
She was surprised to see that Carnelian

03:36:55.200 --> 03:36:57.239
didn't acknowledge the other Skywing.

03:36:57.299 --> 03:37:00.180
He had a horrible scar cross his snout as

03:37:00.180 --> 03:37:01.799
if he'd been in battle, like her.

03:37:01.860 --> 03:37:04.860
She hesitated for a moment, then let go

03:37:04.860 --> 03:37:06.420
of that raindrop for a moment to check

03:37:06.420 --> 03:37:07.739
Carnelian's mind.

03:37:07.799 --> 03:37:11.940
Flame, she heard Carnelian scoff, shooting

03:37:11.940 --> 03:37:12.600
him a glare.

03:37:12.659 --> 03:37:14.280
Talons of peace.

03:37:14.340 --> 03:37:17.459
Oh, that explained it.

03:37:17.520 --> 03:37:19.680
He'd hidden with the underground peace

03:37:19.680 --> 03:37:21.420
movement instead of fighting in the war.

03:37:21.479 --> 03:37:23.940
Moon wondered where he'd gotten that scar

03:37:23.940 --> 03:37:26.340
then, but even brushing the surface of

03:37:26.340 --> 03:37:28.559
his mind gave her a queasy feeling of

03:37:28.559 --> 03:37:29.700
overflowing rage.

03:37:29.760 --> 03:37:31.799
So she decided to stay out of it

03:37:31.799 --> 03:37:32.340
instead.

03:37:32.399 --> 03:37:35.100
Kinkachu spotted a small blue and gold

03:37:35.100 --> 03:37:37.440
rain wing. and dragged Moon over to her

03:37:37.440 --> 03:37:39.959
excited sparks going off in her mind.

03:37:40.020 --> 03:37:42.000
Moon, this is Tamron.

03:37:42.059 --> 03:37:44.280
Tamron, Moon is our new best friend.

03:37:44.340 --> 03:37:45.600
She's super funny.

03:37:45.659 --> 03:37:47.819
Moon, can Tameron touch her face?

03:37:47.879 --> 03:37:49.620
I'm super funny?

03:37:49.680 --> 03:37:50.760
Moon thought.

03:37:50.819 --> 03:37:52.200
In what universe?

03:37:52.319 --> 03:37:54.180
It's all right.

03:37:54.239 --> 03:37:57.299
I don't have to, Cameron said, smiling.

03:37:57.360 --> 03:38:00.959
Moon saw the pale film across Tamron's

03:38:00.959 --> 03:38:03.299
eyes and remembered that the rain wing

03:38:03.299 --> 03:38:03.659
was blind.

03:38:03.719 --> 03:38:05.280
You can.

03:38:05.399 --> 03:38:08.879
Moon let her talons touch tamarinds, and

03:38:08.879 --> 03:38:10.799
the rain wing brushed her claws gently

03:38:10.799 --> 03:38:14.040
across Moon's scales, horns, and snout.

03:38:14.459 --> 03:38:16.200
Moon got a shivering glimpse of a world

03:38:16.200 --> 03:38:18.600
without sight of Tamron's quiet

03:38:18.600 --> 03:38:20.700
competence and immense concentration.

03:38:20.760 --> 03:38:23.100
Have you figured everything out yet?

03:38:23.159 --> 03:38:25.200
Kingaju asked Tamarin.

03:38:25.260 --> 03:38:27.959
She had the rainforest all memorized, but

03:38:27.959 --> 03:38:30.360
of course, this is a whole new place, she

03:38:30.360 --> 03:38:33.000
added to Moon, so Queen Glory arranged

03:38:33.000 --> 03:38:34.799
for her to come early and spend a few

03:38:34.799 --> 03:38:36.180
days walking all the tunnels.

03:38:36.239 --> 03:38:38.520
I bet you know Jade Mountain better than

03:38:38.520 --> 03:38:39.000
anyone now.

03:38:39.120 --> 03:38:40.680
Ha!

03:38:40.739 --> 03:38:41.700
Tamron said.

03:38:41.760 --> 03:38:43.379
Well, I'm getting used to it.

03:38:43.440 --> 03:38:45.479
It's useful to have walls in a way.

03:38:45.600 --> 03:38:48.299
I can't wait for sun time though.

03:38:48.360 --> 03:38:49.559
Kinkachu said.

03:38:49.620 --> 03:38:51.959
Moon, after this, we're going to go sleep

03:38:51.959 --> 03:38:53.340
in the sun for the rest of the day.

03:38:53.399 --> 03:38:54.420
Want to join us?

03:38:54.479 --> 03:38:58.020
Uh, no thanks, Moon said.

03:38:58.079 --> 03:39:00.540
She'd seen rain wings doing that before

03:39:00.540 --> 03:39:01.979
but it still seemed odd to her.

03:39:02.040 --> 03:39:06.059
Everyone sit, Webb's ordered.

03:39:06.120 --> 03:39:09.299
A muscular sandwing, a lot older than the

03:39:09.299 --> 03:39:11.700
others, darted into the cave and sat down

03:39:11.700 --> 03:39:12.540
next to Tameron.

03:39:12.600 --> 03:39:14.579
Hey, she whispered.

03:39:14.639 --> 03:39:15.659
Did I miss anything?

03:39:15.719 --> 03:39:18.719
This is my clawmate.

03:39:18.780 --> 03:39:20.579
Onyx, Tamarin said.

03:39:20.700 --> 03:39:23.579
Onyx had very black eyes, and little

03:39:23.579 --> 03:39:25.680
black diamonds embedded between her pale

03:39:25.680 --> 03:39:27.719
yellow scales all along her wings.

03:39:27.780 --> 03:39:30.479
She wore a metal amulet around her neck

03:39:30.479 --> 03:39:33.059
and branching black lines were tattooed

03:39:33.059 --> 03:39:34.020
on her horns and neck.

03:39:34.079 --> 03:39:36.899
Her gaze was sharp, studying the others

03:39:36.899 --> 03:39:39.120
in the cave, and her mind was like

03:39:39.120 --> 03:39:40.020
shifting sand.

03:39:40.079 --> 03:39:43.079
Moon tipped her head, and realized that

03:39:43.079 --> 03:39:45.000
onyx was as hard to read as turtle.

03:39:45.059 --> 03:39:47.399
Nothing came from her mind but that same

03:39:47.399 --> 03:39:48.840
weird, quiet fuzz.

03:39:48.959 --> 03:39:51.120
How is she doing that?

03:39:51.180 --> 03:39:52.559
Dark Stalker?

03:39:52.620 --> 03:39:54.600
Can you read onyx and turtle?

03:39:54.659 --> 03:39:56.340
Am I just not powerful enough?

03:39:56.459 --> 03:39:59.940
A pause and then, No.

03:40:00.000 --> 03:40:02.520
They are both impenetrable to me as

03:40:02.520 --> 03:40:02.700
well.

03:40:02.819 --> 03:40:04.139
Really?

03:40:04.200 --> 03:40:06.420
Are they just really good at shielding?

03:40:06.479 --> 03:40:08.219
I'm not sure.

03:40:08.280 --> 03:40:11.219
I've never seen mental shielding advanced

03:40:11.219 --> 03:40:13.379
enough to block me, and who would have

03:40:13.379 --> 03:40:13.860
trained them?

03:40:13.979 --> 03:40:16.920
But perhaps my powers have grown weaker

03:40:16.920 --> 03:40:17.459
over time.

03:40:17.520 --> 03:40:20.280
Or perhaps, this kind of shielding

03:40:20.280 --> 03:40:22.200
evolved over the last 2000 years.

03:40:22.260 --> 03:40:26.219
Moon studied onyx, then glanced across

03:40:26.219 --> 03:40:27.120
the cave at Turtle.

03:40:27.239 --> 03:40:29.639
The 2 dragons had nothing in common that

03:40:29.639 --> 03:40:30.059
she could see.

03:40:30.180 --> 03:40:32.819
How could they both be the only dragons

03:40:32.819 --> 03:40:33.780
immune to mind reading?

03:40:33.840 --> 03:40:37.139
Some of you might know. who I am.

03:40:37.260 --> 03:40:39.840
Webb said, clearing his throat

03:40:39.840 --> 03:40:40.620
importantly.

03:40:40.680 --> 03:40:42.780
For those of you who don't.

03:40:42.899 --> 03:40:46.319
My name is Webbs, and I used to be part

03:40:46.319 --> 03:40:48.120
of the talons of peace.

03:40:48.180 --> 03:40:51.959
You may have heard of my son, Riptide, who

03:40:51.959 --> 03:40:54.239
is the new leader of whatever the talons

03:40:54.239 --> 03:40:55.739
of peace is becoming.

03:40:55.799 --> 03:40:58.680
I was one of the guardians who raised the

03:40:58.680 --> 03:41:00.000
dragonettes of destiny.

03:41:00.059 --> 03:41:03.959
I taught them the history of Pyria, and

03:41:03.959 --> 03:41:06.180
now they've asked me to teach it to you.

03:41:06.239 --> 03:41:10.739
So, we'll start at the beginning, with

03:41:10.739 --> 03:41:12.120
the scorching.

03:41:12.180 --> 03:41:16.079
I have a question, Icicle interjected.

03:41:16.139 --> 03:41:17.940
Already?

03:41:18.000 --> 03:41:19.500
Web said ruffled.

03:41:19.559 --> 03:41:21.360
I haven't even begun yet.

03:41:21.420 --> 03:41:24.479
About that Sky Wing.

03:41:24.540 --> 03:41:26.280
Icicle pressed on.

03:41:26.340 --> 03:41:28.200
The one who burns everything she

03:41:28.200 --> 03:41:28.620
touches.

03:41:28.739 --> 03:41:31.020
Have there been other dragons like that

03:41:31.020 --> 03:41:31.500
in history?

03:41:31.559 --> 03:41:33.600
Are they terribly dangerous?

03:41:33.659 --> 03:41:37.079
I mean, even frost breath doesn't work on

03:41:37.079 --> 03:41:37.319
her.

03:41:37.379 --> 03:41:40.620
So how have tribes dealt with dragons

03:41:40.620 --> 03:41:41.819
like that in the past?

03:41:41.879 --> 03:41:43.799
Is there a way to kill her?

03:41:43.860 --> 03:41:49.500
That's rather a gruesome topic for our

03:41:49.500 --> 03:41:51.540
1st day, Webb sputtered.

03:41:51.600 --> 03:41:55.139
I'd like to know more about Thorn, Onyx

03:41:55.139 --> 03:41:55.680
spoke up.

03:41:55.739 --> 03:41:59.459
You mean Queen Thorn, Kibley snapped.

03:41:59.520 --> 03:42:01.620
It's unprecedented, right?

03:42:01.680 --> 03:42:03.479
asked Onyx, ignoring him.

03:42:03.540 --> 03:42:06.000
There's never been a queen in history who

03:42:06.000 --> 03:42:07.620
hasn't descended from the royal family.

03:42:07.680 --> 03:42:08.520
Isn't that true?

03:42:08.579 --> 03:42:11.219
Well, not exactly.

03:42:11.280 --> 03:42:12.959
Webbs tried.

03:42:13.020 --> 03:42:16.379
Queen Thorn is the best queen the

03:42:16.379 --> 03:42:17.219
Sandwings have ever had.

03:42:17.340 --> 03:42:19.979
Kibli flared loyally.

03:42:20.280 --> 03:42:22.200
If you think you could do better, Maybe

03:42:22.200 --> 03:42:23.340
you should challenge her over the

03:42:23.340 --> 03:42:23.760
throne.

03:42:23.819 --> 03:42:27.899
But that's my point, Onyx said sharply.

03:42:27.959 --> 03:42:30.600
Does this mean now anyone could take the

03:42:30.600 --> 03:42:31.860
throne and become queen?

03:42:31.920 --> 03:42:33.840
Could that happen in the other tribes

03:42:33.840 --> 03:42:34.139
too?

03:42:34.200 --> 03:42:36.959
I mean, it sounds like asking for chaos

03:42:36.959 --> 03:42:37.920
and rebellion everywhere.

03:42:37.979 --> 03:42:39.120
That's all I'm saying.

03:42:39.180 --> 03:42:42.780
Uh, but it's rather an unusual.

03:42:42.840 --> 03:42:46.440
I mean, given the eye of onyx, and the

03:42:46.440 --> 03:42:48.239
situation with the 3 sisters.

03:42:48.299 --> 03:42:50.940
This is hardly inappropriate.

03:42:51.000 --> 03:42:53.819
Webbs flapped his wings around, his mind

03:42:53.819 --> 03:42:54.780
spinning.

03:42:54.840 --> 03:42:58.200
This might be a good chance to get some

03:42:58.200 --> 03:42:58.739
answers.

03:42:58.860 --> 03:43:01.079
Dark Stalker whispered in Moon's head.

03:43:01.139 --> 03:43:03.299
Are we going to learn about the night

03:43:03.299 --> 03:43:03.780
wings?

03:43:03.840 --> 03:43:05.100
Moon blurted out.

03:43:05.159 --> 03:43:09.000
I mean, historically, like maybe 2000

03:43:09.000 --> 03:43:12.239
years ago, like where they lived or, um

03:43:12.239 --> 03:43:14.819
where they buried the dark stalker?

03:43:14.879 --> 03:43:17.399
How am I supposed to nonchalantly ask

03:43:17.399 --> 03:43:18.239
that question?

03:43:18.299 --> 03:43:22.559
We may learn more about the night wings

03:43:22.559 --> 03:43:23.879
but not today.

03:43:23.940 --> 03:43:26.159
Webb said grumpily.

03:43:26.219 --> 03:43:30.479
As none of this is relevant to today's

03:43:30.479 --> 03:43:33.600
topic, which is the scorching.

03:43:33.659 --> 03:43:34.860
Ahem.

03:43:34.979 --> 03:43:37.559
He gathered up a bunch of scrolls and

03:43:37.559 --> 03:43:38.639
thrust them at turtle.

03:43:38.700 --> 03:43:40.440
Give these out.

03:43:40.559 --> 03:43:42.600
One to each dragonette.

03:43:42.659 --> 03:43:45.420
We'll begin at the beginning.

03:43:45.479 --> 03:43:50.579
That means over 5000 years ago, before

03:43:50.579 --> 03:43:52.680
there were tribes or kingdoms.

03:43:52.739 --> 03:43:56.280
Back when scavengers swarmed over the

03:43:56.280 --> 03:43:56.940
whole continent.

03:43:57.000 --> 03:44:00.719
Unroll your scrolls to the 1st map

03:44:00.719 --> 03:44:01.079
please.

03:44:01.139 --> 03:44:04.440
Moon took her scroll from Turtle with a

03:44:04.440 --> 03:44:04.739
sigh.

03:44:04.799 --> 03:44:07.079
It was worth a try.

03:44:07.139 --> 03:44:09.059
Dark Stalker observed.

03:44:09.120 --> 03:44:12.059
You said there was something unique, Moon

03:44:12.059 --> 03:44:12.479
thought.

03:44:12.540 --> 03:44:13.739
Yes.

03:44:13.799 --> 03:44:16.920
If you can find it, and bring it to me

03:44:16.920 --> 03:44:18.899
then I could free myself.

03:44:19.020 --> 03:44:21.899
Moon thought of the general reaction to

03:44:21.899 --> 03:44:22.379
peril.

03:44:22.440 --> 03:44:25.079
If they were so terrified of her, how

03:44:25.079 --> 03:44:27.059
would everyone react if Moon brought back

03:44:27.059 --> 03:44:28.559
the creature from their nightmares?

03:44:28.620 --> 03:44:31.440
Could Dark Stalker be trusted any more

03:44:31.440 --> 03:44:31.979
than peril?

03:44:32.040 --> 03:44:34.260
Even if she believed he could be?

03:44:34.319 --> 03:44:35.760
Would anyone else believe it?

03:44:35.819 --> 03:44:38.100
And wouldn't they all hate her even more

03:44:38.100 --> 03:44:40.319
than they already did for being the one

03:44:40.319 --> 03:44:41.700
to bring him into the light again?

03:44:41.760 --> 03:44:43.920
She furrowed her brow.

03:44:43.979 --> 03:44:45.479
Wait.

03:44:45.540 --> 03:44:47.940
Why can't you use your animus power to

03:44:47.940 --> 03:44:48.959
free yourself now?

03:44:49.020 --> 03:44:50.520
Moon asked him.

03:44:50.579 --> 03:44:53.219
There were those animus touched tunnels

03:44:53.219 --> 03:44:54.959
from the rainforest to other parts of

03:44:54.959 --> 03:44:55.620
Pyrea.

03:44:55.680 --> 03:44:57.899
Couldn't dark soccer just make one of

03:44:57.899 --> 03:44:59.399
those and pop out wherever he wanted?

03:44:59.520 --> 03:45:02.940
For a long, nervous moment, Moon had the

03:45:02.940 --> 03:45:04.739
anxious feeling that exactly that might

03:45:04.739 --> 03:45:07.440
happen, that Dark Stalker might suddenly

03:45:07.440 --> 03:45:09.840
just burst through the wall and appear in

03:45:09.840 --> 03:45:10.979
the cave right in front of her.

03:45:11.040 --> 03:45:12.840
I can't.

03:45:12.959 --> 03:45:14.819
Dark Stalker said finally.

03:45:14.879 --> 03:45:16.559
Why not?

03:45:16.680 --> 03:45:18.840
He chuckled sadly.

03:45:18.899 --> 03:45:22.319
I was too smart for my own good.

03:45:22.379 --> 03:45:27.360
There are many stories about life before

03:45:27.360 --> 03:45:28.559
the scorching.

03:45:28.620 --> 03:45:29.940
Webbs intoned.

03:45:30.000 --> 03:45:34.500
After so many 1000s of years, it is hard

03:45:34.500 --> 03:45:36.180
to know which ones to believe.

03:45:36.239 --> 03:45:38.219
What do you mean?

03:45:38.340 --> 03:45:39.420
Moon asked.

03:45:39.479 --> 03:45:43.319
I had a truly brilliant idea.

03:45:43.379 --> 03:45:44.459
He answered.

03:45:44.520 --> 03:45:46.620
After what Albatross did.

03:45:46.680 --> 03:45:48.120
The massacre.

03:45:48.180 --> 03:45:51.540
We realized that animus magic took a

03:45:51.540 --> 03:45:52.920
little of your soul every time you used

03:45:52.920 --> 03:45:53.159
it.

03:45:53.219 --> 03:45:55.799
So I gathered all of my power and put it

03:45:55.799 --> 03:45:57.600
in a, a vessel.

03:45:57.659 --> 03:45:59.219
Do you see what I mean?

03:45:59.280 --> 03:46:01.440
If the power wasn't in me?

03:46:01.500 --> 03:46:03.239
It couldn't turn me evil.

03:46:03.299 --> 03:46:06.299
I could use the vessel to cast my animus

03:46:06.299 --> 03:46:09.360
spells, as many as I wanted, without ever

03:46:09.360 --> 03:46:12.000
being affected, I thought this would

03:46:12.000 --> 03:46:14.100
prove to Clearsight, that she didn't have

03:46:14.100 --> 03:46:14.760
to worry about me.

03:46:14.819 --> 03:46:16.680
I would always be myself.

03:46:16.739 --> 03:46:19.559
And what happened to Albatross would

03:46:19.559 --> 03:46:20.399
never happen to me.

03:46:20.459 --> 03:46:25.139
Of course, that means, I need my object

03:46:25.139 --> 03:46:27.899
of power in order to use it, and of

03:46:27.899 --> 03:46:29.159
course, I didn't have it with me when

03:46:29.159 --> 03:46:30.420
clear sight betrayed me.

03:46:30.479 --> 03:46:32.399
Wherever I am now.

03:46:32.459 --> 03:46:33.840
It's not here.

03:46:33.899 --> 03:46:37.079
But if I had it back, I could get myself

03:46:37.079 --> 03:46:37.559
out.

03:46:37.620 --> 03:46:39.780
You wouldn't have to do anything except

03:46:39.780 --> 03:46:40.620
bring it to me.

03:46:40.680 --> 03:46:44.219
Please, I need your help, Moon.

03:46:44.340 --> 03:46:46.260
I just want to be free.

03:46:46.319 --> 03:46:49.440
After 2000 years, can't you imagine?

03:46:49.500 --> 03:46:51.180
Is that so much to ask?

03:46:51.239 --> 03:46:54.180
Moon rolled a corner of the scroll

03:46:54.180 --> 03:46:56.520
between her claws, transferring the

03:46:56.520 --> 03:46:59.340
animus power to an object that did sound

03:46:59.340 --> 03:47:00.659
like a brilliant idea.

03:47:00.719 --> 03:47:02.760
Had any other animus ever thought of

03:47:02.760 --> 03:47:02.940
that?

03:47:03.000 --> 03:47:05.639
Maybe Dark Stalker was telling the

03:47:05.639 --> 03:47:05.940
truth.

03:47:06.000 --> 03:47:08.700
Maybe he wasn't evil. and never would

03:47:08.700 --> 03:47:09.059
have been.

03:47:09.120 --> 03:47:11.219
Bring it to you.

03:47:11.280 --> 03:47:14.520
She thought, which would mean finding it

03:47:14.520 --> 03:47:17.340
and then finding you, and also figuring

03:47:17.340 --> 03:47:18.420
out how to get it to you.

03:47:18.479 --> 03:47:20.219
Not that simple.

03:47:20.280 --> 03:47:22.319
I'll help you.

03:47:22.379 --> 03:47:23.760
He promised.

03:47:23.819 --> 03:47:25.260
Any way you need.

03:47:25.319 --> 03:47:26.760
Please.

03:47:26.819 --> 03:47:29.159
Don't take away my only hope.

03:47:29.219 --> 03:47:31.680
Please tell me you'll at least think

03:47:31.680 --> 03:47:32.040
about it.

03:47:32.100 --> 03:47:36.120
Most of the prescorching stories would

03:47:36.120 --> 03:47:40.319
best be described as legends, or perhaps

03:47:40.319 --> 03:47:42.059
even fairy tales.

03:47:42.120 --> 03:47:44.159
Webbs was droning on.

03:47:44.219 --> 03:47:47.639
It is unlikely that scavengers were ever

03:47:47.639 --> 03:47:51.000
capable of being as organized or advanced

03:47:51.000 --> 03:47:54.059
as some of these imaginative fictions

03:47:54.059 --> 03:47:55.260
would have us believe.

03:47:55.319 --> 03:47:59.340
Stories often change and grow over time.

03:47:59.399 --> 03:48:03.659
Like Dark Stalker's story, Moon Thought.

03:48:03.719 --> 03:48:06.180
Everything we know about him was passed

03:48:06.180 --> 03:48:08.100
down by those who defeated and feared

03:48:08.100 --> 03:48:08.459
him.

03:48:08.520 --> 03:48:10.440
Maybe there's more to it.

03:48:10.500 --> 03:48:12.420
But how would I know?

03:48:12.540 --> 03:48:15.059
She glanced around the cave.

03:48:15.059 --> 03:48:16.680
At her winglet.

03:48:16.739 --> 03:48:18.840
At these new friends who had accepted her

03:48:18.840 --> 03:48:19.260
so far.

03:48:19.319 --> 03:48:22.440
If they found out about her powers, would

03:48:22.440 --> 03:48:24.600
they be afraid of her, the same way

03:48:24.600 --> 03:48:26.700
Clearsight and Fathom ended up fearing

03:48:26.700 --> 03:48:29.100
Dark Stalker, would they think she was

03:48:29.100 --> 03:48:30.899
dangerous or cursed?

03:48:31.020 --> 03:48:32.700
Was her mother right?

03:48:32.760 --> 03:48:35.700
That they'd reject her, and maybe even

03:48:35.700 --> 03:48:36.600
want to kill her?

03:48:36.659 --> 03:48:39.540
Moon curled her talons in and took a deep

03:48:39.540 --> 03:48:40.139
breath.

03:48:40.200 --> 03:48:43.379
All right, dark stalker, she promised.

03:48:43.440 --> 03:48:45.000
I'll think about it.

03:48:45.059 --> 03:48:49.260
Chapter 11.

03:48:49.559 --> 03:48:52.920
Moon did think about Dark Stalker.

03:48:52.979 --> 03:48:54.659
She thought about him the rest of the day

03:48:54.659 --> 03:48:57.360
as she explored the tunnels of the school

03:48:57.360 --> 03:48:59.579
during Kinkaju's sometime.

03:48:59.639 --> 03:49:01.500
She ran into a dead end and thought about

03:49:01.500 --> 03:49:03.959
what it must be like to be trapped in

03:49:03.959 --> 03:49:04.620
stone forever.

03:49:04.680 --> 03:49:07.500
She heard the flurries of anxieties

03:49:07.500 --> 03:49:09.719
swirling around about how dangerous peril

03:49:09.719 --> 03:49:12.000
was, and she thought about having powers

03:49:12.000 --> 03:49:14.399
you can't control, and what you can

03:49:14.399 --> 03:49:16.920
choose to do with them, or whether what

03:49:16.920 --> 03:49:18.479
you do with them isn't really up to you

03:49:18.479 --> 03:49:18.959
in the end.

03:49:19.020 --> 03:49:21.479
Eventually she realized.

03:49:21.540 --> 03:49:22.920
She was going to have to talk to

03:49:22.920 --> 03:49:23.280
somebody.

03:49:23.340 --> 03:49:26.459
Worse, she was going to have to talk to a

03:49:26.459 --> 03:49:29.280
night wing, one from the tribe, not

03:49:29.280 --> 03:49:31.260
Starflight, or fate speaker.

03:49:31.319 --> 03:49:33.299
There were 4 others at the school.

03:49:33.360 --> 03:49:36.420
Bigtail wouldn't be any help, even if he

03:49:36.420 --> 03:49:38.700
knew anything about dark stalker, which

03:49:38.700 --> 03:49:40.979
left mind reader, mighty Claus, and

03:49:40.979 --> 03:49:41.700
fearless.

03:49:41.819 --> 03:49:44.159
She searched the school carefully with

03:49:44.159 --> 03:49:46.079
her mind until she found one of them

03:49:46.079 --> 03:49:46.319
alone.

03:49:46.379 --> 03:49:49.739
Mighty Claus was in the art cave, with no

03:49:49.739 --> 03:49:50.520
other dragons around.

03:49:50.639 --> 03:49:52.739
Was this a good idea?

03:49:52.799 --> 03:49:55.079
Mighty Claus was one of the more

03:49:55.079 --> 03:49:57.540
outwardly friendly dragons, but she'd

03:49:57.540 --> 03:49:59.219
seen darkness and jealousy in his head

03:49:59.219 --> 03:49:59.520
before.

03:49:59.579 --> 03:50:02.819
They were close to the same age, and once

03:50:02.819 --> 03:50:05.399
she'd heard him think, if my mother had

03:50:05.399 --> 03:50:07.680
any spine, she'd have hidden me in the

03:50:07.680 --> 03:50:08.340
rainforest.

03:50:08.340 --> 03:50:11.100
She hesitated in the entrance to the art

03:50:11.100 --> 03:50:11.639
cave.

03:50:11.700 --> 03:50:14.159
Normally the cave would have been flooded

03:50:14.159 --> 03:50:16.379
with sunlight, coming through holes in

03:50:16.379 --> 03:50:18.120
the walls and ceiling, but it was

03:50:18.120 --> 03:50:19.260
twilight outside now.

03:50:19.319 --> 03:50:21.780
Art supplies were tucked into every

03:50:21.780 --> 03:50:24.719
crevice, brushes, all colors of paint

03:50:24.719 --> 03:50:28.200
blank scrolls, clay for sculpting, wood

03:50:28.200 --> 03:50:31.440
and glass, and metal and beads, even a

03:50:31.440 --> 03:50:32.940
loom where someone had already begun a

03:50:32.940 --> 03:50:33.420
tapestry.

03:50:33.479 --> 03:50:36.659
Clever little wooden dragon statues were

03:50:36.659 --> 03:50:38.760
perched on outcroppings around the walls

03:50:38.760 --> 03:50:41.639
with green or blue or orange glass beads

03:50:41.639 --> 03:50:42.120
for eyes.

03:50:42.180 --> 03:50:44.340
There were too many to have been made in

03:50:44.340 --> 03:50:47.100
the last 2 days, so Moon wondered who had

03:50:47.100 --> 03:50:48.899
made them, one of the school founders.

03:50:49.020 --> 03:50:52.020
Over her head, a giant metalwork

03:50:52.020 --> 03:50:54.120
sculpture made of gleaming copper wire

03:50:54.120 --> 03:50:56.399
wound across the ceiling, looking like

03:50:56.399 --> 03:50:56.940
flames.

03:50:57.000 --> 03:50:59.879
Several clear glass globes were suspended

03:50:59.879 --> 03:51:02.639
from it, glowing with firelight, now that

03:51:02.639 --> 03:51:03.299
the sun was going down.

03:51:03.360 --> 03:51:06.479
A black dragon stood in the middle of the

03:51:06.479 --> 03:51:09.120
cave, considering an easel with a canvas

03:51:09.120 --> 03:51:09.420
on it.

03:51:09.420 --> 03:51:11.879
He was not as thin as he had been when

03:51:11.879 --> 03:51:14.159
she met him 5 months ago, but he looked

03:51:14.159 --> 03:51:15.360
as though he hadn't filled out quite

03:51:15.360 --> 03:51:15.899
evenly.

03:51:15.959 --> 03:51:19.079
He had a round belly now, but his face

03:51:19.079 --> 03:51:21.959
was still lean, with sharp jawbones and

03:51:21.959 --> 03:51:23.159
deep hollows under his eyes.

03:51:23.219 --> 03:51:26.280
Even after 6 months of clean rainforest

03:51:26.280 --> 03:51:28.559
air and healthy eating, he still had a

03:51:28.559 --> 03:51:30.780
hint of a rasp to his voice, and

03:51:30.780 --> 03:51:32.459
sometimes his claws shook a little when

03:51:32.459 --> 03:51:34.500
he reached for something, and he thought

03:51:34.500 --> 03:51:35.940
about food almost constantly.

03:51:36.000 --> 03:51:38.819
Until he was distracted by something.

03:51:38.879 --> 03:51:40.860
For instance, her.

03:51:40.920 --> 03:51:43.319
Mighty Claus looked up and narrowed his

03:51:43.319 --> 03:51:44.760
eyes when he spotted Moon in the

03:51:44.760 --> 03:51:45.000
doorway.

03:51:45.059 --> 03:51:47.459
Hey, he said.

03:51:47.520 --> 03:51:49.379
Neither welcoming nor hostile.

03:51:49.440 --> 03:51:51.360
Never know what to say to her.

03:51:51.479 --> 03:51:52.920
Muttered his mind.

03:51:53.040 --> 03:51:55.979
Hi, Moon said nervously.

03:51:56.040 --> 03:51:58.500
He fiddled with a few small jars of paint

03:51:58.500 --> 03:52:00.840
on a table beside him, then glanced over

03:52:00.840 --> 03:52:01.260
at her again.

03:52:01.319 --> 03:52:05.459
You hear to paint, he asked, or just

03:52:05.459 --> 03:52:06.479
stare at me awkwardly.

03:52:06.540 --> 03:52:10.020
Um, yes, Moon said.

03:52:10.079 --> 03:52:12.000
This was going to be a disaster.

03:52:12.059 --> 03:52:14.280
How could she get any answers to her

03:52:14.280 --> 03:52:16.200
questions if she couldn't even say 2

03:52:16.200 --> 03:52:16.799
words to him.

03:52:16.920 --> 03:52:19.620
He gestured with one wing to a stack of

03:52:19.620 --> 03:52:22.079
canvases, and she took one and propped it

03:52:22.079 --> 03:52:24.420
on an easel not too far from him, but

03:52:24.420 --> 03:52:25.620
where neither of them could see the

03:52:25.620 --> 03:52:26.340
other's painting.

03:52:26.340 --> 03:52:28.739
It felt like it would be too intrusive to

03:52:28.739 --> 03:52:30.000
stand where she could watch what he was

03:52:30.000 --> 03:52:30.780
working on.

03:52:30.840 --> 03:52:33.239
Moon had never tried painting before.

03:52:33.299 --> 03:52:35.340
She had no idea where to begin.

03:52:35.399 --> 03:52:37.500
She ran her claws over the different

03:52:37.500 --> 03:52:40.079
sizes of paint brushes, smooth wooden

03:52:40.079 --> 03:52:42.840
handles, neat bristles ranging from fang

03:52:42.840 --> 03:52:45.120
sharp, thin to fat as a dragon's ear.

03:52:45.239 --> 03:52:47.940
After a minute, she chose one somewhere

03:52:47.940 --> 03:52:49.739
in the middle, and brought it back to her

03:52:49.739 --> 03:52:51.959
canvas, along with a few shades of blue

03:52:51.959 --> 03:52:52.440
and green.

03:52:52.500 --> 03:52:55.739
Mighty Claus didn't say anything for a

03:52:55.739 --> 03:52:55.979
while.

03:52:56.040 --> 03:52:58.200
He looked as though he was concentrating

03:52:58.200 --> 03:53:00.180
on his painting, but his thoughts were

03:53:00.180 --> 03:53:02.280
swooping in all different directions, like

03:53:02.280 --> 03:53:04.200
a disturbed cluster of dragonflies.

03:53:04.260 --> 03:53:06.299
No idea what I'm doing.

03:53:06.360 --> 03:53:08.579
Why does Starfight think this will help

03:53:08.579 --> 03:53:08.819
me?

03:53:08.879 --> 03:53:11.159
Would it be weird to go back to the pray

03:53:11.159 --> 03:53:12.120
center again tonight?

03:53:12.180 --> 03:53:14.280
Maybe there'll be some sheep left.

03:53:14.340 --> 03:53:16.860
Three meals in one day.

03:53:16.920 --> 03:53:19.020
Will anyone notice or yell at me?

03:53:19.079 --> 03:53:20.819
Why is Moon here?

03:53:20.879 --> 03:53:23.159
Maybe Starflight sent her too.

03:53:23.219 --> 03:53:25.860
Although she doesn't have any trauma to

03:53:25.860 --> 03:53:28.139
work through, with her perfect life in

03:53:28.139 --> 03:53:30.420
the rainforest, always as much as she

03:53:30.420 --> 03:53:31.020
wanted to eat.

03:53:31.139 --> 03:53:33.540
No adult dragons yelling at her.

03:53:33.600 --> 03:53:35.639
No class is online.

03:53:35.700 --> 03:53:38.159
No death smoldering right over her head

03:53:38.159 --> 03:53:39.059
all the time.

03:53:39.120 --> 03:53:41.159
Do you like it here?

03:53:41.219 --> 03:53:42.719
Moon finally said.

03:53:42.780 --> 03:53:45.059
Breaking into his thoughts to try and

03:53:45.059 --> 03:53:46.739
stem the flow of resentment about her.

03:53:46.799 --> 03:53:48.180
It worked.

03:53:48.239 --> 03:53:50.879
He stopped and twitched his tail, staring

03:53:50.879 --> 03:53:51.600
at his painting.

03:53:51.659 --> 03:53:53.280
I guess.

03:53:53.340 --> 03:53:55.979
It's more like the fortress here than the

03:53:55.979 --> 03:53:58.860
rainforest, except it smells better, and

03:53:58.860 --> 03:54:02.340
there's sunshine, and prey, and dragons

03:54:02.340 --> 03:54:03.120
of all colors.

03:54:03.180 --> 03:54:05.760
It's weird being around all the other

03:54:05.760 --> 03:54:06.840
tribes, isn't it?

03:54:06.899 --> 03:54:07.739
Moon tried.

03:54:07.799 --> 03:54:10.500
Definitely, he said.

03:54:10.620 --> 03:54:12.479
We were always told to stay away from

03:54:12.479 --> 03:54:13.860
them unless we were on a mission.

03:54:13.920 --> 03:54:17.340
Like to deliver a prophecy, or put the

03:54:17.340 --> 03:54:18.479
fear of night wings in them.

03:54:18.540 --> 03:54:21.540
Otherwise, stay away so they don't figure

03:54:21.540 --> 03:54:22.200
us out.

03:54:22.260 --> 03:54:25.260
That we're ordinary, you mean?

03:54:25.319 --> 03:54:26.399
Moon asked.

03:54:26.459 --> 03:54:28.319
He flicked his wings with a frown.

03:54:28.379 --> 03:54:30.899
Nightwings aren't ordinary.

03:54:30.959 --> 03:54:33.360
Of course, she would think so.

03:54:33.420 --> 03:54:36.059
We're more intelligent than any other

03:54:36.059 --> 03:54:36.540
tribe.

03:54:36.600 --> 03:54:39.420
We shape the world, other dragons just

03:54:39.420 --> 03:54:39.899
live in it.

03:54:39.959 --> 03:54:42.479
She could hear that he was parroting

03:54:42.479 --> 03:54:45.540
lines he'd heard over and over again from

03:54:45.540 --> 03:54:46.559
older night wings.

03:54:46.620 --> 03:54:50.399
I mean, I just meant that we don't have

03:54:50.399 --> 03:54:53.579
the powers we say we do, right?

03:54:53.639 --> 03:54:54.959
Moon stammered.

03:54:55.020 --> 03:54:58.860
Maybe we don't right now, mighty Claus

03:54:58.860 --> 03:54:59.159
said.

03:54:59.219 --> 03:55:01.559
He looked away from her and stabbed his

03:55:01.559 --> 03:55:04.440
paintbrush into a pot of red paint, but

03:55:04.440 --> 03:55:06.719
we did, and we might again one day.

03:55:06.780 --> 03:55:08.940
We should have let everyone keep

03:55:08.940 --> 03:55:09.719
believing in them.

03:55:09.780 --> 03:55:12.059
We were well trained.

03:55:12.120 --> 03:55:13.920
No one would have guessed if we were

03:55:13.920 --> 03:55:16.680
careful, especially after the success of

03:55:16.680 --> 03:55:18.059
the Dragonette prophecy.

03:55:18.120 --> 03:55:20.940
Well trained, moon echoed.

03:55:21.000 --> 03:55:22.860
Our classes.

03:55:22.920 --> 03:55:25.680
Mighty Claus slashed his brush across his

03:55:25.680 --> 03:55:29.280
canvas, how to lie, how to develop a

03:55:29.280 --> 03:55:32.040
convincing prophecy, how to sound like

03:55:32.040 --> 03:55:33.239
you're reading someone's mind.

03:55:33.299 --> 03:55:35.340
You missed out on all of that.

03:55:35.459 --> 03:55:38.639
Lounging around with sloths, eating

03:55:38.639 --> 03:55:39.719
bananas all day.

03:55:39.840 --> 03:55:42.780
But we had to trade all our secrets for

03:55:42.780 --> 03:55:43.079
safety.

03:55:43.139 --> 03:55:46.799
Now, thanks to Queen Glory, and Death

03:55:46.799 --> 03:55:49.020
Bringer, and Sonny, and Stone Mover.

03:55:49.079 --> 03:55:51.360
The whole world knows that night wings

03:55:51.360 --> 03:55:52.079
have no powers.

03:55:52.139 --> 03:55:54.360
No one respects us anymore.

03:55:54.420 --> 03:55:57.180
The looks the other dragons give me

03:55:57.180 --> 03:55:57.360
here.

03:55:57.479 --> 03:56:00.360
Like I either ate their favorite scroll

03:56:00.360 --> 03:56:02.819
or I might suddenly burst into flames, and

03:56:02.819 --> 03:56:03.600
they don't know which.

03:56:03.659 --> 03:56:06.299
But is it true?

03:56:06.360 --> 03:56:09.659
Moon said hesitantly, that no one has

03:56:09.659 --> 03:56:12.000
powers anymore, not anyone?

03:56:12.059 --> 03:56:15.000
He shook his head, glaring at his

03:56:15.000 --> 03:56:15.420
painting.

03:56:15.479 --> 03:56:18.719
Not in 100s of years, he thought.

03:56:18.780 --> 03:56:22.440
If the old scrolls were true, if we ever

03:56:22.440 --> 03:56:23.520
had them in the 1st place.

03:56:23.579 --> 03:56:26.520
Why do you think we lost them?

03:56:26.579 --> 03:56:27.659
Moon wondered.

03:56:27.780 --> 03:56:29.879
Mighty Claus shrugged.

03:56:29.940 --> 03:56:31.860
He looked as if he was hoping to get out

03:56:31.860 --> 03:56:33.719
of the conversation by focusing on his

03:56:33.719 --> 03:56:37.200
canvas, but in his head, she heard maybe

03:56:37.200 --> 03:56:39.120
the volcano sucked it out of us.

03:56:39.239 --> 03:56:41.940
And she felt the heavy smoke and heat

03:56:41.940 --> 03:56:43.920
that lingered in his memory.

03:56:43.979 --> 03:56:46.139
They painted for a while in silence.

03:56:46.200 --> 03:56:50.819
Um, Moon said finally, Do you know

03:56:50.819 --> 03:56:52.319
anything about the dark stalker?

03:56:52.379 --> 03:56:55.500
Mari Claus jumped, as if she'd flung

03:56:55.500 --> 03:56:56.280
paint all over him.

03:56:56.340 --> 03:56:58.079
Don't talk about him.

03:56:58.139 --> 03:57:00.120
Why would you ever talk about him?

03:57:00.239 --> 03:57:04.079
I just wondered, Moon said, startled.

03:57:04.139 --> 03:57:06.059
I thought he was a ghost story.

03:57:06.120 --> 03:57:10.559
No, he's definitely real, and he's

03:57:10.559 --> 03:57:12.299
definitely coming back to kill us all one

03:57:12.299 --> 03:57:12.540
day.

03:57:12.600 --> 03:57:15.239
Matty Claus said with a shudder.

03:57:15.299 --> 03:57:18.780
My father used to tell me about him, while

03:57:18.780 --> 03:57:19.559
he taught me to fly.

03:57:19.620 --> 03:57:21.899
He'd say, flap harder.

03:57:21.959 --> 03:57:24.540
Imagine the dark stalker is chasing you.

03:57:24.600 --> 03:57:28.079
Or if you can't twist into a dive faster

03:57:28.079 --> 03:57:30.479
than that, the dark stalker will catch

03:57:30.479 --> 03:57:32.639
you and rip off your claws and eat your

03:57:32.639 --> 03:57:33.000
brain.

03:57:33.120 --> 03:57:36.299
He told me about how the tribe buried him

03:57:36.299 --> 03:57:38.700
a long time ago, and then ran away to

03:57:38.700 --> 03:57:41.520
hide, but he's slowly clawing his way

03:57:41.520 --> 03:57:41.819
out.

03:57:41.879 --> 03:57:45.420
And one day, he'll break free, and come

03:57:45.420 --> 03:57:46.739
to kill us all for revenge.

03:57:46.799 --> 03:57:50.040
Moon blinked at him for a minute, before

03:57:50.040 --> 03:57:52.500
she realized she was dripping cerulean

03:57:52.500 --> 03:57:53.760
paint all over her talons.

03:57:53.819 --> 03:57:55.319
Wow.

03:57:55.379 --> 03:57:57.719
Dark stalker whispered in her head.

03:57:57.780 --> 03:58:00.600
I seem to have gotten a lot scarier in

03:58:00.600 --> 03:58:01.620
the last 2000 years.

03:58:01.680 --> 03:58:04.920
You must have been pretty scary to begin

03:58:04.920 --> 03:58:06.600
with, Moon observed.

03:58:06.659 --> 03:58:09.420
If the whole tribe moved to hide from you

03:58:09.420 --> 03:58:10.739
even after you'd been defeated.

03:58:10.799 --> 03:58:13.559
Completely unnecessary.

03:58:13.620 --> 03:58:15.600
A huge overreaction.

03:58:15.659 --> 03:58:18.360
I killed one dragon who deserved it.

03:58:18.420 --> 03:58:20.879
What did he do?

03:58:20.940 --> 03:58:22.979
Moon asked Mighty Claus.

03:58:23.040 --> 03:58:25.260
I mean, what was so bad about him?

03:58:25.319 --> 03:58:28.680
Please keep in mind, I'll be terribly

03:58:28.680 --> 03:58:30.420
offended if you believe this scrawny

03:58:30.420 --> 03:58:32.639
dragonette, and his monster fantasies

03:58:32.639 --> 03:58:32.940
over me.

03:58:33.059 --> 03:58:37.079
He killed like 20 dragons.

03:58:37.139 --> 03:58:40.799
Marty Claus said, all at once, with his

03:58:40.799 --> 03:58:41.520
mind.

03:58:41.579 --> 03:58:44.399
He could make anyone do anything he

03:58:44.399 --> 03:58:44.940
wanted to.

03:58:45.000 --> 03:58:46.620
Is that true?

03:58:46.680 --> 03:58:48.899
Moon demanded, appalled.

03:58:48.959 --> 03:58:52.500
I did not kill 20 dragons.

03:58:52.559 --> 03:58:53.879
Maybe two.

03:58:53.940 --> 03:58:56.579
On 2 separate occasions, and I had to.

03:58:56.639 --> 03:58:58.079
Moon, come on.

03:58:58.139 --> 03:59:00.659
I promise not to eat anyone's brains.

03:59:00.719 --> 03:59:04.139
Mighty Claus was not faking his terror of

03:59:04.139 --> 03:59:05.219
the dark stalker, though.

03:59:05.280 --> 03:59:07.680
A 1000000 nightmares from the last few

03:59:07.680 --> 03:59:10.139
years were replaying in his head.

03:59:10.200 --> 03:59:12.120
She also saw a game where the young

03:59:12.120 --> 03:59:14.159
dragonettes took turns pretending to be

03:59:14.159 --> 03:59:16.559
the dark stalker, hiding for a long time

03:59:16.559 --> 03:59:18.899
then bursting out to chase and attack the

03:59:18.899 --> 03:59:19.079
others.

03:59:19.139 --> 03:59:21.840
Mighty Claus had never liked that game.

03:59:21.899 --> 03:59:23.700
It always made his nightmares worse.

03:59:23.819 --> 03:59:26.639
Does anyone know where he's buried?

03:59:26.760 --> 03:59:29.520
she asked. mighty Claus wrinkled its

03:59:29.520 --> 03:59:30.120
snout at her.

03:59:30.180 --> 03:59:31.799
Of course not.

03:59:31.860 --> 03:59:33.899
That was 1000s of years ago.

03:59:33.959 --> 03:59:37.440
What about the old Nightwing Kingdom?

03:59:37.440 --> 03:59:37.979
she asked.

03:59:38.040 --> 03:59:39.239
Where was it?

03:59:39.299 --> 03:59:41.940
I have no idea, he said.

03:59:42.000 --> 03:59:43.920
What's with all the questions?

03:59:43.979 --> 03:59:46.379
Oh, she said.

03:59:46.440 --> 03:59:48.959
I just, I wondered.

03:59:49.020 --> 03:59:50.520
I mean, you're right.

03:59:50.639 --> 03:59:53.040
I missed out on all the stuff a Nightwing

03:59:53.040 --> 03:59:53.879
Dragonette should know.

03:59:53.940 --> 03:59:58.620
I thought maybe if I knew more, I'd be

03:59:58.620 --> 03:59:59.579
more of a night wing.

03:59:59.579 --> 04:00:02.399
Monte Claus stepped around his easel to

04:00:02.399 --> 04:00:05.219
look at her canvas, she'd painted quite

04:00:05.219 --> 04:00:08.340
badly, an evening sky, twinkling with

04:00:08.340 --> 04:00:10.860
stars and all 3 moons, over a quiet

04:00:10.860 --> 04:00:13.139
rainforest scene of green leaves and

04:00:13.139 --> 04:00:13.920
crooked trees.

04:00:13.979 --> 04:00:17.700
He took one look at it and snorted, then

04:00:17.700 --> 04:00:19.200
grabbed his painting and threw it on the

04:00:19.200 --> 04:00:19.799
floor at her feet.

04:00:19.860 --> 04:00:23.040
It was a painting of the volcano she'd

04:00:23.040 --> 04:00:25.020
seen so many times in the night wing's

04:00:25.020 --> 04:00:25.260
heads.

04:00:25.319 --> 04:00:28.559
Red and gold lavas billed down the sides

04:00:28.559 --> 04:00:31.020
of the black mountain, and a dark cloud

04:00:31.020 --> 04:00:33.299
of smoke hung over everything, so you

04:00:33.299 --> 04:00:34.920
couldn't tell if it was day or night.

04:00:34.979 --> 04:00:37.319
It took her a minute of looking at it to

04:00:37.319 --> 04:00:39.840
realize that Mighty Claus had painted

04:00:39.840 --> 04:00:41.760
hidden eyes and teeth all over the

04:00:41.760 --> 04:00:44.760
volcano, as if it was watching, waiting

04:00:44.760 --> 04:00:46.139
to devour someone.

04:00:46.200 --> 04:00:50.700
That's really moon started. wanting to

04:00:50.700 --> 04:00:51.600
tell him how good it was.

04:00:51.659 --> 04:00:54.719
This, mighty Claus said.

04:00:54.780 --> 04:00:56.879
He pointed to her painting and then to

04:00:56.879 --> 04:00:57.420
his.

04:00:57.420 --> 04:01:00.299
This is why you'll never be one of us.

04:01:00.360 --> 04:01:03.899
Because everything was awful, and you

04:01:03.899 --> 04:01:05.819
escaped, and it is not fair.

04:01:05.879 --> 04:01:08.940
He stormed out of the cave before she

04:01:08.940 --> 04:01:09.600
could respond.

04:01:09.659 --> 04:01:11.219
Moonside.

04:01:11.280 --> 04:01:15.000
What's really not fair, Dark Stalker

04:01:15.000 --> 04:01:17.459
pointed out, is everyone blaming you for

04:01:17.459 --> 04:01:18.600
a choice your mother made?

04:01:18.659 --> 04:01:22.200
Moon picked up the volcano painting and

04:01:22.200 --> 04:01:23.940
propped it carefully back on the easel to

04:01:23.940 --> 04:01:24.540
dry.

04:01:24.600 --> 04:01:26.879
She gazed at it for a moment, then

04:01:26.879 --> 04:01:28.200
suddenly glanced back at her own

04:01:28.200 --> 04:01:28.680
painting.

04:01:28.739 --> 04:01:30.239
The sky.

04:01:30.299 --> 04:01:32.159
Her heart flipped over.

04:01:32.219 --> 04:01:36.299
My egg was laid under 2 full moons. and

04:01:36.299 --> 04:01:37.860
hatched under 2 full moons.

04:01:37.920 --> 04:01:40.319
Her mother had told her the story of the

04:01:40.319 --> 04:01:42.420
moonlight, and the way her egg had turned

04:01:42.420 --> 04:01:43.739
strangely silver.

04:01:43.799 --> 04:01:46.379
Is that why I have powers and no one else

04:01:46.379 --> 04:01:46.680
does?

04:01:46.739 --> 04:01:49.319
Did the Nightwing powers come from the

04:01:49.319 --> 04:01:49.739
moons?

04:01:49.799 --> 04:01:52.920
Maybe that's why they disappeared, because

04:01:52.920 --> 04:01:54.719
there was no moonlight on the volcanic

04:01:54.719 --> 04:01:56.940
island, and the eggs were all hatched

04:01:56.940 --> 04:01:58.139
deep inside the caves.

04:01:58.200 --> 04:02:01.379
Dark Stalker rumbled inside her head.

04:02:01.440 --> 04:02:04.260
Of course, our powers come from the

04:02:04.260 --> 04:02:04.680
moons.

04:02:04.739 --> 04:02:07.559
One full moon attaching gives the

04:02:07.559 --> 04:02:09.000
dragonette either mind reading or

04:02:09.000 --> 04:02:09.540
prophecy.

04:02:09.600 --> 04:02:11.100
Two gives them both.

04:02:11.159 --> 04:02:13.860
Three is so rare.

04:02:13.920 --> 04:02:17.280
The theory, for a while, was that perhaps

04:02:17.280 --> 04:02:19.739
the animus powers were a 3rd gift.

04:02:19.799 --> 04:02:22.379
But we eventually determined that those

04:02:22.379 --> 04:02:24.479
are genetic, not moon given.

04:02:24.540 --> 04:02:27.840
We think the 3rd moon makes the 1st 2

04:02:27.840 --> 04:02:29.100
powers even stronger.

04:02:29.219 --> 04:02:32.340
Moon brushed the silver scales by our

04:02:32.340 --> 04:02:32.639
eyes.

04:02:32.700 --> 04:02:35.159
Are these a sign of our powers?

04:02:35.159 --> 04:02:37.500
Because fate speaker has them too.

04:02:37.559 --> 04:02:39.180
They should be.

04:02:39.239 --> 04:02:41.700
But I've seen absolutely everything in

04:02:41.700 --> 04:02:43.799
that silly dragon's mind, and she's

04:02:43.799 --> 04:02:44.760
certainly not a mind reader.

04:02:44.879 --> 04:02:47.819
Nor a prophet, I believe, although she

04:02:47.819 --> 04:02:49.319
may have a very weak power.

04:02:49.379 --> 04:02:52.739
Perhaps she nearly hatched under the

04:02:52.739 --> 04:02:54.719
moons, or while supposed to.

04:02:54.780 --> 04:02:58.559
The talons of peace had her egg, so she

04:02:58.559 --> 04:03:00.719
wasn't on the volcano, but she probably

04:03:00.719 --> 04:03:02.219
wasn't out in the moonlight either.

04:03:02.280 --> 04:03:04.979
Moon thought, and they also had

04:03:04.979 --> 04:03:07.500
starflights, but I know for sure he

04:03:07.500 --> 04:03:08.520
hatched underground.

04:03:08.579 --> 04:03:13.020
Yes, on a brightest night, with three

04:03:13.020 --> 04:03:14.100
full moons.

04:03:14.159 --> 04:03:16.200
Dog stalker growled.

04:03:16.260 --> 04:03:17.579
What a waste.

04:03:17.639 --> 04:03:19.680
Think of the power he could have had.

04:03:19.739 --> 04:03:21.059
He paused.

04:03:21.120 --> 04:03:24.299
But the connection between Moonlight and

04:03:24.299 --> 04:03:26.280
Nightwing Powers was common knowledge in

04:03:26.280 --> 04:03:26.700
the tribe.

04:03:26.760 --> 04:03:28.860
How could everyone have forgotten that

04:03:28.860 --> 04:03:31.260
even in 2000 years?

04:03:31.319 --> 04:03:33.780
Why would the tribe risk losing all our

04:03:33.780 --> 04:03:36.479
powers by hatching their dragonettes away

04:03:36.479 --> 04:03:37.079
from the moonlight?

04:03:37.200 --> 04:03:40.200
I have a guess, Moon whispered.

04:03:40.260 --> 04:03:41.280
What?

04:03:41.399 --> 04:03:44.040
She put her own painting down in a clear

04:03:44.040 --> 04:03:45.000
space on the floor.

04:03:45.059 --> 04:03:48.299
The blues and greens were too bright, all

04:03:48.299 --> 04:03:50.760
the lines too unsure, and the trees

04:03:50.760 --> 04:03:52.440
looked like blobby mushrooms.

04:03:52.500 --> 04:03:54.299
She set it on fire.

04:03:54.360 --> 04:03:57.719
I think, it was because of you.

04:03:57.780 --> 04:04:00.299
She watched the flames for a long

04:04:00.299 --> 04:04:00.600
moment.

04:04:00.659 --> 04:04:03.299
The other night wings were so afraid of

04:04:03.299 --> 04:04:05.159
your powers, and what you did with them.

04:04:05.219 --> 04:04:08.100
Whatever the truth is, whatever you did

04:04:08.100 --> 04:04:10.200
that they stopped having their eggs in

04:04:10.200 --> 04:04:10.680
the moonlight.

04:04:10.739 --> 04:04:13.319
They gave up the night wing powers on

04:04:13.319 --> 04:04:15.420
purpose, because they wanted to be sure

04:04:15.420 --> 04:04:17.040
there would never be another dark

04:04:17.040 --> 04:04:17.700
stalker.

04:04:17.760 --> 04:04:19.139
Another you.

04:04:19.260 --> 04:04:21.360
He was silent.

04:04:21.420 --> 04:04:24.600
Moon wrapped her wings around herself, and

04:04:24.600 --> 04:04:26.280
watched her painting burn to ashes.

04:04:26.340 --> 04:04:30.600
Chapter 12.

04:04:30.959 --> 04:04:33.719
I can't set you free.

04:04:33.840 --> 04:04:36.600
Moon whispered to the wall that night

04:04:36.600 --> 04:04:38.399
after Kinkachu and Carnelian were

04:04:38.399 --> 04:04:38.760
asleep.

04:04:38.819 --> 04:04:42.180
Do I really seem evil to you, Moon?

04:04:42.299 --> 04:04:45.899
She buried her nose in a pile of moss, but

04:04:45.899 --> 04:04:47.100
she knew she couldn't hide the answer

04:04:47.100 --> 04:04:48.059
from him.

04:04:48.120 --> 04:04:48.899
No.

04:04:48.959 --> 04:04:51.719
We don't know what really happened back

04:04:51.719 --> 04:04:52.020
then.

04:04:52.079 --> 04:04:54.719
After Clearsight and Fathom tricked me.

04:04:54.780 --> 04:04:58.379
We can be sure the tribe ran and hid, and

04:04:58.379 --> 04:04:59.819
gave up their powers because of me.

04:04:59.879 --> 04:05:03.719
I mean, nothing I did was awful enough

04:05:03.719 --> 04:05:04.020
for that.

04:05:04.139 --> 04:05:07.739
Moon rolled onto her back, and gazed up

04:05:07.739 --> 04:05:08.219
at the ceiling.

04:05:08.280 --> 04:05:10.799
What about the things they knew you might

04:05:10.799 --> 04:05:12.239
do in the future?

04:05:12.299 --> 04:05:15.659
A rumble in her head, like flames

04:05:15.659 --> 04:05:16.200
building.

04:05:16.260 --> 04:05:17.459
Is it fair?

04:05:17.520 --> 04:05:20.579
To judge me for possibly dreadful deeds, I

04:05:20.579 --> 04:05:21.059
never even did.

04:05:21.120 --> 04:05:24.780
We all might do terrible things.

04:05:24.840 --> 04:05:27.420
Your friend Turtle might kill his

04:05:27.420 --> 04:05:27.719
sister.

04:05:27.780 --> 04:05:31.799
This sky wing in your cave might smother

04:05:31.799 --> 04:05:34.200
Kinkachu in her sleep, just to shut her

04:05:34.200 --> 04:05:34.379
up.

04:05:34.440 --> 04:05:37.559
The ice wings might conspire to murder

04:05:37.559 --> 04:05:38.100
peril.

04:05:38.159 --> 04:05:41.459
Or you might let a killer escape, or you

04:05:41.459 --> 04:05:43.559
might send a friend to certain death.

04:05:43.620 --> 04:05:45.780
What are you talking about?

04:05:45.840 --> 04:05:47.040
Moon asked.

04:05:47.100 --> 04:05:48.600
Do you know what's going to happen?

04:05:48.659 --> 04:05:50.399
Have you had visions of all those

04:05:50.399 --> 04:05:50.700
things?

04:05:50.760 --> 04:05:52.079
She sat up.

04:05:52.200 --> 04:05:54.420
Do you already know if I'm going to free

04:05:54.420 --> 04:05:54.959
you or not?

04:05:55.020 --> 04:05:56.639
He sighed.

04:05:56.700 --> 04:05:58.739
Moon, I told you.

04:05:58.799 --> 04:06:01.440
With a prophecy gift is advanced as

04:06:01.440 --> 04:06:01.680
mine.

04:06:01.739 --> 04:06:03.719
I can see all the possibilities.

04:06:03.780 --> 04:06:06.299
I see futures where you free me.

04:06:06.360 --> 04:06:09.059
And futures where I live like this

04:06:09.059 --> 04:06:13.979
trapped in the dark, alone, for 1000s

04:06:13.979 --> 04:06:14.459
more years.

04:06:14.520 --> 04:06:17.760
All your choices spiral off into

04:06:17.760 --> 04:06:18.479
different futures.

04:06:18.540 --> 04:06:22.139
The visions you've had are only brief

04:06:22.139 --> 04:06:24.360
glimpses of the most likely outcomes.

04:06:24.420 --> 04:06:27.719
You see them about as clearly, as you'd

04:06:27.719 --> 04:06:30.000
see a dark cave with one burst of flame

04:06:30.000 --> 04:06:32.159
and they could still all change.

04:06:32.219 --> 04:06:35.639
So you could manipulate me into freeing

04:06:35.639 --> 04:06:36.899
you, Moon pointed out.

04:06:36.959 --> 04:06:39.479
You can see exactly what you need to say

04:06:39.479 --> 04:06:40.680
to make me say yes.

04:06:40.739 --> 04:06:42.780
A long pause.

04:06:42.780 --> 04:06:45.239
That's not fair, Moon.

04:06:45.360 --> 04:06:47.219
What can I say to that?

04:06:47.280 --> 04:06:50.040
Anything will sound like a trick to you?

04:06:50.100 --> 04:06:53.280
But it's not manipulating you if I tell

04:06:53.280 --> 04:06:54.959
you that what I'm going through now is

04:06:54.959 --> 04:06:55.440
torture.

04:06:55.500 --> 04:06:57.540
That's just the truth.

04:06:57.659 --> 04:07:00.360
This is not what a tribe planned for me.

04:07:00.420 --> 04:07:03.059
Clear sight would not have wanted this.

04:07:03.120 --> 04:07:05.579
How can I not tell you these things?

04:07:05.639 --> 04:07:07.260
If they might convince you.

04:07:07.319 --> 04:07:12.059
However, he went on, I cannot make you do

04:07:12.059 --> 04:07:12.420
anything.

04:07:12.479 --> 04:07:14.639
You make your own choices.

04:07:14.700 --> 04:07:18.420
That, unfortunately, is the essential

04:07:18.420 --> 04:07:19.620
problem with prophecy.

04:07:19.680 --> 04:07:22.260
Every dragon has the power to choose

04:07:22.260 --> 04:07:23.159
their own future.

04:07:23.219 --> 04:07:26.340
He let out a low, sad chuckle.

04:07:26.459 --> 04:07:30.420
Except me, of course, ironically.

04:07:30.479 --> 04:07:32.760
You're going to haunt me for the rest of

04:07:32.760 --> 04:07:35.819
my life, if I don't free you, aren't

04:07:35.819 --> 04:07:36.000
you?

04:07:36.059 --> 04:07:37.319
Moon asked.

04:07:37.379 --> 04:07:38.879
He chuckled again.

04:07:38.940 --> 04:07:41.700
I'd argue that this is not so much

04:07:41.700 --> 04:07:44.280
haunting, as it is clinging desperately

04:07:44.280 --> 04:07:46.020
to my only conversational companion.

04:07:46.139 --> 04:07:50.040
At last, Moon fell asleep, straight into

04:07:50.040 --> 04:07:51.719
another night of dreams about the Jade

04:07:51.719 --> 04:07:54.000
Mountain Academy, collapsing around her

04:07:54.000 --> 04:07:54.659
and her friends.

04:07:54.780 --> 04:07:58.620
Now, Dark Stalker's face from the scroll

04:07:58.620 --> 04:08:00.420
loomed over the whole nightmare.

04:08:00.479 --> 04:08:01.559
A warning?

04:08:01.620 --> 04:08:02.879
A promise.

04:08:02.940 --> 04:08:05.700
Was the fall of Jade Mountain something

04:08:05.700 --> 04:08:07.559
that would happen if she freed Dark

04:08:07.559 --> 04:08:09.600
Stalker, or something that would happen

04:08:09.600 --> 04:08:10.379
if she didn't?

04:08:10.440 --> 04:08:14.879
The next afternoon, the Jade Winglet met

04:08:14.879 --> 04:08:17.219
in the music cave with Anemones group, the

04:08:17.219 --> 04:08:18.059
Silver Winglet.

04:08:18.120 --> 04:08:20.399
Moon could hear the deep warbling sound

04:08:20.399 --> 04:08:22.260
of Didgeradoos as she climbed up the

04:08:22.260 --> 04:08:23.579
tunnels behind Kinkajoo.

04:08:23.700 --> 04:08:25.979
The sound seemed to swallow her up

04:08:25.979 --> 04:08:28.739
reverberating in her bones, and then the

04:08:28.739 --> 04:08:31.139
dragonettes emerged into a vast cave full

04:08:31.139 --> 04:08:31.680
of echoes.

04:08:31.739 --> 04:08:34.620
It was like being inside a singing bowl.

04:08:34.680 --> 04:08:37.139
The music catapulted around the high

04:08:37.139 --> 04:08:40.200
smooth walls, like thread winding around

04:08:40.200 --> 04:08:42.540
and around the assembled dragons.

04:08:42.659 --> 04:08:46.260
Moon recognized Anemone's claw mate, the

04:08:46.260 --> 04:08:48.360
little sandwing named Ostrich, as one of

04:08:48.360 --> 04:08:48.780
the players.

04:08:48.840 --> 04:08:51.659
She held a wing shaped harp and was

04:08:51.659 --> 04:08:53.399
plucking the strings with her claws.

04:08:53.399 --> 04:08:55.739
Beside her, Umber was trying to keep up

04:08:55.739 --> 04:08:58.319
on a hollow stringed instrument, as tall

04:08:58.319 --> 04:09:01.139
as a dragon that boomed in a deep bass

04:09:01.139 --> 04:09:01.739
register.

04:09:01.799 --> 04:09:03.239
Let's join in.

04:09:03.299 --> 04:09:06.059
Kinkachu cried happily. shouting over the

04:09:06.059 --> 04:09:06.239
music.

04:09:06.299 --> 04:09:09.180
She seized a pair of gourds that rattled

04:09:09.180 --> 04:09:11.280
as though they were full of dry seeds, and

04:09:11.280 --> 04:09:13.020
she tossed moon a wooden box.

04:09:13.079 --> 04:09:16.379
The box was square, as long as Moon's

04:09:16.379 --> 04:09:18.239
forearm, and looked like it had several

04:09:18.239 --> 04:09:20.340
metal tongues of different sizes attached

04:09:20.340 --> 04:09:21.000
to the top of it.

04:09:21.059 --> 04:09:23.940
A label carved into the side, said it was

04:09:23.940 --> 04:09:24.899
an Ambira.

04:09:25.020 --> 04:09:27.059
When she plucked one of the tongues with

04:09:27.059 --> 04:09:29.579
her claw, a reverberating twangy noise

04:09:29.579 --> 04:09:31.559
came out, and it turned out to be a

04:09:31.559 --> 04:09:32.700
slightly different noise for each

04:09:32.700 --> 04:09:33.120
tongue.

04:09:33.180 --> 04:09:37.079
She sends to winter arriving, wrapped in

04:09:37.079 --> 04:09:37.920
chili discomfort.

04:09:37.979 --> 04:09:40.979
Moon couldn't imagine him or Cornelian

04:09:40.979 --> 04:09:41.700
ever making music.

04:09:41.760 --> 04:09:44.159
Almost at the same time as she had that

04:09:44.159 --> 04:09:46.379
thought, she caught Kinkachood thinking

04:09:46.379 --> 04:09:47.579
the same thing about her.

04:09:47.639 --> 04:09:50.340
Moon, too shy to make music.

04:09:50.399 --> 04:09:52.200
Sad, she's missing out.

04:09:52.260 --> 04:09:55.319
The reception was blurry in here, with

04:09:55.319 --> 04:09:57.239
all the noise happening, and everyone's

04:09:57.239 --> 04:09:58.260
thoughts were fragmented.

04:09:58.319 --> 04:10:01.200
Still, moon caught enough to understand

04:10:01.200 --> 04:10:03.420
the gist of it, and she focused her

04:10:03.420 --> 04:10:05.520
attention back on the Ambira, trying to

04:10:05.520 --> 04:10:07.739
feel determined and stubborn instead of

04:10:07.739 --> 04:10:08.760
downcast and small.

04:10:08.819 --> 04:10:12.540
Soon after that, Kibli came bounding into

04:10:12.540 --> 04:10:14.700
the cave and straight over to the drums

04:10:14.700 --> 04:10:17.040
where he ousted a bewildered looking sky

04:10:17.040 --> 04:10:17.579
wing.

04:10:17.579 --> 04:10:20.700
As he began to play, Moon managed to stop

04:10:20.700 --> 04:10:22.620
thinking about Dark Stalker for the 1st

04:10:22.620 --> 04:10:23.219
time all day.

04:10:23.280 --> 04:10:26.520
Kibli drummed with his whole body, like

04:10:26.520 --> 04:10:28.200
he was dancing and drumming at the same

04:10:28.200 --> 04:10:28.379
time.

04:10:28.440 --> 04:10:31.319
His tail thumped a rhythm on a huge bass

04:10:31.319 --> 04:10:33.899
drum behind him, while his front talons

04:10:33.899 --> 04:10:36.120
jumped and skipped and bumped from one

04:10:36.120 --> 04:10:37.500
small drum to another.

04:10:37.559 --> 04:10:39.719
Anemone grabbed turtle and started

04:10:39.719 --> 04:10:43.020
dancing, and after a moment, Kinkachu, the

04:10:43.020 --> 04:10:44.940
other rain wing, and the other mud wing

04:10:44.940 --> 04:10:45.420
joined in.

04:10:45.479 --> 04:10:48.479
The rain wings whirled together, their

04:10:48.479 --> 04:10:50.700
scales shimmering from color to color in

04:10:50.700 --> 04:10:51.299
time with the music.

04:10:51.420 --> 04:10:54.299
Moon wished she were brave enough to

04:10:54.299 --> 04:10:56.940
dance, or to drum along with Kibley.

04:10:57.000 --> 04:10:58.319
Maybe one day.

04:10:58.379 --> 04:11:01.680
Across the cave, he grinned at her, and

04:11:01.680 --> 04:11:03.540
in his mind, she saw an entire drum

04:11:03.540 --> 04:11:06.299
circle of sand wings around an oasis pool

04:11:06.299 --> 04:11:08.340
firelight flickering behind them.

04:11:08.399 --> 04:11:11.579
No sign of his family there, only trusted

04:11:11.579 --> 04:11:13.799
friends, and a leader who danced along

04:11:13.799 --> 04:11:14.159
with them.

04:11:14.219 --> 04:11:17.879
Out claws, thorn, safety.

04:11:17.940 --> 04:11:20.639
The scene melted back into the thundering

04:11:20.639 --> 04:11:21.120
rhythms.

04:11:21.180 --> 04:11:23.879
It was even better than the raindrop

04:11:23.879 --> 04:11:24.239
trick.

04:11:24.299 --> 04:11:27.000
Here, with the drums echoing off all the

04:11:27.000 --> 04:11:29.040
walls and swallowing individual

04:11:29.040 --> 04:11:29.459
thoughts.

04:11:29.520 --> 04:11:32.100
Moon felt like her head was clear, and

04:11:32.100 --> 04:11:33.239
she didn't have to worry about anything.

04:11:33.299 --> 04:11:35.700
It seemed to work for Kibley, too.

04:11:35.760 --> 04:11:38.459
For once, his mind was moving at about

04:11:38.459 --> 04:11:40.200
the normal speed of other dragons

04:11:40.200 --> 04:11:42.239
absorbed in the pounding below his

04:11:42.239 --> 04:11:42.840
talons.

04:11:42.899 --> 04:11:45.659
Afterward, to Moon's surprise.

04:11:45.719 --> 04:11:47.520
Winter caught up with her on her way to

04:11:47.520 --> 04:11:48.000
the library.

04:11:48.059 --> 04:11:52.020
I want you to look at my scavenger, he

04:11:52.020 --> 04:11:52.799
said brusquely.

04:11:52.860 --> 04:11:54.719
Don't make eye contact.

04:11:54.840 --> 04:11:56.879
He was shouting at himself inside his

04:11:56.879 --> 04:11:57.180
head.

04:11:57.239 --> 04:11:58.739
Don't think about her.

04:11:58.799 --> 04:12:01.139
You're a disgrace to the royal ice wing

04:12:01.139 --> 04:12:01.979
lineage, Winter.

04:12:02.040 --> 04:12:03.600
Your brother would never have been so

04:12:03.600 --> 04:12:03.959
weak.

04:12:04.020 --> 04:12:07.079
Oh, she faltered.

04:12:07.139 --> 04:12:10.559
I, I mean, sure, but I don't really know

04:12:10.559 --> 04:12:11.219
anything about them.

04:12:11.280 --> 04:12:15.299
Then use your intuition or whatever, he

04:12:15.299 --> 04:12:15.600
said.

04:12:15.659 --> 04:12:17.760
Or whatever.

04:12:17.819 --> 04:12:21.659
His mind echoed ominously, Moon didn't

04:12:21.659 --> 04:12:22.200
like the sound of that.

04:12:22.260 --> 04:12:26.459
I was just, um, going to the library, she

04:12:26.459 --> 04:12:29.520
said, preparing to add, so maybe later.

04:12:29.579 --> 04:12:31.379
But he started talking over her.

04:12:31.440 --> 04:12:32.760
Fun.

04:12:32.819 --> 04:12:33.479
I'll bring him there.

04:12:33.540 --> 04:12:35.819
He whisked away before she could

04:12:35.819 --> 04:12:36.540
protest.

04:12:36.600 --> 04:12:40.500
Ooh, Kinkachu said, pouncing on Moon's

04:12:40.500 --> 04:12:41.040
tail from behind her.

04:12:41.100 --> 04:12:42.239
What did he want?

04:12:42.299 --> 04:12:43.079
What did he say?

04:12:43.139 --> 04:12:45.000
Can you believe he initiated a

04:12:45.000 --> 04:12:47.040
conversation and aren't you so excited?

04:12:47.100 --> 04:12:49.920
It was nothing, Moon said.

04:12:49.979 --> 04:12:51.540
Oh, Moon.

04:12:51.600 --> 04:12:53.459
Sometimes it's like talking to a tree.

04:12:53.520 --> 04:12:55.920
Kinkaju's mind sighed.

04:12:55.979 --> 04:12:59.700
Um, Moon said quickly, just he's bringing

04:12:59.700 --> 04:13:01.319
Bandit to the library for me to look at.

04:13:01.379 --> 04:13:04.559
Oh, wow, Kinkachu said.

04:13:04.620 --> 04:13:07.260
He must like you to be asking for your

04:13:07.260 --> 04:13:07.559
help, right?

04:13:07.620 --> 04:13:10.799
Moon searched Kinkaju's face and thoughts

04:13:10.860 --> 04:13:13.079
but found no jealousy under those words.

04:13:13.139 --> 04:13:15.840
Kinkachu seemed as delighted by the

04:13:15.840 --> 04:13:18.299
prospect of witnessing a romance as she

04:13:18.299 --> 04:13:19.620
was by the idea of being in one.

04:13:19.739 --> 04:13:21.899
It was all part of the thrilling new

04:13:21.899 --> 04:13:22.979
drama of school to her.

04:13:23.040 --> 04:13:26.879
Well, no, I am pretty sure he hates me

04:13:26.879 --> 04:13:28.139
Moon pointed out.

04:13:28.260 --> 04:13:31.379
It was odd because she thought she, of

04:13:31.379 --> 04:13:33.479
all dragons, should be able to be sure

04:13:33.479 --> 04:13:35.340
about how another dragon felt about her.

04:13:35.399 --> 04:13:38.219
But being able to read Winter's mind

04:13:38.219 --> 04:13:39.659
somehow didn't make him any less

04:13:39.659 --> 04:13:40.200
confusing.

04:13:40.260 --> 04:13:42.719
It almost seemed to make things worse

04:13:42.719 --> 04:13:45.360
actually, as if she were trapped in a

04:13:45.360 --> 04:13:46.559
maze of icy mirrors.

04:13:46.620 --> 04:13:48.959
She wondered if that was how he felt all

04:13:48.959 --> 04:13:49.500
the time.

04:13:49.559 --> 04:13:52.319
Sonny and Fate speaker were in the

04:13:52.319 --> 04:13:53.700
library with Starflight.

04:13:53.819 --> 04:13:55.920
Fate speaker was reading to him, and

04:13:55.920 --> 04:13:57.780
Sonny was sorting a new bundle of scrolls

04:13:57.780 --> 04:13:58.680
into neat piles.

04:13:58.739 --> 04:14:00.299
Hi there.

04:14:00.420 --> 04:14:02.040
Sonny greeted them warmly.

04:14:02.100 --> 04:14:05.100
We have some free time before history, and

04:14:05.100 --> 04:14:06.659
Moon said she'd help me practice my

04:14:06.659 --> 04:14:09.420
reading, Kinkachu said, turning her

04:14:09.420 --> 04:14:11.459
scales, the color of old scrolls with

04:14:11.459 --> 04:14:12.540
black speckles.

04:14:12.600 --> 04:14:15.479
That sounds great, Starflight said.

04:14:15.540 --> 04:14:17.520
Did I hear carnelian with you?

04:14:17.579 --> 04:14:18.840
Yes.

04:14:18.899 --> 04:14:21.540
Carnelian muttered behind Moon, making

04:14:21.540 --> 04:14:22.020
her jump.

04:14:22.079 --> 04:14:24.780
She hadn't realized the Sky Wing was

04:14:24.780 --> 04:14:27.239
there, which meant the raindrop trick was

04:14:27.239 --> 04:14:27.899
really working.

04:14:27.959 --> 04:14:30.659
Is there any news from Queen Ruby?

04:14:30.719 --> 04:14:33.719
Maybe calling me home, or at least

04:14:33.719 --> 04:14:35.579
sending me new battle formations to

04:14:35.579 --> 04:14:35.760
learn?

04:14:35.819 --> 04:14:38.579
You got a letter this morning?

04:14:38.639 --> 04:14:40.920
Fate speaker said, producing a small

04:14:40.920 --> 04:14:42.120
scroll from under the desk.

04:14:42.239 --> 04:14:45.299
She handed it to Carnelian, who inspected

04:14:45.299 --> 04:14:47.639
the seals suspiciously, and then retired

04:14:47.639 --> 04:14:49.139
to the darkest corner to read it.

04:14:49.200 --> 04:14:52.139
Kinkadoo had just chosen a scroll called

04:14:52.139 --> 04:14:55.020
Journeys in the Ice Kingdom, when winter

04:14:55.020 --> 04:14:57.420
came hurrying in, carrying a covered

04:14:57.420 --> 04:14:57.780
cage.

04:14:57.840 --> 04:15:00.000
He set it down in front of Moon and

04:15:00.000 --> 04:15:01.139
whisked the cloth off.

04:15:01.200 --> 04:15:04.680
She crouched to peer inside, trying to

04:15:04.680 --> 04:15:06.899
ignore how furious and resentful he felt

04:15:06.899 --> 04:15:07.860
about asking for help.

04:15:07.920 --> 04:15:10.440
The cage looked a bit like a tall bird

04:15:10.440 --> 04:15:12.540
cage, but with an elaborate little

04:15:12.540 --> 04:15:14.340
environment constructed inside of it.

04:15:14.399 --> 04:15:16.739
There were stairs, a kind of running

04:15:16.739 --> 04:15:19.319
wheel on the lower level, a nest with

04:15:19.319 --> 04:15:21.239
tiny blankets piled on it on the upper

04:15:21.239 --> 04:15:23.520
level, and a swing hanging from the top

04:15:23.520 --> 04:15:24.360
bars of the cage.

04:15:24.420 --> 04:15:27.659
It took Moon a moment to spot Bandit

04:15:27.659 --> 04:15:29.520
because he was buried in the heap of

04:15:29.520 --> 04:15:31.739
blankets on the nest, but as the light

04:15:31.739 --> 04:15:34.319
filled the cage, a furry head slowly

04:15:34.319 --> 04:15:36.360
emerged, and then the rest of him

04:15:36.360 --> 04:15:38.520
emitting little groans and rubbing his

04:15:38.520 --> 04:15:38.819
arms.

04:15:38.879 --> 04:15:43.440
Aw, he's so cute, Kinkachu said.

04:15:43.500 --> 04:15:44.760
Winter snorted.

04:15:44.819 --> 04:15:46.739
Did you build all this?

04:15:46.799 --> 04:15:49.680
Moon asked, touching the cage lightly

04:15:49.680 --> 04:15:50.459
with one claw.

04:15:50.579 --> 04:15:52.379
It was very detailed.

04:15:52.440 --> 04:15:54.239
It must have taken a long time and a lot

04:15:54.239 --> 04:15:54.600
of thought.

04:15:54.659 --> 04:15:56.100
He nodded.

04:15:56.219 --> 04:15:57.780
All the stuff inside.

04:15:57.840 --> 04:16:00.479
I thought he'd like it, but he's hardly

04:16:00.479 --> 04:16:01.079
used any of it.

04:16:01.139 --> 04:16:03.840
He won't climb on the swing, or use the

04:16:03.840 --> 04:16:04.319
running wheel.

04:16:04.379 --> 04:16:06.959
Mostly he eats, and then goes back to

04:16:06.959 --> 04:16:07.319
sleep.

04:16:07.379 --> 04:16:09.840
I thought scavengers were curious and

04:16:09.840 --> 04:16:12.479
unpredictable, but he's been unbelievably

04:16:12.479 --> 04:16:12.840
boring.

04:16:12.959 --> 04:16:15.840
The ice wing gave her a sideways look.

04:16:15.899 --> 04:16:17.520
Any suggestions?

04:16:17.579 --> 04:16:18.600
Is he sick?

04:16:18.719 --> 04:16:20.760
I've been feeding him fruit, so he's

04:16:20.760 --> 04:16:21.180
eating fine.

04:16:21.239 --> 04:16:23.280
Why won't he do anything?

04:16:23.340 --> 04:16:26.040
What can I say without making him

04:16:26.040 --> 04:16:26.940
suspicious?

04:16:27.000 --> 04:16:29.459
Moon extended one claw through the bars

04:16:29.459 --> 04:16:30.059
of the cage.

04:16:30.120 --> 04:16:33.180
The scavenger jumped back, then looked up

04:16:33.180 --> 04:16:34.680
and seemed to recognize her.

04:16:34.739 --> 04:16:37.620
Tentatively, Bandit stepped forward and

04:16:37.620 --> 04:16:39.540
put one paw on Moon's talon.

04:16:39.600 --> 04:16:42.360
Again, she could sense, feelings without

04:16:42.360 --> 04:16:45.659
words, but strong, complicated feelings

04:16:45.659 --> 04:16:47.700
she could feel that he was still afraid

04:16:47.700 --> 04:16:50.639
but now there was mostly sadness, huge

04:16:50.639 --> 04:16:51.899
enough to engulf Moon.

04:16:52.020 --> 04:16:54.780
She felt a sudden immense longing for her

04:16:54.780 --> 04:16:54.959
mother.

04:16:55.079 --> 04:16:59.459
Maybe, she started, then hesitated.

04:16:59.579 --> 04:17:01.500
She didn't like the feeling that winter

04:17:01.500 --> 04:17:03.479
was testing her, but she wanted to help

04:17:03.479 --> 04:17:04.379
the little scavenger.

04:17:04.500 --> 04:17:08.100
Maybe he's depressed, Sonny interjected

04:17:08.100 --> 04:17:09.780
coming over to peek inside.

04:17:09.840 --> 04:17:12.479
Webbs was like that for a while after the

04:17:12.479 --> 04:17:13.559
summer palace attack.

04:17:13.620 --> 04:17:15.180
He didn't get out of bed for months.

04:17:15.239 --> 04:17:19.739
Oh, poor little bandit, Kinkaju said.

04:17:19.860 --> 04:17:23.879
Webbs is a dragon, Winter pointed out.

04:17:24.000 --> 04:17:25.440
This is a scavenger.

04:17:25.500 --> 04:17:27.600
Next you'll be telling me the cows and

04:17:27.600 --> 04:17:29.159
fish in the prey center are moping.

04:17:29.280 --> 04:17:32.700
Actually, my theory is that scavengers

04:17:32.700 --> 04:17:34.379
are a lot more complicated than we think

04:17:34.379 --> 04:17:35.700
Sunny said.

04:17:35.700 --> 04:17:38.819
He could be lonely, Moon said.

04:17:38.879 --> 04:17:41.100
She blinked at Bandit and withdrew her

04:17:41.100 --> 04:17:41.520
claw.

04:17:41.579 --> 04:17:44.040
He sat back down on the blankets, his

04:17:44.040 --> 04:17:45.120
shoulders slumped.

04:17:45.180 --> 04:17:47.579
That's true, Sonny said.

04:17:47.639 --> 04:17:50.700
Scavengers usually live in packs, although

04:17:50.700 --> 04:17:52.500
I met one who was happy with just the

04:17:52.500 --> 04:17:54.899
company of dragons for a long time, but

04:17:54.899 --> 04:17:56.100
flour was kind of special.

04:17:56.159 --> 04:17:58.500
Bandit might be special.

04:17:58.559 --> 04:18:00.000
Winter Hoffed.

04:18:00.059 --> 04:18:02.100
He might be delicious.

04:18:02.159 --> 04:18:04.260
Carnelian muttered from her corner.

04:18:04.319 --> 04:18:06.840
She was grumpier than ever, because the

04:18:06.840 --> 04:18:08.340
letter had rejected her official request

04:18:08.340 --> 04:18:09.959
to be sent back to battle training.

04:18:10.020 --> 04:18:12.659
I can think of one good way to find out.

04:18:12.719 --> 04:18:15.059
Winter hissed at her.

04:18:15.120 --> 04:18:16.920
He turned to Moon and growled.

04:18:16.979 --> 04:18:18.239
So what?

04:18:18.299 --> 04:18:20.879
Should I get another scavenger just to

04:18:20.879 --> 04:18:21.540
keep this one happy?

04:18:21.600 --> 04:18:23.639
What if that one is depressed too?

04:18:23.700 --> 04:18:27.479
Or you could make friends with it, Moon

04:18:27.479 --> 04:18:30.360
suggested, and stopped, startled by her

04:18:30.360 --> 04:18:30.959
own boldness.

04:18:31.079 --> 04:18:33.239
He folded his wings back and drew his

04:18:33.239 --> 04:18:33.659
head up.

04:18:33.719 --> 04:18:34.620
What?

04:18:34.680 --> 04:18:37.979
Flower and smolder seem to really like

04:18:37.979 --> 04:18:39.479
each other, Sonny said.

04:18:39.540 --> 04:18:41.940
How am I supposed to do that?

04:18:42.059 --> 04:18:43.260
Winter demanded.

04:18:43.319 --> 04:18:45.420
He flung the cover back on the cage.

04:18:45.479 --> 04:18:49.500
This is useless, he growled, and stormed

04:18:49.500 --> 04:18:50.700
back out of the library with it.

04:18:50.760 --> 04:18:52.860
Sonny shrugged at Moon.

04:18:52.920 --> 04:18:54.180
Don't feel bad.

04:18:54.239 --> 04:18:55.920
He's just worried about Bandit.

04:18:55.979 --> 04:18:57.420
I thought it was a good idea.

04:18:57.479 --> 04:19:00.479
She moved back to her pile of scrolls.

04:19:00.540 --> 04:19:03.239
Moon curled her tail and wings in.

04:19:03.299 --> 04:19:04.500
It was true.

04:19:04.620 --> 04:19:07.440
Winter was worried about Bandit, but he

04:19:07.440 --> 04:19:09.659
was also mad at her in a kind of general

04:19:09.659 --> 04:19:12.180
ongoing way, with no particular reason

04:19:12.180 --> 04:19:12.659
behind it.

04:19:12.719 --> 04:19:14.819
Kinkaju nudged her shoulder.

04:19:14.879 --> 04:19:16.379
Ignore him.

04:19:16.440 --> 04:19:18.120
He clearly doesn't like hearing good

04:19:18.120 --> 04:19:18.479
advice.

04:19:18.540 --> 04:19:21.180
Let's read about ice wings instead, and

04:19:21.180 --> 04:19:22.440
see if they're all that full of

04:19:22.440 --> 04:19:22.979
themselves.

04:19:23.040 --> 04:19:25.979
She started unrolling the scroll on one

04:19:25.979 --> 04:19:27.299
of the low wooden tables.

04:19:27.420 --> 04:19:30.000
Glory once told me that ice wings and

04:19:30.000 --> 04:19:32.159
night wings have always hated each other

04:19:32.159 --> 04:19:34.680
and it goes back to some big tragedy in

04:19:34.680 --> 04:19:37.020
the ice wings past, but she didn't know

04:19:37.020 --> 04:19:37.379
what it was.

04:19:37.440 --> 04:19:39.840
The scrolls she read were mostly written

04:19:39.840 --> 04:19:42.239
by Nightwings or Seawings, and never

04:19:42.239 --> 04:19:43.079
talked about the details.

04:19:43.139 --> 04:19:45.180
I'm so curious, aren't you?

04:19:45.239 --> 04:19:47.940
Did you try asking Starflight?

04:19:48.000 --> 04:19:48.719
Moon asked.

04:19:48.840 --> 04:19:51.780
Yes, but he didn't know either, Kinkaju

04:19:51.780 --> 04:19:52.020
said.

04:19:52.139 --> 04:19:54.719
So I have to learn to read. so I can read

04:19:54.719 --> 04:19:56.819
all the scrolls ever written about ice

04:19:56.819 --> 04:19:58.500
wings and figure it out myself.

04:19:58.559 --> 04:20:01.139
They worked on the scroll for a while

04:20:01.139 --> 04:20:04.139
with Kinkaju puzzling out the words, and

04:20:04.139 --> 04:20:05.879
turning lavender with delight when she

04:20:05.879 --> 04:20:06.299
got them right.

04:20:06.360 --> 04:20:09.780
After a while, Moon paused, thinking, and

04:20:09.780 --> 04:20:12.299
said, Winter or icicle might be able to

04:20:12.299 --> 04:20:12.659
tell you.

04:20:12.719 --> 04:20:14.520
Ha, ha.

04:20:14.579 --> 04:20:16.020
Can you imagine them telling me

04:20:16.020 --> 04:20:16.440
anything?

04:20:16.500 --> 04:20:19.319
Kingaju said, turning herself a chilly

04:20:19.319 --> 04:20:19.680
blue.

04:20:19.739 --> 04:20:23.159
We don't share ice wing secrets with mere

04:20:23.159 --> 04:20:25.260
rain wings, haughty sniff.

04:20:25.379 --> 04:20:28.079
Moon giggled, and Starflight looked up

04:20:28.079 --> 04:20:28.559
with a smile.

04:20:28.680 --> 04:20:31.860
I'm glad you 2 are getting along, he

04:20:31.860 --> 04:20:32.159
said.

04:20:32.219 --> 04:20:34.620
We spent a lot of time working out all

04:20:34.620 --> 04:20:35.399
the claw mates.

04:20:35.459 --> 04:20:38.159
I am still not sure about all of them

04:20:38.159 --> 04:20:40.920
Sonny chimed in, frowning anxiously.

04:20:41.040 --> 04:20:44.819
Like me, Cornelian asked, She had been

04:20:44.819 --> 04:20:46.920
pacing along the shelves, pulling out

04:20:46.920 --> 04:20:49.260
scrolls, glancing at them, and shoving

04:20:49.260 --> 04:20:49.680
them back in.

04:20:49.739 --> 04:20:52.200
Now she came stomping over to the desk.

04:20:52.260 --> 04:20:54.840
Maybe you could move me to a cave where

04:20:54.840 --> 04:20:56.579
there's less talking all the time.

04:20:56.639 --> 04:20:58.799
Don't be silly.

04:20:58.860 --> 04:21:00.059
Kinkachu said.

04:21:00.120 --> 04:21:01.500
Moon hardly ever talks.

04:21:01.559 --> 04:21:03.780
She talks more in her sleep than she ever

04:21:03.780 --> 04:21:04.559
does when she's awake.

04:21:04.680 --> 04:21:06.239
I do?

04:21:06.299 --> 04:21:08.399
Moon said, horrified.

04:21:08.459 --> 04:21:11.940
Three moons, yes. said Cornelian.

04:21:12.000 --> 04:21:13.500
And that's exactly what I mean.

04:21:13.559 --> 04:21:15.180
It is so annoying.

04:21:15.239 --> 04:21:17.520
One of them talks all day, and the other

04:21:17.520 --> 04:21:18.719
one yammers all night.

04:21:18.780 --> 04:21:21.840
Mother, why didn't you ever tell me

04:21:21.840 --> 04:21:22.260
this?

04:21:22.319 --> 04:21:23.700
Why didn't you warn me?

04:21:23.819 --> 04:21:26.040
Why didn't you think that talking in my

04:21:26.040 --> 04:21:28.319
sleep might put me and my secrets in

04:21:28.319 --> 04:21:28.620
danger?

04:21:28.680 --> 04:21:31.020
What do I say?

04:21:31.079 --> 04:21:32.819
Moon asked nervously.

04:21:32.879 --> 04:21:37.079
All kinds of fascinating nonsense, Kingaju

04:21:37.079 --> 04:21:37.440
said.

04:21:37.500 --> 04:21:40.860
Darkness and thunder and talons of doom

04:21:40.860 --> 04:21:42.000
and who knows what else?

04:21:42.059 --> 04:21:43.559
You must be reading something really

04:21:43.559 --> 04:21:44.040
exciting.

04:21:44.159 --> 04:21:45.840
Can I borrow it when you're done?

04:21:45.899 --> 04:21:49.680
Um, Moon said, shifting on her talons.

04:21:49.739 --> 04:21:52.079
You know, I think I might head to history

04:21:52.079 --> 04:21:53.639
a little early if that's all right.

04:21:53.700 --> 04:21:55.139
Why?

04:21:55.200 --> 04:21:56.280
Kinkachu asked.

04:21:56.340 --> 04:21:59.040
I just want to look at the old maps.

04:21:59.100 --> 04:22:01.979
Now that she said it, it sounded like a

04:22:01.979 --> 04:22:02.399
good idea.

04:22:02.459 --> 04:22:04.860
Maybe she'd find a clue about the old

04:22:04.860 --> 04:22:06.180
knight kingdom somewhere on there.

04:22:06.239 --> 04:22:08.819
Kinkachu wrinkled her nose and turned

04:22:08.819 --> 04:22:09.479
pale orange.

04:22:09.540 --> 04:22:12.780
Spend more time in that dank hole?

04:22:12.840 --> 04:22:13.559
No thank you.

04:22:13.620 --> 04:22:15.120
I'll be there when I have to.

04:22:15.180 --> 04:22:18.540
I doubt the maps will be helpful.

04:22:18.659 --> 04:22:21.659
Dark soccer pointed out, as Moon headed

04:22:21.659 --> 04:22:22.319
through the great hall.

04:22:22.379 --> 04:22:23.819
I know.

04:22:23.879 --> 04:22:24.659
Moon thought.

04:22:24.719 --> 04:22:26.819
Night Wings were the ones making the maps

04:22:26.819 --> 04:22:29.219
for 100s of years, and they made sure to

04:22:29.219 --> 04:22:31.200
erase any trace of either Night Wing

04:22:31.200 --> 04:22:32.700
Kingdom, old or new.

04:22:32.819 --> 04:22:35.399
Still, maybe there's something.

04:22:35.639 --> 04:22:38.280
At least you're looking.

04:22:38.340 --> 04:22:39.899
He said quietly.

04:22:39.959 --> 04:22:43.020
Maybe you haven't completely forsaken me

04:22:43.020 --> 04:22:43.319
yet.

04:22:43.379 --> 04:22:47.340
I don't, Moon faltered, as a flash of

04:22:47.340 --> 04:22:49.020
light suddenly blistered through her mind

04:22:49.020 --> 04:22:49.920
then vanished.

04:22:49.979 --> 04:22:52.799
She stopped, blinking and disoriented.

04:22:52.860 --> 04:22:55.020
She was halfway down the tunnel to the

04:22:55.020 --> 04:22:55.620
history cave.

04:22:55.680 --> 04:22:57.059
Did you do that?

04:22:57.120 --> 04:22:57.899
she asked.

04:22:57.959 --> 04:23:01.020
No, moon watch out.

04:23:01.079 --> 04:23:03.719
A slow pounding was working its way up

04:23:03.719 --> 04:23:06.180
her spine, along her neck, to the base of

04:23:06.180 --> 04:23:09.239
her skull, a moment later, pain shot

04:23:09.239 --> 04:23:11.459
through her like a claw brutally stabbing

04:23:11.459 --> 04:23:12.420
into her eye socket.

04:23:12.479 --> 04:23:15.059
She collapsed to the floor, clutching her

04:23:15.059 --> 04:23:16.559
head, and the vision came.

04:23:16.620 --> 04:23:19.500
Roaring flames tearing along the walls of

04:23:19.500 --> 04:23:21.959
the history cave, swallowing the maps

04:23:21.959 --> 04:23:24.239
leaping to the seated dragonettes in the

04:23:24.239 --> 04:23:26.879
space of a breath, fire blistering along

04:23:26.879 --> 04:23:29.639
moon's scales, her own voice screaming

04:23:29.639 --> 04:23:32.399
beside her, Kinkachu shrieking and

04:23:32.399 --> 04:23:34.260
burning white amid the smoke.

04:23:34.319 --> 04:23:37.799
Kibli, winter, turtle, all on fire.

04:23:37.860 --> 04:23:39.719
Everyone dying.

04:23:39.780 --> 04:23:41.819
All of them, dying.

04:23:41.940 --> 04:23:46.260
Chapter 13.

04:23:46.500 --> 04:23:48.840
Moon.

04:23:48.959 --> 04:23:51.299
Dark Stalker shouted, perhaps more than

04:23:51.299 --> 04:23:53.100
once, dragging her back to herself.

04:23:53.159 --> 04:23:55.319
Moon, it's not real.

04:23:55.379 --> 04:23:56.459
You're all right.

04:23:56.579 --> 04:23:58.920
She staggered up and caught herself

04:23:58.920 --> 04:24:00.420
against the rough stone side of the

04:24:00.420 --> 04:24:00.719
tunnel.

04:24:00.780 --> 04:24:02.879
What do you mean it's not real?

04:24:03.000 --> 04:24:04.260
She asked.

04:24:04.319 --> 04:24:06.059
Her heartbeat was too fast.

04:24:06.120 --> 04:24:08.340
Squeezing her chest so she could hardly

04:24:08.340 --> 04:24:08.639
breathe.

04:24:08.700 --> 04:24:11.940
I mean, it could have been, but it won't

04:24:11.940 --> 04:24:13.020
be, he said.

04:24:13.079 --> 04:24:14.340
Whatever that was.

04:24:14.399 --> 04:24:16.020
It's in the history cave.

04:24:16.079 --> 04:24:18.899
Stay away from there, and the vision

04:24:18.899 --> 04:24:21.239
returned fiercer and more agonizing than

04:24:21.239 --> 04:24:21.479
before.

04:24:21.540 --> 04:24:25.739
Now Moon was outside the history cave, and

04:24:25.739 --> 04:24:27.540
fire was pouring out into the tunnel

04:24:27.540 --> 04:24:29.700
along with the screaming, burning figures

04:24:29.700 --> 04:24:30.600
of her friends.

04:24:30.780 --> 04:24:32.819
Kinkachu stumbled to the ground in front

04:24:32.819 --> 04:24:35.399
of Moon, her wings turning crisp and

04:24:35.399 --> 04:24:37.200
black as flames ate them away.

04:24:37.260 --> 04:24:40.079
Cornelian's voice howled in pain from

04:24:40.079 --> 04:24:40.620
inside.

04:24:40.680 --> 04:24:43.680
Tamron and Umber lay half in, half out of

04:24:43.680 --> 04:24:46.680
the cave, gasping as dark smoke filled

04:24:46.680 --> 04:24:47.159
their lungs.

04:24:47.219 --> 04:24:48.899
Moon.

04:24:48.899 --> 04:24:49.860
Moon.

04:24:49.860 --> 04:24:51.780
Dark Stalker pulled her out again.

04:24:51.840 --> 04:24:53.159
Close your eyes.

04:24:53.219 --> 04:24:54.959
I can take your mind to a safe place

04:24:54.959 --> 04:24:56.520
where you won't see any of this.

04:24:56.579 --> 04:24:59.520
No, Moon shouted, don't do that.

04:24:59.639 --> 04:25:02.100
She pushed herself up and started running

04:25:02.100 --> 04:25:03.180
toward the history cave.

04:25:03.239 --> 04:25:04.739
What are you doing?

04:25:04.799 --> 04:25:06.360
Dark Stalker asked.

04:25:06.420 --> 04:25:07.559
I have to stop it.

04:25:07.620 --> 04:25:09.180
There isn't time.

04:25:09.239 --> 04:25:10.020
Can't you tell?

04:25:10.079 --> 04:25:11.760
The explosion is only a few minutes

04:25:11.760 --> 04:25:12.000
away.

04:25:12.059 --> 04:25:13.979
Then I have to warn them.

04:25:14.040 --> 04:25:15.540
Someone might be in there already.

04:25:15.600 --> 04:25:18.000
A half 2nd pause, then.

04:25:18.180 --> 04:25:19.559
Is that wise?

04:25:19.680 --> 04:25:21.360
Don't you want to keep your power

04:25:21.360 --> 04:25:21.840
secret?

04:25:21.899 --> 04:25:24.659
Not if it means my friends will all die.

04:25:24.719 --> 04:25:25.739
Moon cried.

04:25:25.860 --> 04:25:29.639
The vision slammed into again, stamping

04:25:29.639 --> 04:25:32.399
her to the ground like a giant talon, more

04:25:32.399 --> 04:25:35.579
fire, another burning dragon, maybe pike

04:25:35.579 --> 04:25:36.420
or big tail.

04:25:36.479 --> 04:25:38.940
Umber lying in a charred heap on the

04:25:38.940 --> 04:25:41.159
ground, Sora sobbing beside him.

04:25:41.219 --> 04:25:44.280
Kibley with his wings in flames, screaming

04:25:44.280 --> 04:25:44.579
for help.

04:25:44.639 --> 04:25:46.979
What is wrong with you?

04:25:47.040 --> 04:25:49.860
A cool, arrogant voice asked from above

04:25:49.860 --> 04:25:50.100
her.

04:25:50.159 --> 04:25:51.659
Is she all right?

04:25:51.719 --> 04:25:54.299
His brain worried, more sympathetically.

04:25:54.360 --> 04:25:57.780
Winter, moon shook her head, trying to

04:25:57.780 --> 04:25:58.200
clear it.

04:25:58.260 --> 04:26:00.479
The ice wing was really there, standing

04:26:00.479 --> 04:26:03.120
in front of her, really not on fire, not

04:26:03.120 --> 04:26:03.420
dead.

04:26:03.479 --> 04:26:06.180
His scales were smooth, pale blue

04:26:06.180 --> 04:26:07.020
unburnt.

04:26:07.079 --> 04:26:09.059
His eyes were arctic pools.

04:26:09.180 --> 04:26:11.940
Some kind of night wing seizure?

04:26:12.000 --> 04:26:14.760
he asked, looking down his snout adder

04:26:14.760 --> 04:26:16.979
his tail flicked, and he took a step back

04:26:16.979 --> 04:26:18.659
toward the history cave.

04:26:18.719 --> 04:26:20.819
She could see the archway only a few

04:26:20.819 --> 04:26:23.280
paces ahead of them, quiet and flame

04:26:23.280 --> 04:26:23.579
free.

04:26:23.700 --> 04:26:25.979
You can't go in there.

04:26:26.040 --> 04:26:28.079
Moon lunged forward and grabbed his

04:26:28.079 --> 04:26:29.159
forearm in her talons.

04:26:29.219 --> 04:26:30.780
We're touching.

04:26:30.840 --> 04:26:34.260
She's, I'm, her scales against mine.

04:26:34.319 --> 04:26:35.700
I can't want this.

04:26:35.760 --> 04:26:37.620
His mind whirled.

04:26:37.680 --> 04:26:38.879
What are you doing?

04:26:38.940 --> 04:26:41.100
He barked, but didn't pull away.

04:26:41.159 --> 04:26:44.520
Please, don't go in there, she managed.

04:26:44.579 --> 04:26:46.379
The vision was storming back.

04:26:46.440 --> 04:26:49.799
Something terrible is going to, Kibley

04:26:49.799 --> 04:26:52.860
burning, tamarind burning, winter safe

04:26:52.920 --> 04:26:53.940
icicles safe.

04:26:54.059 --> 04:26:55.379
Kinkaju burning.

04:26:55.440 --> 04:26:57.479
Winter was holding her up.

04:26:57.540 --> 04:26:59.879
She'd fallen against him, and he was

04:26:59.879 --> 04:27:01.860
trying to lift her back upright, his

04:27:01.860 --> 04:27:03.120
wings supporting hers.

04:27:03.180 --> 04:27:07.079
What's something terrible, he said, his

04:27:07.079 --> 04:27:07.799
voice rising.

04:27:07.860 --> 04:27:08.700
He shook her.

04:27:08.760 --> 04:27:09.600
How do you know?

04:27:09.659 --> 04:27:12.059
Hey, leave her alone.

04:27:12.120 --> 04:27:13.739
Kibley's voice interjected.

04:27:13.799 --> 04:27:17.520
Stop, Moon cried, pulling away from

04:27:17.520 --> 04:27:19.139
winter and throwing herself in front of

04:27:19.139 --> 04:27:20.159
Kibley and Turtle.

04:27:20.280 --> 04:27:21.180
Don't go in.

04:27:21.239 --> 04:27:22.379
No one can go in.

04:27:22.440 --> 04:27:27.239
Whoa, calm down, Turtle said gently.

04:27:27.299 --> 04:27:29.579
You're having some kind of panic attack.

04:27:29.639 --> 04:27:31.920
No, please listen.

04:27:31.979 --> 04:27:33.959
Moon couldn't catch her breath.

04:27:34.079 --> 04:27:36.659
Not with the visions coming faster, and

04:27:36.659 --> 04:27:38.040
the intensity of the thoughts around

04:27:38.040 --> 04:27:38.940
her.

04:27:39.000 --> 04:27:42.600
Tamarind dead, kinkachu sobbing, carnelian

04:27:42.600 --> 04:27:43.020
burning.

04:27:43.079 --> 04:27:44.879
She's losing her mind.

04:27:44.940 --> 04:27:47.520
Please, please don't let anyone go in

04:27:47.520 --> 04:27:47.760
there.

04:27:47.819 --> 04:27:49.979
Deep breaths.

04:27:50.100 --> 04:27:53.219
Dark Stalker said softly, you'll be all

04:27:53.219 --> 04:27:53.520
right.

04:27:53.579 --> 04:27:57.719
I'm listening, Kibley said, crouching to

04:27:57.719 --> 04:27:58.559
look into her eyes.

04:27:58.620 --> 04:27:59.639
We're here.

04:27:59.700 --> 04:28:00.420
Don't worry.

04:28:00.540 --> 04:28:02.340
Must be something serious.

04:28:02.399 --> 04:28:03.780
Look at her eyes.

04:28:03.840 --> 04:28:04.620
She's terrified.

04:28:04.680 --> 04:28:06.299
Did Winter do this to her?

04:28:06.360 --> 04:28:08.579
No, he doesn't know what's going on

04:28:08.579 --> 04:28:08.819
either.

04:28:08.940 --> 04:28:10.379
What can I do for her?

04:28:10.440 --> 04:28:11.879
Find the threat.

04:28:11.940 --> 04:28:12.780
Neutralize it.

04:28:12.840 --> 04:28:16.200
She grabbed Turtle's talons and tried to

04:28:16.200 --> 04:28:17.879
wrap his muffled mind around hers.

04:28:17.940 --> 04:28:19.260
Kinkatoo.

04:28:19.319 --> 04:28:21.239
I have to stop Kinkatoo.

04:28:21.299 --> 04:28:23.760
The image of the rain wing burning kept

04:28:23.760 --> 04:28:26.879
coming back over and over, like a knife

04:28:26.879 --> 04:28:28.860
plunging repeatedly into her heart.

04:28:28.920 --> 04:28:31.860
She's right behind us, Kibley said.

04:28:31.920 --> 04:28:33.420
He put one wing around her.

04:28:33.479 --> 04:28:35.520
Moon, what is happening?

04:28:35.579 --> 04:28:38.040
Yes, Winter said.

04:28:38.159 --> 04:28:39.059
What do you know?

04:28:39.180 --> 04:28:41.639
Moon could feel the footsteps of the

04:28:41.639 --> 04:28:42.899
other dragons through the floor.

04:28:42.959 --> 04:28:44.879
Dragons were coming for class.

04:28:44.940 --> 04:28:46.319
How could she stop them?

04:28:46.379 --> 04:28:48.059
How could she stop all of them?

04:28:48.120 --> 04:28:51.059
She let out a cry of pain and closed her

04:28:51.059 --> 04:28:51.479
eyes.

04:28:51.540 --> 04:28:54.360
Another vision, and this time peril was

04:28:54.360 --> 04:28:57.059
there, engulfed in flames, clutching

04:28:57.059 --> 04:28:58.139
someone in her talons.

04:28:58.200 --> 04:28:59.940
Was she the cause of the fire?

04:29:00.000 --> 04:29:02.040
If moon could stop peril?

04:29:02.100 --> 04:29:03.420
Could she save everyone?

04:29:03.479 --> 04:29:05.040
She couldn't think straight.

04:29:05.100 --> 04:29:06.959
Couldn't focus long enough to come up

04:29:06.959 --> 04:29:09.120
with a convincing lie or a plan or

04:29:09.120 --> 04:29:09.360
anything?

04:29:09.420 --> 04:29:11.700
Moon, it's all right.

04:29:11.760 --> 04:29:13.319
Moon, breathe.

04:29:13.379 --> 04:29:15.180
Here, lean on me.

04:29:15.239 --> 04:29:18.420
Warm rainbow wings wrapped around her.

04:29:18.479 --> 04:29:20.700
We have to take her to clay and sunny.

04:29:20.760 --> 04:29:21.540
They'll know what to do.

04:29:21.659 --> 04:29:24.540
Good idea, Kibley thought.

04:29:24.600 --> 04:29:25.680
I should have thought of that.

04:29:25.739 --> 04:29:27.659
Kinkajoo.

04:29:27.780 --> 04:29:30.299
Moonside, leaning into her friend.

04:29:30.360 --> 04:29:33.239
The walls were fading in and out, the

04:29:33.239 --> 04:29:35.399
torchlight flaring, and then disappearing

04:29:35.399 --> 04:29:36.420
and flickering back.

04:29:36.479 --> 04:29:38.819
She took a few stumbling steps as

04:29:38.819 --> 04:29:40.319
Kinkachu tried to guide her up the

04:29:40.319 --> 04:29:40.680
tunnel.

04:29:40.739 --> 04:29:43.559
I don't know, Winter was saying to

04:29:43.559 --> 04:29:43.920
someone.

04:29:43.979 --> 04:29:45.659
She just collapsed.

04:29:45.719 --> 04:29:48.239
Hey, Cornelian, Kibley called.

04:29:48.299 --> 04:29:49.260
Don't go in there.

04:29:49.319 --> 04:29:50.819
Why not?

04:29:50.879 --> 04:29:52.680
The Skywing's voice demanded.

04:29:52.739 --> 04:29:56.219
Ah, he said, one of the torches got all

04:29:56.219 --> 04:29:56.639
smoky.

04:29:56.760 --> 04:29:59.520
The whole cave smells. needs to air out.

04:29:59.579 --> 04:30:03.120
Smells fine to me, Cornelian growled.

04:30:03.180 --> 04:30:06.840
Come on, Moon, Kinkachu said, tugging her

04:30:06.840 --> 04:30:07.139
along.

04:30:07.200 --> 04:30:08.700
We'll go find help.

04:30:08.760 --> 04:30:11.280
But the cave, Moon said.

04:30:11.399 --> 04:30:13.559
She shook her head, trying to clear it.

04:30:13.620 --> 04:30:15.600
Kinkachu's worried thoughts were

04:30:15.600 --> 04:30:17.940
scattered all through hers, loud and

04:30:17.940 --> 04:30:19.139
sweet and muddling.

04:30:19.200 --> 04:30:22.020
Kinkatu wanted so badly to take Moon away

04:30:22.020 --> 04:30:23.879
from there that Moon couldn't find her

04:30:23.879 --> 04:30:25.440
way back to what she needed to do.

04:30:25.500 --> 04:30:26.940
I have to.

04:30:27.059 --> 04:30:29.280
Don't worry, Kingaju said.

04:30:29.340 --> 04:30:30.540
We can miss class today.

04:30:30.600 --> 04:30:32.520
Tamron will get us any notes we need.

04:30:32.579 --> 04:30:34.319
Is she in there?

04:30:34.379 --> 04:30:35.940
Moon froze.

04:30:36.000 --> 04:30:38.219
Kibley and Turtle were still beside her.

04:30:38.280 --> 04:30:40.739
Winter was a step away, watching her

04:30:40.739 --> 04:30:41.219
intently.

04:30:41.280 --> 04:30:43.799
Did she go in the history cave?

04:30:43.860 --> 04:30:47.340
Sure, but no, she can't.

04:30:47.399 --> 04:30:48.840
Moon turned.

04:30:48.840 --> 04:30:50.760
In time to see Carnelian at the cave

04:30:50.760 --> 04:30:51.959
entrance, tossing her head.

04:30:52.020 --> 04:30:55.260
You're an idiot, Sandwing, Carnelian

04:30:55.260 --> 04:30:55.500
said.

04:30:55.559 --> 04:30:56.940
It's perfectly fine in there.

04:30:57.000 --> 04:30:59.100
She stepped into the classroom.

04:30:59.159 --> 04:31:01.920
No, Moon cried.

04:31:01.979 --> 04:31:04.920
Farther along the tunnel, icicle was

04:31:04.920 --> 04:31:06.180
coming from the other direction.

04:31:06.360 --> 04:31:08.340
The ice wing stopped and arched her brows

04:31:08.340 --> 04:31:10.680
as Moon dove for the doorway where

04:31:10.680 --> 04:31:11.760
Carnelian had disappeared.

04:31:11.819 --> 04:31:14.520
With a whoosh and a boom.

04:31:14.579 --> 04:31:17.879
The cave exploded in a huge fireball.

04:31:17.940 --> 04:31:22.200
Chapter 14.

04:31:22.440 --> 04:31:26.219
Moon was blown backward, slamming into

04:31:26.219 --> 04:31:27.180
the cave wall behind her.

04:31:27.239 --> 04:31:29.700
She wasn't sure if she lost consciousness

04:31:29.700 --> 04:31:31.559
for a moment, or if her eyes were full of

04:31:31.559 --> 04:31:31.860
smoke.

04:31:31.920 --> 04:31:33.420
She couldn't hear anything.

04:31:33.479 --> 04:31:36.239
She could see Kinkachu screaming at the

04:31:36.239 --> 04:31:37.920
edge of the flames, but there was no

04:31:37.920 --> 04:31:38.100
sound.

04:31:38.219 --> 04:31:41.159
Everything was coming through loud and

04:31:41.159 --> 04:31:42.360
clear inside her head, though.

04:31:42.420 --> 04:31:45.360
Most of it was panicked, wordless images

04:31:45.360 --> 04:31:48.600
and fear, cascading faster and faster

04:31:48.600 --> 04:31:50.520
until Moon felt as if she couldn't be

04:31:50.520 --> 04:31:52.680
anymore afraid, or it would kill her.

04:31:52.739 --> 04:31:54.540
Listen to me.

04:31:54.600 --> 04:31:57.000
Dark Stalker said commandingly.

04:31:57.059 --> 04:31:59.459
I'm the calmest voice you can hear.

04:31:59.520 --> 04:32:01.379
Use me as your anchor.

04:32:01.440 --> 04:32:03.899
I'll keep talking until you calm down.

04:32:03.959 --> 04:32:05.819
Think about your heart beating.

04:32:05.879 --> 04:32:07.799
Remember that you are safe.

04:32:07.860 --> 04:32:08.819
Look around you.

04:32:08.940 --> 04:32:11.940
Moon blinked at the billowing black smoke

04:32:11.940 --> 04:32:13.559
that was pouring out of the history

04:32:13.559 --> 04:32:14.100
cave.

04:32:14.159 --> 04:32:17.520
A burning scroll rolled out, stopping

04:32:17.520 --> 04:32:20.340
just before her talons, shards of glass

04:32:20.340 --> 04:32:22.079
from the broken light globes were

04:32:22.079 --> 04:32:23.219
scattered all over the floor.

04:32:23.280 --> 04:32:25.559
Winter and Kibli were running toward

04:32:25.559 --> 04:32:25.739
her.

04:32:25.799 --> 04:32:28.079
Turtle was pressed to the tunnel wall

04:32:28.079 --> 04:32:31.079
beyond them, behind him, 2 dragons were

04:32:31.079 --> 04:32:31.440
approaching.

04:32:31.500 --> 04:32:33.360
Only a few seconds had passed.

04:32:33.420 --> 04:32:35.819
Kingaju is safe.

04:32:35.879 --> 04:32:37.680
Dark Stalker reminded her.

04:32:37.739 --> 04:32:39.180
Kibli is safe.

04:32:39.239 --> 04:32:41.819
The ice wing and the sea wing, regrettably

04:32:41.819 --> 04:32:42.600
are safe.

04:32:42.659 --> 04:32:45.780
Why, regrettably, Moon asked.

04:32:45.840 --> 04:32:47.520
Ah, you are listening.

04:32:47.579 --> 04:32:48.719
Keep listening.

04:32:48.780 --> 04:32:50.040
Focus on me.

04:32:50.100 --> 04:32:52.379
Don't let anyone else in, just for now.

04:32:52.440 --> 04:32:54.780
Moon!

04:32:54.840 --> 04:32:57.059
Winter skidded to a stop in front of her

04:32:57.120 --> 04:32:59.219
reaching for her shoulders, and then

04:32:59.219 --> 04:33:00.719
pulling back as she flinched away.

04:33:00.719 --> 04:33:02.040
What was that?

04:33:02.100 --> 04:33:05.159
We have to get her out of here, Kibley

04:33:05.159 --> 04:33:07.319
said, sliding his wing under one of moons

04:33:07.319 --> 04:33:08.040
and helping her up.

04:33:08.099 --> 04:33:11.639
The smoke, he broke off in a fit of

04:33:11.639 --> 04:33:11.999
coughing.

04:33:12.060 --> 04:33:15.479
But Tamarin, Cornelian.

04:33:15.540 --> 04:33:16.740
Moon gasped.

04:33:16.799 --> 04:33:18.060
What do we do?

04:33:18.119 --> 04:33:19.559
Kinkachu yelled.

04:33:19.619 --> 04:33:20.219
What do we do?

04:33:20.340 --> 04:33:23.159
Kibli and Moon staggered a few steps

04:33:23.159 --> 04:33:23.639
forward.

04:33:23.700 --> 04:33:25.619
And the 2 approaching dragons came into

04:33:25.619 --> 04:33:27.900
focus, Sora and Dumber.

04:33:27.959 --> 04:33:31.259
Sora's eyes were wild and terrified, and

04:33:31.259 --> 04:33:33.000
her mind was a mess of mud and battle

04:33:33.000 --> 04:33:33.779
flashbacks.

04:33:33.840 --> 04:33:36.119
Focus on my voice.

04:33:36.240 --> 04:33:38.159
Dark Stalker reminded Moon.

04:33:38.220 --> 04:33:40.259
Don't let yourself fall in.

04:33:40.319 --> 04:33:43.200
She steadied herself against his constant

04:33:43.200 --> 04:33:43.860
murmuring.

04:33:43.979 --> 04:33:45.659
I'm going to get help.

04:33:45.779 --> 04:33:46.919
Amber shouted.

04:33:46.979 --> 04:33:48.419
He tore off up the tunnel.

04:33:48.479 --> 04:33:50.040
Is anyone hurt?

04:33:50.099 --> 04:33:51.599
Sora squeaked.

04:33:51.659 --> 04:33:52.740
Where's icicle?

04:33:52.799 --> 04:33:54.360
She's all right.

04:33:54.419 --> 04:33:57.119
She wasn't inside, Moon said.

04:33:57.180 --> 04:33:59.880
She twisted around, but she couldn't see

04:33:59.880 --> 04:34:01.259
Sora's claw mate anymore.

04:34:01.319 --> 04:34:04.200
Even through the thick smoke, icicles

04:34:04.200 --> 04:34:05.880
gleaming white scales should have been

04:34:05.880 --> 04:34:08.099
visible, but there was no sign of the ice

04:34:08.099 --> 04:34:09.779
wing where Moon had seen her before the

04:34:09.779 --> 04:34:10.619
blast.

04:34:10.680 --> 04:34:13.919
At least 2 dragons were in there, Winter

04:34:13.919 --> 04:34:14.340
said.

04:34:14.400 --> 04:34:15.599
Moon felt sick.

04:34:15.659 --> 04:34:18.299
Tamarin, carnelian.

04:34:18.360 --> 04:34:21.060
Stand clear, a voice shouted.

04:34:21.119 --> 04:34:22.799
Footsteps thumping toward them.

04:34:22.919 --> 04:34:26.039
Moon flinched back against Kibley, as the

04:34:26.039 --> 04:34:28.319
ferocious heat of Peril's mind swept

04:34:28.319 --> 04:34:28.919
through her head.

04:34:28.919 --> 04:34:31.559
A moment before, Peril herself came

04:34:31.559 --> 04:34:32.579
charging through the smoke.

04:34:32.639 --> 04:34:34.500
She didn't stop to look at them.

04:34:34.560 --> 04:34:36.900
She ran straight into the burning cave.

04:34:37.020 --> 04:34:39.060
Three moons.

04:34:39.119 --> 04:34:41.759
Kingachu whispered frantically. clutching

04:34:41.759 --> 04:34:42.479
her talons together.

04:34:42.540 --> 04:34:45.840
A minute later, peril's smoking wings

04:34:45.840 --> 04:34:48.299
appeared, and she backed out of the cave

04:34:48.299 --> 04:34:49.860
dragging someone behind her.

04:34:49.919 --> 04:34:52.679
She pulled the burned dragonette level

04:34:52.679 --> 04:34:54.779
with Moon and the others, then later on

04:34:54.779 --> 04:34:56.819
the stone floor and ran back into the

04:34:56.819 --> 04:34:57.059
cave.

04:34:57.119 --> 04:35:00.599
Kinkachu gasped and buried her face in

04:35:00.599 --> 04:35:01.079
her talons.

04:35:01.139 --> 04:35:04.380
Oh no, Moon said softly.

04:35:04.439 --> 04:35:07.319
She let go of Kibley, and crouched beside

04:35:07.319 --> 04:35:07.619
the body.

04:35:07.680 --> 04:35:10.319
She could see patches of unburnt red

04:35:10.319 --> 04:35:12.900
scales, but so much of carnelian was

04:35:12.900 --> 04:35:14.819
burned that she looked more like a night

04:35:14.819 --> 04:35:16.080
wing than a sky wing.

04:35:16.139 --> 04:35:18.060
Maybe I can.

04:35:18.779 --> 04:35:21.299
Winter hesitated, then crouched, and

04:35:21.299 --> 04:35:23.039
breathed a small amount of frost breath

04:35:23.039 --> 04:35:24.299
on Carnelian's neck.

04:35:24.360 --> 04:35:27.479
The scales stopped smoking, but stayed

04:35:27.479 --> 04:35:27.659
black.

04:35:27.720 --> 04:35:29.700
He shook his head in frustration.

04:35:29.759 --> 04:35:31.619
That could make it worse.

04:35:31.680 --> 04:35:32.340
I don't know.

04:35:32.459 --> 04:35:33.599
He worried.

04:35:33.659 --> 04:35:36.299
Moon couldn't tell if Carnelian was even

04:35:36.299 --> 04:35:37.200
still breathing or not.

04:35:37.259 --> 04:35:40.439
Moon's heart jumped as she heard more

04:35:40.439 --> 04:35:41.639
dragons running toward them.

04:35:41.700 --> 04:35:43.680
She could hear that one of them was a

04:35:43.680 --> 04:35:44.939
desperately worried clay.

04:35:45.000 --> 04:35:48.240
He stopped briefly beside Carnelian, grief

04:35:48.240 --> 04:35:50.099
flooding through him, and looked across

04:35:50.099 --> 04:35:50.759
at Sora.

04:35:50.819 --> 04:35:52.500
How many are still in there?

04:35:52.560 --> 04:35:53.400
He asked.

04:35:53.459 --> 04:35:56.459
Zora opened and closed her mouth, unable

04:35:56.459 --> 04:35:56.759
to speak.

04:35:56.819 --> 04:35:58.740
We don't know for sure.

04:35:58.799 --> 04:36:00.240
Kinkaju jumped in.

04:36:00.299 --> 04:36:02.759
At least, Tameron, peril went back in

04:36:02.759 --> 04:36:03.000
too.

04:36:03.119 --> 04:36:05.819
Clay didn't ask any more questions.

04:36:05.880 --> 04:36:08.580
He ran into the fire, limping on his

04:36:08.580 --> 04:36:09.479
scarred leg.

04:36:09.540 --> 04:36:11.639
Flames licking hungrily across his

04:36:11.639 --> 04:36:12.720
fireproof scales.

04:36:12.779 --> 04:36:15.119
Moon could hear how much it hurt him.

04:36:15.180 --> 04:36:18.060
His power meant he healed quickly, but

04:36:18.060 --> 04:36:20.040
the fire still burned him, even just for

04:36:20.040 --> 04:36:21.959
a moment, but he didn't hesitate.

04:36:22.020 --> 04:36:25.200
Sora let out a choked sob and fled.

04:36:25.259 --> 04:36:26.759
What's happening?

04:36:26.819 --> 04:36:29.220
Onyx demanded from behind Moon.

04:36:29.279 --> 04:36:31.859
She and Pike stared in bewilderment at

04:36:31.859 --> 04:36:32.819
the roaring flames.

04:36:32.880 --> 04:36:34.500
Tamarin?

04:36:34.560 --> 04:36:35.880
Kingachu whispered.

04:36:35.939 --> 04:36:38.879
Onyx narrowed her dark eyes at the fire.

04:36:38.939 --> 04:36:41.999
Pike flared his wings, his mind flooding

04:36:41.999 --> 04:36:43.379
with images of the attack on the summer

04:36:43.379 --> 04:36:44.099
palace.

04:36:44.220 --> 04:36:46.740
Moon could see burning logs falling from

04:36:46.740 --> 04:36:49.020
the sky, crashing into a pavilion.

04:36:49.080 --> 04:36:51.240
The palace albatross had built.

04:36:51.360 --> 04:36:53.520
She could see sea wings desperately

04:36:53.520 --> 04:36:54.900
trying to escape through a narrow

04:36:54.900 --> 04:36:55.740
tunnel.

04:36:55.799 --> 04:36:58.680
She saw small explosions going off as

04:36:58.680 --> 04:37:00.720
some of the flaming projectiles smashed

04:37:00.720 --> 04:37:01.979
into panicking dragons.

04:37:02.159 --> 04:37:05.340
We shouldn't be breathing this, Kibley

04:37:05.340 --> 04:37:07.500
said, trying to steer moon away from the

04:37:07.500 --> 04:37:07.740
fire.

04:37:07.799 --> 04:37:10.259
This smoke is as bad as the fire.

04:37:10.259 --> 04:37:11.639
If we breathe too much.

04:37:11.700 --> 04:37:15.240
I'm not leaving until I know Tamron's all

04:37:15.240 --> 04:37:16.619
right, Kinkachu said.

04:37:16.680 --> 04:37:19.500
Moon shook her head in agreement, and

04:37:19.500 --> 04:37:20.279
Kibley gave up.

04:37:20.340 --> 04:37:22.020
A movement in the smoke.

04:37:22.080 --> 04:37:25.080
And then clay emerged, carrying a

04:37:25.080 --> 04:37:26.700
dragonette slung across his back.

04:37:26.759 --> 04:37:28.919
Behind him was peril, with another

04:37:28.919 --> 04:37:29.759
dragonette.

04:37:29.819 --> 04:37:33.000
Moon tried to breathe, tried to focus on

04:37:33.000 --> 04:37:35.580
Dark Stalker's voice, still whispering

04:37:35.580 --> 04:37:38.279
calming things in the background, but who

04:37:38.279 --> 04:37:39.599
was the 3rd dragonette?

04:37:39.659 --> 04:37:41.099
Is it all clear?

04:37:41.220 --> 04:37:43.139
Winter asked Clay.

04:37:43.200 --> 04:37:44.700
Clay nodded tiredly.

04:37:44.759 --> 04:37:47.099
We swept the entire space.

04:37:47.159 --> 04:37:48.959
No one else in there.

04:37:49.020 --> 04:37:52.200
Winter ran toward the cave, opened his

04:37:52.200 --> 04:37:54.299
mouth, and poured out a blast of icy

04:37:54.299 --> 04:37:54.599
air.

04:37:54.659 --> 04:37:57.599
He advanced on the fire, putting it out

04:37:57.599 --> 04:37:59.040
with his frost breath as he stepped

04:37:59.040 --> 04:38:01.020
through the smoke, into the cave.

04:38:01.080 --> 04:38:03.659
I hope he's safe, Moon thought.

04:38:03.720 --> 04:38:05.939
And then all her thoughts were crowded

04:38:05.939 --> 04:38:06.240
out.

04:38:06.240 --> 04:38:08.700
By the sight of the dragonette, Clay was

04:38:08.700 --> 04:38:09.720
sliding gently to the ground.

04:38:09.779 --> 04:38:11.579
Tamarin?

04:38:11.639 --> 04:38:12.959
Kinkachu cried.

04:38:13.080 --> 04:38:15.599
The blind rain wing was not as badly

04:38:15.599 --> 04:38:16.799
burned as carnelian.

04:38:16.860 --> 04:38:19.139
She was unconscious, but she was still

04:38:19.139 --> 04:38:19.560
breathing.

04:38:19.619 --> 04:38:22.859
Kinkachu bent over her, white and green

04:38:22.859 --> 04:38:24.659
patches pummeling each other across her

04:38:24.659 --> 04:38:27.059
scales, and carefully lifted one of her

04:38:27.059 --> 04:38:28.139
friend's talons.

04:38:28.200 --> 04:38:30.119
I think she might have smelled

04:38:30.119 --> 04:38:30.419
something.

04:38:30.479 --> 04:38:33.360
Maybe smoke, right before the explosion

04:38:33.360 --> 04:38:34.979
happened, Clay said.

04:38:35.040 --> 04:38:38.400
She was behind one of the scroll racks, as

04:38:38.400 --> 04:38:39.900
though she'd tipped it over in front of

04:38:39.900 --> 04:38:40.080
her.

04:38:40.139 --> 04:38:42.119
It might have saved your life.

04:38:42.180 --> 04:38:46.319
If she lives, he thought despairingly.

04:38:46.380 --> 04:38:50.279
Tamarin, you're all right, Kinkachu said

04:38:50.279 --> 04:38:51.599
biting back a sob.

04:38:51.659 --> 04:38:54.000
You'd better be all right, or I will tie

04:38:54.000 --> 04:38:55.560
you to a tree and cover you with

04:38:55.560 --> 04:38:56.880
hallucinogenic frogs.

04:38:56.939 --> 04:38:57.719
Tamron.

04:38:57.779 --> 04:38:58.679
Please wake up.

04:38:58.799 --> 04:39:01.680
We should get her some of those rain wing

04:39:01.680 --> 04:39:04.139
tranquilizing darts before she does wake

04:39:04.139 --> 04:39:04.380
up.

04:39:04.500 --> 04:39:07.560
Clay said, touching Kinkachu's wing with

04:39:07.560 --> 04:39:07.799
his own.

04:39:07.860 --> 04:39:10.740
Those burns are going to hurt a lot.

04:39:10.799 --> 04:39:13.979
He crouched to study the 3rd dragonette

04:39:13.979 --> 04:39:15.720
lying on the ground in front of peril.

04:39:15.779 --> 04:39:19.139
For a moment, Moon thought whoever it was

04:39:19.139 --> 04:39:21.659
must have been burned beyond recognition

04:39:21.659 --> 04:39:23.639
and then she realized his scales were

04:39:23.639 --> 04:39:23.939
black.

04:39:24.000 --> 04:39:27.119
It was Big Tail, the other Nightwing.

04:39:27.180 --> 04:39:28.860
He was clearly dead.

04:39:28.919 --> 04:39:31.619
Clay turned to Carnelian for a moment

04:39:31.619 --> 04:39:34.079
touching her neck, and then shook his

04:39:34.079 --> 04:39:34.259
head.

04:39:34.319 --> 04:39:36.240
Cornelian was dead too.

04:39:36.299 --> 04:39:39.000
Tamaron was the only survivor.

04:39:39.060 --> 04:39:41.099
If she survived her burns.

04:39:41.159 --> 04:39:44.700
The underground lake, Pike said suddenly

04:39:44.700 --> 04:39:45.840
let's put her in the lake.

04:39:45.900 --> 04:39:46.560
It's not far.

04:39:46.619 --> 04:39:48.599
Submerging her in water will help.

04:39:48.659 --> 04:39:50.700
I've seen, I saw this work.

04:39:50.819 --> 04:39:54.240
After the attack, he cut himself off

04:39:54.240 --> 04:39:57.060
darted forward, and tried to lift Tamarin

04:39:57.060 --> 04:39:59.159
but he was thin, and she was a little

04:39:59.159 --> 04:40:00.119
bigger than he was.

04:40:00.180 --> 04:40:02.279
He staggered, and Clay stopped him.

04:40:02.340 --> 04:40:04.020
I'll carry her.

04:40:04.080 --> 04:40:05.040
Show me the way.

04:40:05.159 --> 04:40:06.900
I'll come too.

04:40:06.959 --> 04:40:09.720
Onyx said, studying her clawmate with

04:40:09.720 --> 04:40:10.439
apparent concern.

04:40:10.500 --> 04:40:13.799
Go to Sonny, Clay said to Parel.

04:40:13.860 --> 04:40:16.259
Tell her to bring Trank darts and meet us

04:40:16.259 --> 04:40:16.680
at the lake.

04:40:16.799 --> 04:40:19.740
Peril nodded, glanced back at the smoking

04:40:19.740 --> 04:40:20.880
cave, and hurried away.

04:40:20.939 --> 04:40:24.000
Kibley helped lift Tamron onto Clay's

04:40:24.000 --> 04:40:24.180
back.

04:40:24.240 --> 04:40:27.299
Pike scurried away, running full tilt

04:40:27.299 --> 04:40:28.979
with clay and onyx right behind him.

04:40:29.040 --> 04:40:32.220
Kinkaju took a step after them, then

04:40:32.220 --> 04:40:34.319
wavered, looking back at Moon and

04:40:34.319 --> 04:40:34.979
Carnelian.

04:40:35.040 --> 04:40:38.099
By the time her mind said, go with Tamron

04:40:38.099 --> 04:40:38.939
moon will be fine.

04:40:39.000 --> 04:40:41.459
They were gone, and she didn't know where

04:40:41.459 --> 04:40:42.299
the lake was.

04:40:42.360 --> 04:40:46.020
Moon, you're bleeding, Kibley said.

04:40:46.080 --> 04:40:48.479
Moon finally noticed the trail of blood

04:40:48.479 --> 04:40:50.700
down her left shoulder, and the sharp

04:40:50.700 --> 04:40:51.779
pain at the back of her head.

04:40:51.840 --> 04:40:55.319
I'm all right. she said, touching her

04:40:55.319 --> 04:40:56.279
skull gingerly.

04:40:56.340 --> 04:40:58.380
She could hear a lot more dragons coming

04:40:58.380 --> 04:40:58.860
their way.

04:40:58.919 --> 04:41:01.500
Tsunami and Sunny among them.

04:41:01.560 --> 04:41:03.720
You have a lot of explaining to do.

04:41:03.840 --> 04:41:05.939
Dark soccer said quietly.

04:41:06.000 --> 04:41:08.459
Start thinking of a good lie now.

04:41:08.520 --> 04:41:12.119
Let's get you to the infirmary, Kinkachu

04:41:12.119 --> 04:41:12.299
said.

04:41:12.360 --> 04:41:15.779
Wait, Winter said, emerging from the

04:41:15.779 --> 04:41:16.139
cave.

04:41:16.139 --> 04:41:18.360
Behind him the fire was hissing out.

04:41:18.419 --> 04:41:20.700
The wrecked cave was covered in ice

04:41:20.700 --> 04:41:23.279
crystals, a gleaming layer of silver over

04:41:23.279 --> 04:41:25.560
black, frost over soot.

04:41:25.619 --> 04:41:28.500
Scraps of burnt scrolls littered the

04:41:28.500 --> 04:41:30.720
ground, and the ashes of the maps on the

04:41:30.720 --> 04:41:32.279
walls were still drifting down.

04:41:32.340 --> 04:41:34.799
At least it wasn't the library.

04:41:34.860 --> 04:41:37.919
Moon thought, how had everything burned

04:41:37.919 --> 04:41:38.639
so fast?

04:41:38.700 --> 04:41:41.580
Even with the scrolls and maps, there

04:41:41.580 --> 04:41:43.200
shouldn't have been such a big fire

04:41:43.200 --> 04:41:43.740
surely.

04:41:43.799 --> 04:41:44.880
And how did it start?

04:41:44.939 --> 04:41:47.220
It wasn't a normal fire.

04:41:47.279 --> 04:41:48.060
She knew that.

04:41:48.119 --> 04:41:49.919
Something had exploded.

04:41:50.040 --> 04:41:53.159
But did that mean that someone had said

04:41:53.159 --> 04:41:53.819
it on purpose?

04:41:53.880 --> 04:41:56.939
Winter suddenly clamped his claws around

04:41:56.939 --> 04:41:59.759
her uninjured forearm, Moon let out a

04:41:59.759 --> 04:42:02.099
yelp as the freezing shock of his scales

04:42:02.099 --> 04:42:02.939
met hers.

04:42:03.000 --> 04:42:05.400
Hey, Kinkaju protested.

04:42:05.459 --> 04:42:08.759
Don't, Kibley started, but winter didn't

04:42:08.759 --> 04:42:08.939
stop.

04:42:09.000 --> 04:42:11.580
He dragged Moon down the tunnel away from

04:42:11.580 --> 04:42:12.000
the smoke.

04:42:12.060 --> 04:42:14.700
She could hear Kibley and Kinkajou and

04:42:14.700 --> 04:42:16.500
another pair of claws scrambling to

04:42:16.500 --> 04:42:16.860
follow them.

04:42:16.919 --> 04:42:18.599
What are you doing?

04:42:18.659 --> 04:42:19.860
Moon asked him.

04:42:19.919 --> 04:42:22.560
His grip was like being trapped in ice

04:42:22.560 --> 04:42:25.380
trying to pull away did no good, and

04:42:25.380 --> 04:42:27.659
where most dragons' minds became clearer

04:42:27.659 --> 04:42:30.180
when she touched them, his became too

04:42:30.180 --> 04:42:33.060
bright and painfully dazzling, reflecting

04:42:33.060 --> 04:42:34.799
back at her like sun off a field of

04:42:34.799 --> 04:42:35.040
snow.

04:42:35.159 --> 04:42:37.919
All she could get were flashes of sharp

04:42:37.919 --> 04:42:39.900
anger, which she really could have

04:42:39.900 --> 04:42:41.220
figured out on her own from his

04:42:41.220 --> 04:42:41.639
expression.

04:42:41.700 --> 04:42:45.599
Here, Winter said, pushing her into a

04:42:45.599 --> 04:42:47.639
tall, narrow cave, where the air was

04:42:47.639 --> 04:42:48.599
clear enough to breathe.

04:42:48.599 --> 04:42:51.180
They were out of sight of the fire damage

04:42:51.180 --> 04:42:53.279
but close enough that Moon could still

04:42:53.279 --> 04:42:54.900
scent the dragons gathering there.

04:42:54.959 --> 04:42:57.599
Her claws scraped against squat

04:42:57.599 --> 04:42:59.400
stalagmites jutting from the floor.

04:42:59.459 --> 04:43:01.740
The sound of water dripping somewhere

04:43:01.740 --> 04:43:05.639
slowly, drop by drop, echoed against the

04:43:05.639 --> 04:43:07.380
looming walls and distant ceiling.

04:43:07.439 --> 04:43:10.860
Kibli, Kinkachu, and Turtle burst into

04:43:10.860 --> 04:43:12.959
the cavern behind them, bristling with

04:43:12.959 --> 04:43:13.919
outraged thoughts.

04:43:13.979 --> 04:43:16.560
Kibley had grabbed a torch along the way

04:43:16.560 --> 04:43:18.479
and shoved it into a crack in the wall

04:43:18.479 --> 04:43:20.639
adding another circle of firelight to the

04:43:20.639 --> 04:43:20.880
space.

04:43:20.939 --> 04:43:23.639
You can't just push your friends around

04:43:23.639 --> 04:43:26.279
like that, Kinkachu said, hurrying over

04:43:26.279 --> 04:43:28.259
to Moon, especially when she's hurt.

04:43:28.380 --> 04:43:30.959
Moon, there's something in this wound.

04:43:31.080 --> 04:43:33.240
She reached out but didn't touch it.

04:43:33.299 --> 04:43:35.939
Moon twisted her neck and saw that there

04:43:35.939 --> 04:43:37.500
was something sticking out of the cut in

04:43:37.500 --> 04:43:39.959
her shoulder, like a collection of tiny

04:43:39.959 --> 04:43:40.860
sharp splinters.

04:43:40.919 --> 04:43:44.159
Kibli lifted his venomous tail and glared

04:43:44.159 --> 04:43:45.959
at Winter, but before he could say

04:43:45.959 --> 04:43:48.119
anything, Winter took a menacing step

04:43:48.119 --> 04:43:50.700
toward Moon and pointed one silver claw

04:43:50.700 --> 04:43:51.000
at her.

04:43:51.060 --> 04:43:54.479
You knew, he snarled.

04:43:54.540 --> 04:43:56.459
That's why you tried to stop us from

04:43:56.459 --> 04:43:56.880
going in.

04:43:56.939 --> 04:43:59.639
You knew about the explosion and the fire

04:43:59.639 --> 04:44:01.020
before it happened.

04:44:01.080 --> 04:44:04.439
He took another step, until all she could

04:44:04.439 --> 04:44:06.360
see was the bright orange reflection of

04:44:06.360 --> 04:44:07.439
the torchlight in his eyes.

04:44:07.500 --> 04:44:13.560
So, he hissed, exactly how did you know?

04:44:13.680 --> 04:44:17.939
Chapter 15.

04:44:18.360 --> 04:44:22.319
Winter's words had an instant effect on

04:44:22.319 --> 04:44:23.580
the other 3 dragonettes.

04:44:23.639 --> 04:44:25.139
He's right.

04:44:25.200 --> 04:44:27.720
Kinkaju realized, how?

04:44:27.779 --> 04:44:28.860
What?

04:44:28.919 --> 04:44:32.159
Turtle's mind was as opaque as ever, but

04:44:32.159 --> 04:44:34.319
he shifted on his talons and gave Moon a

04:44:34.319 --> 04:44:34.919
curious frown.

04:44:35.040 --> 04:44:37.919
Worst of all was Kibli.

04:44:37.979 --> 04:44:39.540
How did she know?

04:44:39.659 --> 04:44:41.400
She couldn't have done this.

04:44:41.459 --> 04:44:42.540
Could she?

04:44:42.599 --> 04:44:45.840
She's a dragon with secrets, and Thorn

04:44:45.840 --> 04:44:47.580
said not to trust the night wings.

04:44:47.639 --> 04:44:49.020
Why would she?

04:44:49.080 --> 04:44:52.020
I know I haven't figured her out yet, but

04:44:52.020 --> 04:44:53.040
I don't see violence in her.

04:44:53.159 --> 04:44:55.860
And yet, how did she know?

04:44:55.919 --> 04:44:58.680
But if she set the fire, why would she

04:44:58.680 --> 04:44:59.819
try to stop us from going in?

04:44:59.880 --> 04:45:01.799
But surely she wouldn't.

04:45:01.860 --> 04:45:03.419
She couldn't have.

04:45:03.479 --> 04:45:05.159
I can't even believe I'm thinking this.

04:45:05.220 --> 04:45:07.439
You didn't?

04:45:07.500 --> 04:45:10.080
Sorry, but you didn't have anything to do

04:45:10.080 --> 04:45:11.400
with, he started.

04:45:11.459 --> 04:45:13.740
No, Moon cried.

04:45:13.799 --> 04:45:14.939
Of course not.

04:45:15.000 --> 04:45:17.759
She brushed away tears, trying to keep

04:45:17.759 --> 04:45:19.979
her voice steady, trying not to think

04:45:19.979 --> 04:45:22.139
about carnelian, or how everything was

04:45:22.139 --> 04:45:23.040
now falling apart.

04:45:23.099 --> 04:45:24.900
I would never hurt anyone.

04:45:24.959 --> 04:45:28.619
I know, Kibley said, but not

04:45:28.619 --> 04:45:29.220
convincingly.

04:45:29.340 --> 04:45:31.799
She was better at hunting than anyone

04:45:31.799 --> 04:45:32.220
expected.

04:45:32.340 --> 04:45:34.919
There is strength beneath those scales.

04:45:34.979 --> 04:45:36.959
In the right circumstances.

04:45:37.020 --> 04:45:39.180
Wouldn't any dragon be capable of hurting

04:45:39.180 --> 04:45:39.479
another?

04:45:39.540 --> 04:45:40.560
Even her?

04:45:40.619 --> 04:45:41.880
But why?

04:45:41.939 --> 04:45:45.840
If you didn't do it, then do you know who

04:45:45.840 --> 04:45:46.139
did?

04:45:46.200 --> 04:45:47.700
Turtle asked.

04:45:47.759 --> 04:45:49.740
He hadn't spoken since the blast.

04:45:49.799 --> 04:45:51.840
He hadn't moved from a spot by the wall

04:45:51.840 --> 04:45:53.520
until he came chasing after them.

04:45:53.580 --> 04:45:56.279
He looked shaken, but not destroyed.

04:45:56.340 --> 04:45:58.380
Moon wished she knew what he was

04:45:58.380 --> 04:45:58.740
thinking.

04:45:58.799 --> 04:46:00.540
Did he suspect her too?

04:46:00.599 --> 04:46:03.119
Or maybe you saw something?

04:46:03.180 --> 04:46:06.060
Kinkaju suggested, hopefully, something

04:46:06.060 --> 04:46:06.840
that warned you?

04:46:06.900 --> 04:46:10.560
That might work, Dark Stalker said.

04:46:10.619 --> 04:46:13.080
At least 2 of them want to believe that.

04:46:13.139 --> 04:46:15.720
Start with that lie, and build from

04:46:15.720 --> 04:46:15.900
there.

04:46:15.959 --> 04:46:19.139
I don't want to tell them any lies.

04:46:19.259 --> 04:46:22.200
Moon pointed out, even once they want to

04:46:22.200 --> 04:46:22.560
believe.

04:46:22.680 --> 04:46:25.439
She pressed her front claws together

04:46:25.439 --> 04:46:27.720
feeling a wrenching fear all through her

04:46:27.720 --> 04:46:28.200
chest.

04:46:28.259 --> 04:46:30.180
Her mother was echoing through her head.

04:46:30.299 --> 04:46:33.240
Never, never tell anyone about your

04:46:33.240 --> 04:46:33.779
curse.

04:46:33.840 --> 04:46:35.639
Never let anyone find out.

04:46:35.700 --> 04:46:37.200
It will be the end of everything.

04:46:37.259 --> 04:46:41.099
There's only one explanation.

04:46:41.220 --> 04:46:43.979
Winter hissed through his teeth looking

04:46:43.979 --> 04:46:45.240
down his snout at her.

04:46:45.299 --> 04:46:48.479
You did this, you set that fire.

04:46:48.540 --> 04:46:51.180
I don't know why yet, but I will find

04:46:51.180 --> 04:46:51.419
out.

04:46:51.479 --> 04:46:54.360
The other explanation was there.

04:46:54.419 --> 04:46:57.180
Hovering at the edge of his mind, but he

04:46:57.180 --> 04:46:58.319
couldn't bring himself to believe it

04:46:58.319 --> 04:46:58.680
yet.

04:46:58.740 --> 04:47:00.360
He'd been so sure.

04:47:00.419 --> 04:47:04.020
So sure, that the Night Wings were lying

04:47:04.020 --> 04:47:05.159
about their powers all along.

04:47:05.279 --> 04:47:08.700
I swear I didn't, Moon said.

04:47:08.759 --> 04:47:10.619
She spread her wings helplessly.

04:47:10.680 --> 04:47:12.119
Please, believe me.

04:47:12.180 --> 04:47:14.939
Can't you tell us how you knew?

04:47:15.000 --> 04:47:16.500
Kinkachu pleaded.

04:47:16.560 --> 04:47:18.000
Moon couldn't speak.

04:47:18.060 --> 04:47:20.279
She felt as if there were claws clamped

04:47:20.279 --> 04:47:22.259
around her throat, as though her worst

04:47:22.259 --> 04:47:24.479
fear was trying to choke her so she

04:47:24.479 --> 04:47:25.740
wouldn't reveal her secrets.

04:47:25.799 --> 04:47:28.380
Winter stared at her for a long minute

04:47:28.380 --> 04:47:31.139
and then he lashed his tail, spikes

04:47:31.139 --> 04:47:32.939
clattering against the stubby pillars

04:47:32.939 --> 04:47:33.599
dotting the floor.

04:47:33.720 --> 04:47:36.959
I will give you one chance night wing.

04:47:37.020 --> 04:47:39.240
You have until midnight tomorrow to tell

04:47:39.240 --> 04:47:39.720
me the truth.

04:47:39.779 --> 04:47:42.119
Or I'm going to tell everyone what you

04:47:42.119 --> 04:47:42.360
did.

04:47:42.479 --> 04:47:45.299
He took a step toward her, and she

04:47:45.299 --> 04:47:45.959
flinched back.

04:47:46.020 --> 04:47:48.779
I knew Nightwings couldn't be trusted.

04:47:48.840 --> 04:47:50.939
But I was starting to think maybe you

04:47:50.939 --> 04:47:51.360
were different.

04:47:51.419 --> 04:47:53.520
Clearly, I was wrong.

04:47:53.580 --> 04:47:56.099
He stalked out of the cave.

04:47:56.159 --> 04:47:58.619
Moon buried her face and her talons

04:47:58.619 --> 04:47:59.159
shaking.

04:48:00.060 --> 04:48:01.680
Kinkajoo reached for her hesitantly.

04:48:01.740 --> 04:48:04.619
The doubt in Kinkachu's mind, of all

04:48:04.619 --> 04:48:06.959
dragons, made Moon want to disappear

04:48:06.959 --> 04:48:07.740
completely.

04:48:07.799 --> 04:48:11.279
I don't understand, Kibley was thinking.

04:48:11.340 --> 04:48:13.860
And that was clearly an unfamiliar and

04:48:13.860 --> 04:48:15.599
uncomfortable experience for him.

04:48:15.659 --> 04:48:17.880
His brain kept circling all the

04:48:17.880 --> 04:48:21.119
possibilities, including the truth, but

04:48:21.119 --> 04:48:22.319
he kept shying away from it.

04:48:22.439 --> 04:48:25.200
Moon knew it wouldn't be long before he

04:48:25.200 --> 04:48:25.919
came to it though.

04:48:25.979 --> 04:48:28.380
But he wasn't the 1st one there.

04:48:28.439 --> 04:48:32.459
Three moons, Turtles said.

04:48:32.520 --> 04:48:35.340
Glowing lines lit up along his wings and

04:48:35.340 --> 04:48:37.799
neck, making him shimmer eerily in the

04:48:37.799 --> 04:48:38.639
dark cave.

04:48:38.700 --> 04:48:41.220
He took a deep breath, staring at her

04:48:41.220 --> 04:48:42.299
with wide eyes.

04:48:42.360 --> 04:48:45.180
It was a vision, wasn't it?

04:48:45.240 --> 04:48:46.979
You can see the future.

04:48:47.099 --> 04:48:49.319
Kinkaju gasped.

04:48:49.439 --> 04:48:52.200
No way, she whispered.

04:48:52.259 --> 04:48:56.340
Admit nothing, Dark Stalker advised.

04:48:56.400 --> 04:48:58.080
Stay secret.

04:48:58.139 --> 04:48:59.220
Stay hidden.

04:48:59.279 --> 04:49:00.240
Stay safe.

04:49:00.299 --> 04:49:02.580
Her mother's mantra echoed in her head.

04:49:02.639 --> 04:49:04.860
There didn't seem to be any chance of

04:49:04.860 --> 04:49:05.400
that now.

04:49:05.459 --> 04:49:08.880
Moon looked down at her talons, and

04:49:08.880 --> 04:49:09.419
nodded.

04:49:09.479 --> 04:49:10.619
What?

04:49:10.740 --> 04:49:12.180
Kinkachu cried.

04:49:12.240 --> 04:49:13.619
What else have you seen?

04:49:13.680 --> 04:49:14.639
Anything about me?

04:49:14.700 --> 04:49:17.220
When did you know?

04:49:17.340 --> 04:49:20.400
Kibley asked, taking a step back, away

04:49:20.400 --> 04:49:21.060
from Moon.

04:49:21.119 --> 04:49:23.520
But all those powers are supposed to be

04:49:23.520 --> 04:49:23.759
gone.

04:49:23.880 --> 04:49:25.919
So who's lying to us?

04:49:26.040 --> 04:49:27.959
The prophecy dragonettes?

04:49:28.020 --> 04:49:30.419
The Night Wings, or Moon, or all of

04:49:30.419 --> 04:49:30.540
them?

04:49:30.599 --> 04:49:32.819
About the explosion.

04:49:32.880 --> 04:49:34.680
How long did you know without telling

04:49:34.680 --> 04:49:35.099
anyone?

04:49:35.159 --> 04:49:38.639
I just saw it, Moon said.

04:49:38.700 --> 04:49:40.259
It was right before class.

04:49:40.319 --> 04:49:42.900
Sometimes the visions come months before

04:49:42.900 --> 04:49:45.419
something happens, sometimes only a few

04:49:45.419 --> 04:49:45.779
minutes.

04:49:45.840 --> 04:49:46.919
I never know.

04:49:46.919 --> 04:49:49.380
It's not like it's a helpful power.

04:49:49.439 --> 04:49:53.880
But it is, Kinkaju said, bewildered.

04:49:53.939 --> 04:49:55.919
Monkeys and mangoes.

04:49:55.979 --> 04:49:57.659
I love to be able to see the future.

04:49:57.720 --> 04:49:59.580
You saved us.

04:49:59.639 --> 04:50:03.000
Maybe she could have saved the others too

04:50:03.000 --> 04:50:04.139
Kibley thought.

04:50:04.200 --> 04:50:08.040
If she'd told us it was a vision, If we'd

04:50:08.040 --> 04:50:08.939
known what was going to happen.

04:50:09.000 --> 04:50:10.740
We could have stopped them.

04:50:10.799 --> 04:50:12.540
If she'd told the truth.

04:50:12.659 --> 04:50:14.580
If we'd known about her power

04:50:14.580 --> 04:50:15.299
beforehand.

04:50:15.360 --> 04:50:19.799
She saw Carnelian in his head, tangled up

04:50:19.799 --> 04:50:21.360
in his guilt, that he should have tried

04:50:21.360 --> 04:50:22.860
harder to stop her from going in.

04:50:22.919 --> 04:50:25.139
Would you have believed me?

04:50:25.200 --> 04:50:26.400
She asked him.

04:50:26.459 --> 04:50:28.380
If I told you I'd had a vision?

04:50:28.500 --> 04:50:33.779
I would have, Kinkajoo said, wounded, and

04:50:33.779 --> 04:50:35.939
Moon realized with a wrench of guilt that

04:50:35.939 --> 04:50:36.419
that was true.

04:50:36.540 --> 04:50:39.299
Who else knows you can do this?

04:50:39.419 --> 04:50:40.680
Kibley asked.

04:50:40.740 --> 04:50:42.840
Can all the night wings see the future?

04:50:42.900 --> 04:50:47.159
No one knows. she said, wincing as a

04:50:47.159 --> 04:50:49.080
flash of pain from her injury suddenly

04:50:49.080 --> 04:50:51.419
zigzagged from her head down to her spine

04:50:51.419 --> 04:50:54.479
and as far as I know, no one else in the

04:50:54.479 --> 04:50:55.200
tribe can do this.

04:50:55.259 --> 04:50:58.500
Apart from my secret friend, the

04:50:58.500 --> 04:51:00.659
legendary monster dark stalker, of

04:51:00.659 --> 04:51:00.840
course.

04:51:00.900 --> 04:51:02.340
Is that it?

04:51:02.400 --> 04:51:03.720
Turtle asked.

04:51:03.779 --> 04:51:05.700
Or is there anything else we should

04:51:05.700 --> 04:51:05.939
know?

04:51:06.060 --> 04:51:09.299
He inhaled sharply, looking suddenly more

04:51:09.299 --> 04:51:10.259
awake than he ever did.

04:51:10.319 --> 04:51:12.240
Can you read our minds?

04:51:12.299 --> 04:51:15.060
Kinkachu and Kibley stared at her.

04:51:15.180 --> 04:51:16.139
Their eyes wide.

04:51:16.200 --> 04:51:19.740
This is the last moment, they'll like

04:51:19.740 --> 04:51:19.860
me.

04:51:19.919 --> 04:51:22.080
This is how I lose them.

04:51:22.139 --> 04:51:25.319
Moon felt as though she was standing at

04:51:25.319 --> 04:51:27.840
the edge of a precipice, with howling

04:51:27.840 --> 04:51:29.939
winds below her waiting to smash her into

04:51:29.939 --> 04:51:32.520
the mountains, all of her mother's great

04:51:32.520 --> 04:51:35.220
fears, the whole parade of nightmares

04:51:35.220 --> 04:51:37.380
she'd been watching her entire life went

04:51:37.380 --> 04:51:39.840
marching through her head, dragons

04:51:39.840 --> 04:51:42.840
shunning her, dragons screaming at her

04:51:42.840 --> 04:51:44.880
dragons setting her on fire.

04:51:44.939 --> 04:51:48.000
Dragons locking her up, and forcing her

04:51:48.000 --> 04:51:49.200
to use her powers for them.

04:51:49.259 --> 04:51:51.840
But mostly dragons hating her.

04:51:51.900 --> 04:51:54.419
Everybody hating her forever.

04:51:54.479 --> 04:51:56.819
Just lie.

04:51:56.880 --> 04:52:00.479
Dark Stalker whispered, hold on to your

04:52:00.479 --> 04:52:01.319
one advantage.

04:52:01.380 --> 04:52:04.500
Secret, hidden.

04:52:04.619 --> 04:52:06.000
Safe.

04:52:06.119 --> 04:52:08.459
But Moon could hear what her friends were

04:52:08.459 --> 04:52:08.939
thinking too.

04:52:09.000 --> 04:52:10.740
Kibley.

04:52:10.799 --> 04:52:12.779
Won't she just lie to us?

04:52:12.840 --> 04:52:14.400
How can I trust her?

04:52:14.459 --> 04:52:16.319
How will I ever know if she's lying?

04:52:16.380 --> 04:52:19.799
And Kinkaju, the dragon who wanted to be

04:52:19.799 --> 04:52:21.180
her best friend.

04:52:21.240 --> 04:52:22.680
I believe in Moon.

04:52:22.740 --> 04:52:23.819
She'll tell us the truth.

04:52:23.880 --> 04:52:27.060
How could she be the deceitful Nightwing

04:52:27.060 --> 04:52:29.159
Winter thought she was when she had the

04:52:29.159 --> 04:52:31.080
choice to be the dragon Kinkachu saw?

04:52:31.139 --> 04:52:35.520
Yes, Moon confessed, I can read your

04:52:35.520 --> 04:52:35.880
minds.

04:52:36.000 --> 04:52:37.020
I'm sorry.

04:52:37.139 --> 04:52:39.119
She turned to Kinkachu.

04:52:39.180 --> 04:52:40.380
I'm really sorry.

04:52:40.439 --> 04:52:41.279
I can't help it.

04:52:41.340 --> 04:52:42.479
It just happens.

04:52:42.540 --> 04:52:43.500
It's always happening.

04:52:43.560 --> 04:52:44.939
I can't turn it off.

04:52:45.000 --> 04:52:47.159
Please, please don't tell anyone.

04:52:47.220 --> 04:52:50.099
Is she hearing my thoughts right now?

04:52:50.220 --> 04:52:51.779
Kibli wondered.

04:52:51.840 --> 04:52:54.479
He clearly saw the answer on her face

04:52:54.479 --> 04:52:56.159
because he took another step back.

04:52:56.220 --> 04:52:57.659
What has she heard?

04:52:57.720 --> 04:53:01.139
The pace of his thoughts incredibly sped

04:53:01.139 --> 04:53:03.479
up, as he seemed to flash through all the

04:53:03.479 --> 04:53:04.680
possible things she might have seen.

04:53:04.740 --> 04:53:07.740
All my plans to get other dragons to like

04:53:07.740 --> 04:53:07.979
me.

04:53:08.040 --> 04:53:09.959
My nightmares about my family.

04:53:10.080 --> 04:53:11.880
My thoughts about her.

04:53:11.939 --> 04:53:15.479
How many embarrassing, she must know, I

04:53:15.479 --> 04:53:17.759
can't, has she been laughing at me this

04:53:17.759 --> 04:53:18.240
whole time.

04:53:18.299 --> 04:53:20.819
No, Moon cried.

04:53:20.880 --> 04:53:21.900
I really like you.

04:53:21.959 --> 04:53:25.319
He grabbed his head, as if he was trying

04:53:25.319 --> 04:53:27.360
to keep his thoughts inside, and then

04:53:27.360 --> 04:53:28.200
flared his wings.

04:53:28.259 --> 04:53:30.720
What if I accidentally think about one of

04:53:30.720 --> 04:53:33.180
Thorn's secrets, or one of the hidden

04:53:33.180 --> 04:53:34.319
dens of the out claws?

04:53:34.380 --> 04:53:37.259
Secrets she didn't understand started

04:53:37.259 --> 04:53:38.279
spilling through his head.

04:53:38.340 --> 04:53:40.740
What if she hears some of the terrible

04:53:40.740 --> 04:53:42.419
things I think about other dragons?

04:53:42.540 --> 04:53:44.340
Who would ever like me?

04:53:44.340 --> 04:53:45.720
If they knew what I thought about

04:53:45.720 --> 04:53:46.080
everyone.

04:53:46.139 --> 04:53:48.540
Talons and tails.

04:53:48.599 --> 04:53:49.919
He mumbled.

04:53:49.979 --> 04:53:51.180
This is not okay.

04:53:51.240 --> 04:53:52.439
I have to get out of here.

04:53:52.500 --> 04:53:55.080
He turned and bolted through the cave

04:53:55.080 --> 04:53:56.939
entrance, disappearing beyond the

04:53:56.939 --> 04:53:57.479
torchlight.

04:53:57.540 --> 04:54:01.439
But I don't understand, Moon thought, half

04:54:01.439 --> 04:54:03.659
to herself, and half to dark stalker.

04:54:03.720 --> 04:54:06.119
He never thought anything more terrible

04:54:06.119 --> 04:54:07.319
than any other dragon.

04:54:07.380 --> 04:54:10.080
He's more interesting and kinder and more

04:54:10.080 --> 04:54:12.180
insightful on the inside than almost

04:54:12.180 --> 04:54:13.139
anyone else I've met.

04:54:13.200 --> 04:54:15.599
He doesn't know that.

04:54:15.720 --> 04:54:17.759
Dark Stalker pointed out.

04:54:17.819 --> 04:54:21.419
He's never seen inside anyone else, the

04:54:21.419 --> 04:54:21.900
way you have.

04:54:21.959 --> 04:54:24.720
After a few years of reading minds, you'll

04:54:24.720 --> 04:54:24.900
see.

04:54:24.959 --> 04:54:28.139
It's often the most brilliant dragons are

04:54:28.139 --> 04:54:30.840
the most insecure, and the ones who are

04:54:30.840 --> 04:54:32.939
most afraid of having their minds read

04:54:32.939 --> 04:54:34.979
because they think they must have the

04:54:34.979 --> 04:54:37.319
worst, lowest thoughts of anyone, are

04:54:37.319 --> 04:54:39.299
nowhere near as bad, as the ones who

04:54:39.299 --> 04:54:41.040
complacently don't care because they

04:54:41.040 --> 04:54:43.259
assume everyone else is as terrible as

04:54:43.259 --> 04:54:43.439
they are.

04:54:43.500 --> 04:54:46.560
Mostly everyone is terrible, by the way.

04:54:46.619 --> 04:54:50.400
I wish you'd told me, Kinkachu said.

04:54:50.459 --> 04:54:51.659
Her head was spinning.

04:54:51.720 --> 04:54:53.939
I thought she was going to be my best

04:54:53.939 --> 04:54:56.520
friend, but all along she was hiding this

04:54:56.520 --> 04:54:57.779
huge secret from me.

04:54:57.840 --> 04:55:01.439
And now Cornelian is dead, and Tamarin is

04:55:01.439 --> 04:55:03.479
hurt, and someone tried to blow us up.

04:55:03.599 --> 04:55:05.759
And there are all these grumpy dragons

04:55:05.759 --> 04:55:07.560
here, and school is nothing like I

04:55:07.560 --> 04:55:07.979
expected.

04:55:08.040 --> 04:55:09.599
I wish it was yesterday.

04:55:09.659 --> 04:55:11.340
I wish none of this had happened.

04:55:11.400 --> 04:55:13.560
I wish someone who could see the future

04:55:13.560 --> 04:55:15.959
had maybe stopped all of this from

04:55:15.959 --> 04:55:16.319
happening.

04:55:16.380 --> 04:55:20.819
I'm sorry, Moon said again, punching her

04:55:20.819 --> 04:55:21.900
shoulders miserably.

04:55:21.959 --> 04:55:23.099
I was afraid.

04:55:23.220 --> 04:55:25.619
It's not exactly the 1st thing I tell

04:55:25.619 --> 04:55:26.220
other dragons.

04:55:26.279 --> 04:55:28.200
Well, it should be.

04:55:28.259 --> 04:55:31.080
Kinkachu said, fiercely enough to make

04:55:31.080 --> 04:55:31.919
moon flinch.

04:55:31.979 --> 04:55:33.540
If you're going to be in our heads

04:55:33.540 --> 04:55:35.459
hearing everything, then you should at

04:55:35.459 --> 04:55:37.560
least warn your friends, and if you're

04:55:37.560 --> 04:55:39.959
seeing the future and it's bad, then you

04:55:39.959 --> 04:55:42.180
really have to tell someone, I don't

04:55:42.180 --> 04:55:42.659
understand you.

04:55:42.720 --> 04:55:46.560
I didn't want you to hate me, Moon said.

04:55:46.619 --> 04:55:48.959
Well, did you want me to trust you?

04:55:49.020 --> 04:55:50.700
Kinkaju demanded?

04:55:50.759 --> 04:55:52.919
Because this is the opposite of how to do

04:55:52.919 --> 04:55:53.099
that.

04:55:53.159 --> 04:55:56.040
Orange and red were starting to flicker

04:55:56.040 --> 04:55:56.639
through her scales.

04:55:56.700 --> 04:55:58.860
Why am I even bothering?

04:55:58.979 --> 04:56:00.299
She knows what I think.

04:56:00.360 --> 04:56:01.560
She can hear it all herself.

04:56:01.619 --> 04:56:04.380
I have to go check on Tamarin.

04:56:04.439 --> 04:56:06.299
I need to think the kind of thinking

04:56:06.299 --> 04:56:09.240
that's just between me and me, she added

04:56:09.240 --> 04:56:09.959
sternly.

04:56:10.020 --> 04:56:13.259
And then she was gone too, leaving Moon

04:56:13.259 --> 04:56:13.919
with Turtle.

04:56:14.040 --> 04:56:17.759
That's what happens, Dark Stalker said

04:56:17.759 --> 04:56:18.299
with a sigh.

04:56:18.360 --> 04:56:19.919
But don't worry.

04:56:19.979 --> 04:56:22.259
They'll come crawling back when they need

04:56:22.259 --> 04:56:22.500
you.

04:56:22.560 --> 04:56:25.020
I don't want them to crawl.

04:56:25.139 --> 04:56:26.939
Moon thought with a shudder.

04:56:27.000 --> 04:56:28.919
And now what do I do about winter?

04:56:28.979 --> 04:56:31.979
If Kibli and Kinkaju reacted that badly

04:56:31.979 --> 04:56:34.680
won't he hate me even more than they do?

04:56:34.740 --> 04:56:36.840
But if I don't tell him something by

04:56:36.840 --> 04:56:37.259
tomorrow?

04:56:37.319 --> 04:56:40.080
Everyone will think I set that fire.

04:56:40.200 --> 04:56:43.619
That I killed Carnelian and Big Tail.

04:56:43.680 --> 04:56:46.919
She sank to the floor, wrapped her wings

04:56:46.919 --> 04:56:49.020
around herself, and started to cry.

04:56:49.080 --> 04:56:52.619
After a moment, she felt a wing gently

04:56:52.619 --> 04:56:53.819
brush her back.

04:56:53.880 --> 04:56:56.220
Even when he was touching her, she

04:56:56.220 --> 04:56:57.900
couldn't sense anything but that quiet

04:56:57.900 --> 04:56:59.099
fuzz from Turtle.

04:56:59.159 --> 04:57:01.680
He looked down at her with his dark green

04:57:01.680 --> 04:57:01.979
eyes.

04:57:02.040 --> 04:57:03.659
Come with me.

04:57:03.720 --> 04:57:08.340
Chapter 16.

04:57:08.580 --> 04:57:12.119
It occurred to Moon, somewhere deep

04:57:12.119 --> 04:57:14.040
inside the mountain, that perhaps

04:57:14.040 --> 04:57:16.080
following Turtle off to a dark secluded

04:57:16.080 --> 04:57:17.520
spot might not be the best idea.

04:57:17.639 --> 04:57:20.400
Between the vision she'd had of him and

04:57:20.400 --> 04:57:22.560
anemone, and the fact that she had no

04:57:22.560 --> 04:57:23.580
idea what he was thinking.

04:57:23.639 --> 04:57:25.860
She suspected she probably ought to be

04:57:25.860 --> 04:57:26.400
more nervous.

04:57:26.459 --> 04:57:32.040
But his mind was so quiet, and well, cozy

04:57:32.040 --> 04:57:33.840
seemed like a strange way to describe

04:57:33.840 --> 04:57:36.060
someone's brain, but it was the best word

04:57:36.060 --> 04:57:36.419
for his.

04:57:36.479 --> 04:57:39.119
Trying to listen to it was like sinking

04:57:39.119 --> 04:57:41.880
into soft moss, muffling all the voices

04:57:41.880 --> 04:57:44.639
of the other dragons in the school, or

04:57:44.639 --> 04:57:46.259
like being underwater, she guessed.

04:57:46.319 --> 04:57:49.319
The voices got quieter anyway as they

04:57:49.319 --> 04:57:51.779
walked, putting layers of rock and space

04:57:51.779 --> 04:57:53.759
between her and the thinking going on up

04:57:53.759 --> 04:57:54.180
above.

04:57:54.240 --> 04:57:57.119
Neither of them spoke, although she could

04:57:57.119 --> 04:57:58.740
think of a 1000000 things she thought she

04:57:58.740 --> 04:57:59.340
should tell him.

04:57:59.400 --> 04:58:02.580
There were few torches down this far, but

04:58:02.580 --> 04:58:04.919
moon's eyes adjusted to the dark, and

04:58:04.919 --> 04:58:07.020
turtle scales glowed just enough for them

04:58:07.020 --> 04:58:08.520
to see the floor beneath their talons.

04:58:08.580 --> 04:58:11.340
Here and there she saw slick, glowing

04:58:11.340 --> 04:58:14.099
trails along the rocks, and after a while

04:58:14.099 --> 04:58:15.840
she realized they were left by

04:58:15.840 --> 04:58:18.599
luminescent snails as long as her claws.

04:58:18.659 --> 04:58:21.720
Soon after that, she noticed a faint

04:58:21.720 --> 04:58:24.540
dripping sound up ahead, and then, all at

04:58:24.540 --> 04:58:27.000
once, the passage opened up into a huge

04:58:27.000 --> 04:58:29.880
cavern, studded with stalactites

04:58:29.880 --> 04:58:32.220
shimmering with glow worms, and

04:58:32.220 --> 04:58:34.259
surrounding an enormous underground

04:58:34.259 --> 04:58:34.619
lake.

04:58:34.680 --> 04:58:37.860
Oh, moon whispered.

04:58:37.919 --> 04:58:40.259
At 1st she thought there were glow worms

04:58:40.259 --> 04:58:41.040
in the water too.

04:58:41.099 --> 04:58:43.680
And then she realized she was seeing the

04:58:43.680 --> 04:58:45.180
reflections of stars.

04:58:45.240 --> 04:58:48.479
Far above them was a hole in the roof, big

04:58:48.479 --> 04:58:50.159
enough for a dragon to fly through with

04:58:50.159 --> 04:58:52.439
her wings outstretched, big enough for

04:58:52.439 --> 04:58:54.599
the moons to shine through, casting

04:58:54.599 --> 04:58:56.580
broken silvery green light across the

04:58:56.580 --> 04:58:57.119
still water.

04:58:57.180 --> 04:58:59.700
Two of the moons were visible through the

04:58:59.700 --> 04:59:02.880
hole, half full, and swathed with clouds

04:59:02.880 --> 04:59:04.200
in the growing twilight.

04:59:04.380 --> 04:59:06.900
Moon looked around for pike and tamarind

04:59:06.900 --> 04:59:09.180
but although a faint burnt smell still

04:59:09.180 --> 04:59:11.400
hung in the air, there was no sign of the

04:59:11.400 --> 04:59:13.560
injured rain wing or the dragon's taking

04:59:13.560 --> 04:59:15.959
care of her, they must have immersed her

04:59:15.959 --> 04:59:17.400
and then taken her to the healing cave.

04:59:17.459 --> 04:59:19.799
Turtle nodded at the lake.

04:59:19.860 --> 04:59:22.020
You should wash your shoulder.

04:59:22.080 --> 04:59:25.380
I take you to the infirmary, but I

04:59:25.380 --> 04:59:27.419
imagine Clay is busy with Tamarin right

04:59:27.419 --> 04:59:27.599
now.

04:59:27.659 --> 04:59:30.419
It had started to hurt in earnest while

04:59:30.419 --> 04:59:31.259
they were walking.

04:59:31.319 --> 04:59:34.020
Moon peered at it again, then slowly

04:59:34.020 --> 04:59:35.159
edged into the lake.

04:59:35.220 --> 04:59:37.740
The water was colder than she'd expected

04:59:37.740 --> 04:59:40.919
sliding around and under her scales, and

04:59:40.919 --> 04:59:42.959
when it hit her wound, she yelped with

04:59:42.959 --> 04:59:43.139
shock.

04:59:43.200 --> 04:59:46.200
There was a small splash as turtle dove

04:59:46.200 --> 04:59:47.220
into the lake beside her.

04:59:47.279 --> 04:59:49.680
He surfaced and studied her shoulder as

04:59:49.680 --> 04:59:52.020
she gingerly dipped it under, washing off

04:59:52.020 --> 04:59:52.619
the dried blood.

04:59:52.680 --> 04:59:55.619
It started to bleed again, but after a

04:59:55.619 --> 04:59:57.479
minute it stopped, and she could see the

04:59:57.479 --> 04:59:59.099
prickly thing stuck in it more clearly.

04:59:59.159 --> 05:00:01.319
This might hurt.

05:00:01.380 --> 05:00:04.500
Turtle said, and without any more warning

05:00:04.500 --> 05:00:06.840
than that, he pincered his claws around

05:00:06.840 --> 05:00:08.520
the object and yanked it out of the

05:00:08.520 --> 05:00:08.819
wound.

05:00:08.880 --> 05:00:10.319
Ow!

05:00:10.439 --> 05:00:11.400
Moon cried.

05:00:11.520 --> 05:00:13.919
Turtle pressed his talons to her shoulder

05:00:13.919 --> 05:00:15.840
as another spurt of blood fountained

05:00:15.840 --> 05:00:16.020
out.

05:00:16.080 --> 05:00:18.720
She felt a little faint, and caught

05:00:18.720 --> 05:00:20.700
herself, wondering what he would do if

05:00:20.700 --> 05:00:21.959
she collapsed here in the lake.

05:00:22.020 --> 05:00:23.520
Would he leave her to drown?

05:00:23.580 --> 05:00:26.880
He lifted his claws, checked that the

05:00:26.880 --> 05:00:28.860
blood had stopped, and then dipped his

05:00:28.860 --> 05:00:30.119
talons in the leg to wash them off.

05:00:30.180 --> 05:00:32.939
He was still holding the strange object

05:00:32.939 --> 05:00:34.680
and now he rinsed it off and peered at

05:00:34.680 --> 05:00:34.860
it.

05:00:34.919 --> 05:00:36.779
What is that?

05:00:36.900 --> 05:00:39.599
Moon asked, scooping water over her

05:00:39.599 --> 05:00:40.380
shoulder.

05:00:40.439 --> 05:00:42.180
She could see that it was a blackish

05:00:42.180 --> 05:00:44.459
brown, misshapen sphere, about the size

05:00:44.459 --> 05:00:46.860
of a rainforest frog, and covered in

05:00:46.860 --> 05:00:48.240
those sharp thorns.

05:00:48.299 --> 05:00:52.139
I think I know, he said, but I should

05:00:52.139 --> 05:00:53.939
look at it in better light, and maybe

05:00:53.939 --> 05:00:54.779
check the library.

05:00:54.840 --> 05:00:56.520
How's your shoulder?

05:00:56.580 --> 05:00:57.540
Can you fly?

05:00:57.659 --> 05:01:00.479
Probably, Moon said.

05:01:00.540 --> 05:01:02.880
She glanced up at the moons shining

05:01:02.880 --> 05:01:04.740
through the hole in the roof, and caught

05:01:04.740 --> 05:01:06.900
herself wishing she could fly all the way

05:01:06.900 --> 05:01:08.700
to one of them and just stay there

05:01:08.700 --> 05:01:11.400
surrounded by silver and silence.

05:01:11.459 --> 05:01:13.619
Go ahead and try.

05:01:13.740 --> 05:01:15.180
He suggested.

05:01:15.240 --> 05:01:18.419
She knew he meant try flying, but she

05:01:18.419 --> 05:01:20.700
looked into his unreadable eyes and

05:01:20.700 --> 05:01:22.080
wondered if he was offering her the

05:01:22.080 --> 05:01:22.799
chance to escape.

05:01:22.860 --> 05:01:25.619
She could be out that hole and on her way

05:01:25.619 --> 05:01:28.020
to the rainforest in no time, or even

05:01:28.020 --> 05:01:28.439
farther.

05:01:28.500 --> 05:01:30.479
She could run to somewhere where winter

05:01:30.479 --> 05:01:32.580
wouldn't be able to track her down and

05:01:32.580 --> 05:01:34.200
scrape out all her secrets.

05:01:34.259 --> 05:01:36.840
But then he'd really believe I did it.

05:01:36.900 --> 05:01:38.340
And so would everyone.

05:01:38.400 --> 05:01:40.080
Why else would I run away?

05:01:40.139 --> 05:01:43.560
Moon hesitated for a moment, then took to

05:01:43.560 --> 05:01:45.900
the air, soaring over the lake and

05:01:45.900 --> 05:01:46.979
circling in the moonlight.

05:01:47.040 --> 05:01:49.560
Her shoulder hurt, but she could still

05:01:49.560 --> 05:01:50.099
move her wings.

05:01:50.159 --> 05:01:52.560
The silvery touch of the moons on her

05:01:52.560 --> 05:01:54.959
scales calmed her a little, but then she

05:01:54.959 --> 05:01:57.180
remembered Winter's furious expression

05:01:57.180 --> 05:01:58.439
and felt sick all over again.

05:01:58.500 --> 05:02:01.979
She swooped around in an arc, watching

05:02:01.979 --> 05:02:03.299
turtles swim below her.

05:02:03.360 --> 05:02:05.880
Will they tell everyone my secret?

05:02:06.000 --> 05:02:08.340
I guess there's nothing I can do to stop

05:02:08.340 --> 05:02:09.659
them if they decide to do that.

05:02:09.720 --> 05:02:12.659
Do I wish I didn't have this power?

05:02:12.720 --> 05:02:14.759
If I couldn't read minds?

05:02:14.819 --> 05:02:17.220
Everyone I met would be like turtle

05:02:17.220 --> 05:02:18.840
completely unreadable.

05:02:18.900 --> 05:02:20.939
Strange and blank.

05:02:21.000 --> 05:02:23.459
I'd have no way to know if they were kind

05:02:23.459 --> 05:02:24.659
or cruel.

05:02:24.720 --> 05:02:27.299
I'd never understand why they act the way

05:02:27.299 --> 05:02:27.779
they do.

05:02:27.840 --> 05:02:30.119
Everyone would be all surface.

05:02:30.180 --> 05:02:32.759
I'd think winter was just mean.

05:02:32.819 --> 05:02:35.759
I would know about his dead brother. and

05:02:35.759 --> 05:02:37.200
how he hates himself more than anyone

05:02:37.200 --> 05:02:37.500
else.

05:02:37.560 --> 05:02:40.740
I might think Kibley was just goofy and

05:02:40.740 --> 05:02:43.319
ordinary if I didn't know about his lairs

05:02:43.319 --> 05:02:45.900
and his amazing mind and his childhood.

05:02:45.959 --> 05:02:49.200
I'd have stayed away from Kinkaju, because

05:02:49.200 --> 05:02:50.700
I wouldn't have known or believed that

05:02:50.700 --> 05:02:51.540
she really liked me.

05:02:51.599 --> 05:02:54.779
I guess that's how other dragons live

05:02:54.779 --> 05:02:57.240
never knowing how complicated everyone

05:02:57.240 --> 05:02:57.779
else is.

05:02:57.840 --> 05:03:00.720
That's what it would be like to be

05:03:00.720 --> 05:03:01.080
normal.

05:03:01.139 --> 05:03:04.259
But if I could choose, would I want

05:03:04.259 --> 05:03:04.500
that?

05:03:04.560 --> 05:03:07.919
And since I can't choose, should I run

05:03:07.919 --> 05:03:10.200
away from what I can do, or risk

05:03:10.200 --> 05:03:11.580
revealing it to dragons who won't

05:03:11.580 --> 05:03:11.939
understand.

05:03:12.000 --> 05:03:16.080
Moon tilted her wings and sailed down

05:03:16.080 --> 05:03:18.180
until she landed on a craggy boulder that

05:03:18.180 --> 05:03:20.819
jutted out of the lake, spongy, bluish

05:03:20.819 --> 05:03:23.099
moss clung to its sides and squelched

05:03:23.099 --> 05:03:23.819
under her claws.

05:03:23.880 --> 05:03:26.700
Turtles swam over and clambered up beside

05:03:26.700 --> 05:03:26.880
her.

05:03:26.939 --> 05:03:29.400
How did you find this place?

05:03:29.459 --> 05:03:30.180
Moon asked.

05:03:30.240 --> 05:03:31.560
He shrugged.

05:03:31.619 --> 05:03:33.599
I went exploring.

05:03:33.659 --> 05:03:36.360
There are a couple of underground lakes

05:03:36.360 --> 05:03:38.700
but this is the biggest, and the only one

05:03:38.700 --> 05:03:39.540
with a view of the sky.

05:03:39.599 --> 05:03:42.479
He leaned back to look up at the visible

05:03:42.479 --> 05:03:42.959
moons.

05:03:43.020 --> 05:03:45.060
Moon studied him for a minute.

05:03:45.119 --> 05:03:47.040
I don't know him at all.

05:03:47.099 --> 05:03:51.479
So, he said slowly, without meeting her

05:03:51.479 --> 05:03:54.599
eyes, I guess you must know my secret.

05:03:54.659 --> 05:03:59.279
No, she said, stopping him before he

05:03:59.279 --> 05:04:00.119
could say too much.

05:04:00.180 --> 05:04:03.240
She was desperately curious, but she

05:04:03.240 --> 05:04:04.139
didn't want to trick him.

05:04:04.200 --> 05:04:07.439
Turtle, I, I don't know why.

05:04:07.560 --> 05:04:09.479
But I can't read your mind.

05:04:09.540 --> 05:04:11.580
With a few dragons.

05:04:11.639 --> 05:04:12.599
I just don't hear anything.

05:04:12.659 --> 05:04:15.479
He gave her a startled expression.

05:04:15.540 --> 05:04:17.759
Like there's nothing in there?

05:04:17.819 --> 05:04:20.340
It's not crinkled, amused.

05:04:20.400 --> 05:04:21.779
That's alarming.

05:04:21.840 --> 05:04:23.700
What are you saying about me?

05:04:23.759 --> 05:04:27.240
I'm saying you're safe, Moon said.

05:04:27.299 --> 05:04:28.799
Your secrets are safe.

05:04:28.860 --> 05:04:30.779
I can't hear your thoughts.

05:04:30.840 --> 05:04:33.659
She hesitated, wondering if she should

05:04:33.659 --> 05:04:35.220
mention the vision about anemone.

05:04:35.279 --> 05:04:36.779
Something made her hold back.

05:04:36.840 --> 05:04:39.360
Oh, Turtle said.

05:04:39.419 --> 05:04:41.279
Awesome, I think.

05:04:41.340 --> 05:04:43.619
He thought for a moment, then shook his

05:04:43.619 --> 05:04:43.799
head.

05:04:43.860 --> 05:04:46.259
I'm not very interesting anyway.

05:04:46.319 --> 05:04:48.599
I'm sure that's not true.

05:04:48.659 --> 05:04:50.099
Moon thought.

05:04:50.159 --> 05:04:52.799
Thanks for letting me keep my secrets

05:04:52.799 --> 05:04:55.799
then. he said, giving her an easy smile.

05:04:55.919 --> 05:04:58.319
So what are you going to do about

05:04:58.319 --> 05:04:58.680
winter?

05:04:58.740 --> 05:05:01.799
Moon decker talons into the rock.

05:05:01.860 --> 05:05:04.319
Her stomach hurt, and she had this

05:05:04.319 --> 05:05:05.880
horrible, prickling, tense feeling

05:05:05.880 --> 05:05:08.340
everywhere, as if she might erupt out of

05:05:08.340 --> 05:05:09.180
her scales.

05:05:09.240 --> 05:05:11.400
She made herself lie down on the boulder

05:05:11.400 --> 05:05:13.919
and reached to drag one claw through the

05:05:13.919 --> 05:05:14.580
pool below her.

05:05:14.639 --> 05:05:18.000
I guess I have to tell him the truth, she

05:05:18.000 --> 05:05:18.599
said finally.

05:05:18.659 --> 05:05:21.959
Not if you don't want to, Turtle said.

05:05:22.080 --> 05:05:24.180
Why don't you figure out who really

05:05:24.180 --> 05:05:26.639
caused the explosion and tell him that

05:05:26.639 --> 05:05:27.060
instead?

05:05:27.180 --> 05:05:30.060
Moon gave him a bemused look.

05:05:30.119 --> 05:05:31.439
Oh, all right.

05:05:31.500 --> 05:05:33.479
I'll just go solve that mystery by

05:05:33.479 --> 05:05:34.259
midnight tomorrow.

05:05:34.319 --> 05:05:35.040
No problem.

05:05:35.099 --> 05:05:37.799
He shoved her off the rock and she landed

05:05:37.799 --> 05:05:40.139
with a splash, coming back up startled

05:05:40.139 --> 05:05:40.740
and sputtering.

05:05:40.799 --> 05:05:42.419
What was that for?

05:05:42.479 --> 05:05:43.619
she cried.

05:05:43.740 --> 05:05:45.599
You're a mind reader.

05:05:45.720 --> 05:05:46.799
He reminded her.

05:05:46.860 --> 05:05:49.139
All you have to do is walk around the

05:05:49.139 --> 05:05:50.639
school until you hear someone's mind

05:05:50.639 --> 05:05:52.380
going, well done me.

05:05:52.439 --> 05:05:54.419
Tiptop explosion I caused today.

05:05:54.479 --> 05:05:56.459
Aren't I a clever arsonist?

05:05:56.520 --> 05:05:58.619
It's not exactly that easy.

05:05:58.680 --> 05:06:01.560
Moon said, spreading our wings to stay

05:06:01.560 --> 05:06:03.360
afloat, and shivering in the chilly

05:06:03.360 --> 05:06:03.599
lake.

05:06:03.659 --> 05:06:05.639
It's really noisy out there.

05:06:05.700 --> 05:06:06.900
You have no idea.

05:06:06.959 --> 05:06:09.119
And you're not the only dragon who can

05:06:09.119 --> 05:06:10.080
shield his thoughts from me.

05:06:10.139 --> 05:06:12.060
What if it was someone like that?

05:06:12.119 --> 05:06:13.560
Someone like you.

05:06:13.619 --> 05:06:18.299
Well, it wasn't me, he said, not sounding

05:06:18.299 --> 05:06:19.259
the slightest bit offended.

05:06:19.380 --> 05:06:21.479
So anyone else you can't hear.

05:06:21.599 --> 05:06:24.180
Put them on your list of suspects and

05:06:24.180 --> 05:06:25.799
keep listening to everyone else in the

05:06:25.799 --> 05:06:26.279
meanwhile.

05:06:26.340 --> 05:06:27.540
Why wouldn't you?

05:06:27.599 --> 05:06:30.119
You could figure this out in an hour if

05:06:30.119 --> 05:06:31.259
you just hear the right dragon.

05:06:31.319 --> 05:06:34.080
And if they're thinking about it when I

05:06:34.080 --> 05:06:37.319
do hear them, Moon said, she climbed back

05:06:37.319 --> 05:06:38.819
onto the boulder and shook the water off

05:06:38.819 --> 05:06:39.299
her wings.

05:06:39.360 --> 05:06:42.240
But if it were that easy, I should have

05:06:42.240 --> 05:06:44.220
heard them planning it, I should have

05:06:44.220 --> 05:06:45.659
heard something from someone.

05:06:45.779 --> 05:06:49.139
She stopped, realizing she had.

05:06:49.200 --> 05:06:51.959
The conversation with a dream visitor

05:06:51.959 --> 05:06:54.779
planning to kill someone, multiple

05:06:54.779 --> 05:06:57.180
someone's, she couldn't believe she'd

05:06:57.180 --> 05:06:59.279
forgotten about that, even in the chaos

05:06:59.279 --> 05:07:01.740
of the explosion, was the fire in the

05:07:01.740 --> 05:07:04.380
history cave the plan she'd overheard?

05:07:04.439 --> 05:07:07.500
And if so, then perhaps the dragon with a

05:07:07.500 --> 05:07:10.380
dream visitor, Queen Scarlet, would

05:07:10.380 --> 05:07:12.180
return tonight to find out if it worked.

05:07:12.240 --> 05:07:14.159
Maybe there'd be another conversation

05:07:14.159 --> 05:07:16.799
between killers in the dark, under the

05:07:16.799 --> 05:07:17.520
cover of dreams.

05:07:17.580 --> 05:07:19.919
And if Moon was listening at the right

05:07:19.919 --> 05:07:22.500
time, maybe, she'd have a chance to catch

05:07:22.500 --> 05:07:22.860
them.

05:07:22.919 --> 05:07:27.540
Chapter 17.

05:07:27.720 --> 05:07:31.259
I have to get back to my sleeping cave

05:07:31.259 --> 05:07:33.119
Moon said, leaping to her feet and

05:07:33.119 --> 05:07:34.259
slipping on the wet stone.

05:07:34.319 --> 05:07:36.659
Oh, Turtle said.

05:07:36.720 --> 05:07:37.680
Uh, sure.

05:07:37.740 --> 05:07:39.299
Did you figure something out?

05:07:39.360 --> 05:07:41.639
I hope so, she said.

05:07:41.700 --> 05:07:42.959
Can you lead me back?

05:07:43.020 --> 05:07:45.959
As they hurried up the tunnel, leaving

05:07:45.959 --> 05:07:47.279
wet footprints behind them.

05:07:47.340 --> 05:07:49.680
She told him about the conversation she'd

05:07:49.680 --> 05:07:50.639
heard 2 nights ago.

05:07:50.700 --> 05:07:53.400
I wonder if I should tell someone, she

05:07:53.400 --> 05:07:54.180
said nervously.

05:07:54.240 --> 05:07:56.159
Like Starflight or Sonny?

05:07:56.159 --> 05:07:57.119
Or...

05:07:57.119 --> 05:07:58.439
Tsunami?

05:07:58.560 --> 05:08:01.020
She shivered all the way to her toes at

05:08:01.020 --> 05:08:02.220
the thought of trying to tell the

05:08:02.220 --> 05:08:04.020
ferocious sea wing something like this.

05:08:04.080 --> 05:08:07.380
I don't think so, he said.

05:08:07.439 --> 05:08:09.959
I say keep it to yourself until you know

05:08:09.959 --> 05:08:10.200
more.

05:08:10.259 --> 05:08:13.979
You never know how someone will shh.

05:08:14.040 --> 05:08:16.319
Moon put out her tail to stop him from

05:08:16.319 --> 05:08:16.680
moving.

05:08:16.740 --> 05:08:18.959
They were near the history cave again.

05:08:19.020 --> 05:08:21.360
The lingering smell of smoke filled the

05:08:21.360 --> 05:08:23.580
air, along with a deep chill from all the

05:08:23.580 --> 05:08:25.259
frost breath winter had sprayed.

05:08:25.319 --> 05:08:28.080
The corpses of Big Tail and carnelian

05:08:28.080 --> 05:08:30.540
were gone, leaving dark imprints on the

05:08:30.540 --> 05:08:32.759
ash covered floor, surrounded by the

05:08:32.759 --> 05:08:35.400
marks of several talons. someone was in

05:08:35.400 --> 05:08:37.380
the cave, poking through the ashes.

05:08:37.439 --> 05:08:40.380
She could sense 2 dragons arguing.

05:08:40.439 --> 05:08:43.139
She motioned to Turtle to stay quiet, and

05:08:43.139 --> 05:08:44.580
they crept forward until they could hear

05:08:44.580 --> 05:08:45.299
the voices clearly.

05:08:45.360 --> 05:08:48.360
We'll use the dream visitor to tell glory

05:08:48.360 --> 05:08:48.659
tonight.

05:08:48.720 --> 05:08:50.939
She needs to know about Bigtail at

05:08:50.939 --> 05:08:51.119
least.

05:08:51.180 --> 05:08:53.580
But maybe she can also tell us what to

05:08:53.580 --> 05:08:53.819
do.

05:08:53.880 --> 05:08:55.560
It was sunny.

05:08:55.619 --> 05:08:57.900
All her thoughts twisted in a knot of

05:08:57.900 --> 05:08:59.819
guilt and grief and distress.

05:08:59.880 --> 05:09:03.419
I'm the head of school, tsunami said.

05:09:03.479 --> 05:09:04.680
I can tell you what to do.

05:09:04.740 --> 05:09:07.259
That's my job and my favorite thing in

05:09:07.259 --> 05:09:07.560
life.

05:09:07.619 --> 05:09:08.400
I mean, seriously.

05:09:08.459 --> 05:09:11.400
She was trying to break the tension, but

05:09:11.400 --> 05:09:12.360
Sonny was barely listening.

05:09:12.479 --> 05:09:14.759
Should we shut down the school?

05:09:14.819 --> 05:09:15.959
Send everyone home?

05:09:16.020 --> 05:09:19.979
That's what she wants, tsunami said

05:09:19.979 --> 05:09:22.380
fiercely, her mind bristling like it was

05:09:22.380 --> 05:09:23.040
full of spears.

05:09:23.099 --> 05:09:25.439
Moon heard her pick up a piece of debris

05:09:25.439 --> 05:09:26.520
and throw it at the wall.

05:09:26.580 --> 05:09:29.459
Sonny, you know Queen Scarlet must have

05:09:29.459 --> 05:09:30.299
been behind this.

05:09:30.360 --> 05:09:32.639
She's trying to destroy this great thing

05:09:32.639 --> 05:09:34.560
we're building, and we won't let her.

05:09:34.619 --> 05:09:37.979
But what if she hurts more students?

05:09:38.040 --> 05:09:39.000
And who's working with her?

05:09:39.060 --> 05:09:41.459
And how can we stop her if we can't find

05:09:41.459 --> 05:09:41.880
her?

05:09:41.939 --> 05:09:43.860
And how can we keep them all safe?

05:09:43.919 --> 05:09:45.959
Sonny's voice broke.

05:09:46.020 --> 05:09:48.659
We'll catch the dragon who did this

05:09:48.659 --> 05:09:50.040
tsunami said.

05:09:50.099 --> 05:09:51.299
I promise, sonny.

05:09:51.419 --> 05:09:53.340
I will rip them apart myself.

05:09:53.400 --> 05:09:56.040
I should send a message to Queen Ruby

05:09:56.040 --> 05:09:56.939
about Carnelian.

05:09:57.000 --> 05:09:59.939
Sonny said, watching the ashes of a map

05:09:59.939 --> 05:10:01.259
crumble under her claws.

05:10:01.319 --> 05:10:04.380
Maybe we should notify all the queens, in

05:10:04.380 --> 05:10:05.819
case any of them want to withdraw their

05:10:05.819 --> 05:10:06.180
students.

05:10:06.240 --> 05:10:08.580
Tsunami groaned.

05:10:08.700 --> 05:10:10.919
That means my mother will be here by

05:10:10.919 --> 05:10:13.259
sunrise, and Anemone will be gone 20

05:10:13.259 --> 05:10:13.799
seconds later.

05:10:13.860 --> 05:10:16.380
How did it start?

05:10:16.439 --> 05:10:17.340
Sonny wondered.

05:10:17.459 --> 05:10:19.799
There was a shuffling noise as she came

05:10:19.799 --> 05:10:20.819
closer to the entrance.

05:10:20.880 --> 05:10:24.060
Umber said there was an explosion.

05:10:24.119 --> 05:10:26.040
And it must have been something near the

05:10:26.040 --> 05:10:27.900
doorway where carnelian was.

05:10:28.020 --> 05:10:29.459
Tsunami.

05:10:29.520 --> 05:10:30.659
What's this?

05:10:30.720 --> 05:10:33.959
Out in the tunnel, Moon and Turtle

05:10:33.959 --> 05:10:35.580
exchanged glances.

05:10:35.639 --> 05:10:38.819
I don't know, tsunami said, but I know I

05:10:38.819 --> 05:10:39.299
hate them.

05:10:39.360 --> 05:10:41.580
There are others all over the floor

05:10:41.580 --> 05:10:43.200
buried in the ash.

05:10:43.259 --> 05:10:45.060
I've already been stabbed a few times, and

05:10:45.060 --> 05:10:46.139
it's like they have teeth.

05:10:46.200 --> 05:10:48.540
I practically have to dig them out of my

05:10:48.540 --> 05:10:48.959
scales.

05:10:49.020 --> 05:10:50.939
No, don't give it to me.

05:10:51.000 --> 05:10:52.500
It'll just attack me like the others

05:10:52.500 --> 05:10:52.799
did.

05:10:52.860 --> 05:10:55.799
Turtle held out the little ball of thorns

05:10:55.799 --> 05:10:56.819
and gave Moon a look.

05:10:56.880 --> 05:10:58.020
She nodded.

05:10:58.080 --> 05:10:59.700
Guessing it was the same kind of thing

05:10:59.700 --> 05:11:01.380
Sunny and Tsunami had found.

05:11:01.439 --> 05:11:03.540
Apparently that wasn't quite what the

05:11:03.540 --> 05:11:05.459
look meant, though, because he nodded

05:11:05.459 --> 05:11:06.900
back and then stepped right into the

05:11:06.900 --> 05:11:07.560
history cave.

05:11:07.619 --> 05:11:10.319
Moon jumped back, startled, and then

05:11:10.319 --> 05:11:10.919
hurried after him.

05:11:10.979 --> 05:11:13.560
That would have been a useful moment for

05:11:13.560 --> 05:11:15.479
mind reading, she thought to herself.

05:11:15.540 --> 05:11:18.180
She would have voted for staying hidden

05:11:18.180 --> 05:11:19.139
that it was too late for that.

05:11:19.200 --> 05:11:22.139
Tsunami and Sunny whirled around and

05:11:22.139 --> 05:11:22.860
blinked at them.

05:11:22.919 --> 05:11:25.500
Turtle, tsunami said.

05:11:25.560 --> 05:11:26.040
You shouldn't?

05:11:26.159 --> 05:11:28.919
Hey, sorry, he said.

05:11:28.979 --> 05:11:32.520
We heard what you were saying, and I

05:11:32.520 --> 05:11:33.659
might know what this is.

05:11:33.779 --> 05:11:36.599
Turtle held up the thorn ball, which

05:11:36.599 --> 05:11:38.279
matched the one in Sonny's palm.

05:11:38.340 --> 05:11:41.040
Moon tried to take shallow breath.

05:11:41.099 --> 05:11:42.959
The air in here smelled worse than

05:11:42.959 --> 05:11:43.319
smoke.

05:11:43.380 --> 05:11:46.439
It smelled like scorched dragon flesh.

05:11:46.500 --> 05:11:48.240
It was colder too.

05:11:48.299 --> 05:11:50.819
This close to the melting film of frost

05:11:50.819 --> 05:11:51.240
breath.

05:11:51.299 --> 05:11:54.060
The ashes drifting over her claws were

05:11:54.060 --> 05:11:54.900
heavy and damp.

05:11:54.959 --> 05:11:57.180
They got in between her scales and stuck

05:11:57.180 --> 05:11:58.979
to her wings like insidious gray

05:11:58.979 --> 05:11:59.819
cobwebs.

05:11:59.880 --> 05:12:01.979
It was horrible in every way.

05:12:02.040 --> 05:12:05.520
Horrible too, to hear the instant flare

05:12:05.520 --> 05:12:07.740
of suspicion from tsunami's mind.

05:12:07.799 --> 05:12:09.000
What is Moon doing here?

05:12:09.060 --> 05:12:10.860
Why was she listening to us?

05:12:10.919 --> 05:12:14.279
Sonny's reaction was less suspicious, but

05:12:14.279 --> 05:12:15.840
perhaps only because she was too tired

05:12:15.840 --> 05:12:17.099
and worried to think of it.

05:12:17.159 --> 05:12:19.680
Yeah, what are those?

05:12:19.740 --> 05:12:21.419
Tsunami asked her brother.

05:12:21.479 --> 05:12:23.099
And where'd you get that one?

05:12:23.159 --> 05:12:26.220
Moon got hid by it when the explosion

05:12:26.220 --> 05:12:28.799
went off. he said, pointing to the wound

05:12:28.799 --> 05:12:29.340
on her shoulder.

05:12:29.400 --> 05:12:31.799
I'm pretty sure I've seen these before.

05:12:31.860 --> 05:12:34.619
After the attack on the Summer Palace.

05:12:34.680 --> 05:12:36.900
We found things like it on several of the

05:12:36.900 --> 05:12:38.340
surviving sea wings.

05:12:38.459 --> 05:12:40.860
He turned the ball over and cut into it

05:12:40.860 --> 05:12:43.200
with one of his claws, revealing a bright

05:12:43.200 --> 05:12:44.040
green interior.

05:12:44.099 --> 05:12:46.319
It's a seed pod.

05:12:46.380 --> 05:12:49.020
It comes from something called a dragon

05:12:49.020 --> 05:12:51.840
flame cactus, which grows only in high

05:12:51.840 --> 05:12:53.819
altitudes in the mountains.

05:12:53.880 --> 05:12:55.740
How did you figure that out?

05:12:55.799 --> 05:12:57.000
Sonny asked.

05:12:57.060 --> 05:13:00.360
My mother tortured a Skywing prisoner

05:13:00.360 --> 05:13:01.500
until he told us.

05:13:01.560 --> 05:13:03.360
Turtles said matter of factly.

05:13:03.419 --> 05:13:06.000
Sunny and tsunami both winced.

05:13:06.060 --> 05:13:09.060
He said the Sky Wings use the cactized

05:13:09.060 --> 05:13:11.220
bombs, because when they come into

05:13:11.220 --> 05:13:14.580
contact with fire, They explode, sending

05:13:14.580 --> 05:13:17.040
fiery bits of cactus and seed pods

05:13:17.040 --> 05:13:17.279
everywhere.

05:13:17.340 --> 05:13:20.580
I think the idea is that if you tried to

05:13:20.580 --> 05:13:22.319
exterminate them by burning them all

05:13:22.319 --> 05:13:24.659
they'd 1st of all attack you back.

05:13:24.720 --> 05:13:27.720
And 2nd of all, release all these seeds

05:13:27.720 --> 05:13:30.000
so that a 100 more cacti would grow from

05:13:30.000 --> 05:13:30.479
the ashes.

05:13:30.540 --> 05:13:33.599
Kind of a cool evolutionary thing that

05:13:33.599 --> 05:13:36.240
makes sense if you're a plant trying to

05:13:36.240 --> 05:13:37.680
survive on a mountain full of fire

05:13:37.680 --> 05:13:39.000
breathing dragons, right?

05:13:39.060 --> 05:13:41.939
He looked up and caught the expressions

05:13:41.939 --> 05:13:42.659
on their faces.

05:13:42.720 --> 05:13:45.840
But, uh, horrible, obviously.

05:13:45.900 --> 05:13:49.740
So it's a sky wing weapon, tsunami said.

05:13:49.799 --> 05:13:51.299
She studied the floor.

05:13:51.360 --> 05:13:54.240
Probably set with some kind of long views

05:13:54.240 --> 05:13:56.459
slowly burning until it reached the

05:13:56.459 --> 05:13:58.319
cactus, hidden somehow.

05:13:58.319 --> 05:13:59.459
Hmm.

05:13:59.520 --> 05:14:02.639
You think one of our Skywing students did

05:14:02.639 --> 05:14:03.000
this?

05:14:03.060 --> 05:14:05.520
Sonny said, running through the list in

05:14:05.520 --> 05:14:06.000
her head.

05:14:06.060 --> 05:14:08.700
Flame is pretty angry the whole world.

05:14:08.759 --> 05:14:11.400
Fate speaker and glory were both worried

05:14:11.400 --> 05:14:12.599
about his aggression problems.

05:14:12.659 --> 05:14:15.299
But he's more the type to lose his temper

05:14:15.299 --> 05:14:17.939
and start a fight over prey, not plan to

05:14:17.939 --> 05:14:18.959
set a fire from a distance.

05:14:19.080 --> 05:14:22.740
Or someone who is told what to do by a

05:14:22.740 --> 05:14:24.900
Sky Wing, tsunami pointed out.

05:14:24.959 --> 05:14:27.840
A sky wing like Queen Scarlet, for

05:14:27.840 --> 05:14:28.259
instance.

05:14:28.380 --> 05:14:33.000
She paused, then added, or there is

05:14:33.000 --> 05:14:34.080
another sky wing here.

05:14:34.139 --> 05:14:36.000
One who's betrayed us before.

05:14:36.060 --> 05:14:38.639
Sunny was already shaking her head.

05:14:38.700 --> 05:14:40.500
It couldn't be peril.

05:14:40.560 --> 05:14:42.060
Why not?

05:14:42.180 --> 05:14:43.200
Tsunami said.

05:14:43.259 --> 05:14:45.180
We don't know what she's capable of.

05:14:45.240 --> 05:14:49.319
No, I mean it couldn't be, Sonny said.

05:14:49.380 --> 05:14:51.119
She couldn't touch a cactus like this

05:14:51.119 --> 05:14:52.020
without it blowing up.

05:14:52.080 --> 05:14:52.919
Think about it.

05:14:52.979 --> 05:14:55.319
Tsunami frowned, then snorted

05:14:55.319 --> 05:14:55.860
grudgingly.

05:14:55.919 --> 05:14:58.020
I hate it when you're smarter than me.

05:14:58.080 --> 05:15:00.840
Sonny suddenly seemed to remember that

05:15:00.840 --> 05:15:02.040
Moon and Turtle were there.

05:15:02.099 --> 05:15:04.680
You should go back to your sleeping caves

05:15:04.680 --> 05:15:05.279
she said.

05:15:05.340 --> 05:15:07.439
We've told everyone to stay there until

05:15:07.439 --> 05:15:08.639
we figure out what to do next.

05:15:08.700 --> 05:15:11.700
Oh, I shouldn't have let them hear me

05:15:11.700 --> 05:15:12.299
speculate.

05:15:12.360 --> 05:15:13.740
What if they tell everyone?

05:15:13.799 --> 05:15:16.080
I keep forgetting to act like I'm in

05:15:16.080 --> 05:15:17.279
charge instead of one of them.

05:15:17.340 --> 05:15:20.040
Please don't say anything about this for

05:15:20.040 --> 05:15:20.759
now, all right?

05:15:20.880 --> 05:15:24.000
Moon nodded, and turtle handed the seed

05:15:24.000 --> 05:15:24.840
pod over to Sunny.

05:15:24.900 --> 05:15:28.080
I'm sorry about all this, Sonny said.

05:15:28.139 --> 05:15:29.220
It's so awful.

05:15:29.279 --> 05:15:30.779
It shouldn't have happened here.

05:15:30.840 --> 05:15:34.380
But we'll get to the bottom of it, tsunami

05:15:34.380 --> 05:15:35.099
promised.

05:15:35.159 --> 05:15:37.080
We'll find the dragon who set that bomb

05:15:37.080 --> 05:15:39.240
and then I will tear off his wings and

05:15:39.240 --> 05:15:40.919
hang him from the eastern peak of Jade

05:15:40.919 --> 05:15:41.340
Mountain.

05:15:41.400 --> 05:15:43.319
Sonny winced.

05:15:43.380 --> 05:15:44.520
Tsunami.

05:15:44.580 --> 05:15:45.240
Yuck.

05:15:45.360 --> 05:15:48.479
Can we check on Tamron before we go back

05:15:48.479 --> 05:15:49.319
to our caves?

05:15:49.380 --> 05:15:51.000
Moon asked softly.

05:15:51.119 --> 05:15:52.680
Tsunami shook her head.

05:15:52.740 --> 05:15:54.599
Clay is taking care of her.

05:15:54.659 --> 05:15:56.459
We'll let you know soon how she's doing.

05:15:56.520 --> 05:15:59.880
Moon nodded, and then followed Turtle out

05:15:59.880 --> 05:16:00.720
into the tunnel again.

05:16:00.779 --> 05:16:04.080
The sleeping corridor was quiet to dragon

05:16:04.080 --> 05:16:06.540
ears, but Moon could hear the churning

05:16:06.540 --> 05:16:09.419
fear and rumors and guesses rolling

05:16:09.419 --> 05:16:10.319
through everyone's minds.

05:16:10.380 --> 05:16:12.779
Very few of them were actually asleep

05:16:12.779 --> 05:16:14.580
although by now it was fully dark

05:16:14.580 --> 05:16:14.939
outside.

05:16:15.000 --> 05:16:17.700
She hesitated before they reached her

05:16:17.700 --> 05:16:21.180
cave, thinking of carnelian and kinkaju

05:16:21.180 --> 05:16:22.500
and how different everything had been

05:16:22.500 --> 05:16:22.919
this morning.

05:16:22.979 --> 05:16:26.580
It'll be all right, Turtle said.

05:16:26.639 --> 05:16:28.860
You'll find out who did this.

05:16:28.919 --> 05:16:30.659
Let me know if I can help.

05:16:30.720 --> 05:16:33.599
Moon watched him disappear into his

05:16:33.599 --> 05:16:35.880
sleeping cave, where Umber was worrying

05:16:35.880 --> 05:16:37.259
about Marsh and Sora.

05:16:37.319 --> 05:16:40.200
She closed her eyes and found Sora in a

05:16:40.200 --> 05:16:42.299
deep sleep, somewhere farther away.

05:16:42.360 --> 05:16:45.000
The infirmary, moon guest.

05:16:45.060 --> 05:16:47.159
She must have been given tranquilizer

05:16:47.159 --> 05:16:48.060
darts too.

05:16:48.119 --> 05:16:50.639
She listened to the minds around her for

05:16:50.639 --> 05:16:51.360
a long moment.

05:16:51.419 --> 05:16:54.000
But no one was chuckling gleefully over

05:16:54.000 --> 05:16:55.020
their arson today.

05:16:55.080 --> 05:16:58.259
Icicle, Pike, and Mighty Claus were

05:16:58.259 --> 05:16:58.560
asleep.

05:16:58.619 --> 05:17:01.680
She could feel the strange fuzz of Onyx's

05:17:01.680 --> 05:17:03.360
brain, but couldn't tell whether she was

05:17:03.360 --> 05:17:04.139
asleep or awake.

05:17:04.200 --> 05:17:06.900
Flame was not in his sleeping cave at

05:17:06.900 --> 05:17:07.259
all.

05:17:07.319 --> 05:17:09.720
He was somewhere else in the mountain, and

05:17:09.720 --> 05:17:11.520
she could only hear a distant echo of his

05:17:11.520 --> 05:17:12.479
bitter, angry thoughts.

05:17:12.540 --> 05:17:14.520
What can you hear?

05:17:14.580 --> 05:17:16.619
She asked dark stalker.

05:17:16.680 --> 05:17:17.880
Do you know who did it?

05:17:17.939 --> 05:17:20.700
You could leave, you know.

05:17:20.759 --> 05:17:22.919
He answered without answering.

05:17:22.979 --> 05:17:25.560
You don't need these dragons.

05:17:25.619 --> 05:17:28.439
Your friends are furious with you, and

05:17:28.439 --> 05:17:29.520
that ice wing is dangerous.

05:17:29.639 --> 05:17:30.959
But you have me.

05:17:31.020 --> 05:17:33.840
If you leave now, I could help you find

05:17:33.840 --> 05:17:36.180
my talisman, and then you could free me.

05:17:36.240 --> 05:17:38.340
Who would care about the small fire

05:17:38.340 --> 05:17:38.639
then?

05:17:38.700 --> 05:17:40.860
We could change the world, Moon?

05:17:40.919 --> 05:17:43.560
No more war, no more killing.

05:17:43.619 --> 05:17:45.240
We could do that together.

05:17:45.299 --> 05:17:48.419
You and I. Moon didn't know what to say

05:17:48.419 --> 05:17:48.720
to that.

05:17:48.779 --> 05:17:52.080
She could hear Kinkachu, Kibli and Winter

05:17:52.080 --> 05:17:54.659
all thinking about her, and Dark Stalker

05:17:54.659 --> 05:17:54.959
was right.

05:17:55.020 --> 05:17:57.180
It would be safer to get out of here.

05:17:57.240 --> 05:17:58.979
But she didn't want to leave them.

05:17:59.040 --> 05:18:01.259
She didn't want to lose them from her

05:18:01.259 --> 05:18:02.939
life if there was any chance of keeping

05:18:02.939 --> 05:18:03.180
them.

05:18:03.240 --> 05:18:06.119
She folded in her wings and ducked into

05:18:06.119 --> 05:18:06.840
her sleeping cave.

05:18:06.900 --> 05:18:09.599
Kinkachu was curled in her hammock with

05:18:09.599 --> 05:18:10.259
her eyes closed.

05:18:10.319 --> 05:18:13.500
Moon slid over to her nest, trying not to

05:18:13.500 --> 05:18:14.939
look at Carnelian's ledge.

05:18:15.000 --> 05:18:17.459
It felt empty in here without her fuming

05:18:17.459 --> 05:18:18.540
and muttering in the background.

05:18:18.599 --> 05:18:22.380
All right, Kinkachu said suddenly, without

05:18:22.380 --> 05:18:23.279
opening her eyes.

05:18:23.340 --> 05:18:24.779
I know this is silly.

05:18:24.900 --> 05:18:26.759
Of course, you know perfectly well that

05:18:26.759 --> 05:18:28.619
I'm awake, and pretending to be asleep.

05:18:28.680 --> 05:18:31.020
But can you do me a favor and pretend you

05:18:31.020 --> 05:18:31.979
believe it, please?

05:18:32.040 --> 05:18:33.720
I will.

05:18:33.840 --> 05:18:34.979
Moon agreed.

05:18:35.040 --> 05:18:37.740
She laid down and wrapped her tail close

05:18:37.740 --> 05:18:38.220
around her.

05:18:38.279 --> 05:18:41.159
She wished there were a way to shut out

05:18:41.159 --> 05:18:43.619
Kinkachu's thoughts, which were bouncing

05:18:43.619 --> 05:18:45.540
and tumbling all over the place, like

05:18:45.540 --> 05:18:46.860
monkeys that had eaten the wrong

05:18:46.860 --> 05:18:47.400
berries.

05:18:47.459 --> 05:18:49.560
I wouldn't have lied to hurt like that.

05:18:49.619 --> 05:18:52.259
I can't believe Carnelian's dead.

05:18:52.319 --> 05:18:54.119
What would it be like to hear what

05:18:54.119 --> 05:18:55.080
everyone is thinking?

05:18:55.139 --> 05:18:57.000
Who would I want to listen to?

05:18:57.060 --> 05:18:58.500
Maybe winter.

05:18:58.560 --> 05:19:01.500
He seems very mysterious, but I guess he

05:19:01.500 --> 05:19:02.340
isn't a moon.

05:19:02.459 --> 05:19:04.020
I hope Tamron is all right.

05:19:04.080 --> 05:19:05.639
I wish they'd let me see her.

05:19:05.700 --> 05:19:07.799
Maybe I can sneak out and see her

05:19:07.799 --> 05:19:08.159
tonight.

05:19:08.220 --> 05:19:10.259
Is Moon listening to all this?

05:19:10.319 --> 05:19:12.240
Does she know anyone else who can read

05:19:12.240 --> 05:19:12.659
minds?

05:19:12.779 --> 05:19:14.520
Would she tell us if we asked?

05:19:14.580 --> 05:19:16.979
What if all the night wings have these

05:19:16.979 --> 05:19:17.700
powers?

05:19:17.880 --> 05:19:20.220
But Big Tell obviously didn't, or he

05:19:20.220 --> 05:19:21.180
wouldn't have gotten blown up.

05:19:21.240 --> 05:19:22.619
Is she asleep yet?

05:19:22.680 --> 05:19:24.360
I wonder if I should tell someone about

05:19:24.360 --> 05:19:24.599
her.

05:19:24.659 --> 05:19:26.099
Maybe glory.

05:19:26.159 --> 05:19:27.360
Glory would know what to do.

05:19:27.419 --> 05:19:31.259
You could always kill her, Dark Stalker

05:19:31.259 --> 05:19:31.680
suggested.

05:19:31.740 --> 05:19:33.299
I'm kidding.

05:19:33.360 --> 05:19:34.080
Ha ha.

05:19:34.139 --> 05:19:36.000
Evil nightmare dragon, right?

05:19:36.060 --> 05:19:38.939
That's not funny, Moon said.

05:19:39.000 --> 05:19:40.380
Too soon.

05:19:40.439 --> 05:19:41.279
He asked.

05:19:41.340 --> 05:19:42.060
All right.

05:19:42.119 --> 05:19:44.099
I'll wait another 2000 years to make

05:19:44.099 --> 05:19:45.180
jokes about my evilness.

05:19:45.240 --> 05:19:48.180
Moon tried to focus on the dreams of the

05:19:48.180 --> 05:19:49.380
dragons along the corridor.

05:19:49.439 --> 05:19:51.540
Pike was dreaming about swimming with

05:19:51.540 --> 05:19:54.299
whales, except he kept seeing Tamron's

05:19:54.299 --> 05:19:55.319
burnt face on all of them.

05:19:55.380 --> 05:19:57.779
Someone else's dreams were of a battle

05:19:57.779 --> 05:20:00.419
grappling with dragons in a blue sky with

05:20:00.419 --> 05:20:01.380
a waterfall down below.

05:20:01.439 --> 05:20:04.259
Others were deeper, and asleep without

05:20:04.259 --> 05:20:06.900
dreams, and winter was just sliding into

05:20:06.900 --> 05:20:07.500
sleep.

05:20:07.740 --> 05:20:09.479
From the jittery speeding feeling of

05:20:09.479 --> 05:20:11.759
Kibley's brain, Moon guessed he wouldn't

05:20:11.759 --> 05:20:12.479
be able to sleep tonight.

05:20:12.540 --> 05:20:14.639
She didn't think she'd be able to

05:20:14.639 --> 05:20:15.000
either.

05:20:15.060 --> 05:20:17.880
But as the hours passed, she felt her

05:20:17.880 --> 05:20:19.979
wings getting heavier, and her eyelids

05:20:19.979 --> 05:20:21.000
kept trying to close.

05:20:21.060 --> 05:20:23.279
Need to stay awake.

05:20:23.340 --> 05:20:25.919
I have to catch Scarlet if she comes with

05:20:25.919 --> 05:20:26.759
a dream visitor.

05:20:26.819 --> 05:20:29.880
More dragons were asleep now, close to

05:20:29.880 --> 05:20:32.159
midnight, and it was harder to tell whose

05:20:32.159 --> 05:20:34.259
dream was whose, as muddled images

05:20:34.259 --> 05:20:35.819
overlapped and swam together.

05:20:35.880 --> 05:20:38.340
Moon wasn't sure if she was dreaming

05:20:38.340 --> 05:20:40.020
herself when she finally heard the

05:20:40.020 --> 05:20:41.459
slithery voice from 2 nights ago.

05:20:41.580 --> 05:20:43.380
Is it done?

05:20:43.439 --> 05:20:45.000
No.

05:20:45.060 --> 05:20:47.459
It was an eventful day.

05:20:47.520 --> 05:20:50.099
We've had a few deaths, but not the ones

05:20:50.099 --> 05:20:50.459
you want.

05:20:50.520 --> 05:20:54.180
I am not a patient dragon.

05:20:54.240 --> 05:20:55.560
Your time is running out.

05:20:55.619 --> 05:20:57.540
Oh my.

05:20:57.599 --> 05:20:58.979
Do you have a scroll for those?

05:20:59.040 --> 05:21:01.799
Ominous cliches for aspiring villains.

05:21:01.860 --> 05:21:04.200
I wouldn't recommend mocking me.

05:21:04.259 --> 05:21:06.240
It hasn't ended well for anyone.

05:21:06.360 --> 05:21:09.720
You sound pretty menacing for a dragon

05:21:09.720 --> 05:21:11.459
who has to make others do her killing for

05:21:11.459 --> 05:21:11.700
her.

05:21:11.819 --> 05:21:15.659
Tomorrow, said the slithery voice.

05:21:15.720 --> 05:21:17.220
Just one of them.

05:21:17.279 --> 05:21:18.779
Think you can manage that.

05:21:18.840 --> 05:21:21.659
Kill one of them by the end of tomorrow

05:21:21.659 --> 05:21:24.540
or you know what will happen.

05:21:24.599 --> 05:21:27.720
I'll do it, came the response.

05:21:27.840 --> 05:21:31.020
Don't worry, they'll be dead soon, and if

05:21:31.020 --> 05:21:32.880
you touch him, I'll kill you too.

05:21:33.000 --> 05:21:34.740
A rumbling laugh.

05:21:34.860 --> 05:21:36.360
Good luck.

05:21:36.419 --> 05:21:38.819
The connection was severed.

05:21:38.880 --> 05:21:41.459
Tossing moon away and into our own dreams

05:21:41.459 --> 05:21:44.400
which echoed with deadly dragons, falling

05:21:44.400 --> 05:21:47.040
mountains, and clouds of fire for the

05:21:47.040 --> 05:21:47.700
rest of the night.

05:21:47.759 --> 05:21:52.139
Part three.

05:21:52.200 --> 05:21:54.599
The darkness of dragons.

05:21:54.659 --> 05:21:56.759
Chapter 18.

05:21:57.000 --> 05:22:00.299
Kinkaju was gone when Moon woke up.

05:22:00.419 --> 05:22:02.700
Moon could hear her distantly in the

05:22:02.700 --> 05:22:04.560
infirmary, watching over a sleeping

05:22:04.560 --> 05:22:05.340
tamarind.

05:22:05.400 --> 05:22:08.040
She tried to stretch her wings and flinch

05:22:08.040 --> 05:22:09.119
to the pain in her shoulder.

05:22:09.240 --> 05:22:12.000
Her head too still throbbed from hitting

05:22:12.000 --> 05:22:12.779
the cave wall.

05:22:12.840 --> 05:22:15.000
Everything seemed to hurt more than it

05:22:15.000 --> 05:22:15.659
had the day before.

05:22:15.720 --> 05:22:18.840
I couldn't tell who that was last night

05:22:18.840 --> 05:22:19.619
she thought.

05:22:19.680 --> 05:22:21.419
Dark stalker.

05:22:21.479 --> 05:22:23.580
Your power is so much stronger than

05:22:23.580 --> 05:22:23.939
mine.

05:22:24.000 --> 05:22:25.799
Could you see who was talking to

05:22:25.799 --> 05:22:26.279
Scarlett?

05:22:26.340 --> 05:22:27.720
Was that Scarlet?

05:22:27.779 --> 05:22:31.139
He was quiet for so long, she wondered if

05:22:31.139 --> 05:22:33.180
he was asleep, or if that was even a

05:22:33.180 --> 05:22:33.779
thing he did.

05:22:33.840 --> 05:22:37.560
I know some things, he said at last.

05:22:37.619 --> 05:22:41.099
But everything I could tell you, leads to

05:22:41.099 --> 05:22:43.560
futures that end badly, for you and for

05:22:43.560 --> 05:22:43.740
me.

05:22:43.799 --> 05:22:47.580
For instance, I can see clearly that if I

05:22:47.580 --> 05:22:49.319
tell you right now who has been speaking

05:22:49.319 --> 05:22:52.020
with a fallen Skywing queen, you will

05:22:52.020 --> 05:22:53.880
seek out that dragon, and you will end up

05:22:53.880 --> 05:22:57.299
dead, which would be unfortunate, both

05:22:57.299 --> 05:22:59.340
because I quite like you, and because

05:22:59.340 --> 05:23:01.080
then I might have to wait another 1000

05:23:01.080 --> 05:23:02.099
years to be rescued.

05:23:02.159 --> 05:23:04.439
Moon was shaken.

05:23:04.500 --> 05:23:06.360
She straightened the leaves around her

05:23:06.360 --> 05:23:08.459
bed, noticing the way her talons

05:23:08.459 --> 05:23:09.000
trembled.

05:23:09.060 --> 05:23:12.060
You can really see a future where I die

05:23:12.060 --> 05:23:12.240
today?

05:23:12.360 --> 05:23:13.919
Quite clearly.

05:23:13.979 --> 05:23:16.500
Also a few where you die tomorrow.

05:23:16.560 --> 05:23:18.959
Actually, the next couple of months are

05:23:18.959 --> 05:23:20.400
quite perilous for you altogether.

05:23:20.459 --> 05:23:23.580
She stared at the moss of her bed

05:23:23.580 --> 05:23:24.959
wondering if there was enough to bury

05:23:24.959 --> 05:23:26.400
herself in it and never come out.

05:23:26.459 --> 05:23:29.580
You're not exactly helping with my afraid

05:23:29.580 --> 05:23:30.779
of everything problem.

05:23:30.840 --> 05:23:31.799
She pointed out.

05:23:31.860 --> 05:23:34.680
I think you're braver than you think you

05:23:34.680 --> 05:23:34.919
are.

05:23:34.979 --> 05:23:37.799
But maybe that's a future version of you

05:23:37.799 --> 05:23:40.860
one that may never exist if we are not

05:23:40.860 --> 05:23:41.279
careful.

05:23:41.340 --> 05:23:44.459
But I have to find out who set the fire

05:23:44.459 --> 05:23:45.299
she thought.

05:23:45.360 --> 05:23:47.340
I have to tell Winter something by

05:23:47.340 --> 05:23:48.180
midnight tonight.

05:23:48.240 --> 05:23:49.740
Believe me.

05:23:49.799 --> 05:23:52.619
I will do my best to keep you alive, Moon

05:23:52.619 --> 05:23:53.040
Watcher.

05:23:53.099 --> 05:23:56.520
She remembered Sora's calming ritual and

05:23:56.520 --> 05:23:58.139
tried to imitate it.

05:23:58.200 --> 05:24:00.840
Mud didn't feel soothing to her, so she

05:24:00.840 --> 05:24:03.119
thought of the rainforest, and imagined

05:24:03.119 --> 05:24:05.040
that her bones were as strong as the

05:24:05.040 --> 05:24:06.419
giant mahogany trees.

05:24:06.479 --> 05:24:09.360
She imagined that her wings were as vast

05:24:09.360 --> 05:24:12.240
and wide as the treetop canopy, and she

05:24:12.240 --> 05:24:13.680
imagined all the creatures of the

05:24:13.680 --> 05:24:17.340
rainforest, sloths, lizards, frogs

05:24:17.340 --> 05:24:21.479
dragonflies, jaguars, tapirs, toucans

05:24:21.479 --> 05:24:24.180
monkeys, all responding to her talons

05:24:24.180 --> 05:24:26.099
spreading out through the trees, and then

05:24:26.099 --> 05:24:28.380
galloping back to her with news, like the

05:24:28.380 --> 05:24:30.000
scurrying thoughts of the dragons all

05:24:30.000 --> 05:24:30.360
around her.

05:24:30.419 --> 05:24:33.659
She folded her wings, made a determined

05:24:33.659 --> 05:24:36.240
face, and headed for the door, where she

05:24:36.240 --> 05:24:37.680
collided with Kibley coming in.

05:24:37.740 --> 05:24:41.580
Don't say anything, he said quickly, as

05:24:41.580 --> 05:24:42.419
she stumbled back.

05:24:42.479 --> 05:24:45.540
He spoke fast, as if hoping his spoken

05:24:45.540 --> 05:24:47.759
words would drown out his thoughts, but

05:24:47.759 --> 05:24:50.040
those were only a mirror of his speech, as

05:24:50.040 --> 05:24:51.479
though he'd practiced what he was going

05:24:51.479 --> 05:24:52.560
to say a few times over.

05:24:52.619 --> 05:24:54.360
Not yet.

05:24:54.419 --> 05:24:55.200
Give me a chance.

05:24:55.259 --> 05:24:58.380
Listen, I'm sorry about anything you've

05:24:58.380 --> 05:24:59.040
heard in my head.

05:24:59.099 --> 05:25:02.220
I wish I could shut it off, or that I was

05:25:02.220 --> 05:25:03.779
a nicer dragon on the inside.

05:25:03.840 --> 05:25:06.119
But I guess it's too late, and you

05:25:06.119 --> 05:25:07.259
already know how I am.

05:25:07.319 --> 05:25:09.000
I don't know what it's like for you.

05:25:09.060 --> 05:25:12.299
I would think confusing, but at least you

05:25:12.299 --> 05:25:12.779
must know.

05:25:12.840 --> 05:25:15.060
I'm not the one who caused the explosion

05:25:15.060 --> 05:25:16.799
yesterday, and I think that's the most

05:25:16.799 --> 05:25:17.340
important thing.

05:25:17.400 --> 05:25:19.680
And you're the dragon who has the best

05:25:19.680 --> 05:25:20.880
chance of figuring it out.

05:25:20.939 --> 05:25:23.400
So I'm here to help you, is what I wanted

05:25:23.400 --> 05:25:23.759
to say.

05:25:23.880 --> 05:25:26.459
He took a deep breath.

05:25:26.520 --> 05:25:27.840
And now she could hear the struggle he

05:25:27.840 --> 05:25:28.380
was going through.

05:25:28.439 --> 05:25:30.540
Run away from her or stay.

05:25:30.599 --> 05:25:33.599
Find a way to be friends, or warn the

05:25:33.599 --> 05:25:34.259
world about her.

05:25:34.319 --> 05:25:36.119
Trust her or not?

05:25:36.180 --> 05:25:38.939
Why do you think I can figure it out?

05:25:39.000 --> 05:25:39.959
she asked.

05:25:40.020 --> 05:25:41.459
Although she could guess?

05:25:41.520 --> 05:25:43.619
Isn't that what your powers are for?

05:25:43.619 --> 05:25:44.580
he said.

05:25:44.639 --> 05:25:46.919
If I could read minds and see the future

05:25:46.919 --> 05:25:47.880
that's what I would do.

05:25:47.939 --> 05:25:50.279
Stop bad dragons before they hurt

05:25:50.279 --> 05:25:50.700
anyone.

05:25:50.759 --> 05:25:53.700
Or, in this case, hurt anyone else, I

05:25:53.700 --> 05:25:53.939
suppose.

05:25:54.000 --> 05:25:56.040
Why else would you be able to do what you

05:25:56.040 --> 05:25:56.340
can do?

05:25:56.400 --> 05:25:58.200
Don't you think that's why you have

05:25:58.200 --> 05:25:58.380
them?

05:25:58.500 --> 05:26:01.200
Moon had never thought of her powers

05:26:01.200 --> 05:26:01.799
quite that way.

05:26:01.860 --> 05:26:05.220
All she'd ever heard from her mother was

05:26:05.220 --> 05:26:07.380
that they were a curse, a dangerous

05:26:07.380 --> 05:26:09.000
condition, and she should hide them.

05:26:09.060 --> 05:26:11.459
Or, according to dark stalker.

05:26:11.520 --> 05:26:13.380
They were a gift that destined her for

05:26:13.380 --> 05:26:15.060
power and made her better than other

05:26:15.060 --> 05:26:15.659
dragons.

05:26:15.720 --> 05:26:18.000
But there was something entirely new in

05:26:18.000 --> 05:26:19.380
Kibli's shimmering mind.

05:26:19.439 --> 05:26:22.319
A tool she could use to help and protect

05:26:22.319 --> 05:26:25.560
other dragons, if she used them wisely.

05:26:25.680 --> 05:26:28.799
This was a kind of test she realized

05:26:28.799 --> 05:26:30.479
although he didn't consciously know

05:26:30.479 --> 05:26:30.659
that.

05:26:30.779 --> 05:26:33.240
If she helped catch the dragon who killed

05:26:33.240 --> 05:26:35.880
Carnelian and Bigtail, Kibli would be

05:26:35.880 --> 05:26:37.380
able to believe her powers could be used

05:26:37.380 --> 05:26:37.799
for good.

05:26:37.860 --> 05:26:40.439
He'd be able to believe that she was

05:26:40.439 --> 05:26:40.680
good.

05:26:40.740 --> 05:26:43.439
Of course, she said.

05:26:43.500 --> 05:26:45.540
Yes, I was thinking the same thing.

05:26:45.599 --> 05:26:48.180
I want to help, but I don't know where to

05:26:48.180 --> 05:26:48.360
start.

05:26:48.419 --> 05:26:50.819
How does it work?

05:26:51.000 --> 05:26:51.540
He asked.

05:26:51.599 --> 05:26:53.819
Can you just dig around in a dragon's

05:26:53.819 --> 05:26:55.200
brain and find out anything you want?

05:26:55.259 --> 05:26:56.939
She shook her head.

05:26:57.000 --> 05:26:59.580
It's more like walking into a room and

05:26:59.580 --> 05:27:00.479
hearing a conversation.

05:27:00.540 --> 05:27:02.939
I think I pick up whatever's going

05:27:02.939 --> 05:27:04.439
through a dragon's brain when I'm near

05:27:04.439 --> 05:27:04.680
them.

05:27:04.740 --> 05:27:07.500
Sometimes it's clearer, linear thoughts

05:27:07.500 --> 05:27:10.560
and sometimes it's a jumble of words, and

05:27:10.560 --> 05:27:12.779
sometimes it's pictures, and I get a lot

05:27:12.779 --> 05:27:13.860
of emotions too.

05:27:13.979 --> 05:27:16.619
Sometimes it's so strong that it's hard

05:27:16.619 --> 05:27:19.380
to tell what I'm feeling myself, and it's

05:27:19.380 --> 05:27:21.479
always louder and stronger when I'm

05:27:21.479 --> 05:27:21.959
touching someone.

05:27:22.020 --> 05:27:24.419
She reached out unconsciously to

05:27:24.419 --> 05:27:26.340
demonstrate, and he shied away from her.

05:27:26.400 --> 05:27:28.020
She dropped her talons.

05:27:28.080 --> 05:27:29.939
Sorry, I didn't mean to.

05:27:30.060 --> 05:27:31.080
It's all right.

05:27:31.139 --> 05:27:32.520
Sorry, he said.

05:27:32.580 --> 05:27:34.919
Shifting guiltily at the hurt look on her

05:27:34.919 --> 05:27:35.159
face.

05:27:35.220 --> 05:27:37.080
I have to get used to this.

05:27:37.139 --> 05:27:38.400
I know.

05:27:38.459 --> 05:27:40.860
So the bad guy would have to be thinking

05:27:40.860 --> 05:27:42.540
about what he's done in order for you to

05:27:42.540 --> 05:27:45.240
catch him, Kibley said, but they must be

05:27:45.240 --> 05:27:45.419
right.

05:27:45.479 --> 05:27:47.520
After killing 2 dragons.

05:27:47.580 --> 05:27:48.779
Wouldn't that be all you could think

05:27:48.779 --> 05:27:48.959
about?

05:27:49.020 --> 05:27:51.959
Moon rearranged to the scrolls in the

05:27:51.959 --> 05:27:54.060
rack by the door, scanning the thoughts

05:27:54.060 --> 05:27:54.599
along the hall?

05:27:54.659 --> 05:27:56.279
Apparently not.

05:27:56.340 --> 05:27:58.200
I haven't heard anything clear like that

05:27:58.200 --> 05:27:58.500
yet.

05:27:58.619 --> 05:28:00.119
She hesitated.

05:28:00.180 --> 05:28:02.580
But there are a couple of dragons here

05:28:02.580 --> 05:28:04.799
whose thoughts I can't hear, and I don't

05:28:04.799 --> 05:28:07.680
know why. onyx, peril.

05:28:07.799 --> 05:28:09.540
Sometimes a thought gets through, but

05:28:09.540 --> 05:28:13.020
it's all fire in there, and turtle.

05:28:13.080 --> 05:28:15.659
Turtle, kibli echoed.

05:28:15.720 --> 05:28:17.400
He can shield his thoughts from you.

05:28:17.459 --> 05:28:19.380
That's hardly fair.

05:28:19.439 --> 05:28:21.180
How did he figure out how to do that?

05:28:21.240 --> 05:28:24.419
He doesn't seem clever enough for Kibley

05:28:24.419 --> 05:28:25.259
cut his own thoughts off.

05:28:25.319 --> 05:28:27.779
If you heard that, don't listen to it.

05:28:27.840 --> 05:28:28.799
I like turtle.

05:28:28.860 --> 05:28:31.200
I don't mean to be mean, he can't be the

05:28:31.200 --> 05:28:31.979
one who did this, right?

05:28:32.040 --> 05:28:33.659
Peril maybe.

05:28:33.720 --> 05:28:36.000
Onyx, I don't know anything about her.

05:28:36.060 --> 05:28:38.639
I don't think she was in the scorpion den

05:28:38.639 --> 05:28:40.080
or I'd at least have heard of her.

05:28:40.139 --> 05:28:43.200
I'm not sure it's one of them, she said

05:28:43.200 --> 05:28:45.479
but if it is, I wouldn't be able to hear

05:28:45.479 --> 05:28:45.779
them.

05:28:45.840 --> 05:28:46.380
That's all.

05:28:46.439 --> 05:28:47.639
He nodded.

05:28:47.700 --> 05:28:48.959
All right.

05:28:49.020 --> 05:28:51.360
See if anyone else thinks anything

05:28:51.360 --> 05:28:52.860
suspicious at the assembly.

05:28:52.919 --> 05:28:55.560
And if not, we'll focus on those three.

05:28:55.619 --> 05:28:57.720
Assembly?

05:28:57.720 --> 05:28:58.259
she said.

05:28:58.319 --> 05:29:00.720
Kibley stepped into the hallway and

05:29:00.720 --> 05:29:02.220
lifted a small message off the wall.

05:29:02.279 --> 05:29:05.759
In subdued letters, it read, Gather in

05:29:05.759 --> 05:29:07.020
the great hall at the bells.

05:29:07.080 --> 05:29:11.580
Poor Sonny, he said, rubbing chalk dust

05:29:11.580 --> 05:29:13.020
off the edges of the tablet.

05:29:13.080 --> 05:29:14.520
She must be so upset.

05:29:14.580 --> 05:29:17.340
She is, Moon said.

05:29:17.400 --> 05:29:19.979
Three gongs echoed through the tunnels.

05:29:20.040 --> 05:29:22.139
Dragonettes began to emerge from their

05:29:22.139 --> 05:29:24.599
caves in silence, a flowing mass of

05:29:24.599 --> 05:29:26.400
scales and wings all heading in the same

05:29:26.400 --> 05:29:26.759
direction.

05:29:26.819 --> 05:29:29.340
Kibli studied the ones going past

05:29:29.340 --> 05:29:31.259
momentarily forgetting to worry about

05:29:31.259 --> 05:29:32.400
Moon reading his mind.

05:29:32.459 --> 05:29:34.139
Who did it?

05:29:34.200 --> 05:29:36.299
The answer is in a motive.

05:29:36.360 --> 05:29:37.560
That's what Thorn would say.

05:29:37.619 --> 05:29:38.700
So why?

05:29:38.759 --> 05:29:40.979
The outlaws never used anything like

05:29:40.979 --> 05:29:43.139
bombs, because Thorn didn't want any

05:29:43.139 --> 05:29:44.040
collateral damage.

05:29:44.099 --> 05:29:45.959
Targeted killing if necessary.

05:29:46.020 --> 05:29:47.819
Open challenges if possible.

05:29:47.880 --> 05:29:50.700
A picture of his mother flashed through

05:29:50.700 --> 05:29:52.560
his mind, but Moon didn't catch why.

05:29:52.619 --> 05:29:54.900
She was sure from his earlier memories

05:29:54.900 --> 05:29:55.979
that his mother was still alive.

05:29:56.040 --> 05:29:59.220
Blowing up innocent dragons while you're

05:29:59.220 --> 05:29:59.580
far away.

05:29:59.639 --> 05:30:01.500
It's a coward's choice.

05:30:01.560 --> 05:30:03.299
Were they trying to kill someone in

05:30:03.299 --> 05:30:05.340
particular, or as many dragons as

05:30:05.340 --> 05:30:05.639
possible?

05:30:05.700 --> 05:30:07.439
And did they succeed?

05:30:07.500 --> 05:30:09.959
Trying to kill Tamron makes no sense.

05:30:10.020 --> 05:30:11.759
She must have been an accident.

05:30:11.880 --> 05:30:14.279
The carnelian and big tail?

05:30:14.340 --> 05:30:16.500
They were fairly unfriendly dragons.

05:30:16.560 --> 05:30:18.360
They could have made enemies quickly.

05:30:18.419 --> 05:30:20.639
Or one enemy.

05:30:20.700 --> 05:30:24.180
He turned to Moon with his tail raised, an

05:30:24.180 --> 05:30:26.099
expression like lightning striking on his

05:30:26.099 --> 05:30:26.279
face.

05:30:26.340 --> 05:30:29.759
Pike, she said, I didn't think of that.

05:30:29.880 --> 05:30:31.799
Kimberley's eyes widened.

05:30:31.860 --> 05:30:32.819
I'm sorry.

05:30:32.880 --> 05:30:34.259
Moon said immediately.

05:30:34.319 --> 05:30:35.220
I'm really sorry.

05:30:35.279 --> 05:30:36.240
I couldn't help hearing it.

05:30:36.299 --> 05:30:39.479
It's fine, he said, shifting

05:30:39.479 --> 05:30:40.200
uncomfortably.

05:30:40.259 --> 05:30:42.119
I suppose it makes for faster

05:30:42.119 --> 05:30:42.720
conversations.

05:30:42.779 --> 05:30:45.360
Pike fought with both Cornelian and

05:30:45.360 --> 05:30:46.680
Bigtail before the explosion.

05:30:46.740 --> 05:30:48.720
I can't think of anyone else who might

05:30:48.720 --> 05:30:50.279
want both of those dragons dead.

05:30:50.340 --> 05:30:52.439
But do you think it could have been that

05:30:52.439 --> 05:30:53.099
specific?

05:30:53.099 --> 05:30:53.819
she asked.

05:30:53.939 --> 05:30:56.459
How could anyone know who'd be in there

05:30:56.459 --> 05:30:57.720
when the cactus exploded?

05:30:57.779 --> 05:31:00.540
Cactus, he said.

05:31:00.599 --> 05:31:02.340
Two gongs sounded.

05:31:02.400 --> 05:31:04.439
They started toward the great hall

05:31:04.439 --> 05:31:06.479
staying well behind the other dragons, so

05:31:06.479 --> 05:31:08.220
no one could overhear them.

05:31:08.279 --> 05:31:10.080
Keeping her voice low, Moon explained

05:31:10.080 --> 05:31:12.119
about the dragon flame cactus and the

05:31:12.119 --> 05:31:14.819
seed pods, watching his brain spiral out

05:31:14.819 --> 05:31:16.319
into all the possibilities that meant.

05:31:16.380 --> 05:31:19.799
She also told him about Queen Scarlet and

05:31:19.799 --> 05:31:21.000
the dream visitor conversations.

05:31:21.060 --> 05:31:24.479
Oh, she said, stopping suddenly in the

05:31:24.479 --> 05:31:24.779
tunnel.

05:31:24.840 --> 05:31:26.819
I wasn't supposed to tell anyone about

05:31:26.819 --> 05:31:28.500
the cactus, I totally forgot.

05:31:28.619 --> 05:31:30.840
Sonny asked us to keep it a secret.

05:31:30.900 --> 05:31:32.759
But you had to tell me.

05:31:32.819 --> 05:31:34.080
Here reassured her.

05:31:34.139 --> 05:31:36.180
I need all the clues ever going to figure

05:31:36.180 --> 05:31:36.840
this out together.

05:31:36.900 --> 05:31:38.220
Don't feel bad.

05:31:38.279 --> 05:31:39.419
I won't tell anyone else.

05:31:39.540 --> 05:31:40.919
He shrugged.

05:31:40.979 --> 05:31:43.020
And I bet you can see in my brain that

05:31:43.020 --> 05:31:43.680
I'm telling the truth.

05:31:43.799 --> 05:31:45.360
He was.

05:31:45.419 --> 05:31:47.220
And he was also trying to be funny to

05:31:47.220 --> 05:31:49.439
hide how freaked out he was, and then

05:31:49.439 --> 05:31:50.700
feeling stupid for trying to hide

05:31:50.700 --> 05:31:51.419
anything from her.

05:31:51.479 --> 05:31:54.720
So you think it was probably a sky wing

05:31:54.720 --> 05:31:57.240
he said, or at least someone working for

05:31:57.240 --> 05:31:57.779
Scarlet.

05:31:57.840 --> 05:31:59.819
And perhaps they were just trying to

05:31:59.819 --> 05:32:01.979
disrupt the school and didn't care who

05:32:01.979 --> 05:32:02.279
they killed.

05:32:02.340 --> 05:32:03.599
That makes sense.

05:32:03.659 --> 05:32:06.119
But it is possible they were after

05:32:06.119 --> 05:32:06.959
someone in particular.

05:32:07.020 --> 05:32:09.779
And we all heard Pike threaten Bigtail in

05:32:09.779 --> 05:32:10.380
the prey center.

05:32:10.439 --> 05:32:13.020
That's true, said Moon.

05:32:13.080 --> 05:32:15.000
He's really angry on the inside.

05:32:15.060 --> 05:32:17.040
How surprising.

05:32:17.099 --> 05:32:20.159
He's so mellow on the outside, Kibley

05:32:20.159 --> 05:32:20.880
said wryly.

05:32:20.939 --> 05:32:23.099
I think he nearly died in the summer

05:32:23.099 --> 05:32:24.000
palace attack.

05:32:24.060 --> 05:32:26.580
Moon said, then stopped with a gasp.

05:32:26.639 --> 05:32:29.700
Oh, so he must know about the dragon

05:32:29.700 --> 05:32:30.659
flame bombs too.

05:32:30.720 --> 05:32:33.659
The last gong sounded, and they had to

05:32:33.659 --> 05:32:34.080
hurry.

05:32:34.139 --> 05:32:36.720
Even so, they were the last ones to enter

05:32:36.720 --> 05:32:37.259
the great hall.

05:32:37.380 --> 05:32:39.779
The other dragons of Jade Mountain were

05:32:39.779 --> 05:32:41.880
all gathered, with the 5 teachers and

05:32:41.880 --> 05:32:44.279
fate speaker on a raised ledge facing

05:32:44.279 --> 05:32:44.459
them.

05:32:44.520 --> 05:32:46.919
Moon could feel their surging emotions

05:32:46.919 --> 05:32:48.900
clearly, but she thought she could have

05:32:48.900 --> 05:32:50.400
read them just as well by the looks on

05:32:50.400 --> 05:32:52.619
their faces, the way Kibley was doing.

05:32:52.680 --> 05:32:55.560
Sonny devastated.

05:32:55.619 --> 05:32:57.959
Tsunami, furious.

05:32:58.020 --> 05:33:03.240
Clay, grieving, Starflight, anxious, and

05:33:03.240 --> 05:33:04.860
trying desperately to puzzle out what had

05:33:04.860 --> 05:33:05.220
happened.

05:33:05.279 --> 05:33:08.939
Fate speaker, scared for Starflight, and

05:33:08.939 --> 05:33:10.560
a little unsure about whether this school

05:33:10.560 --> 05:33:13.799
was worth it, and Webbs, who was mostly

05:33:13.799 --> 05:33:15.540
relieved that he'd been late to class and

05:33:15.540 --> 05:33:16.500
had therefore survived.

05:33:16.560 --> 05:33:19.919
The students on the other talent were a

05:33:19.919 --> 05:33:21.479
mess of jumbled mental energy.

05:33:21.540 --> 05:33:24.000
Moon stumbled as she approached the

05:33:24.000 --> 05:33:24.419
crowd.

05:33:24.479 --> 05:33:26.700
It felt like stepping into a hurricane.

05:33:26.759 --> 05:33:29.459
It was worse than the fear set off by

05:33:29.459 --> 05:33:30.540
perils arrival.

05:33:30.599 --> 05:33:32.819
This was an avalanche of terror.

05:33:32.880 --> 05:33:35.220
Everyone convinced they'd be the next to

05:33:35.220 --> 05:33:35.459
die.

05:33:35.520 --> 05:33:37.979
Moon thought she'd been scared before.

05:33:38.040 --> 05:33:40.020
Now she felt as though her claws were

05:33:40.020 --> 05:33:41.040
melted to the ground.

05:33:41.159 --> 05:33:43.799
All her nerves screaming run, while her

05:33:43.799 --> 05:33:45.060
frozen body disobeyed.

05:33:45.180 --> 05:33:47.400
Kibley must have seen something in her

05:33:47.400 --> 05:33:47.700
face.

05:33:47.759 --> 05:33:50.340
He stepped closer until she could feel

05:33:50.340 --> 05:33:52.139
the warmth of his scales and whispered

05:33:52.139 --> 05:33:54.959
Remember, you're feeling everyone else's

05:33:54.959 --> 05:33:55.380
fear.

05:33:55.439 --> 05:33:57.180
It's not all yours.

05:33:57.240 --> 05:33:59.099
Find an anchor.

05:33:59.220 --> 05:34:01.080
Dark Stalker reminded her.

05:34:01.139 --> 05:34:03.119
Don't let yourself be overwhelmed.

05:34:03.240 --> 05:34:05.220
Easy for you to say.

05:34:05.279 --> 05:34:08.220
Moonshot back, but she reached out and

05:34:08.220 --> 05:34:09.900
latched onto tsunami's thoughts.

05:34:09.959 --> 05:34:12.540
The sea wing was loud and angry, but at

05:34:12.540 --> 05:34:13.500
least she wasn't petrified.

05:34:13.560 --> 05:34:15.540
Hi, everyone.

05:34:15.599 --> 05:34:17.580
Sonny said somberly.

05:34:17.639 --> 05:34:20.040
I know you're all worried about the awful

05:34:20.040 --> 05:34:21.240
fire that happened yesterday.

05:34:21.299 --> 05:34:24.599
The 1st thing we want you to know is that

05:34:24.599 --> 05:34:27.360
the school is not closing, at least not

05:34:27.360 --> 05:34:27.900
right now.

05:34:27.959 --> 05:34:31.020
But we understand if you want to leave.

05:34:31.080 --> 05:34:33.599
There are dragons on their way here now

05:34:33.599 --> 05:34:35.580
who can escort you safely home.

05:34:35.639 --> 05:34:38.880
Her mind flashed quickly past glory

05:34:38.880 --> 05:34:42.299
Deathbringer, a 6 clawed sandwing, and a

05:34:42.299 --> 05:34:43.919
big mudwing who looked like clay.

05:34:43.979 --> 05:34:47.159
We understand if you want to go.

05:34:47.220 --> 05:34:49.799
But we're hoping you'll choose to stay.

05:34:49.860 --> 05:34:51.419
Clay added.

05:34:51.479 --> 05:34:54.479
We'd ask you all to give us 2 days before

05:34:54.479 --> 05:34:55.080
you decide.

05:34:55.139 --> 05:34:58.080
Give us 2 days to find out what happened

05:34:58.080 --> 05:34:59.580
and who did this.

05:34:59.639 --> 05:35:01.319
If we can't.

05:35:01.380 --> 05:35:03.840
If we think it's too dangerous to stay

05:35:03.840 --> 05:35:04.139
here.

05:35:04.259 --> 05:35:06.659
We'll consider shutting down the school.

05:35:06.720 --> 05:35:10.139
Moon was surprised to realize how sad

05:35:10.139 --> 05:35:10.560
that made her.

05:35:10.619 --> 05:35:13.380
Three days ago, she would have been

05:35:13.380 --> 05:35:15.479
thrilled if the school was closed and she

05:35:15.479 --> 05:35:16.619
could go home with no guilt.

05:35:16.680 --> 05:35:19.560
Now, even with all the trouble with her

05:35:19.560 --> 05:35:21.599
friends, she wanted to stay.

05:35:21.659 --> 05:35:24.180
She wanted the school to go on, and she

05:35:24.180 --> 05:35:25.259
didn't want to give up.

05:35:25.319 --> 05:35:26.639
Moon.

05:35:26.700 --> 05:35:29.400
Startled, Moon looked around and found

05:35:29.400 --> 05:35:30.959
Kibley staring intently at her.

05:35:31.020 --> 05:35:32.159
He tipped his head.

05:35:32.220 --> 05:35:34.319
See if you can edge this way.

05:35:34.439 --> 05:35:36.240
Pike's over here.

05:35:36.299 --> 05:35:40.020
Only half listening to Clay's speech, she

05:35:40.020 --> 05:35:41.700
sidled through the crowd until she was

05:35:41.700 --> 05:35:43.139
directly behind the sea wing.

05:35:43.200 --> 05:35:46.080
Carefully she disengaged from tsunami's

05:35:46.080 --> 05:35:48.000
mind, and opened up to the swarm of

05:35:48.000 --> 05:35:48.720
thoughts around her.

05:35:48.779 --> 05:35:50.759
Maybe I should go home.

05:35:50.819 --> 05:35:52.560
But is it any safer there?

05:35:52.619 --> 05:35:55.080
It must have been someone in this cave.

05:35:55.139 --> 05:35:56.880
It could be the dragon right next to me.

05:35:56.939 --> 05:35:59.580
She does like kind of smug, that worm.

05:35:59.639 --> 05:36:00.479
I should bite her.

05:36:00.540 --> 05:36:03.900
I heard the whole cave exploded and then

05:36:03.900 --> 05:36:04.380
collapsed.

05:36:04.439 --> 05:36:06.659
Maybe the whole mountain will collapse

05:36:06.659 --> 05:36:06.900
next.

05:36:06.959 --> 05:36:09.000
I knew it was stupid to live somewhere

05:36:09.000 --> 05:36:10.619
with rock over your head all the time.

05:36:10.680 --> 05:36:12.779
What would Queen Glory do?

05:36:12.840 --> 05:36:14.220
She'd know how to protect us.

05:36:14.279 --> 05:36:17.340
At least the princess was nowhere near

05:36:17.340 --> 05:36:17.759
the fire.

05:36:17.819 --> 05:36:20.580
There, that was Pike.

05:36:20.639 --> 05:36:22.560
She narrowed her focus onto him.

05:36:22.619 --> 05:36:24.840
He had a confusing mind.

05:36:24.900 --> 05:36:27.779
His thoughts rampaged around like wild

05:36:27.779 --> 05:36:28.919
rhinoceroses.

05:36:28.979 --> 05:36:31.139
Half of them began and then trailed off

05:36:31.139 --> 05:36:31.979
as he jumped to another.

05:36:32.099 --> 05:36:34.619
If Nominee had been hurt.

05:36:34.680 --> 05:36:36.180
Maybe Queen Coral is right.

05:36:36.240 --> 05:36:38.459
Can't protect her if I'm dead.

05:36:38.520 --> 05:36:39.779
Dare to kill me.

05:36:39.840 --> 05:36:40.560
I'll rip off there.

05:36:40.680 --> 05:36:42.540
That poor little rain wing.

05:36:42.599 --> 05:36:44.159
I miss the deep palace.

05:36:44.220 --> 05:36:45.419
Nothing catches on fire there.

05:36:45.479 --> 05:36:47.700
Wish I'd had a chance to fight that night

05:36:47.700 --> 05:36:50.400
wing, would have given him a tail whack

05:36:50.400 --> 05:36:51.000
he'd never forget.

05:36:51.060 --> 05:36:53.819
Never even got to fill his bed with

05:36:53.819 --> 05:36:54.180
slugs.

05:36:54.240 --> 05:36:56.580
So pointless having dead enemies.

05:36:56.639 --> 05:36:57.900
Nobody to yell at.

05:36:57.959 --> 05:36:59.220
There's anemone.

05:36:59.279 --> 05:37:01.020
That ice wing is standing too close to

05:37:01.020 --> 05:37:01.500
her.

05:37:01.560 --> 05:37:02.520
Maybe I'll go bite him.

05:37:02.580 --> 05:37:05.040
Wonder which of these idiots set the

05:37:05.040 --> 05:37:05.400
fire.

05:37:05.459 --> 05:37:07.860
That'd give me someone to snarl at.

05:37:07.919 --> 05:37:11.040
Moon pivoted to me Kibley's eyes and

05:37:11.040 --> 05:37:11.580
shook her head.

05:37:11.639 --> 05:37:15.540
Pike was an odd, bad tempered dragon, and

05:37:15.540 --> 05:37:17.639
might be secretly protecting anemone for

05:37:17.639 --> 05:37:19.560
Queen Coral, but he wasn't their killer.

05:37:19.619 --> 05:37:22.680
Frowning, Kibley scanned the crowd

05:37:22.680 --> 05:37:24.840
choosing and discarding suspects at

05:37:24.840 --> 05:37:27.060
lightning speed, he crossed off all the

05:37:27.060 --> 05:37:29.279
rain wings right away, which moon agreed

05:37:29.279 --> 05:37:29.520
with?

05:37:29.580 --> 05:37:31.619
None of them ever had an aggressive

05:37:31.619 --> 05:37:33.119
thought, as far as she'd seen.

05:37:33.180 --> 05:37:36.479
He paused on umber and thought, too loyal

05:37:36.479 --> 05:37:36.959
to clay.

05:37:37.020 --> 05:37:39.659
Then Marsh, too nervous.

05:37:39.900 --> 05:37:41.520
Moon agreed with that as well.

05:37:41.580 --> 05:37:43.919
From the frantic terror spiking out of

05:37:43.919 --> 05:37:45.659
Marcia's head, she rather thought he

05:37:45.659 --> 05:37:47.580
belonged in the infirmary too

05:37:47.580 --> 05:37:49.740
tranquilized in the bed next to Sores.

05:37:49.799 --> 05:37:52.080
Winter and icicle?

05:37:52.200 --> 05:37:54.479
He wondered, studying the 2 haughty ice

05:37:54.479 --> 05:37:56.759
wings, who stood a few paces away from

05:37:56.759 --> 05:37:58.860
the rest of the crowd, with the other 4

05:37:58.860 --> 05:38:00.599
ice wing students forming a sort of

05:38:00.599 --> 05:38:02.099
barricade between them and everyone

05:38:02.099 --> 05:38:02.939
else.

05:38:03.000 --> 05:38:05.040
Not winter, he mused.

05:38:05.099 --> 05:38:07.560
He was with me or near me most of the day

05:38:07.560 --> 05:38:09.180
especially right before class.

05:38:09.240 --> 05:38:11.459
But maybe Icicle?

05:38:11.520 --> 05:38:13.919
Moon knew she wouldn't be able to get

05:38:13.919 --> 05:38:16.380
very close, but she edged toward the ice

05:38:16.380 --> 05:38:17.099
wings anyway.

05:38:17.159 --> 05:38:19.740
Winter stretched his wings and twisted

05:38:19.740 --> 05:38:20.939
his neck to search the crowd.

05:38:21.000 --> 05:38:24.419
For her, moon realized, ducking out of

05:38:24.419 --> 05:38:25.979
sight behind a large mud wing.

05:38:26.099 --> 05:38:28.380
Midnight tonight, she thought.

05:38:28.439 --> 05:38:31.740
Either I figure out who did it by then, or

05:38:31.740 --> 05:38:34.799
I come up with a really great lie, or he

05:38:34.799 --> 05:38:35.880
exposes me to everyone.

05:38:35.939 --> 05:38:39.659
All of the ice wings had sharp, glittering

05:38:39.659 --> 05:38:41.819
minds, and clumped together like they

05:38:41.819 --> 05:38:44.400
were, it was even harder to distinguish

05:38:44.400 --> 05:38:46.380
icicles' thoughts and read them clearly.

05:38:46.439 --> 05:38:49.200
They seemed to bounce off the others and

05:38:49.200 --> 05:38:50.639
be reflected several times over.

05:38:50.700 --> 05:38:53.759
But after a minute of concentrating, Moon

05:38:53.759 --> 05:38:55.799
found herself balanced on the sword's

05:38:55.799 --> 05:38:57.360
edge that was Icicle's brain.

05:38:57.419 --> 05:39:01.139
By the teeth of the great ice dragon, this

05:39:01.139 --> 05:39:02.279
is boring as sand.

05:39:02.340 --> 05:39:04.680
Icicle grumbled internally.

05:39:04.740 --> 05:39:06.900
I shall certainly tell mother and father

05:39:06.900 --> 05:39:08.520
and aunt Glacier.

05:39:08.580 --> 05:39:10.139
What a waste of time this entire school

05:39:10.139 --> 05:39:10.439
is.

05:39:10.500 --> 05:39:12.360
What have I learned so far?

05:39:12.419 --> 05:39:15.240
Even dragons who have been to war can be

05:39:15.240 --> 05:39:16.619
pitiful emotional wrecks.

05:39:16.680 --> 05:39:19.439
Ice wings are superior to every other

05:39:19.439 --> 05:39:19.979
tribe.

05:39:20.040 --> 05:39:21.779
Of course, we knew that already.

05:39:21.840 --> 05:39:24.720
And don't set any dragons on fire, or

05:39:24.720 --> 05:39:27.419
else a bunch of sentimental soft talons

05:39:27.419 --> 05:39:29.520
will cry and moralize and lecture you

05:39:29.520 --> 05:39:31.259
about it endlessly afterward.

05:39:31.319 --> 05:39:32.279
Yawn.

05:39:32.340 --> 05:39:34.200
Moon tipped her head.

05:39:34.259 --> 05:39:36.180
Was that an admission of guilt?

05:39:36.240 --> 05:39:37.380
It was hard to tell.

05:39:37.439 --> 05:39:40.200
I should also tell her this place has

05:39:40.200 --> 05:39:41.880
done something frightful to winter.

05:39:41.939 --> 05:39:44.580
Clearly he's too weak to associate with

05:39:44.580 --> 05:39:46.020
dragons from other tribes.

05:39:46.080 --> 05:39:48.360
He's talking like you might almost find

05:39:48.360 --> 05:39:49.139
them interesting.

05:39:49.200 --> 05:39:51.240
I wonder if I should tell him about

05:39:51.240 --> 05:39:52.080
Hailstorm.

05:39:52.139 --> 05:39:53.759
He wouldn't try to stop me.

05:39:53.819 --> 05:39:55.860
I don't think, but it would be too

05:39:55.860 --> 05:39:56.939
tiresome if he did.

05:39:57.000 --> 05:39:59.759
Moon wished she could circle back and

05:39:59.759 --> 05:40:00.360
hear that again.

05:40:00.419 --> 05:40:02.400
Who was Hellstorm?

05:40:02.459 --> 05:40:05.939
Icicle made an impatient movement, and

05:40:05.939 --> 05:40:07.380
Winter shot her a warning glance.

05:40:07.439 --> 05:40:09.659
His sister rolled her eyes.

05:40:09.720 --> 05:40:12.540
Why are they still going on about this?

05:40:12.659 --> 05:40:14.700
Two dragons died.

05:40:14.759 --> 05:40:15.180
So what?

05:40:15.240 --> 05:40:17.939
I've killed 9 times that in almost every

05:40:17.939 --> 05:40:18.840
battle I've been in.

05:40:18.900 --> 05:40:20.759
We don't need to hear about it

05:40:20.759 --> 05:40:21.720
endlessly.

05:40:21.779 --> 05:40:24.119
They should just find the dragon who did

05:40:24.119 --> 05:40:26.159
it and give them a slow, horrible death.

05:40:26.220 --> 05:40:28.560
Perhaps by making them listen to

05:40:28.560 --> 05:40:30.479
Starflight talk for the next 100 years.

05:40:30.540 --> 05:40:34.619
Up on the dais, Starflight was earnestly

05:40:34.619 --> 05:40:35.880
trying to explain something about

05:40:35.880 --> 05:40:38.939
psychological trauma, Moon said quietly

05:40:38.939 --> 05:40:41.159
away from the Mudwings shadow, and

05:40:41.159 --> 05:40:43.139
searched until she found Kibley's eyes on

05:40:43.139 --> 05:40:44.639
her, then shook her head.

05:40:44.700 --> 05:40:46.979
It didn't sound as though Icicle had done

05:40:46.979 --> 05:40:49.919
it either, although she had a deeply cold

05:40:49.919 --> 05:40:50.759
unpleasant mind.

05:40:50.880 --> 05:40:54.419
Kibley beckoned surreptitiously, flicking

05:40:54.419 --> 05:40:55.860
one of his wings at the far wall.

05:40:55.919 --> 05:40:58.740
Moon followed his gaze to flame, who was

05:40:58.740 --> 05:41:00.240
brooding in a shadow by one of the

05:41:00.240 --> 05:41:00.659
torches.

05:41:00.720 --> 05:41:04.619
He is a sky wing, Kibley thought, and

05:41:04.619 --> 05:41:05.400
looked at Moon.

05:41:05.459 --> 05:41:06.540
Perhaps.

05:41:06.540 --> 05:41:09.779
She lifted her wings in a maybe gesture

05:41:09.779 --> 05:41:11.759
and started working her way over to the

05:41:11.759 --> 05:41:12.720
scarred dragon.

05:41:12.779 --> 05:41:15.779
Tsunami was speaking now, explaining that

05:41:15.779 --> 05:41:17.580
they would catch the culprit and asking

05:41:17.580 --> 05:41:19.200
for anyone with information to come

05:41:19.200 --> 05:41:19.439
forward.

05:41:19.500 --> 05:41:21.659
Moon could just imagine that

05:41:21.659 --> 05:41:22.619
conversation.

05:41:22.680 --> 05:41:25.439
Hello, I have information about the bomb

05:41:25.439 --> 05:41:27.659
which I gathered by listening in on my

05:41:27.659 --> 05:41:29.159
classmates, thoughts, and dreams.

05:41:29.220 --> 05:41:30.360
That's okay, right?

05:41:30.419 --> 05:41:33.180
I didn't see no telepathic spying on your

05:41:33.180 --> 05:41:34.500
friends in the student handbook.

05:41:34.560 --> 05:41:37.139
Although she was trying to move subtly.

05:41:37.200 --> 05:41:39.419
One step every 30 seconds or so.

05:41:39.479 --> 05:41:42.180
Flame swung his head around to glare at

05:41:42.180 --> 05:41:43.500
her when she was still several paces

05:41:43.500 --> 05:41:43.799
away.

05:41:43.860 --> 05:41:46.680
She froze in place and kept her eyes on

05:41:46.680 --> 05:41:48.479
tsunami, checking his mind.

05:41:48.540 --> 05:41:50.939
Did he know she was deliberately getting

05:41:50.939 --> 05:41:51.599
closer to him?

05:41:51.720 --> 05:41:53.759
If he did, she couldn't tell.

05:41:53.819 --> 05:41:56.459
It seemed as if he was just projecting

05:41:56.459 --> 05:41:58.740
hostility at everyone indiscriminately

05:41:58.740 --> 05:42:01.200
and she'd wandered across his field of

05:42:01.200 --> 05:42:01.560
hatred.

05:42:01.619 --> 05:42:04.860
Darkness filled his head like a torrent

05:42:04.860 --> 05:42:05.700
of inky bile.

05:42:05.759 --> 05:42:08.220
She found herself glancing down at her

05:42:08.220 --> 05:42:10.500
talons, half expecting to see black

05:42:10.500 --> 05:42:12.599
stains left there from even brushing the

05:42:12.599 --> 05:42:13.860
surface of Flame's thoughts.

05:42:13.919 --> 05:42:16.740
But will this convince her to come get

05:42:16.740 --> 05:42:16.979
me?

05:42:17.040 --> 05:42:17.880
No, of course not.

05:42:18.000 --> 05:42:20.400
She'd rather leave me with fools and

05:42:20.400 --> 05:42:22.740
killers than take care of me herself, even

05:42:22.740 --> 05:42:25.020
after what the night wings did to me, even

05:42:25.020 --> 05:42:26.340
after what Viper did to me.

05:42:26.400 --> 05:42:28.860
Even after what the talents of peace did

05:42:28.860 --> 05:42:29.159
to me.

05:42:29.279 --> 05:42:31.319
She's the one who's supposed to care

05:42:31.319 --> 05:42:31.860
about me.

05:42:31.919 --> 05:42:33.000
But she doesn't.

05:42:33.060 --> 05:42:33.900
No one does.

05:42:33.959 --> 05:42:35.819
Will she even worry about me when she

05:42:35.819 --> 05:42:36.240
hears?

05:42:36.299 --> 05:42:37.080
Probably not.

05:42:37.139 --> 05:42:39.720
She hates my face as much as I hate my

05:42:39.720 --> 05:42:39.959
face.

05:42:40.020 --> 05:42:42.779
I wish I could rip off every sand wings

05:42:42.779 --> 05:42:44.939
venom barred, and then use them to stab

05:42:44.939 --> 05:42:46.619
all the night wings in their smug

05:42:46.619 --> 05:42:47.400
snouts.

05:42:47.520 --> 05:42:51.119
Moon's stomach hurt, as though she'd

05:42:51.119 --> 05:42:52.500
eaten a tree full of rotting fruit.

05:42:52.560 --> 05:42:56.220
Flames Fury sucked her in and trapped her

05:42:56.220 --> 05:42:57.959
like a beetle in slime.

05:42:58.080 --> 05:43:00.360
She couldn't climb out, and she couldn't

05:43:00.360 --> 05:43:02.700
get clean, and she felt as if all the

05:43:02.700 --> 05:43:04.860
light was being slurped right out of

05:43:04.860 --> 05:43:05.040
her.

05:43:05.099 --> 05:43:06.959
He could be the one.

05:43:07.020 --> 05:43:10.200
His mind went right past Cornelian and

05:43:10.200 --> 05:43:14.099
Bigtail, stupid, half baked, or all baked

05:43:14.099 --> 05:43:15.840
ha, ha, idiot dragons.

05:43:15.900 --> 05:43:17.580
They're lucky they're dead, or else

05:43:17.580 --> 05:43:19.619
they'd be shambling scarred monsters like

05:43:19.619 --> 05:43:19.860
me.

05:43:19.919 --> 05:43:23.580
Without a flicker of pity, sadness, or

05:43:23.580 --> 05:43:27.000
remorse, his loathing was so unrelenting

05:43:27.000 --> 05:43:28.860
that he barely seemed to have room to

05:43:28.860 --> 05:43:31.080
think about the fire itself, either that

05:43:31.080 --> 05:43:32.159
he'd said it or not.

05:43:32.220 --> 05:43:35.580
Moon forced herself to turn toward Kibley

05:43:35.580 --> 05:43:37.740
but he was studying the other dragonettes

05:43:37.740 --> 05:43:39.659
again and didn't notice her anguished

05:43:39.659 --> 05:43:42.959
expression, and then, wound into the

05:43:42.959 --> 05:43:45.119
tangled gloom in flame's head, she heard

05:43:45.119 --> 05:43:46.799
I wish I'd done it.

05:43:46.860 --> 05:43:49.740
Everyone would take me seriously then, but

05:43:49.740 --> 05:43:50.340
I wouldn't hide it.

05:43:50.400 --> 05:43:52.500
I'd roar it to the world.

05:43:52.560 --> 05:43:56.040
So it wasn't him, and she needed to get

05:43:56.040 --> 05:43:57.659
out of his brain before she drowned

05:43:57.659 --> 05:43:57.959
here.

05:43:58.020 --> 05:43:59.459
Help me.

05:43:59.520 --> 05:44:00.479
She whispered.

05:44:00.540 --> 05:44:03.180
See his thoughts as a boulder.

05:44:03.299 --> 05:44:06.479
Not a wall or a river, Dark Stalker

05:44:06.479 --> 05:44:06.720
said.

05:44:06.840 --> 05:44:08.520
Instantly there when she called.

05:44:08.580 --> 05:44:10.979
Believe they are movable first.

05:44:11.040 --> 05:44:14.459
Wrap them into a ball shape, and then

05:44:14.459 --> 05:44:16.979
imagine a slope below them, and push them

05:44:16.979 --> 05:44:17.819
away downhill.

05:44:17.880 --> 05:44:21.659
Moon tried, dragging the sticky dark webs

05:44:21.659 --> 05:44:23.520
off her mind and rolling them up.

05:44:23.580 --> 05:44:26.400
But as she pushed against them, out of

05:44:26.400 --> 05:44:28.919
the corner of her eye, she saw Flame's

05:44:28.919 --> 05:44:29.580
head shoot up.

05:44:29.639 --> 05:44:31.200
Who's there?

05:44:31.259 --> 05:44:32.040
he demanded.

05:44:32.099 --> 05:44:33.119
Who's there?

05:44:33.180 --> 05:44:36.540
And with a ferocious blast of fury, she

05:44:36.540 --> 05:44:38.459
was thrown forcibly out of his mind.

05:44:38.520 --> 05:44:42.959
Chapter 19.

05:44:43.200 --> 05:44:45.419
Don't react.

05:44:45.540 --> 05:44:47.580
Dark Stalker cautioned.

05:44:47.639 --> 05:44:50.340
Moon kept herself still, although she

05:44:50.340 --> 05:44:51.720
felt as if she had been kicked in the

05:44:51.720 --> 05:44:53.939
face, and she wanted to bolt out of the

05:44:53.939 --> 05:44:54.959
hall as fast as she could.

05:44:55.020 --> 05:44:57.479
Flame was glaring about even more

05:44:57.479 --> 05:45:00.119
viciously now, eyeing all the night wings

05:45:00.119 --> 05:45:01.740
with particular suspicion.

05:45:01.799 --> 05:45:03.360
How did he know?

05:45:03.419 --> 05:45:06.060
She cried frantically to dark stalker.

05:45:06.119 --> 05:45:07.740
I've never seen anyone do that.

05:45:07.799 --> 05:45:09.779
How could he notice that I was there?

05:45:09.840 --> 05:45:12.599
I don't think he knew exactly what was

05:45:12.599 --> 05:45:13.080
happening?

05:45:13.139 --> 05:45:14.580
Dark Stalker said.

05:45:14.639 --> 05:45:17.159
I don't want to risk probing deeper while

05:45:17.159 --> 05:45:18.240
he's on the defensive like that.

05:45:18.299 --> 05:45:22.319
But I suspect he just felt a presence

05:45:22.319 --> 05:45:22.919
let's say.

05:45:23.040 --> 05:45:25.500
He can't be short was a mind reader

05:45:25.500 --> 05:45:27.479
especially if you stay calm.

05:45:27.599 --> 05:45:30.479
Moon wasn't quite sure how to accomplish

05:45:30.479 --> 05:45:30.720
that.

05:45:30.779 --> 05:45:34.139
No one in this entire cave was calm, but

05:45:34.139 --> 05:45:36.360
to her relief, a moment later, Sonny

05:45:36.360 --> 05:45:38.580
announced, that's all we had to say.

05:45:38.639 --> 05:45:40.979
Please come see us if you feel like you

05:45:40.979 --> 05:45:42.840
want to leave, or if you have any

05:45:42.840 --> 05:45:43.560
questions.

05:45:43.560 --> 05:45:46.560
There are no classes today, but we're all

05:45:46.560 --> 05:45:48.180
here to take groups out hunting or

05:45:48.180 --> 05:45:50.580
swimming or flying, and the art and music

05:45:50.580 --> 05:45:51.659
caves are both open.

05:45:51.720 --> 05:45:53.700
We'll let you know what we decide about

05:45:53.700 --> 05:45:54.240
tomorrow.

05:45:54.299 --> 05:45:57.299
She turned to Clay, and the students

05:45:57.299 --> 05:45:59.340
became a milling mob of whispers and

05:45:59.340 --> 05:45:59.939
flashing teeth.

05:46:00.000 --> 05:46:02.639
Moon was able to slip away from flame and

05:46:02.639 --> 05:46:03.360
find Kibley.

05:46:03.419 --> 05:46:04.919
Are you all right?

05:46:04.979 --> 05:46:06.419
He asked immediately.

05:46:06.479 --> 05:46:08.279
Ducking his head to study her face.

05:46:08.340 --> 05:46:11.220
He steered her into a corner, carefully

05:46:11.220 --> 05:46:13.560
not touching her, and spread his wings to

05:46:13.560 --> 05:46:14.939
shield her from the other dragons.

05:46:15.000 --> 05:46:17.580
It didn't stop the stampede of worries

05:46:17.580 --> 05:46:19.619
rumors, and complaints from trampling

05:46:19.619 --> 05:46:20.279
through her head though.

05:46:20.340 --> 05:46:22.680
She couldn't focus, couldn't block

05:46:22.680 --> 05:46:23.159
anything out.

05:46:23.220 --> 05:46:25.979
She was too shaken by flame's attack.

05:46:26.040 --> 05:46:28.560
Kibley's own mind was already speeding

05:46:28.560 --> 05:46:28.799
forward.

05:46:28.919 --> 05:46:31.740
I wonder if reading minds is tiring.

05:46:31.799 --> 05:46:33.959
Is it an infinite resource?

05:46:34.020 --> 05:46:36.240
Or is it a power that drains as she uses

05:46:36.240 --> 05:46:36.419
it?

05:46:36.479 --> 05:46:38.700
Or is it more like a muscle that gets

05:46:38.700 --> 05:46:40.439
stronger the more she exercises it?

05:46:40.500 --> 05:46:42.720
Sure wish I'd had a skill like that when

05:46:42.720 --> 05:46:43.500
I was living at home.

05:46:43.500 --> 05:46:45.779
Could have dodged a few more attacks from

05:46:45.779 --> 05:46:47.099
Sarocco and Rattlesnake.

05:46:47.159 --> 05:46:49.139
Maybe could have figured out how to make

05:46:49.139 --> 05:46:49.860
mum like me.

05:46:49.919 --> 05:46:52.560
Moon looks like she's been slammed into a

05:46:52.560 --> 05:46:52.979
mountain.

05:46:53.040 --> 05:46:55.619
You look tired.

05:46:55.680 --> 05:46:57.419
He said diplomatically.

05:46:57.479 --> 05:47:00.659
I just had a weird experience in flame's

05:47:00.659 --> 05:47:02.580
head, she said in a low voice.

05:47:02.639 --> 05:47:04.500
It's horrible in there.

05:47:04.560 --> 05:47:06.360
So he did it?

05:47:06.479 --> 05:47:07.680
Kibley asked.

05:47:07.740 --> 05:47:09.659
His tail flicked up into a stabbing

05:47:09.659 --> 05:47:12.240
position, and his brain went, did he

05:47:12.240 --> 05:47:14.340
bring the cactus from the Sky Kingdom, or

05:47:14.340 --> 05:47:16.020
find it somewhere near Jade Mountain?

05:47:16.080 --> 05:47:17.759
And how long has he been planning this?

05:47:17.819 --> 05:47:19.740
And how did Scarlet choose him?

05:47:19.799 --> 05:47:22.500
And, no, no, stop, Moon said.

05:47:22.560 --> 05:47:23.759
I don't think it was him.

05:47:23.880 --> 05:47:25.500
I don't think it was any of them.

05:47:25.619 --> 05:47:27.720
Pike, Icicle Flame.

05:47:27.779 --> 05:47:29.220
They were all thinking about the fire

05:47:29.220 --> 05:47:30.540
like someone else did it.

05:47:30.659 --> 05:47:32.819
Camel farts.

05:47:32.880 --> 05:47:34.080
Kibley cursed.

05:47:34.139 --> 05:47:35.939
They all seem like perfect suspects.

05:47:36.060 --> 05:47:38.220
Yes, Moon agreed.

05:47:38.279 --> 05:47:40.619
They may all still do something terrible

05:47:40.619 --> 05:47:42.060
just not this particular thing.

05:47:42.119 --> 05:47:43.860
He squinted at her.

05:47:43.919 --> 05:47:45.779
Was that a prophecy?

05:47:45.840 --> 05:47:47.279
Did you have visions of them?

05:47:47.340 --> 05:47:48.599
She shook her head.

05:47:48.659 --> 05:47:50.279
Just guessing.

05:47:50.340 --> 05:47:52.860
Kibley swiveled his head around to watch

05:47:52.860 --> 05:47:55.259
icicle parading out of the hall with the

05:47:55.259 --> 05:47:56.700
other ice wings trailing behind her.

05:47:56.759 --> 05:48:01.200
If you know that, he said thoughtfully, if

05:48:01.200 --> 05:48:02.880
you had a list of the dragons with the

05:48:02.880 --> 05:48:05.099
darkest thoughts, you could keep track of

05:48:05.099 --> 05:48:06.959
them, you could check their minds every

05:48:06.959 --> 05:48:08.819
day and catch them if they're planning

05:48:08.819 --> 05:48:10.919
something, you'd know who to keep an eye

05:48:10.919 --> 05:48:11.220
on.

05:48:11.279 --> 05:48:15.000
Like Thorn's potential enemies list, but

05:48:15.000 --> 05:48:16.979
even more targeted, with more inside

05:48:16.979 --> 05:48:18.720
information, he mused.

05:48:18.779 --> 05:48:22.979
That, um, moon started, then hesitated.

05:48:23.040 --> 05:48:25.740
She didn't want to argue with him when he

05:48:25.740 --> 05:48:27.180
was starting to see her power in a

05:48:27.180 --> 05:48:30.659
positive light, but that seems kind of

05:48:30.659 --> 05:48:31.560
wrong, doesn't it?

05:48:31.619 --> 05:48:32.639
She admitted.

05:48:32.700 --> 05:48:35.159
I mean, judging dragons by their dark

05:48:35.159 --> 05:48:35.700
thoughts.

05:48:35.759 --> 05:48:38.279
And using that to justify spying on

05:48:38.279 --> 05:48:38.520
them.

05:48:38.580 --> 05:48:41.040
Lots of dragons think dark things

05:48:41.040 --> 05:48:41.580
sometimes.

05:48:41.639 --> 05:48:43.619
It doesn't mean they'll ever actually do

05:48:43.619 --> 05:48:44.220
them.

05:48:44.279 --> 05:48:46.319
Almost half the night wings in the

05:48:46.319 --> 05:48:48.360
rainforest had an occasional fantasy

05:48:48.360 --> 05:48:50.639
about killing glory and stealing the

05:48:50.639 --> 05:48:53.279
throne, but most of the time, they're

05:48:53.279 --> 05:48:54.599
just grateful to be alive and fed.

05:48:54.720 --> 05:48:57.599
I don't know I guess I don't like to

05:48:57.599 --> 05:48:59.700
think of myself as sneaking around in

05:48:59.700 --> 05:49:00.659
dragons heads.

05:49:00.720 --> 05:49:03.720
I can't help what I hear, but it doesn't

05:49:03.720 --> 05:49:04.680
seem fair to do it on purpose.

05:49:04.799 --> 05:49:08.220
I mean, unless we're catching a murderer

05:49:08.220 --> 05:49:08.700
like now.

05:49:08.759 --> 05:49:11.520
Hmm, he said.

05:49:11.580 --> 05:49:13.380
But before his thoughts could swoop off

05:49:13.380 --> 05:49:15.360
on that tangent, he shook his head and

05:49:15.360 --> 05:49:15.840
stepped back.

05:49:15.900 --> 05:49:17.819
Let's go find onyx.

05:49:17.880 --> 05:49:19.919
She seems like the best suspect we have

05:49:19.919 --> 05:49:20.159
left.

05:49:20.220 --> 05:49:23.099
But I won't be able to hear her thoughts

05:49:23.099 --> 05:49:24.060
Moon said.

05:49:24.119 --> 05:49:25.860
How will we learn anything from her?

05:49:25.919 --> 05:49:27.419
He grinned.

05:49:27.479 --> 05:49:30.060
The old-fashioned way, with our eyes and

05:49:30.060 --> 05:49:30.479
ears.

05:49:30.540 --> 05:49:33.900
That sounded alarming and inefficient to

05:49:33.900 --> 05:49:36.180
moon, but she followed him warily to the

05:49:36.180 --> 05:49:37.919
cave opening where most of the

05:49:37.919 --> 05:49:38.819
dragonettes had gone.

05:49:38.880 --> 05:49:41.279
Everyone seemed to want to be out in the

05:49:41.279 --> 05:49:41.819
light.

05:49:41.819 --> 05:49:43.860
It felt sort of inappropriate, how

05:49:43.860 --> 05:49:46.439
gorgeous and sunny it was outside, an

05:49:46.439 --> 05:49:48.060
early morning, full of whistling bird

05:49:48.060 --> 05:49:50.220
song, and humming bumblebees among the

05:49:50.220 --> 05:49:51.240
purple mountain flowers.

05:49:51.299 --> 05:49:54.479
Moon noticed that most of the dragonets

05:49:54.479 --> 05:49:56.159
were staying in clumps with others from

05:49:56.159 --> 05:49:57.240
their own tribes.

05:49:57.299 --> 05:49:59.279
Flame had slithered back into the

05:49:59.279 --> 05:50:01.799
mountain, but the other 3 Sky Wings took

05:50:01.799 --> 05:50:03.720
to the air together, beating their huge

05:50:03.720 --> 05:50:05.639
wings and soaring as high as they could.

05:50:05.700 --> 05:50:09.419
She saw coconut, and 2 subdued rain wings

05:50:09.419 --> 05:50:12.119
find a large swath of sunlit grass and

05:50:12.119 --> 05:50:13.860
lie down, spreading their wings.

05:50:13.919 --> 05:50:16.979
Umber and marsh had gone to check on Sora

05:50:16.979 --> 05:50:19.080
but the other 2 mud wings were tramping

05:50:19.080 --> 05:50:21.060
down the mountain together, looking for a

05:50:21.060 --> 05:50:21.840
cool muddy spot.

05:50:21.900 --> 05:50:24.540
She wondered where all the night wings

05:50:24.540 --> 05:50:25.680
had disappeared to so quickly.

05:50:25.799 --> 05:50:28.259
They wouldn't want her with them anyway

05:50:28.259 --> 05:50:30.119
but did they have a secret place in the

05:50:30.119 --> 05:50:31.560
mountain where they all went together?

05:50:31.680 --> 05:50:33.119
somewhere she didn't know about.

05:50:33.180 --> 05:50:37.139
So much for our winglets, Kibley said.

05:50:37.200 --> 05:50:39.900
It's only been a couple of days, Moon

05:50:39.900 --> 05:50:40.319
said.

05:50:40.380 --> 05:50:41.459
It was true.

05:50:41.520 --> 05:50:43.500
She felt as though she'd been here for

05:50:43.500 --> 05:50:46.020
months, but really, she'd stood right

05:50:46.020 --> 05:50:47.759
here with her mother barely 4 days ago.

05:50:47.819 --> 05:50:50.400
Maybe the winglets will stick together

05:50:50.400 --> 05:50:52.020
more once we all know each other better.

05:50:52.080 --> 05:50:56.040
Anemone pushed past them, leading turtle

05:50:56.040 --> 05:50:57.419
pike, and the other sea wings.

05:50:57.479 --> 05:50:59.759
She cast an arch look around at the other

05:50:59.759 --> 05:51:00.540
dragonettes.

05:51:00.599 --> 05:51:03.720
I could find out who did it in 2 shakes

05:51:03.720 --> 05:51:06.720
of my tail, she thought indignantly, but

05:51:06.720 --> 05:51:07.860
tsunami won't let me.

05:51:07.919 --> 05:51:10.139
Shouldn't use my powers.

05:51:10.200 --> 05:51:11.340
When it's something important like this?

05:51:11.459 --> 05:51:14.099
She shook out her wings and tossed her

05:51:14.099 --> 05:51:14.279
head.

05:51:14.340 --> 05:51:16.560
Maybe she'll change her mind by the time

05:51:16.560 --> 05:51:17.099
we get back.

05:51:17.159 --> 05:51:19.740
Are you sure this is safe?

05:51:19.799 --> 05:51:21.119
Pikeaster.

05:51:21.180 --> 05:51:22.740
Going to the lake, you could be

05:51:22.740 --> 05:51:23.159
attacked.

05:51:23.220 --> 05:51:25.979
Not with all of you strapping dragons

05:51:25.979 --> 05:51:26.880
along to defend me.

05:51:27.000 --> 05:51:29.700
Anemone said, shooting him a smile.

05:51:29.759 --> 05:51:32.099
Ha, she thought to herself.

05:51:32.159 --> 05:51:34.319
I'm more dangerous than any of you if I

05:51:34.319 --> 05:51:34.680
have to be.

05:51:34.799 --> 05:51:37.740
Her mind flashed to an image of her own

05:51:37.740 --> 05:51:40.259
claws holding a spear, then a dragon

05:51:40.259 --> 05:51:42.119
disappearing in a cloud of bubbles and

05:51:42.119 --> 05:51:43.259
slithering green shapes.

05:51:43.319 --> 05:51:45.659
She shuddered, and forced her thoughts

05:51:45.659 --> 05:51:46.860
back to the mountain skies.

05:51:46.919 --> 05:51:48.779
Come on, let's go.

05:51:48.900 --> 05:51:52.259
Moon watched them soar away, and wondered

05:51:52.259 --> 05:51:53.580
what anemone was capable of.

05:51:53.639 --> 05:51:56.639
Beside her, Kibli was thinking the same

05:51:56.639 --> 05:51:59.040
thing about turtle, but he turned instead

05:51:59.040 --> 05:52:00.959
toward the clomb of sand wings who had

05:52:00.959 --> 05:52:03.240
found a stretch of flat gray boulders and

05:52:03.240 --> 05:52:04.740
were baking their scales in the sun.

05:52:04.799 --> 05:52:07.439
Sprawled comfortably in the middle of

05:52:07.439 --> 05:52:10.139
them was onyx, whose black forked tongue

05:52:10.139 --> 05:52:12.779
kept flicking in and out. seeing her with

05:52:12.779 --> 05:52:13.200
all the others.

05:52:13.259 --> 05:52:16.139
It was clear how much older, and bigger

05:52:16.139 --> 05:52:16.560
she was.

05:52:16.619 --> 05:52:19.740
She was no dragonette, Moon couldn't

05:52:19.740 --> 05:52:20.520
understand why she was here.

05:52:20.580 --> 05:52:24.599
The littlest sandwing, Anemones clawmate

05:52:24.599 --> 05:52:27.060
saw Kibley and Moon approaching, and her

05:52:27.060 --> 05:52:27.900
whole face lit up.

05:52:27.959 --> 05:52:30.840
Moon realized she was the one Kibley had

05:52:30.840 --> 05:52:31.919
been talking to on the 1st day.

05:52:31.979 --> 05:52:34.619
Kimley, she cried.

05:52:34.680 --> 05:52:35.400
Are you going home?

05:52:35.459 --> 05:52:36.419
I might go home.

05:52:36.479 --> 05:52:38.520
Do you think father or thorn would be mad

05:52:38.520 --> 05:52:39.000
if I went home?

05:52:39.060 --> 05:52:41.880
They'd be happy to see you, Ostrich.

05:52:41.939 --> 05:52:44.580
Kibley said, with extra gentleness in his

05:52:44.580 --> 05:52:44.700
voice.

05:52:44.819 --> 05:52:47.700
They want you to feel safe, but I

05:52:47.700 --> 05:52:49.979
promised to protect you, and I will.

05:52:50.040 --> 05:52:51.900
So remember, you are safe here too.

05:52:51.959 --> 05:52:52.919
It's up to you.

05:52:52.979 --> 05:52:56.220
I do feel better now that you're here, she

05:52:56.220 --> 05:52:56.459
said.

05:52:56.520 --> 05:52:58.799
He reached one of his wings around her

05:52:58.799 --> 05:53:00.060
and she leaned into his shoulder.

05:53:00.119 --> 05:53:03.299
Why you've got a night wing stuck to your

05:53:03.299 --> 05:53:03.599
tail?

05:53:03.659 --> 05:53:05.939
One of the other sand wings asked.

05:53:06.000 --> 05:53:08.340
The question didn't sound friendly, but

05:53:08.340 --> 05:53:09.900
his mind was more curious than hostile.

05:53:09.959 --> 05:53:12.479
The primary impression Moon got from all

05:53:12.479 --> 05:53:14.939
of them was that if Kibley decided to do

05:53:14.939 --> 05:53:16.919
something, it was probably a good idea.

05:53:16.979 --> 05:53:19.619
They all had him closely linked to Queen

05:53:19.619 --> 05:53:22.139
Thorn in their minds, and even the 2 that

05:53:22.139 --> 05:53:24.540
hadn't been out claws before, were deeply

05:53:24.540 --> 05:53:26.520
respectful of her and anyone associated

05:53:26.520 --> 05:53:26.880
with her.

05:53:26.939 --> 05:53:30.959
She's in my winglet, Kibley said, as if

05:53:30.959 --> 05:53:31.740
that made this normal.

05:53:31.799 --> 05:53:34.139
Everyone, this is Moon.

05:53:34.200 --> 05:53:37.740
They all nodded, even onyx, and ostrich

05:53:37.740 --> 05:53:40.259
said, I like the silver scales by your

05:53:40.259 --> 05:53:40.560
eyes.

05:53:40.619 --> 05:53:42.240
They're not diamonds, are they?

05:53:42.299 --> 05:53:45.060
I wish I had some treasure, or scales

05:53:45.060 --> 05:53:46.200
that looked like treasure.

05:53:46.259 --> 05:53:47.159
They're pretty.

05:53:47.220 --> 05:53:50.880
Moon managed a smile, wishing she could

05:53:50.880 --> 05:53:52.860
pull ferns over her head and hide from

05:53:52.860 --> 05:53:53.939
all their dark stairs.

05:53:54.000 --> 05:53:56.819
But after a minute, the sand wings mostly

05:53:56.819 --> 05:53:57.720
stopped thinking about her.

05:53:57.779 --> 05:54:00.299
Their thoughts were all, what's going to

05:54:00.299 --> 05:54:02.279
happen to me, and what's everyone else

05:54:02.279 --> 05:54:02.939
going to do?

05:54:03.000 --> 05:54:05.639
And if I leave, will the others think I'm

05:54:05.639 --> 05:54:06.119
a coward?

05:54:06.180 --> 05:54:08.279
If I stay, will they think I'm an idiot?

05:54:08.340 --> 05:54:11.340
Moon curled herself as small as she could

05:54:11.340 --> 05:54:13.380
on one of the boulders, feeling the heat

05:54:13.380 --> 05:54:15.540
from the sand wings scales in addition to

05:54:15.540 --> 05:54:15.840
the sun.

05:54:15.900 --> 05:54:18.419
Will you go back to the stronghold

05:54:18.419 --> 05:54:18.840
Kibley?

05:54:18.900 --> 05:54:19.740
One of them asked.

05:54:19.860 --> 05:54:21.779
No, he said.

05:54:21.840 --> 05:54:24.240
Thorn sent me here to learn, and I know

05:54:24.240 --> 05:54:25.020
she'd want me to stay.

05:54:25.080 --> 05:54:28.439
Just a few words, and instantly the

05:54:28.439 --> 05:54:30.959
others were all thinking, yes, stay.

05:54:31.080 --> 05:54:31.799
I should stay.

05:54:31.860 --> 05:54:32.700
He's right.

05:54:32.759 --> 05:54:33.900
Thorn would want that.

05:54:33.959 --> 05:54:36.779
Moon wished she could have even a quarter

05:54:36.779 --> 05:54:38.220
of that effect on other dragons.

05:54:38.279 --> 05:54:40.500
What about you, Onyx?

05:54:40.560 --> 05:54:41.580
Kibley asked her.

05:54:41.639 --> 05:54:43.740
Where would you be going back to if you

05:54:43.740 --> 05:54:43.979
left?

05:54:44.099 --> 05:54:46.740
She narrowed her black eyes at him.

05:54:46.799 --> 05:54:50.159
That quiet, fuzzy hum surrounded her, like

05:54:50.159 --> 05:54:52.319
what listening to fog would be like if it

05:54:52.319 --> 05:54:53.159
were turned into sound.

05:54:53.220 --> 05:54:55.619
Moonfolded her front talons together

05:54:55.619 --> 05:54:56.880
unsettled.

05:54:56.939 --> 05:54:59.400
What was going on in Onyx's head?

05:54:59.459 --> 05:55:01.380
How was she blocking moons so

05:55:01.380 --> 05:55:01.799
completely?

05:55:01.860 --> 05:55:03.659
And me?

05:55:03.720 --> 05:55:06.180
Dark Stalker reminded her quietly.

05:55:06.240 --> 05:55:08.819
I didn't grow up in one of those big

05:55:08.819 --> 05:55:10.860
oases, if that's what you're asking.

05:55:10.919 --> 05:55:12.119
Onyx said.

05:55:12.180 --> 05:55:14.400
It was just me and my mother, roaming the

05:55:14.400 --> 05:55:16.680
desert, and she's dead now, which is why

05:55:16.680 --> 05:55:17.580
I applied to come here.

05:55:17.639 --> 05:55:19.080
I have nowhere else to go.

05:55:19.139 --> 05:55:20.880
But it doesn't matter because I'm

05:55:20.880 --> 05:55:21.119
staying.

05:55:21.180 --> 05:55:23.880
Just her and her mother?

05:55:23.939 --> 05:55:24.779
Moon thought.

05:55:24.840 --> 05:55:27.779
Kind of like me, except she had her

05:55:27.779 --> 05:55:30.419
mother all the time, not just in snatches

05:55:30.419 --> 05:55:32.400
here and there, she was never alone.

05:55:32.459 --> 05:55:34.860
Did you fight in the war?

05:55:34.979 --> 05:55:35.880
Kibley asked.

05:55:35.939 --> 05:55:37.139
Did you?

05:55:37.200 --> 05:55:38.939
Onyx shot back.

05:55:39.000 --> 05:55:41.880
In a way, he said, for Thorn and the out

05:55:41.880 --> 05:55:42.779
claws.

05:55:42.840 --> 05:55:45.180
She flicked her tongue out in.

05:55:45.240 --> 05:55:47.819
I chose not to choose a side.

05:55:47.880 --> 05:55:49.740
None of those dragons were fit to be

05:55:49.740 --> 05:55:50.279
queen.

05:55:50.340 --> 05:55:53.939
The 2 non-outlaw dragons both had unhappy

05:55:53.939 --> 05:55:55.680
rippling reactions to that comment.

05:55:55.740 --> 05:56:00.000
Blaze wasn't so bad, and perhaps not a

05:56:00.000 --> 05:56:01.799
good queen, but Byrne would have been a

05:56:01.799 --> 05:56:02.279
strong queen.

05:56:02.340 --> 05:56:06.060
Then both thought, thank the moons it's

05:56:06.060 --> 05:56:06.540
thorn instead.

05:56:06.599 --> 05:56:09.479
Wow, Kibley said.

05:56:09.540 --> 05:56:11.939
I'm amazed you were able to avoid Burns

05:56:11.939 --> 05:56:13.200
soldiers for so long.

05:56:13.259 --> 05:56:14.340
What are you?

05:56:14.400 --> 05:56:15.119
20 years old?

05:56:15.180 --> 05:56:17.459
And without hiding in the scorpion den

05:56:17.459 --> 05:56:17.819
either.

05:56:17.880 --> 05:56:19.500
At least, I don't remember you being

05:56:19.500 --> 05:56:19.740
there.

05:56:19.799 --> 05:56:22.439
19, Onyx said.

05:56:22.500 --> 05:56:24.720
And no, we stayed away from the Scorpion

05:56:24.720 --> 05:56:25.319
den too.

05:56:25.380 --> 05:56:27.900
Your mother wasn't a fan of other

05:56:27.900 --> 05:56:28.619
dragons.

05:56:28.680 --> 05:56:30.119
Kibley joked lightly.

05:56:30.180 --> 05:56:31.979
He was trying to figure out whether to

05:56:31.979 --> 05:56:34.319
ask if they had had help, perhaps from

05:56:34.319 --> 05:56:36.900
Queen Scarlet, but in a way that wouldn't

05:56:36.900 --> 05:56:39.119
make her even more suspicious, but he

05:56:39.119 --> 05:56:40.080
could tell that she was already

05:56:40.080 --> 05:56:40.799
displeased.

05:56:40.860 --> 05:56:43.500
Questions in general clearly weren't her

05:56:43.500 --> 05:56:44.220
favorite thing.

05:56:44.279 --> 05:56:46.799
That's right, Onyx said.

05:56:46.860 --> 05:56:50.819
Your diamonds are so cool, ostrich said.

05:56:50.880 --> 05:56:52.799
Did it hurt to get them set between your

05:56:52.799 --> 05:56:53.459
scales like that?

05:56:53.520 --> 05:56:57.360
Onyx blinked, and Moon saw that ostrich

05:56:57.360 --> 05:56:59.639
was deliberately disarming her, the

05:56:59.639 --> 05:57:02.220
little sand wing was young, but smart, and

05:57:02.220 --> 05:57:04.020
although she wasn't sure what Kibley was

05:57:04.020 --> 05:57:06.119
fishing for, she instinctively knew how

05:57:06.119 --> 05:57:07.979
to help him get past the surly older

05:57:07.979 --> 05:57:09.119
dragon's defenses.

05:57:09.180 --> 05:57:13.619
Yes, Onyx said, stretching out one wing

05:57:13.619 --> 05:57:15.659
so the small black diamonds could catch

05:57:15.659 --> 05:57:18.180
the sun, winking and sparkling between

05:57:18.180 --> 05:57:19.200
her yellow scales.

05:57:19.259 --> 05:57:21.060
But that is half the point.

05:57:21.119 --> 05:57:23.639
If I could enjoy that much pain just for

05:57:23.639 --> 05:57:25.860
a little beauty, imagine how much I could

05:57:25.860 --> 05:57:27.720
handle in a battle or for my own

05:57:27.720 --> 05:57:28.139
survival.

05:57:28.200 --> 05:57:31.020
I think the most beautiful things should

05:57:31.020 --> 05:57:31.919
also be frightening.

05:57:31.979 --> 05:57:35.400
Kimberly shot Moon a look, but before he

05:57:35.400 --> 05:57:37.560
could say anything, Ostrich leaned

05:57:37.560 --> 05:57:39.479
forward and peered at Onyx's amulet.

05:57:39.540 --> 05:57:41.220
And what's that?

05:57:41.279 --> 05:57:42.360
She asked.

05:57:42.419 --> 05:57:44.040
Genuinely curious now?

05:57:44.099 --> 05:57:45.659
Does it mean something?

05:57:45.720 --> 05:57:47.040
Yes.

05:57:47.099 --> 05:57:49.860
Onyx wrapped her claws around the amulet

05:57:49.860 --> 05:57:52.319
paused, and then flipped a catch to

05:57:52.319 --> 05:57:53.400
reveal that it opened up.

05:57:53.459 --> 05:57:56.279
Inside was a twisted hunk of black rock.

05:57:56.340 --> 05:57:59.040
Bound to the amulet with copper wires.

05:57:59.099 --> 05:58:01.439
This is a piece of the rock that killed

05:58:01.439 --> 05:58:01.860
my mother.

05:58:01.919 --> 05:58:05.520
The other sandwings gasped, and Onyx

05:58:05.520 --> 05:58:06.659
smirked at their expressions.

05:58:06.720 --> 05:58:09.060
Oh, I didn't do it. she said.

05:58:09.119 --> 05:58:11.279
None of the other dragons had had that

05:58:11.279 --> 05:58:12.840
thought, but now they all did.

05:58:12.959 --> 05:58:15.180
No, Onyx went on.

05:58:15.240 --> 05:58:17.159
This rock just fell from the sky one

05:58:17.159 --> 05:58:17.400
night.

05:58:17.459 --> 05:58:20.220
It went straight through her head, leaving

05:58:20.220 --> 05:58:22.080
a burning hole behind and over she went.

05:58:22.139 --> 05:58:25.380
That's when I thought, well, time to join

05:58:25.380 --> 05:58:25.740
the world.

05:58:25.860 --> 05:58:28.860
She snapped the locket shut, making

05:58:28.860 --> 05:58:29.819
ostrich jump.

05:58:29.880 --> 05:58:32.340
Beautiful and frightening.

05:58:32.400 --> 05:58:33.240
Don't you agree?

05:58:33.299 --> 05:58:35.580
Can I see it?

05:58:35.639 --> 05:58:36.840
Ostrich whispered.

05:58:36.959 --> 05:58:39.720
Onyx turned the amulet between her claws

05:58:39.720 --> 05:58:41.759
for a moment, then lifted it off her neck

05:58:41.759 --> 05:58:44.279
just for a moment, she said.

05:58:44.340 --> 05:58:46.139
I think it came from the comet.

05:58:46.200 --> 05:58:48.299
You remember the one in the sky when the

05:58:48.299 --> 05:58:48.900
war ended?

05:58:48.959 --> 05:58:50.759
The false brightest night?

05:58:51.000 --> 05:58:52.439
It was up there when the rock fell.

05:58:52.500 --> 05:58:55.020
So I call it Skyfire.

05:58:55.080 --> 05:58:57.959
She dropped the Amulet into Ostrich's

05:58:57.959 --> 05:59:00.900
Talons, and suddenly, out of the blue

05:59:00.900 --> 05:59:03.119
there was a new voice in Moon's head.

05:59:03.240 --> 05:59:04.560
That's right.

05:59:04.619 --> 05:59:06.299
Admire me.

05:59:06.360 --> 05:59:08.040
Fear me, wonder about me.

05:59:08.099 --> 05:59:11.580
You all have no idea who I am or what

05:59:11.580 --> 05:59:12.479
I'll be one day.

05:59:12.540 --> 05:59:14.279
One day soon.

05:59:14.340 --> 05:59:16.380
No more hiding mother.

05:59:16.439 --> 05:59:18.299
I make the decisions now.

05:59:18.360 --> 05:59:22.139
At the same moment, ostrich's thoughts

05:59:22.139 --> 05:59:22.619
vanished.

05:59:22.680 --> 05:59:24.599
The only thing Moon could hear from the

05:59:24.599 --> 05:59:26.580
little sand wing was that quiet

05:59:26.580 --> 05:59:27.540
shimmering hum.

05:59:27.659 --> 05:59:31.319
Moon stared at onyx, then at the amulet

05:59:31.319 --> 05:59:33.419
which lay open in ostrich's talons.

05:59:33.479 --> 05:59:36.180
The black rock glittered at her like the

05:59:36.180 --> 05:59:37.860
dark heart of a faraway star.

05:59:37.919 --> 05:59:39.180
That was it.

05:59:39.240 --> 05:59:41.939
That was why she couldn't read onyx.

05:59:42.000 --> 05:59:43.619
It was the Skyfire.

05:59:43.680 --> 05:59:47.759
Chapter 20.

05:59:48.060 --> 05:59:52.139
Moon had no time to react before Dark

05:59:52.139 --> 05:59:54.479
Stalker was there in her mind, louder and

05:59:54.479 --> 05:59:56.220
fiercer than he'd ever been before.

05:59:56.279 --> 05:59:58.680
Do not tell anyone about this.

05:59:58.799 --> 06:00:00.119
You understand?

06:00:00.180 --> 06:00:02.520
A stone from the sky, they can block a

06:00:02.520 --> 06:00:03.540
mind reader's powers.

06:00:03.599 --> 06:00:06.000
If other dragons find out, we'll be

06:00:06.000 --> 06:00:06.360
ruined.

06:00:06.479 --> 06:00:09.119
Everyone will get one, and then we'll be

06:00:09.119 --> 06:00:09.959
deaf, Moon.

06:00:10.020 --> 06:00:10.979
Do you understand?

06:00:11.040 --> 06:00:14.040
If this gets out, it'll be like ripping

06:00:14.040 --> 06:00:15.419
our claws off.

06:00:15.479 --> 06:00:17.099
Promise me you won't tell anyone.

06:00:17.159 --> 06:00:20.759
We wouldn't be deaf, she thought back.

06:00:20.819 --> 06:00:22.860
We'd be no worse off than all the normal

06:00:22.860 --> 06:00:23.700
dragons out there.

06:00:23.759 --> 06:00:27.119
If you could give up this gift so easily

06:00:27.119 --> 06:00:28.439
then you shouldn't be allowed to have

06:00:28.439 --> 06:00:28.680
it.

06:00:28.740 --> 06:00:31.680
Moon was flustered by his intensity.

06:00:31.740 --> 06:00:33.720
Shush for a minute, will you?

06:00:33.779 --> 06:00:36.240
This is my one chance to hear what Onyx

06:00:36.240 --> 06:00:36.659
is thinking.

06:00:36.720 --> 06:00:40.080
Dark Stalker subsided, muttering.

06:00:40.139 --> 06:00:43.200
Ostrich was still holding the amulet, all

06:00:43.200 --> 06:00:45.419
her thoughts fuzzed out as she gently

06:00:45.419 --> 06:00:46.500
poked the rock inside.

06:00:46.619 --> 06:00:49.259
If they wanted to find out whether onyx

06:00:49.259 --> 06:00:51.060
had set the bomb, they had to make her

06:00:51.060 --> 06:00:52.020
think about it right now.

06:00:52.080 --> 06:00:55.139
Of course, Kibley had no way of knowing

06:00:55.139 --> 06:00:55.259
that.

06:00:55.319 --> 06:00:58.380
He was busy contemplating Onyx's

06:00:58.380 --> 06:01:00.180
dragonette hood with her mother and

06:01:00.180 --> 06:01:01.740
trying to figure out why she was here.

06:01:01.799 --> 06:01:04.380
He didn't even look up when Moon subtly

06:01:04.380 --> 06:01:05.580
tried to catch his attention.

06:01:05.639 --> 06:01:07.200
She'd have to do this herself.

06:01:07.259 --> 06:01:10.139
Um, Moon blurted.

06:01:10.200 --> 06:01:14.639
What do, hoodoo, have you, uh, the sand

06:01:14.639 --> 06:01:16.319
wings all swiveled their heads to stare

06:01:16.319 --> 06:01:16.860
at her?

06:01:16.919 --> 06:01:18.419
What is she trying to say?

06:01:18.479 --> 06:01:20.580
Weird, crazy nightwing?

06:01:20.639 --> 06:01:22.439
I heard that she can barely form

06:01:22.439 --> 06:01:23.099
sentences.

06:01:23.159 --> 06:01:23.880
Guess that's true.

06:01:24.000 --> 06:01:25.799
She tried not to listen.

06:01:25.860 --> 06:01:27.540
She tried not to think about running

06:01:27.540 --> 06:01:28.139
away.

06:01:28.200 --> 06:01:30.240
And then the right question came to her.

06:01:30.299 --> 06:01:32.459
How's Tamarin?

06:01:32.520 --> 06:01:33.720
She managed at last.

06:01:33.779 --> 06:01:37.080
Have have have you been to see her?

06:01:37.139 --> 06:01:42.119
Oh, my poor little clawmate, Onyx said

06:01:42.119 --> 06:01:42.779
with a sigh.

06:01:42.840 --> 06:01:45.720
At the same time, her mind went, I don't

06:01:45.720 --> 06:01:47.759
see why I have to care about dragons from

06:01:47.759 --> 06:01:50.040
other tribes, but it seems to be expected

06:01:50.040 --> 06:01:50.759
for some reason.

06:01:50.759 --> 06:01:53.580
At least Tamron was a quiet, agreeable

06:01:53.580 --> 06:01:54.900
dragon to share a cave with.

06:01:54.959 --> 06:01:57.659
She didn't snore like mother, or tell

06:01:57.659 --> 06:02:00.540
weepy stories and expect me to care, like

06:02:00.540 --> 06:02:01.020
mother.

06:02:01.080 --> 06:02:02.159
Ugh.

06:02:02.220 --> 06:02:03.540
I hope they don't give me another

06:02:03.540 --> 06:02:04.200
clawmate.

06:02:04.259 --> 06:02:06.599
Perhaps if I act totally shattered.

06:02:06.659 --> 06:02:08.040
They'll let me keep the cave vault

06:02:08.040 --> 06:02:08.340
myself.

06:02:08.400 --> 06:02:12.720
It's absolutely devastating, she said.

06:02:12.779 --> 06:02:14.580
I'm just devastated.

06:02:14.639 --> 06:02:17.159
She reached to take the amulet from

06:02:17.159 --> 06:02:17.819
ostrich.

06:02:17.939 --> 06:02:20.459
But I haven't heard anything useful yet

06:02:20.459 --> 06:02:21.659
Moon thought.

06:02:21.720 --> 06:02:24.419
Um, she said quickly, can I see it?

06:02:24.540 --> 06:02:27.479
Onyx looked as if she wanted to say no

06:02:27.479 --> 06:02:29.340
but Ostrich was already passing the

06:02:29.340 --> 06:02:30.959
amulet into Moon's talons.

06:02:31.020 --> 06:02:34.680
Do you, um, Moon froze in shock.

06:02:34.740 --> 06:02:37.500
The world had gone silent.

06:02:37.560 --> 06:02:39.119
Not the outside world.

06:02:39.180 --> 06:02:40.619
Her inner world.

06:02:40.680 --> 06:02:43.139
The constantly seething, twittering

06:02:43.139 --> 06:02:45.299
background noise of all the minds around

06:02:45.299 --> 06:02:46.860
her had abruptly vanished.

06:02:46.919 --> 06:02:49.860
It felt as though she'd just been plunged

06:02:49.860 --> 06:02:51.540
into the deepest trench in the sea.

06:02:51.599 --> 06:02:53.759
Dark Stalker?

06:02:53.819 --> 06:02:56.459
she called, staring down at the skyfire

06:02:56.459 --> 06:02:57.299
between her claws.

06:02:57.360 --> 06:02:58.740
There was no answer.

06:02:58.860 --> 06:03:00.419
He was gone.

06:03:00.479 --> 06:03:01.919
Everyone was gone.

06:03:01.979 --> 06:03:04.979
It was worse than going underwater.

06:03:05.040 --> 06:03:07.799
It was like being yanked from a 3

06:03:07.799 --> 06:03:09.840
dimensional world into a 2 dimensional

06:03:09.840 --> 06:03:10.080
one.

06:03:10.139 --> 06:03:12.659
The dragons around her might as well have

06:03:12.659 --> 06:03:15.779
been pictures in a scroll, flat and empty

06:03:15.779 --> 06:03:16.560
and unknowable.

06:03:16.619 --> 06:03:20.159
Terrified, moon thrust the amulet into

06:03:20.159 --> 06:03:21.599
Kibley's talons and jumped back.

06:03:21.659 --> 06:03:24.060
Hey, careful with that.

06:03:24.119 --> 06:03:25.560
Onyx snapped.

06:03:25.619 --> 06:03:27.959
Everyone's minds came rushing back at

06:03:27.959 --> 06:03:30.540
once, and Moon, who had always thought

06:03:30.540 --> 06:03:32.880
she wanted more silence, found herself

06:03:32.880 --> 06:03:35.700
unbelievably glad to hear them, even the

06:03:35.700 --> 06:03:37.439
ones who were thinking she was extremely

06:03:37.439 --> 06:03:38.159
peculiar.

06:03:38.220 --> 06:03:39.959
Moon!

06:03:40.020 --> 06:03:41.880
Dark Stalker was yelling.

06:03:41.939 --> 06:03:43.020
Moon!

06:03:43.080 --> 06:03:44.939
I'm here, she said.

06:03:45.000 --> 06:03:48.180
Three moons you scared me, he said.

06:03:48.299 --> 06:03:50.459
You vanished so completely.

06:03:50.520 --> 06:03:51.119
I thought you were dead.

06:03:51.180 --> 06:03:53.040
What am I?

06:03:53.099 --> 06:03:55.020
Kibli began, bewildered.

06:03:55.080 --> 06:03:56.520
It's really cool.

06:03:56.580 --> 06:03:59.099
Look at it, Moon said.

06:03:59.159 --> 06:04:02.220
She wanted to close her eyes and settle

06:04:02.220 --> 06:04:03.180
into the noise around her.

06:04:03.240 --> 06:04:06.360
She needed a moment to calm down, but

06:04:06.360 --> 06:04:08.099
Onyx was full of irritable thoughts about

06:04:08.099 --> 06:04:10.259
her amulet, and not thinking about the

06:04:10.259 --> 06:04:10.860
bomb at all.

06:04:10.919 --> 06:04:13.500
In a minute, she would demand it back.

06:04:13.560 --> 06:04:14.939
Moon didn't have time to recover.

06:04:15.000 --> 06:04:17.340
She needed to get an answer right now.

06:04:17.400 --> 06:04:20.040
Onyx, do you think they'll catch the

06:04:20.040 --> 06:04:21.240
dragon who set the fire?

06:04:21.299 --> 06:04:22.200
She asked her.

06:04:22.259 --> 06:04:24.840
Too direct, but the only thing she could

06:04:24.840 --> 06:04:25.080
do.

06:04:25.200 --> 06:04:27.479
Does she suspect me?

06:04:27.540 --> 06:04:30.119
Onyx thought, how odd.

06:04:30.240 --> 06:04:33.540
Of course, the Sandwing said aloud.

06:04:33.599 --> 06:04:36.000
They're the great dragonettes of destiny

06:04:36.000 --> 06:04:36.540
after all.

06:04:36.599 --> 06:04:38.400
By all the serpents.

06:04:38.459 --> 06:04:40.860
I hope they do catch whoever did it, so

06:04:40.860 --> 06:04:42.119
we can stop blithering about it.

06:04:42.180 --> 06:04:44.759
This is a tiresome distraction for my

06:04:44.759 --> 06:04:45.000
plans.

06:04:45.060 --> 06:04:47.459
Perhaps I should go back to the desert

06:04:47.459 --> 06:04:48.659
and try another approach.

06:04:48.720 --> 06:04:51.959
Or she tipped her head and gave Kibli a

06:04:51.959 --> 06:04:52.560
speculative look.

06:04:52.619 --> 06:04:55.860
They say this one is practically Thorn's

06:04:55.860 --> 06:04:56.340
3rd wing.

06:04:56.400 --> 06:04:57.599
If I...

06:04:58.080 --> 06:05:00.419
Her train of thought abruptly cut off, as

06:05:00.419 --> 06:05:03.000
Onyx snatched the amulet out of Kibble's

06:05:03.000 --> 06:05:03.419
claws.

06:05:03.540 --> 06:05:05.819
That's enough ogling, she said.

06:05:05.880 --> 06:05:08.759
Moon wished she could hear what Onyx's

06:05:08.759 --> 06:05:11.099
mysterious plans were, and how they

06:05:11.099 --> 06:05:13.139
involved Kibley, but at least she knew

06:05:13.139 --> 06:05:13.680
one thing.

06:05:13.740 --> 06:05:15.840
Onyx was not the one who set the fire.

06:05:15.900 --> 06:05:17.099
So who did?

06:05:17.220 --> 06:05:20.099
She sat thoughtfully, staring at her

06:05:20.099 --> 06:05:22.380
talons as Kibley chatted with the other

06:05:22.380 --> 06:05:24.299
sandwings and occasionally shot more

06:05:24.299 --> 06:05:26.459
probing questions at onyx.

06:05:26.520 --> 06:05:30.599
Pike, icicle, flame, onyx.

06:05:30.659 --> 06:05:33.000
If it wasn't one of them, who could it

06:05:33.000 --> 06:05:33.180
be?

06:05:33.240 --> 06:05:36.000
Had she misinterpreted one of the minds

06:05:36.000 --> 06:05:36.659
she'd read?

06:05:36.720 --> 06:05:38.639
Was it really one of them after all?

06:05:38.700 --> 06:05:40.919
Or who else could she be forgetting?

06:05:40.979 --> 06:05:43.200
Are you sure you can't help me?

06:05:43.319 --> 06:05:45.599
She asked Dark Stalker.

06:05:45.659 --> 06:05:48.299
Seems like the same question I've been

06:05:48.299 --> 06:05:48.779
asking you.

06:05:48.840 --> 06:05:50.279
He said quietly.

06:05:50.340 --> 06:05:53.159
She hooked her claws into a crevice in

06:05:53.159 --> 06:05:54.959
the rock and started digging out some

06:05:54.959 --> 06:05:55.799
embedded moss.

06:05:55.860 --> 06:05:58.439
Does that mean you'll tell me who did it

06:05:58.439 --> 06:05:59.819
if I agree to free you?

06:05:59.880 --> 06:06:02.279
No, he said.

06:06:02.340 --> 06:06:04.500
Because then you'll resent me.

06:06:04.560 --> 06:06:06.779
And then you'll start thinking, I'm

06:06:06.779 --> 06:06:08.400
manipulating you, and then you won't

06:06:08.400 --> 06:06:10.500
trust me, and then you'll decide you'll

06:06:10.500 --> 06:06:11.040
never free me.

06:06:11.099 --> 06:06:12.720
He sighed.

06:06:12.779 --> 06:06:15.720
You don't realize how badly I need you

06:06:15.720 --> 06:06:16.080
Moon.

06:06:16.139 --> 06:06:18.000
It's harder than you can imagine.

06:06:18.060 --> 06:06:20.939
Figuring out what I should say to you, and

06:06:20.939 --> 06:06:21.959
trying to help without getting you

06:06:21.959 --> 06:06:22.319
killed.

06:06:22.380 --> 06:06:24.720
Moon felt guilty.

06:06:24.779 --> 06:06:27.240
She'd been focusing on the fire and her

06:06:27.240 --> 06:06:29.220
friends, and all the problems that came

06:06:29.220 --> 06:06:31.860
with being a secret mind reader, and

06:06:31.860 --> 06:06:33.779
meanwhile, the only dragon who accepted

06:06:33.779 --> 06:06:36.180
her completely this way was trapped in a

06:06:36.180 --> 06:06:38.759
stone prison, desperately clinging to the

06:06:38.759 --> 06:06:41.099
one hope he had, that she would take pity

06:06:41.099 --> 06:06:43.319
on him, and find a way to set him free.

06:06:43.380 --> 06:06:45.840
Tell me more about your talisman.

06:06:45.959 --> 06:06:47.220
She suggested.

06:06:47.279 --> 06:06:48.599
A pause.

06:06:48.659 --> 06:06:50.159
Really?

06:06:50.220 --> 06:06:51.060
He asked.

06:06:51.119 --> 06:06:54.779
Well, if I do decide to search for it.

06:06:54.840 --> 06:06:56.520
I need to know what it looks like, don't

06:06:56.520 --> 06:06:56.700
I?

06:06:56.759 --> 06:06:58.619
He hesitated again.

06:06:58.680 --> 06:06:59.939
Finally.

06:07:00.119 --> 06:07:02.759
Can I trust you, Moon?

06:07:02.819 --> 06:07:05.759
She found a tiny green caterpillar

06:07:05.759 --> 06:07:06.900
inching through the crack in the

06:07:06.900 --> 06:07:07.200
boulder.

06:07:07.259 --> 06:07:10.319
Carefully, she let it crawl onto her claw

06:07:10.319 --> 06:07:12.060
and then lifted it safely to the ground

06:07:12.060 --> 06:07:13.979
away from the dragons.

06:07:14.040 --> 06:07:16.500
You tell me, she said to him.

06:07:16.560 --> 06:07:18.659
You can see every single one of my

06:07:18.659 --> 06:07:18.900
thoughts.

06:07:19.020 --> 06:07:21.659
You must know more about me than any

06:07:21.659 --> 06:07:22.500
other dragon in the world.

06:07:22.619 --> 06:07:24.959
So, do you trust me?

06:07:25.020 --> 06:07:28.500
After another moment, Dark Stalker

06:07:28.500 --> 06:07:30.180
suddenly barked a laugh that echoed in

06:07:30.180 --> 06:07:30.540
her skull.

06:07:30.599 --> 06:07:33.360
I guess I don't have any choice, do I?

06:07:33.419 --> 06:07:36.119
You could wait for the next night wing

06:07:36.119 --> 06:07:37.560
mind reader. she pointed out.

06:07:37.680 --> 06:07:39.900
Now that they're living in the rainforest

06:07:39.900 --> 06:07:41.819
having eggs under the moons again.

06:07:41.880 --> 06:07:43.860
There will probably be more, right?

06:07:43.919 --> 06:07:46.259
On the one talon.

06:07:46.319 --> 06:07:48.180
It was reassuring to think there would be

06:07:48.180 --> 06:07:48.599
others.

06:07:48.659 --> 06:07:50.400
She didn't have to bear all the

06:07:50.400 --> 06:07:52.740
responsibility of being dark stalker's

06:07:52.740 --> 06:07:53.580
only hope forever.

06:07:53.639 --> 06:07:56.220
On the other talent, thinking about

06:07:56.220 --> 06:07:58.200
another mind reader, making friends with

06:07:58.200 --> 06:08:00.419
dark stalker, and being the one to rescue

06:08:00.419 --> 06:08:00.659
him.

06:08:00.720 --> 06:08:03.180
It gave her a strange protective feeling

06:08:03.180 --> 06:08:04.560
that she couldn't even explain.

06:08:04.619 --> 06:08:07.860
But on the 3rd talent, maybe somebody

06:08:07.860 --> 06:08:09.119
else would have a better chance of

06:08:09.119 --> 06:08:10.619
figuring out how to rescue him.

06:08:10.680 --> 06:08:13.080
And then she wouldn't be blamed if it all

06:08:13.080 --> 06:08:13.919
went horribly wrong.

06:08:14.040 --> 06:08:18.119
But then on the 4th talent, she liked the

06:08:18.119 --> 06:08:20.279
idea of being somebody's hero, doing

06:08:20.279 --> 06:08:22.200
something brave and dangerous and

06:08:22.200 --> 06:08:23.159
changing the world.

06:08:23.220 --> 06:08:25.439
All right, all right.

06:08:25.439 --> 06:08:27.119
Dark Stalker said.

06:08:27.180 --> 06:08:29.279
I can't listen to you think in circles

06:08:29.279 --> 06:08:29.819
about it anymore.

06:08:29.939 --> 06:08:32.700
But Moon, this is the most important

06:08:32.700 --> 06:08:33.060
thing.

06:08:33.119 --> 06:08:37.200
You must never forget that my talisman is

06:08:37.200 --> 06:08:39.360
the most dangerous, animus touched object

06:08:39.360 --> 06:08:40.560
in all of Pyria.

06:08:40.619 --> 06:08:43.979
If it fell into the wrong clause, it

06:08:43.979 --> 06:08:45.540
would be a disaster like you can't

06:08:45.540 --> 06:08:47.459
imagine, you need to promise me.

06:08:47.520 --> 06:08:50.040
If it looks even for a moment, like

06:08:50.040 --> 06:08:51.000
someone else might take it.

06:08:51.060 --> 06:08:54.659
Someone like Flame, for instance, You'll

06:08:54.659 --> 06:08:55.380
have to destroy it.

06:08:55.439 --> 06:08:57.240
Destroy it?

06:08:57.299 --> 06:08:58.500
Moon thought back.

06:08:58.619 --> 06:09:00.659
But then you'd be trapped forever.

06:09:00.720 --> 06:09:03.119
Yes, probably.

06:09:03.180 --> 06:09:05.340
I can't bear to think about it.

06:09:05.400 --> 06:09:07.680
But even that would be better than the

06:09:07.680 --> 06:09:08.159
alternative.

06:09:08.220 --> 06:09:10.500
A weapon of that kind of power in

06:09:10.500 --> 06:09:11.459
dangerous talents.

06:09:11.520 --> 06:09:13.500
I'm very serious, do you understand?

06:09:13.560 --> 06:09:16.020
I do, Moon thought.

06:09:16.080 --> 06:09:17.220
I promise.

06:09:17.279 --> 06:09:21.000
All right, he said slowly.

06:09:21.060 --> 06:09:23.400
It's a scroll.

06:09:23.459 --> 06:09:26.459
A picture came into her head of a scroll

06:09:26.459 --> 06:09:28.439
wrapped in a black leather casing.

06:09:28.500 --> 06:09:30.479
The casing opened, and the scroll

06:09:30.479 --> 06:09:33.659
unrolled, a pen appeared, writing words

06:09:33.659 --> 06:09:35.880
that blazed for a moment like fire before

06:09:35.880 --> 06:09:38.159
sinking into the page, and turning into

06:09:38.159 --> 06:09:39.419
dark purple ink.

06:09:39.959 --> 06:09:42.659
As with all animus touched objects.

06:09:42.720 --> 06:09:45.000
It can be used by any dragon who comes

06:09:45.000 --> 06:09:45.419
across it.

06:09:45.479 --> 06:09:48.419
Dark Stalker said, You simply write your

06:09:48.419 --> 06:09:48.720
command.

06:09:48.840 --> 06:09:51.599
For instance, give this necklace the

06:09:51.599 --> 06:09:53.159
power to make me invisible when I wear

06:09:53.159 --> 06:09:53.400
it.

06:09:53.520 --> 06:09:56.700
Or, enchant this mirror to spy on

06:09:56.700 --> 06:09:58.080
whichever dragons I choose.

06:09:58.139 --> 06:10:01.740
You must be as specific as possible, or

06:10:01.740 --> 06:10:03.840
the magic is liable to go awry and

06:10:03.840 --> 06:10:05.520
reinterpret your request in some odd

06:10:05.520 --> 06:10:05.819
way.

06:10:05.880 --> 06:10:08.400
Are you sure it still exists?

06:10:08.520 --> 06:10:11.639
Moon asked, studying the scroll in her

06:10:11.639 --> 06:10:11.880
mind.

06:10:11.939 --> 06:10:14.220
It looked like it was made of thicker

06:10:14.220 --> 06:10:16.439
paper than most scrolls, but still

06:10:16.439 --> 06:10:18.540
scrolls could burn so easily.

06:10:18.599 --> 06:10:21.000
If it's out there somewhere.

06:10:21.119 --> 06:10:23.520
Why hasn't anyone figured out its power

06:10:23.520 --> 06:10:26.759
and used it in the last 2000 years?

06:10:26.819 --> 06:10:29.159
Or what if the night wings took it with

06:10:29.159 --> 06:10:31.020
them when they ran away, and it was

06:10:31.020 --> 06:10:32.040
destroyed in the volcano?

06:10:32.099 --> 06:10:36.659
I don't know, Dark Stalker said, in a

06:10:36.659 --> 06:10:39.540
half choked voice, if no one knew what it

06:10:39.540 --> 06:10:42.419
was, and I carefully kept its power a

06:10:42.419 --> 06:10:44.279
secret from everyone but Clearsight.

06:10:44.340 --> 06:10:46.439
Then I don't think anyone would guess how

06:10:46.439 --> 06:10:46.860
to use it.

06:10:46.919 --> 06:10:48.299
It's true though.

06:10:48.419 --> 06:10:51.180
That I don't know if it has survived all

06:10:51.180 --> 06:10:51.599
this time.

06:10:51.659 --> 06:10:55.319
But I have to believe that it has, or

06:10:55.319 --> 06:10:57.779
else, all hope for me is lost.

06:10:57.900 --> 06:11:01.380
Moon side, and Kimberley looked across at

06:11:01.380 --> 06:11:01.979
her curiously.

06:11:02.040 --> 06:11:06.000
Even if I do find it, she thought, how

06:11:06.000 --> 06:11:07.200
could I possibly get it to you?

06:11:07.200 --> 06:11:09.360
Neither of us know where you are.

06:11:09.419 --> 06:11:12.119
Maybe we should figure that out first.

06:11:12.180 --> 06:11:14.520
Maybe it would be easier to dig you out

06:11:14.520 --> 06:11:17.580
than to find one lost scroll in all of

06:11:17.580 --> 06:11:19.740
Pyria, and then what?

06:11:19.799 --> 06:11:21.419
Stuff it through 10 layers of rock.

06:11:21.479 --> 06:11:25.319
I suspect, it's not a matter of a little

06:11:25.319 --> 06:11:28.740
digging, Dark Stalker said, but there is

06:11:28.740 --> 06:11:31.259
a small hole near me, which must reach

06:11:31.259 --> 06:11:32.639
through all the way to the open air

06:11:32.639 --> 06:11:34.319
because every once in a while.

06:11:34.380 --> 06:11:37.740
I can smell a breeze, and sometimes, even

06:11:37.740 --> 06:11:40.500
more rarely, a mouse or insect blunders

06:11:40.500 --> 06:11:41.759
into it, and I get to eat.

06:11:41.819 --> 06:11:44.279
Moon hadn't even thought of that.

06:11:44.340 --> 06:11:47.520
You're surviving on just the occasional

06:11:47.520 --> 06:11:48.479
clumsy mouse?

06:11:48.599 --> 06:11:50.520
How can you live without eating?

06:11:50.580 --> 06:11:53.939
My own foolish enchantment was designed

06:11:53.939 --> 06:11:56.220
to keep me alive through anything, he

06:11:56.220 --> 06:11:56.819
said ruefully.

06:11:56.880 --> 06:12:01.619
Not starvation, nor cold, nor old age, nor

06:12:01.619 --> 06:12:03.659
stabbing or fire or frost breath can kill

06:12:03.659 --> 06:12:03.840
me.

06:12:03.900 --> 06:12:08.340
I can still feel hungry though, extremely

06:12:08.340 --> 06:12:09.659
enormously hungry.

06:12:09.720 --> 06:12:12.599
Turns out it is quite the curse I put on

06:12:12.599 --> 06:12:12.840
myself.

06:12:12.959 --> 06:12:16.740
He made a semi amused noise, as if trying

06:12:16.740 --> 06:12:18.419
to brush aside any self pity.

06:12:18.479 --> 06:12:22.380
And there's no way to undo it?

06:12:22.439 --> 06:12:23.400
Moon asked.

06:12:23.459 --> 06:12:26.040
I mean, whatever you enchanted to make

06:12:26.040 --> 06:12:26.700
you immortal.

06:12:26.759 --> 06:12:29.279
It's not like a necklace you can take

06:12:29.279 --> 06:12:29.520
off.

06:12:29.580 --> 06:12:33.959
You mean, if I decide I want to die.

06:12:34.020 --> 06:12:36.720
Dark stalker thought for a moment.

06:12:36.840 --> 06:12:39.540
No, it's not a necklace.

06:12:39.599 --> 06:12:41.819
I don't think I could undo this

06:12:41.819 --> 06:12:44.639
enchantment, not unless I had my talisman

06:12:44.639 --> 06:12:44.819
back.

06:12:44.880 --> 06:12:46.380
In any case.

06:12:46.439 --> 06:12:48.779
I have not quite reached that level of

06:12:48.779 --> 06:12:49.500
despair yet.

06:12:49.560 --> 06:12:51.900
I still.

06:12:51.959 --> 06:12:54.599
I would like to see the sun, at least

06:12:54.599 --> 06:12:55.740
once more, for instance.

06:12:55.799 --> 06:12:59.159
Moon looked up at the sun, shining

06:12:59.159 --> 06:13:01.319
brightly over the mountain landscape, and

06:13:01.319 --> 06:13:02.880
thought how easily she took it for

06:13:02.880 --> 06:13:03.419
granted.

06:13:03.479 --> 06:13:05.580
Over the mountains to the north, she

06:13:05.580 --> 06:13:07.380
could see heavy gray storm clouds

06:13:07.380 --> 06:13:09.840
gathering, but on Jade Mountain, it was

06:13:09.840 --> 06:13:12.060
still a beautiful day, sort of an

06:13:12.060 --> 06:13:13.200
unfairly beautiful day.

06:13:13.259 --> 06:13:15.840
If you thought about carnelian, and big

06:13:15.840 --> 06:13:17.159
tail, and tamarind.

06:13:17.220 --> 06:13:20.759
There is another option, Dark Stalker

06:13:20.759 --> 06:13:21.000
said.

06:13:21.060 --> 06:13:24.060
If you found my scroll, you could use its

06:13:24.060 --> 06:13:27.119
power to find me and free me yourself, you

06:13:27.119 --> 06:13:28.200
wouldn't need to bring it to me.

06:13:28.259 --> 06:13:31.020
Oh, Moon thought.

06:13:31.080 --> 06:13:32.880
It hadn't occurred to her to use it

06:13:32.880 --> 06:13:33.299
herself.

06:13:33.360 --> 06:13:34.919
Animus magic.

06:13:34.979 --> 06:13:37.020
It sounded so much more dangerous than

06:13:37.020 --> 06:13:38.099
her own little powers.

06:13:38.220 --> 06:13:41.220
You mean, if I wrote something like

06:13:41.220 --> 06:13:43.979
please enchant this map to show me Dark

06:13:43.979 --> 06:13:45.479
Stalker's exact location?

06:13:45.720 --> 06:13:46.680
He laughed.

06:13:46.740 --> 06:13:50.159
Well, I must admit, I never said please

06:13:50.159 --> 06:13:52.319
to my talisman, but you certainly could.

06:13:52.380 --> 06:13:55.439
The dragons around Moon all suddenly

06:13:55.439 --> 06:13:56.099
began to get up.

06:13:56.159 --> 06:13:59.220
She blinked at them, startled, and Kibley

06:13:59.220 --> 06:13:59.639
grinned.

06:13:59.759 --> 06:14:02.340
I suspected you were a 1000000 miles away

06:14:02.340 --> 06:14:03.180
he said.

06:14:03.240 --> 06:14:04.740
We're going to the prey center.

06:14:04.799 --> 06:14:06.959
A few dragons just came back with food, so

06:14:06.959 --> 06:14:08.819
we're hoping there'll be enough for

06:14:08.819 --> 06:14:09.000
everyone.

06:14:09.060 --> 06:14:12.599
I just need a lizard, Ostrich said.

06:14:12.659 --> 06:14:15.060
I couldn't eat yesterday after everything

06:14:15.060 --> 06:14:17.639
so I'm hungry now, although I feel bad

06:14:17.639 --> 06:14:18.240
admitting that.

06:14:18.299 --> 06:14:21.840
Oh, here, Moon said.

06:14:21.900 --> 06:14:24.540
She'd been absently watching a fat

06:14:24.540 --> 06:14:26.099
brownish green lizard for the last few

06:14:26.099 --> 06:14:26.459
minutes.

06:14:26.520 --> 06:14:29.099
It had been inching slowly out into the

06:14:29.099 --> 06:14:31.020
sun below the boulders, looking for

06:14:31.020 --> 06:14:31.919
insects to eat.

06:14:31.979 --> 06:14:33.419
With a quick stab.

06:14:33.479 --> 06:14:35.880
Moon impaled it on her claws, then

06:14:35.880 --> 06:14:36.900
presented it to ostrich.

06:14:37.020 --> 06:14:41.400
Talons and tails, ostrich said, regarding

06:14:41.400 --> 06:14:41.939
her with awe.

06:14:42.000 --> 06:14:43.799
I didn't see that coming.

06:14:43.860 --> 06:14:45.479
You're really fast.

06:14:45.540 --> 06:14:48.479
True, Kibley said.

06:14:48.540 --> 06:14:49.860
She's an amazing hunter.

06:14:49.979 --> 06:14:52.139
Got another one hidden somewhere for me.

06:14:52.200 --> 06:14:55.080
Moon shook her head, although she knew he

06:14:55.080 --> 06:14:55.439
was kidding.

06:14:55.500 --> 06:14:57.240
You can have this one.

06:14:57.299 --> 06:14:59.279
Ostrich said immediately.

06:14:59.340 --> 06:15:00.959
No, thank you.

06:15:01.020 --> 06:15:02.459
You have it, he said.

06:15:02.520 --> 06:15:04.259
I'd like to stop by the pre-center

06:15:04.259 --> 06:15:04.560
anyway.

06:15:04.619 --> 06:15:06.299
Moon, coming to?

06:15:06.360 --> 06:15:07.500
She nodded.

06:15:07.560 --> 06:15:09.599
The other sand wings had already gone on

06:15:09.599 --> 06:15:10.139
ahead.

06:15:10.200 --> 06:15:11.759
Ostrich bounded after them.

06:15:11.819 --> 06:15:14.819
Moon and Kimley followed more slowly, and

06:15:14.819 --> 06:15:17.580
Moon said in a low voice, It wasn't

06:15:17.580 --> 06:15:18.180
onyx.

06:15:18.240 --> 06:15:19.439
Really?

06:15:19.500 --> 06:15:20.040
He said.

06:15:20.099 --> 06:15:21.119
How do you know?

06:15:21.180 --> 06:15:23.400
Don't tell him.

06:15:23.459 --> 06:15:25.740
Dark stalker warned.

06:15:25.799 --> 06:15:26.700
She hesitated.

06:15:26.759 --> 06:15:29.159
I just do.

06:15:29.220 --> 06:15:32.459
He frowned, and she felt all the progress

06:15:32.459 --> 06:15:34.500
of the last few hours spiraling

06:15:34.500 --> 06:15:34.919
backward.

06:15:34.979 --> 06:15:37.020
She's lying to me again.

06:15:37.080 --> 06:15:39.360
I'm sure of it But about what?

06:15:39.419 --> 06:15:40.740
And why?

06:15:40.860 --> 06:15:43.080
If she can hear onyx after all.

06:15:43.139 --> 06:15:44.580
Why not admit to that?

06:15:44.639 --> 06:15:47.459
Unless this is all a trick, to make me

06:15:47.459 --> 06:15:48.540
suspect turtle?

06:15:48.599 --> 06:15:51.360
She could be lying about everything, about

06:15:51.360 --> 06:15:52.619
all the others being innocent.

06:15:52.680 --> 06:15:54.659
She could be trying to steer me to

06:15:54.659 --> 06:15:55.860
someone for her own agenda.

06:15:55.919 --> 06:15:58.080
What do I really know about her after

06:15:58.080 --> 06:15:58.319
all?

06:15:58.380 --> 06:16:00.840
And why would I think she'd want to help

06:16:00.840 --> 06:16:02.819
me find the dragon who killed Carnelian?

06:16:02.880 --> 06:16:04.860
Perhaps she doesn't even care.

06:16:04.919 --> 06:16:07.319
Stop, please stop.

06:16:07.380 --> 06:16:08.459
Moon said.

06:16:08.520 --> 06:16:10.740
Futilely pressing her talons to her

06:16:10.740 --> 06:16:11.580
ears.

06:16:11.639 --> 06:16:13.799
I'm not lying, and I do want to figure

06:16:13.799 --> 06:16:14.459
out who did this.

06:16:14.520 --> 06:16:16.680
Please trust me, Kibley.

06:16:16.799 --> 06:16:19.380
He flicked his tail and took a step away

06:16:19.380 --> 06:16:19.680
from her.

06:16:19.740 --> 06:16:21.659
I'm sorry, he said.

06:16:21.720 --> 06:16:23.459
I'm not sure I can do that yet.

06:16:23.520 --> 06:16:25.860
It's too, you know what?

06:16:25.919 --> 06:16:27.659
Let's split up for a while and try again

06:16:27.659 --> 06:16:27.959
later.

06:16:28.020 --> 06:16:30.299
Without waiting for her answer.

06:16:30.360 --> 06:16:32.880
And now worrying about what else she'd

06:16:32.880 --> 06:16:35.159
see in his head, he took to the sky

06:16:35.159 --> 06:16:37.319
flying down to the pray center cave

06:16:37.319 --> 06:16:37.680
opening.

06:16:37.740 --> 06:16:39.900
Moon's wings drooped.

06:16:39.959 --> 06:16:43.080
I ruined it, she said to Dark Stalker.

06:16:43.139 --> 06:16:45.299
He was almost willing to trust me again.

06:16:45.360 --> 06:16:47.520
I should have just told him the truth.

06:16:47.580 --> 06:16:51.419
You can't tell anyone about the skyfire.

06:16:51.540 --> 06:16:52.799
You must see that.

06:16:52.919 --> 06:16:56.220
You may be back to being my only friend

06:16:56.220 --> 06:16:57.000
she said.

06:16:57.060 --> 06:16:58.500
Possibly forever.

06:16:58.560 --> 06:17:01.979
Well, if you're only going to have one.

06:17:02.040 --> 06:17:05.220
I'm not such a bad one to have, he joked

06:17:05.220 --> 06:17:07.200
or at least she thought he was joking.

06:17:07.259 --> 06:17:10.439
There were more dragons in the prey

06:17:10.439 --> 06:17:11.759
center than she'd expected.

06:17:11.819 --> 06:17:14.279
All the sea wings were back, along with

06:17:14.279 --> 06:17:17.099
all the sky wings, a few ice wings, and a

06:17:17.099 --> 06:17:17.939
couple of night wings.

06:17:18.000 --> 06:17:20.520
It was easier now to use the raindrop

06:17:20.520 --> 06:17:21.060
trick, though.

06:17:21.119 --> 06:17:22.979
She slipped them all quickly into

06:17:22.979 --> 06:17:24.959
background pitter pattering, and her

06:17:24.959 --> 06:17:26.459
oncoming headache faded away again.

06:17:26.520 --> 06:17:30.180
Then she spotted Umber, Marsh, and Sora

06:17:30.180 --> 06:17:32.279
across the cave, and felt her wings

06:17:32.279 --> 06:17:32.639
lift.

06:17:32.700 --> 06:17:35.099
For one thing, Sora must be feeling

06:17:35.099 --> 06:17:37.259
better if they let her come down here, and

06:17:37.259 --> 06:17:39.659
for another thing, Umber and Sora didn't

06:17:39.659 --> 06:17:40.500
completely hate her yet.

06:17:40.560 --> 06:17:43.200
They would probably let her sit with them

06:17:43.200 --> 06:17:45.540
to eat anyway, which would be better than

06:17:45.540 --> 06:17:47.159
trying to sit with that ferocious

06:17:47.159 --> 06:17:48.840
expression Mighty Claus was wearing.

06:17:48.900 --> 06:17:52.080
As she moved toward the siblings, she

06:17:52.080 --> 06:17:53.639
caught a glimpse of Kibley watching her.

06:17:53.700 --> 06:17:56.040
He was wondering whether he should warn

06:17:56.040 --> 06:17:57.659
the mudwings about her mind reading

06:17:57.659 --> 06:17:59.220
especially Umber.

06:17:59.279 --> 06:18:02.340
So I'd better enjoy them now, she thought

06:18:02.340 --> 06:18:04.560
ruefully, since they won't be my friends

06:18:04.560 --> 06:18:05.279
for much longer.

06:18:05.400 --> 06:18:08.939
Hey, Umber said as she approached.

06:18:09.000 --> 06:18:12.060
Sora and Marsh both kind of flinched and

06:18:12.060 --> 06:18:13.319
nodded at the same time.

06:18:13.380 --> 06:18:16.319
Hi, Moon said softly.

06:18:16.380 --> 06:18:18.479
Sora, how are you?

06:18:18.540 --> 06:18:19.560
Are you all right?

06:18:19.619 --> 06:18:21.659
Nothing is all right.

06:18:21.720 --> 06:18:24.540
Nothing, she called from Zora's brain.

06:18:24.599 --> 06:18:27.060
There were fragments of terror and

06:18:27.060 --> 06:18:29.700
memories of battles, and fire jolting

06:18:29.700 --> 06:18:32.220
through the mud pool in Zora's mind, and

06:18:32.220 --> 06:18:33.840
she could tell Zora really would have

06:18:33.840 --> 06:18:36.000
preferred to be tranquilized again, but

06:18:36.000 --> 06:18:37.500
she had forced herself to come down

06:18:37.500 --> 06:18:37.619
here.

06:18:37.680 --> 06:18:41.880
Icicle, moon herd, and guessed that Sora

06:18:41.880 --> 06:18:43.380
wanted to prove herself to be tougher

06:18:43.380 --> 06:18:45.060
than her clawmate thought she was.

06:18:45.180 --> 06:18:48.000
She slid the rest of Sora's restless

06:18:48.000 --> 06:18:50.159
thoughts into a raindrop, conscious of

06:18:50.159 --> 06:18:52.080
Kibley's eyes on her back, and feeling

06:18:52.080 --> 06:18:53.939
like an intruder in Sora's fear.

06:18:54.000 --> 06:18:56.520
She did the same with Marsh and Umber

06:18:56.520 --> 06:18:58.619
although Marsh was mostly surveying the

06:18:58.619 --> 06:19:00.959
cave and nervously wondering what to eat

06:19:00.959 --> 06:19:03.360
while Umber was preoccupied with worrying

06:19:03.360 --> 06:19:04.500
about his brother and sister.

06:19:04.560 --> 06:19:06.299
She's doing better.

06:19:06.419 --> 06:19:08.520
Umber answered for Sora.

06:19:08.580 --> 06:19:11.159
Clay said she even got up and went for a

06:19:11.159 --> 06:19:12.419
walk for a little while last night.

06:19:12.479 --> 06:19:14.159
Really?

06:19:14.220 --> 06:19:16.139
Moon said, looking at her.

06:19:16.200 --> 06:19:18.419
Why would she wander around the mountain

06:19:18.419 --> 06:19:19.560
in the middle of the night?

06:19:19.619 --> 06:19:22.979
She wondered for a split 2nd whether Sora

06:19:22.979 --> 06:19:24.479
could be the dragon who'd been scheming

06:19:24.479 --> 06:19:26.939
with Scarlet, but then she remembered the

06:19:26.939 --> 06:19:28.740
1st night she'd heard the dream visitor

06:19:28.740 --> 06:19:29.220
conversation.

06:19:29.279 --> 06:19:31.860
Sora had been one of the few dragons

06:19:31.860 --> 06:19:32.939
still awake at that hour.

06:19:33.000 --> 06:19:35.880
Moon definitely remembered noticing her

06:19:35.880 --> 06:19:36.959
mental mud ritual.

06:19:37.020 --> 06:19:39.959
She hadn't been asleep and dreaming, so

06:19:39.959 --> 06:19:41.220
she couldn't have been the one talking to

06:19:41.220 --> 06:19:41.639
Scarlett.

06:19:41.759 --> 06:19:44.939
Sora glanced anxiously around the cave.

06:19:45.000 --> 06:19:48.360
Following her gaze, Moon saw winter and

06:19:48.360 --> 06:19:50.159
icicles stalking in from one of the

06:19:50.159 --> 06:19:52.680
tunnels, she felt like bolting, but she

06:19:52.680 --> 06:19:55.139
made herself stay put as winter rapidly

06:19:55.139 --> 06:19:56.639
scanned the cave and spotted her.

06:19:56.700 --> 06:20:00.299
His eyes narrowed, and he thought, only

06:20:00.299 --> 06:20:02.459
half a day left, Nightwing.

06:20:02.520 --> 06:20:04.139
She ducked her head.

06:20:04.200 --> 06:20:06.000
What was she going to tell him at

06:20:06.000 --> 06:20:06.419
midnight?

06:20:06.479 --> 06:20:08.340
She couldn't point to anyone as the

06:20:08.340 --> 06:20:09.000
culprit yet?

06:20:09.119 --> 06:20:11.819
Icicle snatched a fish from the central

06:20:11.819 --> 06:20:14.099
pile and stormed toward her usual ledge.

06:20:14.159 --> 06:20:16.439
Winter picked up a fish too, but

06:20:16.439 --> 06:20:17.340
hesitated.

06:20:17.400 --> 06:20:19.259
Moon could hear him debating whether to

06:20:19.259 --> 06:20:20.159
come over and talk to her.

06:20:20.220 --> 06:20:23.099
Please don't, please don't, please

06:20:23.099 --> 06:20:23.759
don't.

06:20:23.880 --> 06:20:24.599
She prayed.

06:20:24.659 --> 06:20:27.840
Do you want to go talk to icycle?

06:20:27.900 --> 06:20:30.479
Umber asked Sora, who was still staring

06:20:30.479 --> 06:20:31.380
at her clawmate.

06:20:31.439 --> 06:20:33.360
I'm sure she's been worried about you.

06:20:33.479 --> 06:20:36.540
So I didn't answer, but a flash of

06:20:36.540 --> 06:20:38.220
contemptuous disbelief broke through

06:20:38.220 --> 06:20:41.099
Moon's raindrops, so sharp and fierce

06:20:41.099 --> 06:20:43.080
that it took her a moment to realize it

06:20:43.080 --> 06:20:44.580
had come from the quiet mud wing.

06:20:44.639 --> 06:20:47.279
She turned and saw icicle climbing into

06:20:47.279 --> 06:20:50.040
the alcove, with a disdainful flick of

06:20:50.040 --> 06:20:52.380
her wings, icicle turned to look down at

06:20:52.380 --> 06:20:52.860
the crowd.

06:20:52.919 --> 06:20:55.439
One of her wings lightly brushed the

06:20:55.439 --> 06:20:56.639
stalactites over her head.

06:20:56.700 --> 06:20:59.700
There was a loud crack, then a

06:20:59.700 --> 06:21:02.099
splintering sound, and suddenly, the

06:21:02.099 --> 06:21:04.319
sharpest, most wicked looking stalactite

06:21:04.319 --> 06:21:06.599
broke off from the ceiling and plummeted

06:21:06.599 --> 06:21:07.680
down toward icicle.

06:21:07.740 --> 06:21:12.119
Chapter 21.

06:21:12.360 --> 06:21:15.119
Moon shrieked.

06:21:15.180 --> 06:21:17.340
Sure, the rock spear would impale the ice

06:21:17.340 --> 06:21:18.779
wing through the head or neck.

06:21:18.840 --> 06:21:21.180
The raindrops all vanished in a scream of

06:21:21.180 --> 06:21:22.799
terror from everyone in the cave.

06:21:22.860 --> 06:21:27.540
Then she'll be dead, dead, sang one voice

06:21:27.540 --> 06:21:29.880
in the rising tumult in moon's head.

06:21:29.939 --> 06:21:32.340
But Icicle twisted out of the way at the

06:21:32.340 --> 06:21:34.919
last moment, and the stalactite shattered

06:21:34.919 --> 06:21:35.459
against the ground.

06:21:35.520 --> 06:21:38.099
There was a frozen minute of shock.

06:21:38.159 --> 06:21:40.500
Oh, that's interesting.

06:21:40.560 --> 06:21:42.599
Dark Stalker mused.

06:21:42.659 --> 06:21:45.360
And most of the futures I saw, that

06:21:45.360 --> 06:21:46.560
worked and she died.

06:21:46.619 --> 06:21:48.479
This changes.

06:21:48.540 --> 06:21:50.040
Many things.

06:21:50.099 --> 06:21:52.619
Moon didn't have time to respond to

06:21:52.619 --> 06:21:52.860
that.

06:21:52.919 --> 06:21:55.139
The whole cave it erupted in chaos.

06:21:55.200 --> 06:21:57.180
Icicle!

06:21:57.240 --> 06:21:57.840
Winter shouted.

06:21:57.900 --> 06:22:00.180
He spread his wings and sprang toward her

06:22:00.180 --> 06:22:02.459
fighting past the dragons who were all

06:22:02.459 --> 06:22:03.540
stampeding the other way.

06:22:03.599 --> 06:22:06.360
Icicle was staring at the spot where it

06:22:06.360 --> 06:22:08.099
had fallen, her heart pounding.

06:22:08.159 --> 06:22:10.919
Even above everyone else, Moon could hear

06:22:10.919 --> 06:22:12.540
her fury and disbelief.

06:22:12.599 --> 06:22:14.880
Who dared attack me?

06:22:14.939 --> 06:22:19.380
Still reeling, Moon turned and found that

06:22:19.380 --> 06:22:22.139
Umber, Marsh, and Zora had fled with most

06:22:22.139 --> 06:22:23.279
of the other dragons.

06:22:23.279 --> 06:22:25.799
A few moments later, no one was left in

06:22:25.799 --> 06:22:28.080
the praise center except the 2 ice wings

06:22:28.080 --> 06:22:31.020
Kibley, Moon, and Clay, who had also

06:22:31.020 --> 06:22:32.580
rushed to Icicle's side.

06:22:32.639 --> 06:22:35.759
By all the moons, Clay cried.

06:22:35.819 --> 06:22:36.779
How did that happen?

06:22:36.840 --> 06:22:37.919
Are you all right?

06:22:37.979 --> 06:22:39.540
No!

06:22:39.599 --> 06:22:41.880
Icicle roared, lashing her tail.

06:22:42.000 --> 06:22:43.619
Someone tried to kill me.

06:22:43.680 --> 06:22:46.560
The niece of Queen Glacier.

06:22:46.619 --> 06:22:49.020
Kibley thought, and then reprimanded

06:22:49.020 --> 06:22:49.439
himself.

06:22:49.500 --> 06:22:51.119
Not the time, Kibley.

06:22:51.180 --> 06:22:52.319
What?

06:22:52.380 --> 06:22:55.020
Clay looked up at the others stalactites

06:22:55.020 --> 06:22:58.740
in the alcove, but no, surely that was an

06:22:58.740 --> 06:22:59.099
accident.

06:22:59.159 --> 06:23:00.959
How and who?

06:23:00.959 --> 06:23:04.860
That was no accident, Winter said

06:23:04.860 --> 06:23:06.959
pointing grimly at the spot where the

06:23:06.959 --> 06:23:08.459
fallen stalactite had hung.

06:23:08.520 --> 06:23:10.919
Claw marks were clearly visible in the

06:23:10.919 --> 06:23:12.959
rock, as if someone had scraped

06:23:12.959 --> 06:23:15.779
painstakingly through the spire until it

06:23:15.779 --> 06:23:18.119
had been barely suspended, ready to fall

06:23:18.119 --> 06:23:19.139
at the lightest touch.

06:23:19.200 --> 06:23:21.659
But who?

06:23:21.659 --> 06:23:23.400
Clay said again, searching his brain.

06:23:23.459 --> 06:23:26.400
She's unfriendly. but not bad enough to

06:23:26.400 --> 06:23:26.639
kill.

06:23:26.700 --> 06:23:29.340
I'll tell you what else.

06:23:29.400 --> 06:23:30.360
Isaacle spat.

06:23:30.419 --> 06:23:32.580
That bomb yesterday was probably meant

06:23:32.580 --> 06:23:33.299
for me too.

06:23:33.360 --> 06:23:34.680
I'm the target.

06:23:34.740 --> 06:23:36.840
Someone was trying to kill me.

06:23:36.959 --> 06:23:39.720
And I'm going to find whoever it is and

06:23:39.720 --> 06:23:41.939
turn them into a glittering ice statue

06:23:41.939 --> 06:23:44.400
which I will then beat to smithereens

06:23:44.400 --> 06:23:45.000
with my tail.

06:23:45.060 --> 06:23:48.540
Icicle was the target all along.

06:23:48.599 --> 06:23:50.700
Kibli and Moon exchanged looks.

06:23:50.759 --> 06:23:53.340
If she was right, what did that mean?

06:23:53.400 --> 06:23:56.520
Kibley's brain was rapidly organizing the

06:23:56.520 --> 06:23:58.799
students into possible categories of ice

06:23:58.799 --> 06:24:02.759
wing enemies, but Moon had an awful, awful

06:24:02.759 --> 06:24:05.400
sinking feeling that she already knew who

06:24:05.400 --> 06:24:06.119
this pointed to.

06:24:06.180 --> 06:24:09.659
You can't do that, and that's impossible

06:24:09.659 --> 06:24:11.639
anyway, Clay said again.

06:24:11.700 --> 06:24:13.740
No one could have known who'd be in the

06:24:13.740 --> 06:24:15.419
cave when the cat has exploded.

06:24:15.479 --> 06:24:17.220
We think it was said to happen before

06:24:17.220 --> 06:24:19.979
class started, so there was no guarantee

06:24:19.979 --> 06:24:20.880
that you'd be in there then.

06:24:20.939 --> 06:24:23.639
If it was an assassination attempt

06:24:23.639 --> 06:24:25.740
against you, wouldn't they have made sure

06:24:25.740 --> 06:24:26.220
you were there?

06:24:26.220 --> 06:24:30.779
I was supposed to be, Icicle hissed.

06:24:30.840 --> 06:24:32.340
I had planned to go early because I

06:24:32.340 --> 06:24:33.540
needed one of the scrolls.

06:24:33.540 --> 06:24:36.180
Just by luck, I decided to go by the

06:24:36.180 --> 06:24:37.560
underground lake first.

06:24:37.619 --> 06:24:40.139
Otherwise, I would have been in the

06:24:40.139 --> 06:24:42.659
history cave, and I would now be dead.

06:24:42.720 --> 06:24:45.360
So who knew that?

06:24:45.360 --> 06:24:46.619
Winter asked.

06:24:46.680 --> 06:24:47.939
That would narrow it down?

06:24:48.000 --> 06:24:50.400
Did you tell anyone you were planning to

06:24:50.400 --> 06:24:50.700
go early?

06:24:50.819 --> 06:24:53.639
Icicle snapped her jaw shut?

06:24:53.700 --> 06:24:56.580
and stared at him and clay, her pale blue

06:24:56.580 --> 06:24:57.720
eyes glittering.

06:24:57.779 --> 06:25:00.659
Only one dragon, she thought.

06:25:00.720 --> 06:25:03.540
I only told one dragon that.

06:25:03.599 --> 06:25:06.060
So I know exactly who to kill.

06:25:06.119 --> 06:25:09.540
A freezing shiver rattled down Moon's

06:25:09.540 --> 06:25:09.900
spine.

06:25:09.959 --> 06:25:11.459
Sora.

06:25:11.520 --> 06:25:14.220
Moon turned and bolted out of the cave.

06:25:14.279 --> 06:25:15.779
I have to find her first.

06:25:15.840 --> 06:25:18.000
She didn't know exactly what she was

06:25:18.000 --> 06:25:20.279
going to do, but she had very clearly

06:25:20.279 --> 06:25:22.919
seen what icicle planned for her clawmate

06:25:22.919 --> 06:25:24.959
and Moon knew she couldn't let that

06:25:24.959 --> 06:25:25.200
happen.

06:25:25.259 --> 06:25:28.380
Even though Sora killed Carnelian and

06:25:28.380 --> 06:25:30.479
Bigtail, even though she could have

06:25:30.479 --> 06:25:32.700
killed any of us, didn't she care?

06:25:32.759 --> 06:25:34.139
What about Umber?

06:25:34.200 --> 06:25:36.060
She must have delayed him.

06:25:36.119 --> 06:25:37.259
She would never hurt him.

06:25:37.319 --> 06:25:39.900
Sora, where are you?

06:25:39.959 --> 06:25:42.599
Moon raced through the tunnels, checking

06:25:42.599 --> 06:25:43.799
the library first.

06:25:43.919 --> 06:25:46.020
Starflight was in there, alone.

06:25:46.080 --> 06:25:48.599
He lifted his head, startled as she

06:25:48.599 --> 06:25:50.340
sprinted through, but she didn't stop.

06:25:50.400 --> 06:25:52.619
She didn't have time to explain or ask

06:25:52.619 --> 06:25:53.040
for help.

06:25:53.099 --> 06:25:55.799
She knew icicle would be on Sora's trail

06:25:55.799 --> 06:25:56.340
any second.

06:25:56.459 --> 06:25:59.580
In the great hall, she stopped to catch

06:25:59.580 --> 06:26:01.319
her breath and reached out with her mind

06:26:01.319 --> 06:26:04.740
the music cave, the underground lake, the

06:26:04.740 --> 06:26:05.279
art cave.

06:26:05.340 --> 06:26:07.080
What was Thor thinking about?

06:26:07.139 --> 06:26:09.659
An image of Tamarin came through?

06:26:09.720 --> 06:26:11.939
Zora had gone back to the infirmary.

06:26:12.060 --> 06:26:15.000
Moon World and dashed toward that

06:26:15.000 --> 06:26:15.599
corridor.

06:26:15.659 --> 06:26:18.060
At the mouth of the tunnel, she collided

06:26:18.060 --> 06:26:20.520
hard with a small brown dragon, and for a

06:26:20.520 --> 06:26:22.500
confused moment, She thought she'd found

06:26:22.500 --> 06:26:23.459
Sora already.

06:26:23.520 --> 06:26:24.720
You're not safe.

06:26:24.779 --> 06:26:27.720
She started to gasp, and then realized it

06:26:27.720 --> 06:26:28.619
wasn't Sora.

06:26:28.680 --> 06:26:29.759
It was Umber.

06:26:29.819 --> 06:26:30.959
I'm not?

06:26:31.020 --> 06:26:31.860
What?

06:26:31.979 --> 06:26:32.700
He said.

06:26:32.759 --> 06:26:34.080
Sorry, not you.

06:26:34.139 --> 06:26:34.680
I have to.

06:26:35.040 --> 06:26:35.939
She stepped around him.

06:26:36.000 --> 06:26:38.040
Wait, Umber said.

06:26:38.099 --> 06:26:38.819
What's wrong?

06:26:38.880 --> 06:26:42.599
Moon, you have to tell him.

06:26:42.659 --> 06:26:45.540
Moon turned and saw Kibli hurrying across

06:26:45.540 --> 06:26:46.200
the great hall.

06:26:46.259 --> 06:26:47.639
He'd seen her run.

06:26:47.700 --> 06:26:50.159
He knew that she'd figured it out, and

06:26:50.159 --> 06:26:51.840
one of the 3 guesses in his head was even

06:26:51.840 --> 06:26:52.860
right.

06:26:52.919 --> 06:26:55.319
But if I tell Umber what his sister did.

06:26:55.380 --> 06:26:58.560
It'll destroy him, she thought, if he

06:26:58.560 --> 06:26:59.220
even believes me.

06:26:59.340 --> 06:27:02.159
If Kibley hadn't been there, she would

06:27:02.159 --> 06:27:02.759
have kept running.

06:27:02.819 --> 06:27:04.919
She would have dealt with Sora herself.

06:27:04.979 --> 06:27:07.680
In his mind, though, she found a

06:27:07.680 --> 06:27:09.599
lightning fast list of reasons to tell

06:27:09.599 --> 06:27:11.099
Umber that she would never have thought

06:27:11.099 --> 06:27:11.880
of herself.

06:27:12.060 --> 06:27:14.220
He wasn't consciously sending them to her

06:27:14.220 --> 06:27:16.319
but they were all there on the surface as

06:27:16.319 --> 06:27:17.340
he struggled with what to do.

06:27:17.400 --> 06:27:20.700
He may not understand, but he'll want to

06:27:20.700 --> 06:27:21.060
protect her.

06:27:21.119 --> 06:27:22.919
He can do that better than you can.

06:27:22.979 --> 06:27:25.139
You need someone to help you if you're

06:27:25.139 --> 06:27:26.580
planning to stand an icicle's way.

06:27:26.700 --> 06:27:28.619
He needs to know the truth about her.

06:27:28.680 --> 06:27:30.659
The way you'd want to know if someone in

06:27:30.659 --> 06:27:31.560
your family did this.

06:27:31.619 --> 06:27:33.659
He's good and loyal.

06:27:33.779 --> 06:27:35.520
He's the only one who can help her.

06:27:35.580 --> 06:27:37.500
And if Zora is still dangerous.

06:27:37.560 --> 06:27:39.599
He may also be the only one who can stop

06:27:39.599 --> 06:27:39.900
her.

06:27:39.959 --> 06:27:42.779
Moon met Kibley's eyes.

06:27:42.840 --> 06:27:44.220
He was right about all of that.

06:27:44.279 --> 06:27:47.939
Umber. she said I'm sorry.

06:27:48.060 --> 06:27:50.279
I have to tell you something awful.

06:27:50.340 --> 06:27:53.819
Oh no, Umber said.

06:27:53.939 --> 06:27:56.520
His face twisted, and it was almost like

06:27:56.520 --> 06:27:58.380
his heart spoke rather than his mind.

06:27:58.500 --> 06:28:01.979
Sora, Marsh, clay.

06:28:02.040 --> 06:28:04.799
We know who said the bomb yesterday

06:28:04.799 --> 06:28:05.880
Kibley said.

06:28:05.939 --> 06:28:09.180
And she just tried to kill icicle, Moon

06:28:09.180 --> 06:28:09.659
said.

06:28:09.720 --> 06:28:12.240
Umber took a step back, shaking his

06:28:12.240 --> 06:28:12.419
head.

06:28:12.479 --> 06:28:14.700
No, it's not true.

06:28:14.759 --> 06:28:17.700
But he saw the pieces falling into place

06:28:17.700 --> 06:28:19.020
and knew it was.

06:28:19.080 --> 06:28:21.419
Pheasant thought this would be too much

06:28:21.419 --> 06:28:23.700
for her, but I thought she was stronger

06:28:23.700 --> 06:28:24.060
than this.

06:28:24.119 --> 06:28:26.159
I thought we were all better now.

06:28:26.220 --> 06:28:31.380
It was Sora, Moon said gently, and Icicle

06:28:31.380 --> 06:28:32.700
knows it too.

06:28:32.759 --> 06:28:34.500
We have to get to her before Icicle finds

06:28:34.500 --> 06:28:35.700
her, or she's dead.

06:28:35.759 --> 06:28:37.799
He didn't argue anymore.

06:28:37.860 --> 06:28:39.599
He didn't ask how they knew.

06:28:39.659 --> 06:28:42.240
He just turned and ran, and they

06:28:42.240 --> 06:28:42.599
followed.

06:28:42.659 --> 06:28:46.919
Up the winding stone tunnel, their claws

06:28:46.919 --> 06:28:48.959
scraping against the rock, their wings

06:28:48.959 --> 06:28:51.060
pulled in, their tails hitting the walls

06:28:51.060 --> 06:28:51.900
as they ran.

06:28:51.959 --> 06:28:53.099
Why?

06:28:53.159 --> 06:28:54.360
Why would she do this?

06:28:54.419 --> 06:28:57.299
Umber kept thinking over and over in a

06:28:57.299 --> 06:28:58.080
jagged rhythm.

06:28:58.139 --> 06:29:00.000
Moon didn't know.

06:29:00.119 --> 06:29:02.639
All the things she'd learned and all the

06:29:02.639 --> 06:29:04.500
thoughts she'd read, and she'd still

06:29:04.500 --> 06:29:04.919
missed it.

06:29:04.979 --> 06:29:08.279
Quiet Sora had taught herself to bury her

06:29:08.279 --> 06:29:10.080
thoughts so she couldn't even hear them

06:29:10.080 --> 06:29:11.099
herself.

06:29:11.159 --> 06:29:13.799
So many things scared her that the only

06:29:13.799 --> 06:29:15.360
way to deal with them was to push them

06:29:15.360 --> 06:29:17.580
under and stop them from entering her

06:29:17.580 --> 06:29:18.840
brain in the 1st place.

06:29:18.900 --> 06:29:21.180
Whatever she felt about icicle.

06:29:21.240 --> 06:29:24.180
It was hidden under all the mud, buried

06:29:24.180 --> 06:29:26.520
deep, along with her nightmares and

06:29:26.520 --> 06:29:27.180
memories of the war.

06:29:27.240 --> 06:29:30.299
They burst into the healing cave.

06:29:30.360 --> 06:29:32.939
Sora was crouched by Tamron's bedside

06:29:32.939 --> 06:29:34.139
crying.

06:29:34.200 --> 06:29:35.279
Kinkaju was not there.

06:29:35.340 --> 06:29:37.200
But she just left.

06:29:37.259 --> 06:29:38.400
Moon realized.

06:29:38.459 --> 06:29:41.099
Zora asked her to leave, so she could

06:29:41.099 --> 06:29:42.240
apologize to Tamarin.

06:29:42.360 --> 06:29:44.520
The rain wing was still unconscious

06:29:44.520 --> 06:29:46.799
wrapped in white bandages from wings to

06:29:46.799 --> 06:29:47.099
tail.

06:29:47.159 --> 06:29:50.220
Sora looked up, and saw it in their

06:29:50.220 --> 06:29:50.400
eyes.

06:29:50.459 --> 06:29:55.259
I'm sorry, umber, she sobbed, collapsing

06:29:55.259 --> 06:29:55.619
forward.

06:29:55.740 --> 06:29:57.779
I didn't mean for anyone else to get

06:29:57.779 --> 06:29:58.080
hurt.

06:29:58.139 --> 06:30:00.360
Oh, Sora.

06:30:00.419 --> 06:30:01.680
Umber said.

06:30:01.740 --> 06:30:03.540
He went over and put his wings around

06:30:03.540 --> 06:30:03.840
her.

06:30:03.900 --> 06:30:05.580
Sora.

06:30:05.639 --> 06:30:07.259
Sore, I love you anyway.

06:30:07.319 --> 06:30:08.880
But why did you do it?

06:30:08.939 --> 06:30:12.540
She covered her face with her claws.

06:30:12.599 --> 06:30:13.919
Don't you know who she is?

06:30:13.979 --> 06:30:17.759
Her words came in gasps between hiccups

06:30:17.759 --> 06:30:18.479
and sobs.

06:30:18.540 --> 06:30:21.540
The flood of images from Zora's mind was

06:30:21.540 --> 06:30:22.319
inescapable.

06:30:22.380 --> 06:30:25.799
Moon felt them like a waterfall pounding

06:30:25.799 --> 06:30:28.319
along her wings, a waterfall she could

06:30:28.319 --> 06:30:30.840
suddenly see, over an open plain with

06:30:30.840 --> 06:30:33.299
rivers running through it to the ocean, a

06:30:33.299 --> 06:30:34.200
battle was raging.

06:30:34.259 --> 06:30:37.380
Brown dragons and white dragons grappled

06:30:37.380 --> 06:30:39.659
in the air, shooting fire and frost

06:30:39.659 --> 06:30:42.840
breath, roaring with fury and pain, and

06:30:42.840 --> 06:30:44.639
there was Sora, darting through the

06:30:44.639 --> 06:30:45.180
melee.

06:30:45.240 --> 06:30:47.700
Her face was set grimly, behind her.

06:30:47.759 --> 06:30:50.159
Marsh was close on her tail, his features

06:30:50.159 --> 06:30:51.180
racked with fear.

06:30:51.240 --> 06:30:53.880
A pair of ice wings lashed out at them

06:30:53.880 --> 06:30:56.279
with their serrated claws, and so had

06:30:56.279 --> 06:30:58.380
just managed to pull marsh out of the way

06:30:58.380 --> 06:30:58.860
in time.

06:30:58.919 --> 06:31:00.720
They swooped around to try again.

06:31:00.779 --> 06:31:02.459
Reed?

06:31:02.520 --> 06:31:03.419
Sori yelled.

06:31:03.479 --> 06:31:04.020
Help us.

06:31:04.139 --> 06:31:07.799
A big mud wing dove toward them, swatting

06:31:07.799 --> 06:31:10.020
ice wings aside with his tail as he flew

06:31:10.020 --> 06:31:12.060
but another mud wing got there first.

06:31:12.119 --> 06:31:14.880
A thin brown female that Moon had seen in

06:31:14.880 --> 06:31:15.900
Sora's mind before.

06:31:15.959 --> 06:31:18.599
She slashed one ice wing through the neck

06:31:18.599 --> 06:31:20.580
and then twisted to set the other ice

06:31:20.580 --> 06:31:21.659
wing on fire.

06:31:21.720 --> 06:31:24.360
He flapped away, shrieking and batting at

06:31:24.360 --> 06:31:25.619
the flames along his wings.

06:31:25.680 --> 06:31:27.540
Thank you, Crane.

06:31:27.599 --> 06:31:28.500
Marsh called.

06:31:28.560 --> 06:31:31.020
Their sister turned to smile at Marsh and

06:31:31.020 --> 06:31:34.319
Sora, and then, an ice wing plummeted out

06:31:34.319 --> 06:31:37.259
of the sky out of nowhere, seized Crane

06:31:37.259 --> 06:31:39.180
in her talons, and slit her throat.

06:31:39.240 --> 06:31:42.360
No, Saurus screamed.

06:31:42.479 --> 06:31:45.360
The ice wing turned. to give her a

06:31:45.360 --> 06:31:47.040
malicious, triumphant grin.

06:31:47.099 --> 06:31:49.139
It was icicle.

06:31:49.200 --> 06:31:52.740
The memory faded, but the destroyed

06:31:52.740 --> 06:31:54.599
feeling hung heavily in Moon's chest.

06:31:54.659 --> 06:31:56.939
She killed Crane.

06:31:57.000 --> 06:31:59.819
Sora sobbed into Umber's shoulder.

06:31:59.880 --> 06:32:00.840
I saw her.

06:32:00.900 --> 06:32:02.220
I saw her.

06:32:02.279 --> 06:32:04.560
She's the one who killed our sister.

06:32:04.619 --> 06:32:06.360
Sora.

06:32:06.419 --> 06:32:07.919
How can you be sure?

06:32:07.919 --> 06:32:10.020
he asked, pulling her clothes.

06:32:10.080 --> 06:32:12.060
It was a terrible battle.

06:32:12.119 --> 06:32:15.299
There were a 100 ice wings there, and we

06:32:15.299 --> 06:32:16.500
were all fighting for our lives.

06:32:16.560 --> 06:32:19.259
Your memory could be playing tricks on

06:32:19.259 --> 06:32:19.380
you.

06:32:19.439 --> 06:32:22.259
She could be finding the enemy of her

06:32:22.259 --> 06:32:24.959
nightmares in the 1st ice wing face she

06:32:24.959 --> 06:32:26.400
saw here, he thought.

06:32:26.459 --> 06:32:30.360
Or else, if she's right, we have the

06:32:30.360 --> 06:32:31.439
worst luck in the world.

06:32:31.560 --> 06:32:34.380
Ending up in the same cave as Crane's

06:32:34.380 --> 06:32:34.860
murderer.

06:32:34.979 --> 06:32:36.900
I would have lost my mind too.

06:32:36.959 --> 06:32:39.659
Moon didn't think that was true.

06:32:39.720 --> 06:32:42.720
Umber's mind was a lot more resilient

06:32:42.720 --> 06:32:43.619
than Sora's.

06:32:43.680 --> 06:32:46.680
She could see that, and now she could

06:32:46.680 --> 06:32:48.900
also see that she was not as much like

06:32:48.900 --> 06:32:50.279
Sora as she'd thought.

06:32:50.340 --> 06:32:53.639
Perhaps they were both shy, but Sora was

06:32:53.639 --> 06:32:56.400
also fragile, too fragile for the awful

06:32:56.400 --> 06:32:57.659
things she'd been through.

06:32:57.720 --> 06:32:59.819
I'm afraid.

06:32:59.880 --> 06:33:02.400
There may be awful things ahead for you

06:33:02.400 --> 06:33:03.299
too, little moon.

06:33:03.419 --> 06:33:05.340
Dark Stalker whispered.

06:33:05.400 --> 06:33:09.659
But I'm not fragile, Moon said, I won't

06:33:09.659 --> 06:33:10.380
be fragile.

06:33:10.500 --> 06:33:11.220
I refuse.

06:33:11.340 --> 06:33:14.759
I think you're right about that, he

06:33:14.759 --> 06:33:15.119
agreed.

06:33:15.240 --> 06:33:18.419
I'm sure it was her, Sora said.

06:33:18.479 --> 06:33:19.979
I'm not crazy, Amber.

06:33:20.040 --> 06:33:22.380
I got a scroll to look up ice wing

06:33:22.380 --> 06:33:23.159
physiognomy.

06:33:23.220 --> 06:33:25.259
I made sure she'd been on the front

06:33:25.259 --> 06:33:25.680
lines.

06:33:25.740 --> 06:33:28.380
I couldn't ask more specific questions

06:33:28.380 --> 06:33:30.659
without making her suspicious, but I knew

06:33:30.659 --> 06:33:32.939
what she did, and I couldn't let her

06:33:32.939 --> 06:33:33.240
live.

06:33:33.299 --> 06:33:35.700
The war is over, Sora.

06:33:35.819 --> 06:33:37.080
Umber protested.

06:33:37.139 --> 06:33:40.200
This had nothing to do with the war, she

06:33:40.200 --> 06:33:40.439
said.

06:33:40.560 --> 06:33:42.840
But what about everyone else?

06:33:42.900 --> 06:33:44.159
Kibley asked.

06:33:44.220 --> 06:33:46.319
Didn't you care if the rest of us died?

06:33:46.439 --> 06:33:49.080
Sora couldn't meet his eyes.

06:33:49.139 --> 06:33:51.479
I thought she'd be the only one in

06:33:51.479 --> 06:33:51.659
there.

06:33:51.720 --> 06:33:54.360
I'd never used a dragon plant cactus

06:33:54.360 --> 06:33:55.259
before.

06:33:55.319 --> 06:33:57.599
I expected it to go off sooner, and she

06:33:57.599 --> 06:33:58.319
should have been in there.

06:33:58.380 --> 06:34:01.020
I can't believe I failed twice.

06:34:01.080 --> 06:34:03.959
She gave Tamron an anguished look.

06:34:04.020 --> 06:34:07.319
And then the other 2 dragons, and poor

06:34:07.319 --> 06:34:08.040
Tamarind.

06:34:08.099 --> 06:34:11.159
But it's just collateral damage, isn't it

06:34:11.159 --> 06:34:11.520
Umber?

06:34:11.580 --> 06:34:13.799
We learned about that from the sky wing

06:34:13.799 --> 06:34:14.459
generals.

06:34:14.520 --> 06:34:17.459
He shook his head, unable to speak.

06:34:17.520 --> 06:34:21.299
And then everyone was looking at me, Sora

06:34:21.299 --> 06:34:21.779
whispered.

06:34:21.840 --> 06:34:24.779
Everyone was thinking about me and how

06:34:24.779 --> 06:34:27.000
awful I am, and how much they hate me.

06:34:27.060 --> 06:34:28.799
They could see right through me.

06:34:28.860 --> 06:34:29.939
I know they could.

06:34:30.000 --> 06:34:32.580
No, Sora, Moon said.

06:34:32.639 --> 06:34:34.439
They weren't, truly.

06:34:34.500 --> 06:34:37.380
Dragons think mostly about themselves.

06:34:37.500 --> 06:34:39.479
Everyone is so worried about what other

06:34:39.479 --> 06:34:40.560
dragons think of them.

06:34:40.619 --> 06:34:42.720
They hardly stop to decide what they

06:34:42.720 --> 06:34:43.500
think of everyone else.

06:34:43.560 --> 06:34:46.619
Believe me, no one is thinking about you

06:34:46.619 --> 06:34:47.880
as much as you think they are.

06:34:47.939 --> 06:34:51.180
She'd finally realized how reassuring

06:34:51.180 --> 06:34:51.779
that was.

06:34:51.840 --> 06:34:54.419
All of our self doubt and nerves and

06:34:54.419 --> 06:34:55.619
feeling like an outsider.

06:34:55.680 --> 06:34:57.779
Once she paid attention to what she could

06:34:57.779 --> 06:35:00.000
hear around her, it turned out those were

06:35:00.000 --> 06:35:01.139
the things that made her the most

06:35:01.139 --> 06:35:01.619
normal.

06:35:01.680 --> 06:35:04.560
It turned out, that was how everyone

06:35:04.560 --> 06:35:05.040
felt.

06:35:05.099 --> 06:35:07.799
And certainly no one is thinking about

06:35:07.799 --> 06:35:09.599
you as much as you are thinking about

06:35:09.599 --> 06:35:09.840
you.

06:35:09.900 --> 06:35:14.220
Except maybe Icicle, Kibley said abruptly

06:35:14.220 --> 06:35:16.200
who is coming to kill you right now.

06:35:16.259 --> 06:35:18.060
Moon jumped.

06:35:18.119 --> 06:35:19.740
She'd almost forgotten about that.

06:35:19.799 --> 06:35:22.560
We need to get you to Sunny and Tsunami

06:35:22.560 --> 06:35:24.119
so you can confess and they can keep you

06:35:24.119 --> 06:35:24.419
safe.

06:35:24.479 --> 06:35:27.720
We can't, Umber said.

06:35:27.779 --> 06:35:31.139
I'm sorry, but if we do that, Sora ends

06:35:31.139 --> 06:35:31.500
up dead.

06:35:31.560 --> 06:35:33.959
Either Isaac will find a way to kill her

06:35:33.959 --> 06:35:36.540
or Queen Ruby will demand an eye for an

06:35:36.540 --> 06:35:37.560
eye for carnelian.

06:35:37.619 --> 06:35:39.119
He's right.

06:35:39.180 --> 06:35:43.259
Dark Stalker said, handing her over. leads

06:35:43.259 --> 06:35:45.360
to very few paths where Zora is alive 2

06:35:45.360 --> 06:35:45.840
months from now.

06:35:45.959 --> 06:35:49.139
But otherwise, you're letting a killer go

06:35:49.139 --> 06:35:49.380
free.

06:35:49.439 --> 06:35:52.259
You hinted at this once, didn't you?

06:35:52.319 --> 06:35:54.360
Moon thought, remembering.

06:35:54.419 --> 06:35:57.299
Send a friend to her death, or help a

06:35:57.299 --> 06:35:58.139
killer escape.

06:35:58.200 --> 06:35:59.700
You meant Sora.

06:35:59.759 --> 06:36:03.419
We'll leave now, Umber said.

06:36:03.479 --> 06:36:04.860
I'll go with her.

06:36:04.919 --> 06:36:06.180
I'll keep her safe.

06:36:06.299 --> 06:36:09.720
And keep everyone else safe from her.

06:36:09.779 --> 06:36:11.759
His mind finished the thought.

06:36:11.819 --> 06:36:15.720
But then you'll be a fugitive too, Sora

06:36:15.720 --> 06:36:16.020
said.

06:36:16.080 --> 06:36:17.580
And what about Marsh?

06:36:17.639 --> 06:36:19.799
Clay will get him back to Reed and

06:36:19.799 --> 06:36:20.340
Pheasant?

06:36:20.400 --> 06:36:21.479
Umber said.

06:36:21.540 --> 06:36:23.220
He turned to Kibley.

06:36:23.279 --> 06:36:25.439
Please tell Clay everything.

06:36:25.500 --> 06:36:26.880
Tell him we're sorry.

06:36:26.939 --> 06:36:28.799
I know he'll understand.

06:36:28.860 --> 06:36:31.680
But if we involve him, the queens will

06:36:31.680 --> 06:36:32.700
shut down the school.

06:36:32.759 --> 06:36:34.979
We have to leave without saying goodbye.

06:36:35.040 --> 06:36:37.619
Umber blinked back tears.

06:36:37.740 --> 06:36:39.720
Should we stop them?

06:36:39.779 --> 06:36:41.040
Kibli was thinking.

06:36:41.099 --> 06:36:42.479
What's the right thing to do?

06:36:42.540 --> 06:36:44.159
What would Thorn do?

06:36:44.220 --> 06:36:47.040
Soor is not well, and I don't want her to

06:36:47.040 --> 06:36:47.400
be killed.

06:36:47.459 --> 06:36:50.400
But she did kill Carnelian and Bigtail

06:36:50.400 --> 06:36:53.459
and tried to kill Icicle, but she needs

06:36:53.459 --> 06:36:54.299
to be taken care of.

06:36:54.360 --> 06:36:56.639
And where does the cycle end?

06:36:56.700 --> 06:36:59.220
If icicle kills Sora?

06:36:59.279 --> 06:37:01.619
Wouldn't Umber or Marsh be justified in

06:37:01.619 --> 06:37:02.040
killing her?

06:37:02.159 --> 06:37:04.319
And then wouldn't winter want to kill

06:37:04.319 --> 06:37:04.619
them?

06:37:04.680 --> 06:37:07.619
Isn't the whole point that the war is

06:37:07.619 --> 06:37:08.279
supposed to be over?

06:37:08.340 --> 06:37:11.340
Replacing it with a series of vengeance

06:37:11.340 --> 06:37:13.080
killings is not going to make the world

06:37:13.080 --> 06:37:15.180
any better or safer.

06:37:15.240 --> 06:37:18.419
And then Moon heard icicles' thoughts

06:37:18.419 --> 06:37:19.979
coming closer and closer.

06:37:20.040 --> 06:37:22.139
She made up her mind.

06:37:22.200 --> 06:37:25.860
Go, she said, stepping toward the window

06:37:25.860 --> 06:37:28.020
a tall open hole big enough for a

06:37:28.020 --> 06:37:30.299
dragonette sore's size to squeeze through

06:37:30.299 --> 06:37:32.400
as fast and as far as you can.

06:37:32.459 --> 06:37:35.700
Thank you, Sora whispered.

06:37:35.759 --> 06:37:38.340
She squeezed Umber's talons and darted

06:37:38.340 --> 06:37:38.880
toward the window.

06:37:38.939 --> 06:37:40.319
At the edge.

06:37:40.380 --> 06:37:42.000
She turned to look back at Moon.

06:37:42.060 --> 06:37:43.979
It was self-defense too.

06:37:44.040 --> 06:37:46.319
Beware of icicle Moon.

06:37:46.380 --> 06:37:48.180
She talks about killing all the time.

06:37:48.240 --> 06:37:49.740
Even in her sleep.

06:37:49.799 --> 06:37:51.599
What did she say?

06:37:51.659 --> 06:37:52.619
Moon asked.

06:37:52.680 --> 06:37:56.220
Our very 1st night here, Sora said, when

06:37:56.220 --> 06:37:57.240
I still wasn't sure.

06:37:57.299 --> 06:38:00.180
I was almost sure it was her, but I

06:38:00.180 --> 06:38:02.400
thought I must be mad, and I couldn't let

06:38:02.400 --> 06:38:04.619
myself sleep because what if she did the

06:38:04.619 --> 06:38:06.479
same thing to me that she did to Crane?

06:38:06.540 --> 06:38:08.880
And then in her sleep, she muttered

06:38:08.880 --> 06:38:10.560
killing is easy enough.

06:38:10.619 --> 06:38:12.540
That's when I knew.

06:38:12.599 --> 06:38:15.540
She's a murderer, and she won't stop

06:38:15.540 --> 06:38:17.520
until someone does what I failed to do.

06:38:17.580 --> 06:38:20.099
Let's go, Zora.

06:38:20.159 --> 06:38:21.659
Umber said sadly.

06:38:21.720 --> 06:38:25.139
Kibli stepped forward and twined his tail

06:38:25.139 --> 06:38:26.279
around Umbers for a moment.

06:38:26.340 --> 06:38:29.639
Moon felt Umber's longing and heartbreak

06:38:29.639 --> 06:38:32.220
and loyalty, like a physical pain in her

06:38:32.220 --> 06:38:32.520
chest.

06:38:32.639 --> 06:38:35.220
He leaned forward to give Kibley a quick

06:38:35.220 --> 06:38:38.159
hug, and then Moon, and then he scrambled

06:38:38.159 --> 06:38:38.939
up after his sister.

06:38:38.939 --> 06:38:40.860
A heartbeat later.

06:38:40.919 --> 06:38:41.819
They were gone.

06:38:41.880 --> 06:38:45.119
Two small shapes, winging away into the

06:38:45.119 --> 06:38:48.000
dark clouds, moon turned to Kibley

06:38:48.000 --> 06:38:49.200
realization dawning.

06:38:49.259 --> 06:38:52.500
Icicle is the one conspiring with Queen

06:38:52.500 --> 06:38:53.939
Scarlet, she said.

06:38:54.000 --> 06:38:56.459
Killing is easy enough.

06:38:56.520 --> 06:38:59.759
Moon had heard those exact words in the

06:38:59.759 --> 06:39:01.380
1st dream visitor conversation.

06:39:01.439 --> 06:39:04.560
She noticed that the violent blizzard of

06:39:04.560 --> 06:39:06.240
Isaacle's mind had veered off.

06:39:06.299 --> 06:39:08.520
She wasn't thinking about just Sora

06:39:08.520 --> 06:39:08.939
anymore.

06:39:09.000 --> 06:39:11.400
She was thinking about the caves where

06:39:11.400 --> 06:39:14.220
Sonny, clay, tsunami, and Starflight

06:39:14.220 --> 06:39:14.520
lived.

06:39:14.580 --> 06:39:17.220
We have to hurry, Moon said.

06:39:17.279 --> 06:39:19.919
She may not get to kill Zora, but that's

06:39:19.919 --> 06:39:21.659
not the only dragon she promised to kill

06:39:21.659 --> 06:39:21.840
today.

06:39:21.900 --> 06:39:26.279
Chapter 22.

06:39:26.520 --> 06:39:30.180
Moon and Kibli ran to the winding tunnels

06:39:30.180 --> 06:39:31.020
of Jade Mountain.

06:39:31.080 --> 06:39:33.419
Dragons jumped out of the way and stared

06:39:33.419 --> 06:39:34.560
at them as they shot past.

06:39:34.619 --> 06:39:37.380
Moon caught flashes of, what's

06:39:37.380 --> 06:39:37.680
happening?

06:39:37.740 --> 06:39:39.419
And was there another fire?

06:39:39.479 --> 06:39:41.939
And should I be running too?

06:39:42.060 --> 06:39:45.180
And, oi, sandwing, watch it with that

06:39:45.180 --> 06:39:45.419
tail.

06:39:45.540 --> 06:39:48.060
She thought she saw winter looking out of

06:39:48.060 --> 06:39:49.979
one of the caves they passed, but didn't

06:39:49.979 --> 06:39:50.520
slow down to check.

06:39:50.580 --> 06:39:52.860
Moon stop.

06:39:52.919 --> 06:39:53.939
You can't do this.

06:39:54.000 --> 06:39:55.380
I have to stop you.

06:39:55.439 --> 06:39:57.060
Dark Stalker said.

06:39:57.119 --> 06:39:58.439
This is not wise.

06:39:58.500 --> 06:39:59.400
It's not safe.

06:39:59.459 --> 06:40:01.560
I can't let you confront Icicle.

06:40:01.619 --> 06:40:03.360
There's so many ways in which it goes

06:40:03.360 --> 06:40:03.959
horribly wrong.

06:40:04.020 --> 06:40:05.939
Like, she kills me?

06:40:06.000 --> 06:40:07.080
Moon asked.

06:40:07.139 --> 06:40:09.240
Are there possibilities where she doesn't

06:40:09.240 --> 06:40:09.599
kill me?

06:40:09.659 --> 06:40:12.900
Yes, but they're faint.

06:40:12.959 --> 06:40:14.700
Moon, I can't lose you.

06:40:14.819 --> 06:40:17.819
I can't sit by and do nothing, she

06:40:17.819 --> 06:40:18.360
answered back.

06:40:18.479 --> 06:40:21.540
While Icicle kills somebody, somebody who

06:40:21.540 --> 06:40:23.220
might change the future of this world?

06:40:23.279 --> 06:40:25.979
Look into those futures, Dark Stalker

06:40:25.979 --> 06:40:29.040
without Sonny, or Starflight, clay, or

06:40:29.040 --> 06:40:29.700
tsunami.

06:40:29.759 --> 06:40:31.740
Isn't the world a darker place?

06:40:31.799 --> 06:40:33.720
If this school fails?

06:40:33.840 --> 06:40:35.939
How soon are the tribes back at war?

06:40:36.000 --> 06:40:38.759
He was silent for a long moment.

06:40:38.880 --> 06:40:41.220
I see your point.

06:40:41.279 --> 06:40:44.340
But a world without you in it is also

06:40:44.340 --> 06:40:45.479
much diminished moon.

06:40:45.599 --> 06:40:47.099
Really?

06:40:47.159 --> 06:40:49.619
She couldn't imagine that was true.

06:40:49.680 --> 06:40:52.680
Let Kibley go stop her on his own.

06:40:52.799 --> 06:40:54.659
Dog stalker suggested.

06:40:54.720 --> 06:40:56.639
Can he do that and survive?

06:40:56.700 --> 06:40:57.540
She asked.

06:40:57.599 --> 06:40:58.560
Honestly.

06:40:58.619 --> 06:41:01.139
Hmm, he said.

06:41:01.200 --> 06:41:03.599
Maybe a one in 300 chance.

06:41:03.659 --> 06:41:05.880
Not good enough. she said.

06:41:05.939 --> 06:41:06.959
I need to be there.

06:41:07.020 --> 06:41:11.520
For him to survive, Dark Stalker side.

06:41:11.580 --> 06:41:13.560
Yes, you do.

06:41:13.619 --> 06:41:16.500
She tried not to be terrified by this

06:41:16.500 --> 06:41:18.599
reminder that she was running toward her

06:41:18.599 --> 06:41:19.020
own death.

06:41:19.080 --> 06:41:21.659
She tried to just focus on the distant

06:41:21.659 --> 06:41:22.740
echo of icicle.

06:41:22.799 --> 06:41:24.779
Where was the ice wing going?

06:41:24.840 --> 06:41:27.540
The rage was clear enough, but her

06:41:27.540 --> 06:41:28.560
surroundings were not.

06:41:28.619 --> 06:41:30.779
Moon concentrated and heard.

06:41:30.900 --> 06:41:32.220
Not here.

06:41:32.279 --> 06:41:33.360
Not here.

06:41:33.419 --> 06:41:36.119
They're not in their sleeping quarters

06:41:36.119 --> 06:41:37.979
she said between gasping breaths.

06:41:38.040 --> 06:41:39.959
She has to look for them somewhere else.

06:41:40.020 --> 06:41:42.659
She could have killed clay in the parade

06:41:42.659 --> 06:41:43.020
center.

06:41:43.080 --> 06:41:44.220
Kibley pointed out.

06:41:44.279 --> 06:41:45.540
So why didn't she?

06:41:45.599 --> 06:41:48.659
I think, I think she didn't want to do it

06:41:48.659 --> 06:41:51.479
in front of winter, Moon said, stopping

06:41:51.479 --> 06:41:53.939
and pressing on her temples, and Clay's

06:41:53.939 --> 06:41:54.419
the biggest.

06:41:54.479 --> 06:41:56.580
Maybe she wants to kill off the easiest

06:41:56.580 --> 06:41:57.119
ones first.

06:41:57.240 --> 06:41:58.500
Sonny?

06:41:58.619 --> 06:42:01.919
Sonny's, not that easy to kill, said

06:42:01.919 --> 06:42:02.580
Kibley.

06:42:02.639 --> 06:42:04.200
Starflight.

06:42:04.259 --> 06:42:06.599
They both said at the same time, and

06:42:06.599 --> 06:42:08.220
whirled to race to the library.

06:42:08.279 --> 06:42:10.740
Icicle got their first.

06:42:10.799 --> 06:42:13.740
Moon and Kibley burst in to find her

06:42:13.740 --> 06:42:15.720
silently creeping up on Starflight.

06:42:15.779 --> 06:42:18.000
Her lethally sharp claws were

06:42:18.000 --> 06:42:20.220
outstretched, and her jaw was moving

06:42:20.220 --> 06:42:22.680
calling out the deadly ice wing frost

06:42:22.680 --> 06:42:22.979
breath.

06:42:23.040 --> 06:42:26.099
When she saw them, her eyes widened and

06:42:26.099 --> 06:42:27.599
flicked from them to Starflight and

06:42:27.599 --> 06:42:27.840
back.

06:42:27.900 --> 06:42:30.479
The blind night wing was crouched in a

06:42:30.479 --> 06:42:32.759
corner, sorting scrolls by touching the

06:42:32.759 --> 06:42:34.860
stamps on the edges, but he raised his

06:42:34.860 --> 06:42:35.819
head in moon's direction.

06:42:35.880 --> 06:42:38.159
StoreFlight, look out!

06:42:38.220 --> 06:42:39.299
Kibley shouted.

06:42:39.419 --> 06:42:41.880
Icicle leapt forward and landed on

06:42:41.880 --> 06:42:42.659
Starflight's back.

06:42:42.720 --> 06:42:45.900
He yelled with pain, and she wrenched him

06:42:45.900 --> 06:42:48.180
around so his body was between her and

06:42:48.180 --> 06:42:49.020
the others.

06:42:49.080 --> 06:42:51.599
Her talons wrapped around his throat, and

06:42:51.599 --> 06:42:53.400
her wings pinned his to his sides.

06:42:53.459 --> 06:42:55.799
Don't do anything stupid.

06:42:55.919 --> 06:42:57.240
She hissed.

06:42:57.299 --> 06:42:59.580
There's a window right behind her.

06:42:59.639 --> 06:43:00.900
Kibley thought.

06:43:00.959 --> 06:43:03.540
If she realizes that, she could kill him

06:43:03.540 --> 06:43:05.099
and jump out before we could stop her.

06:43:05.159 --> 06:43:08.220
But right now, she thinks she needs him

06:43:08.220 --> 06:43:09.720
as leverage, so we'll let her go.

06:43:09.779 --> 06:43:12.060
Will have to distract her so I can

06:43:12.060 --> 06:43:12.360
attack.

06:43:12.419 --> 06:43:13.979
Too dangerous this way.

06:43:14.040 --> 06:43:16.500
I might hit Starfight with my tail

06:43:16.500 --> 06:43:17.040
instead of her.

06:43:17.099 --> 06:43:20.159
Search for weaknesses, get closer if I

06:43:20.159 --> 06:43:20.340
can.

06:43:20.400 --> 06:43:22.740
Please don't kill him.

06:43:22.799 --> 06:43:25.380
Moon said, holding out her claws.

06:43:25.439 --> 06:43:27.779
Just let him live, and we won't stop

06:43:27.779 --> 06:43:28.020
you.

06:43:28.080 --> 06:43:29.159
You can leave.

06:43:29.220 --> 06:43:30.180
Go wherever you want.

06:43:30.240 --> 06:43:34.080
I promise, Starflight said, his voice

06:43:34.080 --> 06:43:35.159
hoarse with fear.

06:43:35.220 --> 06:43:37.080
You won't have done anything wrong

06:43:37.080 --> 06:43:37.740
icicle.

06:43:37.799 --> 06:43:39.479
You can still go home now.

06:43:39.540 --> 06:43:42.659
But if you kill me, Queen Glacier might

06:43:42.659 --> 06:43:43.139
not take you back.

06:43:43.259 --> 06:43:44.880
Is he right?

06:43:44.939 --> 06:43:46.319
Icicle wondered.

06:43:46.380 --> 06:43:48.779
She might appreciate a reason to get rid

06:43:48.779 --> 06:43:51.119
of me, so I'm not a threat to her or her

06:43:51.119 --> 06:43:51.540
daughters.

06:43:51.659 --> 06:43:54.720
But if I succeed, and Scarlett gives me

06:43:54.720 --> 06:43:55.740
what I've been promised.

06:43:55.799 --> 06:43:58.680
I'll return home a hero, no matter who I

06:43:58.680 --> 06:43:59.340
kill along the way.

06:43:59.400 --> 06:44:03.599
You can't trust Queen Scarlet, Moon

06:44:03.599 --> 06:44:03.959
said.

06:44:04.020 --> 06:44:06.299
Isaacle jerked her head around to stare

06:44:06.299 --> 06:44:06.720
at Moon.

06:44:06.779 --> 06:44:10.139
Listen, please, set him free, and I

06:44:10.139 --> 06:44:11.639
promise we won't tell anyone you were

06:44:11.639 --> 06:44:12.419
conspiring with her.

06:44:12.479 --> 06:44:14.819
Icicles' wings flared.

06:44:14.880 --> 06:44:16.500
How did you know that?

06:44:16.560 --> 06:44:17.819
She snarled.

06:44:17.880 --> 06:44:19.799
Queen Scarlet?

06:44:19.919 --> 06:44:21.419
said a voice behind them.

06:44:21.479 --> 06:44:22.979
Icicle.

06:44:23.040 --> 06:44:24.180
What are you doing?

06:44:24.240 --> 06:44:27.720
It had been winter they'd run past, and

06:44:27.720 --> 06:44:28.860
of course he had followed them.

06:44:28.919 --> 06:44:31.139
The dazzling confusion of his mind was

06:44:31.139 --> 06:44:31.919
brighter than ever.

06:44:31.979 --> 06:44:33.959
He couldn't even process what he was

06:44:33.959 --> 06:44:34.259
seeing.

06:44:34.319 --> 06:44:37.619
His sister about to kill Starfight.

06:44:37.680 --> 06:44:39.599
Stay out of this.

06:44:39.659 --> 06:44:42.360
Isaicle warned him, unless you'd like to

06:44:42.360 --> 06:44:45.119
be helpful, in which case, go find Sonny

06:44:45.119 --> 06:44:45.540
and kill her.

06:44:45.659 --> 06:44:47.700
What are you talking about?

06:44:47.759 --> 06:44:49.080
Winter shouted.

06:44:49.139 --> 06:44:50.340
Why would we do that?

06:44:50.400 --> 06:44:55.020
He's a weak fool, Icicle thought, cold

06:44:55.020 --> 06:44:55.740
and clear.

06:44:55.799 --> 06:44:58.319
Mother always said you weren't as strong

06:44:58.319 --> 06:45:00.900
or smart as hailstorm, she spat.

06:45:01.020 --> 06:45:03.840
Winter flinched as if he'd been struck.

06:45:03.900 --> 06:45:06.959
I see you edging closer sandwing.

06:45:07.080 --> 06:45:09.720
Icicle said, glaring at Kibley.

06:45:09.779 --> 06:45:11.099
He stopped moving.

06:45:11.159 --> 06:45:14.159
Listen, I'll just take this librarian

06:45:14.159 --> 06:45:15.720
with me to make sure no one follows.

06:45:15.779 --> 06:45:17.880
I'll release him once I'm a safe distance

06:45:17.880 --> 06:45:18.299
away.

06:45:18.360 --> 06:45:20.459
That's the best deal you're going to

06:45:20.459 --> 06:45:20.639
get.

06:45:20.700 --> 06:45:22.319
She's lying.

06:45:22.380 --> 06:45:23.400
Moon said.

06:45:23.459 --> 06:45:25.259
She'll kill him as soon as she gets a

06:45:25.259 --> 06:45:25.500
chance.

06:45:25.560 --> 06:45:29.220
And Moon would know, Kibley thought.

06:45:29.279 --> 06:45:32.040
Icicle shot a poisonous look at Moon.

06:45:32.099 --> 06:45:33.360
Very well?

06:45:33.419 --> 06:45:35.819
Plan B, the ice wing thought.

06:45:35.880 --> 06:45:38.340
Multiple kills, escape in the chaos.

06:45:38.400 --> 06:45:40.919
That sand wing is just within range of my

06:45:40.919 --> 06:45:42.900
frost breath, and then I slit

06:45:42.900 --> 06:45:44.939
Starflight's throat, break the little

06:45:44.939 --> 06:45:47.040
night wing's neck, and go after Sonny and

06:45:47.040 --> 06:45:47.400
the others.

06:45:47.459 --> 06:45:49.919
Winter can stay and whimper over their

06:45:49.919 --> 06:45:50.819
bones if he wants to.

06:45:50.880 --> 06:45:54.419
She seemed to be focused on Moon, but her

06:45:54.419 --> 06:45:56.099
mind was waiting for Kibli to try

06:45:56.099 --> 06:45:57.180
sneaking forward again.

06:45:57.240 --> 06:45:59.759
One step closer, Sandwing.

06:45:59.819 --> 06:46:02.340
One, Step.

06:46:02.520 --> 06:46:05.040
Now, Kibley!

06:46:05.099 --> 06:46:07.860
Moon yelled, weeping at him, she shoved

06:46:07.860 --> 06:46:09.720
him out of the way as a blast of freezing

06:46:09.720 --> 06:46:11.400
air shot out of icicle's mouth.

06:46:11.459 --> 06:46:12.959
Get down.

06:46:13.020 --> 06:46:15.060
Dark Stalker roared in her brain.

06:46:15.119 --> 06:46:18.840
Moon felt as if he'd slammed great talons

06:46:18.840 --> 06:46:20.580
into her back and thrown her to the

06:46:20.580 --> 06:46:20.700
ground.

06:46:20.759 --> 06:46:23.700
The frost breath went over her head, and

06:46:23.700 --> 06:46:25.560
caught just the edge of Moon's wing.

06:46:25.619 --> 06:46:27.900
She screamed at the sudden pain.

06:46:27.959 --> 06:46:31.200
Everything happened at once, along with a

06:46:31.200 --> 06:46:32.880
deafening thunderclap of fury and

06:46:32.880 --> 06:46:35.279
adrenaline that surged into moon from all

06:46:35.279 --> 06:46:36.240
the dragons in the room.

06:46:36.299 --> 06:46:39.479
Winter roared and charged toward them.

06:46:39.540 --> 06:46:42.060
Starflight jabbed icicle hard in the

06:46:42.060 --> 06:46:43.979
chest, and she let go of his neck with a

06:46:43.979 --> 06:46:44.340
grunt.

06:46:44.400 --> 06:46:47.159
But as he staggered away, she grabbed him

06:46:47.159 --> 06:46:48.840
again and smashed him into the cave

06:46:48.840 --> 06:46:49.200
wall.

06:46:49.259 --> 06:46:51.419
He crumpled to the ground with his eyes

06:46:51.419 --> 06:46:51.840
closed.

06:46:51.900 --> 06:46:55.619
Moon let out a cry, and ran forward to

06:46:55.619 --> 06:46:56.459
crouch beside him.

06:46:56.520 --> 06:46:59.159
She reached out and felt the flicker of

06:46:59.159 --> 06:47:00.900
his brain dropping into unconsciousness.

06:47:00.959 --> 06:47:02.520
He was still alive.

06:47:02.580 --> 06:47:04.500
In the same moment.

06:47:04.560 --> 06:47:06.840
Kibley threw himself at icicle and

06:47:06.840 --> 06:47:07.740
knocked her off her feet.

06:47:07.799 --> 06:47:10.860
The ice wing and the sand wing struggled

06:47:10.860 --> 06:47:13.380
rolling across the floor, kicking scrolls

06:47:13.380 --> 06:47:14.279
in all directions.

06:47:14.340 --> 06:47:16.619
Kibley stabbed his tail at her, but

06:47:16.619 --> 06:47:16.919
missed.

06:47:16.979 --> 06:47:19.860
She flung him away, so he crashed hard on

06:47:19.860 --> 06:47:21.779
top of the main desk, and slid over

06:47:21.779 --> 06:47:22.139
behind it.

06:47:22.200 --> 06:47:26.400
Seconds later, moon was seized by cruel

06:47:26.400 --> 06:47:29.340
cold talons and pinned to the ground

06:47:29.400 --> 06:47:31.380
icicles, claws wrapped around her neck.

06:47:31.439 --> 06:47:34.259
Icicle don't, Winter yelled.

06:47:34.319 --> 06:47:36.419
He grabbed his sister and tried to drag

06:47:36.419 --> 06:47:38.459
her off moon, but she was bigger than he

06:47:38.459 --> 06:47:39.900
was, and too heavy to move.

06:47:40.020 --> 06:47:42.659
You never won when we fought in the

06:47:42.659 --> 06:47:43.259
hatchery.

06:47:43.319 --> 06:47:44.700
She snarled at him.

06:47:44.759 --> 06:47:46.080
Don't bother trying now.

06:47:46.139 --> 06:47:47.040
And for what?

06:47:47.099 --> 06:47:48.659
A couple of night wings?

06:47:48.720 --> 06:47:50.459
Don't you remember that we hate them?

06:47:50.520 --> 06:47:52.860
Don't you remember what they did to our

06:47:52.860 --> 06:47:53.400
tribe?

06:47:53.459 --> 06:47:54.720
To hailstorm?

06:47:54.779 --> 06:47:58.020
Winter froze, still clutching her

06:47:58.020 --> 06:47:58.319
shoulders.

06:47:58.439 --> 06:48:01.259
His mind slipped into the well worn

06:48:01.259 --> 06:48:03.540
tracks had heard on the 1st day she met

06:48:03.540 --> 06:48:03.900
him.

06:48:03.959 --> 06:48:06.779
The night wings killed him, and all of

06:48:06.779 --> 06:48:07.020
them.

06:48:07.080 --> 06:48:09.599
All of Scarlet's Ice Wing prisoners.

06:48:09.659 --> 06:48:12.299
The Nightwings came right out of the sky

06:48:12.299 --> 06:48:15.060
and killed every last ice wing in

06:48:15.060 --> 06:48:17.400
Scarlet's Mountain Prison, Icicle said.

06:48:17.459 --> 06:48:19.860
While the ice wings were still bound and

06:48:19.860 --> 06:48:20.400
chained.

06:48:20.459 --> 06:48:21.299
Remember?

06:48:21.419 --> 06:48:23.159
And do you remember why?

06:48:23.220 --> 06:48:26.340
To make Queen Scarlet free that one?

06:48:26.459 --> 06:48:29.220
She let go of Moon's neck with one talon

06:48:29.220 --> 06:48:30.659
to point at Starflight.

06:48:30.720 --> 06:48:32.400
He's the reason they're all dead.

06:48:32.459 --> 06:48:34.680
Winter did remember.

06:48:34.740 --> 06:48:36.959
Moon could see it all flooding through

06:48:36.959 --> 06:48:37.259
his head.

06:48:37.319 --> 06:48:39.599
This was the heart of his guilt.

06:48:39.659 --> 06:48:42.119
He'd gotten his brother captured by

06:48:42.119 --> 06:48:44.279
Skywing soldiers when they went looking

06:48:44.279 --> 06:48:46.259
for scavenger dens in the mountains.

06:48:46.319 --> 06:48:48.479
So his brother had been in Queen

06:48:48.479 --> 06:48:50.880
Scarlet's prison, when the night wings

06:48:50.880 --> 06:48:53.459
arrived to save Starflight, and they had

06:48:53.459 --> 06:48:55.080
killed all the ice wings in a show of

06:48:55.080 --> 06:48:55.560
strength.

06:48:55.619 --> 06:48:57.659
Every last one.

06:48:57.720 --> 06:49:00.659
That was why Winter hated Nightwings.

06:49:00.720 --> 06:49:03.659
But Starflight's not to blame?

06:49:03.720 --> 06:49:05.580
Moon choked out wretchedly.

06:49:05.639 --> 06:49:08.700
He's the kind of dragon who will stop the

06:49:08.700 --> 06:49:10.860
killing winter, not cause anymore.

06:49:10.919 --> 06:49:13.619
He's good inside, just like you are.

06:49:13.740 --> 06:49:15.540
His eyes.

06:49:15.599 --> 06:49:18.599
Blue as Arctic oceans stared into hers.

06:49:18.659 --> 06:49:19.919
Good.

06:49:19.979 --> 06:49:23.520
Would you rather be good or strong?

06:49:23.580 --> 06:49:25.380
Isicle spat at him.

06:49:25.439 --> 06:49:26.939
In response.

06:49:27.000 --> 06:49:29.099
Winter smashed his sister across the head

06:49:29.099 --> 06:49:29.700
with his tail.

06:49:29.759 --> 06:49:33.720
Icicle fell back roaring, and Moon gasped

06:49:33.720 --> 06:49:34.139
for air.

06:49:34.200 --> 06:49:36.599
Starflight and Moon didn't kill

06:49:36.599 --> 06:49:37.500
Hellstorm.

06:49:37.560 --> 06:49:38.580
Winter shouted.

06:49:38.639 --> 06:49:40.080
Queen Scarlet did.

06:49:40.139 --> 06:49:42.000
She's the one who took him prisoner.

06:49:42.060 --> 06:49:44.220
He would have died in her arena sooner or

06:49:44.220 --> 06:49:44.400
later.

06:49:44.459 --> 06:49:45.840
How can you work with her?

06:49:45.900 --> 06:49:47.639
How can you work for her?

06:49:47.700 --> 06:49:49.200
How can you do anything she says?

06:49:49.319 --> 06:49:53.340
He advanced, and Icicle retreated, back

06:49:53.340 --> 06:49:55.259
toward the bank of leaf covered windows.

06:49:55.319 --> 06:49:57.840
A trickle of dark blue blood was running

06:49:57.840 --> 06:49:59.819
down the side of her head from a gash

06:49:59.819 --> 06:50:00.900
near one of her horns.

06:50:00.959 --> 06:50:03.720
The same dark blue was smeared across her

06:50:03.720 --> 06:50:06.060
white shoulders, bleeding from a dozen

06:50:06.060 --> 06:50:07.979
cuts left by Kibley's claws.

06:50:08.040 --> 06:50:09.360
She was panting heavily.

06:50:09.419 --> 06:50:12.779
You are the worst kind of dirt covered

06:50:12.779 --> 06:50:13.619
whale chum.

06:50:13.680 --> 06:50:15.659
Icicle growled at Winter.

06:50:15.720 --> 06:50:17.040
You've ruined everything.

06:50:17.099 --> 06:50:20.220
It seems to me, like you're the one who's

06:50:20.220 --> 06:50:21.599
done that, he said.

06:50:21.659 --> 06:50:24.959
You don't understand, she said, you

06:50:24.959 --> 06:50:25.979
idiot.

06:50:26.040 --> 06:50:27.119
Winter stopped.

06:50:27.180 --> 06:50:28.799
His wings spread menacingly.

06:50:28.860 --> 06:50:31.919
So explain it to me, he said.

06:50:31.979 --> 06:50:35.459
Our brother is alive, you fool, she

06:50:35.459 --> 06:50:36.000
snarled.

06:50:36.119 --> 06:50:37.799
Queen Scarlet told me.

06:50:37.860 --> 06:50:40.740
She kept the most important prisoners in

06:50:40.740 --> 06:50:42.119
a secret separate prison.

06:50:42.240 --> 06:50:45.180
He wasn't killed by the night wings

06:50:45.180 --> 06:50:46.619
although 12 of our fellow dragons

06:50:46.619 --> 06:50:47.279
were...

06:50:47.340 --> 06:50:50.459
Moon clutched her head as agonizing

06:50:50.459 --> 06:50:52.139
spears of shock ricocheted through

06:50:52.139 --> 06:50:54.540
Winter's brain, like flying shards of a

06:50:54.540 --> 06:50:55.139
broken mirror.

06:50:55.259 --> 06:50:57.479
Hellstorm is alive?

06:50:57.540 --> 06:50:58.619
Winter cried.

06:50:58.680 --> 06:51:02.159
Yes, and if I had succeeded in killing

06:51:02.159 --> 06:51:03.900
the prophecy dragonettes for Queen

06:51:03.900 --> 06:51:06.060
Scarlet, she would have given him back to

06:51:06.060 --> 06:51:07.500
me, to us.

06:51:07.619 --> 06:51:10.799
Isaicle hissed, but instead, you've

06:51:10.799 --> 06:51:13.560
killed him all over again, and now you

06:51:13.560 --> 06:51:14.700
have to live with that forever.

06:51:14.759 --> 06:51:19.380
Chapter 23.

06:51:19.680 --> 06:51:22.560
Winter turned to moon.

06:51:22.619 --> 06:51:24.479
Agony written across his face.

06:51:24.540 --> 06:51:26.279
She knew what he was asking.

06:51:26.340 --> 06:51:28.680
Even though his mind couldn't put it into

06:51:28.680 --> 06:51:29.520
clear thoughts yet.

06:51:29.580 --> 06:51:33.900
It's true, Moon said, scanning Icicle's

06:51:33.900 --> 06:51:34.200
thoughts.

06:51:34.259 --> 06:51:36.360
At least, that's what Scarlett has told

06:51:36.360 --> 06:51:36.540
her.

06:51:36.659 --> 06:51:39.119
Scarlett could be lying, but Icycle

06:51:39.119 --> 06:51:39.479
believes her.

06:51:39.540 --> 06:51:41.819
Why didn't you tell me?

06:51:41.939 --> 06:51:43.680
Winter said to his sister.

06:51:43.740 --> 06:51:47.099
Because you're worthless, she spat, and I

06:51:47.099 --> 06:51:48.599
didn't want to waste time arguing with

06:51:48.599 --> 06:51:50.580
your sensitive moral sensibilities.

06:51:50.639 --> 06:51:52.860
She means she didn't want to be talked

06:51:52.860 --> 06:51:53.459
out of it.

06:51:53.520 --> 06:51:55.080
Moon said fiercely.

06:51:55.139 --> 06:51:57.959
And she knew you would try, and you might

06:51:57.959 --> 06:52:00.060
even have succeeded, because you're not

06:52:00.060 --> 06:52:00.659
worthless.

06:52:00.720 --> 06:52:03.659
You're smart and brave, and capable of

06:52:03.659 --> 06:52:04.740
caring about other dragons.

06:52:04.860 --> 06:52:06.840
Is it really true though?

06:52:06.900 --> 06:52:08.040
He said.

06:52:08.099 --> 06:52:10.740
A question not quite for either moon or

06:52:10.740 --> 06:52:11.400
icicle.

06:52:11.459 --> 06:52:13.799
Hailstorm isn't dead.

06:52:13.860 --> 06:52:16.919
Icicle narrowed her eyes and flicked her

06:52:16.919 --> 06:52:18.599
tail, weighing the possibilities.

06:52:18.720 --> 06:52:22.200
There's still time, she hissed at him.

06:52:22.259 --> 06:52:24.540
We could still kill the dragonettes and

06:52:24.540 --> 06:52:25.080
get him back.

06:52:25.139 --> 06:52:28.020
Winter hesitated, wavering.

06:52:28.080 --> 06:52:30.720
The memories of his brother were warm and

06:52:30.720 --> 06:52:33.419
tense, loving and terrible at the same

06:52:33.419 --> 06:52:33.659
time.

06:52:33.720 --> 06:52:36.840
He missed him desperately, and he needed

06:52:36.840 --> 06:52:38.580
to atone for the guilt of losing him in

06:52:38.580 --> 06:52:39.180
the 1st place.

06:52:39.240 --> 06:52:42.360
But he shook his head, not with more

06:52:42.360 --> 06:52:44.639
killing, not for Queen Scarlet.

06:52:44.700 --> 06:52:45.419
It won't work.

06:52:45.479 --> 06:52:46.740
Fine.

06:52:46.860 --> 06:52:48.419
Icicle snarled.

06:52:48.479 --> 06:52:50.759
I hope you choke on a walrus and die.

06:52:50.819 --> 06:52:53.580
She whirled and dove out the nearest

06:52:53.580 --> 06:52:56.159
window, tearing straight to the leaf pane

06:52:56.159 --> 06:52:57.659
and letting in a burst of too bright

06:52:57.659 --> 06:52:58.200
sunlight.

06:52:58.319 --> 06:53:00.240
Icicle, stop!

06:53:00.299 --> 06:53:01.319
Winter yelled.

06:53:01.380 --> 06:53:03.360
He ran to the window and leaned out.

06:53:03.419 --> 06:53:04.200
Come back.

06:53:04.259 --> 06:53:05.639
We can find him together.

06:53:05.700 --> 06:53:07.680
There was no response.

06:53:07.740 --> 06:53:10.380
In the fading echoes Moon could hear as

06:53:10.380 --> 06:53:11.340
icicle flew away.

06:53:11.400 --> 06:53:13.680
She saw that the ice wing was planning to

06:53:13.680 --> 06:53:15.720
find Queen Scarlet and complete her

06:53:15.720 --> 06:53:16.380
mission somehow.

06:53:16.500 --> 06:53:18.959
The dragonettes were far from safe.

06:53:19.080 --> 06:53:22.919
Behind the desk, Kibley groaned, and Moon

06:53:22.919 --> 06:53:24.419
darted over to him as he sat out

06:53:24.419 --> 06:53:24.959
gingerly.

06:53:25.020 --> 06:53:27.479
His pale yellow scales were dented and

06:53:27.479 --> 06:53:29.819
bruised, and his amber earring had been

06:53:29.819 --> 06:53:32.099
nearly torn out of his ear, making a

06:53:32.099 --> 06:53:33.900
small ragged tear where the hole had

06:53:33.900 --> 06:53:34.200
been.

06:53:34.259 --> 06:53:37.560
Six claws said it was idiotic to get this

06:53:37.619 --> 06:53:40.259
he thought, touching his earring with a

06:53:40.259 --> 06:53:40.680
wince.

06:53:40.740 --> 06:53:43.319
I can't believe I let an ice wing knock

06:53:43.319 --> 06:53:43.740
me out.

06:53:43.799 --> 06:53:46.020
Thorn would be unimpressed.

06:53:46.080 --> 06:53:48.419
I should have started with a fire burst

06:53:48.419 --> 06:53:48.900
to her face.

06:53:48.959 --> 06:53:50.700
But I thought she was going to attack

06:53:50.700 --> 06:53:52.919
Moon, and I just jumped in without

06:53:52.919 --> 06:53:53.459
thinking.

06:53:53.520 --> 06:53:55.500
Stupid, impulsive.

06:53:55.560 --> 06:53:57.659
Everything Thorn says, I need to learn to

06:53:57.659 --> 06:53:57.900
fix.

06:53:57.959 --> 06:54:00.659
Moon reached toward him and then

06:54:00.659 --> 06:54:01.200
hesitated.

06:54:01.259 --> 06:54:02.340
Can I?

06:54:02.400 --> 06:54:03.240
She asked.

06:54:03.299 --> 06:54:05.819
He met her eyes and nodded.

06:54:05.880 --> 06:54:08.400
She took one of his warm talons in hers

06:54:08.400 --> 06:54:09.479
and gently felt his head.

06:54:09.540 --> 06:54:12.779
There was a sizable bump over one eye, and

06:54:12.779 --> 06:54:14.759
a couple of claw marks slashed across his

06:54:14.759 --> 06:54:16.979
chest, but nothing as bad as she'd

06:54:16.979 --> 06:54:17.220
feared.

06:54:17.340 --> 06:54:20.400
Considering icicles formidable claws.

06:54:20.459 --> 06:54:22.979
That's right, Kibley said.

06:54:23.040 --> 06:54:25.860
He tried to stand up, flinched, and sat

06:54:25.860 --> 06:54:26.220
down again.

06:54:26.279 --> 06:54:28.139
She'd better run.

06:54:28.200 --> 06:54:30.240
I was just resting for part two.

06:54:30.299 --> 06:54:34.680
The crushing, or I do some crushing, and

06:54:34.680 --> 06:54:36.479
it's very impressive.

06:54:36.540 --> 06:54:38.400
I think I'd better lie down.

06:54:38.520 --> 06:54:42.000
Looks like you'll live, she said to him

06:54:42.000 --> 06:54:42.659
relieved.

06:54:42.720 --> 06:54:46.799
As will you, said Dark Stalker, sounding

06:54:46.799 --> 06:54:49.919
pleased, at least for now, tomorrow.

06:54:49.979 --> 06:54:52.500
Let's not think about tomorrow right this

06:54:52.500 --> 06:54:52.919
second.

06:54:52.979 --> 06:54:54.779
Moon suggested.

06:54:54.840 --> 06:54:56.700
And by the way, thank you.

06:54:56.759 --> 06:55:01.500
Moon sat with Sonny as night fell, on the

06:55:01.500 --> 06:55:03.840
tallest peak of Jade Mountain, watching a

06:55:03.840 --> 06:55:06.479
storm approach, a wall of rain was

06:55:06.479 --> 06:55:08.639
visible to the south, sweeping slowly

06:55:08.639 --> 06:55:11.279
toward them, patches of blue sky still

06:55:11.279 --> 06:55:13.080
peaked through the building banks of dark

06:55:13.080 --> 06:55:14.099
gray clouds.

06:55:14.159 --> 06:55:16.439
The wind seemed to carry the faraway

06:55:16.439 --> 06:55:17.700
scent of dragon fire.

06:55:17.759 --> 06:55:20.340
Ocean spray, and the rainforest.

06:55:20.400 --> 06:55:23.040
Moon wrapped her wings around herself

06:55:23.040 --> 06:55:25.740
shivering as the breeze picked up, and

06:55:25.740 --> 06:55:27.180
small raindrops began to fall.

06:55:27.240 --> 06:55:30.180
Sunny had her tail tucked around her back

06:55:30.180 --> 06:55:32.639
talons and was pressing her front talons

06:55:32.639 --> 06:55:33.180
together.

06:55:33.240 --> 06:55:36.000
Her strange green gray eyes were fixed on

06:55:36.000 --> 06:55:37.680
the line of desert, they could still

06:55:37.680 --> 06:55:38.819
faintly see to the west.

06:55:38.880 --> 06:55:42.060
Poor Sora, she said.

06:55:42.180 --> 06:55:44.520
Queen Morhen and Queen Ruby will be

06:55:44.520 --> 06:55:44.939
looking for her.

06:55:45.000 --> 06:55:46.919
Poor everybody really.

06:55:46.979 --> 06:55:48.419
Even Icicle.

06:55:48.540 --> 06:55:51.599
I mean, if Queen Scarlet had clay.

06:55:51.659 --> 06:55:53.220
I don't know what I'd do.

06:55:53.340 --> 06:55:55.560
There's one more thing I have to tell

06:55:55.560 --> 06:55:55.799
you.

06:55:55.860 --> 06:55:56.819
Moon said.

06:55:56.880 --> 06:56:00.180
I'm not sure this is wise.

06:56:00.240 --> 06:56:01.919
Dark Stalker interjected.

06:56:01.979 --> 06:56:04.919
I'm not going to hide anymore, she

06:56:04.919 --> 06:56:05.279
answered.

06:56:05.340 --> 06:56:07.439
Even if that means giving up a little

06:56:07.439 --> 06:56:07.979
safety.

06:56:08.040 --> 06:56:10.380
Or, all right, a lot of safety.

06:56:10.500 --> 06:56:11.639
You've made your point.

06:56:11.759 --> 06:56:13.500
She took a deep breath.

06:56:13.560 --> 06:56:17.459
I can read minds and see the future.

06:56:17.520 --> 06:56:21.840
Oh dear, Sonny thought immediately, her

06:56:21.840 --> 06:56:23.459
face creasing with skepticism.

06:56:23.520 --> 06:56:25.380
Another fate speaker.

06:56:25.439 --> 06:56:28.139
It's true, Moon said.

06:56:28.259 --> 06:56:30.900
She explained about the full moons, and

06:56:30.900 --> 06:56:32.459
about how she'd hidden her powers from

06:56:32.459 --> 06:56:34.919
everyone, and about how she'd used them

06:56:34.919 --> 06:56:37.139
to overhear icicle and scarlet, and

06:56:37.139 --> 06:56:38.459
foresee the fire.

06:56:38.520 --> 06:56:41.099
When she finished, Sonny's thoughts were

06:56:41.099 --> 06:56:42.299
a lot less skeptical.

06:56:42.360 --> 06:56:45.299
That's kind of a huge secret to have kept

06:56:45.299 --> 06:56:48.479
for so long, she said, studying Moon's

06:56:48.479 --> 06:56:48.779
eyes.

06:56:48.840 --> 06:56:50.459
It must have been hard.

06:56:50.580 --> 06:56:52.380
Moon nodded.

06:56:52.439 --> 06:56:55.319
There was a pause, and then Sonny said

06:56:55.319 --> 06:56:57.180
can you tell what I'm thinking right

06:56:57.180 --> 06:56:57.659
now?

06:56:57.720 --> 06:56:59.279
Sure.

06:56:59.400 --> 06:57:02.099
Moon check out her wings, tilting her

06:57:02.099 --> 06:57:02.639
head at Sonny.

06:57:02.700 --> 06:57:05.099
You're wondering how tsunami will react

06:57:05.099 --> 06:57:05.520
to this.

06:57:05.580 --> 06:57:08.040
You don't think she'll believe me, and

06:57:08.040 --> 06:57:09.720
part of you is worrying about Starflight

06:57:09.720 --> 06:57:11.939
and hoping fate speaker will take care of

06:57:11.939 --> 06:57:12.479
him properly.

06:57:12.540 --> 06:57:15.659
Sunny arched her brows, startled.

06:57:15.720 --> 06:57:19.139
But mostly, Moon hurried on, you're

06:57:19.139 --> 06:57:20.819
thinking about the school, and wondering

06:57:20.819 --> 06:57:21.900
if it's already failed.

06:57:21.959 --> 06:57:24.540
You're thinking about giving up, and

06:57:24.540 --> 06:57:26.459
sending everyone home, because it's only

06:57:26.459 --> 06:57:28.439
the 1st week, and all these terrible

06:57:28.439 --> 06:57:29.099
things have happened.

06:57:29.159 --> 06:57:31.500
You're wondering if bringing peace to all

06:57:31.500 --> 06:57:32.639
the tribes is too hard.

06:57:32.700 --> 06:57:34.799
And if you're not the right dragon for

06:57:34.799 --> 06:57:35.040
the job.

06:57:35.159 --> 06:57:38.520
Wow, Sonny said faintly.

06:57:38.639 --> 06:57:40.979
But you are, Moon blurted.

06:57:41.040 --> 06:57:42.060
You can't give up.

06:57:42.119 --> 06:57:43.680
Of course it's hard.

06:57:43.740 --> 06:57:45.479
The whole point is that you're trying to

06:57:45.479 --> 06:57:47.400
fix something that's nearly impossible to

06:57:47.400 --> 06:57:51.000
fix, but if no one ever even tries, then

06:57:51.000 --> 06:57:51.959
it will always be terrible.

06:57:52.020 --> 06:57:54.299
You and Clay and the others.

06:57:54.360 --> 06:57:56.099
Dragons believe in you.

06:57:56.159 --> 06:57:58.380
You have to take that gift and do

06:57:58.380 --> 06:58:00.419
something with it, not run away from it.

06:58:00.479 --> 06:58:02.099
Hmm.

06:58:02.220 --> 06:58:04.619
Dark Stalker said significantly.

06:58:04.680 --> 06:58:07.860
I know, I hear myself, she said.

06:58:07.919 --> 06:58:09.959
Was that a prophecy?

06:58:10.080 --> 06:58:11.400
Sonny said hopefully.

06:58:11.459 --> 06:58:13.319
Did you see us changing the world?

06:58:13.380 --> 06:58:16.380
Like, 5 eggs to hatch on brightest night

06:58:16.380 --> 06:58:18.959
5 dragons born to teach history and art

06:58:18.959 --> 06:58:21.119
and get everyone to calm down and be nice

06:58:21.119 --> 06:58:21.540
to each other?

06:58:21.599 --> 06:58:23.340
Moon laughed.

06:58:23.400 --> 06:58:26.580
When the school has lasted 20 years, the

06:58:26.580 --> 06:58:27.540
tribes will be at peace.

06:58:27.599 --> 06:58:28.919
She shook her head.

06:58:28.979 --> 06:58:31.319
No, it's not a prophecy.

06:58:31.380 --> 06:58:32.880
It's just faith.

06:58:33.000 --> 06:58:34.740
Sonny nodded.

06:58:34.799 --> 06:58:36.419
I know all about that.

06:58:36.479 --> 06:58:40.200
And if we make our own destiny, That's

06:58:40.200 --> 06:58:42.060
what I want mine to be, she thought.

06:58:42.119 --> 06:58:45.180
Let's go back inside before those clouds

06:58:45.180 --> 06:58:45.959
really open up on us.

06:58:46.080 --> 06:58:48.599
She reached out and touched Moon's

06:58:48.599 --> 06:58:49.020
shoulder.

06:58:49.080 --> 06:58:51.180
Thank you for telling me all that, Moon.

06:58:51.299 --> 06:58:53.159
I mean, about your powers and

06:58:53.159 --> 06:58:53.400
everything.

06:58:53.459 --> 06:58:56.939
They flew down to the great hall, where

06:58:56.939 --> 06:58:58.919
Moon found Kinkaju and Kibli waiting for

06:58:58.919 --> 06:58:59.099
her.

06:58:59.159 --> 06:59:01.919
Kinkaju ran over and threw her wings

06:59:01.919 --> 06:59:02.819
around Moon.

06:59:02.880 --> 06:59:05.580
Her frantic, relieved thoughts seemed to

06:59:05.580 --> 06:59:08.220
bounce wildly along Moon's scales.

06:59:08.279 --> 06:59:11.580
Alive, friends, heroes, averting tragedy

06:59:11.580 --> 06:59:12.419
and saving the day.

06:59:12.479 --> 06:59:15.900
Kibley told me what happened, she said.

06:59:15.959 --> 06:59:17.159
I can't believe I missed it all.

06:59:17.220 --> 06:59:19.259
I can't believe I wasn't there to protect

06:59:19.259 --> 06:59:19.680
you.

06:59:19.740 --> 06:59:22.619
You're totally heroes, saving us all from

06:59:22.619 --> 06:59:23.580
bad guys.

06:59:23.639 --> 06:59:25.919
Although I'm kind of confused about who's

06:59:25.919 --> 06:59:27.779
the bad guy and who I should be mad at

06:59:27.779 --> 06:59:29.700
because Sora?

06:59:29.759 --> 06:59:30.119
What?

06:59:30.180 --> 06:59:33.360
But also, Icicle was totally scary, but

06:59:33.360 --> 06:59:35.580
then saving her brother, Eck.

06:59:35.639 --> 06:59:38.400
So I get it, but still, attacking my

06:59:38.400 --> 06:59:39.119
winglet?

06:59:39.180 --> 06:59:40.080
My best friend?

06:59:40.139 --> 06:59:41.040
Not okay.

06:59:41.099 --> 06:59:43.200
Best friend?

06:59:43.319 --> 06:59:44.220
After everything?

06:59:44.279 --> 06:59:47.520
I thought you were mad at me, Moon said.

06:59:47.580 --> 06:59:49.799
Out of the corner of her eyes, she saw

06:59:49.799 --> 06:59:51.299
Sunny slipping away with a wave.

06:59:51.360 --> 06:59:54.060
I was, but that was yesterday.

06:59:54.180 --> 06:59:55.259
Kinkaju said.

06:59:55.319 --> 06:59:57.299
She released Moon and stepped back

06:59:57.299 --> 06:59:59.819
gleaming gold and pink with blue all

06:59:59.819 --> 07:00:00.540
along her spine.

07:00:00.599 --> 07:00:03.360
I mean, I realized it's not that big a

07:00:03.360 --> 07:00:03.540
deal.

07:00:03.599 --> 07:00:05.340
I kind of say everything I'm thinking

07:00:05.340 --> 07:00:06.060
anyway, right?

07:00:06.119 --> 07:00:07.319
She grinned.

07:00:07.380 --> 07:00:09.119
Or if you hear something, you shouldn't.

07:00:09.180 --> 07:00:11.040
That's kind of worse for you than for me

07:00:11.040 --> 07:00:11.580
I figure.

07:00:11.639 --> 07:00:14.400
And I was thinking if you promised to

07:00:14.400 --> 07:00:17.459
tell me all your secrets from now on, then

07:00:17.459 --> 07:00:19.139
it won't matter if you know all of mine

07:00:19.139 --> 07:00:20.159
right?

07:00:20.220 --> 07:00:23.099
Moon smiled back, the thought

07:00:23.099 --> 07:00:24.959
uncomfortably of Dark Stalker.

07:00:25.020 --> 07:00:27.659
Stop, stop, he said.

07:00:27.720 --> 07:00:29.939
I see all the bad decisions you're about

07:00:29.939 --> 07:00:30.240
to make.

07:00:30.299 --> 07:00:31.560
Don't do it, Moon.

07:00:31.680 --> 07:00:33.779
Where's Turtle?

07:00:33.840 --> 07:00:35.459
Moon asked, ignoring him.

07:00:35.520 --> 07:00:38.880
Here, he said, stepping out of the

07:00:38.880 --> 07:00:39.299
shadows.

07:00:39.360 --> 07:00:41.939
She hadn't noticed the quiet fuzz of his

07:00:41.939 --> 07:00:43.860
mind beyond the clamor of Kinkaju's

07:00:43.860 --> 07:00:44.220
thoughts.

07:00:44.279 --> 07:00:45.840
Can I see your armband?

07:00:45.959 --> 07:00:46.680
She asked.

07:00:46.740 --> 07:00:49.560
Inside her head, Dark Stalker sighed.

07:00:49.619 --> 07:00:52.560
I literally can't see any future where I

07:00:52.560 --> 07:00:53.279
can talk you out of this.

07:00:53.340 --> 07:00:56.099
Oh, good, Moon thought.

07:00:56.159 --> 07:00:57.599
Then take a break and don't try.

07:00:57.659 --> 07:01:00.840
Turtle slid the golden band down and over

07:01:00.840 --> 07:01:02.340
his talons and handed it to her.

07:01:02.400 --> 07:01:04.439
The silence instantly fell over

07:01:04.439 --> 07:01:06.360
everything, and Moon shivered.

07:01:06.419 --> 07:01:08.459
It was such a lonely feeling.

07:01:08.520 --> 07:01:11.159
How did other dragons live like this all

07:01:11.159 --> 07:01:11.400
the time?

07:01:11.459 --> 07:01:14.580
She studied the black rocks studded

07:01:14.580 --> 07:01:15.119
around the band.

07:01:15.180 --> 07:01:18.540
There were 6 of them, smaller than onyx's

07:01:18.540 --> 07:01:20.159
stone, but they were all the same

07:01:20.159 --> 07:01:22.259
scorched looking black with flecks of

07:01:22.259 --> 07:01:24.180
silver and otherworldly metals.

07:01:24.240 --> 07:01:26.880
Where did these stones come from?

07:01:26.939 --> 07:01:28.259
She asked Turtle.

07:01:28.319 --> 07:01:32.279
Oh, it's kind of a cool story, he said.

07:01:32.340 --> 07:01:35.279
I was out swimming at night with a few of

07:01:35.279 --> 07:01:36.299
my brothers a while ago.

07:01:36.360 --> 07:01:37.979
It's great.

07:01:38.040 --> 07:01:39.659
The sea at night with all the stars.

07:01:39.720 --> 07:01:42.180
And we were watching the comet that was

07:01:42.180 --> 07:01:43.200
so bright, remember?

07:01:43.259 --> 07:01:45.900
And then I saw something like a trail of

07:01:45.900 --> 07:01:47.819
fire fall from the sky into the ocean.

07:01:47.939 --> 07:01:50.400
No one else wanted to come search for it

07:01:50.400 --> 07:01:52.680
with me, so I figured I could keep what I

07:01:52.680 --> 07:01:55.439
found, which was this big chunk of black

07:01:55.439 --> 07:01:57.779
rock that had fallen all the way to the

07:01:57.779 --> 07:01:58.380
seafloor.

07:01:58.439 --> 07:02:00.659
It wasn't hard to find actually.

07:02:00.659 --> 07:02:03.180
It turned the water all around it a whole

07:02:03.180 --> 07:02:03.779
lot hotter.

07:02:03.840 --> 07:02:06.720
Anyway, I took a few bits that had broken

07:02:06.720 --> 07:02:08.939
off and had them made into that armband.

07:02:09.000 --> 07:02:13.380
Skyfire, Moon said, passing it back to

07:02:13.380 --> 07:02:13.619
him.

07:02:13.680 --> 07:02:15.959
She had a brief, intensely curious

07:02:15.959 --> 07:02:18.180
impulse to give the armband to Kibley for

07:02:18.180 --> 07:02:20.040
a minute, so she could hear what turtle

07:02:20.040 --> 07:02:21.840
was thinking and maybe find out his

07:02:21.840 --> 07:02:22.139
secret.

07:02:22.200 --> 07:02:24.599
But that was exactly the kind of thing

07:02:24.599 --> 07:02:26.819
she needed them to trust her not to do.

07:02:26.880 --> 07:02:29.759
That's what Onyx calls it.

07:02:29.819 --> 07:02:31.080
She has a piece of it too.

07:02:31.139 --> 07:02:34.139
Kimberly went still, looking at her.

07:02:34.200 --> 07:02:36.180
He was already figuring out what she was

07:02:36.180 --> 07:02:36.599
going to say.

07:02:36.659 --> 07:02:40.139
She turned to include Kinkaju as well.

07:02:40.200 --> 07:02:43.319
It turns out that Skyfire can block mind

07:02:43.319 --> 07:02:43.619
reading.

07:02:43.740 --> 07:02:46.259
I discovered that today while we were

07:02:46.259 --> 07:02:47.159
talking to Onyx.

07:02:47.220 --> 07:02:49.799
That's why I can't read her, or Turtle.

07:02:49.860 --> 07:02:52.560
If you're wearing this rock, I can't hear

07:02:52.560 --> 07:02:53.220
your thoughts at all.

07:02:53.279 --> 07:02:55.560
She faced Turtle again.

07:02:55.619 --> 07:02:58.799
I was hoping, if it's all right with you

07:02:58.799 --> 07:03:01.500
Turtle, I wondered if Kinkaju and Kibli

07:03:01.500 --> 07:03:02.939
and Winter could each have one of these

07:03:02.939 --> 07:03:03.299
rocks.

07:03:03.360 --> 07:03:05.279
You're all my friends.

07:03:05.340 --> 07:03:08.580
My winglet, and I want you to have a way

07:03:08.580 --> 07:03:10.259
to keep your thoughts private.

07:03:10.319 --> 07:03:12.779
Kingatu leaped up and hugged her again.

07:03:12.840 --> 07:03:16.439
Very cool, Kibley said, giving her a

07:03:16.439 --> 07:03:16.680
smile.

07:03:16.799 --> 07:03:20.400
That explains a lot, Turtle said.

07:03:20.520 --> 07:03:22.259
He started picking at the stones in the

07:03:22.259 --> 07:03:22.500
band.

07:03:22.560 --> 07:03:24.180
Of course they can have them.

07:03:24.240 --> 07:03:26.759
I'll take winter his and explain

07:03:26.759 --> 07:03:28.979
everything, Moon said with a deep

07:03:28.979 --> 07:03:29.459
breath.

07:03:29.520 --> 07:03:33.240
Actually, Kibley said, I have bad news.

07:03:33.299 --> 07:03:35.400
Moon saw it in his mind.

07:03:35.520 --> 07:03:37.560
She couldn't believe she hadn't picked it

07:03:37.560 --> 07:03:38.580
out of the torrent of his thoughts

07:03:38.580 --> 07:03:38.819
before.

07:03:38.880 --> 07:03:40.439
Oh no.

07:03:40.560 --> 07:03:41.220
Really?

07:03:41.279 --> 07:03:41.939
She said.

07:03:42.000 --> 07:03:42.959
What?

07:03:43.020 --> 07:03:44.099
Kinkaju asked.

07:03:44.159 --> 07:03:44.880
What?

07:03:44.939 --> 07:03:45.479
What?, what?

07:03:45.599 --> 07:03:48.000
It's winter, Kibley said.

07:03:48.060 --> 07:03:50.099
I checked our cave for him an hour ago.

07:03:50.159 --> 07:03:51.180
He's gone.

07:03:51.240 --> 07:03:55.740
Chapter 24.

07:03:55.979 --> 07:03:57.959
Gone?

07:03:58.020 --> 07:04:00.180
Kinkaju cried with dismay.

07:04:00.240 --> 07:04:01.020
Why?

07:04:01.080 --> 07:04:01.680
Where'd he go?

07:04:01.740 --> 07:04:03.479
I don't know.

07:04:03.540 --> 07:04:06.119
But Bandit's Cage is missing too, Kibley

07:04:06.119 --> 07:04:08.040
said, so I don't think he's coming back.

07:04:08.099 --> 07:04:11.279
Oh, Turtles said.

07:04:11.340 --> 07:04:14.159
I saw him leaving, but I thought he was

07:04:14.159 --> 07:04:15.419
just going hunting.

07:04:15.479 --> 07:04:16.740
I should have stopped him.

07:04:16.860 --> 07:04:20.759
He managed to pry 2 rocks free and handed

07:04:20.759 --> 07:04:23.099
one to Kibley, then another to Kinkachu.

07:04:23.159 --> 07:04:25.200
Their thoughts fuzzed out into that quiet

07:04:25.200 --> 07:04:27.599
hum as they slipped the rocks into the

07:04:27.599 --> 07:04:29.279
library card pouches around their necks.

07:04:29.340 --> 07:04:31.919
Moon could still hear dragons elsewhere

07:04:31.919 --> 07:04:33.900
in the school, but she knew she'd miss

07:04:33.900 --> 07:04:35.639
listening to Kibley and Kinkaju.

07:04:35.700 --> 07:04:38.099
I'll just have to listen better to what

07:04:38.099 --> 07:04:40.439
they actually say, she promised herself.

07:04:40.500 --> 07:04:43.380
Which way was he going?

07:04:43.439 --> 07:04:45.119
Moon asked Turtle.

07:04:45.180 --> 07:04:48.180
Northwest, toward the forest that's

07:04:48.180 --> 07:04:50.159
between the mountains and the desert, he

07:04:50.159 --> 07:04:50.340
said.

07:04:50.400 --> 07:04:52.619
Uh, where are you going?

07:04:52.680 --> 07:04:54.959
Moon was heading for the mouth of the

07:04:54.959 --> 07:04:57.060
cave, where they could see sheets of rain

07:04:57.060 --> 07:04:57.959
pouring down.

07:04:58.020 --> 07:05:00.540
I'm going to find him, she said.

07:05:00.599 --> 07:05:02.400
In this weather?

07:05:02.520 --> 07:05:03.779
Turtle protested.

07:05:03.840 --> 07:05:05.040
Oh, yay.

07:05:05.099 --> 07:05:06.240
Kinkachu cried.

07:05:06.299 --> 07:05:06.720
Me too.

07:05:06.840 --> 07:05:08.340
Are you sure?

07:05:08.400 --> 07:05:11.040
Moon said to her, waving one wing at the

07:05:11.040 --> 07:05:11.580
storm outside.

07:05:11.639 --> 07:05:13.560
I understand if you don't.

07:05:13.619 --> 07:05:16.860
I'm a rain wing, Kinkachu said.

07:05:16.919 --> 07:05:19.560
It rains all the time in the rainforest.

07:05:19.619 --> 07:05:21.240
Trust me, I can handle it.

07:05:21.299 --> 07:05:23.340
I'm not sure I can.

07:05:23.459 --> 07:05:25.860
Kibley said, rubbing the back of his head

07:05:25.860 --> 07:05:27.659
but I'm coming with you anyway.

07:05:27.720 --> 07:05:30.479
Kingachu looked expectantly at Turtle.

07:05:30.540 --> 07:05:33.119
He shuffled his feet, flickering his glow

07:05:33.119 --> 07:05:34.380
in the dark scales nervously.

07:05:34.439 --> 07:05:36.779
In this weather?

07:05:36.779 --> 07:05:37.799
he said again.

07:05:37.860 --> 07:05:39.479
Come on, turtle?

07:05:39.540 --> 07:05:40.139
she said.

07:05:40.200 --> 07:05:41.340
We're a winglet.

07:05:41.400 --> 07:05:42.779
We're all that's left of the jade

07:05:42.779 --> 07:05:43.439
winglet.

07:05:43.500 --> 07:05:44.400
We should stick together.

07:05:44.459 --> 07:05:46.860
Also, how can you be bothered by little

07:05:46.860 --> 07:05:47.580
water?

07:05:47.639 --> 07:05:48.540
You live in it.

07:05:48.599 --> 07:05:50.159
You can actually breathe it.

07:05:50.220 --> 07:05:51.240
You'll be fine.

07:05:51.299 --> 07:05:53.400
She bumped his hip hard enough to

07:05:53.400 --> 07:05:54.240
overbalance him.

07:05:54.299 --> 07:05:56.220
And he took a staggering step sideways.

07:05:56.279 --> 07:05:58.319
It's different.

07:05:58.380 --> 07:05:59.580
He objected.

07:05:59.639 --> 07:06:02.220
Swimming is not the same, is trying to

07:06:02.220 --> 07:06:04.740
fly. while getting blown about and

07:06:04.740 --> 07:06:07.080
whacked in the face with little balls of

07:06:07.080 --> 07:06:08.580
water and also lightning.

07:06:08.639 --> 07:06:10.860
Have we talked about the lightning?

07:06:10.919 --> 07:06:12.479
He's coming too.

07:06:12.540 --> 07:06:13.919
Can get you said to moon?

07:06:13.979 --> 07:06:15.659
Turtles, side, and defeat.

07:06:15.720 --> 07:06:18.840
None of you have to do this, Moon said.

07:06:18.900 --> 07:06:21.599
I just, I feel like I owe it to him.

07:06:21.720 --> 07:06:25.139
He's my clawmate, Kibley pointed out.

07:06:25.200 --> 07:06:28.139
Also, I am a total expert on evil

07:06:28.139 --> 07:06:29.040
brothers and sisters.

07:06:29.099 --> 07:06:32.700
And I am coming to keep you safe, Kinkachu

07:06:32.700 --> 07:06:33.000
said.

07:06:33.000 --> 07:06:34.200
Don't argue with me.

07:06:34.259 --> 07:06:35.639
I'm very menacing.

07:06:35.759 --> 07:06:38.520
She turned her wings black and bared her

07:06:38.520 --> 07:06:40.860
teeth, but the pink scales that remained

07:06:40.860 --> 07:06:42.180
rather undercut the effect.

07:06:42.240 --> 07:06:43.860
Moon smiled at them.

07:06:43.919 --> 07:06:45.540
All right, she said.

07:06:45.599 --> 07:06:46.500
Let's go.

07:06:46.560 --> 07:06:50.400
It seemed as though they flew for hours

07:06:50.400 --> 07:06:52.860
before they reached the outskirts of the

07:06:52.860 --> 07:06:54.659
forest, and then they spent forever

07:06:54.659 --> 07:06:56.700
circling over the trees.

07:06:56.700 --> 07:06:58.500
Moon kept thinking she heard a distant

07:06:58.500 --> 07:07:00.959
whisper that sounded like winter, but the

07:07:00.959 --> 07:07:02.939
forest and fury of the storm drowned out

07:07:02.939 --> 07:07:04.380
even the noise in her head.

07:07:04.439 --> 07:07:06.659
Maybe we should go back.

07:07:06.779 --> 07:07:08.639
Turtle shouted to her.

07:07:08.700 --> 07:07:10.860
As they did another passover clearing, she

07:07:10.860 --> 07:07:12.419
was sure they'd flown over 3 times.

07:07:12.479 --> 07:07:15.540
Maybe he's halfway to the ice kingdom

07:07:15.540 --> 07:07:16.020
already.

07:07:16.080 --> 07:07:19.500
I don't think so, Kibley called back, not

07:07:19.500 --> 07:07:20.099
with Bandit.

07:07:20.159 --> 07:07:22.319
He wouldn't fly too far with that cage.

07:07:22.380 --> 07:07:24.479
Scavengers don't handle this kind of

07:07:24.479 --> 07:07:25.439
weather as well as we do.

07:07:25.500 --> 07:07:28.740
Turtle Mayday would rather not handle

07:07:28.740 --> 07:07:31.380
this weather either myself, face, and

07:07:31.380 --> 07:07:33.000
tried to shake some of the rain off his

07:07:33.000 --> 07:07:34.080
waterlogged wings.

07:07:35.099 --> 07:07:37.680
Wait, Moon cried, grabbing Kinkaju's

07:07:37.680 --> 07:07:37.979
tail.

07:07:38.040 --> 07:07:39.599
I heard him, this way.

07:07:39.720 --> 07:07:42.959
She swooped toward the trees, half

07:07:42.959 --> 07:07:44.220
blinded by the downpour.

07:07:44.279 --> 07:07:46.919
A gust of wind blew her sideways at the

07:07:46.919 --> 07:07:48.840
wrong moment, and she collided with the

07:07:48.840 --> 07:07:51.180
top of a tree, but she righted herself

07:07:51.180 --> 07:07:52.799
and dropped down through the branches to

07:07:52.799 --> 07:07:53.580
the forest floor.

07:07:53.639 --> 07:07:56.759
The others followed, one by one as she

07:07:56.759 --> 07:07:58.259
led the way through the dark forest.

07:07:58.319 --> 07:08:00.779
Suddenly she stopped to listen to a voice

07:08:00.779 --> 07:08:01.500
up ahead.

07:08:01.560 --> 07:08:03.840
Go on, get out of here.

07:08:03.900 --> 07:08:06.360
I know it's raining, but it's better than

07:08:06.360 --> 07:08:07.500
the Ice Kingdom, trust me.

07:08:07.560 --> 07:08:09.360
Winter!

07:08:09.720 --> 07:08:10.500
Kingachu yelped.

07:08:10.560 --> 07:08:11.159
That's him.

07:08:11.220 --> 07:08:14.639
Moon breathed a plume of fire, and it

07:08:14.639 --> 07:08:16.439
reflected off silvery scales and a

07:08:16.439 --> 07:08:17.400
clearing to their right.

07:08:17.459 --> 07:08:19.380
They hurried over and found winter

07:08:19.380 --> 07:08:21.479
crouched beside a scavenger cage.

07:08:21.540 --> 07:08:24.299
The door was open, and bandit stood at

07:08:24.299 --> 07:08:26.759
the edge, staring bleakly out of the huge

07:08:26.759 --> 07:08:28.860
dark forest and the storm.

07:08:28.919 --> 07:08:31.200
By all the snow monsters.

07:08:31.259 --> 07:08:32.220
What are you doing here?

07:08:32.279 --> 07:08:34.979
Winter demanded, flapping his wet wings.

07:08:35.040 --> 07:08:37.740
Looking for you, Moon said.

07:08:37.799 --> 07:08:40.380
And we found you, Kinkachu added.

07:08:40.439 --> 07:08:40.979
We're amazing.

07:08:41.040 --> 07:08:43.799
He turned his head to look back at Bandit

07:08:43.799 --> 07:08:44.819
avoiding their eyes.

07:08:44.939 --> 07:08:47.759
I'm not going back to Jade Mountain, he

07:08:47.759 --> 07:08:48.119
said.

07:08:48.180 --> 07:08:49.500
I'm going to look for my brother.

07:08:49.560 --> 07:08:52.380
I thought so, Moon said.

07:08:52.439 --> 07:08:53.459
We want to help you.

07:08:53.520 --> 07:08:55.319
We do?

07:08:55.380 --> 07:08:57.659
Turtle said, sounding alarmed.

07:08:57.720 --> 07:08:58.680
Yes.

07:08:58.740 --> 07:08:59.819
Kinkachu said.

07:08:59.880 --> 07:09:01.799
I didn't know we did, but now I totally

07:09:01.799 --> 07:09:02.159
do.

07:09:02.220 --> 07:09:06.360
Wait, came the voice of dark stalker

07:09:06.360 --> 07:09:07.619
faint and whispery.

07:09:07.680 --> 07:09:08.639
Moon.

07:09:08.700 --> 07:09:10.200
Please don't leave me.

07:09:10.319 --> 07:09:13.380
She hadn't thought of that, that if she

07:09:13.380 --> 07:09:15.479
went with winter, wherever he meant to go

07:09:15.479 --> 07:09:17.459
she'd be flying out of dark stalkers

07:09:17.459 --> 07:09:17.880
range.

07:09:17.939 --> 07:09:19.740
He wouldn't be able to communicate with

07:09:19.740 --> 07:09:20.159
her anymore.

07:09:20.220 --> 07:09:21.659
He'd be all alone.

07:09:21.720 --> 07:09:26.520
I'm afraid I'll go mad, he said, with no

07:09:26.520 --> 07:09:27.060
one to talk to.

07:09:27.119 --> 07:09:29.099
No way to know if you're all right.

07:09:29.159 --> 07:09:32.459
For the 1st time ever, his surface

07:09:32.459 --> 07:09:34.979
cracked, and she saw past what he wanted

07:09:34.979 --> 07:09:35.459
her to see.

07:09:35.520 --> 07:09:38.639
Beneath the funny, confident, commanding

07:09:38.639 --> 07:09:42.299
voice she knew, she felt a deep hole, and

07:09:42.299 --> 07:09:44.580
all the way down the hole, reverberated

07:09:44.580 --> 07:09:46.020
with infinite loneliness.

07:09:46.080 --> 07:09:47.639
A moment later.

07:09:47.700 --> 07:09:50.939
Dark Stalker pulled his guard back up, and

07:09:50.939 --> 07:09:52.259
she was left skating on his

07:09:52.259 --> 07:09:53.580
conversational thoughts again.

07:09:53.639 --> 07:09:57.360
I'll come back, she promised, feeling

07:09:57.360 --> 07:09:58.500
hugely sorry for him.

07:09:58.619 --> 07:10:02.040
And listen, while I'm out there, I can

07:10:02.040 --> 07:10:03.180
look for your talisman.

07:10:03.240 --> 07:10:05.220
Will you?

07:10:05.220 --> 07:10:06.060
he asked.

07:10:06.119 --> 07:10:06.900
Really?

07:10:06.959 --> 07:10:08.700
I will try.

07:10:08.759 --> 07:10:10.799
Winter was shaking his head.

07:10:10.860 --> 07:10:13.619
You can't come with me, he said.

07:10:13.680 --> 07:10:15.360
I'm going to Queen Glacier.

07:10:15.419 --> 07:10:17.459
I need to explain it all to her and get

07:10:17.459 --> 07:10:19.200
her to help me find Hillstorm.

07:10:19.259 --> 07:10:21.779
Wouldn't it make more sense to go to the

07:10:21.779 --> 07:10:22.560
Sky Kingdom?

07:10:22.619 --> 07:10:24.060
Kinkichu asked.

07:10:24.119 --> 07:10:25.799
Your brother must be imprisoned there

07:10:25.799 --> 07:10:26.400
somewhere, right?

07:10:26.459 --> 07:10:29.340
We could look for him in, like, all the

07:10:29.340 --> 07:10:30.299
mountain caves or something.

07:10:30.360 --> 07:10:34.500
Or you could go after Icicle, Kibley

07:10:34.500 --> 07:10:34.740
said.

07:10:34.799 --> 07:10:36.900
Try to find out more about what Scarlett

07:10:36.900 --> 07:10:37.319
told her.

07:10:37.380 --> 07:10:40.919
I don't know where she's gone, Winter

07:10:40.919 --> 07:10:41.520
said bitterly.

07:10:41.580 --> 07:10:45.119
I have a guess, Kibley said, with a

07:10:45.119 --> 07:10:46.200
glance at Kinkaju.

07:10:46.259 --> 07:10:47.520
You won't like it, though.

07:10:47.580 --> 07:10:49.619
I think she's gone to the rainforest.

07:10:49.680 --> 07:10:52.560
She knows the one Scarlet hates the most

07:10:52.560 --> 07:10:53.700
is glory.

07:10:53.759 --> 07:10:55.259
Everyone knows that.

07:10:55.319 --> 07:10:57.360
If they know the story of what glory did

07:10:57.360 --> 07:10:57.900
to her face.

07:10:57.959 --> 07:11:00.900
So I think Icicle might think that if she

07:11:00.900 --> 07:11:03.360
kills glory, Scarlet will forgive her for

07:11:03.360 --> 07:11:04.439
failing to kill the others.

07:11:04.500 --> 07:11:08.220
There is a hushed silence, broken by the

07:11:08.220 --> 07:11:10.439
patter of raindrops and a roll of thunder

07:11:10.439 --> 07:11:10.979
overhead.

07:11:11.040 --> 07:11:15.060
Then I'm going to the rainforest, Kinkaju

07:11:15.060 --> 07:11:15.720
said fiercely.

07:11:15.779 --> 07:11:17.819
I'm not letting her kill my awesome

07:11:17.819 --> 07:11:18.180
queen.

07:11:18.240 --> 07:11:20.639
Which is the right way?

07:11:20.700 --> 07:11:22.080
Moon wondered.

07:11:22.139 --> 07:11:23.220
Where should we go?

07:11:23.279 --> 07:11:27.119
If only Dark Stalker could tell them, this

07:11:27.119 --> 07:11:28.799
seems like exactly the right time for a

07:11:28.799 --> 07:11:29.580
vision of the future.

07:11:29.700 --> 07:11:31.680
Are you sure?

07:11:31.680 --> 07:11:32.819
he asked.

07:11:32.880 --> 07:11:35.700
Yes, can you tell us how to find her?

07:11:35.700 --> 07:11:37.020
Moon asked.

07:11:37.080 --> 07:11:38.939
No, he said.

07:11:39.000 --> 07:11:41.159
But I've been trying to protect you from

07:11:41.159 --> 07:11:41.340
this.

07:11:41.400 --> 07:11:44.220
And if you're leaving my range, that I

07:11:44.220 --> 07:11:45.119
won't be able to anymore.

07:11:45.180 --> 07:11:46.860
What?

07:11:46.979 --> 07:11:50.700
Moon started to ask, but then suddenly, a

07:11:50.700 --> 07:11:52.500
headache hit her like nothing she'd ever

07:11:52.500 --> 07:11:55.139
felt before, like an entire tribe of

07:11:55.139 --> 07:11:57.180
dragons descending on her head with their

07:11:57.180 --> 07:11:57.779
claws out.

07:11:57.840 --> 07:12:00.840
She staggered back with a cry, and the

07:12:00.840 --> 07:12:01.860
others whirled toward her.

07:12:01.919 --> 07:12:03.240
Moon?

07:12:03.360 --> 07:12:06.360
Kinkaju leaped over, colliding wetly with

07:12:06.360 --> 07:12:06.959
her in the dark.

07:12:07.020 --> 07:12:09.540
Her scales were slick with raindrops as

07:12:09.540 --> 07:12:10.740
she tried to hold moon up.

07:12:10.799 --> 07:12:12.479
But Moon couldn't stand.

07:12:12.540 --> 07:12:15.060
The weight of the vision was bearing down

07:12:15.060 --> 07:12:15.540
on her.

07:12:15.599 --> 07:12:17.639
It was everything from her nightmare.

07:12:17.700 --> 07:12:20.639
The mountain falling, the dragons dying

07:12:20.639 --> 07:12:23.159
the fire, and earth cracking and

07:12:23.159 --> 07:12:23.580
destruction.

07:12:23.639 --> 07:12:25.919
Words were marching through her head and

07:12:25.919 --> 07:12:28.139
out of her mouth, inexorable and

07:12:28.139 --> 07:12:28.500
strange.

07:12:28.560 --> 07:12:31.979
Beware the darkness of dragons.

07:12:32.040 --> 07:12:34.619
Beware the stalker of dreams.

07:12:34.680 --> 07:12:37.259
Beware the talons of power and fire.

07:12:37.319 --> 07:12:40.259
Beware one who is not what she seems.

07:12:40.319 --> 07:12:43.380
Something is coming to shake the earth.

07:12:43.439 --> 07:12:46.139
Something is coming to scorch the

07:12:46.139 --> 07:12:46.380
ground.

07:12:46.439 --> 07:12:49.020
Jade Mountain will fall beneath thunder

07:12:49.020 --> 07:12:52.380
and ice, unless the lost city of night

07:12:52.380 --> 07:12:53.819
can be found.

07:12:53.880 --> 07:12:56.580
She choked for a moment on the last line

07:12:56.580 --> 07:12:59.099
as though it were coming out edged with

07:12:59.099 --> 07:12:59.580
thorns.

07:12:59.639 --> 07:13:02.279
But at last it was said, and she

07:13:02.279 --> 07:13:04.500
collapsed into Kinkachu's wings, and the

07:13:04.500 --> 07:13:06.540
vision disappeared, taking the headache

07:13:06.540 --> 07:13:06.840
with it.

07:13:06.900 --> 07:13:10.680
By all the snakes, Kibley said.

07:13:10.740 --> 07:13:13.380
Thunder rolled across the sky again and

07:13:13.380 --> 07:13:15.419
lightning flashed, illuminating the

07:13:15.419 --> 07:13:16.680
scared faces around her.

07:13:16.919 --> 07:13:18.119
What was that?

07:13:18.180 --> 07:13:21.119
That's what you've been muttering in your

07:13:21.119 --> 07:13:22.680
sleep, Kinkachu said.

07:13:22.740 --> 07:13:27.360
It sounded like a prophecy, Winter said

07:13:27.360 --> 07:13:28.259
disbelievingly.

07:13:28.319 --> 07:13:31.380
Moon forced herself to stand up, although

07:13:31.380 --> 07:13:33.119
her wings were shaking so hard, she

07:13:33.119 --> 07:13:33.959
thought they might fall off.

07:13:34.080 --> 07:13:37.560
Turtle, she said, please give him one of

07:13:37.560 --> 07:13:37.919
the rocks.

07:13:38.040 --> 07:13:41.159
Winter eyed the small black stone with

07:13:41.159 --> 07:13:43.380
suspicion as Turtle dropped it in his

07:13:43.380 --> 07:13:43.860
palm.

07:13:43.919 --> 07:13:45.000
What's this?

07:13:45.060 --> 07:13:48.119
I have a lot to explain. she said.

07:13:48.180 --> 07:13:49.259
Everything.

07:13:49.319 --> 07:13:50.340
The whole truth.

07:13:50.400 --> 07:13:52.200
I'm going to tell you everything.

07:13:52.259 --> 07:13:55.020
Everything.

07:13:55.139 --> 07:13:57.599
Dark Stalker said with a distant sigh.

07:13:57.720 --> 07:14:00.959
That sounds ominous, Winter said.

07:14:01.020 --> 07:14:04.200
No more ominous than Jade Mountain will

07:14:04.200 --> 07:14:06.360
fall beneath thunder and ice, Kibley

07:14:06.360 --> 07:14:06.779
said.

07:14:06.840 --> 07:14:08.700
I hope we're all planning to talk about

07:14:08.700 --> 07:14:11.459
that because I'm extremely unsettled

07:14:11.459 --> 07:14:11.759
right now.

07:14:11.819 --> 07:14:14.939
She said we have to find the lost city of

07:14:14.939 --> 07:14:16.500
night, Kinkaju said.

07:14:16.560 --> 07:14:18.360
That's all, and then everything will be

07:14:18.360 --> 07:14:19.080
fine, right?

07:14:19.200 --> 07:14:20.880
Isn't that what everyone else heard?

07:14:20.939 --> 07:14:24.479
I'm pretty sure I heard that we're all

07:14:24.479 --> 07:14:26.459
going to die, Turtle said.

07:14:26.520 --> 07:14:30.119
Death, death, monsters everywhere, death.

07:14:30.180 --> 07:14:32.040
Is that it?

07:14:32.099 --> 07:14:33.479
Kibley asked Moon.

07:14:33.540 --> 07:14:34.740
Is that what you saw?

07:14:34.799 --> 07:14:36.959
Jade Mountain is going to fall on us

07:14:36.959 --> 07:14:37.319
all?

07:14:37.380 --> 07:14:40.380
I don't know, Moon said.

07:14:40.439 --> 07:14:42.900
I've had visions, but none of them ever

07:14:42.900 --> 07:14:44.279
came out in words like that before.

07:14:44.340 --> 07:14:46.020
I don't know what it means.

07:14:46.080 --> 07:14:49.680
Probably means it's important.

07:14:49.799 --> 07:14:51.479
Dark Stalker offered.

07:14:51.599 --> 07:14:52.560
Thank you.

07:14:52.619 --> 07:14:54.659
That's very helpful, she retorted.

07:14:54.720 --> 07:14:56.459
Does it mean that what I saw is

07:14:56.459 --> 07:14:57.060
inevitable?

07:14:57.119 --> 07:14:58.740
No.

07:14:58.860 --> 07:15:02.580
There's another possible future, he said

07:15:02.580 --> 07:15:05.340
but it's along a very difficult and dark

07:15:05.340 --> 07:15:05.819
path.

07:15:05.880 --> 07:15:09.360
She closed her eyes, can I see that one?

07:15:09.419 --> 07:15:10.500
Is it awful too?

07:15:10.560 --> 07:15:14.340
In response, she felt a slow spreading

07:15:14.340 --> 07:15:16.380
pain through her temples, and a moment

07:15:16.380 --> 07:15:17.819
later, a vision appeared.

07:15:17.880 --> 07:15:20.880
It looked like Jade Mountain Academy, but

07:15:20.880 --> 07:15:21.540
somehow different.

07:15:21.599 --> 07:15:24.060
Sunlight poured through the windows as

07:15:24.060 --> 07:15:25.200
she moved through the caves.

07:15:25.259 --> 07:15:28.200
Small dragonette she didn't know, each of

07:15:28.200 --> 07:15:30.060
them a different color, played a game of

07:15:30.060 --> 07:15:31.259
chase in the sky.

07:15:31.319 --> 07:15:33.959
She came into the library and the dragon

07:15:33.959 --> 07:15:36.000
at the desk raised his head, listening.

07:15:36.060 --> 07:15:38.639
It was Starflight, but he was older

07:15:38.639 --> 07:15:40.860
radiating happiness and peace.

07:15:40.919 --> 07:15:43.560
A small black dragonette raced into the

07:15:43.560 --> 07:15:46.139
cave, leaped onto the desk, kissed the

07:15:46.139 --> 07:15:48.299
side of his head, took one of the scrolls

07:15:48.299 --> 07:15:50.639
and flew off down another tunnel calling

07:15:50.639 --> 07:15:51.599
thank you, father.

07:15:51.659 --> 07:15:55.139
No flying in the tunnels. he called after

07:15:55.139 --> 07:15:56.520
her, but he was smiling.

07:15:56.580 --> 07:16:01.380
Clay, older, bigger clay, poked his head

07:16:01.380 --> 07:16:03.840
into another entrance and said, my class

07:16:03.840 --> 07:16:06.000
is asking for more scrolls about the War

07:16:06.000 --> 07:16:07.200
of Sandwing succession.

07:16:07.319 --> 07:16:10.319
I thought maybe you could come talk and

07:16:10.319 --> 07:16:12.119
talk and talk at them instead.

07:16:12.180 --> 07:16:15.000
And then maybe they'll go to sleep and

07:16:15.000 --> 07:16:16.259
stop asking me questions.

07:16:16.319 --> 07:16:21.180
Ha ha, hilarious, Starflight said, sliding

07:16:21.180 --> 07:16:22.020
out from behind the desk.

07:16:22.080 --> 07:16:24.659
Firefly, just put that back when you're

07:16:24.659 --> 07:16:25.259
done, all right?

07:16:25.319 --> 07:16:27.240
Over in the window bay.

07:16:27.299 --> 07:16:30.180
A dark purple dragonette answered, sure

07:16:30.180 --> 07:16:31.439
absentmindedly.

07:16:31.500 --> 07:16:33.959
She was curled up with two other dragons

07:16:33.959 --> 07:16:37.080
one blue and won a deep orange brown moon

07:16:37.080 --> 07:16:37.919
had never seen before.

07:16:37.979 --> 07:16:40.500
They had a scroll spread out in front of

07:16:40.500 --> 07:16:41.520
them and were studying it together.

07:16:41.580 --> 07:16:43.380
Can you imagine?

07:16:43.500 --> 07:16:44.580
The blue one said.

07:16:44.639 --> 07:16:46.740
The tribes hated each other so much back

07:16:46.740 --> 07:16:47.040
then.

07:16:47.099 --> 07:16:49.919
It's a good thing we're so much smarter

07:16:49.919 --> 07:16:51.959
than all the dragons who lived before us

07:16:51.959 --> 07:16:53.700
said the purple one importantly.

07:16:53.759 --> 07:16:55.860
We'd never make their mistakes.

07:16:55.919 --> 07:16:59.279
I'm glad we're here, though, said the 3rd

07:16:59.279 --> 07:17:01.439
dragonette at the Jade Mountain Academy.

07:17:01.500 --> 07:17:02.700
I'm glad it exists.

07:17:02.819 --> 07:17:05.819
Me too, the other said in unison.

07:17:05.880 --> 07:17:08.400
The vision faded quietly away.

07:17:08.459 --> 07:17:11.400
That's what we're fighting for, Moon

07:17:11.400 --> 07:17:11.819
thought.

07:17:11.880 --> 07:17:13.799
Thank you, Dark Stalker.

07:17:13.919 --> 07:17:17.220
I can help you make it real, he said.

07:17:17.279 --> 07:17:18.540
Remember that.

07:17:18.599 --> 07:17:20.040
When you can't hear me anymore.

07:17:20.099 --> 07:17:23.099
Moon felt the rain splattering against

07:17:23.099 --> 07:17:23.580
her wings.

07:17:23.700 --> 07:17:26.279
She looked around at her friends, all of

07:17:26.279 --> 07:17:28.619
their minds humming quietly, closed off.

07:17:28.680 --> 07:17:31.860
She wasn't a scared dragonette alone in

07:17:31.860 --> 07:17:32.759
the rainforest anymore.

07:17:32.819 --> 07:17:36.720
She was a mind reader, and a prophet, and

07:17:36.720 --> 07:17:39.180
she had a prophecy to fulfill, an ice

07:17:39.180 --> 07:17:42.419
wing to rescue, a talisman to find, a

07:17:42.419 --> 07:17:45.659
possible supervillain to release, or not

07:17:45.659 --> 07:17:47.700
and a world to save, even though it

07:17:47.700 --> 07:17:50.279
didn't know it needed saving yet, no more

07:17:50.279 --> 07:17:50.700
hiding.

07:17:50.759 --> 07:17:53.279
Winter, she said.

07:17:53.340 --> 07:17:55.139
There are a few things you need to know

07:17:55.139 --> 07:17:55.500
about me.

07:17:55.619 --> 07:18:00.119
Epilogue.

07:18:00.240 --> 07:18:03.840
Frogs, spit, and goat tongues.

07:18:03.900 --> 07:18:05.580
Queen Scarlet cursed.

07:18:05.639 --> 07:18:07.740
She shook the sapphire in her talons

07:18:07.740 --> 07:18:08.459
violently.

07:18:08.520 --> 07:18:09.840
Why isn't it working?

07:18:09.900 --> 07:18:12.240
It probably is.

07:18:12.299 --> 07:18:14.220
Her companion said smoothly.

07:18:14.340 --> 07:18:16.560
The dragon you're looking for must still

07:18:16.560 --> 07:18:16.919
be awake.

07:18:16.979 --> 07:18:19.380
Scarlet glared at him.

07:18:19.439 --> 07:18:22.080
The vast black sky wheeled over their

07:18:22.080 --> 07:18:24.779
heads, studded with stars like diamonds.

07:18:24.840 --> 07:18:27.779
The 3 moons lit up the toothy peaks of

07:18:27.779 --> 07:18:28.740
the mountains all around them.

07:18:28.799 --> 07:18:31.020
It's the middle of the night.

07:18:31.080 --> 07:18:32.520
Why wouldn't you be asleep?

07:18:32.580 --> 07:18:34.439
I gave her an ultimatum.

07:18:34.560 --> 07:18:36.419
I need to know what's happening there.

07:18:36.479 --> 07:18:38.279
He shrugged.

07:18:38.340 --> 07:18:40.139
Tapping something between his front

07:18:40.139 --> 07:18:40.860
talons.

07:18:40.919 --> 07:18:42.599
Tap, tap.

07:18:42.599 --> 07:18:44.400
So try a different dragon.

07:18:44.459 --> 07:18:46.799
She wrapped her claws around the blue

07:18:46.799 --> 07:18:48.779
stone again, growling to herself.

07:18:48.900 --> 07:18:52.500
Has to be someone I know, she muttered

07:18:52.500 --> 07:18:55.259
but I don't want those dragonettes to see

07:18:55.259 --> 07:18:55.799
where I am.

07:18:55.860 --> 07:18:58.979
After a moment, she closed her eyes.

07:18:59.040 --> 07:19:00.240
All right.

07:19:00.299 --> 07:19:02.520
An old favorite.

07:19:02.580 --> 07:19:04.860
It only took a minute for her to drop

07:19:04.860 --> 07:19:06.299
into peril's dream.

07:19:06.360 --> 07:19:09.419
As usual, it was tortured and weird, with

07:19:09.419 --> 07:19:11.279
several Queen Scarlets chasing her

07:19:11.279 --> 07:19:13.680
through the Sky Palace, while corpses of

07:19:13.680 --> 07:19:15.540
burnt dragons lurched out of various

07:19:15.540 --> 07:19:16.619
doorways to attack her.

07:19:16.680 --> 07:19:18.360
Scarlett snorted.

07:19:18.479 --> 07:19:21.000
What was the point of being a glorious

07:19:21.000 --> 07:19:22.799
monster with talons of fire?

07:19:22.860 --> 07:19:25.500
If you were going to agonize over it so

07:19:25.500 --> 07:19:28.380
much, peril's power was absolutely wasted

07:19:28.380 --> 07:19:28.680
on her.

07:19:28.740 --> 07:19:33.180
Stop, she roared, planting herself in

07:19:33.180 --> 07:19:36.180
peril's path, peril skidded to a halt, and

07:19:36.180 --> 07:19:37.139
looked frantically around.

07:19:37.259 --> 07:19:39.659
She thought Scarlet was another one of

07:19:39.659 --> 07:19:40.919
the dream queens.

07:19:40.979 --> 07:19:42.840
She'd always had trouble figuring out

07:19:42.840 --> 07:19:44.340
when Scarlet was really visiting her

07:19:44.400 --> 07:19:46.860
which could be useful, especially at

07:19:46.860 --> 07:19:47.400
times like this.

07:19:47.459 --> 07:19:49.740
Who died today?

07:19:49.799 --> 07:19:51.119
Scarlett demanded.

07:19:51.180 --> 07:19:53.159
Tell me, who is dead?

07:19:53.220 --> 07:19:56.220
No one, peril cried.

07:19:56.279 --> 07:19:58.080
I didn't kill anyone, I swear.

07:19:58.139 --> 07:20:00.419
Stop lithering.

07:20:00.540 --> 07:20:01.740
Scarlet growled.

07:20:01.799 --> 07:20:04.020
Someone must have died today at that

07:20:04.020 --> 07:20:04.799
ludicrous school.

07:20:04.860 --> 07:20:07.740
Peril shook her head wildly.

07:20:07.799 --> 07:20:09.479
No, no, no one is dead.

07:20:09.540 --> 07:20:10.560
Clay is safe.

07:20:10.619 --> 07:20:11.580
That's what's important.

07:20:11.639 --> 07:20:12.540
No one is dead.

07:20:12.599 --> 07:20:15.060
Oh, a mudwing and an ice wing are gone

07:20:15.060 --> 07:20:16.500
but they're alive, not dead.

07:20:16.619 --> 07:20:17.279
No one is dead.

07:20:17.400 --> 07:20:19.439
Scarlet hissed.

07:20:19.500 --> 07:20:21.900
She yanked the sapphire away from her

07:20:21.900 --> 07:20:24.479
head, snapping abruptly out of peril's

07:20:24.479 --> 07:20:24.720
dream.

07:20:24.779 --> 07:20:28.200
I'm going to murder that ice wing, she

07:20:28.200 --> 07:20:28.619
yelled.

07:20:28.680 --> 07:20:30.900
This is not thrilling at all.

07:20:31.020 --> 07:20:34.680
She failed, said the other dragon.

07:20:34.740 --> 07:20:37.139
He shifted from shadow to moonlight.

07:20:37.200 --> 07:20:39.779
His scales rippling in strange moonlit

07:20:39.779 --> 07:20:40.200
colors.

07:20:40.259 --> 07:20:42.659
Tap, tap, tap.

07:20:42.720 --> 07:20:44.220
How surprising.

07:20:44.279 --> 07:20:46.319
Should I kill your prisoner?

07:20:46.380 --> 07:20:49.439
Yes, Scarlet hissed.

07:20:49.500 --> 07:20:50.580
Wait, no.

07:20:50.700 --> 07:20:53.819
She paced along the ledge, fuming.

07:20:53.880 --> 07:20:56.580
If she let Hellstorm live, Icicle would

07:20:56.580 --> 07:20:58.619
stop being frightened of her, her threats

07:20:58.619 --> 07:20:59.159
would mean nothing.

07:20:59.220 --> 07:21:01.860
But if she killed him, she'd have lost

07:21:01.860 --> 07:21:03.779
her only bit of leverage on a very useful

07:21:03.779 --> 07:21:04.259
pawn.

07:21:04.380 --> 07:21:06.599
Tap, tap, tap.

07:21:06.659 --> 07:21:09.599
Of course, Icicle wasn't the only dragon

07:21:09.599 --> 07:21:11.279
who wanted this particular prisoner

07:21:11.279 --> 07:21:11.520
back.

07:21:11.580 --> 07:21:14.099
There was another brother, wasn't there?

07:21:14.159 --> 07:21:16.200
But Scarlett had never seen him.

07:21:16.259 --> 07:21:18.119
How would she get into his dreams?

07:21:18.180 --> 07:21:20.819
Was there another way to get to him?

07:21:20.880 --> 07:21:22.979
Or someone else who could kill the

07:21:22.979 --> 07:21:23.759
dragonettes?

07:21:23.880 --> 07:21:27.659
I should do it myself, she muttered.

07:21:27.720 --> 07:21:28.860
She knew that.

07:21:28.919 --> 07:21:31.979
She just, every time she thought about

07:21:31.979 --> 07:21:34.740
that rain wing, the jaw extending

07:21:34.740 --> 07:21:37.799
horribly, the fangs pointed straight at

07:21:37.799 --> 07:21:40.200
her, and the venom flying toward her

07:21:40.200 --> 07:21:40.439
face.

07:21:40.500 --> 07:21:44.580
It gave her a sick, squashed feeling that

07:21:44.580 --> 07:21:46.259
reminded her of her melted scales.

07:21:46.319 --> 07:21:49.259
It wasn't fear, exactly.

07:21:49.319 --> 07:21:51.000
She would never say that.

07:21:51.060 --> 07:21:53.759
But if she could find a way to kill them

07:21:53.759 --> 07:21:56.340
from a distance, or at least glory.

07:21:56.400 --> 07:21:59.099
That would be preferable, certainly.

07:21:59.159 --> 07:22:02.759
Stop that infernal tapping, she roared.

07:22:02.819 --> 07:22:04.200
What is it anyhow?

07:22:04.259 --> 07:22:06.900
What are you fiddling within your hoard

07:22:06.900 --> 07:22:07.439
gloaty way?

07:22:07.500 --> 07:22:09.240
Oh.

07:22:09.299 --> 07:22:10.560
This?

07:22:10.619 --> 07:22:13.500
The dragon lifted the ancient scroll into

07:22:13.500 --> 07:22:15.840
the moonlight. looked up at it and

07:22:15.840 --> 07:22:16.259
smiled.

07:22:16.319 --> 07:22:18.299
Don't you worry.

07:22:18.360 --> 07:22:19.680
This is nothing.

